author: waymar royce
content: What do you expect? They're savages. One lot steals a goat from another lot and before you know it, they're ripping each other to pieces.

author: will
content: I've never seen wildlings do a thing like this. I've never seen a thing like this, not ever in my life.

author: waymar royce
content: How close did you get?

author: will
content: Close as any man would.

author: gared
content: We should head back to the wall.

author: royce
content: Do the dead frighten you?

author: gared
content: Our orders were to track the wildlings. We tracked them. They won't trouble us no more.

author: royce
content: You don't think he'll ask us how they died? Get back on your horse.

author: will
content: Whatever did it to them could do it to us. They even killed the children.

author: royce
content: It's a good thing we're not children. You want to run away south, run away. Of course, they will behead you as a deserter … If I don't catch you first. Get back on your horse. I won't say it again.

author: royce
content: Your dead men seem to have moved camp.

author: will
content: They were here.

author: gared
content: See where they went.

author: royce
content: What is it?

author: gared
content: It's …

author: jon snow
content: Go on. Father's watching.

author: jon snow
content: And your mother.

author: septa mordane
content: Fine work, as always. Well done.

author: sansa stark
content: Thank you.

author: septa mordane
content: I love the detail that you've managed to get in this corners. … Quite beautiful … the stitching …

author: eddard stark
content: And which one of you was a marksman at ten? Keep practicing, Bran. Go on.

author: jon snow
content: Don't think too much, Bran.

author: robb stark
content: Relax your bow arm.

author: jonrobb
content: Quick, Bran, faster!

author: cassel
content: Lord Stark. My lady. A guardsman just rode in from the hills. They've captured a deserter from the Night's Watch.

author: eddard stark
content: Get the lads to saddle their horses.

author: catelyn stark
content: Do you have to?

author: eddard stark
content: He swore an oath, Cat.

author: cassel
content: The law is law, my lady.

author: eddard stark
content: Tell Bran he's coming, too.

author: catelyn stark
content: Ned. Ten is too young to see such things.

author: eddard stark
content: He won't be a boy forever. And winter is coming.

author: robb stark
content: Lad, go run back and get the rest.

author: will
content: White Walkers. I saw the White Walkers. White Walkers. The White Walkers, I saw them.

author: will
content: I know I broke my oath. And I know I'm a deserter. I should have gone back to the Wall and warned them. But I saw what I saw. I saw the White Walkers. People need to know. If you can get word to my family, tell them I'm no coward. Tell them I'm sorry.

author: eddard stark
content: nods yes, and WILL is positioned on the tree limb that serves as a block.

author: will
content: Forgive me, lord.

author: eddard stark
content: In the name of Robert of the House Baratheon, first of his name …

author: jon snow
content: Don't look away.

author: eddard stark
content: King of the Andals and the First Men …

author: jon snow
content: Father will know if you do.

author: eddard stark
content: Lord of the Seven Kingdoms and protector of the realm, I, Eddard of the House Stark, Lord of Winterfell and Warden of the North, sentence you to die.

author: jon snow
content: You did well.

author: eddard stark
content: You understand why I did it?

author: bran stark
content: Jon said he was a deserter.

author: eddard stark
content: But do you understand why I had to kill him?

author: bran stark
content: Our way is the old way?

author: eddard stark
content: The man who passes the sentence should swing the sword.

author: bran stark
content: Is it true he saw the White Walkers?

author: eddard stark
content: The White Walkers have been gone for thousands of years.

author: bran stark
content: So he was lying?

author: eddard stark
content: A madman sees what he sees.

author: jon snow
content: What is it?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Mountain lion?

author: eddard stark
content: There are no mountain lions in these woods.

author: theon greyjoy
content: It's a freak.

author: eddard stark
content: It's a direwolf.

author: eddard stark
content: Tough old beast.

author: robb stark
content: There are no direwolves south of the Wall.

author: jon snow
content: Now there are five.

author: jon snow
content: You want to hold it?

author: bran stark
content: Where will they go? Their mother's dead.

author: cassel
content: They don't belong down here.

author: eddard stark
content: Better a quick death. They won't last without their mother.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Right. Give it here.

author: bran stark
content: NO!

author: robb stark
content: Put away your blade.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I take orders from your father, not you.

author: bran stark
content: Please, father!

author: eddard stark
content: I'm sorry, Bran.

author: jon snow
content: Lord Stark? There are five pups. One for each of the Stark children. The direwolf is the sigil of your House. They were meant to have them.

author: eddard stark
content: You will train them yourselves. You will feed them yourselves. And if they die, you will bury them yourselves.

author: bran stark
content: What about you?

author: jon snow
content: I'm not a Stark. Get on.

author: robb stark
content: What is it?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The runt of the litter. That one's yours, Snow.

author: jaime lannister
content: As your brother, I feel it's my duty to warn you

author: cersei lannister
content: And you never worry about anything. When we were seven, you jumped off the cliffs as Casterly Rock. One hundred foot drop into the water. And you were never afraid.

author: jaime lannister
content: There was nothing to be afraid of until you told father. [In a whisper, mimicking] We're Lannisters. Lannisters don't act like fools.

author: cersei lannister
content: What if Jon Arryn told someone?

author: jaime lannister
content: But who would he tell?

author: cersei lannister
content: My husband.

author: jaime lannister
content: If he told the king, both our heads would be skewered on the city gates by now. Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know, it died with him. And Robert will choose a new Hand of the king, someone to do his job while he's off fucking boars and hunting whores. Or is it the other way around? And life will go on.

author: cersei lannister
content: You should be the Hand of the king.

author: jaime lannister
content: That's an honor I can do without. Their days are too long, their lives are too short.

author: catelyn stark
content: All these years and I still feel like an outsider when I come here.

author: eddard stark
content: You have five northern children. You're not an outsider.

author: catelyn stark
content: I wonder if the old gods agree.

author: eddard stark
content: It's your gods with all the rules.

author: catelyn stark
content: I am so sorry, my love.

author: eddard stark
content: Tell me.

author: catelyn stark
content: There was a raven from Kings Landing. Jon Arryn is dead. A fever took him. I know he was like a father to you.

author: eddard stark
content: Your sister. The boy …

author: catelyn stark
content: They both have their health. Gods be good. [pause] The raven brought more news. The king rides for Winterfell. With the queen and all the rest of them.

author: eddard stark
content: He's coming this far North, there's only one thing he's after.

author: catelyn stark
content: You can always say no, Ned.

author: catelyn stark
content: We need plenty of candles for Lord Tyrion's chamber. I'm told he reads all night.

author: maester luwin
content: I'm told he drinks all night.

author: catelyn stark
content: How much could he possibly drink? A man of his … stature.

author: luwin
content: We've brought up eight barrels of ale from the cellar. Perhaps we'll find out.

author: catelyn stark
content: In any case, candles.

author: jon snow
content: Why's your mother so dead-set on us getting pretty for the king?

author: theon greyjoy
content: It's for the queen, I bet. I hear she's [sleek as a mink?]

author: robb stark
content: I hear the prince is a right royal prick.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab with his right royal prick.

author: robb stark
content: Go on, Tommy, shave him good. He's never met a girl he likes better than his own hair.

author: catelyn stark
content: Gods, but they grow fast. [Seeing BRAN on the wall] Brandon!

author: bran stark
content: I saw the king! He's got hundreds of people!

author: catelyn stark
content: How many times have I told you

author: bran stark
content: But he's coming right now! Down our road!

author: catelyn stark
content: I want you to promise me

author: bran stark
content: I promise.

author: catelyn stark
content: D'you know what?

author: bran stark
content: What?

author: catelyn stark
content: You always look at your feet before you lie. Run and find your father. Tell him the king is close.

author: catelyn stark
content: Where's Arya? Sansa, where's your sister?

author: eddard stark
content: Hey,, hey, hey, hey. What are you doing with that on? [Pulls off ARYA's helm]

author: arya stark
content: Move!

author: eddard stark
content: Your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: You've got fat.

author: robert baratheon
content: Cat!

author: catelyn stark
content: Your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: Nine years. Why haven't I seen you? Where the hell have you been?

author: eddard stark
content: Guarding the North for you, Your Grace. Winterfell is yours.

author: arya stark
content: Where's the Imp?

author: sansa stark
content: Will you shut up?

author: robert baratheon
content: Who have we here? You must be Robb. My, you're a pretty one. Your name is?

author: arya stark
content: Arya.

author: robert baratheon
content: Ooh. Show us your muscles. You'll be a soldier.

author: arya stark
content: That's Jaime Lannister. The queen's twin brother.

author: sansa stark
content: Would you please shut up.

author: eddard stark
content: My queen.

author: catelyn stark
content: My queen.

author: robert baratheon
content: Take me to your crypt. I want to pay my respects.

author: cersei lannister
content: We've been riding for a month, my love. Surely the dead can wait.

author: robert baratheon
content: Ned.

author: cersei lannister
content: Where is our brother? Go find the little beast.

author: eddard stark
content: Tell me about Jon Arryn.

author: robert baratheon
content: One minute he was fine, and then … Burned right through him, whatever it was. I loved that man.

author: eddard stark
content: We both did.

author: robert baratheon
content: He never had to teach you much, but me … You remember me at 16? All I wanted to do was crack skulls and fuck girls. He showed me what was what.

author: eddard stark
content: Aye.

author: robert baratheon
content: Don't look at me like that. Not his fault I didn't listen. I need you, Ned. Down at Kings Landing. Not up here, where you're no damn use to anybody. Lord Eddard Stark, I would name you the Hand of the king.

author: eddard stark
content: I'm not worthy of the honor.

author: robert baratheon
content: I'm not trying to honor you. I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom while I eat, drink, and whore my way to an early grave. Damn it, Ned, stand up. You helped me win the Iron Throne, now help me keep the damn thing. We were meant to rule together. If your sister had lived, we would have been bound by blood. Well, it's not too late. I have a son, you have a daughter. We'll join our Houses.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mmh. It is true what they say about the Northern girls.

author: ros
content: Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I did hear something about that.

author: ros
content: And the queen. And her twin brother. They say that he is the most handsome man in the Seven Kingdoms.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And the other brother?

author: ros
content: The queen has two brothers?

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's the pretty one. And there's the clever one.

author: ros
content: I hear they call him the Imp.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I hear he hates that nickname.

author: ros
content: Oh? I hear he's more than earned it. I hear he's a drunken little lecher into all manner of perversions.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Clever girl.

author: ros
content: We've been expecting you, Lord Tyrion.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Have you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The gods gave me one blessing.

author: jaime lannister
content: Don't get up.

author: ros
content: M'lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Should I explain to you the meaning of a closed door in a whorehouse, brother?

author: jaime lannister
content: You've much to teach me, no doubt. But our sister craves your attention.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She has odd cravings, our sister.

author: jaime lannister
content: A family trait. Now, the Starks are feasting us at sundown. Don't leave me alone with these people.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm sorry, I've begun the feast a bit early. And this is the first of many courses.

author: jaime lannister
content: I thought you might say that. But since we're short on time, Come on, girls. See you at sundown.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Close the door!

author: robert baratheon
content: Did you have to bury her in a place like this? She should be on a hill somewhere with the sun and the clouds above her.

author: eddard stark
content: She was my sister. This is where she belongs.

author: robert baratheon
content: She belonged with me.

author: robert baratheon
content: In my dreams, I kill him every night.

author: eddard stark
content: It's done, Your Grace. The Targaryens are gone.

author: robert baratheon
content: Not all of them.

author: viserys
content: Daenerys!

author: viserys
content: Daenerys! There's our bride to be! Look – a gift from Illyrio. Touch it. Come on. Feel the fabric. Mmmm. Isn't he a gracious host?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We've been his guests for over a year and he's never asked us for anything.

author: viserys
content: Illyrio is no fool. He knows I won't forget my friends when I come into my throne. You still slouch. Let me see. You have a woman's body now. I need you to be perfect today. Can you do that for me? You don't want to wake the dragon, do you?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: viserys
content: When they write the history of my reign, sweet sister, they will say it began today.

author: maid
content: It's too hot, my lady.

author: viserys
content: Where is he?

author: illyrio
content: The Dothraki are not known for their punctuality.

author: illyrio
content: May I present my honored guests? Viserys of House Targaryen, the third of his name. The rightful King of the Andals and the First Men. And his sister, Daenerys, of the House Targaryen.

author: viserys
content: Do you see how long his hair is? When Dothraki are defeated in combat, they cut off their braid so the whole world can see their shame. Khal Drogo has never been defeated. He's a savage, of course, but he's one of the finest killers alive. And you will be his queen.

author: illyrio
content: Come forward, my dear.

author: viserys
content: Where's he going?

author: illyrio
content: The ceremony is over.

author: viserys
content: But he didn't say anything. Did he like her?

author: illyrio
content: Trust me, Your Grace. If he didn't like her, we'd know.

author: illyrio
content: It won't be long now. Soon you will cross the Narrow Sea and take back your father's throne. The people drink secret toasts to your health. They cry out for their true king.

author: viserys
content: When will they be married?

author: illyrio
content: Soon. The Dothraki never stay still for long.

author: viserys
content: Is it true they lie with their horses?

author: illyrio
content: I wouldn't ask Khal Drogo.

author: viserys
content: Do you take me for a fool?

author: illyrio
content: I take you for a king. Kings lack the caution of common men. My apologies if I've given offense.

author: viserys
content: I know how to play a man like Drogo. I give him a queen and he gives me an army.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't want to be his queen. I want to go home.

author: viserys
content: So do I. I want us both to go home. But they took it from us. So tell me, sweet sister, how do we go home?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't know.

author: viserys
content: We go home with an army. With Khal Drogo's army. I would let his whole tribe fuck you, all 40,000 men and their horses too, if that's what it took.

author: sansa stark
content: Do you think Joffrey will like me? What if he thinks I'm ugly?

author: catelyn stark
content: Then he is the stupidest prince that ever lived.

author: sansa stark
content: He's so handsome.

author: sansa stark
content: When would we be married? Soon or do we have to wait?

author: catelyn stark
content: Hush now. Your father hasn't even said yes.

author: sansa stark
content: Why would he say no? He'd be the second most powerful man in the kingdoms.

author: catelyn stark
content: He'd have to leave home. He'd have to leave me. And so would you.

author: sansa stark
content: You left your home to come here. And I'd be queen someday. Please make father say yes.

author: catelyn stark
content: Sansa…

author: sansa stark
content: Please, please. It's the only thing I ever wanted.

author: benjen
content: Is he dead yet?

author: jon snow
content: Uncle Benjen!

author: benjen
content: You got bigger. I rode all day. Didn't want to leave you alone with the Lannisters. Why aren't you at the feast?

author: jon snow
content: Lady Stark thought it might insult the royal family to seat a bastard in their midst.

author: benjen
content: Well, you're always welcome on the wall. No bastard was ever refused a seat there.

author: jon snow
content: So take me with you when you go back.

author: benjen
content: Jon…

author: jon snow
content: Father will let me if you ask him, I know he will.

author: benjen
content: The Wall isn't going anywhere.

author: jon snow
content: I'm ready to swear your oath.

author: benjen
content: You don't understand what you'd be giving up. We have no families. None of us will ever father sons.

author: jon snow
content: I don't care about that.

author: benjen
content: You might, if you knew what it meant. … I'd better get inside. Rescue your father from his guests. We'll talk later.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your uncle's in the Night's Watch.

author: jon snow
content: What're you doing back there?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Preparing for a night with your family. I've always wanted to see the Wall.

author: jon snow
content: You're Tyrion Lannister. The queen's brother?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My greatest accomplishment. You – you're Ned Stark's bastard, aren't you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did I offend you? Sorry. You are the bastard, though.

author: jon snow
content: Lord Eddard Stark is my father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And Lady Stark is not your mother. Making you a bastard. Let me give you some advice, bastard. Never forget what you are. The rest of the world will not. Wear it like armor. Then it can never be used to hurt you.

author: jon snow
content: What the hell do you know about being a bastard?

author: tyrion lannister
content: All dwarves are bastards in their fathers' eyes.

author: benjen
content: You at a feast -- It's like a bear in a trap.

author: eddard stark
content: The boy I beheaded. Did you know him?

author: benjen
content: Of course I did. Just a lad. But he was tough, Ned. A true Ranger.

author: eddard stark
content: He was talking madness. Said the Walkers slaughtered his friends.

author: benjen
content: The two he was with are still missing.

author: eddard stark
content: A wildling ambush.

author: benjen
content: Maybe. Direwolves south of the wall. Talk of the Walkers. My brother might be the next Hand to the king. Winter is coming.

author: eddard stark
content: Winter is coming.

author: robb stark
content: Uncle Benjen.

author: benjen
content: Robb boy. How are ye?

author: robb stark
content: I'm good.

author: catelyn stark
content: Is this your first time in the North, Your Grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes. Lovely country.

author: catelyn stark
content: I'm sure it's very grim, after Kings Landing. I remember how scared I was when Ned brought me up here for the first time.

author: cersei lannister
content: Hello, little dove. But you are a beauty. How old are you?

author: sansa stark
content: Thirteen, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're tall. Still growing?

author: sansa stark
content: I think so, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: And have you bled yet?

author: sansa stark
content: No, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: And your dress. Did you make it?

author: cersei lannister
content: Such talent. You must make something for me.

author: cersei lannister
content: I hear we might share a grandchild someday.

author: catelyn stark
content: I hear the same.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your daughter will do well in the capital. Such a beauty shouldn't stay hidden up here forever.

author: eddard stark
content: Your pardon.

author: jaime lannister
content: I hear we might be neighbors soon. I hope it's true.

author: eddard stark
content: Yes, the king has honored me with his offer.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm sure we'll have a tournament to celebrate the new title, if you accept. It would be good to have you in the field. The competition has become a bit stale.

author: eddard stark
content: I don't fight in tournaments.

author: jaime lannister
content: No? Getting a little old for it?

author: eddard stark
content: I don't fight in tournaments because when I fight a man for real, I don't want him to know what I can do.

author: jaime lannister
content: Well said.

author: sansa stark
content: Arya!

author: robb stark
content: Time for bed.

author: eddard stark
content: I'm a Northman. I belong here with you, not down south in that rat's nest they call a capital.

author: catelyn stark
content: I won't let him take you.

author: eddard stark
content: The king takes what he wants. That's why he's king.

author: catelyn stark
content: I'll say, ‘Listen, fat man, you are not taking my husband anywhere. He belongs to me now.'

author: eddard stark
content: How did he get so fat?

author: catelyn stark
content: He only stops eating when it's time for a drink.

author: a voice
content: It's Maester Luwin, my lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Send him in.

author: luwin
content: Pardon, my lord, my lady. A rider in the night from your sister.

author: eddard stark
content: Stay.

author: catelyn stark
content: This was sent from the Eyrie. What's she doing at the Eyrie? She hasn't been back there since her wedding.

author: eddard stark
content: What news?

author: catelyn stark
content: She's fled the capital. She says Jon Arryn was murdered. By the Lannisters. She says the king is in danger.

author: eddard stark
content: She's fresh widowed, Cat. She doesn't know what she's saying.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lysa's head would be on a spike right now if the wrong people had found that letter. Do you think she would risk her life, her son's life, if she wasn't certain her husband was murdered?

author: luwin
content: If this news is true, and the Lannisters conspire against the throne, who but you can protect the king?

author: catelyn stark
content: They murdered the last Hand. Now you want Ned to take the job.

author: luwin
content: The king rode for a month to ask Lord Stark's help. He's the only one he trusts. You swore the king an oath, my lord.

author: catelyn stark
content: He spent half his life fighting Robert's wars. He owes him nothing. Your father and brother rode south once on a king's demand.

author: luwin
content: A different time. Different king.

author: viserys
content: When do I meet with the Khal? We need to begin planning the invasion.

author: illyrio
content: If Khal Drogo has promised you a crown, you shall have it.

author: viserys
content: When?

author: illyrio
content: When their omens favor war.

author: viserys
content: I piss on Dothraki omens. I waited 17 years to get my throne back.

author: illyrio
content: A Dothraki wedding without at least three deaths is considered a dull affair.

author: jorah mormont
content: A small gift for the new Khaleesi. Songs and histories from the Seven Kingdoms.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you, ser. Are you from my country?

author: jorah mormont
content: Ser Jorah Mormont of Bear Island. I served your father for many years. Gods be good, I hope to always serve the rightful king.

author: illyrio
content: Dragons' eggs, Daenerys. From the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai. The ages have turned them to stone, but they will always be beautiful.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you, Magister.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: She's beautiful. … Ser Jorah, I don't know how to say ‘thank you' in Dothraki.

author: jorah mormont
content: There is no word for ‘thank you' in Dothraki.

author: viserys
content: Make him happy.

author: khal drogo
content: No.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do you know the Common Tongue?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Is ‘no' the only word that you know?

author: sandor clegane
content: Rough night, Imp?

author: tyrion lannister
content: If I get through this without squirting from one end or the other, it will be a miracle.

author: sandor clegane
content: I didn't pick you for a hunter.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The greatest in the land. My spear never misses.

author: sandor clegane
content: It's not hunting if you pay for it.

author: robert baratheon
content: Are you as good with a spear as you used to be?

author: eddard stark
content: No, but I'm still better than you.

author: robert baratheon
content: I know what I'm putting you through. Thank you for saying yes. I only ask you because I need you. You're a loyal friend. You hear me? A loyal friend. The last one I've got.

author: eddard stark
content: I hope I'll serve you well.

author: robert baratheon
content: You will. And I'll make sure you don't look so fucking grim all the time. Come on, boys, let's go kill some boar!

author: bran stark
content: Come on, you.

author: cersei lannister
content: Stop. STOP.

author: jaime lannister
content: Are you completely mad?

author: cersei lannister
content: He saw us.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's all right. It's all right.

author: cersei lannister
content: He saw us!

author: jaime lannister
content: I heard you the first time. Quite the little climber, aren't you? How old are you, boy?

author: bran stark
content: Ten

author: jaime lannister
content: Ten.

author: jaime lannister
content: The things I do for love.

author: jorah mormont
content: You need to drink, child... And eat.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Isn't there anything else?

author: jorah mormont
content: The Dothraki have two things in abundance

author: doreah
content: Khaleesi!

author: irri
content: Your hands.

author: jorah mormont
content: We're still not far from Pentos, your Grace. Magister Illyrio has extended his hospitality. You'd be more comfortable there.

author: viserys targaryen
content: I have no interest in hospitality or comfort. I'll stay with Drogo until he fulfils his end of the bargain and I have my crown.

author: jorah mormont
content: As you wish, your Grace.

author: viserys targaryen
content: Well, Mormont, as brutish as this life is, I suppose it is preferable to beheading. What did Ned Stark want you for? Buying from a slaver?

author: jorah mormont
content: Selling to one... Some poachers I caught on my land.

author: viserys targaryen
content: Under my reign, you won't be punished for such nonsense. You can rest assured of that.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Better-looking bitches than you're used to, Uncle. My mother's been looking for you. We ride for King's Landing today.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Before you go, you will call on Lord and Lady Stark and offer your sympathies.

author: joffrey lannister
content: What good will my sympathies do them?

author: tyrion lannister
content: None. But it is expected of you. Your absence has already been noted.

author: joffrey lannister
content: The boy means nothing to me. And I can't stand the wailing of women.

author: tyrion lannister
content: One word and I'll hit you again.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'm telling mother!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Go! Tell her. But first you will get to Lord and Lady Stark and you will fall on your knees in front of them and tell them how very sorry you are, that you are at their service, and that all your prayers are with them. Do you understand?

author: joffrey lannister
content: You can't...

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you understand?

author: sandor clegane
content: The Prince will remember that, little lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I hope so. If he forgets, be a good dog and remind him. Time for breakfast...

author: tyrion lannister
content: Bread. And two of those little fish. And a mug of dark beer to wash it down. And bacon, burnt black.

author: jaime lannister
content: Little brother.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Beloved siblings.

author: myrcella baratheon
content: Is Bran going to die?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Apparently not.

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you mean?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Maester says the boy may live.

author: cersei lannister
content: It's no mercy, letting a child linger in such pain.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Only the gods know for certain. All the rest of us can do is pray. The charms of the north seem entirely lost on you.

author: cersei lannister
content: I still can't believe you're going. It's ridiculous even for you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where's your sense of wonder? The greatest structure ever built, the intrepid men of the Night's Watch, the wintry abode of the White Walkers.

author: jaime lannister
content: Tell me you're not thinking of taking the black.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And go celibate? The whores would go begging from Dorne to Casterly Rock. I just want to stand on top of the Wall and piss off the edge of the world.

author: cersei lannister
content: The children don't need to hear your filth. Come.

author: jaime lannister
content: Even if the boy lives, he'll be a cripple, a grotesque. Give me a good clean death any day.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Speaking for the grotesques, I'd have to disagree. Death is so final, whereas life... Life is full of possibilities. I hope the boy does wake. I'd be very interested to hear what he has to say.

author: jaime lannister
content: My dear brother, there are times you make me wonder whose side you're on.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My dear brother, you wound me. You know how much I love my family.

author: cersei lannister
content: Please.

author: catelyn stark
content: I would have dressed, your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: This is your home. I'm your guest. Handsome one, isn't he? I lost my first boy, a little black-haired beauty. He was a fighter too... Tried to beat the fever that took him. Forgive me. It's the last thing you need to hear right now.

author: catelyn stark
content: I never knew.

author: cersei lannister
content: It was years ago. Robert was crazed, beat his hands bloody on the wall, all the things men do to show you how much they care... The boy looked just like him. Such a little thing... A bird without feathers. They came to take his body away and Robert held me. I screamed and I battled, but he held me. That little bundle. They took him away and I never saw him again. Never have visited the crypt, never. I pray to the Mother every morning and night that she return your child to you.

author: catelyn stark
content: I am grateful..

author: cersei lannister
content: Perhaps this time she'll listen.

author: jaime lannister
content: A sword for the wall?

author: jon snow
content: I already have one.

author: jaime lannister
content: Good man. Have you swung it yet?

author: jon snow
content: Of course I have.

author: jaime lannister
content: At someone, I mean. It's a strange thing, the first time you cut a man. You realize we're nothing but sacks of meat and blood and some bone to keep it all standing. Let me thank you ahead of time for guarding us all from the perils beyond the Wall... Wildlings and White Walkers and whatnot. We're grateful to have good, strong men like you protecting us.

author: jon snow
content: We've guarded the Kingdoms for 8 000 years.

author: jaime lannister
content: Is it "we" already? Have you taken your vows then?

author: jon snow
content: Soon enough.

author: jaime lannister
content: Give my regards to the Night's Watch. I'm sure it will be thrilling to serve in such an elite force. And if not, It's only for life.

author: arya stark
content: Thank you, Nymeria. Septa Mordane says I have to do it again. "My things weren't properly folded", she says. Who cares how they're folded?! They're going to get all messed up anyway.

author: jon snow
content: It's good you've got help.

author: arya stark
content: Watch. Nymeria, gloves.

author: jon snow
content: Impressive.

author: arya stark
content: Shut up. Nymeria, gloves!

author: jon snow
content: I have something for you. And it has to be packed very carefully.

author: arya stark
content: A present?

author: jon snow
content: Close the door. This is no toy. Be careful you don't cut yourself.

author: arya stark
content: It's so skinny.

author: jon snow
content: So are you. I had the blacksmith make it for you special. It won't hack a man's head off, but it can poke him full of holes if you're quick enough.

author: arya stark
content: I can be quick.

author: jon snow
content: You'll have to work at it every day. How does it feel? Do you like the balance?

author: arya stark
content: I think so.

author: jon snow
content: First lesson

author: arya stark
content: I know which end to use.

author: jon snow
content: I'm going to miss you... Careful... All the best swords have names, you know.

author: arya stark
content: Sansa can keep her sewing needles. I've got a needle of my own.

author: jon snow
content: I came to say goodbye to Bran.

author: catelyn stark
content: You've said it.

author: jon snow
content: I wish I could be here when you wake up. I'm going north with Uncle Benjen. I'm taking the black. I know we always talked about seeing the Wall together, but you'll be able to come visit me at Castle Black when you're better. I'll know my way around by then. I'll be a sworn brother of the Night's Watch. We can go out walking beyond the Wall, if you're not afraid.

author: catelyn stark
content: I want you to leave.

author: catelyn stark
content: 17 years ago you rode off with Robert Baratheon. You came back a year later with another woman's son. And now you're leaving again.

author: eddard stark
content: I have no choice.

author: catelyn stark
content: That's what men always say when honor calls. That's what you tell your families, tell yourselves. You do have a choice. And you've made it. I can't do it, Ned. I really can't.

author: eddard stark
content: You can. You must.

author: robb stark
content: You've said goodbye to Bran? He's not going to die. I know it.

author: jon snow
content: You Starks are hard to kill.

author: robb stark
content: My mother?

author: jon snow
content: She was very kind.

author: robb stark
content: Good. Next time I see you, you'll be all in black.

author: jon snow
content: It was always my color.

author: robb stark
content: Farewell, Snow.

author: jon snow
content: And you, Stark.

author: eddard stark
content: There's great honor serving in the Night's Watch. The Starks have manned the Wall for thousands of years. And you are a Stark. You might not have my name, but you have my blood.

author: jon snow
content: Is my mother alive? Does she know about me? Where I am, where I'm going? Does she care?

author: eddard stark
content: The next time we see each other, we'll talk about your mother. I promise.

author: robert baratheon
content: Gods, this is country! I've half a mind to leave them all behind and keep going.

author: eddard stark
content: I've half a mind to go with you.

author: robert baratheon
content: What do you say, just you and me on the Kingsroad, swords at our sides, a couple of tavern wenches to warm our beds tonight.

author: eddard stark
content: You should have asked me 20 years ago.

author: robert baratheon
content: There were wars to fight, women to marry... We never had the chance to be young.

author: eddard stark
content: I recall a few chances.

author: robert baratheon
content: There was that one... Oh, what was her name? That common girl of yours? Becca? With the great big tits you could bury your face in.

author: eddard stark
content: Bessie. She was one of yours.

author: robert baratheon
content: Bessie! Thank the gods for Bessie and her tits. Yours was... Aleena? No. You told me once. Meryl? Your bastardo s mother?

author: eddard stark
content: Wylla.

author: robert baratheon
content: That's it. She must have been a rare wench to make Lord Eddard Stark forget his honor. You never told me what she looked like.

author: eddard stark
content: Nor will I.

author: robert baratheon
content: We were at war. None of us knew if we were gonna go back home again. You're too hard on yourself. You always have been. I swear if I weren't your King, you'd have hit me already.

author: eddard stark
content: The worst thing about your coronation... I'll never get to hit you again.

author: robert baratheon
content: Trust me, that's not the worst thing. There was a rider in the night.

author: eddard stark
content: Daenerys Targaryen has wed some Dothraki horselord. What of it? Should we send her a wedding gift?

author: robert baratheon
content: A knife perhaps, a good sharp one, and a bold man to wield it.

author: eddard stark
content: She's little more than a child.

author: robert baratheon
content: Soon enough that child will spread her legs and start breeding.

author: eddard stark
content: Tell me we're not speaking of this.

author: robert baratheon
content: Oh, it's unspeakable to you? What her father did to your family... That was unspeakable. What Rhaegar Targaryen did to your sister... the woman I loved. I'll kill every Targaryen I get my hands on.

author: eddard stark
content: But you can't get your hands on this one, can you?

author: robert baratheon
content: This Khal Drogo, it's said he has 100,000 men in his horde.

author: eddard stark
content: Even a million Dothraki are no threat to the realm, as long as they remain on the other side of the Narrow Sea. They have no ships, Robert.

author: robert baratheon
content: There are still those in the Seven Kingdoms who call me Usurper. If the Targaryen boy crosses with a Dothraki horde at his back, the scum will join him.

author: eddard stark
content: He will not cross. And if by chance he does, we'll throw him back into the sea.

author: robert baratheon
content: There's a war coming, Ned. I don't know when, I don't know who we'll be fighting, but it's coming.

author: benjen stark
content: Sit. You'll be fed. Untie them.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Rapers. They were given a choice no doubt... Castration or the Wall. Most choose the knife. Not impressed by your new brothers? Lovely thing about the Watch... You discard your old family and get a whole new one.

author: jon snow
content: Why do you read so much?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Look at me and tell me what you see.

author: jon snow
content: Is this a trick?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What you see is a dwarf. If I'd been born a peasant they might've left me out in the woods to die. Alas, I was born a Lannister of Casterly Rock. Things are expected of me. My father was the Hand of the King for 20 years.

author: jon snow
content: Until your brother killed that King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, until my brother killed him. Life is full of these little ironies. My sister married the new King and my repulsive nephew will be King after him. I must do my part for the honor of my house, wouldn't you agree? But how? Well, my brother has his sword and I have my mind. And a mind needs books like a sword needs a whetstone. That's why I read so much. And you? What's your story, bastard?

author: jon snow
content: Ask me nicely and maybe I'll tell you, dwarf.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A bastard boy with nothing to inherit, off to join the ancient order of the Night's Watch, alongside his valiant brothers-in-arms.

author: jon snow
content: The Night's Watch protects the realm from...

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes yes, against grumpkins and snarks and all the other monsters your wet nurse warned you about. You're a smart boy. You don't believe that nonsense... Everything's better with some wine in the belly.

author: maester luwin
content: It's time we reviewed the accounts, my lady. You'll want to know how much this royal visit has cost us.

author: catelyn stark
content: Talk to Poole about it.

author: maester luwin
content: Poole went south with Lord Stark, my lady. We need a new steward, and there are several other appointments that require our immediate attention...

author: catelyn stark
content: I don't care about appointments!

author: robb stark
content: I'll make the appointments. We'll talk about it first thing in the morning.

author: maester luwin
content: Very good, my Lord. My Lady.

author: robb stark
content: When was the last time you left this room?

author: catelyn stark
content: I have to take care of him.

author: robb stark
content: He's not going to die, mother. Maester Luwin says the most dangerous time has passed.

author: catelyn stark
content: What if he's wrong? Bran needs me.

author: robb stark
content: Rickon needs you. He's six. He doesn't know what's happening. He follows me around all day, clutching my leg, crying...

author: catelyn stark
content: Close the windows! I can't stand it! Please make them stop!

author: robb stark
content: Fire. You stay here. I'll come back.

author: assassin
content: You're not supposed to be here. No one is supposed to be here. It's a mercy. He's dead already.

author: catelyn stark
content: No!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Have you ever seen a dragon?

author: irri
content: Dragon gone, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Everywhere? Even in the east?

author: irri
content: No dragon. Brave men kill them. It is known.

author: jhiqui
content: It is known.

author: doreah
content: A trader from Garth told me that dragons come from the moon.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The moon?

author: doreah
content: He told me the moon was an egg, Khaleesi, that once there were two moons in the sky. But one wandered too close to the sun and it cracked from the heat. Out of it poured a thousand thousand dragons and they drank the sun's fire.

author: irri
content: Moon is no egg. Moon is goddess... wife of sun. It is known.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Leave me with her. Why did the trader from Garth tell you these stories?

author: doreah
content: Men like to talk when they're happy. Before your brother bought me for you, it was my job to make men happy.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How old were you?

author: doreah
content: I was nine when my mother sold me to the pleasure house.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Nine?!

author: doreah
content: I did not touch a man for three years, Khaleesi. First you must learn.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Can you teach me how to make the Khal happy?

author: doreah
content: Yes.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will it take three years?

author: doreah
content: No.

author: benjen stark
content: Welcome.

author: catelyn stark
content: What I am about to tell you must remain between us. I don't think Bran fell from that tower. I think he was thrown.

author: maester luwin
content: The boy was always sure-footed before.

author: catelyn stark
content: Someone tried to kill him twice. Why? Why murder an innocent child? Unless he saw something he wasn't meant to see.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Saw what, my lady?

author: catelyn stark
content: I don't know. But I would stake my life the Lannisters are involved. We already have reason to suspect their loyalty to the crown.

author: rodrick cassel
content: Did you notice the dagger the killer used? It's too fine a weapon for such a man. The blade is Valyrian steel, the handle dragonbone. Someone gave it to him.

author: robb stark
content: They come into our home and try to murder my brother? If it's war they want...

author: theon greyjoy
content: If it comes to that, you know I'll stand behind you.

author: maester luwin
content: What, is there going to be a battle in the Godswood? Too easily words of war become acts of war. We don't know the truth yet. Lord Stark must be told of this.

author: catelyn stark
content: I don't trust a raven to carry these words.

author: robb stark
content: I'll ride to King's Landing.

author: catelyn stark
content: No. There must always be a Stark in Winterfell. I will go myself.

author: robb stark
content: Mother, you can't.

author: catelyn stark
content: I must.

author: rodrick cassel
content: I'll send Hal with a squad of guardsmen to escort you.

author: catelyn stark
content: Too large a party attracts unwanted attention. I don't want the Lannisters to know I'm coming.

author: rodrick cassel
content: Let me accompany you at least. The Kingsroad can be a dangerous place for a woman alone.

author: robb stark
content: What about Bran?

author: catelyn stark
content: I have prayed to the Seven for more than a month. Bran's life is in their hands now.

author: doreah
content: No, Khaleesi. You must look in his eyes always. Love comes in at the eyes. It is said that Irogenia of Lys could finish a man with nothing but her eyes.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Finish a man?

author: doreah
content: Kings traveled across the world for a night with Irogenia. Magisters sold their palaces. Khals burned her enemies just to have her for a few hours. They say a thousand men proposed to her and she refused them all.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, she sounds like an interesting woman. I don't think that Drogo will like it with me on top.

author: doreah
content: You will make him like it, Khaleesi. Men want what they've never had. And the Dothraki take slaves like a hound takes a bitch. Are you a slave, Khaleesi? Then don't make love like a slave. Very good, Khaleesi. Out there he is the mighty Khal, but in this tent, he belongs to you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't think that this is the Dothraki way.

author: doreah
content: If he wanted the Dothraki way, why did he marry you?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No. No. Tonight I would look upon your face.

author: sansa stark
content: Pardon me, Ser.

author: sandor clegane
content: Do I frighten you so much, girl? Or is it him there making you shake? He frightens me too. Look at that face.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm sorry if I offended you, Ser. Why won't he speak to me?

author: sandor clegane
content: He hasn't been very talkative these last 20 years. Since the mad King had his tongue ripped out with hot pincers.

author: joffrey lannister
content: He speaks damn well with his sword though. Ser Ilyn Payne, the King's justice. The royal executioner. What is it, sweet lady? Does the hound frighten you? Away with you, dog. You're scaring my lady. I don't like to see you upset. The sun is finally shining. Come walk with me.

author: sansa stark
content: Stay, Lady. I probably shouldn't have any more. Father only lets us have one cup at feasts.

author: joffrey lannister
content: My princess can drink as much as she wants. Don't worry... You're safe with me.

author: mycah
content: I'll get you!

author: sansa stark
content: Arya!

author: arya stark
content: What are you doing here? Go away.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Your sister? And who are you, boy?

author: mycah
content: Mycah, my Lord.

author: sansa stark
content: He the butcher's boy.

author: arya stark
content: He's my friend.

author: joffrey lannister
content: A butcher's boy who wants to be a Knight, eh? Pick up your sword, butcher's boy. Let's see how good you are.

author: mycah
content: She asked me to, my Lord. She asked me to.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'm your prince, not your lord, and I said pick up your sword.

author: mycah
content: It's not a sword, my prince. It's only a stick.

author: joffrey lannister
content: And you're not a Knight. Only a butcher's boy. That was my lady's sister you were hitting, do you know that?

author: arya stark
content: Stop it!

author: sansa stark
content: Arya, stay out of this.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I won't hurt him... Much. Filthy little bitch!

author: sansa stark
content: No no, stop it, stop it, both of you. You're spoiling it. You're spoiling everything!

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'll gut you, you little cunt!

author: arya stark
content: Nymeria!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Please don't.

author: sansa stark
content: Arya, leave him alone. My prince, my poor prince, look what they did to you. Stay here, I'll go back to the inn and bring help.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Then go! Don't touch me.

author: soldier
content: The wolf's not here. Look down by the stream.

author: arya stark
content: You've got to go. They'll kill you for what you did to Joffrey. Go on... run. Go! Leave now!

author: soldier
content: It's a direwolf.

author: soldier
content: I'll check down here.

author: soldier
content: I think I heard a noise.

author: arya stark
content: Go!

author: jory cassel
content: My lord! My lord! They found her. She's unharmed.

author: eddard stark
content: Where is she?

author: jory cassel
content: She's been taken directly before the King.

author: eddard stark
content: Who took her?

author: jory cassel
content: The Lannisters found her.

author: eddard stark
content: Right, get back.

author: jory cassel
content: The Queen ordered them to bring her straight to him.

author: eddard stark
content: Back! Back to the inn. All back!

author: arya stark
content: I'm sorry.

author: eddard stark
content: Are you hurt?

author: arya stark
content: No.

author: eddard stark
content: It's all right. What is the meaning of this? Why was my daughter not brought to me at once?

author: cersei lannister
content: How dare you speak to your King in that manner?

author: robert baratheon
content: Quiet, woman. Sorry, Ned. I never meant to frighten the girl. But we need to get this business done quickly.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your girl and that butcher's boy attacked my son. That animal of hers nearly tore his arm off.

author: arya stark
content: That's not true! She just... Bit him a little. He was hurting Mycah.

author: cersei lannister
content: Joffrey told us what happened. You and that boy beat him with clubs while you set your wolf on him.

author: arya stark
content: That's not what happened!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Yes it is! They all attacked me and she threw my sword in the river.

author: arya stark
content: Liar!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Shut up!

author: robert baratheon
content: Enough! He tells me one thing, she tells me another. Seven hells! What am I to make of this? Where's your other daughter, Ned?

author: eddard stark
content: In bed asleep.

author: cersei lannister
content: She's not. Sansa, come here, darling.

author: robert baratheon
content: Now, child... Tell me what happened. Tell it all and tell it true. It's a great crime to lie to a King.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't know. I don't remember. Everything happened so fast. I didn't see.

author: arya stark
content: Liar! Liar liar liar!

author: eddard stark
content: Stop it! That's enough of that.

author: arya stark
content: Liar liar liar!

author: eddard stark
content: Stop! Arya!

author: cersei lannister
content: She's as wild as that animal of hers. I want her punished.

author: robert baratheon
content: What would you have me do, whip her through the streets? Damn it, children fight. It's over.

author: cersei lannister
content: Joffrey will bear these scars for the rest of his life.

author: robert baratheon
content: You let that little girl disarm you? See to it that your daughter is disciplined. I'll do the same with my son.

author: eddard stark
content: Gladly, your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: And what of the direwolf? What of the beast that savaged your son?

author: robert baratheon
content: I'd forgot the damned wolf.

author: soldier
content: We found no trace of the direwolf, your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: So be it.

author: cersei lannister
content: We have another wolf.

author: robert baratheon
content: As you will.

author: eddard stark
content: You can't mean it.

author: robert baratheon
content: A direwolf's no pet. Get her a dog. She'll be happier for it.

author: sansa stark
content: He doesn't mean Lady, does he? No no, not Lady! Lady didn't bite anyone! She's good!

author: arya stark
content: Lady wasn't there! You leave her alone!

author: sansa stark
content: Stop them. Don't let them do it. Please! It wasn't Lady!

author: eddard stark
content: s this your command... your Grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: Where is the beast?

author: soldier
content: Chained up outside, your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Ser Ilyn, do me the honor.

author: eddard stark
content: No. Jory... Take the girls to their rooms. If it must be done, then I'll do it myself.

author: cersei lannister
content: Is this some trick?

author: eddard stark
content: The wolf is of the north. She deserves better than a butcher.

author: eddard stark
content: The butcher's boy... You rode him down?

author: sandor clegane
content: He ran... Not very fast.

author: kings landing guard
content: Welcome, Lord Stark. Grand Maester Pycelle has called a meeting of the Small Council. The honor of your presence is requested.

author: eddard stark
content: Get the girls settled in. I'll be back in time for supper. And, Jory, you go with them.

author: jory cassel
content: Yes, my Lord.

author: kings landing guard
content: If you'd like to change into something more appropriate…

author: jaime lannister
content: Thank the gods you're here, Stark. About time we had some stern northern leadership.

author: eddard stark
content: Glad to see you're protecting the throne.

author: jaime lannister
content: Sturdy old thing. How many kings' asses have polished it, I wonder? What's the line? The King shits and the Hand wipes.

author: eddard stark
content: Very handsome armor. Not a scratch on it.

author: jaime lannister
content: I know. People have been swinging at me for years, but they always seem to miss.

author: eddard stark
content: You've chosen your opponents wisely then.

author: jaime lannister
content: I have a knack for it. It must be strange for you coming into this room. I was standing right here when it happened. He was very brave, your brother. Your father too. They didn't deserve to die like that. Nobody deserves to die like that.

author: eddard stark
content: But you just stood there and watched.

author: jaime lannister
content: 500 men just stood there and watched. All the great knights of the Seven Kingdoms. You think anyone said a word, lifted a finger? No, Lord Stark. 500 men and this room was silent as a crypt. Except for the screams, of course, and the Mad King laughing. And later... When I watched the Mad King die, I remembered him laughing as your father burned... It felt like justice.

author: eddard stark
content: Is that what you tell yourself at night? You're a servant of justice? That you were avenging my father when you shoved your sword in Aerys Targaryen's back?

author: jaime lannister
content: Tell me... If I'd stabbed the Mad King in the belly instead of the back, would you admire me more?

author: eddard stark
content: You served him well, when serving was safe.

author: varys
content: Lord Stark.

author: eddard stark
content: Lord Varys.

author: varys
content: I was grievously sorry to hear of your troubles on the Kingsroad. We are all praying for Prince Joffrey's full recovery.

author: eddard stark
content: A shame you didn't say a prayer for the butcher's son. Renly! You're looking well.

author: renly baratheon
content: And you look tired from the road. I told them this meeting could wait another day, but...

author: petyr baelish
content: But we have a Kingdom to look after. I've hoped to meet you for some time, Lord Stark. No doubt Lady Catelyn has mentioned me.

author: eddard stark
content: She has, Lord Baelish. I understand you knew my brother Brandon as well.

author: petyr baelish
content: All too well. I still carry a token of his esteem from navel to collarbone.

author: eddard stark
content: Perhaps you chose the wrong man to duel with.

author: petyr baelish
content: It wasn't the man that I chose, my Lord. It was Catelyn Tully. A woman worth fighting for, I'm sure you'll agree.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: I humbly beg your pardon, my Lord Stark.

author: eddard stark
content: Grand Maester.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: How many years has it been? You were a young man.

author: eddard stark
content: And you served another King.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: How forgetful of me. This belongs to you, now. Should we begin?

author: eddard stark
content: Without the King?

author: renly baratheon
content: Winter may be coming, but I'm afraid the same cannot be said for my brother.

author: varys
content: His Grace has many cares. He entrusts some small matters to us that we might lighten the load.

author: petyr baelish
content: We are the lords of small matters here.

author: renly baratheon
content: My brother instructs us to stage a tournament in honor of Lord Stark's appointment as Hand of the King.

author: petyr baelish
content: Mmm, how much?

author: eddard stark
content: 40,000 gold dragons to the champion, 20,000 to the runner-up, 20,000 to the winning archer.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Can the treasury bear such expense?

author: petyr baelish
content: I'll have to borrow it. The Lannisters will accommodate, I expect. We already owe Lord Tywin 3 million gold. What's another 80,000?

author: eddard stark
content: Are you telling me the Crown is three million in debt?

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm telling you the Crown is six million in debt.

author: eddard stark
content: How could you let this happen?

author: petyr baelish
content: The Master of Coin finds the money. The King and the Hand spend it.

author: eddard stark
content: I will not believe Jon Arryn allowed Robert to bankrupt the realm.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Lord Arryn gave wise and prudent advice, but I fear His Grace doesn't always listen.

author: renly baratheon
content: Counting coppers," he calls it.

author: eddard stark
content: I'll speak to him tomorrow. This tournament is an extravagance we cannot afford.

author: petyr baelish
content: As you will. But still, we'd best make our plans.

author: eddard stark
content: There will be no plans until I speak to Robert. Forgive me, my Lords. I had a long ride.

author: varys
content: You are the King's Hand, Lord Stark, we serve at your pleasure.

author: cersei lannister
content: Please, it's nearly healed.

author: joffrey lannister
content: It's ugly.

author: cersei lannister
content: A King should have scars, you fought off a direwolf. You're a warrior like your father.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'm not like him. I didn't fight off anything. It bit me and all I did was scream. And the two Stark girls saw it, both of them.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's not true. You killed the beast. You only spared the girl because of the love your father bears her father. When Aerys Targaryen sat on the Iron Throne, your father was a rebel and a traitor. Someday you'll sit on the throne and the truth will be what you make it.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Do I have to marry her?

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes. She's very beautiful and young. If you don't like her, you only need to see her on formal occasions and when the time comes, to make little princes and princesses. And if you'd rather fuck painted whores, you'll fuck painted whores. And if you'd rather lie with noble virgins, so be it. You are my darling boy and the world will be exactly as you want it to be. Do something nice for the Stark girl.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I don't want to.

author: cersei lannister
content: No, but you will. The occasional kindness will spare you all sorts of trouble down the road.

author: joffrey lannister
content: We allow the northerners too much power. They consider themselves our equals.

author: cersei lannister
content: How would you handle them?

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'd double their taxes and command them to supply 10,000 men to the royal army.

author: cersei lannister
content: A royal army?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Why should every lord command his own men? It's primitive, no better than the hill tribes. We should have a standing army of men loyal to the Crown, trained by experienced soldiers... Instead of a mob of peasants who've never held pikes in their lives.

author: cersei lannister
content: And if the northerners rebel?

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'd crush them. Seize Winterfell and install someone loyal to the realm as Warden of the North. Uncle Kevan, maybe.

author: cersei lannister
content: And these 10,000 northern troops, would they fight for you or their lord?

author: joffrey lannister
content: For me. I'm their King.

author: cersei lannister
content: But you've just invaded their homeland, asked them to kill their brothers.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'm not asking.

author: cersei lannister
content: The North cannot be held... not by an outsider. It's too big and too wild. When the winter comes, the Seven gods together couldn't save you and your royal army. A good King knows when to save his strength... And when to destroy his enemies.

author: joffrey lannister
content: So you agree... The Starks are enemies?

author: cersei lannister
content: Everyone who isn't us is an enemy.

author: septa mordane
content: Enough of that, young lady. Eat your food.

author: arya stark
content: I'm practicing.

author: sansa stark
content: Practicing for what?

author: arya stark
content: The Prince.

author: septa mordane
content: Arya, stop!

author: arya stark
content: He's a liar and a coward and he killed my friend.

author: sansa stark
content: The Hound killed your friend.

author: arya stark
content: The Hound does whatever the Prince tells him to do.

author: sansa stark
content: You're an idiot.

author: arya stark
content: You're a liar. And if you told the truth, Mycah would be alive.

author: septa mordane
content: Enough!

author: eddard stark
content: What's happening here?

author: septa mordane
content: Arya would rather act like a beast than a lady.

author: eddard stark
content: Go to your room. We'll speak later. That's for you, love…

author: eddard stark
content: The same dollmaker makes all of Princess Myrcella's toys. Don't you like it?

author: sansa stark
content: I haven't played with dolls since I was eight. May I be excused?

author: septa mordane
content: You've barely eaten a thing.

author: eddard stark
content: It's all right. Go on.

author: eddard stark
content: War was easier than daughters.

author: arya stark
content: Go away!

author: eddard stark
content: Arya, open the door. May I come in? Whose sword is that?

author: arya stark
content: Mine.

author: eddard stark
content: Give it to me. I know this maker's mark. This is Mikken's work. Where did you get this? This is no toy. Little ladies shouldn't play with swords.

author: arya stark
content: I wasn't playing. And I don't want to be a lady.

author: eddard stark
content: Come here. Now what do you want with this?

author: arya stark
content: It's called Needle.

author: eddard stark
content: A blade with a name. And who were you hoping to skewer with Needle? Your sister? Do you know the first thing about sword fighting?

author: arya stark
content: Stick 'em with the pointy end.

author: eddard stark
content: laughs] That's the essence of it.

author: arya stark
content: I was trying to learn. I asked Mycah to practice with me. I asked him. It was my fault.

author: eddard stark
content: No, sweet girl. You didn't kill the butcher's boy.

author: arya stark
content: I hate them! I hate all of them. The Hound, the Queen and the King and Joffrey and Sansa.

author: eddard stark
content: Sansa was dragged before the King and Queen... And asked to call the Prince a liar.

author: arya stark
content: So was I! He is a liar.

author: eddard stark
content: Darling, listen to me. Sansa will be married to Joffrey someday. She cannot betray him. She must take his side even when he's wrong.

author: arya stark
content: But how you can let her marry someone like that?

author: eddard stark
content: Well… Look at me. You're a Stark of Winterfell. You know our words.

author: arya stark
content: Winter is coming.

author: eddard stark
content: You were born in the long summer. You've never known anything else. But now winter is truly coming. And in the winter, we must protect ourselves, look after one another. Sansa is your sister.

author: arya stark
content: I don't hate her. Not really.

author: eddard stark
content: I don't want to frighten you, but I won't lie to you either. We've come to a dangerous place. We cannot fight a war amongst ourselves. All right? Go on. It's yours.

author: arya stark
content: I can keep it?

author: eddard stark
content: Try not to stab your sister with it. If you're going to own a sword, you'd better know how to use it.

author: old nan
content: Don't listen to it. Crows are all liars. I know a story about a crow.

author: bran stark
content: I hate your stories.

author: old nan
content: I know a story about a boy who hated stories. I could tell you about Ser Duncan the Tall. Those were always your favorites.

author: bran stark
content: Those weren't my favorites. My favorites were the scary ones.

author: old nan
content: Oh, my sweet summer child. What do you know about fear? Fear is for the winter, when the snows fall a hundred feet deep. Fear is for the long night, when the sun hides for years and children are born and live and die all in darkness. That is the time for fear, my little Lord, when the White Walkers move through the woods. Thousands of years ago there came a night that lasted a generation. Kings froze to death in their castles, same as the shepherds in their huts. And women smothered their babies rather than see them starve, and wept and felt the tears freeze on their cheeks. So is this the sort of story that you like? In that darkness, the White Walkers came for the first time. They swept through cities and kingdoms, riding their dead horses, hunting with their packs of pale spiders big as hounds…

author: robb stark
content: What are you telling him now?

author: old nan
content: Only what the little Lord wants to hear.

author: robb stark
content: Get your supper. I want some time with him. One time she told me the sky is blue because we live inside the eye of a blue-eyed giant named Macumber.

author: bran stark
content: Maybe we do.

author: robb stark
content: How do you feel? You still don't remember anything? I've seen you climb a thousand times. In the wind, in the rain... A thousand times. You never fall.

author: bran stark
content: I did though. It's true, isn't it... what Maester Luwin says about my legs? I'd rather be dead.

author: robb stark
content: Don't ever say that.

author: bran stark
content: I'd rather be dead.

author: rodrick cassel
content: Fewer eyes back here, my Lady. But still too many.

author: catelyn stark
content: It's nine years since I've set foot in the capital. And no one knew who I was the last time I came either.

author: rodrick cassel
content: My Lady.

author: guard
content: Welcome to King's Landing, Lady Stark. Would you mind following us?

author: catelyn stark
content: I would. We've done nothing wrong.

author: guard
content: We've been instructed to escort you into the city.

author: catelyn stark
content: Instructed? I don't know who's providing your instructions, but...

author: guard
content: Follow me, Lady Stark.

author: petyr baelish
content: Cat! Go on. Go upstairs.

author: catelyn stark
content: You little worm! You take me for some back-alley Sally you can drag into a…

author: petyr baelish
content: I meant no disrespect to you of all people.

author: catelyn stark
content: How dare you bring me here! Have you lost your mind?

author: petyr baelish
content: No one will come looking for you here. Isn't that what like you wanted? I'm truly sorry... about the locale.

author: catelyn stark
content: How did you know I was coming to King's Landing?

author: petyr baelish
content: A dear friend told me.

author: varys
content: Lady Stark.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord Varys.

author: varys
content: To see you again after so many years is a blessing. Your poor hands.

author: catelyn stark
content: How did you know I was coming?

author: varys
content: Knowledge is my trade, my Lady. Did you bring the dagger with you, by any chance? My little birds are everywhere. Even in the north. They whisper to me the strangest stories. Valyrian steel.

author: catelyn stark
content: Do you know whose dagger this is?

author: varys
content: I must admit I do not.

author: petyr baelish
content: Well well, this is an historic day. Something you don't know that I do. There's only one dagger like this in all of the Seven Kingdoms. It's mine.

author: catelyn stark
content: Yours?

author: petyr baelish
content: At least it was, until the tournament on Prince Joffrey's last nameday. I bet on Ser Jaime in the jousting, as any sane man would. When the Knight of the Flowers unseated him, I lost this dagger.

author: catelyn stark
content: To whom?

author: petyr baelish
content: Tyrion Lannister. The Imp.

author: alliser thorne
content: If that were a real sword, you'd be dead. Lord Snow here grew up in a castle spitting down on the likes of you. Pyp. Do you think Ned Stark's bastard bleeds like the rest of us?

author: alliser thorne
content: Next!

author: alliser thorne
content: Lord Snow, it appears you're the least useless person here. Go clean yourselves up. There's only so much I can stomach in a day.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A charming man.

author: jeor mormont
content: I don't need him to be charming. I need him to turn this bunch of thieves and runaways into men of the Night's Watch.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And how's that going, Commander Mormont?

author: jeor mormont
content: Slowly. A raven came for Ned Stark's son.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good news or bad?

author: jeor mormont
content: Both.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Lord Stark. I meant to give you this earlier. So forgetful these days. A raven from Winterfell this morning.

author: petyr baelish
content: Good news? Perhaps you'd like to share it with your wife?

author: eddard stark
content: My wife is in Winterfell.

author: petyr baelish
content: Is she?

author: petyr baelish
content: I thought that she'd be safest in here. One of several such establishments I own.

author: eddard stark
content: You're a funny man. A very funny man.

author: catelyn stark
content: Ned! [poking her head out of a window]

author: petyr baelish
content: The Starks... Quick tempers, slow minds.

author: grenn
content: You broke my nose, bastard!

author: jon snow
content: It's an improvement.

author: grenn
content: If we threw you over the Wall, wonder how long it'd take you to hit.

author: pyp
content: I wonder if they'd find you before the wolves did.

author: grenn
content: What're you looking at, halfman?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm looking at you. You've got an interesting face. Very distinctive faces. All of you.

author: rast
content: What do you care about our faces?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's just I think they would look marvelous decorating spikes in King's Landing. Perhaps I'll write my sister, the Queen, about it.

author: grenn
content: We'll talk later, Lord Snow.

author: jon snow
content: Everybody knew what this place was and no one told me. No one but you. My father knew and left me to rot here at the Wall all the same.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Grenn's father left him too... Outside a farmhouse when he was three. Pyp was caught stealing a wheel of cheese. His little sister hadn't eaten in three days. He was given a choice

author: jon snow
content: They hate me because I'm better than they are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's a lucky thing none of them were trained by a master-at-arms like your Ser Rodrik. I don't imagine any of them have ever held a real sword before they came here. Your brother Bran. He's woken up.

author: petyr baelish
content: The mere suggestion that the Queen's brother tried to kill your boy would be considered treason.

author: catelyn stark
content: We have proof. We have the blade.

author: petyr baelish
content: Which Lord Tyrion will say was stolen from him. The only man who could say otherwise has no throat, thanks to your boy's wolf.

author: catelyn stark
content: Petyr has promised to help us find the truth. He's like a little brother to me. He would never betray my trust.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'll try to keep you alive, for her sake. A fool's task, admittedly, but I've never been able to refuse your wife anything.

author: catelyn stark
content: I won't forget this. You're a true friend.

author: petyr baelish
content: Don't tell anyone. I have a reputation to maintain.

author: cersei lannister
content: How could you be so stupid?

author: jaime lannister
content: Calm down.

author: cersei lannister
content: He's a child... 10 years old. What were you thinking?

author: jaime lannister
content: I was thinking of us. You're a bit late to start complaining about it now. What has the boy told them?

author: cersei lannister
content: Nothing. He's said nothing. He remembers nothing.

author: jaime lannister
content: Then what are you raving about?

author: cersei lannister
content: What if it comes back to him? If he tells his father what he saw...

author: jaime lannister
content: We'll say he was lying. We'll say he was dreaming. We'll say whatever we like. I think we can outfox a 10-year-old.

author: cersei lannister
content: And my husband?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll go to war with him if I have to. They can write a ballad about us

author: cersei lannister
content: Let me go.

author: jaime lannister
content: Never.

author: jaime lannister
content: The boy won't talk. And if he does, I'll kill him. Him, Ned Stark, the King... the whole bloody lot of them, until you and I are the only people left in this world.

author: catelyn stark
content: I wish I could see the girls.

author: eddard stark
content: It's too dangerous.

author: catelyn stark
content: Just for a moment.

author: eddard stark
content: Until we know who our enemies are...

author: catelyn stark
content: I know they did it, Ned. The Lannisters. In my bones, I know it.

author: eddard stark
content: Littlefinger's right. I can't do anything without proof.

author: cersei lannister
content: And if you find the proof?

author: eddard stark
content: Then I bring it to Robert... And hope he's still the man I once knew. You watch yourself on the road, huh? That temper of yours is a dangerous thing.

author: catelyn stark
content: My temper? Gods be good, you nearly killed poor Littlefinger yesterday.

author: eddard stark
content: He still loves you.

author: catelyn stark
content: Does he?

author: eddard stark
content: Off with you.

author: robert baratheon
content: It's been a long time. But I still remember every face. You remember your first?

author: barristan selmy
content: Of course, your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: Who was it?

author: barristan selmy
content: A Tyroshi. Never learned the name.

author: robert baratheon
content: How'd you do it?

author: barristan selmy
content: Lance through the heart.

author: robert baratheon
content: Quick one. Lucky for you. Mine was some Tarly boy at the Battle of Summerhall. My horse took an arrow so I was on foot, slogging through the mud. He came running at me, this dumb high-born lad, thinking he could end the rebellion with the single swing of his sword. I knocked him down with the hammer. Gods, I was strong then. Caved in his breastplate. Probably shattered every rib he had. Stood over him, hammer in the air. Right before I brought it down he shouted, "Wait! Wait!"... They never tell you how they all shit themselves. They don't put that part in the songs. Stupid boy. Now the Tarlys bend the knee like everyone else. He could have lingered on the edge of the battle with the smart boys and today his wife would be making him miserable, his sons would be ingrates, and he'd be waking three times in the night to piss into a bowl. Wine! Lancel. Gods, what a stupid name. Lancel Lannister. Who named you? Some halfwit with a stutter? What are you doing?

author: lancel lannister
content: It's empty, your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: What do you mean it's empty?

author: lancel lannister
content: There's no more wine.

author: robert baratheon
content: Is that what empty means?! So get more. Tell your cousin to get in here. Kingslayer! Get in here. Surrounded by Lannisters. Every time I close my eyes I see their blond hair and their smug, satisfied faces. It must wound your pride, huh? Standing out there like a glorified sentry. Jaime Lannister, son of the mighty Tywin... Forced to mind the door while your King eats and drinks and shits and fucks. So come on. We're telling war stories. Who was your first kill, not counting old men?

author: jaime lannister
content: One of the outlaws in the Brotherhood.

author: barristan selmy
content: I was there that day. You were only a squire, 16 years old.

author: jaime lannister
content: You killed Simon Toyne with a counter riposte. Best move I ever saw.

author: barristan selmy
content: A good fighter, Toyne, but he lacked stamina.

author: robert baratheon
content: Your outlaw... Any last words?

author: jaime lannister
content: I cut his head off, so no.

author: robert baratheon
content: What about Aerys Targaryen? What did the Mad King say when you stabbed him in the back? I never asked. Did he call you a traitor? Did he plead for a reprieve?

author: jaime lannister
