author: robin arryn
content: He's little.

author: lysa arryn
content: He's Tyrion the Imp of House Lannister. He killed your father. He murdered the Hand of the King!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh? Did I kill him too? I've been a very busy man.

author: lysa arryn
content: You will watch your tongue! These men are Knights of the Vale. Every one of the loved Jon Arryn. Every one of them would die for me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If any harm comes to me, my brother, Jaime, will see that they do.

author: robin arryn
content: You can't hurt us! No one can hurt us here! Tell him, mommy! Tell him!

author: lysa arryn
content: Shh... Shh... Shh, my sweet boy. He's just trying to frighten us. Lannisters are all liars. No one will hurt my baby.

author: robin arryn
content: Mommy... I want to see the bad man fly.

author: lysa arryn
content: Perhaps you will, my little love.

author: catelyn stark
content: This man is my prisoner. I will not have him harmed.

author: lysa arryn
content: Ser Vardis, my sister's guest is weary. Take him down below so he can rest. Introduce him to Mord.

author: mord
content: You go sleep, dwarf man. Sleep good, little dwarf. man!

author: loras tyrell
content: Lord Stark's lucky he still has a head.

author: renly baratheon
content: Robert will rant for a few days, but he won't do anything. He adores the man.

author: loras tyrell
content: You're jealous.

author: renly baratheon
content: Are you sure this won't hurt?

author: loras tyrell
content: Only if I slip.

author: renly baratheon
content: And you prefer me like this?

author: loras tyrell
content: Mhmm.

author: renly baratheon
content: If you want hairless, maybe you should find a little boy.

author: loras tyrell
content: I want you.

author: renly baratheon
content: My brother thinks that anyone who hasn't been to war isn't a man. He treats me as if I'm a spoiled child. Oh, and you're not? Loras Tyrell, the Knight of the Flowers? How many wars have you fought in? Oh, and how much did your father spend on that armor of yours?

author: loras tyrell
content: Hold still.

author: renly baratheon
content: All I ever hear from Robert and Stannis is how I'm not tough enough, how I squirm at the sight of blood.

author: loras tyrell
content: You did vomit when that boy's eye was knocked out in the mêlée.

author: renly baratheon
content: His eye was dangling out of the damn socket!

author: loras tyrell
content: He shouldn't have entered the mêlée if he didn't know how to fight.

author: renly baratheon
content: Easy for you to say. Not everyone is such a gifted swordsman.

author: loras tyrell
content: It's not a gift. No one gave it to me. I'm good because I work at it -- every day of my life since I could hold a stick.

author: renly baratheon
content: I could work at fighting all day, every day, and still never be as good as you.

author: loras tyrell
content: Yes well, I guess we'll never know.

author: renly baratheon
content: Everywhere?

author: loras tyrell
content: Everywhere. So how did it end up? The Targaryen girl will die?

author: renly baratheon
content: It needs to be done, unpleasant as it is. Robert's rather tasteless about it. Every time he talks about killing her, I swear the table rises six inches.

author: loras tyrell
content: It's a shame he can't muster the same enthusiasm for his wife.

author: renly baratheon
content: He does have a deep, abiding lust for her money. You have to give it to the Lannisters, they may be the most pompous, ponderous cunts the gods ever suffered to walk the world, but they do have outrageous amounts of money.

author: loras tyrell
content: I have an outrageous amount of money.

author: renly baratheon
content: Not as much as the Lannisters.

author: loras tyrell
content: But a lot more than you.

author: renly baratheon
content: Robert's threatening to take me hunting with him. Last time we were out there for two weeks, tramping through the trees in the rain, day after day. All so he can stick his spear into something's flesh! Oh. but Robert loves his killing. And he's the King.

author: loras tyrell
content: Hmm... How did that ever happen?

author: renly baratheon
content: Because he loves his killing and he used to be good at it.

author: loras tyrell
content: Do you know who should be King?

author: renly baratheon
content: Be serious.

author: loras tyrell
content: I am. My father could be your bank. I've never fought in a war before, but I'd fight for you.

author: renly baratheon
content: I'm fourth in line.

author: loras tyrell
content: And where was Robert in the line of royal succession? Joffrey is a monster. Tommen is eight.

author: renly baratheon
content: Stannis?

author: loras tyrell
content: Stannis has the personality of a lobster.

author: renly baratheon
content: He's still my older brother.

author: renly baratheon
content: What are you doing?!

author: loras tyrell
content: Look at it.

author: renly baratheon
content: You cut me!

author: loras tyrell
content: It's just blood. We've all got it in us. Sometimes a little spills. If you become King, you're going to see a lot of this. You need to get used to it. Go on. Look. People love you. They love to serve you because you're kind to them. They want to be near you.

author: loras tyrell
content: You're willing to do what needs to be done, but you don't gloat over it. You don't love killing. Where is it written that power is the sole province of the worst? That thrones are only made for the hated and the feared. You would be a wonderful King.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm sorry your marriage to Ned Stark didn't work out. You seemed so good together.

author: robert baratheon
content: I'm glad I could do something to make you happy.

author: cersei lannister
content: Without a Hand, everything will fall to pieces.

author: robert baratheon
content: I suppose this is where you tell me to give the job to your brother Jaime.

author: cersei lannister
content: No. He's not serious enough. I'll say this for Ned Stark - he's serious enough. Was it really worth it? Losing him this way?

author: robert baratheon
content: I don't know. But I do know this, if the Targaryen girl convinces her horse-lord husband to invade and the Dothraki horde crosses The Narrow Sea... We won't be able to stop them.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Dothraki don't sail. Every child knows that. They don't have discipline. They don't have armor. They don't have siege weapons.

author: robert baratheon
content: It's a neat little trick you do, you move your lips and your father's voice comes out.

author: cersei lannister
content: Is my father wrong?

author: robert baratheon
content: Let's say Viserys Targaryen lands with forty thousand Dothraki screamers at his back. We hole up in our castles, a wise move. Only a fool would meet the Dothraki in an open field. They leave us in our castles. They go from town to town, looting and burning, killing every man who can't hide behind a stone wall, stealing all our crops and livestock, enslaving all our women and children. How long do the people of the Seven Kingdoms stand behind their absentee King, their cowardly King hiding behind high walls? When do the people decide that Viserys Targaryen is the rightful monarch after all.

author: cersei lannister
content: We still outnumber them.

author: robert baratheon
content: Which is the bigger number -- five or one?

author: cersei lannister
content: Five.

author: robert baratheon
content: Five... one. One army, a real army, united behind one leader with one purpose. Our purpose died with the Mad King. Now we've got as many armies as there are men with gold in their purse. And everybody wants something different. Your father wants to own the world. Ned Stark wants to run away and bury his head in the snow.

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you want?

author: robert baratheon
content: We haven't had a real fight in nine years. Back-stabbing doesn't prepare you for a fight. And that's all the realm is now, back-stabbing and scheming and arse-licking and money-grubbing. Sometimes I don't know what holds it together.

author: cersei lannister
content: Our marriage.

author: robert baratheon
content: Ah, so here we sit, seventeen years later, holding it all together. Don't you get tired?

author: cersei lannister
content: Every day.

author: robert baratheon
content: How long can hate hold a thing together?

author: cersei lannister
content: Well, seventeen years is quite a long time.

author: robert baratheon
content: Yes, it is.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes, it tis. What was she like?

author: robert baratheon
content: You've never asked about her, not once. Why not?

author: cersei lannister
content: At first, just saying her name, even in private felt like I was breathing life back into her. I thought if I didn't talk about her, she'd just fade away for you. When I realized that wasn't going to happen, I refused to ask out of spite. I didn't want to give you the satisfaction of thinking I cared enough to ask. And eventually it became clear that my spite didn't mean anything to you, as far as I could tell, you actually enjoyed it.

author: robert baratheon
content: So why now?

author: cersei lannister
content: What harm could Lyanna Stark's ghost do to either of us that we haven't done to each other a hundred times over?

author: robert baratheon
content: You want to know the horrible truth? I can't even remember what she looked like. I only know she was the one thing I ever wanted... Someone took her away from me, and Seven Kingdoms couldn't fill the hole she left behind.

author: cersei lannister
content: I felt something for you once, you know?

author: robert baratheon
content: I know.

author: cersei lannister
content: Even after we lost our first boy -- for quite a while, actually. Was it ever possible for us? Was there ever a time, ever a... moment?

author: robert baratheon
content: No. Does that make you feel better or worse?

author: cersei lannister
content: It doesn't make me feel anything.

author: mhaegen
content: She looks like him, don't she, my Lord? She has his nose, his black hair.

author: mhaegen
content: Tell him when you see him, my Lord. If it please you... Tell him how beautiful she is.

author: eddard stark
content: I will.

author: mhaegen
content: And tell him I've been with no one else. I swear it, my Lord, by the old gods and new. I don't want no jewels or nothing, just him. The King was always good to me.

author: eddard stark
content: When Jon Arryn came to visit you, what did he want?

author: mhaegen
content: He wasn't that sort of man, my Lord. He just wanted to know if the child was happy, healthy.

author: eddard stark
content: She looks healthy enough to me. The girl shall want for nothing.

author: petyr baelish
content: Brothels make a much better investment than ship, I've found. Whores rarely sink.

author: eddard stark
content: What do you know of King Robert's bastards?

author: petyr baelish
content: Well, he has more than you, for a start.

author: eddard stark
content: How many?

author: petyr baelish
content: Does it matter? If you fuck enough women, some of them will give you presents.

author: eddard stark
content: And Jon Arryn tracked them all down. Why?

author: petyr baelish
content: He was the King's Hand. Perhaps Robert wanted them looked after. He was overcome with fatherly love.

author: eddard stark
content: Come.

author: eddard stark
content: Jory!

author: jory cassel
content: My Lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: Such a small pack of wolves.

author: jory cassel
content: Stay back, Ser! This is the Hand of the King!

author: jaime lannister
content: Was!... the Hand of the King. Now I'm not sure what he is... Lord of somewhere very far away.

author: petyr baelish
content: What's the meaning of this, Lannister?

author: jaime lannister
content: Get back inside where it's safe. I'm looking for my brother. You remember my brother, don't you, Lord Stark? Blond hair, sharp tongue, short man.

author: eddard stark
content: I remember him well.

author: jaime lannister
content: It seems he had some trouble on the road. You wouldn't know what happened to him, would you?

author: eddard stark
content: He was taken at my command to answer for his crimes.

author: petyr baelish
content: My Lords! I'll bring the City Watch!

author: jaime lannister
content: Come, Stark. I'd rather you die sword in hand.

author: jory cassel
content: If you threaten my Lord again...

author: jaime lannister
content: Threaten? As in, "I'm going to open your Lord from balls to brains and see what Starks are made of”?

author: eddard stark
content: You kill me, your brother's a dead man.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're right. Take him alive! Kill his men!

author: jaime lannister
content: My brother, Lord Stark... We want him back.

author: eddard stark
content: Your pardon, your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you know what your wife has done?

author: eddard stark
content: She did nothing I did not command.

author: robert baratheon
content: Who'd have thought she had it in her?

author: cersei lannister
content: By what right dare you lay hands on my blood?

author: eddard stark
content: I am the King's Hand -

author: cersei lannister
content: You were the King's Hand!

author: eddard stark
content: trying to keep the peace -

author: cersei lannister
content: You shall now be held accountable.

author: robert baratheon
content: Oh, will both of you shut your mouths? Catelyn will release Tyrion and you'll make your peace with Jaime.

author: eddard stark
content: He butchered my men.

author: cersei lannister
content: Lord Stark was returning drunk from a brothel when his men attacked Jaime.

author: robert baratheon
content: Quiet, woman.

author: eddard stark
content: Jaime has fled the city. Give me leave to bring him back to justice.

author: cersei lannister
content: I took you for a king.

author: robert baratheon
content: Hold your tongue.

author: cersei lannister
content: He's attacked my brother and abducted the other. I should wear the armor and you the gown.

author: cersei lannister
content: I shall wear this like a badge of honor.

author: robert baratheon
content: Wear it in silence or I'll honor you again.

author: robert baratheon
content: See what she does to me? My loving wife. I should not have hit her. That was not… That was not kingly.

author: eddard stark
content: If we don't act… there will be a war.

author: robert baratheon
content: So tell your wife to return that little shit of an Imp to King's Landing. She's had her fun, now put an end to it. You hear me? Send a raven and put an end to it.

author: eddard stark
content: And what about Jaime Lannister? What about Jaime?

author: robert baratheon
content: I'm half a kingdom in debt to his bloody father. I don't know what happened between you and those yellow-haired shits. I don't want to know. This is what matters - I can't rule the kingdoms if the Starks and the Lannisters are at each other's throats, so enough!

author: eddard stark
content: As you command your Grace. With your leave, I will return to Winterfell and set matters straight.

author: robert baratheon
content: Piss on that! Send a raven. I want you to stay. I'm the king, I get what I want… I never loved my brothers. A sad thing for a man to admit, but it's true. You were the brother I chose. We'll talk when I return from the hunt.

author: eddard stark
content: The hunt?

author: robert baratheon
content: Killing things clears my head. You'll have to sit on the throne while I'm away. You'll hate it more than I do.

author: eddard stark
content: The Targaryen girl -

author: robert baratheon
content: Seven hells! Don't start with her again! The girl will die and I'll hear no more of it. Put on the badge. And if you ever take it off again, I swear to the Mother I'll pin the damn thing on Jaime Lannister.

author: irri
content: Khaleesi?

author: irri
content: Oh, Khaleesi!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You're hurt.

author: robb stark
content: Not too fast.

author: bran stark
content: Come on, Dancer.

author: theon greyjoy
content: When are you gonna tell him?

author: robb stark
content: Not now.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Blood for blood. You need to make the Lannisters to pay for Jory and the others.

author: robb stark
content: You're talking about war.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm talking about justice.

author: robb stark
content: Only the Lord of Winterfell can call in the bannermen and raise an army.

author: theon greyjoy
content: A Lannister put his spear through your father's leg. The Kingslayer rides to Casterly Rock where no one can touch -

author: robb stark
content: You want me to march on Casterly Rock?!

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're not a boy anymore. They attacked your father. They've already started the war. It's your duty to represent your House when your father can't.

author: robb stark
content: And it's not your duty, because it's not your House.

author: robb stark
content: Where's Bran?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I don't know. It's not my House.

author: bran stark
content: Robb?

author: osha
content: All alone in the deep dark woods.

author: bran stark
content: I'm not alone, my brother is with me.

author: wildling
content: I don't see him. Got him hidden under your cloak?

author: osha
content: Oh, that's a pretty pin. Silver.

author: wildling
content: We'll take the pin. And the horse. Get down… Be quick about it.

author: bran stark
content: I can't. The saddle, the straps.

author: wildling
content: What's wrong with you? You some kind of cripple?

author: bran stark
content: I'm Brandon Stark of Winterfell and if you don't let me be, I'll have you all killed!

author: wildling
content: Cut his little cock off and stuff it in his mouth.

author: osha
content: the boy's worth nothing dead. Benjen Stark's own blood. Think what Mance would give us.

author: wildling
content: Piss on Mance rayder and piss on the North. We're going as far south as south goes. There ain't no white walkers down in Dorne.

author: robb stark
content: Drop the knife. Let him go and I'll let you live.

author: bran stark
content: Robb!

author: wildling
content: Shut up! Drop the blade!

author: bran stark
content: No, don't.

author: wildling
content: Do it.

author: robb stark
content: Are you all right?

author: bran stark
content: Yes, it doesn't hurt.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Tough little lad. In the Iron Islands, you're not a man until you've killed your first enemy. Well done.

author: robb stark
content: Have you lost your mind? What if you'd missed?

author: theon greyjoy
content: He would have killed you and cut Bran's throat.

author: robb stark
content: You don't have the right -

author: theon greyjoy
content: To what, to save your brother's life? It was the only thing to do, so I did it.

author: robb stark
content: What about her?

author: osha
content: Give me my life, my lord, and I'm yours.

author: robb stark
content: We'll keep her alive.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mord! Turnkey! Mord! Mord!

author: mord
content: Dwarf man making noise!

author: tyrion lannister
content: How would you like to be rich?

author: mord
content: Dwarf man still making noise.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My family is rich. We have gold, lots of gold. I'm prepared to give you lots of gold.

author: mord
content: No gold!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, I don't have it here.

author: mord
content: No gold! Fuck off.

author: arya stark
content: I don't want to practice today.

author: syrio forel
content: No?

author: arya stark
content: They killed Jory. My father is hurt. I don't care about stupid wooden swords.

author: syrio forel
content: You are troubled.

author: arya stark
content: Yes -

author: syrio forel
content: Good! Trouble is the perfect time for training. When you are dancing in the meadow with your dolls and kittens, this is not when fighting happens.

author: arya stark
content: I don't like dolls and k -

author: syrio forel
content: You're not here. You're with your trouble. If you're with your trouble when fighting happens…

author: syrio forel
content: More trouble for you. Just so… How can you be quick as a snake, or as quiet as a shadow, when you are somewhere else? You are fearing for your father, hmm? That is right. Do you pray to the gods?

author: syrio forel
content: The old and the new.

author: syrio forel
content: There is only one god. And his name is death. And there is only one thing we say to death - “Not today.”

author: viserys targaryen
content: She has to eat a whole heart? I hope that wasn't my horse.

author: jorah mormont
content: She's doing well.

author: viserys targaryen
content: She'll never keep it down.

author: viserys targaryen
content: Tell me what she is saying.

author: jorah mormont
content: The prince is riding. I have heard the thunder of the hooves. Swift as the wind he rides. His enemies will cower before him… and their wives will weep tears of blood.”

author: jorah mormont
content: She's going to have a boy.

author: viserys targaryen
content: He won't be a real Targaryen. He won't be a true dragon.

author: jorah mormont
content: The stallion who mounts the world.” The stallion, is the khal of khals. He shall unite the people into a single khalasar. All the people of the world will be his herd.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: A prince rides inside me! And he shall be called Rhaego!

author: viserys targaryen
content: They love her.

author: jorah mormont
content: She truly is a queen today.

author: jorah mormont
content: Don't let them see you carrying a sword in Vaes Dothrak. You know the law.

author: viserys targaryen
content: It's not my law.

author: jorah mormont
content: They don't belong to you.

author: viserys targaryen
content: Whatever is hers is also mine.

author: jorah mormont
content: Once, perhaps.

author: viserys targaryen
content: If I sell one egg, I'll have enough to buy a ship. Two eggs - a ship and an army.

author: jorah mormont
content: And you have all three.

author: viserys targaryen
content: I need a large army… I'm the last hope of a dynasty, Mormont. The greatest dynasty this world has ever seen, on my shoulders since I was five years old and no one has ever given me what they gave to her in that tent. Never. Not a piece of it… How can I carry what I need to carry without it? Hmm? Who can rule without wealth, or fear, or love? Oh, you stand there, all nobility and honor. You don't think I see you looking at my little sister, hmm? Don't think I know what you want? I don't care. You can have her. She can be queen of the savages and dine on the finest bloody horseparts, and you can dine on whichever parts of her you like. But let me go.

author: jorah mormont
content: You can go, but you can't have the eggs.

author: viserys targaryen
content: You swore an oath to me. Does loyalty mean nothing to you?

author: jorah mormont
content: It means everything to me.

author: viserys targaryen
content: And yet here you stand?

author: jorah mormont
content: And here I stand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mord! Mord! Mord! Mord! Mord!

author: mord
content: Noise again!

author: tyrion lannister
content: About the gold -

author: tyrion lannister
content: Listen to me! Listen to me! Sometimes possession… is an abstract concept. When they captured me they took my purse, but the gold is still mine.

author: mord
content: Where?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where? I don't know where, but when they free me -

author: mord
content: You want free? Go be free.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Have you ever heard the phrase “Rich as a Lannister”? Of course you have. You're a smart man. You know who the Lannisters are. I am a Lannister. Tyrion, son of Tywin! And of course, you have also heard the phrase, “a Lannister always pays his debts.” If you deliver a message from me to Lady Arryn, I will be in your debt. I will owe you gold. If you deliver the message and I live, which I very much intend to do.

author: mord
content: What message?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Tell her I wish to confess my crimes.

author: lysa arryn
content: You wish to confess your crimes?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, my lady. I do, my lady.

author: lysa arryn
content: Skycells always break them. Speak, Imp. Meet your gods as an honest man.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where do I begin, my lords and ladies? I'm a vile man, I confess it. My crimes and sins are beyond counting. I have lied and cheated, gambled and whored. I'm not particularly good at violence, but I'm good at convincing others to do violence for me. You want specifics, I suppose. When I was seven, I saw a servant girl bathing in the river. I stole her robe. She was forced to return to the castle, naked and in tears. I close my eyes, I can still see her tits bouncing. When I was ten, I stuffed my uncle's boots with goatshit. When confronted with my crime, I blamed a squire. Poor boy was flogged and… I escaped justice. When I was twelve, I milked my eel into a pot of turtle stew. I flogged the one-eyed snake. I skinned my sausage. I made the bald man cry into the turtle stew, which I do believe my sister ate. At least I hope she did. I once brought a jackass and a honeycomb into a brothel -

author: lysa arryn
content: Silence!

author: robin arryn
content: What happened next?!

author: lysa arryn
content: What do you think you're doing?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Confessing my crimes.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord Tyrion, you are accused of hiring a man to slay my son Bran in his bed, and of conspiring to murder my sister's husband; Lord Jon Arryn, the Hand of the King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, I'm very sorry. I don't know anything about all that.

author: lysa arryn
content: You've had your little joke. I trust you enjoyed it. Mord, take him back to the dungeon. But this time find a smaller cell, with a steeper floor.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Is this how justice is done in the Vale? you accuse me of crimes, I deny them, so you throw me in a cell to freeze and starve? Where is the King's Justice? I'm accused and demand a trial.

author: lysa arryn
content: If you're tried and found guilty, then by the king's own laws you will pay with your life.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I understand the law.

author: lysa arryn
content: We have no executioner in the Eyrie. Life is more elegant here. Open the Moon Door.

author: lysa arryn
content: You want a trial, my Lord Lannister. Very well. My son will listen to whatever you have to say, and you will hear his judgement. Then you will leave, by one door or the other.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No need to bother Lord Robin. I demand a trial by combat.

author: lysa arryn
content: You have that right.

author: knight
content: My lady, I beg the honor. Let me be your champion.

author: knight
content: The honor should be mine. For the love I bore your lord husband let me avenge his death.

author: knight
content: I'll fight for you, my Lady.

author: knight
content: It'll be my honor.

author: knight
content: The honor should be mine.

author: robin arryn
content: Make the bad man fly!

author: lysa arryn
content: Ser Vardis… You're quiet. Did you want to avenge my husband?

author: ser vardis
content: With all my heart, my Lady. But the Imp is half my size. It would be shameful to slaughter such a man and call it justice.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Agreed.

author: lysa arryn
content: You demanded a trial by combat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Now I demand a champion. I have that right, same as you.

author: ser vardis
content: My Lady, I would gladly fight the Imp's champion for you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wouldn't be too glad, ser. I name my brother, Jaime Lannister.

author: lysa arryn
content: The Kingslayer is hundreds of miles from here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Send a raven for him, I'm happy to wait.

author: lysa arryn
content: The trial will be today.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do I have a volunteer?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Anyone?... Anyone?

author: lysa arryn
content: I think that we can assume that no one is willing -

author: bronn
content: I'll stand for the dwarf.

author: lancel lannister
content: More wine, your Grace?

author: robert baratheon
content: Oh, what was I saying?

author: renly baratheon
content: A simpler time.

author: robert baratheon
content: It was! It was. You're too young to remember. Wasn't it, Selmy?

author: barriston
content: It was, your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: The enemy was right there in the open, vicious as you like, all but sending you a bloody invitation. Nothing like today.

author: renly baratheon
content: Sounds exhilarating.

author: robert baratheon
content: Exhilarating, yes. Not as exhilarating as those balls and masquerades you like to throw. You ever fucked a Riverlands girl?

author: renly baratheon
content: Once, I think.

author: robert baratheon
content: You think? I think you'd remember. Back in our day, you weren't a real man until you fucked a girl from each of the Seven Kingdoms and the Riverlands. We called it “making the eight.”

author: renly baratheon
content: Those were some lucky girls.

author: robert baratheon
content: You ever make the eight, Barristan?

author: barristan selmy
content: I don't believe so, your Grace.

author: robert baratheon
content: Those were the days!

author: renly baratheon
content: What days were those? The ones where half of Westeros fought the other half and millions died? Or before that, when the Mad King slaughtered women and babies because the voices in his head told him they deserved it? Or way before that when dragons burned whole cities to the ground?

author: robert baratheon
content: Easy, boy. You might be my brother, but you're speaking to the King.

author: renly baratheon
content: I suppose it was all rather heroic. If you were drunk enough and had some poor Riverlands whore to shove your price inside and “make the eight.”

author: man
content: They burned most everything in the Riverlands, our fields, our granaries, our homes. They took our women and then they took ‘em again. When they was done, they butchered them as if they was animals. They covered our children in pitch and lit them on fire.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Brigands, most likely.

author: man
content: They weren't thieves, they didn't steal nothing. They even left something behind, your Grace.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: It's the King's Hand you're addressing, not the king. The king is hunting.

author: petyr baelish
content: Fish. The sigil of House Tully. Isn't that your wife's House - Tully - my Lord Hand?

author: eddard stark
content: These men, were they flying a sigil? … A banner.

author: man
content: None, your… Hand. The one who was leading them… Taller by a foot than any man I've ever met, saw him cut the blacksmith, saw him take the head off a horse with a single swing of his sword.

author: petyr baelish
content: That sounds like someone we know. The Mountain.

author: eddard stark
content: You're describing Ser Gregor Clegane.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Why should Ser Gregor turn brigand? The man is an anointed knight.

author: petyr baelish
content: I've heard him called “Tywin Lannister's mad dog.” I'm sure you have as well. Can you think of any reason the Lannisters might possibly have for being angry with your wife?

author: grand maester pycelle
content: If the Lannisters were to order attacks on villages under the king's protection, it would be -

author: petyr baelish
content: It would be almost as brazen as attacking the Hand of the King in the streets of the capital.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Wel…

author: eddard stark
content: I cannot give you back your homes or restore your dead to life. But perhaps I can give you justice in the name of our king, Robert. Lord Beric Dondarrion.

author: eddard stark
content: You shall have the command. Assemble 100 men and ride to Ser Gregor's keep.

author: beric dondarrion
content: As you command.

author: eddard stark
content: In the name of Robert of the House Baratheon, the First of his Name, King of the Andals and the First Men, Lord of the Seven Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm, I charge you to bring the king's justice to the false knight Gregor Clegane and all those who shared in his crimes. I denounce him and attaint him. I strip him of all ranks and titles of all lands and holdings, and sentence him to death.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: My lord… This… This is a drastic action. It would be better to wait for King Robert's return.

author: eddard stark
content: Grand Maester Pycelle.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: My Lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Send a raven to Casterly Rock. Inform Tywin Lannister that he has been summoned to court to answer for the crimes of his bannermen. He will arrive within the fortnight, or be branded an enemy of the crown and a traitor to the realm.

author: petyr baelish
content: A bold move, my Lord, and admirable. But is it wise to yank the lion's tail? Tywin Lannister is the richest man in all the Seven Kingdoms. Gold wins wars, not soldiers.

author: eddard stark
content: Then how come Robert is king and not Tywin Lannister?

author: robin arryn
content: Is it over?

author: lysa arryn
content: You don't fight with honor!

author: bronn
content: No. He did.

author: robin arryn
content: Can I make the little man fly now?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not this little man. This little man is going home. I believe you have something of mine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A Lannister always pays his debts.

author: mordane
content: You wear your hair like a real southern lady now.

author: sansa stark
content: Well, why shouldn't I? We're in the south.

author: mordane
content: It's important to remember where you come from. I'm not sure your mother would like these new styles.

author: sansa stark
content: My mother isn't from the North.

author: mordane
content: I'm aware of that.

author: sansa stark
content: Why do you care? Do you even have hair under there?

author: mordane
content: Yes. I have hair.

author: sansa stark
content: I've never seen it.

author: mordane
content: Would you like to?

author: sansa stark
content: No. Where are you from anyway, the north or the south?

author: mordane
content: I come from a very small village in -

author: sansa stark
content: Oh, wait. I just realized… I don't care.

author: mordane
content: Sansa -

author: sansa stark
content: Septa.

author: mordane
content: Now you are being rude.

author: mordane
content: My prince.

author: sansa stark
content: My prince.

author: joffrey lannister
content: My lady. I fear I have behaved monstrously the past few weeks. With your permission?

author: sansa stark
content: It's beautiful. Like the one your mother wears.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You'll be queen one day, it's only fitting that you should look the part. Will you forgive me for my rudeness?

author: sansa stark
content: There's nothing to forgive.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You're my lady. One day we'll be married in the throne room. Lords and ladies from all over the Seven Kingdoms will come, from the last hearth in the North, to the salt shore of the south. And you will be queen over all of them. I'll never disrespect you again. I'll never be cruel to you again. Do you understand me? You're my lady now, from this day, until my last day.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Stop! Stop! What are you doing?!

author: ros
content: Going to King's Landing.

author: theon greyjoy
content: In a turnip cart?

author: ros
content: I'll find a ship heading south in White Harbor.

author: theon greyjoy
content: And you can afford that?

author: ros
content: Some of my friends are more generous than others.

author: theon greyjoy
content: There's a thousand girls like you in King's Landing.

author: ros
content: I'll have lots of company…

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes, you'll be very popular until some fat lord comes to visit with a big belly and a little prick and he can't get it up so he knocks all your teeth out.

author: ros
content: And what will happen to me if I stay here? Will I become Lady Greyjoy, Mistress of the Iron Islands?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Don't be a fool.

author: ros
content: I hear Jaime Lannister attacked Lord Stark in the streets of King's Landing. Every man for a hundred miles will be marching off to war soon and most of them will never come back, there's nothing more for me here. Let's go, Steffon.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Let me see it one more time?

author: ros
content: See what?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm going to miss you!

author: ros
content: I know.

author: eddard stark
content: I'm sending you both back to Winterfell.

author: sansa stark
content: What?!

author: eddard stark
content: Listen -

author: sansa stark
content: What about Joffrey?

author: arya stark
content: Are you dying because of your leg? Is that why you're sending us home?

author: eddard stark
content: What? No.

author: sansa stark

author: arya stark

author: eddard stark
content: This isn't a punishment. I want you back in Winterfell for your own safety.

content: Who cares about your stupid dancing teacher? I can't go. I'm supposed to marry Prince Joffrey. I love him and I'm meant to be his queen and have his babies.

author: arya stark
content: Seven hells.

author: eddard stark
content: When you're old enough, I'll make you a match with someone who's worthy of you, someone who's brave and gentle and strong -

author: sansa stark
content: I don't want someone brave and gentle and strong. I want him! He'll be the greatest king that ever was, a golden lion, and I'll give him sons with beautiful blond hair.

author: arya stark
content: The lion's not his sigil, idiot. He's a stag, like his father.

author: sansa stark
content: He is not. He's nothing like that old drunk king.

author: eddard stark
content: Go on, girls. Get your septa and start packing your things.

author: sansa stark
content: Wait!

author: arya stark
content: Come on!

author: sansa stark
content: It's not fair!

author: eddard stark
content: Lord Orys Baratheon, black of hair.” “Axel Baratheon, black of hair.” “Lyonel Baratheon, black of hair.” “Steffon Baratheon, black of hair.” “Robert Baratheon, black of hair.” “Joffrey Baratheon… golden-haired.”

author: viserys targaryen
content: Daenerys! Where's my sister?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Stop him.

content: Keep away from me!

content: Viserys, please.

content: What's he saying?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He says yes. You shall have a golden crown, that men shall tremble to behold.

author: viserys targaryen
content: That was all I wanted. W-what was promised.

author: viserys targaryen
content: No! You cannot touch me! I am the dragon! I am the dragon! I want my crown! Ahh!

author: jorah mormont
content: Look away Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: viserys targaryen
content: No. Dany! Dany, tell them, make them! You can't!

author: viserys targaryen
content: Dany please!

author: khal drogo
content: A crown for a king.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi…

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He was no dragon. Fire cannot kill a dragon.

content: Summoned to court to answer for the crimes of your bannerman Gregor Clegane, the Mountain

author: tywin lannister
content: Attacking him was stupid.

author: tywin lannister
content: Lannisters don't act like fools.

content: Catelyn Stark took my brother.

content: Why is he still alive?

content: Tyrion?

author: tywin lannister
content: Ned Stark.

content: It wouldn't have been clean.

author: tywin lannister
content: Clean...

content: You spend too much time worrying about what other people think of you.

author: jaime lannister

author: tywin lannister
content: Now that's what you want people to think of you.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's the truth.

author: tywin lannister
content: When you hear them whispering "Kingslayer" behind your back, doesn't it bother you?

author: jaime lannister
content: Of course it bothers me.

author: tywin lannister
content: The lion doesn't concern himself with the opinions of the sheep.

author: jaime lannister
content: I didn't realize you placed such a high value on my brother's life.

author: tywin lannister
content: He's a Lannister. He might be the lowest of the Lannisters, but he's one of us.

author: jaime lannister
content: So the lion does concern himself with the opinions of..

author: tywin lannister
content: No, it's not an opinion, it's a fact!

author: tywin lannister
content: Hmm.

content: You're in pain.

content: I've had worse, my lady.

author: cersei lannister
content: Perhaps it's time to go home.

author: eddard stark
content: The South doesn't seem to agree with you.

author: eddard stark
content: I know the truth Jon Arryn died for.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you, Lord Stark? Is that why you called me here, to pose me riddles?

author: eddard stark
content: Has he done this before?

author: cersei lannister
content: Jaime would have killed him.

author: cersei lannister
content: My brother is worth a thousand of your friend.

author: eddard stark
content: Your brother Or your lover?

author: cersei lannister
content: The Targaryens wed brothers and sisters for 300 years to keep bloodlines pure.

author: cersei lannister
content: Jaime and I are more than brother and sister. We shared a womb. We came into this world together. We belong together.

author: eddard stark
content: My son saw you with him.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you love your children?

author: eddard stark
content: With all my heart.

author: cersei lannister
content: No more than I love mine.

author: eddard stark
content: And they are all Jaime's.

author: cersei lannister
content: Thank the Gods.

author: eddard stark
content: You've always hated him.

author: cersei lannister
content: Hated him? I worshiped him.

author: eddard stark
content: When the King returns from his hunt, I'll tell him the truth.

author: cersei lannister
content: And what of my wrath, Lord Stark? You should have taken the realm for yourself.

author: eddard stark
content: I've made many mistakes in my life, but that wasn't one of them.

author: cersei lannister
content: Oh, but it was.

author: ros
content: Come here.

author: petyr baelish
content: No no no no! Is that what they teach you up in the North? And you-- wherever you're from, do you have any idea how ridiculous you sound? Either of you understand a thing that I'm saying?

author: ros
content: Yes, My Lord.

author: petyr baelish
content: Let's start over, shall we? You be the man and you be the woman.

author: ros
content: Why don't you join us, My Lord?

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm saving myself for another.

author: ros
content: What she doesn't know won't hurt her.

author: petyr baelish
content: A stupid saying.

author: ros
content: She must be very beautiful.

author: petyr baelish
content: No, not really. Impeccable bloodlines though.

author: ros
content: I do believe my lordo s in love.

author: petyr baelish
content: For many years. Most of my life really.

author: ros
content: Is she still married to him?

author: petyr baelish
content: Oh no. He got himself killed before the wedding.

author: ros
content: And what do you want?

author: petyr baelish
content: Oh, everything, my dear. Everything there is.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're a very lucky girl. Do you know that?

author: osha
content: Where is it you come from?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The Iron Islands.

author: osha
content: They far away?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You've never heard of the Iron Islands?

author: osha
content: Trust me, you've never heard where I'm from neither.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Trust me, My Lord. You're not living in the wilderness anymore.

author: osha
content: And what's that?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Lord.

author: osha
content: Why?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Why? What do you mean why? My father is Balon Greyjoy, Lord of the Iron Islands.

author: osha
content: What's that got to do with you? If your father's lord, how can you be lord too?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I will be lord after my father.

author: osha
content: So you're not lord now?

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, you...You having a go at me? Is that it?

author: osha
content: I just don't understand how you Southerners do things.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm not a Southerner.

author: osha
content: You're from South of the wall. That makes you a Southerner to me.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're an impudent little wench, aren't you?

author: osha
content: Couldn't say, My Lord. Don't know what "impunent" means.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Impudent. It means rude. Disrespectful.

author: maester luwin
content: Theon Greyjoy! The lady is our guest.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I thought she was our prisoner.

author: maester luwin
content: Are the two mutually exclusive in your experience?

author: maester luwin
content: Chances are I won't be nearby the next time that happens.

author: osha
content: I'm used to worse than him.

author: osha
content: I'm used to men who could chew that boy up and pick their teeth with his bones.

author: maester luwin
content: Why did you come here?

author: osha
content: Didn't mean to come here. Meant to get much further South than this.

author: maester luwin
content: Why? What are you afraid of?

author: osha
content: There's things that sleep in the day and hunt at night.

author: maester luwin
content: Owls and Shadowcats and...

author: osha
content: I'm not talking about Owls and Shadowcats.

author: maester luwin
content: The "things" you speak of-- they've been gone for thousands of years.

author: osha
content: They wasn't gone, old man. They was sleeping.

author: sam tarly
content: I miss girls.

author: jon snow
content: Why is he alone?

author: sam tarly
content: One blast for a Ranger returning, two for Wildlings, three for...

author: jon snow
content: There's no rider.

author: night watch stable boy
content: Whoa, boy, whoa.

author: jon snow
content: That's my Uncle Benjen's horse.

author: renly baratheon
content: Ned! It's Robert.

author: robert baratheon
content: I should have spent more time with you, shown you how to be a man.

author: robert baratheon
content: My fault. Too much wine, missed my thrust.

author: cersei lannister
content: Robert, my sweet...

author: robert baratheon
content: Out, all of you!

author: eddard stark
content: You damned fool.

author: robert baratheon
content: Paper and ink on the table, write down what I say.

author: robert baratheon
content: Give it to the council after I'm dead.

author: eddard stark
content: I will.

author: robert baratheon
content: And my son Help him, Ned. Make him better than me.

author: eddard stark
content: I'll, I'll do everything I can to honor your memory.

author: robert baratheon
content: My memory.

author: eddard stark
content: Give him milk of the poppy.

author: barristan selmy
content: He was reeling from the wine.

author: eddard stark
content: No man could have protected him from himself.

author: lord varys
content: I wonder, Ser Barristan, who gave the king this wine?

author: barristan selmy
content: His squire, from the king's own skin.

author: eddard stark
content: His squire? The Lannister boy?

author: lord varys
content: Such a dutiful boy to make sure his Grace did not lack refreshment.

author: eddard stark
content: His Grace has had a change of heart concerning Daenerys Targaryen.

author: lord varys
content: I'm afraid those birds have flown.

author: khal drogo
content: The stallion who mounts the world, has no need for iron chairs.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: According to the prophecy, the stallions will ride to the ends of the world.

author: khal drogo
content: The earth ends at the black salt sea. No horse can cross the poison water.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The earth does not end at the sea, there are many dirts beyond the sea.

author: khal drogo
content: Not dirt. Lands.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Lands, yes...

author: khal drogo
content: Let's speak no more of wooden horses and iron chairs.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's not a chair. It's a...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: A chair for a King to sit upon, or a Queen.

author: khal drogo
content: A King does not need a chair to sit upon. He only needs a horse.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Can't you help me make him understand?

author: jorah mormont
content: The Dothraki do things in their own time, for their own reasons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My brother was a fool, I know, but he was the rightful heir to the Seven Kingdoms.

author: jorah mormont
content: Forgive me, Khaleesi, but your ancestor Aegon the Conqueror didn't seize six of the kingdoms because they were his right.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And because he had dragons.

author: jorah mormont
content: Ah well, having a few dragons makes things easier.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You don't believe it.

author: jorah mormont
content: Have you ever seen a dragon, Khaleesi? I believe what my eyes and ears report.

author: deanerys targarian
content: Well, I'll come with you.

author: jorah mormont
content: No no, don't trouble yourself. Enjoy the market. I'll rejoin you soon enough.

content: Psst, Jorah the Andal.

content: Virzetha gizikhven! Mra qora! Mra qora!

content: My son already has his name, but I'll try your summerwine.

author: doreah
content: You have the honor of addressing Daenerys of the House Targaryen.

content: Princess.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Rise. I'd still like to taste that wine.

content: You honor me, Ser.

author: rakharo
content: Huh-uh, huh-uh.

content: You know there are many in your homeland that pray for your return, princess.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I hope to repay your kindness someday.

author: jorah mormont
content: Rakharo.

author: rakharo
content: Huh.

content: Is something wrong?

content: I have a thirst. Open it.

content: Open it.

content: Pour.

content: It would be a crime to drink a wine this rich without at least giving it time to breathe.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do as he says.

author: wine merchant

content: Me? I'm afraid I am not worthy of the vintage.

author: daenerys targaryen

content: Khaleesi! Stop him!

content: Here you begin anew.

content: I do, my lord.

content: You'll want to take your vow before a heart tree as your Uncle did.

content: Yes, my lord.

content: Stannis is your older brother.

author: renly baratheon
content: This isn't about the bloody line of succession.

author: eddard stark
content: Stannis is a commander. He's led men into war twice.

author: renly baratheon
content: Yes, he's a good soldier. Everyone knows that. So was Robert.

author: tell me something
content: Do you still believe good soldiers make good kings?

author: eddard stark
content: I will not dishonor Robert's last hours by shedding blood in his halls and dragging frightened children from their beds.

author: eddard stark
content: You will sail to dragonstone tonight.

author: tomard
content: Yes, My Lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Now leave us.

author: petyr baelish
content: My Lord protector.

author: eddard stark
content: The King has no true born sons.

author: petyr baelish
content: So when the King dies...

author: eddard stark
content: The throne passes to his brother Lord Stannis.

author: petyr baelish
content: So it would seem. Unless...

author: eddard stark
content: There is no "unless".

author: petyr baelish
content: And he cannot take the throne without your help.

author: eddard stark
content: Do you have a shred of honor?

author: petyr baelish
content: You are now Hand of the King and Protector of the Realm.

author: eddard stark
content: We?

author: petyr baelish
content: You'll need someone to share these burdens. I assure you, my price would be modest.

author: eddard stark
content: What you suggest is treason.

author: petyr baelish
content: Only if we lose.

author: eddard stark
content: Make peace with the Lannisters, you say. With the people who tried to murder my boy..

author: eddard stark
content: No. I won't do it.

author: petyr baelish
content: So it will be Stannis and war?

author: eddard stark
content: There is no other choice. He is the heir.

author: petyr baelish
content: So why did you call me here? Not for my wisdom, clearly.

author: eddard stark
content: You promised Catelyn you would help me.

author: petyr baelish
content: Look at you. You know what you want me to do.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I thought he'd leave me alone, now that my brother is gone.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He will not have my son.

author: khal drogo
content: Moon of my life. Are you hurt?

author: khal drogo
content: Jorah the Andal, I heard what you did.

author: king joffrey
content: Liar!

author: cersei lannister
content: You condemn yourself with your own mouth, Lord Stark.

author: eddard stark
content: Ser Barristan is a good man, a loyal man. Do him no harm.

author: cersei lannister
content: You think he stands alone?

author: king joffrey
content: Kill him! Kill all of them, I command it!

author: eddard stark
content: Commander! Take the Queen and her children into custody.

author: janos slynt
content: Men of the Watch!

author: eddard stark
content: I want no bloodshed.

author: petyr baelish
content: Now!

author: petyr baelish
content: I did warn you not to trust me.

author: syrio forel
content: Yah! Left high, left low.

author: syrio forel
content: Right low, lunge right.

author: steward of house stark
content: If you break anything, the Septa will have my head. What is...

author: septa mordane
content: Your sister knew perfectly well we were to leave today.

author: sansa stark
content: She didn't forget. She's with her dancing master.

author: septa mordane
content: Hush! Go back to your room.

author: sansa stark
content: What is it? What's happening?

author: septa mordane
content: Do as I told you. Run!

author: syrio forel
content: This way! Left, right.

author: arya stark
content: You said right, but you went left.

author: syrio forel
content: And now you are a dead girl.

author: arya stark
content: Only 'cause you lied.

author: syrio forel
content: My tongue lied.

author: arya stark
content: I was so. I watched, but you...

author: syrio forel
content: Watching is not seeing, dead girl.

author: meryn trant
content: Arya Stark, come with us.

author: syrio forel
content: And why is it that Lord Eddard is sending Lannister men in place of his own? I am wondering.

author: meryn trant
content: Mind your place, dancing master.

author: arya stark
content: My father wouldn't send you.

author: arya stark
content: And I don't have to go with you if I don't want.

author: maryn trant
content: Take her.

author: syrio forel
content: Are you men or snakes, that you would threaten a child?

author: kings guard
content: Get out of my way, little man.

author: syrio forel
content: I am Syrio Forel.

author: kings guard
content: Foreign bastard.

author: syrio forel
content: And you will be speaking to me with more respect.

author: meryn trant
content: Kill the Braavosi. Bring the girl.

author: syrio forel
content: Arya child, we are done with dancing for the day.

author: meryn trant
content: Bloody oafs.

author: syrio forel
content: Be gone now, Arya.

author: arya stark
content: Come with me. Run.

author: syrio forel
content: The first sword of Braavos does not run.

author: syrio forel
content: What do we say to the God of death?

author: arya stark
content: Not today.

author: syrio forel
content: Go.

author: arya stark
content: Not today. Not today.

author: sansa stark
content: Stay away from me.

author: sandor clegane
content: Who do you think sent me?

author: arya stark
content: Needle.

author: stable boy
content: There she is.

author: arya stark
content: What do you want?

author: stable boy
content: I want you, wolf girl. Come here.

author: arya stark
content: Leave me be. My father's a lord. He'll reward you.

author: stable boy
content: She'll reward me, the Queen!

author: arya stark
content: Stay away!

author: lord varys
content: Lord Stark, you must be thirsty.

author: eddard stark
content: Varys.

author: lord varys
content: I promise you it isn't poisoned.

author: eddard stark
content: What about my daughters?

author: lord varys
content: The younger one seems to have escaped the castle.

author: eddard stark
content: And Sansa?

author: lord varys
content: Still engaged to Joffrey.

author: eddard stark
content: You watched my men being slaughtered and did nothing.

author: lord varys
content: And would again, My Lord.

author: eddard stark
content: The madness of mercy. That she might save her children.

author: lord varys
content: Ah, the children. It is always the innocents who suffer.

author: eddard stark
content: The Queen can't kill me. Cat holds her brother.

author: lord varys
content: The wrong brother sadly.

author: eddard stark
content: If that's true, then slit my throat and be done with it.

author: lord varys
content: Not today, My Lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Tell me something, Varys.

author: lord varys
content: The Realm, My Lord.

author: jeor mormont
content: It's Othor, without a doubt.

author: othell yarwyck
content: The other one is Jafer Flowers, My Lord, less the hand the wolf tore off.

author: jeor mormont
content: Any sign of Benjen or the rest of his party?

author: jon snow
content: Just these two, My Lord. Been dead awhile, I'd say.

author: jeor mormont
content: Mmm.

author: sam tarly
content: The smell.

author: othell yarwyck
content: What smell?

author: sam tarly
content: There is none.

author: jon snow
content: We should burn them.

author: othell yarwyck
content: Snow's not wrong, My Lord.

author: jeor mormont
content: I want Maester Aemon to examine them first.

author: othell yarwyck
content: You heard him.

author: ser alliser
content: Lord Commander, Maester Aemon awaits you in his chambers. A raven from King's Landing.

author: nights watch brother
content: Come on, move 'em out.

author: jeor mormont
content: Bring me a horn of ale, Snow, and pour one for yourself.

author: jon snow
content: Is there any word of my father?

author: jeor mormont
content: Sit.

author: jeor mormont
content: I hope you're not thinking of doing anything stupid.

author: jon snow
content: My sisters were in King's Landing too.

author: jeor mormont
content: I'm sure they'll be treated gently.

author: lord varys
content: Your father has proved to be an awful traitor, dear.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: King Robert's body was still warm when Lord Eddard began plotting to steal Joffrey's rightful throne.

author: sansa stark
content: He wouldn't do that. He knows how much I love Joffrey.

author: cersei lannister
content: Sansa sweetling, you are innocent of any wrong.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: A child born of a traitor's seed is no fit consort for our King.

author: sansa stark
content: No, I'm not.

author: petyr baelish
content: The girl is innocent, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Little dove, you must write to Lady Catelyn and your brother, the eldest.

author: sansa stark
content: Robb.

author: cersei lannister
content: Word of your father's arrest will reach him soon, no doubt.

author: sansa stark
content: If...if I could see my father, talk to him about...

author: cersei lannister
content: You disappoint me, child.

author: sansa stark
content: I only meant that...what will happen to him?

author: cersei lannister
content: That depends.

author: sansa stark
content: On...on what?

author: cersei lannister
content: On your brother. And on you.

author: robb stark
content: Treason? Sansa wrote this?

author: maester luwin
content: It is your sister's hand, but the Queen's words.

author: robb stark
content: Joffrey puts my father in chains, now he wants his ass kissed?

author: maester luwin
content: This is a royal command, My Lord.

author: robb stark
content: I won't refuse. His Grace summons me to King's Landing, I'll go to King's Landing.

author: robin arryn
content: I'm hungry.

author: lysa arryn
content: Hush now, darling. You just ate.

author: catelyn stark
content: You will not support us then? Do I understand you correctly?

author: robin arryn
content: But I'm hungry!

author: lysa arryn
content: Soon, love, soon.

author: catelyn stark
content: That is what I ask.

author: lysa arryn
content: Go on, sweet. Time for your bath. I'll feed you after.

author: catelyn stark
content: If you fear for the safety of your son...

author: lysa arryn
content: Of course I fear for the safety of my son!

author: catelyn stark
content: And that is why we have to stop them.

author: lysa arryn
content: The knights of the Vale will stay in the Vale where they belong, to protect their Lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: From here it might be best if Bronn and I continue alone.

author: shagga
content: Best for Tyrion son of Tywin. Not best for me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And feed it to the goats, yes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Uncle. Father.

author: tywin lannister
content: The rumors of your demise were unfounded.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sorry to disappoint you.

author: tywin lannister
content: And who are these Companions of yours?

author: tywin lannister
content: This is Shagga Son of Dolf, Chieftain of the Stone Crows.

author: bronn
content: You wouldn't know him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: May I present My Lord Father, Tywin son of Tytos of House Lannister.

author: tywin lannister
content: You left us no choice. The honor of the House was at stake.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We have our differences, Jaime and I.

author: jaime lannister
content: He's been covering himself in glory.

author: kevan lannister
content: Jaime smashed the River Lords at the Golden Tooth, and now lays siege to Riverrun, Catelyn Stark's homeland.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And the Starks? Lord Eddard?

author: tywin lannister
content: Is our hostage.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How did my sweet sister persuade the King to imprison his dear friend Ned?

author: tywin lannister
content: Robert Baratheon is dead.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My sister rules, you mean.

author: kevan lannister
content: Stark's son has called his banners.

author: tywin lannister
content: A green boy.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Maybe. Though the boy does have a certain belligerence.

author: messenger
content: If it please My Lord, Ser Addam bids me report that the Northmen have crossed the neck.

author: tywin lannister
content: The wolf rushes into the lion's jaws.

author: kevan lannister
content: At once, My Lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: It is said that the men of the Mountain clans are great warriors.

author: shagga
content: Only if the half man fights with us.

author: rodrik cassal
content: The scouts report Lord Tywin moves north.

author: greatjon umber
content: No, we need to get around him and break Jaime Lannister's siege of Riverrun.

author: robb stark
content: To do either we need to cross the river and the only crossing is at The Twins.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Lord Frey controls that bridge.

author: catelyn stark
content: The late Lord Frey" my father calls him.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Robb's right.

author: greatjon umber
content: So what's it gonna be? Do we move against Jaime or Lord Tywin?

author: stark guard
content: Your pardon, my lords.

author: greatjon umber
content: Don't worry, lad.

author: robb stark
content: Where did you find him?

author: stark guard
content: In the brush above the encampment.

author: robb stark
content: How high did you get?

author: lannister scout
content: 20,000. Maybe more.

author: robb stark
content: My father understands mercy, when there is room for it.

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb.

author: robb stark
content: Tell Lord Tywin, Winter is coming for him.

author: lannister scout
content: Yes, My Lord. Thank you, My Lord.

author: greatjon umber
content: Are you touched, boy?! Letting him go?

author: robb stark
content: You call me boy again.

author: robb stark
content: Go on.

author: greatjon umber
content: Oi.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: It is also the wish of His Grace, that his loyal servant Janos Slynt, Commander of the City Watch...

author: sansa stark
content: Ser Aron.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Be at once raised to the rank of Lord.

author: sansa stark
content: Lord Gyles.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: And granted the ancient seat of Harrenhal, and that his sons and grandsons shall hold this honor after him, until the end of time.

author: cersei lannister
content: Ser Barristan Selmy.

author: barristan selmy
content: Your Grace, I am yours to command.

author: cersei lannister
content: Rise, Ser Barristan.

author: barristan selmy
content: Your Grace, the Kingsguard is a sworn brotherhood.

author: cersei lannister
content: Whose death, Ser Barristan? Yours or your King's?

author: king joffrey
content: You let my father die.

author: barristan selmy
content: Your Grace...

author: cersei lannister
content: The Council has determined that Ser Jaime Lannister will take your place as Lord Commander of the Kingsguard.

author: barristan selmy
content: The man who profaned his blade with the blood of the King he had sworn to defend!

author: cersei lannister
content: Careful, Ser.

author: lord varys
content: We have nothing but gratitude for your long service, good Ser.

author: barristan selmy
content: A hall to die in and men to bury me.

author: petyr baelish
content: A naked Knight, apparently.

author: barristan selmy
content: Even now I could cut through the five of you like carving a cake!

author: kings landing page
content: If any man in this hall has other matters to set before His Grace, let him speak now or go forth and hold his silence.

author: sansa stark
content: Your Grace.

author: king joffrey
content: Come forward, My Lady.

author: kings landing page
content: The Lady Sansa of House Stark.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you have some business for the King and the Council, Sansa?

author: sansa stark
content: I do.

author: sansa stark
content: As it please Your Grace, I ask mercy for my father, Lord Eddard Stark, who was Hand of the King.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Treason is a noxious weed.

author: king joffrey
content: Let her speak.

author: sansa stark
content: Thank you, Your Grace.

author: petyr baelish
content: Do you deny your father's crime?

author: sansa stark
content: No, My Lords. I know he must be punished.

author: king joffrey
content: He said I wasn't the King. Why did he say that?

author: sansa stark
content: He was badly hurt.

author: lord varys
content: A childo s faith Such sweet innocence.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Treason is treason!

author: king joffrey
content: Anything else?

author: sansa stark
content: If you still have any affection in your heart for me, please do me this kindness, Your Grace.

author: king joffrey
content: Your sweet words have moved me.

author: sansa stark
content: He will.

author: varys
content: You've seen better days, my lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Another visit? lt seems you're my last friend.

author: varys
content: No, no, many still love you. Sansa came to court this morning to plead for your life.

author: eddard stark
content: On her knees begging for me. Hm! Did you laugh with the others?

author: varys
content: You do me wrong, my lord. Your blood is the last thing l want.

author: eddard stark
content: l don't know what you want. l've given up trying to guess.

author: varys
content: When l was still a boy - before they cut my balls off with a hot knife - l traveled with a group of actors through the free cities. They taught me that each man has a role to play. The same is true at court. l am the master of whisperers. My role is to be sly, obsequious and without scruples. l'm a good actor, my lord.

author: eddard stark
content: Huh. Can you free me from this pit?

author: varys
content: l could. But will l? No. As l said, I'm no hero.

author: eddard stark
content: What do you want? Tell me. No riddles, no stories. Tell me, what do you want?

author: varys
content: Peace. Did you know that your son is marching south with an army of Northmen? Loyal lad. Fighting for his father's freedom.

author: eddard stark
content: Robb? He's just a boy.

author: varys
content: Boys have been conquerors before. But the man giving Cersei sleepless nights is the king's the late king's brother. Lord Stannis has the best claim to the throne. He is a proven battle commander and he is utterly without mercy.

author: eddard stark
content: Stannis Baratheon is Robert's true heir. The throne is his by rights.

author: varys
content: Sansa pleaded so sweetly for your life. lt would be a shame to throw it away. Cersei is no fool. She knows a tame wolf is more use to her than a dead one.

author: eddard stark
content: You want me to serve the woman who murdered my king, who butchered my men, who crippled my son?

author: varys
content: l want you to serve the realm! Tell the queen you will confess your vile treason, tell your son to lay down his sword and proclaim Joffrey as the true heir. Cersei knows you as a man of honor. lf you give her the peace she needs, and promise to carry her secret to your grave, l believe she will allow you to take the black and live out your days on the Wall with your brother and your bastard son.

author: eddard stark
content: You think my life is some precious thing to me? That l would trade my honor for a few more years of... of what? You grew up with actors. You learned their craft and you learnt it well. But l grew up with soldiers. l learned how to die a long time ago.

author: varys
content: Pity. Such a pity. What of your daughter's life, my lord? ls that a precious thing to you?

author: robb stark
content: lt's a birthday message to his grand-niece Walda.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Or so Walder Frey would have you think.

author: catelyn stark
content: Keep shooting them down. We can't risk Lord Walder sending word of your movements to the Lannisters.

author: robb stark
content: He's Grandfather's bannerman. We can't expect his support?

author: greatjon umber
content: Expect nothing of Walder Frey and you'll never be surprised. Look.

author: robb stark
content: Father rots in a dungeon. How long before they take his head? We need to cross the Trident and we need to do it now.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Just march up to his gates and tell him you're crossing. We've got five times his numbers. You can take the Twins if you have to.

author: greatjon umber
content: Not in time. Tywin Lannister marches north as we speak.

author: catelyn stark
content: The Freys have held the crossing for 600 years, and for 600 years they have never failed to exact their toll.

author: robb stark
content: Have my horse saddled and ready.

author: greatjon umber
content: Enter the Twins alone and he'll sell you to the Lannisters as he likes.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Or throw you in a dungeon. Or slit your throat.

author: robb stark
content: My father would do whatever it took to secure our crossing. Whatever it took. lf l'm going to lead this army, l can't have other men doing my bargaining for me.

author: catelyn stark
content: l agree. l'll go.

author: everyone
content: You can't!

author: catelyn stark
content: l have known Lord Walder since l was a girl. He would never harm me.

author: greatjon umber
content: Unless there was a profit in it.

author: walder frey
content: What do you want?

author: catelyn stark
content: lt is a great pleasure to see you again after so many years, my lord.

author: walder frey
content: Oh, spare me. Your boy's too proud to come before me himself. What am l supposed to do with you?

author: stevron frey
content: Father, you forget yourself. Lady Stark is –

author: walder frey
content: Who asked you? You're not Lord Frey yet, not until l die. Do l look dead to you?

author: ryger rivers
content: Father, please –

author: walder frey
content: l need lessons in courtesy from you, bastard? Your mother would still be a milkmaid if l hadn't squirted you into her belly.

author: catelyn stark
content: ls there somewhere we can talk?

author: walder frey
content: We're talking right now. Fine. Out! All of you!

author: catelyn stark
content: l'm sure she will give you many sons.

author: walder frey
content: Huh. Your father didn't come to the wedding.

author: catelyn stark
content: He is quite ill, my lord.

author: walder frey
content: Huh. Didn't come to the last one, either. Or the one before that. Your family has always pissed on me.

author: catelyn stark
content: My lord, l –

author: walder frey
content: Don't deny it. You know it's true. The fine Lord Tully would never marry any of his children to mine.

author: catelyn stark
content: l'm sure there were reasons –

author: walder frey
content: l didn't need reasons. l needed to get rid of sons and daughters. You see how they pile up? Why are you here?

author: catelyn stark
content: To ask you to open your gates, my lord, so my son and his bannermen may cross the Trident and be on their way.

author: walder frey
content: Why should l let him?

author: catelyn stark
content: lf you could climb your own battlements, you would see that he has 20,000 men outside your walls.

author: walder frey
content: There will be 20,000 corpses when Tywin Lannister gets here. Don't try and frighten me, Lady Stark. Your husbando s in a cell beneath the Red Keep and your son's got no fur to keep his balls warm.

author: catelyn stark
content: You swore an oath to my father.

author: walder frey
content: Oh, yes, l said some words. And l swore oaths to the crown too, if l remember right. Joffrey's king now, which makes your boy and his corpses-to-be nothing but rebels, it seems to me. lf l had the sense the gods gave a fish, l'd hand you both over to the Lannisters.

author: catelyn stark
content: Why don't you?

author: walder frey
content: Stark, Tully, Lannister, Baratheon. Give me one good reason why l should waste a single thought on any of you?

author: voices outside
content: And engage!

author: jeor mormont
content: When does Aemon think you'll be able to use that hand?

author: jon snow
content: Soon, he says.

author: jeor mormont
content: Good. You'll be ready for this, then. l thought a wolf was more appropriate for you than a bear so l had a new pommel made. lt's called Longclaw. Works as well for a wolf as a bear, l think.

author: jon snow
content: This is Valyrian steel.

author: jeor mormont
content: lt was my father's sword, his father before him. The Mormonts have carried it for five centuries. lt was meant for my son Jorah. He brought dishonor to our House, but he had the grace to leave the sword before he fled from Westeros.

author: jon snow
content: My lord, you honor me, but l can't –

author: jeor mormont
content: Oh, you can. And you will. l wouldn't be standing here if it wasn't for you and your beast. A bloody dead man tried to kill me, so you'll take it. l'll hear no more about it. ls that understood?

author: jon snow
content: Yes, my lord.

author: jeor mormont
content: Right. Now, don't think this means l approve of this nonsense with you and Alliser Thorne. That's a man's sword. lt'll take a man to wield it.

author: jon snow
content: l'll apologize to Ser Alliser tonight.

author: jeor mormont
content: No, you won't. l sent him to King's Landing yesterday. The hand that your wolf tore off that thing's wrist – l've ordered Thorne to lay it at the feet of this boy king. That should get young Joffrey's attention. And it, uh, puts a thousand leagues between you and Thorne. Now go and put your sword somewhere safe and bring me my supper.

author: unidentified nights watchers
content: Well done. Well done.

author: nights watcher
content: You earned that, Snow.

author: nights watcher
content: Well done.

author: pyp
content: Go on, let's have a look.

author: jon snow
content: At what?

author: grenn
content: The sword! Show us the sword.

author: all
content: Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword!

author: pyp
content: Let's have a look.

author: grenn
content: Piss off.

author: pyp
content: Come on, l want to have a look at it in the light. Give it here!

author: grenn
content: Look at its eyes.

author: jon snow
content: What is it?

author: sam tarly
content: l - l can't.

author: jon snow
content: You can't what?

author: sam tarly
content: l'm really not supposed to say.

author: jon snow
content: And yet you really want to say. You want to say that…

author: sam tarly
content: There was a raven. l read the message to Maester Aemon. lt's your brother Robb.

author: jon snow
content: What? What about him?

author: sam tarly
content: He's heading south. To war. All his bannermen have rallied to his side, they'll keep him safe.

author: jon snow
content: l should be there. l should be with him.

author: greatjon umber
content: lf we do that, they'll never get back across.

author: robb stark
content: Well? What did he say?

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord Walder has granted your crossing. His men are yours, as well.

author: robb stark
content: Huh.

author: catelyn stark
content: Less the 400 he will keep here to hold the crossing against any who would pursue you.

author: robb stark
content: What does he want in return?

author: catelyn stark
content: You will be taking on his son Olyvar as your personal squire. He expects a knighthood in good time.

author: robb stark
content: Fine, fine. And?

author: catelyn stark
content: And Arya will marry his son Waldron when they both come of age.

author: robb stark
content: She won't be happy about that. And?

author: catelyn stark
content: And when the fighting is done you will marry one of his daughters. Whichever you prefer. He has a number he thinks will be suitable.

author: robb stark
content: l see. Did you get a look at his daughters?

author: catelyn stark
content: l did.

author: robb stark
content: And?

author: catelyn stark
content: One was – Do you consent?

author: robb stark
content: Can l refuse?

author: catelyn stark
content: Not if you want to cross.

author: robb stark
content: Then l consent.

author: jon snow
content: Sam said you wanted to see me?

author: maester aemon
content: l did indeed. Perhaps you would be kind enough to assist me. Tell me, did you ever wonder why the men of the Night's Watch take no wives and father no children?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: maester aemon
content: So they will not love. Love is the death of duty. lf the day should ever come when your lord father was forced to choose between honor on the one hand and those he loves on the other, what would he do?

author: jon snow
content: He would do whatever was right, no matter what.

author: maester aemon
