content: Then Lord Stark is one man in 10,000. Most of us are not so strong. What is honor compared to a woman's love? And what is duty against the feel of a newborn son in your arms? Or a brother's smile?

author: jon snow
content: Sam told you.

author: maester aemon
content: We're all human. Oh, we all do our duty when there's no cost to it. Honor comes easy then. Yet sooner or later in every man's life there comes a day when it is not easy. A day when he must choose.

author: jon snow
content: And this is my day? ls that what you're saying?

author: maester aemon
content: Oh, it hurts, boy. Oh, yes. l know.

author: jon snow
content: You do not know. No one knows. l may be a bastard, but he is my father and Robb is my brother.

author: maester aemon
content: The gods were cruel when they saw fit to test my vows. They waited till l was old. What could l do when the ravens brought the news from the South

author: jon snow
content: Who are you?

author: maester aemon
content: My father was Maekar, the first of his name. My brother Aegon reigned after him when l had refused the throne. And he was followed by his son Aerys whom they called the Mad King.

author: jon snow
content: You're Aemon Targaryen.

author: maester aemon
content: l'm a maester of the Citadel, bound in service to Castle Black and the Night's Watch. l will not tell you to stay or go. You must make that choice yourself and live with it for the rest of your days. As l have.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My lord… My sun and stars… Drogo.

author: khal drogo
content: My horse…

author: cohollo
content: Blood of my blood…

author: khal drogo
content: No, l must ride.

author: qotho
content: He fell from his horse. A Khal who cannot ride is no Khal.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He's tired, that's all. He needs to rest. We've ridden far enough today. We'll camp here.

author: qotho
content: This is no place to camp. A woman does not give us orders. Not even a Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We'll camp here. Tell them Khal Drogo commanded it.

author: qotho
content: You do not command me, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Find Mirri Maz Duur. Bring her to me.

author: qotho
content: The witch? l'll bring you her head, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Bring her to me unharmed or Khal Drogo will hear why you denied me.

author: qotho
content: Hyah! Hyah!

author: kevan lannister
content: Our scouts tell us the Stark host has moved south from the Twins with Lord Frey's levies in tow. They're a day's march north.

author: tywin lannister
content: The boy may lack experience and sense, but he does have a certain mindless provincial courage.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, do continue. Didn't mean to interrupt.

author: tywin lannister
content: l do hope your savages are going to be of some use, otherwise we've wasted good steel on them.

author: kevan lannister
content: The great hairy one insisted he must have two battleaxes. Heavy black steel, double-sided.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shagga likes axes.

author: tywin lannister
content: When the battle commences, you and your wildlings will be in the vanguard.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The vanguard? Me and the tribesmen on the front lines?

author: kevan lannister
content: They do seem rather ferocious.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ferocious? Last night a Moon Brother stabbed a Stone Crow over a sausage. Three Stone Crows seized the Moon Brother and opened his throat. Bronn managed to keep Shagga from chopping off the dead man's cock, which was fortunate, but even still, Ulf is demanding blood money, which Shagga and Gunthor refuse to pay.

author: tywin lannister
content: When soldiers lack discipline, the fault lies with their commander.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Surely there are ways to have me killed that would be less detrimental to the war effort.

author: tywin lannister
content: There'll be no more discussion on the matter.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt appears l'm not hungry after all. Excuse me, my lords.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where did you find one so pretty at this hour?

author: bronn
content: l took her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Took her? From whom?

author: bronn
content: From, uh, Ser What's-his-name? l don't know. Ginger cunt, three tents down.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And he didn't have anything to say about it?

author: bronn
content: He said something.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, the odds of me living long enough for him to retaliate have just dropped drastically. We'll be at the vanguard tomorrow.

author: bronn
content: Oh, well. l, uh, think l'll go and find myself one.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who are you?

author: prostitute
content: Who would you like me to be?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What did your mother call you?

author: prostitute
content: Shae. What did your mother call you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My mother died giving birth to me.

author: shae
content: ls that why l'm here? So we can talk about our mothers?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What sort of accent is that?

author: shae
content: Foreign.

author: tyrion lannister
content: For-

author: shae
content: What do you want from me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What do l want from you? l want you to share my tent. l want you to pour my wine, laugh at my jokes, rub my legs when they're sore after a day's ride. l want you to take no other man to bed for as long as we're together. And l want you to fuck me like it's my last night in this world. Which it may well be.

author: shae
content: And what do l get?

author: tyrion lannister
content: One - safety. No one will hurt you for as long as you're mine. Two - the pleasure of my company, which l have heard is spectacular.

author: shae
content: Who told you this? Women you paid?

author: tyrion lannister
content: And three - more gold than you can spend if you lived a thousand years. Do you accept my proposal?

author: shae
content: Let's start with your last night in this world.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Come. He's very strong. No one understands how strong he is.

author: jorah mormont
content: He will die tonight, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He can't. He can't. l won't let him.

author: jorah mormont
content: Even a queen doesn't have that power. We must go quickly. l've heard there's a good port in Asshai.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l won't leave him.

author: jorah mormont
content: He's already gone, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Even if he dies, why would l run? l am khaleesi, and my my son will be khal after Drogo.

author: jorah mormont
content: This isn't Westeros, where men honor blood. Here they only honor strength. There will be fighting after Drogo dies. Whoever wins that fight will be the new khal. He won't want any rivals. Your boy will be plucked from your breast and given to the dogs.

author: mirri maz duur
content: The wound has festered.

author: qotho
content: You did this, witch.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Stop it! l don't want her hurt.

author: qotho
content: No? No? You don't want her hurt? Pray we don't hurt you, too. You let this witch put her hands on our Khal.

author: jorah mormont
content: Rein in your tongue. She is still your Khaleesi.

author: qotho
content: Only while the blood of my blood lives. When he dies, she is nothing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l have never been nothing. l am the blood of the dragon.

author: qotho
content: The dragons are all dead, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l think you should wear your armor tonight, ser.

author: jorah mormont
content: l think you're right.

author: mirri maz duur
content: You've saved me once more.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And now you must save him.

author: mirri maz duur
content: He's beyond the healer's skills. All l can do is ease his path.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Save him and l will free you. l swear it. You must know a way. Some – some magic.

author: mirri maz duur
content: There is a spell. Some would say death is cleaner.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do it. Save him.

author: mirri maz duur
content: There is a price.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You'll have gold, whatever you want.

author: mirri maz duur
content: lt's not a matter of gold. This is blood magic. Only death pays for life.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My death?

author: mirri maz duur
content: No, not your death, Khaleesi. Bring me his horse.

author: rakharo
content: Khaleesi, do not do this thing. Let me kill this witch.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Kill her and you kill your khal.

author: rakharo
content: This is blood magic. lt is forbidden.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l am your khaleesi. l tell you what is forbidden.

author: mirri maz duur
content: Go. Now.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Take her and leave. Take her!

author: mirri maz duur
content: You must go also, lady. Once l begin to sing, no one must enter the tent. The dead will dance here tonight.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No one will enter.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Bring him back to me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l have to save him.

author: qotho
content: This must not be.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This must be.

author: qotho
content: Witch.

author: rakharo
content: Nothing good will come of this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No, you can't.

author: irri
content: Khaleesi!

author: jorah mormont
content: No further, horselord.

author: jorah mormont
content: Are you hurt?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The baby –

author: jorah mormont
content: Hmm?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: is coming.

author: jorah mormont
content: Fetch the midwives.

author: rakharo
content: They will not come. They say she is cursed.

author: jorah mormont
content: They'll come or l'll have their heads.

author: rakharo
content: The witch - she can bring baby. l hear her say so.

author: shae
content: Are you in agony, my lion?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No.

author: shae
content: You look like you're in agony. The fire is burning your pretty soft skin.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah! Damn you, woman. Are you immune to pain?

author: shae
content: Just used to it.

author: bronn
content: Drink.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Let's play a new game.

author: bronn
content: There's a Braavosi knife game l could teach you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Does it involve the potential for losing fingers?

author: bronn
content: Not if you win.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No! No fire games, no knife games. Let's do something l'm good at.

author: shae
content: What are you good at?

author: tyrion lannister
content: l happen to be a great judge of character.

author: bronn
content: This sounds like a boring game.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt's not. Here's how it works - l make a statement about your past. lf l'm right, you drink. lf l'm wrong, l drink. And no lying. l'll know if you're lying.

author: shae
content: l don't want to play this game.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Fine. Bronn first. Your father beat you.

author: bronn
content: But my mother hit harder.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You killed your first man before you were 12.

author: bronn
content: lt was a woman. She swung an axe at me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You've been north of the Wall.

author: shae
content: What brought you up there?

author: bronn
content: Work.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And you once loved a woman many years ago, but it turned out badly so you've never let yourself love again. Oh, wait, that's me. Your turn, my mysterious foreign beauty.

author: shae
content: l don't want to play.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt's fun! Look at the fun we're having. Your mother was a whore.

author: shae
content: Drink.

author: tyrion lannister
content: All right. Your father left the family when you were very young, never to return.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And we've established the rules about lying?

author: shae
content: Drink!

author: tyrion lannister
content: You wanted a different life. You came from somewhere and you wanted to be elsewhere.

author: bronn
content: The whole shit-stained world could drink off that one.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So, specifics… You wanted to be elsewhere, but how would you get there? l don't believe the life of the Silent Sisters is for you. So, what's a lowborn girl to do?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Are you sure –

author: shae
content: Drink! And don't talk about my mother and father ever, or l will carve your eyes from your head.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My dear lady, if l have offended you, l apologize.

author: shae
content: My turn.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Fine, fine. Ask away. Try to penetrate the enigma that is me.

author: shae
content: Who were you in love with?

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's not how the game works.

author: shae
content: l don't care the way the game works.

author: bronn
content: Our lord here used to be married.

author: shae
content: Married?

author: tyrion lannister
content: How did you hear that?

author: bronn
content: You hear lots of things playing dice with Lannister soldiers.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Another night, perhaps.

author: shae
content: Not another night. This night.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt's not a pleasant story.

author: shae
content: Oh, maybe l will cry.

author: bronn
content: l'm guessing the lady and l can tell more unpleasant stories than your lordship.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So l was 16. My brother Jaime and l were riding, when we heard a scream. She ran out onto the road, clothes half torn off, with two men on her heels. Jaime scared away the men easily enough, while l wrapped her in my cloak. She was too scared to send off on her own, so while Jaime hunted down the rapers l took her to the nearest inn and fed her. Her name was Tysha. She was a wheelwright's orphan. And she was hungry. Together we finished off three chickens and a flagon of wine. lmpossible as it seems, there was a time when l was unaccustomed to wine. l forgot how afraid l was around girls. how l was always waiting for them to laugh at me or look away embarrassed, or ask me about my tall, handsome brother. l forgot about everything but Tysha. And somehow l found myself in her bed.

author: bronn
content: For three chickens, l should hope so.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt didn't last long. l didn't know what the hell l was doing. But she was good to me. She kissed me afterwards and sang me a song. And by morning l was deep enough in love to ask for her hand. A few lies, a few gold coins, one drunken septon and there you have it - man and wife. For a fortnight anyway, until the septon sobered up and told my father.

author: bronn
content: Well, l imagine that was the end of all that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not quite. First, my father had Jaime tell me the truth. The girl was a whore, you see. Jaime had arranged the whole thing - the road, the rapers, all of it. He thought it was time l had a woman. After my brother confessed, my father brought in my wife and gave her to his guards. He paid her well - a silver for each man. How many whores command that kind of price? He brought me into the barracks and made me watch. By the end, she had so much silver that the coins were slipping through her fingers and rolling on to the floor.

author: bronn
content: l would have killed the man who did that to me.

author: shae
content: You should have known she was a whore.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Really? l was 16, drunk and in love.

author: shae
content: A girl who was almost raped doesn't invite another man into her bed two hours later.

author: tyrion lannister
content: As l said, l was young and stupid.

author: shae
content: You are still young and stupid.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What is it? What do you want?

author: bronn
content: You're sleeping through the war.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What?

author: bronn
content: They stole a night's march on us. They're a mile north.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Get my squire!

author: bronn
content: You don't have a squire.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lf l die, weep for me.

author: shae
content: You'll be dead. How will you know?

author: tyrion lannister
content: l'll know.

author: lannister soldier
content: Watch out! Move!

author: lannister soldier
content: Out of the way! Move aside!

author: bronn
content: Stay low.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stay low?

author: bronn
content: lf you're lucky, no one will notice you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: l was born lucky. Tribesmen of the Vale, gather round! Stone Crows! Black Ears! Burned Men! Moon Brothers! And Painted Dogs! Your dominion over the Vale begins now! Onward, to claim what is yours!

author: tribesmen of vale
content: Half man! Half man! Half man! Half man! Half man! Half man!

author: tyrion lannister
content: To battle!

author: bronn
content: You're a shit warrior.

author: tyrion lannister
content: l'm alive?

author: bronn
content: You're alive.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did we win?

author: bronn
content: We wouldn't be having this conversation if we didn't.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How did our tribesmen do?

author: bronn
content: Yeah, good.

author: tyrion lannister
content: lt's nice to see them getting along.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're wounded.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good of you to notice. l hear we won.

author: tywin lannister
content: Huh! The scouts were wrong. There were 2,000 Stark bannermen, not 20 [thousand].

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did we get the Stark boy, at least?

author: tywin lannister
content: He wasn't here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where was he?

author: tywin lannister
content: With his other 18,000 men.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And where are they?

author: rodrik cassel
content: We should go, my lady.

author: catelyn stark
content: No!

author: rodrik cassel
content: My lady!

author: stark bannermen
content: Hyah! Hyah!

author: robb stark
content: By the time they knew what was happening, it had already happened.

author: jaime lannister
content: Lady Stark. l'd offer you my sword, but l seem to have lost it.

author: catelyn stark
content: lt is not your sword l want. Give me my daughters back. Give me my husband.

author: jaime lannister
content: l've lost them too, l'm afraid.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Kill him, Robb. Send his head to his father. He cut down ten of our men. You saw him.

author: robb stark
content: He's more use to us alive than dead.

author: catelyn stark
content: Take him away and put him in irons.

author: jaime lannister
content: We could end this war right now, boy, save thousands of lives. You fight for the Starks, l fight for the Lannisters. Swords or lances, teeth, nails - choose your weapons and let's end this here and now.

author: robb stark
content: lf we do it your way, Kingslayer, you'd win. We're not doing it your way.

author: greatjon umber
content: Come on, pretty man.

author: robb stark
content: l sent 2,000 men to their graves today.

author: theon greyjoy
content: The bards will sing songs of their sacrifice.

author: robb stark
content: Aye. But the dead won't hear them. One victory does not make us conquerors. Did we free my father? Did we rescue my sisters from the queen? Did we free the North from those who want us on our knees? This war is far from over.

author: arya stark
content: Could l have one? A lemon one or any of them.

author: kings landing baker
content: Three coppers.

author: arya stark
content: How about a nice fat pigeon?

author: kings landing baker
content: Oh, piss off now. Go on.

author: arya stark
content: Do you have any stale ones from yesterday? Or any burnt ones?

author: kings landing baker
content: Piss off!

author: arya stark
content: Hey, where's everyone going? What's happening?

author: street urchin
content: They're taking him to the Sept of Baelor.

author: arya stark
content: Who?

author: street urchin
content: The Hand of the King.

author: populace
content: Traitor! Coward!

author: eddark stark
content: Baelor!

author: populace
content: Traitor! Traitor!

author: eddark stark
content: I am Eddard Stark, Lord of Winterfell and Hand of the King. I come before you to confess my treason in the sight of Gods and men. I betrayed the faith of my King and the trust of my friend Robert. I swore to protect and defend his children, but before his blood was cold I plotted to murder his son and seize the Throne for myself. Let the High Septon and Baelor the Blessed bear witness to what I say

author: grand maester pycelle
content: As we sin, so do we suffer. This man has confessed his crimes in sight of Gods and men. The Gods are just but beloved Baelor taught us they can also be merciful. What is to be done with this traitor, Your Grace?

author: joffrey lannister
content: My mother wishes me to let Lord Eddard join The Night's Watch. Stripped of all titles and powers, he would serve the realm in permanent exile. And My Lady Sansa has begged mercy for her father. But they have the soft hearts of women. So long as I am your King, treason shall never go unpunished. Ser Ilyn, bring me his head!

author: sansa stark
content: No, stop! Please, someone stop him!

author: cersei lannister
content: My son, this is madness.

author: populace
content: Put him down!

author: yoren
content: Don't look!

author: arya stark
content: Let me go.

author: yoren
content: Shut your mouth. Look at me.

author: sansa stark
content: Stop him, stop!

author: yoren
content: Look at me. Look at me! Do you remember me now, boy, eh? Remember me? There's a bright boy. You'll be coming with me, boy, and you'll be keeping your mouth shut.

author: yoren
content: Keep your mouth shut, boy.

author: arya stark
content: l'm not a boy!

author: yoren
content: You're not a smart boy, is that what you're trying to say? Do you want to live, boy?! North, boy, we're going north.

author: bran stark
content: lt had three eyes. lt told me to come with him, so l did. We went down into the crypts and my father was there.

author: osha
content: Your father's not down there, little lord. Not for many years yet.

author: bran stark
content: You're afraid. Just like Hodor.

author: osha
content: l'm not afraid of some hole in the ground.

author: bran stark
content: You've lived beyond the Wall. What are you scared of? l'm a crippled boy and l'm willing to go.

author: bran stark
content: That's my grandfather, Lord Rickard. He was burned alive by the Mad King, Aerys. That's Lyanna, my father's sister. King Robert was supposed to marry her, but Rhaegar Targaryen kidnapped her. Robert started a war to win her back. He killed Rhaegar, but she died anyway. That's where l saw Father.

author: osha
content: You see? He's not here.

author: rickon stark
content: Here, Shaggydog.

author: bran stark
content: Rickon!

author: osha
content: That beast is supposed to be chained in the kennels!

author: rickon stark
content: He doesn't like chains.

author: bran stark
content: What are you doing down here? Come back up with us.

author: rickon stark
content: No, l came to see Father.

author: bran stark
content: How many times have l told you? He's in King's Landing with Sansa and Arya.

author: rickon stark
content: He was down here. l saw him.

author: bran stark
content: Saw him when?

author: rickon stark
content: Last night, when l was sleeping. Here, Shaggydog.

author: osha
content: You both miss him. lt's only natural he should be in your thoughts and dreams, but that doesn't mean that –

author: maester luwin
content: Bran…

author: several stark bannermen
content: My lady. My lady. My lady.

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb. Robb! You've ruined your sword.

author: catelyn stark
content: Shh! Shh! Shh!

author: robb stark
content: l'll kill them all. Every one of them. l will kill them all.

author: catelyn stark
content: My boy. They have your sisters. We have to get the girls back. And then we will kill them all.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Very amusing. lsn't it a funny song? Thank you for your rendition. l imagine it was even better received at that tavern.

author: marillion
content: l'm so sorry, Your Grace. l'll never sing it again, l swear.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Tell me, which do you favor - your fingers or your tongue?

author: marillion
content: Your Grace?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Fingers or your tongue? lf you got to keep one, which would it be? Or l could just cut your throat.

author: marillion
content: Every man needs hands, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Good. Tongue it is.

author: marillion
content: Your Grace, please. l won't sing, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Ser llyn, who better than you to carry out the sentence?

author: marillion
content: l beg you! Please, no. No!

author: marillion
content: Your Grace, please. l beg you, l will never sing again! No!

author: joffrey lannister
content: l'm done for the day. l'll leave the rest of the matters to you, Mother.

author: marillion
content: Your Grace, please!

author: joffrey lannister
content: You look quite nice.

author: sansa stark
content: Thank you, my lord.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Your Grace. l'm King now.

author: marillion
content: Stop! No!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Walk with me. l want to show you something.

author: sandor clegane
content: Do as you're bid, child.

author: joffrey lannister
content: And as soon as you've had your blood, l'll put a son in you. Mother says that shouldn't be long.

author: sansa stark
content: No! Please, no!

author: joffrey lannister
content: This one's your father. This one here. Look at it and see what happens to traitors.

author: sansa stark
content: You promised to be merciful.

author: joffrey lannister
content: l was. l gave him a clean death. Look at him.

author: sansa stark
content: Please let me go home. l won't do any treason, l swear –

author: joffrey lannister
content: Mother says l'm still to marry you. So you'll stay here, and obey. Look at him!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Well?

author: sansa stark
content: How long do l have to look?

author: joffrey lannister
content: As long as it pleases me. Do you want to see the rest?

author: sansa stark
content: lf it please Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: That's your Septa there. l'll tell you what, l'm going to give you a present. After l raise my armies and kill your traitor brother, l'm going to give you his head as well.

author: sansa stark
content: Or maybe he'll give me yours.

author: sandor clegane
content: Here, girl.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Will you obey now? Or do you need another lesson? l'll look for you in court.

author: sandor clegane
content: Save yourself some pain, girl. Give him what he wants.

author: sandor clegane
content: You'll be needing that again.

author: jonos bracken
content: The proper course is clear - pledge fealty to King Renly and move south to join our forces with his.

author: robb stark
content: Renly is not the king.

author: jonos bracken
content: You cannot mean to hold to Joffrey, my lord. He put your father to death.

author: robb stark
content: That doesn't make Renly king. He's Robert's youngest brother. lf Bran can't be Lord of Winterfell before me, Renly can't be king before Stannis.

author: jonos bracken
content: Do you mean to declare us for Stannis?

author: galbart glover
content: Renly is not right! lf we put ourselves behind Stannis…

author: greatjon umber
content: My Lords. My Lords! Here is what l say to these two kings. Renly Baratheon is nothing to me, nor Stannis neither. Why should they rule over me and mine from some flowery seat in the South? What do they know of the Wall or the Wolfswood? Even their gods are wrong! Why shouldn't we rule ourselves again? lt was the dragons we bowed to and now the dragons are dead! There sits the only king l mean to bend my knee to - the King in the North!

author: rickard karstark
content: l'll have peace on those terms. They can keep their Red Castle and their iron chair too. The King in the North!

author: theon greyjoy
content: Am l your brother, now and always?

author: robb stark
content: Now and always.

author: theon greyjoy
content: My sword is yours in victory and defeat, from this day until my last day.

author: greatjon umber
content: The King in the North!

author: all
content: The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North!

author: stark guard
content: Lady Stark.

author: catelyn stark
content: l want to see him. Now! Leave us.

author: catelyn stark
content: Leave us.

author: jaime lannister
content: You look lovely tonight, Lady Stark. Widowhood becomes you. Your bed must be lonely. ls that why you came? l'm not at my best, but l think l could be of service. You slip out of that gown and we'll see if l'm up to it. Oh, l do like a violent woman.

author: catelyn stark
content: l will kill you tonight, Ser. Pack your head in a box and send it to your sister.

author: jaime lannister
content: Let me show you how. Hit me again, over the ear. And again and again. You're stronger than you look, it shouldn't take long.

author: catelyn stark
content: That is what you want the world to believe, isn't it? That you don't fear death.

author: jaime lannister
content: But l don't, my lady. The dark is coming for all of us. Why cry about it?

author: catelyn stark
content: Because you are going to the deepest of the seven hells, if the gods are just.

author: jaime lannister
content: What gods are those? The trees your husband prayed to? Where were the trees when his head was getting chopped off? lf your gods are real and if they are just why is the world so full of injustice?

author: catelyn stark
content: Because of men like you.

author: jaime lannister
content: There are no men like me. Only me.

author: catelyn stark
content: My son Bran. How did he come to fall from that tower?

author: jaime lannister
content: l pushed him out the window.

author: catelyn stark
content: Why?

author: jaime lannister
content: I hoped the fall would kill him.

author: jaime lannister
content: You should get some sleep. lt's going to be a long war.

author: lancel lannister
content: l can't believe we're actually at war. Was it this exciting last time, when you were young? What does it say? Have we captured Robb Stark yet? What's our next move?

author: cersei lannister
content: Stop talking. Get back into bed.

author: tywin lannister
content: They have my son.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Stark boy appears to be less green than we'd hoped.

author: leo lefford
content: l've heard his wolf killed a dozen men and as many horses.

author: addam marbrand
content: ls it true about Stannis and Renly?

author: kevan lannister
content: Both Baratheon brothers have taken up against us. Jaime captured, his armies scattered. lt's a catastrophe. Perhaps we should sue for peace.

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's your peace. Joffrey saw to that when he decided to remove Ned Stark's head. You'll have an easier time drinking from that cup than you will bringing Robb Stark to the table now. He's winning – in case you hadn't noticed.

author: kevan lannister
content: l'm told we still have his sisters.

author: leo lefford
content: The first order of business is ransoming Ser Jaime.

author: addam marbrand
content: Kevan Lannister

author: tywin lannister
content: They have my son! Get out, all of you. Not you. You were right about Eddard Stark. lf he were alive, we could have used him to broker a peace with Winterfell and Riverrun, which would have given us more time to deal with Robert's brothers. But now – madness. Madness and stupidity. l always thought you were a stunted fool. Perhaps l was wrong.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Half wrong. l'm new to strategy, but unless we want to be surrounded by three armies, it appears we can't stay here.

author: tywin lannister
content: No one will stay here. Ser Gregor will head out with 500 riders and set the Riverland on fire from Godo s Eye to the Red Fork. The rest of us will regroup at Harrenhal. And you will go to King's Landing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And do what?

author: tywin lannister
content: Rule. You will serve as Hand of the King in my stead. You will bring that boy king to heel, and his mother too, if needs be. And if you get so much as a whiff of treason from any of the rest – Baelish, Varys, Pycelle…

author: tyrion lannister
content: Heads, spikes, walls. Why not my uncle? Why not anyone? Why me?

author: tywin lannister
content: You're my son. Oh, one more thing. You will not take that whore to court. Do you understand?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Ser Jorah?

author: jorah mormont
content: Gently, gently.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My son – where is he? l want him. Where is he?

author: jorah mormont
content: The boy did not live.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Tell me.

author: jorah mormont
content: What is there to tell?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How did my son die?

author: jorah mormont
content: He never lived, my princess. The women say –

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What do the women say?

author: jorah mormont
content: They say the child was –

author: mirri maz duur
content: Monstrous, twisted. l pulled him out myself. He was scaled like a lizard, blind, with leather wings like the wings of a bat. When l touched him the skin fell from his bones. Inside he was full of graveworms. l warned you that only death can pay for life. You knew the price.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Where is Khal Drogo? Show him to me. Show me what l bought with my son's life.

author: mirri maz duur
content: As you command, lady. Come. l will take you to him.

author: jorah mormont
content: Time enough for that later –

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l want to see him now.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The khalasar is gone.

author: jorah mormont
content: A khal who cannot ride is no khal. The Dothraki follow only the strong. l'm sorry, my Princess.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Drogo! My sun and stars. Why is he out here alone?

author: jorah mormont
content: He seems to like the warmth, Princess.

author: mirri maz duur
content: He lives. You asked for life, you paid for life.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This is not life. When will he be as he was?

author: mirri maz duur
content: When the sun rises in the west, sets in the east. When the seas go dry. When the mountains blow in the wind like leaves.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Leave us.

author: jorah mormont
content: l don't want you alone with this sorceress.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l have nothing more to fear from this woman. Go.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You knew what l was buying and you knew the price.

author: mirri maz duur
content: lt was wrong of them to burn my temple. lt angered the Great Shepherd.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This is not Godo s work. My child was innocent.

author: mirri maz duur
content: lnnocent? He would have been The Stallion Who Mounts The World. Now he will burn no cities. Now his khalasar will trample no nations into dust.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l spoke for you. l saved you.

author: mirri maz duur
content: Saved me? Three of those riders had already raped me before you saved me, girl. l saw my godo s house burn, there where l had healed men and women beyond counting. ln the streets l saw piles of heads, the head of the baker who makes my bread, the head of a young boy that l had cured of fever just three moons past. So tell me again exactly what it was that you saved?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your life.

author: mirri maz duur
content: Why don't you take a look at your khal. Then you will see exactly what life is worth when all the rest has gone.

author: sam tarly
content: You can't!

author: jon snow
content: Get out of my way, Sam.

author: sam tarly
content: They'll put out the word. They'll send out ravens. People will come after you. Do you know what happens to deserters?

author: jon snow
content: Better than you do.

author: sam tarly
content: What are you going to do?

author: jon snow
content: l'm gonna find my brother and put a sword through King Joffrey's throat.

author: sam tarly
content: You can't leave us now. We need you here.

author: jon snow
content: Move.

author: sam tarly
content: l won't let you go.

author: sam tarly
content: No.

author: jon snow
content: Hyah!

author: shae
content: Hand of the King?

author: tyrion lannister
content: So it would seem.

author: shae
content: And your father said you couldn't take anyone with you to King's Landing?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, he said l couldn't take with me to King's Landing. He was very specific on that point.

author: shae
content: He knew my name?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What?

author: shae
content: He said, "Don't bring Shae with you to King's Landing"?

author: tyrion lannister
content: l believe he used the word "whore".

author: shae
content: Are you ashamed of me? Are you afraid that l'm dancing around the court with my tits out?

author: shae
content: I'm funny now? l'm Shae, the funny whore.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My father's probably the most powerful man in the country. Certainly the richest. He has all Seven Kingdoms in his pockets. Everyone everywhere always has to do exactly what my father says. He's always been a cunt. l believe the ladies of the court could learn a great deal from a girl like you. Why don't you come with me, be the Hando s lady? Because the King needs a Hand and the Hand –

author: shae
content: l know what a Hand needs.

author: jon snow
content: Ghost?

author: sam pyp and grenn
content: Hyah! Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!

author: grenn
content: Samwell!

author: pyp
content: ls he dead?

author: grenn
content: No, he's not dead.

author: sam tarly
content: Did we get him?

author: grenn
content: Come on, help me get him up.

author: pyp
content: Lucky you've got plenty of padding. We're taking you back to where you belong.

author: jon snow
content: l belong with my brother.

author: sam tarly
content: But we're your brothers now.

author: grenn
content: They'll kill you if they find out you've gone.

author: jon snow
content: They'll kill you if they know you came after me. Go back.

author: pyp
content: Sam told us everything. We're sorry about your father.

author: grenn
content: But it doesn't matter. You took the oath. You can't leave.

author: jon snow
content: l have to.

author: grenn
content: You can't. You said the words.

author: jon snow
content: I don't care about –

author: sam tarly
content: Hear my words and bear witness to my vow

author: jon snow
content: To hell with all of you.

author: pyp
content: Night gathers and now my watch begins. lt shall not end until my death. l shall live and die at my post.

author: grenn
content: l am the sword in the darkness –

author: sam pyp and grenn
content: l am the sword in the darkness, the watcher on the walls, the shield that guards the realms of men. l pledge my life and honor to the Night's Watch, for this night and all nights to come.”

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do you remember our first ride, my sun and stars? lf you are in there, if you haven't gone away, show me. You're a fighter. You've always been a fighter. l need you to fight now. l know you're very far away, but come back to me, my sun and stars.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: When the sun rises in the west and sets in the east. Then you shall return to me, my sun and stars.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Kings? Oh, l can tell you all there is to know about kings. The thing you need to understand about kings is – For the past 67 years, l've known truly known more kings than any man alive. They're complicated men, but l know how to serve them. Yes, and keep on serving them. Aerys Targaryen. Of all the thousand thousand maladies the Gods visit on us, madness is the worst. He was a good man. Such a charmer. To watch him melt away before my eyes, consumed by dreams of fire and blood. Robert Baratheon was an entirely different animal – powerful man, great warrior, but alas - winning a kingdom and ruling a kingdom are rather different things. They say that if a man goes through life with his battle visor down, he can often be blind to the enemies at his side. Now l serve his son King Joffrey, may the Gods bless his reign.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: He is a capable young man. Strong military mind. Stern. But sternness in defense of the realm is no vice. lt's far too soon to know what manner of king he will be, but l sense true greatness on the horizon for our new King. Mmm. True greatness.

author: ros
content: So what's the thing?

author: grand maester pycelle
content: What thing?

author: ros
content: About kings. You said, "The thing you need to understand about kings".

author: grand maester pycelle
content: What? Things? What?

author: ros
content: When you started, you… Never mind.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Let me see you out, my dear.

author: ros
content: lt's all right. No need.

author: grand maester pycelle
content: Yes, yes. Till the next time. Right.

author: varys
content: When you imagine yourself up there, how do you look? Does the crown fit? Do all the lords and ladies simper and bow, the ones who sneered at you for years?

author: petyr baelish
content: lt's hard for them to simper and bow without heads.

author: varys
content: A man with great ambition and no morals… l wouldn't bet against you.

author: petyr baelish
content: And what would you do, my friend, if you found yourself sitting up there?

author: varys
content: l must be one of the few men in this city who doesn't want to be King.

author: petyr baelish
content: You must be one of the few men in the city who isn't a man.

author: varys
content: Oh, you can do better than that.

author: petyr baelish
content: When they castrated you, did they take the pillar with the stones? l've always wondered.

author: varys
content: Have you? Do you spend a lot of time wondering what's between my legs?

author: petyr baelish
content: l picture a gash. Like a woman's. ls that about right?

author: varys
content: l am flattered, of course, to be pictured at all.

author: petyr baelish
content: Must be strange for you, even after all these years… a man from another land, despised by most, feared by all.

author: varys
content: Am l? That is good to know. Do you lie awake at night fearing my gash?

author: petyr baelish
content: But you carry on whispering in one king's ear and then the next. l admire you.

author: varys
content: And l admire you, Lord Baelish. A grasper from a minor House with a major talent for befriending powerful men – and women.

author: petyr baelish
content: A useful talent, l'm sure you'd agree.

author: varys
content: So here we stand in mutual admiration and respect.

author: petyr baelish
content: Playing our roles.

author: varys
content: Serving a new King.

author: petyr baelish
content: Long may he reign. My king.

author: varys
content: My king.

author: joffrey lannister
content: My lords. Shall we begin?

author: yoren
content: You're Arry now, hear me? Arry the orphan boy. No one asks an orphan too many questions, ‘cause nobody gives three shits. What's your name?

author: arya stark
content: Arry.

author: yoren
content: You've a long way to travel, and in bad company. l've 20 this time – men and boys all bound for the Wall. Your lord father gave me the pick of the dungeons, and l didn't find no little lordlings down there. This lot – half of them would turn you over to the King quick as spit for a pardon. And the other half would do the same, except they'd rape you first. So keep to yourself – and when you piss, do it in the woods alone. You stay with this lot, boy. And stay or l'll lock you in the back of the wagon with these three.

author: hot pie
content: Watch yourself, midget.

author: lommy greenhands
content: He's got a sword, this one.

author: hot pie
content: What's a gutter rat like you doing with a sword?

author: lommy greenhands
content: Maybe he's a little squire.

author: hot pie
content: He ain't no squire. Look at him. He looks like a girl. l bet he stole that sword.

author: lommy greenhands
content: Let's have a look.

author: hot pie
content: l could use me a sword like that.

author: lommy greenhands
content: Take it off him.

author: hot pie
content: Give it here, midget.

author: lommy greenhands
content: Look at him! You'd better give Hot Pie the sword. l've seen him kick a boy to death.

author: hot pie
content: l knocked him down and l kicked him in the balls and l kept kicking him until he was dead. l kicked him all to pieces. You better give me that sword!

author: arya stark
content: You want it? l'll give it to you. l already killed one fat boy. l bet you never killed anyone. l bet you're a liar. But l'm not. l'm good at killing fat boys. l like killing fat boys.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Your like picking on the little ones, do you? l've been hammering an anvil these past 10 years. When l hit that steel, it sings. Are you gonna sing when l hit you? This is castle-forged steel. Where'd you steal it?

author: arya stark
content: lt was a gift.

author: gendry baratheon
content: lt don't matter now. Where we're going, they don't care what you've done. They've got rapers, pickpockets, highwaymen, murderers.

author: arya stark
content: Which are you?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Armourer's apprentice. But my master got sick of me, so here l am.

author: yoren
content: Come on, you sorry sons of whores! lt's a thousand leagues from here to the Wall, and winter is coming!

author: jeor mormont
content: Ham. How many days in a row must a man be expected to start his day with ham? Bring me some beer at least. You look exhausted. Was your moonlight ride that tiring?

author: jon snow
content: My friends brought me back.

author: jeor mormont
content: l didn't say it was your honor.

author: jon snow
content: They killed my father.

author: jeor mormont
content: And you're gonna bring him back to life, are you? No? Good. We've had enough of that sort of thing. Beyond the Wall, the Rangers are reporting whole villages abandoned. At night they see fires blazing in the mountains from dusk until dawn. A captured wildling swears their tribes are uniting in some secret stronghold, to what ends the gods only know. Outside Eastwatch Cotter Pyke's men discovered four blue-eyed corpses. Unlike us, they were wise enough to burn them. Do you think your brother's war is more important than ours?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: jeor mormont
content: When dead men and worse come hunting for us in the night, do you think it matters who sits on the lron Throne?

author: jeor mormont
content: Good. Because l want you and your wolf with us when we ride out beyond the Wall tomorrow.

author: jon snow
content: Beyond the Wall?

author: jeor mormont
content: l'll not sit meekly by and wait for the snows. l mean to find out what's happening. The Night's Watch will ride in force against the wildlings, the White Walkers and whatever else is out there. And we will find Benjen Stark, alive or dead. l will command them myself. So l'll only ask you once, Lord Snow, are you a brother of the Night's Watch or a bastard boy who wants to play at war?

author: rakharo
content: ls this your command, Khaleesi?

author: jorah mormont
content: Drogo will have no use for dragon eggs in the Night Lands. Sell them. You can return to the Free Cities and live as a wealthy woman for all your days.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They were not given to me to sell.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi, my Queen, l vow to serve you, obey you, to die for you if need be, but let him go, Khaleesi. l know what you intend. Do not.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: l must. You don't understand.

author: jorah mormont
content: Don't ask me to stand aside as you climb on that pyre. l won't watch you burn.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: ls that what you fear? You will be my khalasar. l see the faces of slaves. l free you. Take off your collars. Go if you wish, no one will stop you. But if you stay it will be as brothers and sisters, as husbands and wives.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Ser Jorah, bind this woman to the pyre. You swore to obey me.

author: mirri maz duur
content: You will not hear me scream.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will. But it is not your screams I want. Only your life.

author: jorah mormont
content: Blood of my blood.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Well struck… Well struck, Dog.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Did you like that?

author: sansa stark
content: It was well struck, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I already said it was well struck.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Who's next?

author: announcer
content: Lothor Brune, freerider in the service of Lord Baelish.

author: announcer
content: Ser Dontos the Red of House Hollard.

author: announcer
content: Ser Dontos the Red of House Hollard!

author: ser dontos
content: Here I am. . Here I am. . Sorry, Your Grace. . My deepest apologies. .

author: joffrey lannister
content: Are you drunk?

author: ser dontos
content: No. Uh, no, Your Grace. I had - I had two cups of wine.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Two cups? . That's not much at all. . Please, have another cup.

author: ser dontos
content: Are you sure, Your Grace?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Yes, to celebrate my name day. Have two, have as much as you like.

author: ser dontos
content: I would be honored, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Ser Meryn, help Ser Dontos celebrate my name day. See that he drinks his fill.

author: sansa stark
content: You can't!

author: joffrey lannister
content: What did you say? Did you say I can't?

author: sansa stark
content: I only meant… it would be bad luck to kill a man on your name day.

author: joffrey lannister
content: What kind of stupid peasant's superstition...

author: sandor clegane
content: The girl is right. What a man sows on his name day, he reaps all year.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Take him away. I'll have him killed tomorrow, the fool.

author: sansa stark
content: He is. A fool - you're so clever to see it. He'll make a much better fool than a knight. He doesn't deserve the mercy of a quick death.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Did you hear My Lady, Ser Dontos? . From this day, , you'll be my new fool.

author: ser dontos
content: Thank you, Your Grace. . And you, My Lady, thank you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Beloved nephew.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We looked for you on the battlefield. . You were nowhere to be found.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I've been here, ruling the kingdoms.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What a fine job you've done. . Look at you. . More beautiful than ever. . And you! You, you're going to be bigger than the Hound, but much better looking. . This one doesn't like me.

author: bronn
content: Can't imagine why.

author: joffrey lannister
content: We heard you were dead.

author: myrcella
content: I'm glad you're not dead.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Me, too, dear. Death is so boring, especially now with so much excitement in the world. . My Lady, I'm sorry for your loss.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Her loss? Her father was a confessed traitor!

author: tyrion lannister
content: But still her father. Surely having so recently lost your own beloved father you can sympathize.

author: sansa stark
content: My father was a traitor. My mother and brother are traitors, too. I am loyal to my beloved Joffrey.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course you are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, , enjoy your name day, Your Grace. Wish I could stay and celebrate, but there is work to be done.

author: joffrey lannister
content: What work? . Why are you here?

author: pycelle
content: The raven arrived from the Citadel this morning, Your Grace. The conclave has met, , considered reports from Maesters all over the Seven Kingdoms, and declared this great summer done, at last. The longest summer in living memory.

author: varys
content: The peasants say, a long summer means an even longer winter.

author: pycelle
content: A common superstition.

author: petyr baelish
content: We have enough wheat for a five-year winter. If it lasts any longer, , we'll have fewer peasants.

author: janos
content: The city's drowning in refugees, Your Grace, fleeing the war. We have nowhere to house them, and with winter coming, it'll only get worse.

author: cersei lannister
content: You command the City Watch, do you not, Lord Slynt?

author: janos
content: I do, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: And are you not a Lord at my command?

author: janos
content: I owe my title and lands to your generosity, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Then do your job. Shut the gates to the peasants. They belong in the field, not our capital.

author: janos
content: Yes, Your Grace.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Don't get up. More ravishing than ever, big sister. . War agrees with you. Forgive the interruption, carry on.

author: cersei lannister
content: What are you doing here?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's been a remarkable journey. I, , pissed off the edge of the Wall, I slept in a sky cell. . I fought with the hill tribes. So many adventures, so much to be thankful for.

author: cersei lannister
content: What are you doing here? This is the small council.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes., well, I, do believe the Hand of the King is welcome at all small council meetings.

author: cersei lannister
content: Our father is Hand of the King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, but in his absence…

author: varys
content: Your father has named Lord Tyrion to serve as Hand in his stead while he fights -

author: cersei lannister
content: Out! All of you out. . I would like to know how you tricked father into this.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If I were capable of tricking father, I'd be emperor of the world by now. You brought this on yourself. .

author: cersei lannister
content: I've done nothing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Quite right. You did nothing when your son called for Ned Stark's head. Now the entire North has risen up against us.

author: cersei lannister
content: I tried to stop it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did you? You failed. That bit of theater will haunt our family for a generation.

author: cersei lannister
content: Robb Stark is a child.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who's won every battle he's fought. Do you understand we're losing the war?

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you know about warfare?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Nothing. But I know people. And I know that our enemies hate each other almost as much as they hate us.

author: cersei lannister
content: Joffrey is King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Joffrey is King.

author: cersei lannister
content: You are here to advise him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm only here to advise him. And if the King listens to what I say, the King might just get his Uncle Jaime back.

author: cersei lannister
content: How?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You love your children. It's your one redeeming quality. That and your cheekbones. The Starks love their children as well. And we have two of them.

author: cersei lannister
content: One.

author: tyrion lannister
content: One?

author: cersei lannister
content: Arya, little animal, she disappeared.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Disappeared? What, in a puff of smoke? We had three Starks to trade. You chopped one's head off and let another escape. Father will be furious. It must be odd for you to be the disappointing child.

author: lord
content: My Lord, may the Old Gods watch over your brother and all our northern sons.

author: lord
content: The walls of my Holdfast will not stand the winter. The stones were last mortared in the time of King Aerys, and I'm afraid the masons today are not fit to carry their fathers' hammers. When I was a boy, I remember seeing them put up a new tower at Torrhen's Square in a summer. Men worked back then. Today, my Holdfast looks like it was built by drunk children. At night you can hear the wind howling through the gaps. And the Gods forbid it rains. Why, I might as well sleep beneath a waterfall.

author: luwin
content: Maintenance of a Holdfast generally falls to the lord of that Holdfast.

author: lord
content: Generally, yes, but I've sent all the young men off to fight Robb Stark's war.

author: bran stark
content: King Robb. And it's not his war. He didn't choose it.

author: lord
content: Maybe not, My Lord, but he called in his Banners, and took the men.

author: bran stark
content: Joffrey killed my father, your liege lord. Do you remember your vows, Ser?

author: lord
content: Of course I remember!

author: luwin
content: We can spare four masons for a week, My Lord. Will that be sufficient to repair your walls?

author: lord
content: I - I believe it will.

author: luwin
content: We didn't want him here all day, did we?

author: bran stark
content: I didn't like the way he was talking about Robb.

author: luwin
content: Nor did I. But listening to people you'd rather not listen to is one of your responsibilities as Lord of Winterfell. . Lord Portan.

author: portan
content: My Lord, may the Old Gods watch over your brother and all our northern sons.

author: osha
content: Boil this for an hour and drink the tea. Makes all your pain go away.

author: bran stark
content: Don't have any pain.

author: osha
content: Lucky for you.

author: bran stark
content: That way.

author: osha
content: You've been having those dreams again.

author: bran stark
content: I don't dream.

author: osha
content: Everyone dreams.

author: bran stark
content: I don't. Heard some of the men talking about the comet. . They say it's an omen. They say it means Robb will win a great victory in the South.

author: osha
content: Did they? . I heard some other fools say it's Lannister Red. Means the Lannisters will rule all Seven Kingdoms before long. I heard a stable boy say it's the color of blood, to mark the death of your father.

author: osha
content: The stars don't fall for men. The red comet means one thing, boy. Dragons.

author: bran stark
content: The dragons are all dead. They've been dead for centuries.

author: doreah
content: What did your brother say about them, Khaleesi?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He said they ate meat.

author: doreah
content: He didn't tell you what kind of meat?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My brother didn't know anything about dragons. He didn't know anything about anything.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: She was Drogo's first gift to me.

author: jorah mormont
content: I remember.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I promised to protect them. Promised them their enemies would die screaming. How do I make starvation scream?

author: jorah mormont
content: A trick I never learned, I'm afraid.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Does it ever end?

author: jorah mormont
content: This is further east than I've ever been. But, yes, Khaleesi, everything ends, even the red waste.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you're sure there's no other way?

author: jorah mormont
content: If we go south to the land of the Lazarheen, the Lamb Men will kill us and take your dragons. If we go west to the Dothraki Sea, the first Khalasar we meet will kill us and take your dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No one will take my dragons.

author: jorah mormont
content: They are too weak to fight, as are your people. You must be their strength.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: As you are mine.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Rakharo, Aggo, Kovarro. Take our remaining horses. You will ride east, you southeast, and you northeast.

author: rakharo
content: What do we seek, Khaleesi?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Cities, living or dead. Caravans and people. Rivers or lakes or the great salt sea. Find how far the Red Waste extends before us, and what lies on the other side.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Rokharo, you are my last hope, blood of my blood.

author: rakharo
content: I will not fail you, blood of my blood.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You never have.

author: rakharo
content: This is… bad time to start.

author: jon snow
content: Having a rough time of it?

author: sam
content: Nothing's killed me yet.

author: grenn
content: Your ass killed the sledge.

author: sam
content: You offered me a ride!

author: grenn
content: I just wanted you to shut up about your damn blisters.

author: edd
content: I was born in a place like this. Later, I fell on hard times.

author: sam
content: Are those girls?

author: edd
content: Craster's daughters.

author: sam
content: I haven't seen a girl in six months.

author: edd
content: I'd keep on not seeing them if I were you.

author: grenn
content: What, he don't like people messing with his daughters?

author: edd
content: He don't like people messing with his wives.

author: edd
content: He marries his daughters, and they give him more daughters, and on, and on it goes.

author: sam
content: That's foul.

author: grenn
content: It's beyond foul.

author: edd
content: All the other wildlings for a hundred leagues have disappeared. Craster's still here. He must be doing something right.

author: jon snow
content: What happens to the boys?

author: sam
content: Hmm?

author: jon snow
content: He marries his daughters. What does he do with his sons?

author: lord mormont
content: He said he planned to stop here on his way to the Frostfangs.

author: craster
content: People make all sorts of plans. I haven't seen Benjen Stark in three years. Haven't missed him. Always treated me like scum. . Haven't had any good wine for a long time. You Southerners make good wine, I'll give you that.

author: jon snow
content: We're not Southerners.

author: craster
content: Who's this little girl? You're prettier than half my daughters. You got a nice wet twat between your legs? What's your name?

author: jon snow
content: Jon Snow.

author: craster
content: Snow, eh? Listen to me, bastard. All you lot from south of the Wall, you're Southerners. But now you're in the North, the real North.

author: lord mormont
content: The lad meant no harm.

author: craster
content: I catch that pretty little bastard talking to my daughters -

author: lord mormont
content: No one will talk to your daughters, you have my word. Now, sit down and shut your mouth.

author: craster
content: You bring any of that good wine with you?

author: lord mormont
content: We did. We passed through six villages on the way here. All six were abandoned. Where have all the wildlings gone?

author: craster
content: I could tell you, but I'm thirsty.

author: lord mormont
content: There's a barrel of Dornish wine on the sledge. Bring it in here.

author: watchman
content: Yes, commander.

author: craster
content: You want to know where they've all gone? North! To join up with Mance Rayder Your old friend.

author: lord mormont
content: He's no friend of mine. He broke his vows, betrayed his brothers!

author: craster
content: Oh, aye. But once he was just a poor black crow. And now he's King-Beyond-the-Wall.

author: lord mormont
content: He's been calling himself that for years. What's he king of? A frozen lake somewhere?

author: craster
content: That's a good-looking axe. Fresh forged?

author: lord mormont
content: Give it here.

author: lord mormont
content: You'll have another one made at Castle Black. . Here.

author: craster
content: Oh, that's some lovely steel. . You want to know what Mance Rayder is doing? Gathering an army. What I hear, he's already got more men than any of your southern kings.

author: lord mormont
content: And where does he plan marching this army?

author: craster
content: When you're all the way north, there's only one direction to go.

author: lord mormont
content: These are bad times to be living alone in the wild. The cold winds are rising.

author: craster
content: Let them come. My roots are sunk deep. Wife, tell the Lord Crow how content we are.

author: gilly
content: This is our place. Our husband keeps us safe. Better to live free than die a slave.

author: craster
content: Don't it make you jealous, old man, to see me with all these young wives and you with no one to warm your bed?

author: lord mormont
content: We chose different paths.

author: craster
content: Oh, aye, and you chose the path with no one but boys on it. . You'll be wanting to sleep beneath my roof, I suppose, and eat me out of pigs.

author: lord mormont
content: A roof would be welcome. It's been hard riding. We've brought our own food and good steel for you.

author: craster
content: Any man lays a hand on one of my wives, he loses the hand. And I see this one, , staring too long, I might just gouge his eyes out.

author: lord mormont
content: Your roof, your rules.

author: lord mormont
content: Who am I? Who am I?

author: jon snow
content: Lord commander.

author: lord mormont
content: And who are you?

author: lord mormont
content: Who are you?

author: jon snow
content: Your steward.

author: lord mormont
content: You want to lead one day? . Then learn how to follow.

author: melisandre
content: Lord of Light, come to us in our darkness. We offer you these false Gods.

author: melisandre
content: Take them and cast your light upon us. For the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: group
content: For the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: melisandre
content: After the long summer, darkness will fall heavy on the world. Stars will bleed.

author: cressen
content: We need to stop her!

author: melisandre
content: The cold breath of winter will freeze the seas.

author: davos
content: Not now.

author: melisandre
content: And the dead shall rise in the North.

author: cressen
content: All you men were named in the Light of the Seven! Is this how you treat the Gods of your fathers? Are you so eager to spit on your ancestors?

author: melisandre
content: You smell of fear, fear and piss and old bones. Do you want to stop me? Stop me.

author: melisandre
content: In the ancient books, it's written that a warrior will draw a burning sword from the fire. And that sword shall be Lightbringer. Stannis Baratheon, warrior of light, your sword awaits you.

author: crowd
content: Lord, cast your light upon us!

author: melisandre
content: For the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: stannis baratheon
content: For the night is dark and full of terror.

author: cressen
content: This woman will lead him into a war he cannot win.

author: davos
content: Stannis is our king. We follow where he leads, even if we don't like the path.

author: cressen
content: King. Since that boar killed his brother, every lord wants a coronation.

author: davos
content: I don't serve the others. I serve Stannis.

author: cressen
content: As do I, but loyal service means telling hard truths. He's surrounded by fools and fanatics, but he trusts you, Davos. . If you tell him the truth…

author: davos
content: What's the truth?

author: matthos
content: And I declare upon the honor of my house that my beloved brother Robert le-”

author: stannis baratheon
content: He wasn't my beloved brother. . I didn't love him, he didn't love me.

author: davos
content: A harmless courtesy, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: A lie. Take it out.

author: matthos
content: That my brother Robert left no trueborn heirs; the boy Joffrey, the boy Tommen, and the girl Myrcella, being born of incest between Cersei Lannister and her brother Jaime Lannister. By right of birth -"

author: stannis baratheon
content: Jaime Lannister, the Kingslayer. Call him what he is.

author: matthos
content: And her brother Jaime Lannister, the Kingslayer. By right of birth and blood, I do this day lay claim -

author: stannis baratheon
content: Make it Ser Jaime Lannister, the Kingslayer. Whatever else he is, the man's still a knight.

author: matthos
content: Ser Jaime Lannister, the Kingslayer. By right of birth and blood, I do this day lay claim to the Iron Throne of Westeros. . Let all true men declare their loyalty.”

author: stannis baratheon
content: When Eddard Stark learned the truth, he told only me. I'll not make the same mistake. Send copies of that letter to every corner of the Realm, from the Arbor to the Wall. The time has come to choose. Let no man claim ignorance as an excuse.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, the Lannisters are the true enemy. If, for the time being, you could make peace with your brother -

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'll not make peace with Renly while he calls himself King.

author: davos
content: Well, many have already declared for him; Mace Tyrell, Randyll Tarly.

author: melisandre
content: Stannis does not need to beg this lord or that lord for support. The Lord of Light stands behind him.

author: davos
content: And how many ships has the Lord of Light got in his fleet?

author: melisandre
content: He has no need for ships.

author: davos
content: I'm sure he doesn't, but we do if we're going to war. If not Renly, Your Grace, join forces with Robb Stark.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Who would steal the northern half of my kingdom. I've always served thieves according to their desserts, as you well know, Ser Davos. Joffrey, Renly, Robb Stark, they're all thieves. They'll bend the knee or I'll destroy them.

author: cressen
content: I owe you an apology, my King. My duty is to serve. You have chosen the new God over the Old Gods. May the Lord of Light watch over us all. Shall we drink together?

author: davos
content: Don't.

author: cressen
content: A cup of wine to honor the one true God.

author: melisandre
content: The night is dark and full of terrors, old man, but the fire burns them all away. Your Grace.

author: jaime lannister
content: King in the North. I keep expecting you to leave me in one castle or another for safekeeping, but you drag me along from camp to camp. Have you grown fond of me, Stark? Is that it? I've never seen you with a girl.

author: robb stark
content: If I left you with one of my bannermen, your father would know within a fortnight, and my bannerman would receive a raven with a message, "Release my son and you'll be rich beyond your dreams. Refuse and your house will be destroyed, root and stem.”

author: jaime lannister
content: You don't trust the loyalty of the men following you into battle?

author: robb stark
content: Oh, I trust them with my life. Just not with yours.

author: jaime lannister
content: Smart boy. What's wrong? Don't like being called ‘boy'? Insulted?

author: robb stark
content: You insult yourself, Kingslayer. You've been defeated by a boy.

author: robb stark
content: You're held captive by a boy. Perhaps you'll be killed by a boy. . Stannis Baratheon sent ravens to all the high lords of Westeros. King Joffrey Baratheon is neither a true king nor a true Baratheon. . He's your bastard son.

author: jaime lannister
content: If that's true, Stannis is the rightful king. How convenient for him.

author: robb stark
content: My father learned the truth. That's why you had him executed.

author: jaime lannister
content: I was your prisoner when Ned Stark lost his head.

author: robb stark
content: Your son killed him so the world wouldn't learn who fathered him. And you... you pushed my brother from a window because he saw you with the queen.

author: jaime lannister
content: You have proof? Or do you want to trade gossip like a couple of fishwives?

author: robb stark
content: I'm sending one of your cousins down to King's Landing with my peace terms.

author: jaime lannister
content: You think my father's going to negotiate with you? You don't know him very well.

author: robb stark
content: No, but he's starting to know me.

author: jaime lannister
content: Three victories don't make you a conqueror.

author: robb stark
content: It's better than three defeats.

author: shae
content: This city stinks Like dead bodies.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A bit corpsey, yes.

author: shae
content: And shit.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I thought you wanted to come here.

author: shae
content: I love it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You love the smell of dead bodies and shit?

author: shae
content: And cum and garlic and rum.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You can smell cum from the balcony?

author: shae
content: I love the stink. I love the noise. Cities make me want to fuck.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And so did the country.

author: shae
content: This is where I belong.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, well, you need to be careful. No one can know you're here.

author: shae
content: No one will know.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You can't trust anyone in King's Landing. They're all liars; good liars, bad liars, one or two great liars.

author: shae
content: What about you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Me? I'm not from here. I'm a slave to the truth.

author: shae
content: Truth? You are the biggest little liar I have ever met.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why do you think I am so little? I'm being, , crushed beneath the weight of all that truth.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ned Stark actually slept on this, as if the poor man didn't suffer enough. One of the many changes we'll have to make around here.

author: cersei lannister
content: Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: I wonder if I might ask you for a favor.

author: petyr baelish
content: Of course, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Ned Stark's youngest daughter Arya... we can't seem to locate her.

author: petyr baelish
content: If she's escaped the capital, Winterfell seems the logical destination.

author: cersei lannister
content: And yet my friends in the North report no sign of her.

author: petyr baelish
content: Curious.

author: cersei lannister
content: If we choose to negotiate with the Starks, the girl has some value. Whoever finds her, well, you know what they say about Lannisters and debts.

author: petyr baelish
content: Well, you could ask Varys where she is. He'll have an answer for you. Whether you believe it,,, Myself, I have always had a hard time trusting eunuchs. Who knows what they want?

author: cersei lannister
content: A mockingbird. . You created your own Sigil, didn't you?

author: petyr baelish
content: Yes.

author: cersei lannister
content: Appropriate for a self-made man with so many songs to sing.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm glad you like it. Some people are fortunate enough to be born into the right family. Others have to find their own way.

author: cersei lannister
content: I heard a song once about a boy of modest means who found his way into the home of a very prominent family. He loved the eldest daughter. Sadly, she had eyes for another.

author: petyr baelish
content: When boys and girls live in the same home, awkward situations can arise. Sometimes, I've heard, even brothers and sisters develop certain affections. And when these affections become common knowledge, well, that is an awkward situation, indeed. Especially in a prominent family. But prominent families often forget a simple truth, I've found.

author: cersei lannister
content: And which truth is that?

author: petyr baelish
content: Knowledge is power.

author: cersei lannister
content: Seize him. . Cut his throat. . Stop. Wait. I've changed my mind. Let him go. . Step back three paces. Turn around. Close your eyes. . Power is power. Do see if you can take some time away from your coins and your whores to locate the Stark girl for me. I would very much appreciate it.

author: robb stark
content: You're Ser Alton Lannister?

author: alton
content: I am, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: I offer your cousins peace if they meet my terms. First, your family must release my sisters. Second, my father's bones must be returned to us so he may rest beside his brother and sister in the crypts beneath Winterfell. And the remains of all those who died in his service must also be returned. Their families can honor them with proper funerals.

author: alton
content: An honorable request, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: Third... Joffrey and the Queen Regent must renounce all claim to dominion of the North. From this time, till the end of time, we are a free and independent kingdom.

author: ser rodrik
content: The King in the North.

author: others at table
content: King in the North.

author: robb stark
content: Neither Joffrey nor any of his men shall set foot in our lands again. If he disregards this command, he shall suffer the same fate as my father, only I don't need a servant to do my beheading for me.

author: alton
content: These are... Your Grace, these are...

author: robb stark
content: These are my terms. If the Queen Regent and her son meet them, I'll give them peace. If not, I will litter the south with Lannister dead.

author: alton
content: King Joffrey is a Baratheon, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: Oh, is he? You'll ride at daybreak, Ser Alton. That will be all for tonight.

author: theon greyjoy
content: A word, Your Grace?

author: robb stark
content: You don't have to call me ‘Your Grace' when no one's around.

author: theon greyjoy
content: It's not so bad once you get used to it.

author: robb stark
content: I'm glad someone's gotten used to it.

She cried, often. I asked her why but, we didn't have the kind of rapport that you and I have. Yes, it was quite sad. Girls from Elysium pleasure houses are expensive. Extremely expensive. And this one wasn't making me any money. I hate bad investments. Really, I do. They haunt me. I had no idea how to make her happy, no idea how to mitigate my losses. A very wealthy patron, he offered me a tremendous amount of money to let him transform this lovely, sad girl. To use her in ways that never occur to most men. And you know what occurs to most men. I would not say he succeeded in making her happy but my losses were definitely mitigated. . Take tonight off to mourn Mhaegen's child. I'll see you tomorrow. But you'll be happy? .
