content: There's a ship leaving for East Watch by the sea tonight. From there, I'm afraid it's rather a long walk to Castle Black. I hope you enjoy the Wall. I found it surprisingly beautiful, in a brutal, horribly uncomfortable sort of way.

author: bronn
content: The lads will escort you. The streets aren't safe at night, my lord.

author: janos
content: These men are under my command. . I command you to arrest this cutthroat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: His name is Bronn... and he is the new commander of the City Watch.

author: bronn
content: Boys?

author: janos
content: I have friends at court! Powerful friends! The king himself made me a lord!

author: tyrion lannister
content: To the new Commander.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If I told you to murder, an infant girl say, still at her mother's breast, would you do it without question?

author: bronn
content: Without question? No. I'd ask how much.

author: lommy
content: If they come back, I say we yield. Gendry's the one they want. I don't want to get caught in the middle of a battle.

author: hot pie
content: I'm not afraid of no battles.

author: arya stark
content: If you got within a mile of a battle, you'd fill your pants.

author: hot pie
content: I've seen lots of battles. I saw -

author: arya stark
content: Liar.

author: hot pie
content: I saw a man kill another man just outside a tavern in Flea Bottom. Stabbed him right in the neck.

author: lommy
content: Two men fighting isn't a battle.

author: hot pie
content: They had armor on.

author: arya stark
content: So?

author: hot pie
content: So, if they got armor on, it's a battle.

author: lommy
content: No, it isn't.

author: hot pie
content: What's a dyer's apprentice know about battles anyway?

author: arya stark
content: Gendry's an armorer's apprentice. Hot Pie, tell Gendry what makes it a battle.

author: hot pie
content: It's when they've got armor on.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Now who told you that.

author: hot pie
content: A knight?

author: gendry baratheon
content: How'd you know he was a knight?

author: hot pie
content: Well, cause he got armor on.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You don't have to be a knight to have armor. Any idiot can buy armor. .

author: hot pie
content: How'd you know?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Cause I sold armor.

author: arya stark
content: What do the gold cloaks want with you?

author: gendry baratheon
content: No idea.

author: arya stark
content: You're a liar.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You shouldn't insult people that are bigger than you.

author: arya stark
content: Then I wouldn't get to insult anyone. .

author: gendry baratheon
content: Well, I don't care what any of them want. No goodo s ever come of their questions.

author: arya stark
content: No goodo s ever come? Who asked questions before?

author: gendry baratheon
content: How can someone so small be such a huge pain in my ass?

author: arya stark
content: Who asked questions?

author: gendry baratheon
content: The Hand of the King. Er, hands of the King. Lord Arryn came first, a few weeks before he died. And then Lord Stark came, a few weeks before he died.

author: arya stark
content: Lord Stark.

author: gendry baratheon
content: See? Asking me questions is bad luck. . You'll probably be dead soon.

author: arya stark
content: What did they ask about?

author: gendry baratheon
content: My mom.

author: arya stark
content: Who's your mom?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Just my mom. Worked in a tavern. Died when I was little.

author: arya stark
content: And who was your father?

author: gendry baratheon
content: He could be one of those gold-hatted bastards, for all I know. What about you, anyway? You thought they were after you, why? Did you kill someone, or is it just because you're a girl?

author: arya stark
content: I'm not a girl!

author: gendry baratheon
content: Yes you are. You think I'm as stupid as the rest of them?

author: arya stark
content: Stupider. Night's Watch doesn't take girls, everyone knows that.

author: gendry baratheon
content: That's true. You're still a girl.

author: arya stark
content: I am not!

author: gendry baratheon
content: Well, pull your cock out and take a piss then.

author: arya stark
content: I don't need to take a piss… Lommy and Hot Pie can't know. No one can know.

author: gendry baratheon
content: They won't. Not from me.

author: arya stark
content: My name's not Arry. It's Arya. Of House Stark. Yoren is taking me home to Winterfell.

author: gendry baratheon
content: He was your father. The Hand. The traitor.

author: arya stark
content: He was never a traitor! Joffrey is a liar.

author: gendry baratheon
content: So you're a highborn, then. You're a lady.

author: arya stark
content: No. I mean yes. My mother was a lady, and my sister -

author: gendry baratheon
content: You were a lordo s daughter and you lived in a castle. Look, all that about cocks. I should never have said that. I've been pissing in front of you and everything. I should be calling you milady.

author: arya stark
content: Do not call me milady.

author: gendry baratheon
content: As milady commands. . Well, that was unladylike.

author: man
content: What you carrying?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Pears and oranges. Wine from the Arbor. And the heir to Pyke of the Iron Islands. . The only living son of Balon Greyjoy. . Me.

author: man
content: Don't like wine. Woman's drink. .

author: theon greyjoy
content: I need to get to Pyke.

author: man
content: I'll find you a horse.

author: yara greyjoy
content: I'm heading that way. I can take you there.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I bet you can.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You been at sea long? Or were there just no women where you came from?

author: theon greyjoy
content: None like you.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You don't know what I'm like.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You don't know what you're like. You need someone to teach you. Know who I am?

author: yara greyjoy
content: You think I offer free rides to every man in jewelry. Lord Greyjoy.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Have my things sent up to the castle.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You should give me the reins, I'm a better rider than you. I've been on horseback for the last nine years.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Nine years. Do you still know your way around a ship? Have these hands ever touched a rope?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Don't you worry about my hands. . The sea's in my blood.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Your blood will be in the sea if I don't watch where I'm going.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I have a proposal for my father. One that will make him king again. And me after him. You may stay at the castle tonight, if you're lucky.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Is that an offer from my future king?

author: theon greyjoy
content: An order, from your future king. You can tell your grandchildren about this night.

author: yara greyjoy
content: I don't imagine it will be a story fit for children.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Father.

author: balon
content: Nine years, is it? They took a frightened boy. What have they given back?

author: theon greyjoy
content: A man. Your blood and your heir.

author: balon
content: We shall see. Stark had you longer than I did.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Lord Stark is gone.

author: balon
content: And how do you feel about that?

author: theon greyjoy
content: What's done is done. I've brought you a proposal from Robb Stark.

author: balon
content: Who gave you those clothes? . Was it Ned Stark's pleasure to make you his daughter?

author: theon greyjoy
content: If my clothes offend you, I will change them.

author: balon
content: It will. . That bauble around your neck. Did you pay the iron price for it or the gold? . I asked a question. Did you pull it from the neck of a corpse you made or did you buy it to match your fine clothes? Iron or gold?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Gold.

author: balon
content: I'll not have my son dressed as a whore. . My fears have come true. The Starks have made you theirs.

author: theon greyjoy
content: My blood is salt and iron.

author: balon
content: Yet, , the Stark boy sends you to me like a trained raven, clutching his message.

author: theon greyjoy
content: The offer he makes, is one I proposed.

author: balon
content: He heeds your counsel?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I've lived with him, hunted with him, fought at his side, he thinks of me as a brother.

author: balon
content: No, not here, , not in my hearing, you will not name him brother. This son of the man who put your true brothers to the sword. Or have you forgotten your own blood?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I forget nothing. I remember my brothers. And I remember when my father was a king.

author: balon
content: I see. I destroy Robb Stark's enemies for him and he will make me King of the Iron Islands once again.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I will lead the attack myself.

author: balon
content: Oh, you will?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm your son. Your only living heir. Who else?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I told you to wait outside. . How did you get past the guards?

author: yara greyjoy
content: Anything with a cock is easy to fool.

author: balon
content: My dear.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yara?

author: yara greyjoy
content: So good to see you, brother. This is a homecoming I'll tell my grandchildren about.

author: theon greyjoy
content: She can't lead an attack!

author: balon
content: And why not?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're a woman!

author: yara greyjoy
content: You're the one in skirts.

author: balon
content: This isn't Winterfell, boy. Your sister took over command of your eldest brother's ship after your new father killed him.

author: all three
content: What's dead may never die.

author: balon
content: No man gives me a crown. I pay the iron price. I will take my crown. . That is who I am. That is who we have always been.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You won't stand a chance against the Lannisters on your own.

author: balon
content: Who said anything about the Lannisters?

author: davos
content: You'll have your gold when we take the treasury at King's Landing.

author: saan
content: All these kings fighting for the throne, and this Stannis has the smallest army. Why would I bet on the man with the worst chance?

author: davos
content: Because you're a smart gambler. Stannis has proved himself in war. Twice. His baby brother has never set foot on a battlefield. Neither has the false king, Joffrey.

author: saan
content: And yet, they both have larger armies.

author: davos
content: Stannis has just begun the fight. His bannermen will rally to his cause. There's no man in the Seven Kingdoms more honorable than Stannis Baratheon. Or more worthy of loyalty.

author: saan
content: What is the world coming to when smugglers must vouch for the honor of kings.

author: matthos
content: Mind your words, pirate. .

author: davos
content: Matthos.

author: saan
content: You think I'm insulted? I am a pirate. I'm an excellent pirate. I don't sail for promises.

author: davos
content: Of course you do. Every time you leave harbor, you're leaving on a promise. A promise that somewhere on the seas, somebody's got some gold and you can take it from them.

author: saan
content: That's a promise that always comes true.

author: davos
content: As is mine. You're not the young man, Salladhor. And correct me if I'm wrong

author: saan
content: Only the clever ones.

author: davos
content: You want to spend your last few years on the sea, stealing from Pentoshi cheesemongers and Midanese silk merchants, then go. They're out there waiting for you. That's easy. What I'm offering you is hard. Come with me and plunder the greatest city in Westeros. You'll be the richest man in Lysene. And the most famous. They'll be singing songs about you as long as men have voices to sing.

author: saan
content: Salladhor Saan is a good name for songs.

author: davos
content: It is. .

author: saan
content: One thing, I want the queen.

author: davos
content: The queen?

author: saan
content: Cersei, I want her. I'll sail with your fleet, all 30 of my ships, and if we don't drown at the bottom of Blackwater Bay, I will fuck this blonde queen and I will fuck her well.

author: matthos
content: This war isn't about you. We're not attacking King's Landing so that you can rape the queen.

author: saan
content: I'm not going to rape her, I'm going to fuck her.

author: matthos
content: As if she would just let you!

author: saan
content: You don't know how persuasive I am. I never tried to fuck you.

author: matthos
content: Stannis is the rightful king, and the Lord of Light. The one true god.

author: saan
content: I've been all over the world, my boy, and everywhere I go, people tell me about the true god. They all think they found the right one. The one true god is what's between a woman's legs, and better yet a queen's legs.

author: saan
content: I never thought you'd have a true believer for a son.

author: davos
content: He's young yet. I promise you the gold. I promise you the glory. I cannot promise you the queen.

author: matthos
content: You believe your king can win?

author: davos
content: He is the one true king.

author: saan
content: You Westerosee are funny people. A man chops off your fingers and you fall in love with him. . I'll sail with you, Davos Seaworth. You are the most honest smuggler I ever met. Make me rich.

author: davos
content: Get me to the gates of King's Landing and I will.

author: matthos
content: When will the King have a sail?

author: davos
content: As soon as his God wills it.

author: matthos
content: He's my God too, and yours. But you were too blind to see. . Let me teach you how to read.

author: davos
content: Oh you and your mother.

author: matthos
content: It won't take long. You already know the letters. The holy books are much more persuasive than I can be.

author: davos
content: I wish I had a God, truly! I'm not mocking you, but I've seen men pray to every God there is. Pray for wind, pray for rain, pray for home. None of it works!

author: matthos
content: But you always came home.

author: davos
content: I wasn't praying.

author: matthos
content: But I was. Every night that you were at sea, I lit a candle and I prayed, for you.

author: davos
content: You want me to have a god, fine. King Stannis is my god. He raised me up and blessed me with his trust. He gave you a future I could never have imagined. You know how to read, you'll be a knight someday. You think your fire god commanded all that? It was Stannis. Only Stannis.

author: matthos
content: Stannis is my king, but he's only a man.

author: davos
content: Don't tell him that.

author: cersei lannister
content: Lord Janos Slynt was Commander of the City Watch. You had no right to exile him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I have every right. I am the King's Hand.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're serving as the King's Hand until father gets here. I am Queen Regent.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Listen to me, Queen Regent, you're losing the people. Do you hear me?

author: cersei lannister
content: Ha, the people. You think I care?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You might find it difficult to rule over millions who want you dead. Half the city will starve when winter comes. The other half will plot to overthrow you. And your gold-plated thugs just gave them the rallying cry, “The Queen slaughters babies.” . You don't even have the decency to deny it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It wasn't you who gave the order, was it? Joffrey didn't even tell you. Or did he tell you? I imagine that would be even worse.

author: cersei lannister
content: He did what needed to be done. . You want to be the Hand of the King? You want to rule? This is what ruling is! Lying on a bed of weeds, ripping them out by the root one by one before they strangle you in your sleep.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm no king, but I think there's more to ruling that that.

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't care what you think! You've never taken it seriously. You haven't, Jaime hasn't. . It's all fallen on me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: As has Jaime repeatedly, according to Stannis Baratheon.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're funny. . You've always been funny. But none of your jokes will ever match the first one, will they? You remember... back when you ripped my mother open on your way out of her and she bled to death.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She was my mother too.

author: cersei lannister
content: Now they're gone, for the sake of you. There's no bigger joke in the world than that. .

author: davos
content: Your Grace.

author: matthos
content: Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: How did it fare with your pirate?

author: davos
content: Salladhor Saan will join our fleet. 30 ships. His men know how to fight.

author: stannis baratheon
content: In my experience, pirates prefer fighting unarmed men.

author: davos
content: Does seem the wiser choice.

author: stannis baratheon
content: It won't be a choice this time. Do you trust him?

author: davos
content: Salladhor Saan is an old friend, I've known him 30 years. I've never trusted him.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Well if he does his job, he'll have his share. Leave us.

author: davos
content: At once, Your Grace.

author: melisandre
content: The Lord of Light shines through you, young warrior.

author: davos
content: Come.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What did you say to him?

author: melisandre
content: I told him death by fire is the purest death.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Why?

author: melisandre
content: Because it is true. You're troubled my king.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Yeah.

author: melisandre
content: These armies are but toys for the Lord of Light.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Tell your lord to burn them then.

author: melisandre
content: I tell him nothing! I pray for his commands and I obey.

author: stannis baratheon
content: My little brother has a hundred thousand men according to the scouts. Men whose allegiance rightly belongs to me.

author: melisandre
content: You must have faith.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Faith? In a real war, the side with the greater number wins nine times out of ten.

author: melisandre
content: Then we must be the ten.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I cannot defeat my brother in the field, and I can't take King's Landing without the men he stole.

author: melisandre
content: I have seen the path to victory in the flames. At first, you must give yourself to the Lord of Light.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I've said the words, damn you! I burnt the idols.

author: melisandre
content: You must give... all of yourself.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I have a wife. I took a vow.

author: melisandre
content: She's sick. Weak. Shut away in the tower. And she disgusts you. And she's given you nothing. No sons. Only stillborns. Only death. . I will give you a son, my King.

author: stannis baratheon
content: A son?

author: craster
content: Out, all of you.

author: craster
content: This bastardo s been meddling where he shouldn't!

author: craster
content: I want you and your men gone. And you will make this right.

author: jeor
content: Wait outside.

author: jon snow
content: Lord Commander-

author: jeor
content: Now!

author: sam
content: Lord Commander-

author: jeor
content: Leave us.

content: What did you do?

author: jon snow
content: I followed him. He took the baby into the woods, the newborn.

author: jeor
content: What business is that of yours?

author: jon snow
content: No, you don't understand. He's killing them, all the boys...

author: jon snow
content: You know.

author: jeor
content: Wildlings serve crueler gods than you or I. Those boys are Craster's offerings.

author: jon snow
content: Offerings? He's murdering his own children. He's a monster.

author: jeor
content: Aye, many a time that monster has been the difference between life and death for our rangers, your uncle among them. We have other wars to fight, out there. Like it or not, we need men like Craster.

author: jon snow
content: I... I saw it. I saw... something take that child.

author: jeor
content: Yeah. Whatever it was, I daresay you'll see it again. Now, ready my horse. We leave at dawn.

author: jeor
content: Don't lose it again.

author: sam
content: Gilly.

author: gilly
content: You're leaving.

author: sam
content: I, I wanted to give you something. It belonged to my mother.

author: gilly
content: I can't take it.

author: sam
content: Please. I want you to. My mother used it for sewing. She'd let me sit with her in her chamber while she sewed and I'd read to her. My father put a stop to it when he found out. It's the only thing I have of hers. She gave it to me before I left for the Wall.

author: gilly
content: You, you shouldn't give it away.

author: sam
content: I'm not giving it away. I'm giving it to you.

author: sam
content: Keep it safe for me. Til I come back.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: luwin
content: Hodor. Rouse Bran, will you? It's time for his lessons.

author: bran stark
content: Every night it's the same.

author: bran stark
content: I'm walking and running, but I'm not I'm not me. I'm running through the godswood, sniffing the dirt, tasting blood in my mouth when I've made a fresh kill, howling. Old Nan used to tell me stories about magical people who could live inside stags, birds, wolves.

author: luwin
content: That's exactly what they are, Bran - stories.

author: bran stark
content: So she was lying? They don't exist?

author: luwin
content: Well, they may have done. But they're gone from the world, along with much else. These are dreams, Bran, nothing more.

author: bran stark
content: No, my dreams are different. Mine are true. I dreamt of my father dying. And Rickon had the same dream.

author: luwin
content: What about all the dreams you had that didn't come true? Hmm? Right.

author: luwin
content: This link is made of Valyrian steel. Only one maester in a hundred wears it on his chain. It signifies that I have studied the higher mysteries. And all who study these mysteries try their hand at spells. I was no different. I was young. And what boy doesn't secretly wish for hidden powers to lift him out of his dull life into a special one? But in the end, for all my efforts, I got no more out of it than a thousand boys before me. Come on.

author: luwin
content: All right. Maybe magic once was a mighty force in the world. But not anymore. The dragons are gone. The giants are dead. And the Children of the Forest forgotten.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Loras! Highgarden!

author: man
content: Get him!

author: crowd
content: Oh!

author: loras
content: Yield! I yield.

author: renly
content: Well fought. Approach.

author: renly
content: Rise. Remove your helm.

author: renly
content: You are all your father promised and more, my lady. I've seen Ser Loras bested once or twice, but never quite in that fashion.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Now, now, my love. My brother fought valiantly for you.

author: renly
content: That he did, my queen. But there can only be one champion. Brienne of Tarth, you may ask anything of me you desire. If it is within my power, it is yours.

author: brienne
content: Your Grace, I ask the honor of a place in your Kingsguard.

author: loras
content: What?

author: brienne
content: I will be one of your seven, pledge my life to yours, and keep you safe from all harm.

author: renly
content: Done. Rise, Brienne of the Kingsguard.

author: colen
content: Your Grace, I have the honor to bring you Lady Catelyn Stark, sent as an envoy by her son Robb, Lord of Winterfell.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord of Winterfell and King in the North.

author: renly
content: Lady Catelyn. I'm pleased to see you. May I present my wife, Margaery of House Tyrell?

author: margaery tyrell
content: You are very welcome here, Lady Stark. I'm so sorry for your loss.

author: catelyn stark
content: You are most kind.

author: renly
content: My lady, I swear to you I will see the Lannisters answer for your husbando s murder. When I take King's Landing, I'll bring you Joffrey's head.

author: catelyn stark
content: It will be enough to know that justice was done, my lord.

author: brienne
content: Your Grace. And you should kneel when you approach the King.

author: renly
content: There's no need for that. Lady Stark is an honored guest.

author: loras
content: Has your son marched against Tywin Lannister yet?

author: catelyn stark
content: I do not sit on my son's war councils. And if I did, I would not share his strategies with you.

author: loras
content: If Robb Stark wants a pact with us, he should come himself, not hide behind his mother's skirts.

author: catelyn stark
content: My son is fighting a war, not playing at one.

author: renly
content: Don't worry, my lady. Our war is just beginning.

author: gerard
content: Your Grace.

author: renly
content: Gerard. How's your foot?

author: gerard
content: Better, Your Grace.

author: gerard
content: They don't know their own size is all.

author: renly
content: Good man.

author: renly
content: I have a hundred thousand men at my command. All the might of the Stormlands and the Reach.

author: catelyn stark
content: And all of them young and bold like your Knight of Flowers? It's a game to you, isn't it? I pity them.

author: renly
content: Why?

author: catelyn stark
content: Because it won't last. Because they are the knights of summer and winter is coming.

author: renly
content: Brienne, escort Lady Catelyn to her tent. She's tired from her journey.

author: brienne
content: At once, Your Grace. Shall I return after?

author: renly
content: That won't be necessary. I would pray awhile. Alone.

author: brienne
content: If you'll follow me, my lady.

author: catelyn stark
content: You fought bravely today, Lady Brienne.

author: brienne
content: I fought for my king. Soon I'll fight for him on the battlefield. Die for him if I must. And, if it please you, Brienne's enough. I'm no lady.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What are you doing here?

author: yara greyjoy
content: I live here. Are you angry with me, brother?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You lying bitch.

author: yara greyjoy
content: It's not my fault you didn't recognize me.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Recognize you? How could I? The last time I saw you- you looked like a fat little boy.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You were a fat little boy, too, but I recognized you.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Why didn't you tell me?

author: yara greyjoy
content: I wanted to see who you were first. And I did.

author: balon
content: The plans are made. It's time you heard them.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Father.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Father.

author: balon
content: The wolf pup has gone south with the entirety of the Northern army at his back. While he's tangling with the lion in the Westerlands, the North is ripe for the taking. The Ironborn will reave and pillage, as it was in the old days, all along the northern coast. We'll spread our dominion across the green lands, securing the Neck and everything above. Every stronghold will yield to us, one by one. Winterfell may defy us for a year, but what of it? The rest shall be ours, forest, field, and hall.

author: balon
content: Yara, my daughter, you'll take thirty longships to attack Deepwood Motte.

author: yara greyjoy
content: I've always wanted a castle.

author: theon greyjoy
content: And what's my role in all this?

author: balon
content: You'll take a ship to raid the fishing villages on the Stoney Shore.

author: theon greyjoy
content: A ship? You give her thirty and I get one?

author: yara greyjoy
content: The Sea Bitch. We thought she'd be perfect for you.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm to fight fishermen?

author: yara greyjoy
content: Be careful of their nets.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Father, I fought with Robb Stark. I know his men. He won't give up the North so easily.

author: yara greyjoy
content: They won't even know we're there until it's too late.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What do you know of it, woman? I'm a proven warrior.

author: balon
content: Your brothers were warriors, both of them dead at the hands of those you seem so eager to protect.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm not protecting anyone. I just wonder if it's not wiser to wait. Why risk going against the North if they would be our allies? Rise up against them and they could destroy us. But if we pledge fealty to them, they'll give us Casterly Rock.

author: balon
content: What are our words? Our words?

author: theon greyjoy
content: We do not sow.

author: balon
content: We do not sow. We are Ironborn. We're not subjects. We're not slaves. We do not plow the fields or toil in the mine. We take what is ours. Your time with the wolves has made you weak.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You act as if I volunteered to go. You gave me away, if you remember. The day you bent the knee to Robert Baratheon. After he crushed you. Did you take what was yours then?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You gave me away!

author: theon greyjoy
content: Your boy! Your last boy! You gave me away like I was some dog you didn't want anymore. And now you curse me because I've come home.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You'd have our father bow down to your other family?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I have no other family.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Don't you? Make your choice, Theon, and do it quickly. Our ships sail with or without you.

author: shae
content: You won't let me leave this room. You won't let me-

author: tyrion lannister
content: Keep your voice down.

author: shae
content: Why? You think your father can hear me? He's three hundred miles away!

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't intend for you to stay here. I might be able to bring you into the castle kitchens.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Again, only temporary.

author: shae
content: Every man who has tasted my cooking has told me what a good whore I am.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But you wouldn't be a cook. You'd pose as a scullion.

author: shae
content: Scullion? What is a scullion?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Kitchen wench.

author: shae
content: A kitchen wench?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, but-

author: shae
content: Cleaning pots? Is that how my lion wants to see me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your lion wants to see you alive. We've come to a dangerous place. My sister wants to hurt me. She'll look for any weakness she can find. She can't know about you.

author: shae
content: I'm the weakness?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's a compliment, my lady.

author: shae
content: How is being a weakness a compliment?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Language can be a bit tricky here.

author: shae
content: Oh, I'm too stupid to understand. The stupid foreign girl. I am not a kitchen wench.

author: myrcella
content: When will Joffrey and Sansa be married?

author: cersei lannister
content: Soon, darling, when the war is over.

author: myrcella
content: Mother says I'll have a new gown for the ceremony and another for the feast. But yours will be ivory, since you're the bride.

author: cersei lannister
content: The princess just spoke to you.

author: sansa stark
content: Pardon, Your Grace. I'm sure your dress will be beautiful, Myrcella. I'm counting the days until the fighting is done and I can pledge my love to the King in sight of the gods.

author: tommen lannister
content: Is Joffrey going to kill Sansa's brother?

author: cersei lannister
content: He might.

author: cersei lannister
content: Would you like that?

author: tommen lannister
content: No. I don't think so.

author: cersei lannister
content: Even if he does, Sansa will do her duty. Won't you, little dove?

author: sansa stark
content: Come in.

author: sansa stark
content: Who are you?

author: shae
content: I'm Shae, my lady. Your new handmaiden.

author: sansa stark
content: I didn't know I needed a new handmaiden. You're not from here.

author: shae
content: No.

author: sansa stark
content: What are you doing?

author: shae
content: Waiting for you to tell me what to do.

author: sansa stark
content: I shouldn't have to tell you to do things. You should just do them.

author: shae
content: What things?

author: sansa stark
content: Change my linens, wash my clothing, scrub the floor, empty my chamber pot, brush my hair.

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: shae
content: You said to brush your-

author: sansa stark
content: Not now.

author: shae
content: Your chamber pot is empty.

author: sansa stark
content: Clean the table.

author: sansa stark
content: Have you ever been a handmaiden before?

author: shae
content: Yes.

author: sansa stark
content: For whom?

author: shae
content: Lady Zuriff.

author: sansa stark
content: Lady Zuriff

author: sansa stark
content: There is no Lady Zuriff in this city.

author: shae
content: She wasn't in this city.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't know how they did things in that city, but in this city, handmaidens wait on ladies, not the other way around. And I don't have time to answer a thousand questions and teach you how to do your job.

author: shae
content: Do you want me to leave?

author: sansa stark
content: Just brush my hair.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh! Thank the gods. I haven't had a proper shit in six days.

author: pycelle
content: I've encountered this problem before, my lord. The stresses of power often have this insalubrious effect. Two drops with water, daily.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Right. I'm so grateful to have a man of your vast knowledge and wisdom on my side.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Please.

author: pycelle
content: Thank you, my lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can trust you, Pycelle, can I not?

author: pycelle
content: Why, yes, of course, my lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: These are perilous times. And the crown must forge new alliances. And these alliances must often be sealed in matrimony.

author: pycelle
content: Matrimony, huh? Yes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm trusting the council with these plans, but the Queen mustn't know. We can't have her meddling in affairs that could determine the future of the realm. There's too much at stake.

author: pycelle
content: Oh, yes, yes. Indeed, yes. I shall be silent as the grave.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm brokering an alliance with House Martell of Dorne. Princess Myrcella will wed their youngest son when she comes of age, ensuring their loyalty and their army, should we need it.

author: pycelle
content: Myrcella sent away to Dorne?

author: tyrion lannister
content: But remember, the Queen mustn't know.

author: varys
content: Ooh. "The Queen mustn't know." I love conversations that begin this way.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I plan to marry Princess Myrcella off to Theon Greyjoy.

author: varys
content: Theon Greyjoy? Forgive me, my lord, but how? He grew up a ward of Winterfell. He fights for Robb Stark.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Precisely.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Theon's father loathes the Starks and will convince the boy to come to our side. Greyjoy can destroy the Northern army from within and we can have his father's ships.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But remember, you must tell no one.

author: petyr baelish
content: Tell no one what?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I plan to wed Princess Myrcella to Robin Arryn of the Vale. Lysa is not fond of me. But perhaps the promise of a royal match will convince her to let bygones be bygones.

author: petyr baelish
content: She imprisoned you. She tried to execute you. And you offer her son a princess?

author: tyrion lannister
content: For men in our position, holding grudges can be an encumbrance, don't you think?

author: petyr baelish
content: And I suppose you want me to broker this agreement?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who better?

author: petyr baelish
content: Yes, I could sing this song to Lysa, if I cared to. What's in it for me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The gratitude of the people of Westeros for helping to end this war, the adoration of the King for bringing the Vale back into the fold... and Harrenhal.

author: petyr baelish
content: Harrenhal is cursed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Never took you for a superstitious man. By all means, tear it down and rebuild. You'll be able to afford it. I plan to make you Lord of the Riverlands.

author: petyr baelish
content: With a single stroke, you'd make me one of the greatest lords in the realm.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You served my family well in the matter of the succession.

author: petyr baelish
content: So did Janos Slynt, and he was given Harrenhal, too. Until you snatched it away.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I need you to deliver Lysa Arryn. I didn't need Janos Slynt. It's settled, then?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. Oh. And remember-

author: petyr baelish
content: The Queen mustn't know.

author: renly
content: That must hurt.

author: renly
content: What? What is it?

author: loras
content: A member of the Kingsguard? As if I wasn't humiliated enough already.

author: renly
content: Brienne is a very capable warrior.

author: renly
content: And she's devoted to me. You're jealous.

author: loras
content: Jealous? Of Brienne the Beauty? Don't make me laugh.

author: renly
content: I'll make it up to you.

author: loras
content: No, Your Grace. Not tonight. There's another Tyrell who requires your attention. You didn't win my father's support or his army on charm alone.

author: loras
content: Your vassals are starting to snigger behind your back. Brides aren't usually virgins two weeks after their wedding night.

author: renly
content: And Margaery's a virgin?

author: loras
content: Officially. Shall I bring her to you?

author: renly
content: I should warn you, I've had quite a bit of wine.

author: margaery tyrell
content: As is your right. You are a king.

author: renly
content: You look very beautiful.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Thank you, Your Grace.

author: renly
content: It's a lovely gown.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You think so? I can't decide how I like it better. This way, or this way.

author: renly
content: You certainly don't need it.

author: renly
content: Although, some say the beauty most desired is the beauty concealed.

author: renly
content: Must be the wine.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Here, let me.

author: renly
content: I'm sorry.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Do you want my brother to come in and help?

author: renly
content: What?

author: margaery tyrell
content: He could get you started. I know he wouldn't mind. Or I can turn over and you can pretend I'm him.

author: renly
content: I don't know what you're talking about.

author: margaery tyrell
content: There's no need for us to play games. Save your lies for court. You're going to need a lot of them.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Your enemies aren't happy about us. They want to tear us apart. And the best way to stop them is to put your baby in my belly. We can try again later. You decide how you want to do it, with me, with me and Loras, however else you like.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Whatever you need to do. You are a king.

author: cersei lannister
content: You monster. Myrcella is my only daughter. Do you really think I'll let you sell her like a common whore?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Myrcella's a princess. Some would say she was born for this.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not let you ship her off to Dorne as I was shipped off to Robert Baratheon.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Dorne is the safest place for her.

author: cersei lannister
content: Are you mad? The Martells loathe us.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's why we need to seduce them. We're going to need their support in the war your son started.

author: cersei lannister
content: She'll be a hostage.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A guest.

author: cersei lannister
content: You won't get away with this. You think the piece of paper Father gave you keeps you safe. Ned Stark had a piece of paper, too.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's done, Cersei.

author: cersei lannister
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You cannot stop it.

author: cersei lannister
content: No!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Just how safe do you think Myrcella is if this city falls? Do you want to see her raped, butchered like the Targaryen children? Make no mistake. They'll mount her pretty little head on a spike right beside yours.

author: cersei lannister
content: Get out! Get out!

author: priest
content: Theon of the House Greyjoy, you would this day consecrate your faith to the Drowned God?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I would.

author: drowned priest
content: Kneel.

author: drowned priest
content: Let Theon, your servant, be born again from the sea as you were. Bless him with salt. Bless him with stone. Bless him with steel.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What is dead may never die.

author: drowned priest
content: What is dead may never die. But rises again harder and stronger. Stand.

author: petyr baelish
content: I don't appreciate being made a fool of, dwarf. If Myrcella marries the Martell boy, she can't very well marry Robin Arryn, can she?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, afraid not. Sorry about that.

author: petyr baelish
content: And Harrenhal, I suppose that's off the table as well.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, I fear so. Sorry about that, too.

author: petyr baelish
content: Leave me out of your next deception.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, that's a shame. You were to be the centerpiece of my next deception. My brother Jaime rots in a Northern stockade. I would see him released. That's where you come in.

author: petyr baelish
content: Robb Stark will never release the Kingslayer.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, he won't. But his mother might. How would you like to see your beloved Cat again?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Find him?

author: bronn
content: Oh, aye. And he has company. Filthy old stoat. Almost hate to interrupt.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, you don't.

author: bronn
content: No, I don't.

author: pycelle
content: What is the meaning of this?

author: pycelle
content: No, please, please.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You disappoint me, Grand Maester.

author: pycelle
content: I am your loyal servant.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So loyal that you told the Queen about my plans to send Myrcella to Dorne.

author: pycelle
content: No! Never! It's a falsehood. I swear it. It wasn't me. Ah, Varys. It was Varys the Spider.

author: tyrion lannister
content: See, I told Varys that I was giving the Princess to the Greyjoys. I told Littlefinger that I planned to wed her to Robin Arryn. I told no one that I was offering her to the Dornish. No one but you.

author: pycelle
content: The eunuch has spies everywhere.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cut off his manhood and feed it to the goats.

author: pycelle
content: No, no, no.

author: timett
content: There are no goats, halfman.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, make do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How long have you been spying for my sister?

author: pycelle
content: All I did, I did for House Lannister. Always. Your lord father, ask him. I've always been his servant since the days of the Mad King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't like his beard.

author: pycelle
content: What? What?

author: pycelle
content: Oh, no. No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How many Hands have you betrayed, Pycelle? Eddard Stark? Jon Arryn?

author: pycelle
content: Oh, Lord Arryn, h-he knew. He, he knew the t-truth about, about, about the Queen. An-And he planned to act, to t-tell King Robert.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So you poisoned him?

author: pycelle
content: No. Never.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But you let him die, made sure he succumbed.

author: pycelle
content: Lannister, I always served Lannister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Get him out of my sight. Throw him in one of the black cells.

author: pycelle
content: Oh, no. No, no, no. No, please. Don't! You can't do this to me!

author: tyrion lannister
content: For your trouble.

author: varys
content: You'll be pleased to know our mutual friend is doing quite well in Lady Sansa's service.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. One of my better ideas.

author: varys
content: And it seems the Grand Maester has found his way into a black cell?

author: varys
content: Well played, My Lord Hand. But should I be worried? Janos Slynt, Pycelle - The Small Council grows smaller every day.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Council has a reputation for serving past Hands poorly. I don't mean to follow Ned Stark to the grave.

author: varys
content: Power is a curious thing, my lord. Are you fond of riddles?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why, am I about to hear one?

author: varys
content: Three great men sit in a room. A king, a priest and a rich man. Between them stands a common sellsword. Each great man bids the sellsword kill the other two. Who lives, who dies?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Depends on the sellsword.

author: varys
content: Does it? He has neither crown nor gold nor favor with the gods.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He has a sword, the power of life and death.

author: varys
content: But if it's swordsmen who rule, why do we pretend kings hold all the power? When Ned Stark lost his head, who was truly responsible? Joffrey? The executioner? Or something else?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I've decided I don't like riddles.

author: varys
content: Power resides where men believe it resides. It's a trick, a shadow on the wall. And a very small man can cast a very large shadow.

author: yoren
content: You should be sleeping. Tomorrow's a long march. Thirty miles, if it don't piss on us.

author: arya stark
content: I can't sleep.

author: arya stark
content: I don't like the taste.

author: yoren
content: Well... You don't drink it for the flavor, to be honest.

author: yoren
content: What?

author: arya stark
content: How do you sleep?

author: yoren
content: Same as most men, I think.

author: arya stark
content: But you've seen things, horrible things.

author: yoren
content: Aye. I've seen some pretty things, too, but not nearly so many.

author: arya stark
content: How do you sleep when you... when you have those things in your head?

author: yoren
content: You didn't see that. I made damn sure.

author: arya stark
content: I close my eyes and I see them up there. All of them standing there. Joffrey, the Queen and... and my sister.

author: yoren
content: You know, we've got something in common, me and you. You know that? I must have been a couple of years older than you. I saw my brother stabbed through the heart right on our doorstep. He weren't much of a villain what skewered him. Willem, the lado s name was. He ran off before anyone could spit. And I just stood there, watching my brother die. Here's the funny part. I can't picture my brother's face anymore. But Willem, oh, he was a nice-looking boy. He had good white teeth, blue eyes, one of those dimpled chins all the girls like. I would think about him when I was working, when I was drinking, when I was having a shit. It got to the point where I would say his name every night before I went to bed. Willem. Willem. Willem. A prayer almost. Well, one day, Willem came riding back into town. I buried an ax so deep into Willem's skull, they had to bury him with it. Willem's horse got me to the Wall and I've been wearing black ever since. Well... That'll help you sleep, eh?

author: yoren
content: Ho! Get up, you lazy sons of whores! Arm yourselves.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Get up.

author: arya stark
content: Get up.

author: yoren
content: Keep out of sight, both of you.

author: arya stark
content: No, I'm not afraid.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I can fight.

author: yoren
content: Keep out of sight. If things go wrong, you run. Do you hear me? You run along north and don't look back.

author: yoren
content: Hey, there's men out there who want to fuck your corpses. Outside, now!

author: man
content: Come on, move, move!

author: guard
content: It's got to be the Mountain. He's the biggest. He's the strongest.

author: rennick
content: Bulls are bigger than lions. Doesn't mean I'd pick a bull in a fight.

author: guard
content: If the bull had fangs and claws, I would. Right, the Mountain or our man Jaime.

author: rennick
content: If he ever gets out.

author: guard
content: Loras Tyrell?

author: rennick
content: Loras Tyrell. He's prettier than the Queen.

author: guard
content: I don't care about pretty. He's better with a sword than any of them.

author: rennick
content: How good could he be? He's been stabbing Renly Baratheon for years, and Renly ain't dead.

author: rennick
content: The horses seem a little spooked to you? They're horses.

author: guard
content: They get spooked by their own shadows.

author: rennick
content: Shh. Do you hear that?

author: guard
content: No.

author: rennick
content: There's something out there.

author: guard
content: Oh. Oh, you're a right little prick. You should see your face.

author: rennick
content: I swear you pissed yourself. "Oh, who goes there? Ahh!"

author: guard
content: There is something out there.

author: rennick
content: Yeah, don't even try me.

author: guard
content: Rennick.

author: rennick
content: Do you think I'm an idiot?

author: guard
content: Rennick!

author: man
content: King in the North!

author: men
content: The King in the North!

author: roose bolton
content: Five Lannisters dead for every one of ours. They're dead. Take everything they've got. We've nowhere to keep all these prisoners. Barely enough food to feed our own.

author: robb stark
content: We're not executing prisoners, Lord Bolton.

author: roose bolton
content: Of course, Your Grace. The officers will be useful. Some of them may be privy to Tywin Lannister's plans.

author: robb stark
content: I doubt it.

author: roose bolton
content: Well, we'll learn soon enough. In my family, we say, "A naked man has few secrets. "A flayed man none."

author: robb stark
content: My father outlawed flaying in the North.

author: roose bolton
content: We're not in the North.

author: robb stark
content: We're not torturing them.

author: roose bolton
content: The high roado s very pretty, but you'll have a hard time marching your army down it.

author: robb stark
content: The Lannisters hold prisoners of their own. I won't give them an excuse to abuse my sisters.

author: wounded soldier
content: No, don't! Don't! Please!

author: talisa
content: Shhh.

author: talisa
content: The rot's set in.

author: wounded soldier
content: No, don't! No, don't!

author: talisa
content: Shh.

author: wounded soldier
content: Please, don't! It'll get better. It doesn't even hurt.

author: talisa
content: The rot will spread if we don't take the foot now

author: wounded soldier
content: No, you can't!

author: wounded soldier
content: Ser! Please, ser. I can't lose-

author: robb stark
content: You'll die if she doesn't.

author: wounded soldier
content: I don't want to be a cripple, please.

author: roose bolton
content: Surely one of our men needs your attention more than this cub.

author: talisa
content: Your men are not my men, my lord.

author: robb stark
content: Put this in your mouth and lie down. You don't want to watch.

author: wounded soldier
content: No! You can't!

author: robb stark
content: Bite on it. It's better than biting your own tongue, believe me.

author: robb stark
content: What's your name?

author: talisa
content: Talisa.

author: robb stark
content: Your last name?

author: talisa
content: You want to know what side my family fights on?

author: robb stark
content: You know my family name. You have me at a disadvantage.

author: talisa
content: That boy lost his foot on your orders.

author: robb stark
content: They killed my father.

author: talisa
content: That boy did?

author: robb stark
content: The family he fights for.

author: talisa
content: Do you think he's friends with King Joffrey? He's a fisherman's son that grew up near Lannisport. He probably never held a spear before they shoved one in his hands a few months ago.

author: robb stark
content: I have no hatred for the lad.

author: talisa
content: That should help his foot grow back.

author: robb stark
content: You'd have us surrender, end all this bloodshed. I understand. The country would be at peace and life would be just under the righteous hand of good King Joffrey.

author: talisa
content: You're going to kill Joffrey?

author: robb stark
content: If the gods give me strength.

author: talisa
content: And then what?

author: robb stark
content: I don't know. We'll go back to Winterfell. I have no desire to sit on the Iron Throne.

author: talisa
content: So who will?

author: robb stark
content: I don't know.

author: talisa
content: You're fighting to overthrow a king, and yet you have no plan for what comes after?

author: robb stark
content: First we have to win the war.

author: robb stark
content: You never told me where you're from.

author: talisa
content: Volantis.

author: robb stark
content: Volantis? You're far from home. The boy was lucky you were here.

author: talisa
content: He was unlucky that you were.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You're here to answer for your brother's latest treasons.

author: sansa stark
content: Your Grace, whatever my traitor brother has done, I had no part. You know that. I beg you, please

author: joffrey lannister
content: Ser Lancel, tell her of this outrage.

author: lancel
content: Using some vile sorcery, your brother fell on Stafford Lannister with an army of wolves. Thousands of good men were butchered. After the slaughter, the Northmen feasted on the flesh of the slain.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Killing you would send your brother a message.

author: joffrey lannister
content: But my mother insists on keeping you alive. Stand. So we'll have to send your brother a message some other way. Meryn.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Leave her face. I like her pretty.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Meryn, my lady is overdressed. Unburden her.

author: joffrey lannister
content: If you want Robb Stark to hear us, we're going to have to speak louder.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What is the meaning of this?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What kind of knight beats a helpless girl?

author: meryn
content: The kind who serves his king, Imp.

author: bronn
content: Careful, now. We don't want to get blood all over your pretty white cloak.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Someone get the girl something to cover herself with. She is to be your queen. Have you no regard for her honor?

author: joffrey lannister
content: I'm punishing her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: For what crimes? She did not fight her brother's battle, you half-wit.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You can't talk to me like that. The king can do as he likes!

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Mad King did as he liked. Has your Uncle Jaime ever told you what happened to him?

author: meryn
content: No one threatens His Grace in the presence of the Kingsguard.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm not threatening the king, ser. I am educating my nephew. Bronn, the next time Ser Meryn speaks, kill him. That was a threat. See the difference?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I apologize for my nephew's behavior. Tell me the truth. Do you want an end to this engagement?

author: sansa stark
content: I am loyal to King Joffrey, my one true love.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Lady Stark, you may survive us yet.

author: bronn
content: The little king's backed up. Clogged from balls to brains.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You think dipping his wick will cure what ails him?

author: bronn
content: There's no cure for being a cunt. But the boy's at that age. And he's got nothing to do all day but pick wings off flies. Couldn't hurt to get some of the poison out.

author: joffrey lannister
content: What are you doing here, dog?

author: sandor clegane
content: Your uncle left your nameday present and asked me to see that you got it.

author: joffrey lannister
content: And? What is it?

author: sandor clegane
content: Look inside, Your Grace.

author: daisy
content: Your Grace.

author: ros
content: Happy nameday, Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: My nameday has passed.

author: ros
content: We won't tell if you won't.

author: joffrey lannister
content: No. Her. Touch her.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Could you hit her?

author: joffrey lannister
content: My uncle sent you?

author: daisy
content: Yes, Your Grace. He chose us himself.

author: ros
content: Hmm.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Use this.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Harder.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I said harder. He'd want me to get his money's worth.

author: ros
content: Your Grace, too much pain will spoil the pleasure.

author: daisy
content: Please, Your Grace.

author: ros
content: Your Grace, if your uncle finds out

author: joffrey lannister
content: Oh, I want him to find out. You will bring her to his chambers when you're finished and show him what you've done, or the same thing will happen to you.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Begin.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Harder!

author: renly
content: Well, if it isn't my favorite whoremonger. Pray I haven't kept you waiting long.

author: petyr baelish
content: Your Grace.

author: renly
content: Now you do the Lannisters' bidding, is that it? Tell me, was my brother's body even cold before you secured your newest patron?

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm a practical man.

author: renly
content: Just not a loyal one.

author: petyr baelish
content: And who would you have me be loyal to? Your brother's corpse?

author: renly
content: I don't like you, Lord Baelish. I don't like your face. I don't like the words that come oozing out of your mouth. I don't want you in my tent one minute more than necessary. So tell me, why are you here?

author: renly
content: You can trust Brienne. Her loyalty comes without charge.

author: petyr baelish
content: You still have many friends at court, Your Grace, many who believe Ned Stark erred by not supporting your claim.

author: renly
content: Now I understand. You know I have the numbers. You know I'm marching on King's Landing. When I take the throne, you hope to retain your position. And your head.

author: petyr baelish
content: I would give priority to my head.

author: petyr baelish
content: I understand that you don't like me, and while that saddens me greatly, I did not come here today seeking your affection. When you march on King's Landing, you may find yourself facing a protracted siege or open gates.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: All of these tents look the same to me. Would you be so kind-

author: margaery tyrell
content: It would be my pleasure. It took me weeks to learn my way around the camp. Twice I walked in on officers in stages of undress. And the moment I learn which tent is mine, we're on the move again.

author: petyr baelish
content: Your tent"? Not "Our tent"? The king snores, perhaps? Or simply prefers solitude? Pressures of command, no doubt. Four kings vying for the throne.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I am not tutored in warfare, but basic arithmetic favors the side with the greater numbers.

author: petyr baelish
content: If war were arithmetic, the mathematicians would rule the world. I did notice your brother entering His Grace's tent just now.

author: margaery tyrell
content: The place of a Kingsguard is by the king's side.

author: petyr baelish
content: And on the night of your wedding, who was by the king's side then?

author: margaery tyrell
content: You seem quite interested in our marriage.

author: petyr baelish
content: Your marriage is quite interesting. Not only to me, but to the realm. The marriage of a wealthy girl always breeds interest, if nothing else.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You've never married, have you?

author: petyr baelish
content: I've been unlucky in my affections, sadly.

author: margaery tyrell
content: That is sad. Though perhaps it's for the best. The whole notion of marriage seems to confuse you, so allow me to explain. My husband is my king, and my king is my husband. Here is your tent, Lord Baelish. Good night.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This isn't your horse.

author: kovarro
content: It was given to me by the Thirteen. The Elders of Qarth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Qarth?

author: kovarro
content: Three days to the east, on the sea.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will they let us in?

author: kovarro
content: They said they would be honored to receive the Mother of Dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What do you know of this place?

author: jorah mormont
content: Only that the desert around their walls is called the Garden of Bones. Every time the Qartheen shut their gates on a traveler, the garden grows.

author: man
content: Go on!

author: man
content: You, keep moving!

author: man
content: Bring her about!

author: hot pie
content: What kind of fire melts stone?

author: arya stark
content: Dragonfire.

author: hot pie
content: There's dragons here?

author: gendry baratheon
content: No, all the dragons are dead.

author: hot pie
content: What's that smell?

author: arya stark
content: Dead people.

author: soldier
content: Move.

author: man
content: Please, please, no, no! No.

author: woman
content: He's dead. He was my son. My sister was three days ago. My husband, the day before that.

author: gendry baratheon
content: They take someone every day?

author: arya stark
content: Does anyone live?

author: arya stark
content: Joffrey. Cersei. llyn Payne. The Hound. Joffrey. Cersei. llyn Payne. The Hound. Joffrey. Cersei. llyn Payne. The Hound.

author: catelyn stark
content: How dare you?

author: petyr baelish
content: You may have heard false reports.

author: catelyn stark
content: You betrayed Ned.

author: petyr baelish
content: Betrayed? I wanted him to serve as Protector of the Realm. I begged him to seize the moment.

author: catelyn stark
content: I trusted you. My husband trusted you. And you repaid our faith with treachery.

author: petyr baelish
content: No, my lady.

author: catelyn stark
content: Get out!

author: petyr baelish
content: Cat, I've I've loved you since I was a boy. It seems to me that fate has given us this chance

author: catelyn stark
content: Have you lost your mind? Get out!

author: petyr baelish
content: Do you want to see your girls again? Sansa, more beautiful than ever? And Arya, just as wild as ever?

author: catelyn stark
content: You have Arya, too?

author: petyr baelish
content: Both girls are healthy and safe. For now. But you know the Queen and you know Joffrey. I fear for their longevity if they remain in the capital.

author: catelyn stark
content: What do you want?

author: petyr baelish
content: The Lannisters will trade your daughters for the Kingslayer.

author: catelyn stark
content: Of course they will. Jaime Lannister for two girls? Robb will never agree to those terms.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm not bringing these terms to him. I'm bringing them to you.

author: catelyn stark
content: You think I keep secrets from my son?

author: petyr baelish
content: Robb has surprised them all with his skills in battle, but he's not a mother. Consider it, Cat. You may not get another chance. I've brought you a gift.

author: catelyn stark
content: I don't want your gifts. A token of Tyrion Lannister's goodwill. He wants you to understand that this exchange of prisoners is offered in good faith.

author: catelyn stark
content: Good faith?

author: catelyn stark
content: What's this?

author: petyr baelish
content: Your husband was an honorable man. He should rest beside his family in the crypts beneath Winterfell. You may not believe

author: catelyn stark
content: Get out.

author: man
content: Get up, you dogs!

author: hot pie
content: That's him, the one who picks.

author: arya stark
content: The Mountain. What are you doing?

author: hot pie
content: He told me he stares at him every day. That's why he doesn't get picked.

author: mountain
content: You.

author: soldier
content: Move, boy! Move!

author: tickler
content: Is there gold and silver in the village?

author: prisoner
content: I don't know.

author: tickler
content: Gems?

author: prisoner
content: I didn't see any.

author: tickler
content: Where is the Brotherhood?

author: prisoner
content: I don't know. Please.

author: tickler
content: Which of the villagers aided them?

author: tickler
content: Who?

author: prisoner
content: I-

author: prisoner
content: I never saw. Please. Please, stop. Please, it's starting to-

author: prisoner
content: I didn't see anyone help him. Take it off! Take it off!

author: tickler
content: Who helped him?

author: prisoner
content: Ganes, the butcher, and his son.

author: tickler
content: That's better. You've been very helpful.

author: prisoner
content: No, stop, please! What are you doing? Please, stop! Please, stop!

author: prisoner
content: No! No! I told you everything! No! No!

author: arya stark
content: Joffrey. Cersei. llyn Payne. The Hound.

author: woman
content: Please, Polliver. Some food. Just a crust of bread.

author: arya stark
content: Polliver. The Mountain.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Lady Stark, I had not thought to find you in the Stormlands.

author: catelyn stark
content: I had not thought to be here, Lord Stannis.

author: renly
content: Can that truly be you?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Who else might it be?

author: renly
content: When I saw your standard, I couldn't be sure. Whose banner is that?

author: stannis baratheon
content: My own.

author: renly
content: I suppose if we used the same one, the battle would be terribly confusing. Why is your stag on fire?

author: melisandre
content: The king has taken for his sigil the fiery heart of the Lord of Light.

author: renly
content: Ah, you must be this fire priestess we hear so much about. Mmm, brother, now I understand why you found religion in your old age.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Watch yourself, Renly.

author: renly
content: No, no, I'm relieved. I never really believed you were a fanatic. Charmless, rigid, a bore, yes, but not a godly man.

author: melisandre
content: You should kneel before your brother. He's the Lordo s chosen, born amidst salt and smoke.

author: renly
content: Born amidst salt and smoke? Is he a ham?

author: stannis baratheon
content: That's twice I've warned you.

author: catelyn stark
content: Listen to yourselves. If you were sons of mine, I would knock your heads together and lock you in a bedchamber until you remembered that you were brothers.

author: stannis baratheon
content: It is strange to find you beside my brother, Lady Stark. Your husband was a supporter of my claim. Lord Eddardo s integrity cost him his head. And you sit beside this pretender and chastise me.

author: catelyn stark
content: We share a common enemy.

author: stannis baratheon
content: The Iron Throne is mine by right. All those that deny that are my foes.

author: renly
content: The whole realm denies it, from Dorne to the Wall. Old men deny it with their death rattle and unborn children deny it in their mother's wombs. No one wants you for their king. You never wanted any friends, brother. But a man without friends is a man without power.

author: stannis baratheon
content: For the sake of the mother who bore us, I will give you this one night to reconsider. Strike your banners, come to me before dawn, and I will grant you your old seat in the Council. I'll even name you my heir until a son is born to me. Otherwise I shall destroy you.

author: renly
content: Look across those fields, brother. Can you see all those banners?

author: stannis baratheon
content: You think a few bolts of cloth will make you king?

author: renly
content: No. The men holding those bolts of cloth will make me king.

author: stannis baratheon
content: We shall see, Renly. Come the dawn, we shall see.

author: melisandre
content: Look to your sins, Lord Renly. The night is dark and full of terrors.

author: renly
content: Would you believe I loved him once?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I thought we were welcome.

author: jorah mormont
content: If you heard a Dothraki horde was approaching your city, you might do the same, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Horde?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My name is Daenerys-

author: spice king
content: Daenerys Stormborn of the house Targaryen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You know me, my lord?

author: spice king
content: Only by reputation, Khaleesi. And I'm no lord, merely a humble merchant. They call you the Mother of Dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what should I call you?

author: spice king
content: Oh, my name is quite long and quite impossible for foreigners to pronounce. I am simply a trader of spices. But we are the Thirteen, charged with the governance and protection of Qarth, the greatest city that ever was or will be.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The beauty of Quarth is legendary-

author: spice
content: KING Qarth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Qarth.

author: spice king
content: Might we see the dragons?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My friend, we have traveled very far. We have no food, no water. Once I see my people fed, I would be honored

author: spice king
content: Forgive me, Mother of Dragons, but no man alive has seen a living dragon. Some of my more skeptical friends refuse to believe your children even exist. All we ask is the chance to see for ourselves.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I am not a liar.

author: spice king
content: Oh, I don't think you are. But as I've never met you before, my opinion on the matter is of limited value.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Where I come from, guests are treated with respect, not insulted at the gates.

author: spice king
content: Then perhaps you should return to where you come from. We wish you well.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What are you doing? You promised to receive me.

author: spice king
content: We have received you. Here we are, and here you are.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If you do not let us in, all of us will die.

author: spice king
content: Which we shall deeply regret. But Qarth did not become the greatest city that ever was or will be by letting Dothraki savages through its gates.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi, please be careful.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thirteen! When my dragons are grown, we will take back what was stolen from me and destroy those who have wronged me. We will lay waste to armies and burn cities to the ground. Turn us away and we will burn you first.

author: spice king
content: Ah. You are a true Targaryen. Only, as you said a moment ago, if we don't let you into the city, you will all die. And so-

author: xaro
content: Retreating in fear from a little girl is unbecoming of the greatest city that ever was or will be.

author: spice king
content: The discussion is over, Xaro Xhoan Daxos. The Thirteen have spoken.

author: xaro
content: I am one of the Thirteen, and I am still speaking.

author: spice king
content: The girl threatens to burn our city to the ground and you would invite her in for a cup of wine? She is the Mother of Dragons.

author: xaro
content: Do you expect her to watch her people starve without breathing fire? I believe we can allow a few Dothraki through our gates without dooming our city. After all, here I am, a savage from the Summer Isles, and Qarth still stands.

author: spice king
content: Our decision is final.

author: xaro
content: Very well. I invoke soumai.

author: xaro
content: I will vouch for her, her people, and her dragons, in accordance with the law.

author: spice king
content: Be it on your head.

author: xaro
content: Welcome to Qarth, my lady.

author: tickler
content: Is there gold or silver in the village?

author: gendry baratheon
content: I'm not from the village.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I don't know what that is.

author: man
content: You two. Take Lord Lannister's things to his quarters.

author: tywin lannister
content: What's this?

author: mountain
content: We weren't expecting you till tomorrow, Lord Tywin.

author: tywin lannister
content: Evidently not. Why are these prisoners not in their cells?

author: mountain
content: Cells are overflowing, my lord.

author: polliver
content: This lot won't be here long. Don't need no permanent place. After we interrogate 'em, we usually just-

author: tywin lannister
content: Are we so well-manned that we can afford to discard able young bodies and skilled laborers?

author: tywin lannister
content: You, do you have a trade?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Smith, my lord.

author: polliver
content: What are you looking at? Kneel! Kneel or I'll carve your lungs out, boy.

author: tywin lannister
content: He'll do no such thing. This one's a girl, you idiot, dressed as a boy. Why?

author: arya stark
content: Safer to travel, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: Smart. More than I can say for this lot. Get these prisoners to work. Bring the girl. I need a new cupbearer.

author: mountain
content: My lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your visits are too few, cousin.

author: lancel
content: Her Grace, the Queen Regent, commands you to release Grand Maester Pycelle. Here's your warrant.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So it is. Will you take a cup with me? I find that mulled wine helps me sleep.

author: lancel
content: I am here at Her Grace's behest, not to drink with you, Imp.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If my sister was so concerned for Pycelle, I would have thought she'd come herself. Instead she sends you. What am I to make of that?

author: lancel
content: I don't care what you make of it, so long as you release your prisoner immediately.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And you've received these instructions directly from Cersei?

author: lancel
content: As I said several times.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And you've waited this long to deliver the information?

author: lancel
content: When the Queen Regent gives me a command, I carry it out without delay.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cersei must have great trust in you, allowing you into her chamber during the hour of the wolf.

author: lancel
content: The Queen Regent has a great many responsibilities. She often works from dusk till dawn.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She must be very glad to have you helping her from dusk till dawn.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah. Lavender oil. She always loved lavender oil, even as a girl.

author: lancel
content: I am a knight!

author: tyrion lannister
content: An anointed knight, yes. Tell me, did Cersei have you knighted before or after she took you into her bed? What? Nothing to say? No more warnings for me, ser?

author: lancel
content: You will withdraw these filthy accusations.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Have you ever given any thought to what King Joffrey will have to say when he finds out you've been bedding his mother?

author: lancel
content: It's not my fault!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did she take you against your will? Can you not defend yourself, knight?

author: lancel
content: Your own father, Lord Tywin, when I was named the King's squire, he told me to obey her in everything.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did he tell you to fuck her, too?

author: lancel
content: I only meant I did as I was bid.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Hated every moment of it, is that what you'll have me believe? A high place in court, a knighthood, my sister's legs spreading open for you at night. Oh, yes, it must have been terrible. Wait here. His Grace will want to hear this.

author: lancel
content: Mercy! Mercy, my lord! I beg you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Save it for Joffrey. He loves a good grovel.

author: lancel
content: My lord, it was your sister's bidding, the Queen. I'll leave the city at once, I swear.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, I think not.

author: lancel
content: My lord?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You heard me. My father told you to obey my sister. Obey her. Stay close to her side. Keep her trust. Pleasure her whenever she requires. No one ever need know, as long as you keep faith with me. I want to know what Cersei is doing, where she goes, who she sees, what they talk of, everything. And you will tell me.

author: lancel
content: Yes, my lord, I will. I swear it, as you command.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, rise, rise. Let us drink to our understanding. Oh, you don't have a cup. Oh, well. Smile, cousin. My sister is a beautiful woman, and it's all for the good of the realm. Go back and tell her that I beg her forgiveness, that I want no more conflict between us and that, henceforth, I shall do nothing without her consent.

author: lancel
content: But her demands?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, I'll give her Pycelle.

author: lancel
content: You will?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, I'll release him in the morning. Cersei can keep him as a pet, if she wants, but I will not have him on the Council. I could swear that I had not harmed a single hair on his head, but that would not, strictly speaking, be true. Stay within one table length.

author: davos
content: Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Do your knuckle bones bring you luck?

author: davos
content: Well, life's been good since you hacked them off, Your Grace. And it's four less fingernails to clean.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Fewer.

author: davos
content: Pardon?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Four fewer fingernails to clean. Never understood why you had to wear them.

author: davos
content: It reminds me of where I come from and where I am now. It reminds me of your justice. It was an honest punishment and you were good with the cleaver.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You were a hero and a smuggler. A good act does not wash out the bad, nor a bad the good.

author: davos
content: A lesson I've tried to teach my son.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Does he listen?

author: davos
content: To me? Gods, no. But if your Red Woman told him to leap from the crow's nest

author: stannis baratheon
content: She has a name. I trust you've not forgotten your smuggler's tricks.

author: davos
content: I've lived within the law for seventeen-

author: stannis baratheon
content: I want you to be a smuggler this time.

author: davos
content: Any shore, any night. What am I bringing ashore?

author: stannis baratheon
content: The Red Woman. No one must know what you do and we'll not speak of this again.
