author: davos
content: I am true to Your Grace and always will be, but surely there are other ways, cleaner ways.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Cleaner ways don't win wars.

author: melisandre
content: Are you afraid, Onion Knight?

author: davos
content: Someone once told me the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: melisandre
content: You've carried more unpleasant cargo in your time. Are you a good man, Ser Davos Seaworth?

author: davos
content: I'd say my parts are mixed, my lady, good and bad.

author: melisandre
content: If half an onion is black with rot, it's a rotten onion. A man is good or he is evil.

author: davos
content: And which are you?

author: melisandre
content: Oh, good. I'm a knight myself, of sorts, a champion of light and life.

author: davos
content: Well, that must be very nice for you.

author: melisandre
content: Do you love your wife?

author: davos
content: I do.

author: melisandre
content: Yet you have known other women.

author: davos
content: Don't talk about my wife.

author: melisandre
content: I'm not. I'm talking about other women. Like me, Ser Davos. You want me. You want to see what's beneath this robe.

author: melisandre
content: And you will.

author: davos
content: Strange that this Lord of Light asks you to work in the shadows.

author: melisandre
content: Shadows cannot live in the dark, Ser Davos. They are servants of light, the children of fire. And the brighter the flame, the darker they are.

author: davos
content: These weren't here before. They've barred the passage.

author: melisandre
content: They can't bar our passage.

author: davos
content: Gods protect us.

author: melisandre
content: There's only one god, Ser Davos, and he only protects those who serve him.

author: renly
content: You swear it?

author: catelyn stark
content: By the mother. My son has no interest in the Iron Throne.

author: renly
content: Then I see no reason for hostility between us. Your son can go on calling himself King in the North. The Starks will have dominion over all lands north of Moat Cailin, provided he swears me an oath of fealty.

author: catelyn stark
content: And the wording of this oath?

author: renly
content: The same Ned Stark swore to Robert eighteen years ago. Cat, their friendship held the kingdoms together.

author: catelyn stark
content: And in return for my son's loyalty?

author: renly
content: In the morning, I'll destroy my brother's army.

author: renly
content: When that's done, Baratheon and Stark will fight their common enemy together, as they have done many times before.

author: catelyn stark
content: Our two houses have always been close, which is why I am begging you to reconsider this battle. Negotiate a peace with your brother.

author: renly
content: Negotiate with Stannis? You heard him out there. I'd have better luck debating the wind.

author: renly
content: Please bring my terms to your son. I believe we are natural allies. I hope he feels the same. Together we could end this war in a fortnight.

author: brienne
content: No! No.

author: soldier
content: Follow me!

author: soldier
content: You'll die for this.

author: catelyn stark
content: No, wait, it wasn't her!

author: catelyn stark
content: We've got to leave. They'll hang you for this.

author: man
content: Inside the king's tent - go

author: man
content: Now.

author: brienne
content: I won't leave him.

author: catelyn stark
content: You can't avenge him if you're dead.

author: man
content: Over there, go!

author: brienne
content: Not that way.

author: margaery tyrell
content: We need to go home. Loras.

author: petyr baelish
content: My lord, my lady.

author: loras
content: Get out.

author: petyr baelish
content: Stannis will be here in an hour. When he arrives, Renly's bannermen will flock to him. Your former companions will fight for the privilege of selling you to their new king.

author: loras
content: And you want that privilege for yourself.

author: petyr baelish
content: You will note that I am standing here talking to you, not Stannis.

author: margaery tyrell
content: There's no time for this.

author: loras
content: Ride back to Highgarden, sister. I'm not running from Stannis.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Brienne of Tarth murdered Renly.

author: loras
content: I don't believe that. You don't believe that. Who gained the most from our king's death?

author: petyr baelish
content: Stannis.

author: loras
content: I will put a sword through his righteous face.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You can't stay here.

author: loras
content: He would have been a true king, a good king.

author: petyr baelish
content: Tell me, Ser Loras, what do you desire most in this world?

author: loras
content: Revenge.

author: petyr baelish
content: I have always found that to be the purest of motivations, but you won't have a chance to put your sword through Stannis, not today. You'll be cut to pieces before he sets foot on solid ground. If it is justice that you want, be smart about it.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You can't avenge him from the grave. Bring the horses. Please.

author: margaery tyrell
content: He was very handsome.

author: petyr baelish
content: He was, Your Grace.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Your Grace." Calling yourself king doesn't make you one. And if Renly wasn't a king, I wasn't a queen.

author: petyr baelish
content: Do you want to be a queen?

author: margaery tyrell
content: No. I want to be the queen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Killed? By whom?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Accounts differ. Most seem to implicate Catelyn Stark in some way.

author: cersei lannister
content: Really? Who'd have thought?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Some say it was one of his own Kingsguard, while still others say it was Stannis himself who did it after negotiations went sour.

author: cersei lannister
content: Whomever did it, I say well done.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not what Varys says. He says Renly's army is flocking to support Stannis, which would give Stannis superiority over us on both land and sea.

author: cersei lannister
content: Littlefinger says we can outspend him three to one.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And I say Father raised you to have too much respect for money. Stannis Baratheon is coming for us, sooner rather than later.

author: cersei lannister
content: Aren't there other things you should be doing, like sealing my daughter in a crate so you can ship her away?

author: tyrion lannister
content: She'll be safer in Dorne.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes, I know how concerned you are for her safety.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It so happens that I am. Myrcella is a sweet, innocent girl and I don't blame her at all for you.

author: cersei lannister
content: So clever. Aren't you always so clever with your schemes and your plots?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Schemes and plots are the same thing. They are going to attack us. We need to be ready.

author: cersei lannister
content: No need to concern yourself over it. The king is taking personal charge of siege preparations.

author: tyrion lannister
content: May I ask specifically what the king has in mind?

author: cersei lannister
content: You may, specifically, or you may ask vaguely. The answer will be the same.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's important that we talk about this.

author: cersei lannister
content: It's the king's royal prerogative to withhold sensitive information from his councilors.

author: lancel
content: It's wildfire.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Wildfire? You wouldn't lie to me, would you, cousin?

author: lancel
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: MThat's a lie right there.

author: lancel
content: It is not a lie. Why would I lie?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Tell me, if the vile allegations against my brother and sister are true, do you think it will make Jaime more likely to kill you or less likely? When I tell him you're fucking her, I mean.

author: lancel
content: I'm telling you the truth.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The smart money would be on more likely.

author: lancel
content: She's making wildfire.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But then perhaps his own unnatural urges will give him sympathy for yours.

author: lancel
content: The Alchemists' Guild is being commissioned.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I suppose there's only one way to find out.

author: lancel
content: They have thousands of pots already stored in their vaults. They are planning to launch it from the city walls into Stannis' ships and armies. Please.

author: tyrion lannister
content: When did she tell you this?

author: lancel
content: I heard her talking with the pyromancer. And the other night, after I left her, she went to meet him. I swear to you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Swear to me on what?

author: lancel
content: On my life.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But I don't care about your life.

author: lancel
content: In the light of the Seven, by all that is holy and right, I, Lancel Lannister, do solemnly vow...

author: tyrion lannister
content: All right, all right. Enough. Even torturing you is boring. Just get out.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, Lancel, tell my friend Bronn to please kill you if anything should happen to me.

author: lancel
content: Please kill me if anything should happen to Lord Tyrion.

author: bronn
content: It will be my pleasure.

author: davos
content: Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What is it?

author: davos
content: I'm sorry about your brother, Your Grace, I wanted to let you know that people grieve for him.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Fools love a fool. I grieve for him as well, for the boy he was, not the man he grew to be.

author: davos
content: I need to speak to you - about what I saw in that cave.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I thought I made it clear to you there'd be no need to speak to me on this matter.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, I-

author: stannis baratheon
content: I've never known you to need to hear a thing twice.

author: davos
content: And I've never known you to hide from the truth.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You've come to lecture me on truth?

author: davos
content: I've come to tell you that what I saw.

author: stannis baratheon
content: All my brother's bannermen have come to my side. Except the Tyrells, who fled like cowards. They won't be able to resist us now. Soon I shall be sitting on the Iron Throne.

author: davos
content: Nothing is worth what this will cost you, not even the Iron

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'll hear no more about it.

author: man
content: Take a company of men, secure the perimeter.

author: davos
content: When do we sail for King's Landing?

author: stannis baratheon
content: As soon as I've consolidated my troops. We'll make short work of the Lannisters' fleet. Once Blackwater Bay is cleared, we'll deliver our troops to their doorstep and take the city.

author: davos
content: And will you bring Lady Melisandre with you?

author: stannis baratheon
content: That's not your concern.

author: davos
content: If you take King's Landing with her by your side, the victory will be hers.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I never thought I'd have reason to doubt your loyalty. Was I wrong?

author: davos
content: Loyal service means telling hard truths.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Oh, truth again. All right, what's the truth? The hard truth?

author: davos
content: She's a foreigner preaching her foreign religion. Some believe she whispers orders in your ear and you obey.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What do you believe?

author: davos
content: You won those bannermen from Renly. Don't lose them to her.

author: stannis baratheon
content: We set out for King's Landing without Lady Melisandre. And you lead the fleet into Blackwater Bay.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, I'm honored, but my time on the sea was spent evading ships, not attacking them. The other lords won't be happy.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Most of those lords should consider themselves lucky I don't hang them for treason. Hard truths cut both ways, Ser Davos.

author: girl
content: I've got it! I've got it!

author: man
content: So it's that one there at the top, on the right.

author: man
content: Buy my fruit, my lord. Fresh fruit.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stannis has more infantry, more ships, more horses. What do we have?

author: bronn
content: There's that mind of yours you keep going on about.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, I've never actually been able to kill people with it.

author: bronn
content: Good thing. I'd be out of a job. What about your father?

author: tyrion lannister
content: He hasn't sent a raven in weeks. He's very busy. Being repeatedly humiliated by Robb Stark is time-consuming. We won't be able to hold the city against Stannis, not the way Joffrey's planning on holding it.

author: protester
content: Corruption.

author: crowd
content: Yes!

author: protester
content: We are swollen, bloated, foul. Brother fornicates with sister in the bed of kings and we're surprised when the fruit of their incest is rotten? Yes, a rotten king.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's hard to argue with his assessment.

author: bronn
content: Not after what he did to your birthday present.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The king is a lost cause. It's the rest of us I'm worried about now.

author: man
content: A dancing king, prancing down his bloodstained halls to the tune of a twisted demon monkey.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You have to admire his imagination.

author: bronn
content: He's talking about you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What? Demon monkey?

author: bronn
content: People think you're pulling the king's strings. They blame you for the city's ills.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Blame me? I'm trying to save them.

author: bronn
content: You don't need to convince me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Demon monkey.

author: man
content: Yeah, come on.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're the crew of the Sea Bitch? I'm your commander. Welcome.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Stop. Stop! Your captain commands you to stop!

author: black lorren
content: Where are we headed, Captain?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The Stony Shore, to raid their villages. There'll be spoils in it for you, and women, if you do your jobs well.

author: black lorren
content: And who decides if we've done our jobs well?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I do. Your captain.

author: black lorren
content: I have been reaving and raping since before you left Balon's balls, Captain. Don't reckon I've got much use for your ideas on how to do it. Don't reckon I've got much use for a captain at all. I'm thinking I can do the job of captain real well myself. All I need is a ship. You wouldn't know where I could find myself a ship now, would you?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You could do that, take the ship, head out on your own. And I will hunt you down, drag you back here in chains and hang you for a traitor.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Stop. We yield.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Congratulations on your first command.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Thank you. Kind of you to come see me off.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Oh, I'm not here for you. I was just on my way to Red Harbor. I've got thirty ships. There's nowhere to put them here. Too narrow.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You'd better get out there. Wouldn't want her to set sail without you.

author: yara greyjoy
content: That would never happen. My crew would wait on deck for a year if I asked them to. This lot, though... Enjoy the Stony Shore.

author: dagmer
content: Come on, I'll take you out.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Who are you?

author: dagmer
content: Dagmer, your first mate.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Why aren't you with the rest of them? Or did they send you to row me out and dump me halfway in the sea? That would be good for a laugh.

author: dagmer
content: They're not gonna respect you until you prove yourself.

author: theon greyjoy
content: And how am I supposed to prove myself by pillaging piss-poor fishing villages?

author: dagmer
content: You're not.

author: theon greyjoy
content: And yet that's the task my father has given me to prove that I'm a true Iron Islander.

author: dagmer
content: They're all Iron Islanders. Do they do as they're told or do they do as they like?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The Stony Shore's not far from Torrhen's Square.

author: dagmer
content: The seat of the House of Tallhart, a more impressive prize than a few fishermen's daughters. What, you don't think we could take it?

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, we could. We could never hold it for more than a few days. As soon as Winterfell got word that we'd taken Torrhen's Square, the Starks would send their men to take it back. And then-

author: theon greyjoy
content: Take me to my ship.

author: reginald
content: The Starks have overextended their lines. Now that summer's over, they'll have a hard time keeping their men and horses fed.

author: tywin lannister
content: The Starks understand winter better than we ever will. The cold won't beat them.

author: amory
content: Our spies report growing discontent among the Northern lords. They want to return home and gather the harvest before the crops turn.

author: tywin lannister
content: And I'm sure if those same spies snuck into our own encampments, they would report growing discontent amongst the Southern lords. This is war, no one's content. We've underestimated the Stark boy for too long. He has a good mind for warfare, his men worship him. And as long as he keeps winning battles, they'll keep believing he is King in the North. You've been waiting for him to fail. He is not going to fail, not without our help. So how do we stop him?

author: reginald
content: We've worked through the night, my lord. Perhaps we'd profit from some sleep.

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes, I think you would, Reginald. And because you're my cousin, I might even let you wake from that sleep. Go, I'm sure your wife must miss you.

author: reginald
content: My wife's in Lannisport.

author: tywin lannister
content: Well, then you'd better start riding. Go, before I change my mind and send her your head.

author: tywin lannister
content: If your name wasn't Lannister, you'd be scrubbing out pots in the cook's tent. Go!

author: tywin lannister
content: Not wine, water. We'll be here for some time. Girl, where are you from?

author: arya stark
content: Maidenpool, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: And who are the Lords of Maidenpool? Remind me.

author: arya stark
content: House Mooton, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: And what is their sigil?

author: tywin lannister
content: A red salmon. I think a Maidenpool girl would remember that. You're a Northerner, aren't you?

author: tywin lannister
content: Good. One more time, where are you from?

author: arya stark
content: Barrowton, my lord. House Dustin. Two crossed longaxes beneath a black crown.

author: tywin lannister
content: And what do they say of Robb Stark in the North?

author: arya stark
content: They call him the Young Wolf.

author: tywin lannister
content: And?

author: arya stark
content: They say he rides into battle on the back of a giant direwolf. They say he can turn into a wolf himself when he wants. They say he can't be killed.

author: tywin lannister
content: And do you believe them?

author: arya stark
content: No, my lord. Anyone can be killed.

author: tywin lannister
content: Fetch that water.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl says nothing.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl keeps her mouth closed. No one hears, and friends may talk in secret, yes? A boy becomes a girl.

author: arya stark
content: I was always a girl.

author: jaqen hghar
content: And I was always aware. But the girl keeps secrets. It is not for a man to spoil them.

author: arya stark
content: You're one of them now. I should have let you burn.

author: jaqen hghar
content: And you fetch water for one of them now. Why is this right for you and wrong for me?

author: arya stark
content: I didn't have a choice.

author: jaqen hghar
content: You did. I did. And here we are.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A man pays his debts. A man owes three.

author: arya stark
content: Three what?

author: jaqen hghar
content: The Red God takes what is his, lovely girl. And only death may pay for life. You saved me and the two I was with. You stole three deaths from the Red God. We have to give them back. Speak three names and the man will do the rest. Three lives I will give you, no more, no less, and we're done.

author: arya stark
content: I can name anyone and you'll kill him?

author: jaqen hghar
content: A man has said.

author: arya stark
content: The one who tortures everyone.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A man needs a name.

author: arya stark
content: I don't know his name. They call him the Tickler.

author: jaqen hghar
content: That is enough. Go now, girl. Your master is thirsty.

author: jeor
content: He's not here yet. He'd have seen us, blown the horn.

author: jon snow
content: When will he come?

author: jeor
content: The Halfhand does things in his own time.

author: jon snow
content: My uncle told me stories about him.

author: jeor
content: Most of them are true.

author: jon snow
content: I heard the Halfhand spent half of last winter beyond the Wall.

author: jeor
content: The whole winter. He was north of the Skirling Pass when the snows came. Had to wait for the thaw.

author: jon snow
content: So it is possible for someone to survive out here on their own.

author: jeor
content: Well, possible for the Halfhand.

author: sam
content: Beautiful, isn't it? Gilly would love it here.

author: dolorous edd
content: There's nothing more sickening than a man in love.

author: man
content: About time you did something. At least you'll keep warm.

author: sam
content: The Fist of the First Men. Think of how old this place is. Before the Targaryens defeated the Andals, before the Andals took Westeros from the First Men.

author: dolorous edd
content: Before I die, please, stop talking.

author: sam
content: Thousands and thousands of years ago, the First Men stood here where we're standing all through the long night. What do you think they were like, the First Men?

author: dolorous edd
content: Stupid. Smart people don't find themselves in places like this.

author: jon snow
content: I think they were afraid. I think they came here to get away from something. And I don't think it worked.

author: grenn
content: Wildlings?

author: jon snow
content: One blast is for rangers returning. Wildlings is two blasts.

author: dolorous edd
content: So you got to stand there waiting, wondering. One blast for friends, two for foes.

author: sam
content: And three for White Walkers. It's been a thousand years, but that's the only time they blow the horn three times.

author: grenn
content: But if it's been a thousand years, how do you know?

author: sam
content: Well I read it in a book.

author: dolorous edd
content: I read it in a book.

author: jon snow
content: Look. It's Qhorin Halfhand.

author: dolorous
content: EDD Aye, we'll live another day. Hurrah.

author: haylene
content: Take care, my lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I remember reading an old sailors' proverb, "Piss on wildfire and your cock burns off. "

author: haylene
content: Oh, I have not conducted this experiment. It could well be true. The substance burns so hot, it melts wood, stone, even steel, and, of course, flesh. The substance burns so hot, it melts flesh like tallow.

author: haylene
content: After the dragons died, wildfire was the key to the Targaryen power.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My companion takes issue.

author: bronn
content: If I could tell you how many crazy old men I've seen pushing carts around army camps making grand claims about jars full of pig shit. No offense meant.

author: haylene
content: Our order does not deal in pig shit. The substance is fire given form. And we have been perfecting it since the days of Maegor.

author: bronn
content: To do what?

author: haylene
content: The jars are put in catapults and flung at the enemy.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How much do you have?

author: bronn
content: If you could get real soldiers to man the catapults, then maybe you'd hit your target one time in ten, but all the real soldiers are in the Riverlands with your father.

author: haylene
content: My lord, this man is insulting.

author: bronn
content: I don't know if you've ever seen a battle, old man, but things can get a bit messy. 'Cause when we're flinging things at Stannis, he's flinging them right back at us. Men die, men shit themselves, men run, which means pots falling, which means fire inside the walls, which means the poor cunts trying to defend the city end up burning it down.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My friend remains unconvinced.

author: haylene
content: He would not dare insult my order whilst Aerys Targaryen lived.

author: bronn
content: Well, he's not living anymore. And all his pots of wildfire didn't help him, did they? Men win wars, not magic tricks.

author: haylene
content: We have been working tirelessly, day and night, ever since your royal sister commanded us to do so. Our present count stands at 7,811. Enough to burn Stannis Baratheon's fleet and armies both.

author: bronn
content: This is a shit idea.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm afraid I have to concur with my advisor, Wisdom Haylene. The contents of this room could lay King's Landing low. You won't be making wildfire for my sister any longer. You'll be making it for me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dracarys. Dracarys.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He'll be able to feed himself from now on.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Let him sleep, Doreah.

author: doreah
content: Yes, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He loves you.

author: irri
content: I rewove this part of the top. And I fixed the heel on this one.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you, my friend.

author: doreah
content: Did you see the dress Xaro had made for you? They say he's the wealthiest man in Qarth.

author: irri
content: It is known.

author: doreah
content: And if Qarth is the wealthiest city in Essos-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The last time a rich man gave me a dress, he was selling me to Khal Drogo.

author: irri
content: May he ride forever through the night lands.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Xaro is our host, but we know nothing about him. Men like to talk about other men when they're happy.

author: doreah
content: You would look like a real princess in Xaro's-

author: irri
content: She's not a princess. She's a Khaleesi. You should wear it, Khaleesi.

author: irri
content: You are their guest. It would be rude not to.

author: woman
content: And you must visit the night market. The Qartheen night market is like no night market you've ever seen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It sounds wonderful.

author: woman
content: The Meereenis think they have a night market. I will take you there myself.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Please excuse me for a moment.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What are they doing?

author: jorah mormont
content: Malakko says the statue is too heavy to carry. Kovarro says that Malakko is an idiot. They can pry out the gems, the rest is pure gold. Very soft. He can chop off as much as we can carry.

author: kovarro
content: Or melt it. Very simple.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We are his guests! You can't pry it or chop it or melt it.

author: kovarro
content: Of course not, Khaleesi! We will wait until we leave.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Not even when we leave.

author: kovarro
content: Why not?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Our host saved us from the Red Waste and you want to steal from him? I will hear no more.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My brother used to say the only thing the Dothraki knew how to do was steal things better men have built.

author: jorah mormont
content: It's not the only thing. They're quite good at killing the better men.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That's not the kind of queen I'm going to be.

author: pyatt pree
content: Mother of Dragons. On behalf of the warlocks of Qarth, I welcome you. A demonstration?

author: pyatt pree
content: Take this gem. Look at it. Into its depths. So many facets. Look closely enough and you can see yourself in them. Often more than once.

author: pyatt pree
content: Should you grow tired of Xaro's baubles and trinkets, it would be an honor to host you at the House of the Undying. You are always welcome, Mother of Dragons.

author: xaro
content: My apologies. Pyatt Pree is one of the Thirteen. It was customary for me to extend him an invitation. Customs die slow deaths in Qarth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What is the House of the Undying?

author: xaro
content: It is where the warlocks go to squint at dusty books and drink shade of the evening. It turns their lips blue and their minds soft. So soft, they actually believe their parlor tricks are magic.

author: quaithe
content: You watch over her.

author: jorah mormont
content: Do I know you?

author: quaithe
content: I know you. Jorah Mormont of Bear Island.

author: jorah mormont
content: Who are you?

author: quaithe
content: I'm no one. But she is the Mother of Dragons. She needs true protectors, now more than ever. They shall come day and night to see the wonder born into the world again. And when they see, they shall lust, for dragons are fire made flesh. And fire is power.

author: brienne
content: It looked like Stannis.

author: catelyn stark
content: To me it just looked like... A shadow in the shape of a man.

author: brienne
content: In the shape of Stannis.

author: catelyn stark
content: We should reach my son's camp tomorrow.

author: brienne
content: Will you stay there long, my lady?

author: catelyn stark
content: Only long enough to tell Robb what I have seen. After that, I will leave for Winterfell. My two youngest need me. I've been away from them for far too long.

author: brienne
content: I never knew my mother.

author: catelyn stark
content: I'm sorry.

author: catelyn stark
content: My own mother died on the birthing bed when I was very young.

author: brienne
content: It's a bloody business.

author: catelyn stark
content: What comes after is even harder.

author: brienne
content: Once you're safely back amongst your own people, will you give me leave to go, my lady?

author: catelyn stark
content: You mean to kill Stannis.

author: brienne
content: I swore a vow.

author: catelyn stark
content: But Stannis has a great army around him. His own guards are sworn to keep him safe.

author: catelyn stark
content: I'm as good as any of them. I should never have fled.

author: catelyn stark
content: Renly's death was no fault of yours. You served him bravely.

author: brienne
content: I only held him that once as he was dying.

author: catelyn stark
content: He's gone, Brienne. You serve nothing and no one by following him into the earth. Renly's enemies are Robb's enemies as well.

author: brienne
content: I do not know your son, my lady. But I could serve you, if you would have me. You have courage. Not battle courage, perhaps, but, I don't know, a woman's kind of courage. And I think that when the time comes, you will not hold me back. Promise me that you will not hold me back from Stannis.

author: catelyn stark
content: When the time comes, I will not hold you back.

author: brienne
content: Then I am yours, my lady. I will shield your back and give my life for yours, if it comes to that. I swear it by the Old Gods and the new.

author: catelyn stark
content: I vow that you shall always have a place in my home and at my table and that I shall ask no service of you that might bring you dishonor. I swear it by the Old Gods and the new.

author: winterfell shepherd
content: And it's not just thieves, my lord. There's wolves in them hills now, more than I ever seen. They come down in the night and they kill my sheep. My three sons is away fighting for your brother, my lord. They'll fight, keep fighting till they're told to go home. I have no one to man my flock now. Only me. I can't keep watch all day and all night.

author: bran stark
content: We can send two orphan boys from Winterstown home with you to help watch over your flock if you can give them room and board.

author: winterfell shepherd
content: My wife always prayed for more children. We'll look after them. Thank you, my lord. And may the gods bless you and yours.

author: bran stark
content: Stop it. If that's everyone, I'm going to go for a ride before dark.

author: luwin
content: Good.

author: bran stark
content: Hodor.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: rodrik
content: Bran! Lord Stark. Torrhen's Square is under siege.

author: luwin
content: Torrhen's Square is barely forty leagues from here. How can the Lannisters strike so far north?

author: rodrik
content: Might be a raiding party led by the Mountain. Might be sellswords paid by Tywin Lannister.

author: bran stark
content: We have to help them.

author: rodrik
content: Most of the fighting men are away with Robb, but I can gather two hundred decent men.

author: luwin
content: Do you need so many?

author: bran stark
content: If we can't protect our own bannermen, why should they protect us? Go, Ser Rodrik. Take the men you need.

author: rodrik
content: Won't take long, my lord. Southerners don't do well up here.

author: bran stark
content: So, what does it mean?

author: osha
content: Ask your Maester Luwin. He's the one studying books all the time.

author: bran stark
content: I did ask him. He'd never heard of a three-eyed raven.

author: osha
content: Must not mean anything, then.

author: bran stark
content: You're lying.

author: osha
content: You might be a little lord, but don't you call me a liar.

author: bran stark
content: You know what it means.

author: osha
content: I never said I didn't.

author: bran stark
content: You didn't give me an honest answer.

author: osha
content: That's not the same as being a liar.

author: bran stark
content: Well, it's not far off.

author: osha
content: So, you've been dreaming of a three-eyed raven again? In the godswood, you told me you didn't dream. Now who's a liar? What did you see in your dream?

author: osha
content: Something bad? Tell me, boy.

author: bran stark
content: I dreamt that the sea came to Winterfell. I saw waves crashing against the gates and the water came flowing over the walls. It flooded the castle. Drowned men were floating here, in the yard. Ser Rodrik was one of them.

author: osha
content: The sea is hundreds of miles away.

author: bran stark
content: I know. It's just a stupid dream.

author: osha
content: I've got to get these potatoes to the kitchen. Otherwise they'll put me in chains again.

author: bran stark
content: Osha. The three-eyed raven, what do they say about it north of the Wall?

author: osha
content: They say all sorts of crazy things north of the Wall.

author: qhorin
content: There.

author: jeor
content: Where?

author: qhorin
content: On that mountain.

author: sam
content: I don't see very well.

author: jon snow
content: A fire.

author: qhorin
content: There's a fire. The people sitting around it have better eyes than yours or mine. When they see us coming, that fire becomes a signal. Gives Mance Rayder plenty of time to throw a party in our honor.

author: jeor
content: How many wildlings have joined him?

author: qhorin
content: From what we can tell, all of them. Mance has gathered them all like deer against the wolves. They're almost ready to make their move.

author: jon snow
content: Where?

author: qhorin
content: Somewhere safe. Somewhere south. Can't just march into their midst. And we can't wait for them here with nothing but a pile of stones to protect us.

author: jeor
content: You saying we should fall back to the Wall?

author: qhorin
content: Mance was one of us once. Now he's one of them. He's going to teach them our way of doing things. They'll hit us in force and they won't run away when we hit back. They're gonna be more organized than before, more disciplined, more like us. So we need to be more like them, do things their way. Sneak in, kill Mance, and scatter them to the winds before they can march on the Wall. And to do that

author: jeor
content: We need to get rid of those lookouts.

author: qhorin
content: It's not a job for 400 men. I need to move fast and silent. Harker, Stonesnake, Borba.

author: jon snow
content: Lord Commander, I'd like to join Lord Qhorin.

author: qhorin
content: I've been called lots of things, but that might be my first Lord Qhorin. You're a steward, Snow, not a ranger.

author: jon snow
content: I've fought and killed a wight. How many rangers can say that?

author: qhorin
content: He's the one?

author: jeor
content: Aye. You killed a wight. You also let an old man beat you bloody and take your sword.

author: qhorin
content: Craster? In the boy's defense, that's a tough old goat.

author: sam
content: I could take up Jon's duties while he's gone, my lord. It would be no trouble.

author: jeor
content: Well, I hope you make a better ranger than you do a steward. Go on.

author: xaro
content: So, tell me, how long has your manservant been in love with you?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He's not my manservant and he's not in love with me. He's my advisor and he's my friend.

author: xaro
content: Unlikely. I can almost always tell what a man wants.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what about what a woman wants?

author: xaro
content: Much more complicated. You, for example, what do you want?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: To cross the Narrow Sea and take back the Iron Throne.

author: xaro
content: Why?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Because I promised my khalasar I'd protect them and find them a safe home.

author: xaro
content: You want to conquer the Seven Kingdoms for the Dothraki?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I want them because they're mine by right. The Iron Throne is mine and I will take it.

author: xaro
content: Ah, a conqueror.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And how did you get all of this? Did someone give it to you?

author: xaro
content: No. I come from nothing. I hit the docks like a piece of cargo, except someone normally cares what happens to cargo.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So you wanted more than you had and you took it. You're a conqueror, too. You're just less ambitious.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What do you want, Xaro Xhoan Daxos? At the gates of the city, you bled for me. Why?

author: xaro
content: I will show you why.

author: xaro
content: The door and the vault is made of Valyrian stone. The hardest steel does not make a mark. I offered the greatest locksmiths in Qarth their weight in gold if they could break into it. I made the same offer to the greatest thieves. They all went home empty-handed. The only thing that can open this door is this key.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And behind the door?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And it can all be mine?

author: xaro
content: All? Let us say half. More than enough to buy horses, ships, armies. Enough to go home.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: All I have to do?

author: xaro
content: Is marry me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That was a romantic proposal.

author: xaro
content: I've already married once for love, but the gods stole her from me. I come from nothing. My mother and father never owned a pair of shoes. But marry me, and I will give you the Seven Kingdoms and our children will be princes and princesses.

author: xaro
content: See? I have more ambition than you thought. The time is right, Daenerys Targaryen, First of Your Name. Robert Baratheon is dead.

author: jorah mormont
content: If you cross the sea with an army you bought and a foreign husband who paid for it...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Seven Kingdoms are at war with one another. Four false kings destroying the country.

author: jorah mormont
content: To win Westeros, you need support from Westeros.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The usurper is dead.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Starks fight the Lannisters, and Baratheons fight each other.

author: jorah mormont
content: According to your new friend who earned your trust by cutting his hand?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The time to strike is now. We need to find ships and an army or we'll spend the rest of our lives rotting away at the edge of the world.

author: jorah mormont
content: Rich men do not become rich by giving more than they get. They'll give you ships and soldiers and they'll own you forever. Moving carefully is the hard way, but it's the right way.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And if I'd listened to that advice outside the gates of Qarth, we'd all be dead by now.

author: jorah mormont
content: I know the opportunity before you seems like the last you'll ever have, but you musT-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do not speak to me like I'm a child.

author: jorah mormont
content: I only want-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What do you want? Tell me.

author: jorah mormont
content: To see you on the Iron Throne.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why?

author: jorah mormont
content: You have a good claim. A title. A birthright. But you have something more than that. You may cover it up and deny it, but you have a gentle heart. You would not only be respected and feared, you would be loved. Someone who can rule and should rule. Centuries come and go without a person like that coming into the world. There are times when I look at you and I still can't believe you're real.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So what would you have me do, as my advisor?

author: jorah mormont
content: Make your own way. Find your own ship. You only need one. The allies we need are in Westeros, not Qarth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And how do I get the ship?

author: jorah mormont
content: I'll find it for you. A sound ship with a good captain.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I look forward to meeting him.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi.

author: arya stark
content: You should stand sideface.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Sideface?

author: arya stark
content: Sideways.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Why?

author: arya stark
content: Smaller target.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Am I fighting someone?

author: arya stark
content: You're practicing for a fight. You should practice right.

author: gold cloak
content: Guards! Did you see anything? Go up there. Go and see where he fell from.

author: gold cloak
content: Go up the battlement.

author: woman
content: That is strange.

author: gold cloak
content: Move away. Stand back. He's dead.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I've taken your castle.

author: bran stark
content: Theon?

author: theon greyjoy
content: It's Prince Theon now. Get up. You have to get dressed. I've taken Winterfell. I took it. I'm occupying it. I sent men over the walls with grappling claws and ropes.

author: bran stark
content: Why?

author: theon greyjoy
content: To take the castle.

author: bran stark
content: You went with Robb.

author: theon greyjoy
content: And he sent me back to Pyke. I'm a Greyjoy. I can't fight for Robb and my father both. Where's Hodor?

author: bran stark
content: I don't know.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Find the halfwit.

author: theon greyjoy
content: My men are bringing your people together in the courtyard.

author: theon greyjoy
content: So you and I can go down and tell them - how you've yielded Winterfell to me.

author: bran stark
content: I won't.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes, you will.

author: bran stark
content: I won't. I'll never yield. We'll fight you and throw you out.

author: theon greyjoy
content: The castle is mine. But these people are still yours. You'll yield to keep them safe, to keep them alive. That's what a good lord would do. Think carefully about what you want to say.

author: bran stark
content: Theon. Did you hate us the whole time?

author: bran stark
content: I've yielded Winterfell to Theon.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Louder. Say Prince Theon.

author: bran stark
content: I've yielded Winterfell to Prince Theon. You all know me.

author: farlen
content: Aye, we know you for a steaming sack of shit.

author: bran stark
content: Farlen, you be silent.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Listen to your little lord, Farlen. He has more sense than you do.

author: bran stark
content: All of you should do as he commands.

author: theon greyjoy
content: My father has donned the ancient crown of Salt and Rock and declared himself King of the Iron Islands. He claims the North as well by right of conquest. You are all his subjects.

author: farlen
content: Bugger that. I serve the Starks. If you think you can hold the North with it-

author: ironborn
content: Shut up!

author: theon greyjoy
content: If you serve me as loyally as you served Ned Stark, I will be as good to you as he ever was. Betray me, and you will wish you hadn't. Maester Luwin, send a raven to Pyke informing my father of my victory here. And one to Deepwood Motte to my sister. Inform her that she's to bring You are a maester of the Citadel, sworn to serve the Lord of Winterfell, are you not?

author: luwin
content: I am.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I am the Lord of Winterfell as Bran just informed you. Send the ravens.

author: luwin
content: My lord.

author: osha
content: My Lord Greyjoy.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I see you've finally learned how to address your betters. What do you want? I was brought here a captive.

author: osha
content: You were here the day I was taken.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm the one who took you. What of it?

author: osha
content: Let me serve you.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Serve me how? I need fighters, not kitchen sluts.

author: osha
content: It was Robb Stark who put me in the kitchens. Put a spear in my hand again.

author: theon greyjoy
content: So you can bury it in my neck? Do you take me for a fool? Get up.

author: osha
content: Step aside.

author: osha
content: It's your dream, little lord. The ocean has come to swallow this place. I ain't letting it drown me.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You'll all go about your tasks as usual. And in a few days' time-

author: black lorren
content: Greyjoy!

author: black lorren
content: We caught this one on his way back from Torrhen's Square. Took out two of ours before I got his sword.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Ser Rodrik, it grieves me that we meet as foes.

author: rodrik
content: It grieves me you've less honor than a back alley whore. You were raised here under this roof. These people are your people.

author: theon greyjoy
content: They are not my people.

author: rodrik
content: King Robb thought of you as a brother.

author: theon greyjoy
content: My brothers are dead. They died fighting Stark men, men like you.

author: rodrik
content: Aye, they died fighting a war your father started. Lord Stark raised you among his own sons.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Among them, but not one of them. I was his hostage, taken from my home.

author: rodrik
content: If he were alive to see this

author: theon greyjoy
content: He's not. He's dead. The Seven Kingdoms are at war. And Winterfell is mine.

author: rodrik
content: I should have put a sword in your belly instead of in your hand.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You've served this house faithfully, old man. But keep talking and I'll-

author: theon greyjoy
content: Take him to the cells. Lock him up

author: dagmer
content: My prince. You cannot let that stand. He must pay.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'll lock him in a cell until he rots.

author: dagmer
content: No, he has to pay the iron price. They'll never respect you while he lives.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Ser Rodrik, I sentence you to death!

author: bran stark
content: No! You said no harm would come to them if I yielded.

author: theon greyjoy
content: The old man couldn't keep his mouth shut.

author: luwin
content: I urge you not to make a hasty decision.

author: theon greyjoy
content: He disrespected me in front of my men. That was his decision, not mine.

author: luwin
content: He is worth more to you alive than dead. The Starks will pay. Please, Theon, think what you do.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You'll address me as Prince Theon or you'll be next.

author: dagmer
content: Come.

author: bran stark
content: No! No! Theon! Please. Ser Rodrik!

author: rodrik
content: He who passes the sentence should swing the sword.

author: bran stark
content: I'm begging you.

author: rodrik
content: Coward.

author: bran stark
content: Stop. Stop! Stop right now!

author: theon greyjoy
content: You don't give commands anymore, little lord.

author: bran stark
content: Please, stop this. Please stop him.

author: rodrik
content: Hush now, child. I'm off to see your father.

author: bran stark
content: You said no harm would come! You said no harm would come. Theon, please.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Any last words, old man?

author: rodrik
content: Gods help you, Theon Greyjoy. Now you are truly lost.

author: bran stark
content: Theon, please don't.

author: rickon
content: Do something!

author: bran stark
content: I'll do anything, please! No, please stop it!

author: jon snow
content: Ghost, stay with us. Ghost!

author: qhorin
content: There goes your pet.

author: jon snow
content: He's not a pet.

author: qhorin
content: No, you're right, he's not. You can't tame a wild thing. You can't trust a wild thing.

author: jon snow
content: Ghost is different.

author: qhorin
content: So you think. Wild creatures have their own rules, their own reasons. And you'll never know them. Now the wildlings we're looking for sleep during the day and hunt at night.

author: jon snow
content: I thought you said you couldn't know wild things.

author: qhorin
content: I said you can't. They find a nice cave to hide in while the sun's up and do their killing when it's dark.

author: jon snow
content: We could do the same.

author: qhorin
content: No, we couldn't. This is their country. They know where to walk, where not to walk. I've lost good men who fell into a crevasse they didn't see till they were in it.

author: jon snow
content: My father always said I'm of the North.

author: jon snow
content: I wasn't joking.

author: qhorin
content: Look around, boy. This look like home to you? You start thinking you know this place, it will kill you. You understand me?

author: qhorin
content: No, you don't. We're at war. We've always been at war. It's never going to end 'cause we're not fighting an enemy. We're fighting the North, and it's not going anywhere. The Watch has given you a great gift. You only have one thing to give in return, your life.

author: jon snow
content: I'll gladly give my life.

author: qhorin
content: I don't want you to be glad about it. I want you to curse and fight until your heart's done pumping. And know this, boy. Your death will be a gift for them south of the Wall. They'll never know what you've done. They'll never know how you died. They won't even know your damn name. But they'll be alive because some nameless bastard north of the Wall gave his life for theirs. Now, do you understand me?

author: jon snow
content: I do.

author: qhorin
content: You're even dumber than you look. It's just words, boy, to keep us a little warmer in the night. Make us feel like we've got a purpose. Come on. We've got to find these goat fuckers before night falls and they find us.

author: tywin lannister
content: Can you read?

author: amory
content: My lord?

author: tywin lannister
content: This letter detailing our infantry movements was meant for Lord Damon of House Marbrand. It was sent to Lord Marlyn of House Dormand.

author: amory
content: My apologies, my lord. I must have-

author: tywin lannister
content: Girl, fetch me the History of the Greater and the Lesser Houses. It's the one on this-

author: tywin lannister
content: My cupbearer can read better than you.

author: tywin lannister
content: To whom does House Dormand owe allegiance?

author: armory
content: My lord, I-

author: tywin lannister
content: To the Starks of Winterfell! Who have twenty thousand men and my son! I judged you might be good for something more than brutalizing peasants. I see I overestimated you. If you ever put my son's life at risk again, I'll Leave us.

author: tywin lannister
content: Put the book away, girl. Maybe you should devise our next battle plan while you're about it.

author: guard
content: Lord Petyr Baelish.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm. Give us the room.

author: tywin lannister
content: Clear all this.

author: petyr baelish
content: Lord Tywin.

author: tywin lannister
content: Baelish.

author: tywin lannister
content: Wine?

author: petyr baelish
content: Thank you.

author: tywin lannister
content: What news from the capital?

author: petyr baelish
content: I traveled here directly from Renly Baratheon's camp.

author: tywin lannister
content: Ah, the late King Renly. Rather a short reign. Murdered by a woman, I hear.

author: petyr baelish
content: So they say. There has been talk of other forces at work. Dark forces.

author: tywin lannister
content: Here. Men love to blame demons when their grand plans unravel.

author: petyr baelish
content: It is my belief that a moment of chaos affords opportunities lost soon after.

author: tywin lannister
content: You say that as if you were the first man alive to think it. Yes, a crisis is an opportunity. What other brilliant insights have you brought me today?

author: petyr baelish
content: After the Lannisters and the Starks, the Tyrells command the largest host. Their lands are the most fertile in the Seven Kingdoms, feeding horses and soldiers.

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes, yes, yes.

author: petyr baelish
content: The Tyrells have not yet declared for any of the surviving kings. Loras wants revenge. He blames Stannis for Renly's death. And Margaery-

author: tywin lannister
content: Wants to be queen.

author: petyr baelish
content: Yes, she does.

author: tywin lannister
content: House Tyrell rebelled against the Iron Throne. Against my grandson.

author: petyr baelish
content: They did. And perhaps that treason should be punished one day, after Stannis and Robb Stark are defeated.

author: tywin lannister
content: More wine for Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: If you will allow me to represent your family's interests, I believe that an advantageous agreement TYWIN

author: petyr baelish
content: They have.

author: arya stark
content: Pardon, my lord.

author: petyr baelish
content: It's only wine.

author: tywin lannister
content: You would ride there yourself?

author: petyr baelish
content: Tonight, with your leave.

author: tywin lannister
content: I'll have an answer by nightfall. That'll be all, girl.

author: tywin lannister
content: And what else?

author: petyr baelish
content: On your son Tyrion's directive, I met with Catelyn Stark.

author: tywin lannister
content: Why?

author: petyr baelish
content: He had an interesting proposal for her concerning her daughters.

author: tywin lannister
content: Hmm.

author: jon snow
content: A girl.

author: qhorin
content: A wildling.

author: jon snow
content: We could question her.

author: qhorin
content: You could. She won't answer. I've known a wildling to bite off his tongue instead of talking.

author: jon snow
content: What's your name?

author: ygritte
content: Ygritte.

author: qhorin
content: She was reaching for this ax when you got to her. Give her half a chance, she'll bury it in your face.

author: ygritte
content: I gave you my name.

author: jon snow
content: I'm Jon Snow.

author: ygritte
content: You ought to burn them you killed.

author: qhorin
content: We'd need a big fire for that. Tell me, Ygritte. Why do you want us to build a big fire? Are there some more friends in the area?

author: ygritte
content: Burn them or maybe you'll need those swords again.

author: qhorin
content: Our boy here's already killed one dead man. He can do it again if he has to. What waits beyond the pass?

author: ygritte
content: The Free Folk.

author: qhorin
content: How many?

author: ygritte
content: Hundreds and thousands. More than you've ever seen, crow.

author: qhorin
content: Why come to the mountains? What's in the Frostfangs your king could want?

author: qhorin
content: Do you mean to march on the Wall?

author: qhorin
content: Do you know who I am, girl?

author: ygritte
content: Qhorin Halfhand.

author: qhorin
content: Tell me true. If your people captured me, would they take me prisoner?

author: ygritte
content: They'd take your head off your shoulders if they was feeling kind. If not, they'd kill you slow.

author: qhorin
content: We have no food for her. Can't spare a man to watch her. Can't let her go. She'll bring Mance Rayder's army down on us. It needs to be done. Want me to do it?

author: jon snow
content: No. No, I'll do it.

author: qhorin
content: Come, brothers. We'll leave him to it. We'll meet you at the top. Don't take too long. We're deep in their country now.

author: ygritte
content: You never killed a woman before, did you? You don't need to do it. Mance would take you. I know he would. There's secret ways. The crows would never catch us.

author: jon snow
content: I'm as much a crow as they are.

author: ygritte
content: Will you burn me? After?

author: jon snow
content: Can't. Someone might see the smoke.

author: ygritte
content: Strike hard and true, Jon Snow, or I'll come back and haunt you. That's cold.

author: ygritte
content: Go on. Be quick about it.

author: ygritte
content: Do it. Bastard, do it!

author: ygritte
content: You can't do it. We both know it.

author: ygritte
content: The sun's going down, Jon Snow. And your friends are nowhere close.

author: jon snow
content: I'll find them.

author: ygritte
content: Call for them. Go on. Call loudly.

author: septon
content: May the Seven guide the princess on her journey. May the Mother give her health. May the crone give her wisdom. May the warrior give her courage.

author: cersei lannister
content: One day I pray you love someone. I pray you love her so much, when you close your eyes, you see her face. I want that for you. I want you to know what it's like to love someone, to truly love someone. Before I take her from you.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You sound like a little cat mewling for his mother. Princes don't cry.

author: sansa stark
content: I saw you cry.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Did you say something, my lady?

author: sansa stark
content: My little brother cried when I left Winterfell.

author: joffrey lannister
content: So?

author: sansa stark
content: It seems a normal thing.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Is your little brother a prince?

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Not really relevant then, is it? Come, dog.

author: man
content: Hail Joffrey! Hail to the King. Seven blessings on you, Your Grace.

author: man
content: Murderer! Bastard!

author: man
content: All hail the King.

author: man
content: He's no king.

author: man
content: He's a bastard!

author: man
content: Please, Your Grace, we're hungry.

author: man
content: Freak.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Get the Prince back to the Keep now.

author: guard
content: Yes, my lord. Come, quickly.

author: woman
content: Please, Your Grace, give us some food!

author: man
content: Bread, Your Grace, please!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Who threw that? I want the man who threw that. Find who did that and bring him to me!

author: guard
content: Hold on!

author: guard
content: Hold them back!

author: joffrey lannister
content: Just kill them! Kill them all!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Move. Move!

author: guard
content: Pull back!

author: man
content: Tear him to pieces!

author: joffrey lannister
content: What are you doing? I want these people executed!

author: sandor clegane
content: And they want the same for you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where's Sansa?

author: guard
content: Through the door.

author: guard
content: Come on.

author: guard
content: Push hard.

author: meryn
content: Protect the king!

author: guard
content: Get back!

author: guard
content: Fall back! Keep him safe!

author: guard
content: Come in! Come in!

author: cuard
content: Keep him safe!

author: crowd
content: Motherfucker! Brotherfucker!

author: guard
content: Watch out. Hold them back.

author: man
content: Hey.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Traitors! I'll have all their heads.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, you blind, bloody fool!

author: joffrey lannister
content: You can't insult me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We've had vicious kings and we've had idiot kings, but I don't know if we've ever been cursed with a vicious idiot for a king.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You can't-

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can, I am.

author: joffrey lannister
content: They attacked me!

author: tyrion lannister
content: They threw a cow pie at you, so you decided to kill them all? They're starving, you fool! All because of a war you started.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You're talking to a king!

author: tyrion lannister
content: And now I've struck a king. Did my hand fall from my wrist? Where is the Stark girl?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Let them have her!

author: tyrion lannister
content: If she dies, you'll never get your Uncle Jaime back! You owe him quite a bit, you know.

author: man
content: Where are you going?

author: man
content: You ever been fucked, little girl? Come here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Take some men and go and find the Stark girl.

author: meryn
content: I take my orders from the king.

author: man
content: Where? This way.

author: sansa stark
content: Please! No! No!

author: man
content: Please!

author: sandor clegane
content: You're all right now, little bird. You're all right.

author: man
content: We'll get you.

author: man
content: This way.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Are you hurt, my lady?

author: sandor clegane
content: The little birdo s bleeding. Someone take her back to her cage. See to that cut.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well done, Clegane.

author: sandor clegane
content: I didn't do it for you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He shouldn't make me wait.

author: xaro
content: The Spice King is the second wealthiest man in Qarth. He makes everyone wait. Of course, you could have avoided this embarrassment if you married the wealthiest man in Qarth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I already have a husband.

author: xaro
content: Khal Drogo is gone, Khaleesi. You are far too young to be a widow forever and far too beautiful.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you are far too smart to think that I will succumb to flattery.

author: xaro
content: I have traveled very far in my life and met many women, but none that are immune to flattery.

author: spice king
content: The Mother of Dragons!

author: xaro
content: Ah, here he comes.

author: spice king
content: Forgive me. I had terrible dreams last night. Terrible dreams. I could not sleep until the sun was shining and the birds were singing. Look what a beauty you are now the Red Waste has been washed off you. I am sorry about all that unpleasantness. The silver hair of a true Targaryen. Xaro Xhoan Daxos, she is far too lovely for a glorified dockworker like yourself.

author: xaro
content: Very true, and yet they say that your grandfather, who sold pepper off the back of a wagon, married a lady far lovelier and higher born than himself.

author: spice king
content: Every lady alive was lovelier and higher born than my grandfather. Did my servants not offer you something to eat, to drink? I'll have them flogged in the square.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you, my lord. You are a gracious host, but there is no servant alive that can bring me what I want.

author: spice king
content: Oh, she has a talent for drama, this one. So, my little princess, what is it you want?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My birthright. The Seven Kingdoms of Westeros.

author: spice king
content: I fear I'm no better than a servant in this regard. I cannot give you what I do not have.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not asking you for the kingdoms. I'm asking you for ships.

author: spice king
content: I need to cross the Narrow Sea. I need my ships as well. I use them, you see, to bring spices from one port to another.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Whatever you grant me now will be repaid three times over when I retake the Iron Throne.

author: spice king
content: Retake? Did you once sit on the Iron Throne?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My father sat there, before he was murdered.

author: spice king
content: But if you did not sit on it yourself, would it not be correct to say "take the Iron Throne"?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I didn't come here to argue grammar.

author: spice king
content: Of course not. You came to take my ships. So let me explain my position, little princess. Unlike you, I do not have exalted ancestors. I make my living by trade. And I judge every trade on its merits. You ask for ships. You say I shall be repaid triple. I do not doubt your honesty or your intentions. But before you repay your debts, you must seize the Seven Kingdoms. Do you have an army?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Not yet.

author: spice king
content: You do not have an army. Do you have powerful allies in Westeros?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: There are many there that support my claim.

author: spice king
content: When were you there last?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I left when I was a baby.

author: spice king
content: So, in truth, you have no allies.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The people will rise to fight for their rightful queen when I return.

author: spice king
content: Ah. Forgive me, little princess, but I cannot make an investment based on wishes and dreams. Now if you'll pardon me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do you know lllyrio Mopatis, Magister of Pentos? Yes, we've met.

author: spice king
content: A shrewd man.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: For my wedding, he gave me three petrified dragon eggs. He believed The world believed that the ages had turned them to stone. How many centuries has it been since dragons roamed the skies? But I dreamt that if I carried those eggs into a great fire, they would hatch. When I stepped into the fire, my own people thought I was mad. But when the fire burned out, I was unhurt, the Mother of Dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do you understand? I'm no ordinary woman. My dreams come true.

author: spice king
content: I admire your passion. But in business, I trust in logic, not passion. I'm sorry, little princess.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I am not your little princess. I am Daenerys Stormborn of the blood of Old Valyria, and I will take what is mine. With fire and blood, I will take it.

author: spice king
content: Yes, my lady, but not with my ships.

author: tywin lannister
content: Who taught you to read?

author: arya stark
content: My father, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: Hmm. I taught my son Jaime to read. The maester came to me one day, told me he wasn't learning. He couldn't make sense of the letters. He reversed them in his head. The maester said he'd heard tell of this affliction and that we simply must accept it. Ha! After that, I sat Jaime down for four hours every day until he learned. He hated me for it, for a time. For a long time. But he learned. Hmm. Where is your father? Is he alive? Who was he?

author: arya stark
content: A stonemason.

author: tywin lannister
content: A stonemason who could read? Hmm.

author: arya stark
content: He taught himself.

author: tywin lannister
content: Quite a man. What killed him?

author: arya stark
content: Loyalty.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're a sharp little thing, aren't you?

author: arya stark
content: Did... Forgive me, my lord. I shouldn't ask questions.

author: tywin lannister
content: No. But you've already begun.

author: arya stark
content: Did you know your father, my lord?

author: tywin lannister
content: I did. I grew up with him. I watched him grow old.

author: tywin lannister
content: He loved us. He was a good man, but a weak man. A weak man who nearly destroyed our house and name. I'm cold.

author: arya stark
content: I'll fetch more wood for the fire, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm.

author: amory
content: Where are you going, girl?

author: arya stark
content: The armory, my lord.

author: amory
content: Why?

author: arya stark
content: Lord Tywin sent me.

author: amory
content: What might this be?

author: arya stark
content: Lord Tywin gave it to me.

author: amory
content: What for?

author: arya stark
content: To take to the armory.

author: amory
content: Why would he do that? Let's go and ask him.

author: amory
content: Move! Get out of the way!

author: arya stark
content: Amory Lorch.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl has named a second name. A man will do what must be done.

author: arya stark
content: Now!

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl cannot tell a man when exactly he must do a thing. A man cannot make a thing happen before its time.

author: arya stark
content: But he's going to tell Tywin. He's getting away. It has to be now.

author: tywin lannister
content: Guard!

author: soldier
content: Your Grace.

author: soldier
content: My honor, Your Grace.

author: quent
content: Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: Quent.

author: robb stark
content: Lady Talisa.

author: talisa
content: Your Grace. I'm not sure I'm a lady. Westerosi customs are still a bit foreign to me.

author: robb stark
content: It's hard to keep all the rules straight. But if I remember my lessons, a woman of noble birth is always called a lady. Unless she's a queen or a princess. I could find someone who knows.

author: talisa
content: Why are you so sure I'm of noble birth?

author: robb stark
content: Because it's obvious.

author: talisa
content: What if I told you my father sold lace on the Long Bridge, and my mother, my brother, and I lived with him above our shop?

author: robb stark
content: I'd call you a liar.

author: talisa
content: Not very noble to accuse a lady of dishonesty.

author: talisa
content: I always thought I was a brilliant liar.

author: robb stark
content: Better at amputations, I'm afraid.

author: robb stark
content: Quite a pretty spot.

author: talisa
content: Will we be here long?

author: robb stark
content: I couldn't really discuss troop movements with you.

author: talisa
content: I'm not a spy.

author: robb stark
content: Of course, a spy would deny being a spy.

author: talisa
content: You're right. You've found me out. I'm writing a letter to the Lannisters. "The Young Wolf is on the move. "

author: robb stark
content: Perhaps you'd join me... If you've got time, of course, for, well-

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb.

author: robb stark
content: Mother. Mother, this is Lady Talisa. She's been helping with the wounded. She's been very... helpful.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lady Talisa.

author: talisa
content: Lady Stark.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lady Talisa...?

author: talisa
content: Maegyr.

author: catelyn stark
content: Maegyr? Forgive me, I do not know this name.

author: talisa
content: An uncommon name here. An old name in Volantis. Excuse me, my lady. Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: I've missed you.

author: catelyn stark
content: Yes, you look positively forlorn.

author: robb stark
content: You surprised me, that's all. I didn't think I'd see you today.

author: catelyn stark
content: I wish that you were free to follow your heart.

author: robb stark
content: I know.

author: catelyn stark
content: You have inherited your father's responsibilities. I'm afraid they come at a cost. You are promised to another.

author: catelyn stark
content: A debt that must be paid.

author: robb stark
content: I haven't forgotten.

author: roose bolton
content: Your Grace. My lady. News from Winterfell.

author: ygritte
content: Your brothers desert you? I can tell you which way to go.

author: jon snow
content: We'll stop here. Too dark to go any farther today.

author: ygritte
content: Here? There's no shelter here.

author: jon snow
content: There's no shelter anywhere.

author: ygritte
content: There is if you know where to look. The cold could kill us both. If you light a fire-

author: jon snow
content: No fire.

author: ygritte
content: But a fire is-

author: ygritte
content: Have it your way.

author: ygritte
content: We'll stay warmer if we stay close.

author: ygritte
content: Bet you freeze to death before I do. Bet your life.

author: ygritte
content: Think they're out looking for you?

author: jon snow
content: Yes.

author: ygritte
content: Think they'll find you?

author: ygritte
content: You're brave. Stupid, but brave.

author: jon snow
content: We start again at first light. Get some sleep.

author: jon snow
content: Stop moving.

author: ygritte
content: I'm just trying to get comfortable.

author: jon snow
content: Stop it!

author: jon snow
content: You're still moving.

author: ygritte
content: Was I? I didn't notice that time.

author: robb stark
content: This cannot be true.

author: roose
content: We've had ravens from White Harbor, Barrowton and the Dreadfort. I'm afraid it is true.

author: robb stark
content: Why? Why would Theon-

author: roose
content: Because the Greyjoys are treasonous whores.

author: robb stark
content: My brothers?

author: roose
content: We've heard nothing of them. But Rodrik Cassel is dead.

author: catelyn stark
content: I told you, never trust a Greyjoy!

author: robb stark
content: I must go north at once.

author: roose
content: There's still a war to win, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: How can I call myself king if I can't hold my own castle? How can I ask men to follow me if I can't-

author: roose
content: You are a king. And that means you don't have to do everything yourself.

author: catelyn stark
content: Let me go and talk to Theon.

author: robb stark
content: There will be no talk. He will die for this.

author: roose
content: Theon holds the castle with a skeleton crew. Let me send word to my bastard at the Dreadfort. He can raise a few hundred men and retake Winterfell before the new moon. We have the Lannisters on the run. If you march all the way back north now, you'll lose what you gained. My boy would be honored to bring you Prince Theon's head.

author: robb stark
content: Tell your son Bran and Rickon's safety is paramount. And Theon, I want him brought to me alive. I want to look him in the eye and ask him why. And then I'll take his head myself.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Why on earth would I trust the word of a lying little savage like you?

author: osha
content: I'm no liar.

author: theon greyjoy
content: All wildlings are liars and savages with no loyalty to anything or anyone.

author: osha
content: I done what I had to do to stay alive. I hate the Starks as well as you do. Let me serve you, my lord.

author: theon greyjoy
content: How? And don't tell me to put a spear in your hand.

author: osha
content: There are other ways to serve, my lord.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm a prince now, and you'd do well-

author: ahsa
content: There are other ways to serve, my prince.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Like what?

author: osha
content: We know things, the free people.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You know things? Like what? How to eat dirt?

author: osha
content: Other things.

author: osha
content: Savage things.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Wait outside.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I always wondered what you had under there.

author: osha
content: It comes at a price.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm not killing you. That's your price.

author: osha
content: I already had that.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What do you want then, other than your miserable life?

author: ahsa
content: What all free people want. My freedom.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Well, you shall have it, then. But only if you serve me well.

author: sansa stark
content: Ow!

author: shae
content: Shh. It's not deep.

author: sansa stark
content: I thought they were going to kill me.

author: shae
content: They thought so, too.

author: sansa stark
content: He hated me, the man who hit me. I saw it in his eyes. Hated me. He never met me before, but he wanted to hurt me.

author: shae
content: Of course he did.

author: sansa stark
content: Why? Why would a stranger-

author: shae
content: You are everything he will never have. Your horse eats better than his children. It doesn't matter now. He's dead.

author: sansa stark
content: I would have given them bread if I had it. I hate the king more than any of them.

author: shae
content: Don't say these things. If the wrong people hear you-

author: sansa stark
content: But you're not the wrong people.

author: shae
content: Don't trust anybody. Life is safer that way.

author: guard
content: And where are you going?

author: osha
content: I have something for you from Prince Theon.

author: guard
content: What?

author: osha
content: Me. He says I'm to make the rounds. And keep you warm.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Spice King refuses me because I'm a bad investment. The Silk King won't support me because of his business with the Lannisters. Why offend his best customer? And the Copper King offers me a single ship on the condition that I lie with him for a night. Does he think I will whore myself for a boat?

author: xaro
content: When I came to this city, I had nothing. Truly nothing. I slept by the docks. And when I could find work loading the ships, I would eat. If not, I dreamed of food. Today, I am the richest man in Qarth. Do you think the path from poverty to wealth is always pure and honorable? I have done many things, Khaleesi, that a righteous man would condemn. And here I am, with no regrets.

author: xaro
content: Bar the gates. Ring the bells. Slowly, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Where are they? Where are my dragons?

author: theon greyjoy
content: A cripple? You let a cripple escape? The boy can't walk, but somehow he slipped past you?

author: black lorren
content: The giant must have took him.

author: theon greyjoy
content: The giant? Hodor? Oh, that's all right, then. You let a halfwit escape with a cripple. And Rickon, too? The little one?

author: black lorren
content: Gone, along with the wildling woman. The one you were fucking.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Right. Get the horses and the hounds.

author: man
content: Come on, find the scent. Where they going?

author: dagmer
content: Halt!

author: theon greyjoy
content: Enjoying your first hunt?
