author: luwin
content: So far, hunting seems very similar to riding, my lord.

author: theon greyjoy
content: With hunting, there's blood at the end.

author: luwin
content: They're little boys.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I was a little boy when I was torn away from my home and brought here. So I kept my word. I never ran away. If I find them soon enough, I won't hurt them. Well, I'll hurt them, but I won't kill them.

author: luwin
content: Those boys are of far more value to you alive than dead.

author: theon greyjoy
content: They have no value to me missing.

author: luwin
content: Robb will have sent a force to retake Winterfell by now.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Robb's in the Riverlands. My sister's in Deepwood Motte. She'll get here long before they do. And Ned Stark always said 500 men could hold Winterfell again 10,000.

author: man
content: We have a scent!

author: theon greyjoy
content: The hounds have the scent. Come, Maester, don't look so grim. It's all just a game.

author: osha
content: We should have took more food.

author: bran stark
content: We couldn't risk going to the kitchens.

author: osha
content: Those people all love you. They would have given you whatever you needed.

author: bran stark
content: And if Theon found out, he'd hang them.

author: osha
content: The boy can't survive on walnuts.

author: rickon
content: I'm fine.

author: osha
content: We've been walking since before sunrise. Even Hodor will tire.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: osha
content: Even you, sweet giant.

author: bran stark
content: Wait, I know that farm. I sent those two Winterfell orphans there.

author: rickon
content: Jack and Billy. They'll give us some food.

author: bran stark
content: We can't risk it. If Theon tracks us here, he'll torture them until he finds out where we are.

author: rikon
content: Billy climbs a tree better than anyone.

author: osha
content: You've never seen me climb a tree, little man.

author: bran stark
content: They'll be after us with hounds.

author: osha
content: We got a good start on them, but we can't outrun hounds forever.

author: ygritte
content: Did you pull a knife on me in the night?

author: ygritte
content: What's the matter? Can't be the first time you pressed your bone against a woman's arse.

author: jon snow
content: Let's move.

author: ygritte
content: It is the first time. How old are you, boy?

author: jon snow
content: I'm a man of the Night's Watch.

author: ygritte
content: You're a boy who's never been with a girl. Don't your stones start to hurt if your bone never gets-

author: jon snow
content: Don't call them that.

author: ygritte
content: What, stones? Or bone?

author: jon snow
content: Neither. Both.

author: jon snow
content: Move!

author: ygritte
content: I heard they get all swollen and bruised if you don't use them. Of course, maybe that's just what the lads say when they want me feeling sorry for them. As if I'd feel sorry for them. Are there no girl crows?

author: jon snow
content: There are no women of the Night's Watch, no.

author: ygritte
content: So the lads just do it with each other?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: ygritte
content: Never?

author: jon snow
content: Never. We swore an oath.

author: ygritte
content: You have sheep at the Wall? With your hands, then? No wonder you're all so miserable.

author: jon snow
content: Would you please shut up?

author: ygritte
content: Would you please shut up? You think you're better than me, crow. I'm a free woman.

author: jon snow
content: You're a free woman?

author: ygritte
content: I might be your prisoner, but I'm a free woman.

author: jon snow
content: If you're my prisoner, you're not a free woman. That's what "prisoner" means.

author: ygritte
content: And you think you're free? You swore some stupid oath and now you can never touch a girl.

author: jon snow
content: It was my choice to say the words.

author: ygritte
content: So you don't like girls?

author: jon snow
content: Of course I like girls.

author: ygritte
content: But you chose never to touch them.

author: jon snow
content: That's the price you pay if you want to be a man of the Night's Watch.

author: ygritte
content: So instead of getting naked with a girl, you'd prefer to invade our lands-

author: jon snow
content: Invade your lands? Wildlings raid our lands all the time. Some of them tried to kill my little brother, a crippled boy!

author: ygritte
content: They're not your lands! We've been here the whole time. You lot came along and just put up a big wall and said it was yours.

author: jon snow
content: My father was Ned Stark. I have the blood of the First Men. My ancestors lived here, same as yours.

author: ygritte
content: So why are you fighting us?

author: man
content: Go on. Now I want you to tell me what happened. Come on, this way. Come on, speak up. Speak up.

author: tywin lannister
content: Wolfsbane. A rare substance. This is no common assassin.

author: mountian
content: We hanged twenty men last night.

author: tywin lannister
content: I don't care if you hanged a hundred. A man tried to kill me. I want his name and I want his head.

author: mountain
content: We think it was an infiltrator from the Brotherhood Without Banners.

author: tywin lannister
content: Pretentious name for a band of outlaws. We can't allow rebels behind our lines to harass us with impunity. We look like fools and they look like heroes. That's how kings fall. I want them dead, every one.

author: mountain
content: Killing them isn't the problem. It's finding them. Have you gone soft, Clegane? I always thought you had a talent for violence.

author: tywin lannister
content: Burn the villages, burn the farms. Let them know what it means to choose the wrong side.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm. Is that mutton?

author: arya stark
content: Yes, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: Don't like mutton.

author: arya stark
content: I'll bring something else.

author: tywin lannister
content: Leave it. Are you hungry?

author: arya stark
content: No.

author: tywin lannister
content: Of course you are. Eat.

author: arya stark
content: I'll eat in the kitchen later.

author: tywin lannister
content: It's bad manners to refuse a lordo s offer. Sit. Eat.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're small for your age. I suppose you've been underfed your whole life.

author: arya stark
content: I eat a lot. I just don't grow.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm. This will be my last war. Win or lose.

author: arya stark
content: Have you ever lost before?

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you think I'd be in my position if I had lost a war?

author: tywin lannister
content: But this is the one I'll be remembered for. The War of the Five Kings, they're calling it. My legacy will be determined in the coming months.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you know what legacy means? It's what you pass down to your children and your children's children. It's what remains of you when you're gone. Harren the Black thought this castle would be his legacy. The greatest fortress ever built.

author: tywin lannister
content: The tallest towers, the strongest walls. The Great Hall had thirty-five hearths. Thirty-five. Can you imagine? Look at it now. A blasted ruin. Do you know what happened?

author: arya stark
content: Dragons?

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes. Dragons happened.

author: tywin lannister
content: Harrenhal was built to withstand an attack from the land. A million men could have marched on these walls, and a million men would have been repelled. But an attack from the air with dragon fire, Mmm-mmm. Harren and all his sons roasted alive within these walls. Aegon Targaryen changed the rules. That's why every child alive still knows his name

author: arya stark
content: Aegon and his sisters.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm?

author: arya stark
content: It wasn't just Aegon riding his dragon. It was Rhaenys and Visenya, too.

author: tywin lannister
content: Correct. A student of history, are you?

author: arya stark
content: Rhaenys rode Meraxes. Visenya rode Vhagar.

author: tywin lannister
content: I'm sure I knew that when I was a boy.

author: arya stark
content: Visenya Targaryen was a great warrior. She had a Valyrian steel sword she called Dark Sister.

author: tywin lannister
content: Hmm. She's a heroine of yours, I take it?

author: tywin lannister
content: Aren't most girls more interested in the pretty maidens from the songs? Jonquil with the flowers in her hair?

author: arya stark
content: Most girls are idiots.

author: tywin lannister
content: You remind me of my daughter. Where did you learn all this stuff about Visenya and her Valyrian steel sword?

author: arya stark
content: From my father.

author: tywin lannister
content: He was a well-read stonemason. Can't say I've ever met a literate stonemason.

author: arya stark
content: Have you met many stonemasons, my lord?

author: tywin lannister
content: Careful now, girl. I enjoy you, but be careful. Take that back to the kitchen. Eat what you want.

author: tywin lannister
content: And, girl.

author: tywin lannister
content: M'lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: Lowborn girls say "m'lord," not "my lord. " If you're going to pose as a commoner, you should do it properly.

author: arya stark
content: My mother served Lady Dustin for many years, my lord. She taught me how to speak proper Properly.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're too smart for your own good. Has anyone told you that?

author: arya stark
content: Yes.

author: tywin lannister
content: Go on.

author: sansa stark
content: I beg pardon, ser. I should have come to you after to thank you for saving me. You were so brave.

author: sandor clegane
content: Brave? A dog doesn't need courage to chase off rats.

author: sansa stark
content: Does it give you joy to scare people?

author: sandor clegane
content: No, it gives me joy to kill people.

author: sandor clegane
content: Spare me. You can't tell me Lord Eddard Stark of Winterfell never killed a man.

author: sansa stark
content: It was his duty. He never liked it.

author: sandor clegane
content: Is that what he told you? He lied. Killing is the sweetest thing there is.

author: sansa stark
content: Why are you always so hateful?

author: sandor clegane
content: You'll be glad of the hateful things I do someday when you're queen and I'm all that stands between you and your beloved king.

author: xaro
content: I've demanded a meeting of the Thirteen. One of them did this or knows who did.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You are one of the Thirteen.

author: xaro
content: If I wanted your dragons, I would have taken them. They mean nothing to me on their own.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Nothing? They're more valuable than anything in the world.

author: xaro
content: Shall we look inside my vault and see what selling your dragons would buy me I cannot buy already? We will get them back.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: There is no we, so why would you help me get them back?

author: xaro
content: I took you under my protection in front of the rulers of my city. A man is what others say he is and no more. If they say that Xaro Xhoan Daxos is a liar, my word is worth nothing. I cannot let this thing happen to you under my roof.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But it did happen under your roof.

author: xaro
content: Khaleesi, many times in my life, I have been-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't care where you've been.

author: ygritte
content: You think we're savages because we don't live in stone castles. We can't make steel as good as yours, it's true, but We're free. If someone tried to tell us we couldn't lie down as man and woman, we'd shove a spear up his arse. We don't go serving some shit king who's only king because his father was.

author: jon snow
content: No. No, you serve Mance Rayder, the King beyond the Wall.

author: ygritte
content: We chose Mance Rayder to lead us. He was a crow, same as you, but he wanted to be free. You could be free, too. You don't need to live your whole life taking commands from old men. Wake up when you want to wake up. I could show you the streams to fish, the woods to hunt. Build yourself a cabin and find a woman to lie with in the night.

author: ygritte
content: You're a pretty lad. The girls would claw each other's eyes out to get naked with you.

author: jon snow
content: Walk.

author: ygritte
content: I could teach you how to do it.

author: jon snow
content: I know how to do it.

author: ygritte
content: You know nothing, Jon Snow.

author: robb stark
content: And what did she say?

author: alton
content: She admired your spirit, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: And what then?

author: alton
content: She, uh...

author: robb stark
content: If every man were held accountable for the actions of every distant relative, Ser Alton, we'd all hang.

author: alton
content: She tore the paper in half, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: You've acted with honor. I thank you for it. Lord Karstark, see that Ser Alton's pen is clean, and give him a hot supper.

author: rickard karstark
content: Ser Alton's pen is occupied, Your Grace. The prisoners from the Yellow Fork.

author: roose
content: Too many prisoners.

author: robb stark
content: Is there room for Ser Alton?

author: rickard karstark
content: Does he need to lie down?

author: robb stark
content: Have the men build him a new pen. Put him in with the Kingslayer for now. Have your boy watch over them.

author: rickard karstark
content: Torrhen.

author: robb stark
content: That will be all.

author: talisa
content: Your Grace. A minute of your time?

author: talisa
content: I've been treating your wounded men.

author: robb stark
content: And my enemies, as some of my bannermen are fond of mentioning.

author: talisa
content: They're not my enemies.

author: robb stark
content: That's what I tell my bannermen.

author: talisa
content: I've already run through the supplies I brought with me. Some are easily replaced. Egg yolks, turpentine, oil of roses.

author: robb stark
content: But some are not.

author: talisa
content: I need silk for stitching.

author: talisa
content: I need fennel root for those with fever, willow bark. Mostly I need milk of the poppy. You saw what it was like to amputate a foot without any. I assume there will be more loss of limb before this war is over.

author: robb stark
content: If you need help finding these-

author: talisa
content: I know where to find them. I'm sorry, I shouldn't interrupt you.

author: robb stark
content: Continue, my lady.

author: talisa
content: You're riding to the Crag to negotiate a surrender?

author: robb stark
content: Yes.

author: talisa
content: The Crag will have a maester and he will have what I need.

author: robb stark
content: I expect he will.

author: talisa
content: If I could write a list-

author: robb stark
content: Come with me to the Crag.

author: talisa
content: I don't think that will be-

author: robb stark
content: Let the maester show you his stores. I want the wounded men to be treated well, all the wounded men.

author: woman
content: Children, come inside, quick. Come on.

author: child
content: Hurry up!

author: man
content: Can't find anything, ser. They've lost the scent.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Try again.

author: man
content: We've circled this farmhouse twice. There's no sign of them.

author: luwin
content: We could start the search fresh in the morning, my lord.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm looking at spending the rest of my life being treated like a fool and a eunuch by my own people. Ask yourself, is there anything I wouldn't do to stop that from happening? The hounds will find the scent again. I'll beat them until they do. I'll whip every man here until I have both those boys in hand. And once I've got them, the pampered little shits It's better to be cruel than weak.

author: man
content: Prince Theon.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Where are they?

author: winterfell shepherd
content: Who, m'lord?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The Stark boys. Where are they?

author: winterfell shepherd
content: I don't know. I seen no one.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Think harder.

author: winterfell shepherd
content: I swear, m'lord. I don't know.

author: dagmer
content: My lord, over here. I think I've found what we're looking for.

author: dagmer
content: Send the old man home.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Go back to Winterfell. Take him back.

author: luwin
content: Theon, don't do this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You came back.

author: jorah mormont
content: As soon as I heard. Do you know anything?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Irri is dead.

author: jorah mormont
content: I know. She was a good-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: She's dead. She died alone. She died for me and I couldn't protect her.

author: jorah mormont
content: Doreah?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We can't find her. She must be dead, too. I led my people out of the Red Waste and into the slaughterhouse.

author: jorah mormont
content: I should have been here.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You went to find me a ship.

author: jorah mormont
content: My place is by your side. I shouldn't have left you alone with these people.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: These people"?

author: jorah mormont
content: They are not to be trusted.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And who is to be trusted? Who are my people? The Targaryens? I only knew one, my brother, and he would have let a thousand men rape me if it had got him the crown. The Dothraki? Most of them turned on me the day that Khal Drogo fell from his horse.

author: jorah mormont
content: Your people are in Westeros.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The people in Westeros don't know I'm alive.

author: jorah mormont
content: They will soon enough.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And then what? They'll pray for my return? They'll wave dragon banners and shout my name? That's what my brother believed and he was a fool.

author: jorah mormont
content: You are not your brother. Trust me, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: There it is. "Trust me. " And it's you I should trust, Ser Jorah? Only you? I don't need trust any longer. I don't want it and I don't have room for it.

author: jorah mormont
content: You are too young to be so-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you are too familiar.

author: jorah mormont
content: Forgive me, Khaleesi. No one can survive in this world without help. No one. Let me help you, please. Tell me how.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Find my dragons.

author: ygritte
content: How long till we get back to your crows?

author: jon snow
content: We're close.

author: ygritte
content: What, a day? A half-day? You don't know, do you? Do you even know where they are?

author: ygritte
content: What do you think they'll say when they hear about you and me?

author: jon snow
content: Nothing happened between you and me.

author: ygritte
content: I swear it, Old Master King Crow, ser, we were only close together for warmth. And then I felt it, right up against me backside like a club. I can show you the bruise on me tailbone. And before I knew what was where, his his Well, it was all out in the open, all angry as you like. And I didn't want to want it, but oh, I did! And he spread me legs and ruined. The shame of it. Now I can never marry a perfumed lord. What will me poor savage father say?

author: jon snow
content: Turn back around.

author: ygritte
content: And I thought that we were done, but he said, ''Turn back around.'" I'll tell you what, Jon Snow. Since it's gonna be your word against mine, and since you can't talk about it without blushing, we may as well just-

author: jon snow
content: What, right here in the muck?

author: ygritte
content: I'll keep you warm enough.

author: ygritte
content: Are you that afraid of it?

author: jon snow
content: That's enough.

author: ygritte
content: It's nice and wet and warm.

author: jon snow
content: Enough!

author: ygritte
content: It don't have teeth.

author: ygritte
content: All right! All right. Gods, you're dull.

author: ygritte
content: Should have took me while you had the chance.

author: sansa stark
content: No, no!

author: sansa stark
content: No. Oh, no.

author: shae
content: It's all right. Give me that.

author: sansa stark
content: If the Queen sees, I can have Joffrey's children now.

author: shae
content: Help me flip it over.

author: shae
content: Where are you going?

author: handmaiden
content: To tell Her Grace.

author: shae
content: You'll say nothing to anyone. Do you understand?

author: cersei lannister
content: Your mother might have prepared you. You flowered, my dear. No more.

author: sansa stark
content: My mother told me, but I thought it would be different.

author: cersei lannister
content: In what way?

author: sansa stark
content: I thought it would be less messy.

author: cersei lannister
content: Wait until you birth a child.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're a woman now. Do you have any idea what that means?

author: sansa stark
content: I'm fit to bear children for the king?

author: cersei lannister
content: A prospect that once delighted you, bringing little princes and princesses into the world, the greatest honor for a queen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Joffrey has always been difficult. Even his birth, I labored a day and a half to bring him into this world. You cannot imagine the pain. I screamed so loudly, I was sure Robert would hear me in the Kingswood.

author: sansa stark
content: His Grace was not with you?

author: cersei lannister
content: Robert was hunting. That was his custom. Whenever my time was near, my royal husband would flee to the trees with his huntsmen and his hounds. And when he returned, he would present me with some pelts or a stag's head, and I would present him with a baby. Not that I wanted him there, mind you. I had Grand Maester Pycelle, an army of midwives, and I had my brother. When they told Jaime he wasn't allowed in the birthing room, he smiled and asked which one of them proposed to keep him out. Joffrey will show you no such devotion.

author: cersei lannister
content: You may never love the king, but you will love his children.

author: sansa stark
content: I love His Grace with all my heart.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's so very touching to hear. Permit me to share some womanly wisdom with you on this very special day. The more people you love, the weaker you are. You'll do things for them that you know you shouldn't do. You'll act the fool to make them happy, to keep them safe. Love no one but your children. On that front, a mother has no choice.

author: sansa stark
content: But shouldn't I love Joffrey, Your Grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: You can try, little dove.

author: jaime lannister
content: Who did you say your mother was again?

author: alton
content: Cinda Lannister.

author: jaime lannister
content: Is she the fat one?

author: alton
content: Well, perhaps she's gotten a little larger than she-

author: jaime lannister
content: No, no. There's only one fat Lannister. If she was your mother, you'd know it.

author: alton
content: I squired for you once, you know.

author: jaime lannister
content: When?

author: alton
content: The tournament, the day of Willem Frey's wedding.

author: jaime lannister
content: I went to Willem Frey's wedding?

author: alton
content: You did. Your squire had gotten so drunk the night before that he threw up.

author: jaime lannister
content: He threw up on his horse on the way to the tourney grounds. What was his name?

author: alton
content: Bryan.

author: jaime lannister
content: Poor lad. That was my brother's doing, I seem to recall. I remember you. You'd never squired for anyone before.

author: alton
content: That's right. I ran up and volunteered. "Let me, my lord. Let me." My father was furious. Afraid I'd embarrass our family in front of the Family.

author: jaime lannister
content: You didn't, though.

author: alton
content: You really remember?

author: jaime lannister
content: You knew when you were needed and when to go away. It's a rare talent. Most of my squires, they mean well, but young men with big jobs, they tend to overdo them.

author: alton
content: When I think back to that day-

author: guard
content: Shh!

author: jaime lannister
content: You were saying?

author: alton
content: I- Never mind. It's embarrassing.

author: jaime lannister
content: More embarrassing than being chained to a post covered in your own shit?

author: alton
content: I remember everything about that day, your helmet, your horse, the rake lines in the dirt along the list, where the sun was in the sky when you knocked Balon from his horse, and the dent in your shield when you handed it back to me. I'll remember it all until I die. That was the best day of my life. And I remember being on the field after it was over. All the competitors were done. I was the last one out there. And I couldn't leave. I couldn't bring myself to go and sit with my family at a table so far on the edge of the feast you could barely even see the bride. And I couldn't bear to tell them what it had been like squiring for you, when I knew that they could never have the faintest idea what I was talking about.

author: jaime lannister
content: I understand completely.

author: alton
content: How could you? Sorry, I I didn't mean to doubt you.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's just that I, I was sixteen once. I also had to replace someone's squire on short notice.

author: alton
content: Which knight was it?

author: jaime lannister
content: Barristan Selmy. The fight against the Kingswood Outlaws. Before your time.

author: alton
content: What was he like?

author: jaime lannister
content: He was a painter. A painter who only used red. I couldn't imagine being able to fight like that, not back then. And to help him do that, to be a part of something that perfect. I don't need to explain how that felt, not to you.

author: alton
content: It's hard to put into words.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's like stepping into a dream you've been dreaming for as long as you can remember, and finding out that the dream is more real than your life.

author: alton
content: Leaving that battlefield was like being dragged off to prison.

author: alton
content: Did you squire for him again?

author: jaime lannister
content: No. I didn't have your gift. He couldn't take a step without stepping on me. I was awful, a complete liability. Until one of the outlaws decided to take on a sixteen-year-old squire.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's a good thing I am who I am. I'd have been useless at anything else. I'm not well-suited for imprisonment. Shocking, I know. Some men are. Ned Stark, I imagine he made an excellent prisoner right up until the end. Not me, though. My life has left me uniquely unfit for constraint.

author: alton
content: And have you thought about

author: jaime lannister
content: Of course. Every day.

author: alton
content: And?

author: jaime lannister
content: Good prisoners breed good jailers, apparently. The Starks are very careful.

author: jaime lannister
content: But there is a way, I think. It wasn't possible until now.

author: alton
content: What is it?

author: jaime lannister
content: It's actually quite simple.

author: alton
content: Well, let me help you.

author: jaime lannister
content: You'll only have to do one thing.

author: alton
content: Tell me.

author: jaime lannister
content: You'll have to die.

author: quaith
content: Jorah the Andal. This man must sail past old Valyria. All who travel too close to the doom must have protection.

author: jorah mormont
content: I didn't come here for lessons.

author: quaith
content: No, you came for the dragons.

author: jorah mormont
content: You have them? Where are they?

author: quaith
content: Draw your sword. See what your steel is worth. You want to please the Mother of Dragons.

author: quaith
content: You love her.

author: jorah mormont
content: Where are the dragons?

author: quaith
content: Will you betray her again, Jorah the Andal?

author: quaith
content: Will you betray her again?

author: jorah mormont
content: Never.

author: quaith
content: The thief you seek is with her now.

author: spice king
content: I did not leave the comfort of my home to come to yours and be called a thief.

author: xaro
content: No one is calling you a thief. Who is she to accuse us?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Please, they're my children. I'm begging you.

author: silk king
content: Begging us? It wasn't very long ago you were threatening us.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Without me, the dragons will die.

author: spice king
content: It will be for the best. Your dragons will bring the world nothing but death and misery, my dear. If I knew where they were, I would not tell you.

author: pyat pree
content: You are cruel, my friend. The Mother of Dragons is in the right. She must be reunited with her babies. I will help you, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How?

author: pyatt pree
content: I will take you to the House of the Undying where I have put them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You have my dragons?

author: pyat pree
content: When I learned you were coming to our city, I made an arrangement with the King of Qarth. He procured them for me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But there is no King of Qarth.

author: xaro
content: There is now. That was the other half of the arrangement.

author: xaro
content: You would keep your gates and your minds closed to everything outside your walls, but Qarth cannot remain the greatest city that ever was if it refuses to change. I will open Qarth to the world as I have forced it to open itself to me.

author: spice king
content: Your ambition is an inspiration. But like all upstarts, you overreach. Three dragons the size of cats and an alliance with a charlatan do not make you a king.

author: xaro
content: An upstart and a charlatan? Empires have been built by less. Those on the margins often come to control the center, and those in the center make room for them, willingly or otherwise.

author: pyat pree
content: The Mother of Dragons will be with her babies. She will give them her love and they will thrive by her side, forever.

author: pyattpree
content: A mother should be with her children.

author: pyat pree
content: Where will you run to, Daenerys Stormborn? Your dragons wait for you in the House of the Undying. Come see them.

author: jacks
content: Lady Stark!

author: brienne
content: No farther.

author: jacks
content: Keep your hands off me, woman.

author: brienne
content: Don't enter without an invitation, man.

author: jacks
content: Forgive me. Lady Stark.

author: catelyn stark
content: What is it?

author: jacks
content: They caught the Kingslayer.

author: man
content: Kingslayer!

author: man
content: Kill the fucking Kingslayer!

author: man
content: Hang him!

author: man
content: You'll die today.

content: Justice for the Karstark.

author: man
content: Gut him!

content: This monster killed my son.

content: And where is our king now?

author: robb stark
content: You know very well.

author: rickard karstark
content: He has gone to the Crag to accept the surrender. Aye, gone to the Crag, but not to negotiate. He brought that foreign bitch with him.

author: catelyn stark
content: How dare you!

author: brienne
content: Threatening my lady is an act of treason.

author: rickard karstark
content: Treason? How can it be treason to kill Lannisters?

author: catelyn stark
content: I understand your grief, my lord, better than most, I understand it. But in the name of my son, the King in the North, stand down.

author: rickard karstark
content: When your son returns, I will demand this murderer's head.

author: catelyn stark
content: Wise men do not make demands of kings.

author: rickard karstark

author: jaime lannister
content: Thank you for fighting on my behalf, Lady Stark. I would have come to your defense, but-

content: Take him to the stockades. Bind him with every chain you can find!

content: You've become a real she-wolf in your later years. There's not much fish left in you.

content: Since I decided that I can't stand to look at any of my handmaidens for another instant.

author: cersei lannister
content: How many times can you read one raven scroll?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stannis Baratheon's fleet has been spotted sailing north past Tarth, two hundred ships.

author: cersei lannister
content: More than we have.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, that's more than we have. He'll be at our gates within five days, four if he has the wind.

author: cersei lannister
content: We have strong, high walls. We'll rain fire down on them from above.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Rain fire on them from above." You're quoting Father, aren't you?

author: cersei lannister
content: Why not? He has a good mind for strategy, doesn't he?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Call it tactics, not strategy. But, yes, he does have a good mind for it. The best mind, some would say. Sadly, he's not here. It's just you, me and Joffrey, the Lord of the Seven Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm sure you'll make a point eventually.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He needs to start acting like a king. This war you started is coming to our doorstep. And if the entire city wants Joffrey dead

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm not the one giving the boy whores to abuse.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I thought the girls might help him.

author: cersei lannister
content: Did you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I was wrong. If we can't control him

content: Do you think I haven't tried? He doesn't listen to me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's hard to put a leash on a dog once you've put a crown on its head.

author: cersei lannister
content: I always hoped he'd be like Jaime. He looks like him. In a certain light.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The boy is more Robert than Jaime.

author: cersei lannister
content: Robert was a drunken fool, but he didn't enjoy cruelty. Sometimes I wonder. What? If this is the price for what we've done, for our sins.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sins?

content: The Targaryens wed brother and sister for hundreds of years, I know. That's what Jaime and I would say to each other in our moments of doubt. It's what I told Ned Stark when he was stupid enough to confront me. Half the Targaryens went mad, didn't they? What's the saying? "Every time a Targaryen is born, the Gods flip a coin."

author: tyrion lannister
content: You've beaten the odds. Tommen and Myrcella are good, decent children, both of them.

author: man
content: Then why wait?

author: man
content: We're sworn to the king.

author: man
content: There's not a king.

author: man
content: That's treason.

author: man
content: So is saving Lannisters, yeah?

author: man
content: Back off, you.

author: man
content: No, I won't.

author: brienne
content: Your son returns at dawn, my lady?

author: catelyn stark
content: So they say.

author: brienne
content: The Kingslayer won't last the night. The more they drink, the angrier they'll get. And when the Karstarks draw their swords Who wants to die defending a Lannister?

content: Come.

content: I need to be alone with him.

author: catelyn stark
content: You strangled his son with your chains.

author: jaime lannister
content: Oh. Oh. Was he the one on guard duty? He was in my way. Any knight would have done the same.

author: catelyn stark
content: You are no knight. You have forsaken every vow you ever took.

author: jaime lannister
content: So many vows. They make you swear and swear. Defend the king, obey the king, obey your father, protect the innocent, defend the weak. But what if your father despises the king? What if the king massacres the innocent? It's too much. No matter what you do, you're forsaking one vow or another. Where did you find this beast?

author: catelyn stark
content: She is a truer knight than you will ever be, Kingslayer.

author: jaime lannister
content: Kingslayer. What a king he was. Here's to Aerys Targaryen, the Second of His Name, Lord of the Seven Kingdoms, Protector of the Realm, and to the sword I shoved in his back.

author: catelyn stark
content: You are a man without honor.

author: jaime lannister
content: Do you know, I've never been with any woman but Cersei. So in my own way, I have more honor than poor old dead Ned. What was the name of that bastard he fathered?

author: catelyn stark
content: Brienne.

author: jaime lannister
content: No, that wasn't it. Snow, a bastard from the North. Now, when When good old Ned came home with some whore's baby, did you pretend to love it? No. You're not very good at pretending. You're an honest woman. You hated that boy, didn't you? How could you not hate him? The walking, talking reminder that the honorable Lord Eddard Stark fucked another woman.

author: catelyn stark
content: Your sword.

content: You should be proud of your brother's achievement. I took the great castle of Winterfell with twenty men.

content: I treated the Stark boys with honor, and they repaid me with treachery.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You treated them with honor? By butchering them?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Before I had to kill them- I treated them-

content: You seized their home, as is your right. We're Ironborn, we take what we need.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Exactly.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Then you made them prisoners in their home and they ran away. Is that treachery? I'd call it bravery.

author: theon greyjoy
content: They made me a promise

author: yara greyjoy
content: Your little boy prisoners made you a promise and you got mad when they broke it? Are you the dumbest cunt alive?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Don't call me

author: yara greyjoy
content: A cunt. A dumb cunt who killed the only two Starks in Winterfell. You know how valuable those boys were?

author: theon greyjoy
content: If I hadn't killed them, the Northerners would think me weak.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You are weak. And you're stupid.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm warning you.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Go on, then. Warn me.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You haven't brought enough men. How am I supposed to defend Winterfell with just this lot?

author: yara greyjoy
content: You're not. I've come to bring you home. Father wants a word.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Is this a joke? Winterfell is the heart of the North.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Aye, it is, hundreds of miles from the sea. We're islanders, baby brother. Had you forgotten that? Our power comes from our ships. And now that you've decorated your walls with the bodies of the Stark boys, every man in the North wants to see you hanged. When Robb Stark finds out-

author: theon greyjoy
content: He won't find out. We've killed all the ravens. We have all the horses. I've taken Winterfell. And I will keep Winterfell.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Leave us.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Theon, you're my blood. We both loved our mother. We both endured our father. Come home with me. Don't die here alone.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I don't intend to die.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You were a terrible baby, do you know that? Bawling all the time, never sleeping. And one night, you just wouldn't shut up, screaming like a dying pig. I walked over to your crib, I looked down at you. I wanted to strangle you. And you looked up at me and you stopped screaming. You smiled at me. Don't die so far from the sea.

author: ygritte
content: I've brought you a present, Lord of Bones.

author: lord of bones
content: I already got one crow. Don't need two.

author: ygritte
content: Mance will want to question this one. Knows all about where the crows are and what they're planning.

author: lord of bones
content: The Halfhand knows more. This one is just a little boy. Gut him.

author: ygritte
content: He could have killed me half a dozen times.

author: lord of bones
content: And now he wishes he did. Gut him.

author: ygritte
content: He's a bastard of Winterfell, Ned Stark's son.

author: ygritte
content: Mance will want him.

content: What does Mance want with a dead man's bastard?

author: ygritte
content: I don't know. I think he'll want to decide for himself.

author: lord of bones
content: He runs, I'll chop his balls off.

author: ygritte
content: He runs, I'll do it meself.

author: ygritte
content: We're even now, Jon Snow.

author: jon snow
content: I couldn't do it. I had the sword on her neck, I just couldn't-

content: I know.

author: jon snow
content: The others?

author: qhorin
content: When you didn't come back, we went looking for you. We found your tracks fast enough. But they found us before we found you.

author: jon snow
content: They died because of me.

author: qhorin
content: See that it wasn't for nothing.

author: wildling
content: All right, up, lad.

author: wildling
content: Come on, on your feet, now. Move it.

author: talisa
content: Is she beautiful?

author: robb stark
content: I've never met her.

author: talisa
content: What's her name?

author: robb stark
content: Frey, I suppose. I don't know her first name.

author: talisa
content: I'm sure you'll be very happy.

author: talisa
content: And you're marrying her for a bridge?

author: robb stark
content: An important bridge.

author: talisa
content: Ah.

author: robb stark
content: It was before they killed my father. I still thought I could march south and rescue him in time, but only if I crossed that bridge.

author: talisa
content: When I speak to people from the North, they all loved your father.

author: robb stark
content: He was the best man I ever met. I know children always think that about their fathers, but

author: talisa
content: Children do not always think that about their fathers, believe me.

author: robb stark
content: He once told me that being a lord is like being a father, except you have thousands of children and you worry about all of them. The farmers plowing the fields are yours to protect. The charwomen scrubbing the floors, yours to protect. The soldiers you order into battle. He told me he woke with fear in the morning and went to bed with fear in the night. I didn't believe him. I asked him, "How can a man be brave if he's afraid?" "That is the only time a man can be brave," he told me.

author: talisa
content: I wish I could have met him.

author: robb stark
content: He would have liked you.

author: talisa
content: Most lords worry more about their gold and their glory than the charwomen scrubbing their floors.

author: robb stark
content: He didn't care much about gold or glory.

author: talisa
content: And you? You think I'm fighting this war so they'll sing songs about me? I want to go home. I want the men following me to go home.

author: talisa
content: Then why don't you?

author: robb stark
content: Because we'll never be safe until the Lannisters are defeated. And because I believe in justice.

author: talisa
content: Chopping off Joffrey's head, you mean.

author: robb stark

content: Your Grace, milady. The Kingslayer, he escaped in the night.

author: robb stark
content: How? How?

author: robb stark
content: Tell me this isn't true.

author: robb stark
content: Why?

content: For the girls.

author: robb stark
content: You betrayed me.

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb-

content: No! You knew I would not allow it and you did it anyway.

author: catelyn stark
content: Bran and Rickon are captives in Winterfell. Sansa and Arya are captives in King's Landing. I have five children, and only one of them is free.

author: rickard karstark
content: I lost one son fighting by your son's side. I lost another to the Kingslayer, strangled with a chain. You commit treason because your children are prisoners? I would carve out my heart and offer it to the Father, if he would let my sons wake from their graves and step into a prison cell.

author: catelyn stark
content: I grieve for your sons, my lord.

author: rickard karstark
content: I don't want your grief. I want my vengeance. And you stole it from me.

author: catelyn stark
content: Killing Jaime Lannister would not buy life for your children, but returning him to King's Landing may buy life for mine.

author: robb stark
content: Jaime Lannister has played you for a fool. You've weakened our position. You've brought discord into our camp. And you did it all behind my back. Make sure she's guarded day and night.

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb. How many men did we send in pursuit of the Kingslayer?

author: soldier
content: Forty, Your Grace.

author: robb stark
content: Send another forty with our fastest horses.

author: catelyn stark
content: Robb.

author: jaime lannister
content: Damn.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're much uglier in daylight. What's your name? I'm Jaime Lannister of Casterly Rock, son of Tywin.

author: jaime lannister
content: A captive knight has a right to know his captor's identity.

author: brienne
content: Brienne of Tarth.

author: jaime lannister
content: Tarth, Tarth, Tarth. Crescent moons and starbursts. Lord Selwyn Tarth. Your father. Do you have any brothers and sisters, my lady? It's a long way to King's Landing. Might as well get to know one another.

author: jaime lannister
content: Have you known many men? I suppose not. Women? Horses? Ah.

author: jaime lannister
content: I didn't mean to give offense, my lady. Forgive me.

author: brienne
content: Your crimes are past forgiveness, Kingslayer.

author: jaime lannister
content: Why do you hate me so much? Have I ever harmed you?

author: brienne
content: You've harmed others, those you were sworn to protect, the weak, the innocent.

author: jaime lannister
content: Has anyone ever told you you're as boring as you are ugly?

author: brienne
content: You will not provoke me to anger.

author: jaime lannister
content: I already have. Look at you. You're ready to chop my head off. Do you think you could? Do you think you could beat me in a fair fight?

author: brienne
content: I've never seen you fight.

author: jaime lannister
content: The answer is no. There are three men in the kingdoms who might have a chance against me. You're not one of them.

author: brienne
content: All my life men like you have sneered at me. And all my life I've been knocking men like you into the dust.

author: jaime lannister
content: If you're so confident, unlock my chains. Let's see what happens.

author: brienne
content: Do you take me for an idiot? In!

author: jaime lannister
content: I took you for a fighter, a man Pardon. Woman of honor. Was I wrong? You're afraid.

author: brienne
content: Maybe one day we'll find out, Kingslayer.

author: kevan
content: King's Landing will fall an hour after Stannis lands his force. It's not too late for King Joffrey and Cersei and the court to ride west to safety.

author: tywin lannister
content: Surrender the Iron Throne?

content: No, a king who runs will not be king for long. He's a Lannister. He'll stand and fight. Stannis, two days from the capital and the wolf at my doorstep.

author: kevan
content: The scouts assure us Robb Stark remains north of Ashemark.

author: tywin lannister
content: Ha! The last time the scouts assured us of Stark's movement, he lured us into a trap. Which is why my son is his prisoner.

author: tywin lannister
content: Too close to Casterly Rock.

author: kevan
content: He sent a splinter force to recapture Winterfell. The Greyjoys have done us a great favor. Stark won't risk marching on Casterly Rock until he's at full force.

author: tywin lannister
content: He's a boy and he's never lost a battle. He'll risk anything at any time because he doesn't know enough to be afraid.

author: tywin lannister
content: We'll ride at nightfall. I want a full night's march before he knows we're on the move. Clegane, you'll maintain a garrison here at Harrenhal. Track down this brotherhood and destroy them. The girl has proven herself a good servant. She'll stay on with you. See that he doesn't get drunk in the evenings. He's poor company when he's sober, but he's better at his work.

content: Do you have to do that here?

content: Yes, but do you have to do it here?

content: You should start wearing the gold cloak.

content: I don't want to wear a gold cloak.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're commander of the City Watch. You shouldn't be dressed like a common

content: A cloak slows you down in a fight. Makes it hard to move quietly. And the gold catches the light, so you're nice and easy to spot at night.

content: Well, you're not sneaking through alleyways any longer. You're supposed to stand out.

author: bronn

content: Fine, fine. No gold cloak.

content: What?

author: bronn
content: What?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What? What? Why are you staring at me?

author: bronn
content: You don't want me cleaning me nails. You don't want me looking your way. Why am I here?

author: tyrion lannister
content: To help me plan the defense of King's Landing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stannis will be here any day.

author: bronn

author: tyrion lannister
content: An History of the Great Sieges of Westeros. " By Archmaester Shevelathin. Shevelatesh.

author: bronn
content: Chevalteesh. I'd swap all your books for a few good archers.

author: varys
content: My Lord Hand. Commander. I must compliment you on the gold cloaks' performance these last few weeks. Did you know there has been a marked drop in thievery?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I did not know. And how did you accomplish this marked drop in thievery?

author: bronn
content: Me and the lads rounded up all the known thieves.

author: tyrion lannister
content: For questioning?

author: bronn
content: No. It's just the unknown thieves we need to worry about now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We talked about this.

author: bronn
content: Aye, we talked about it. Have you ever been in a city under siege? Maybe this part's not in your books. See, it's not the fighting that kills most people. It's the starving. Foodo s worth more than gold. Noble ladies sell their diamonds for a sack of potatoes. Things get bad enough, the poor start eating each other.

author: bronn
content: The thieves, they love a siege. Soon as the gates are sealed, they steal all the food. By the time it's all over, they're the richest men in town.

author: varys
content: Given the circumstances, my lord, I believe extreme measures are warranted.

author: varys

And then every wound he suffers, she'll suffer, too. And if he dies, there isn't a man alive who could devise a more painful death for your little cunt.

author: talisa
content: When I was twelve, my mother and father went to a wedding. Weddings in Volantis last for days, you know. And they left me with my little brother. The second afternoon they were gone was the hottest day in the three-year summer. We couldn't bear to be inside, so we ran down to the Rhoyne. Every child in Volantis was in the Rhoyne that day. The rich, the poor, we were all there. Naked, screaming, racing to the little islands. Drummers were playing for coppers on the east bank. I was treading water, talking to a friend, when I realized I hadn't seen my brother. I called his name. Then I started screaming his name. And then I saw him floating face down. My heart just stopped. I was I dragged him from the water. My friend helped me, I think. I don't even remember. He was so little. Then we pulled him onto the riverbank. And I screamed at him and I shook him. And he was dead. Just dead. A man ran over. He had a fish tattoo on his face. In Volantis, the slaves have tattoos. So you know what they are without having to talk to them. And this man worked on a fishing boat. And he pushed me out of the way. You have to understand, for a slave to push a highborn girl, that's death for the man, a terrible death. But he pushed me out of the way, and he started pressing on my brother's chest again and again and again, until my brother spat out half of the Rhoyne and cried out. And the man cradled his head and told him to be calm. I decided two things that day. I would not waste my years planning dances and masquerades with the other noble ladies. And when I came of age, I would never live in a slave city again. I'm sorry, Your Grace. You told me of your problems and I've blathered on.

author: stannis baratheon
content: First, we ate the horses. We weren't riding anywhere, not with the castle surrounded. We couldn't feed them, so fine, the horses. Then the cats. Never liked cats. So fine. I do like dogs. Good animals. Loyal. But we ate them. Then the rats. The night before you slipped through, I thought my wife was dying. She couldn't speak anymore, she was so frail. And then you made it through the lines. Slipped right through in your little black sailboat with your onions.

author: davos
content: And potatoes. Some salted beef, I believe.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Every man in Storm's End wanted to kiss you that night.

author: davos
content: I was relieved they did not.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Robert told me to hold Storm's End, so I held it. Then he told me he was giving it to Renly, so I gave it up. Insult or no, I gave it up. Because Robert was my older brother, and he was the king and I've always done my duty. But now, I'm the rightful king by every law of Westeros. And when I sit the Iron Throne, you'll be my Hand.

I have consulted with the High Septon and he assures me that their crimes against the realm free you from any promise you have made to them in the sight of the gods.

content: This is dark magic, like the magic that took you from me. Took you from me before I could even Maybe I am dead and I just don't know it yet. Maybe I am with you in the Night Lands.

author: drogo
content: Or maybe I refused to enter the Night Lands without you. Maybe I told the Great Stallion to go fuck himself and came back here to wait for you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That sounds like something you would do.

author: drogo
content: Or maybe it is a dream. Your dream, my dream I do not know. These are questions for wise men with skinny arms.

author: drogo
content: You are the moon of my life. That is all I know and all I need to know.

author: drogo
content: And if this is a dream, I will kill the man who tries to wake me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Until the sun rises in the west and sets in the east, until the rivers run dry and the mountains blow in the wind like leaves.

author: pyatt pree
content: They miss their mother.

author: pyat pree
content: They want to be with you.

author: pyat pree
content: Do you want to be with them?

author: pyat pree
content: You will be.

author: pyat pree
content: When your dragons were born,

author: pyat pree
content: our magic was born again.

author: pyat pree
content: It is strongest in their presence.

author: pyat pree
content: And they are strongest in yours.

author: pyat pree
content: You will be with them, through winter, summer, winter again. Across a thousand, thousand seasons you will be with them.

author: pyat pree
content: And we will be with you until time comes to an end.

author: pyat pree
content: Welcome home, Daenerys Stormborn.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This is not my home. My home is across the sea, where my people are waiting for me.

author: pyat pree
content: They will be waiting a long time.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dracarys.

author: ygritte
content: We should be there by sundown. Won't be a fun night for you. Mance knows how to make crows sing. If you know what to say, you might just make it through the night. Not talking's not the way to go.

author: jon snow
content: Careful with that. You might cut yourself.

author: jon snow
content: Never swung a sword before, have you? You look like a baby with a rattle.

author: rattleshirt
content: Enough of that!

author: jon snow
content: Stop!

author: qhorin
content: Why, traitor? So you can give Mance Rayder an invitation to Castle Black?

author: rattleshirt
content: Let 'em fight.

author: qhorin
content: That's it? That's what you can do? You little shit.

author: qhorin
content: Your traitor father teach you that?

author: qhorin
content: Or was it your whore mother?

author: qhorin
content: We are the watchers on the Wall.

author: ygritte
content: You can tell Mance that's the man who killed Qhorin Halfhand.

author: rattleshirt
content: Burn the body.

author: wildling
content: Aye.

author: rattleshirt
content: You don't want this one coming back for you.

author: ygritte
content: Come along, Jon Snow.

author: ygritte
content: Time to meet the King-beyond-the-Wall.

author: xaro
content: What the-

author: doreah
content: Khaleesi, please. He said you'd never leave Qarth alive.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Come.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Nothing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you, Xaro Xhoan Daxos. Thank you for teaching me this lesson.

author: xaro
content: I am king of Qarth. I can help you now, truly help you. We can take the Iron Throne. I'll bring you a thousand ships.

author: doreah
content: Please, Khaleesi, I beg you.

author: xaro
content: All that you have dreamed is within your reach!

author: doreah
content: I beg you, please!

author: xaro
content: Khaleesi.

author: doreah
content: Please! Please!

author: xaro
content: Khaleesi!

author: jorah mormont
content: It's all a lie.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Looks real enough to me. Real enough to buy a ship?

author: jorah mormont
content: Aye, a small ship.

author: jorah mormont
content: Take all the gold and jewels.

author: grenn
content: I thought we were coming north to fight wildlings.

author: grenn
content: Is this goat?

author: dolorous edd
content: It's moose. People shouldn't live anywhere you need to burn shit to keep warm.

author: grenn
content: Well, you see a tree, let me know.

author: sam
content: If you step back and think about it, the thing about Gilly that's so interesting is

author: grenn
content: Just bloody kill me.

author: sam
content: No, truly. The thing about her that I find so interesting is that after all that Craster's done to her, she's still got hope that life might get better.

author: dolorous edd
content: The thing about Gilly that you find so interesting is that she said six words to you.

author: sam
content: And the thing about you that I find so interesting is absolutely nothing.

author: sam
content: It's Jon and the Halfhand. They're back.

author: grenn
content: Two blasts is wildlings. You're not fighting them alone.

author: dolorous edd
content: Come on.

author: grenn
content: Three blasts?

author: dolorous edd
content: Run!

author: sam
content: Wait! Wait for me!

author: sam
content: Grenn!

author: sam
content: Edd!

author: man
content: Fall back!

author: sam
content: Brother?

author: jeor
content: Did you send the ravens?

author: jeor
content: Tarly, look at me. Did you send the ravens?

author: jeor
content: That was your job. Your only job. We need to get back to the Wall. It's a long march. We know what's out there, but we have to make it, have to warn them or before winter's done, everyone you've ever known will be dead.

author: main
content: CREDITS

author: ygritte
content: First time you've seen a giant, Jon Snow?

author: ygritte
content: Well, don't stare too long. They're shy. When they stop being shy, they get angry. And when they're angry, I've seen them pound a man straight into the ground like a hammer on a nail.

author: man
content: Crow!

author: boy
content: Crow!

author: girl
content: Look over there!

author: girl
content: Crow! Look over here! Look!

author: woman
content: Ah, look, crow coming!

author: ygritte
content: You're wearing the wrong color.

author: jon snow
content: Mance was a ranger.

author: ygritte
content: In your hearts, all you crows want to fly free.

author: jon snow
content: When I'm free, will I be free to go?

author: ygritte
content: Sure, you will.

author: boy
content: Oh!

author: ygritte
content: And I'll be free to kill you. Got no respect, this lot. Got no fathers to slap 'em when they're foul.

author: jon snow
content: What happened to their fathers?

author: ygritte
content: Some of them were killed by crows like you. Don't look so grim, Jon Snow. If Mance Rayder likes you, you'll live another day. And if he don't...

author: tormund
content: I smell a crow.

author: rattleshirt
content: We killed his friends. Thought you'd want to question this one.

author: tormund
content: What do we want with a baby crow?

author: ygritte
content: This baby killed Qhorin Halfhand. He wants to be one of us.

author: tormund
content: That half-handed cunt killed friends of mine. Friends twice your size.

author: jon snow
content: My father told me big men fall just as quick as little ones if you put a sword through their hearts.

author: tormund
content: Plenty of little men tried to put their swords through my heart. And there's plenty of little skeletons buried in the woods. What's your name, boy?

author: jon snow
content: Jon Snow.

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace.

author: tormund
content: Your Grace? Did you hear that? From now on, you'd better kneel every time I fart.

author: mance
content: Stand, boy. We don't kneel for anyone beyond the Wall.

author: mance
content: So, you're Ned Stark's bastard. Thank you for the gift, Lord of Bones. You can leave us.

author: mance
content: The girl likes you. You like her back, Snow? That why you want to join us?

author: tormund
content: Don't panic, boy. This isn't the damned Night's Watch where we make you swear off girls.

author: mance
content: This chicken eater you thought was king is Tormund Giantsbane.

author: tormund
content: Can't believe this pup killed the Halfhand.

author: mance
content: He was our enemy and I'm glad he's dead.

author: mance
content: He was my brother once. Back when he had a whole hand. What were you doing with him?

author: jon snow
content: The Lord Commander sent me to the Halfhand for seasoning.

author: mance
content: Why?

author: jon snow
content: He wants me to lead one day.

author: mance
content: But here you are, a traitor kneeling before the King-Beyond-the-Wall.

author: jon snow
content: If I'm a traitor, then you are, too.

author: mance
content: Why do you want to join us, Jon Snow?

author: jon snow
content: I want to be free.

author: mance
content: No, I don't think so. I think what you want most of all is to be a hero. I'll ask you one last time ... why do you want to join us?

author: jon snow
content: We stopped at Craster's Keep on the way north. I saw...

author: mance
content: You saw what?

author: jon snow
content: I saw Craster take his own baby boy and leave it in the woods. I saw what took it.

author: mance
content: You're telling me you saw one of them? And why would that make you desert your brothers?

author: jon snow
content: Because when I told the Lord Commander, he already knew. Thousands of years ago, the First Men battled the White Walkers and defeated them. I want to fight for the side that fights for the living. Did I come to the right place?

author: mance
content: We'll need to find you a new cloak.

author: bronn
content: What if you took off that bit there?

author: whore
content: Don't you want to leave something to the imagination?

author: bronn
content: Trouble is, I've never had much imagination.

author: whore
content: I want you to take it off.

author: whore
content: Mouth.

author: podrick
content: Ser Bronn. Ser Bronn.

author: bronn
content: I didn't hear that.

author: podrick
content: Apologies, ser.

author: bronn
content: Back away. Keep backing away till you're outside this establishment. Then back away some more.

author: podrick
content: Lord Tyrion sent me.

author: bronn
content: I will murder you, boy.

author: podrick
content: He said it was a matter of life and death.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Pod?

author: cersei lannister
content: It's your sister. The queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What are they doing here?

author: cersei lannister
content: Protecting me, I assume. Will you let me in?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, I don't think so.

author: cersei lannister
content: If I wanted to kill you, do you think I'd let a wooden door stop me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: They stay outside.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm not afraid of you, little brother.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why are you here?

author: cersei lannister
content: I wanted to see your face. They said you'd lost your nose, but it's not as gruesome as all that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The man who cut me lost more than his nose.

author: cersei lannister
content: I should hope so. The rebels came for Joffrey's head, they lost their own. Thanks to Father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thanks to Father. Of course, it wasn't a rebel who tried to kill me.

author: cersei lannister
content: No? Curious. Bit of a comedown from chamber of the Hand. But then I don't suppose you need much room.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Grand Maester Pycelle made the same joke. You must be proud to be as funny as a man whose balls brush his knees.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're meeting Father today?

author: tyrion lannister
content: How do you know that?

author: cersei lannister
content: Because I have hundreds of spies in my employ. The Master of Whisperers owes me a favor or two. Father told me. What do you want from him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What do I want from him? He's my father. Do I need to want something? I'm sure he loves me dearly, as any father loves his child, his baby boy. Yet he hasn't come to visit once since arriving in King's Landing. I lay here, my face split in half, but Father never came.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're going to make me cry.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why do you care what I want from him?

author: cersei lannister
content: Because you've slandered me to Father before.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Slandered? When?

author: cersei lannister
content: You told him I had my guards beat that servant girl at Casterly Rock.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You did have your guards beat her. A girl of nine, I believe.

author: cersei lannister
content: I was nine, too.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She lost an eye, if I remember correctly.

author: cersei lannister
content: If I remember correctly, she never stole a necklace again.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not slander if it's true.

author: cersei lannister
content: And what's this truth you plan on telling him today?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why are you so nervous about what I'm going to say to Father?

author: cersei lannister
content: Because you're a liar. I expect you'll tell lies about me, about Joffrey.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Any lies in particular?

author: cersei lannister
content: You're a clever man, but you're not half as clever as you think you are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Still makes me more clever than you.

author: bronn
content: Oh, look at these two shining warriors. Ser Taryn Mant and... Ser Whosit of Whocares.

author: meryn trant
content: Ser Meryn Trant.

author: bronn
content: Ser Bronn of the Blackwater.

author: meryn trant
content: You're no knight.

author: bronn
content: Pod.

author: podrick
content: Ser Bronn of the Blackwater was anointed by the king himself.

author: meryn trant
content: You're an up-jumped cutthroat, nothing more.

author: bronn
content: That's exactly who I am. And you're a grub in fancy armor who's better at beating little girls than fighting men. Now, I have an appointment with Lord Tyrion.

author: meryn trant
content: You put your hand on that door, you lose the hand.

author: bronn
content: As much as I appreciate a walk in the sunshine, your lordship, I am wondering why you sent for me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A number of people in this city want to kill me. You're here to protect me.

author: bronn
content: I've been doing that for a while now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you grow bored protecting me?

author: bronn
content: I grow poor protecting you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Poor? Poor? Under my patronage you've become a knight, you've served as Commander of the City Watch.

author: bronn
content: Briefly.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm sure you filled your pockets.

author: bronn
content: And now my pockets are empty. You've given me a taste for the finer things. And if you want me to carry on protecting you, you'll need to pay more.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I thought we were friends.

author: bronn
content: We are. But I'm a sellsword. I sell my sword. I don't loan it out to friends as a favor.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How much?

author: bronn
content: Double.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Double?

author: bronn
content: I'm a knight now. Knights are worth double.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't even know how much I'm paying you now.

author: bronn
content: Which means you can afford it.

author: davos
content: Here. Here! Help me!

author: man
content: Who are you?

author: davos
content: I was in the battle at Blackwater. I was a captain and a knight.

author: man
content: Aye, ser, and serving which king?

author: davos
content: The one true king of Westeros... Stannis Baratheon.

author: salladhor
content: I thought you were dead. Everyone thought you were dead. And your son?

author: salladhor
content: He may have swam ashore as you did.

author: davos
content: No, the wildfire took him. I saw it.

author: salladhor
content: I'm so sorry, my friend. I, too, have lost a son. There is nothing worse in this world. But, Davos, you were a good father.

author: davos
content: If I was a good father, he'd still be here. Stannis lives?

author: salladhor
content: He licks his wounds at Dragonstone.

author: davos
content: Will you take me there?

author: salladhor
content: There is nothing for me at Dragonstone.

author: davos
content: This war is not over.

author: salladhor
content: Not for you, maybe. But for Salladhor Saan, the war is over.

author: davos
content: We're both sworn to King Stannis.

author: salladhor
content: I am sworn to no man. I promised you 30 ships and you promised me riches and glory. I delivered the ships.

author: davos
content: Stannis never gives up. Never. Now he will regroup ...

author: salladhor
content: He's a broken man. His fleet lies at the bottom of Blackwater Bay. They say he sees no one ... not his generals, not even his wife. Only the Red Woman whispering in his ear, telling him what she sees in the flames and burning men alive.

author: davos
content: What?

author: salladhor
content: They built a great fire when Stannis returned. All those who spoke against her she called servants of darkness. They say she sang to them as they burned.

author: salladhor
content: I'm a pirate.

author: davos
content: You're a smuggler.

author: salladhor
content: Servants of darkness. I'm thinking Dragonstone is a good place for us to avoid.

author: davos
content: Take me back there, please.

author: salladhor
content: You cannot turn Stannis against her.

author: davos
content: Maybe not, but I could carve her heart out.

author: salladhor
content: You could try. If you fail, they will burn you. If you succeed, they'll burn you. And you've only just come back to life. Stay alive a little longer, my friend.

author: davos
content: You call me friend. You drank with me on my wedding day.

author: salladhor
content: And you drank with me on four of my wedding days, but I don't ask you for favors.

author: davos
content: I have to stop her. Please, do this for me.

author: salladhor
content: When you are dead, I will gather your bones in a little sack and let your widow wear them around her neck.

author: roose bolton
content: We should set the siege lines a thousand yards from Harrenhal.

author: robb stark
content: There won't be a siege. The Mountain can't defend a ruin.

author: roose bolton
content: I imagine the Mountain will defend whatever Tywin Lannister tells him to defend.

author: robb stark
content: The Lannisters have been running from us since Oxcross. I'd love a fight. The men would love a fight. I don't think we're going to get one.

author: rickard karstark
content: Two hundred Northmen slaughtered like sheep.

author: roose bolton
content: The debt will be repaid, my friend. For them and for your sons.

author: rickard karstark
content: Will it? They rot in the ground while their killer runs free.

author: roose bolton
content: The Kingslayer won't remain free for long. My best hunters are after him.

author: robb stark
content: A Mallister?

author: catelyn stark
content: Ser Jeremy. My father's bannerman.

author: robb stark
content: Find her a chamber that will serve as a cell.

author: talisa
content: She's your mother.

author: robb stark
content: She freed Jaime Lannister. The Lannisters robbed them of their sons and she robbed them of their justice.

author: qyburn
content: Water. Water.

author: talisa
content: This needs to be cleaned and closed.

author: robb stark
content: What's your name, friend?

author: qyburn
content: Qyburn.

author: talisa
content: You're lucky to be alive.

author: qyburn
content: Lucky?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The badge looks good on you. Almost as good as it looked on me. Are you enjoying your new position?

author: tywin lannister
content: Am I enjoying it?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I was very happy as Hand of the King.

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes. I heard how happy you were.

author: tywin lannister
content: blows on his paper to dry the ink.

author: tywin lannister
content: You brought a whore into my bed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It wasn't your bed at the time.

author: tywin lannister
content: I sent you here to advise the king. I gave you real power and authority. You chose to spend your days as you always have, bedding harlots and drinking with thieves.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Occasionally I drank with the harlots.

author: tywin lannister
content: What do you want, Tyrion?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why does everyone assume I want something? Can't I simply visit with my beloved father? My beloved father who somehow forgot to visit his wounded son after he fell on the battlefield.

author: tywin lannister
content: Maester Pycelle assured me your wounds were not fatal.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I organized the defense of this city while you held court in the ruins of Harrenhal. I led the foray when the enemies were at the gate while your grandson, the king, quivered in fear behind the walls. I bled in the mud for our family. And as my reward, I was trundled off to some dark little cell. But what do I want? A little bloody gratitude would be a start.

author: tywin lannister
content: Jugglers and singers require applause. You are a Lannister. Do you think I demanded a garland of roses every time I suffered a wound on a battlefield? Hmm? Now, I have seven kingdoms to look after and three of them are in open rebellion. So tell me what you want.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I want what is mine by right. Jaime is your eldest son, heir to your lands and titles. But he is a Kingsguard, forbidden from marriage or inheritance. The day Jaime put on the white cloak, he gave up his claim to Casterly Rock. I am your son and lawful heir.

author: tywin lannister
content: You want Casterly Rock?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It is mine by right.

author: tywin lannister
content: We'll find you accommodations more suited to your name and as a reward for your accomplishments during the battle of Blackwater Bay. And when the time is right, you will be given a position fit for your talents so that you can serve your family and protect our legacy. And if you serve faithfully, you will be rewarded with a suitable wife. And I would let myself be consumed by maggots before mocking the family name and making you heir to Casterly Rock.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why?

author: tywin lannister
content: Why? You ask that? You, who killed your mother to come into the world? You are an ill-made, spiteful little creature full of envy, lust, and low cunning. Men's laws give you the right to bear my name and display my colors since I cannot prove that you are not mine. And to teach me humility, the gods have condemned me to watch you waddle about wearing that proud lion that was my father's sigil and his father's before him. But neither gods nor men will ever compel me to let you turn Casterly Rock into your whorehouse. Go, now. Speak no more of your rights to Casterly Rock. Go.

author: tywin lannister
content: Oh, one more thing. The next whore I catch in your bed, I'll hang.

author: sansa stark
content: Dorne. It's going to Dorne.

author: shae
content: Why Dorne?

author: sansa stark
content: It's carrying silk and it's supposed to bring back wine in exchange. But it's not coming back. The captain's tired of risking his life so King's Landing lords and ladies can get drunk on better wine than they deserve. He's going to stay in Dorne. Wait out the winter where it's beautiful and warm.

author: shae
content: I met some people in Dorne who weren't so beautiful and warm.

author: sansa stark
content: Don't ruin the game.

author: shae
content: I told you, I don't want to play.

author: sansa stark
content: What about that one there?

author: shae
content: That one? It's going to Volantis.

author: sansa stark
content: Why?

author: shae
content: Because when I got on a ship in Volantis, it looked like that one.

author: sansa stark
content: That's not how the game works. You're not supposed to just blurt out the right answer. You've got to invent a story about where the ship is going and why.

author: shae
content: Why should I make up a story when I know the truth?

author: sansa stark
content: Because the truth is always either terrible or boring.

author: petyr baelish
content: Lovely day for it. Watching the ships.

author: sansa stark
content: Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: Might I speak with Lady Sansa alone for a moment?

author: petyr baelish
content: I saw your mother not long ago. She's very eager to see you. And your sister.

author: sansa stark
content: Arya's alive? You said you'd take me home.

author: petyr baelish
content: You said King's Landing was your home. You are the property of the crown. Stealing you would be treason. If you were to tell just one person ...

author: sansa stark
content: I won't tell anyone.

author: petyr baelish
content: How do I know?

author: sansa stark
content: Because I'm a terrible liar. You said so yourself. Please, Lord Baelish. Tell me what to do. Tell me when.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm waiting for word on an assignment that will take me far away from the capital. When I set sail, I might be able to take you with me. But you'll need to be ready to leave on a moment's notice.

author: ros
content: You're her handmaiden?

author: shae
content: Yes. And you're his...?

author: ros
