content: Let me guess. He's not a magician.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No.

author: bronn
content: He's stealing it?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Worse, he's borrowing it.

author: bronn
content: What's wrong with that?

author: tyrion lannister
content: We can't afford to pay it back, that's what's wrong with it. The crown owes millions to my father.

author: bronn
content: Seeing as it's his grandson's ass on the throne, I imagine he'll forgive that debt.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Forgive a debt, my father? For a man of the world, you're strangely naive.

author: bronn
content: I've never borrowed money before. I'm not clear on the rules.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, ahem, the basic principle is I lend you money, and after an agreed upon period of time, you return it with interest.

author: bronn
content: And what if I don't?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, you have to.

author: bronn
content: But what if I don't?

author: tyrion lannister
content: This is why I don't lend you money. Anyway, it's not my father I'm worried about. It's the Iron Bank of Braavos. We owe them tens of millions. If we fail to repay these loans, the bank will fund our enemies. One way or another, they always get their gold back.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah, the return of the conquering hero. Does he have a little jaunt in his step?

author: bronn
content: The lado s practically skipping.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You were gone a long time. I trust you got your money's worth. Or should I say my money's worth?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, it was a gift, Podrick. This is more than I give you in a year.

author: bronn
content: He's a squire. You don't pay him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, then it's much more than I give you in a year.

author: podrick

author: varys
content: As a boy, I traveled with a troupe of actors through the Free Cities. One day in Myr, a certain man made my master an offer too tempting to refuse. I feared the man meant to use me as I'd heard some men used small boys. But what he wanted was far worse. He gave me a potion that made me powerless to move or speak, yet did nothing to dull my senses. With a hooked blade he sliced me, root and stem, chanting all the while. He burned my parts in a brazier. The flames turned blue and I heard a voice answer his call. I still dream of that night. Not of the sorcerer, not of his blade. I dream of the voice from the flames. Was it a god? A demon? A conjurer's trick? I don't know. But the sorcerer called and a voice answered. And ever since that day, I have hated magic and all those who practice it. But you can see why I was eager to aid in your fight against Stannis and his Red Priestess. A symbolic revenge of sorts.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, ahem. I feel the need for actual revenge against the actual person who tried to have me killed. Which will require a degree of influence, which-

author: varys
content: You do not possess at the moment.

author: varys
content: But influence is largely a matter of patience, I have found. Once I had served the sorcerer's purpose, he threw me out of his house to die. I resolved to live to spite him. I begged. I sold what parts of my body remained to me. I became an excellent thief and soon learned that the contents of a man's letters are more valuable than the contents of his purse. Step by step, one distasteful task after another, I made my way from the slums of Myr to the small council chamber. Influence grows like a weed. I tended mine patiently until its tendrils reached from the Red Keep all the way across to the far side of the world where I managed to wrap them around something very special.

content: Will I die?

author: qyburn
content: No. The corruption has spread. I fear it must be cut away. The safest course would be to take the whole arm off.

author: jaime lannister
content: Then you'll die. You're no maester. Where's your chain?

author: qyburn
content: The Citadel stripped me of it. They found some of my experiments too bold. I can leave your upper arm, make the cut at your elbow.

author: jaime lannister
content: I don't need my right hand to kill you.

author: qyburn
content: I can take away the rotting flesh and try and burn out the corruption - with boiling wine.

author: jaime lannister
content: Mmm.

author: qyburn
content: With any luck, that will suffice. You'll need milk of the poppy.

author: jaime lannister
content: No milk of the poppy.

author: qyburn
content: There will be pain.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll scream.

author: qyburn
content: Quite a bit of pain.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll scream loudly.

author: cersei lannister
content: Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: I wonder if I might ask you for a favor.

author: petyr baelish
content: Of course, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: I have reason to believe that House Tyrell do not hold the crown's best interests at heart.

author: petyr baelish
content: I see. And have you shared these suspicions with Lord Tywin?

author: cersei lannister
content: My father's a practical man. He appreciates facts.

author: petyr baelish
content: Myself, I often find them a hindrance.

author: cersei lannister
content: And he appreciates those who aid his family, as you well know. He's almost as generous to those who help us as he is unpleasant towards those who don't. You have a good working relationship with the Tyrells. I thought you might look into it before you leave the capital.

author: petyr baelish
content: I shall do my best.

author: cersei lannister
content: Thank you. And your best will prove better than when I asked you to locate Arya Stark?

author: petyr baelish
content: I assure you that it will.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Gods, boy, that's enough. We're not in a tavern.

author: podrick
content: Pardon, my lady.

author: olenna tyrell
content: No need to speak. Are there any figs? Fetch some. I always take figs midafternoon. They help move the bowels. To what do I owe this summons?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank you for seeing me, my lady. I had hoped we might discuss a few financial matters.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I climbed all those steps to discuss financial matters?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's the royal wedding. I'm told you had a hand in planning it.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Naturally.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's shaping up to be a very involved affair. The word extravagant has been used.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What good is the word extravagant if it can't be used to describe a royal wedding?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I understand that.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Good.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But, as Master of Coin, it falls upon me to calculate the cost for the crown. As of now, it's a huge expense.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And?

author: tyrion lannister
content: And we're at war, Lady Olenna.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Oh, I'd nearly forgotten.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, and maintaining supply lines-

author: olenna tyrell
content: I can't think how it slipped my mind. What is it, twelve thousand infantrymen the Tyrell family has supplied? Two thousand in support. Provisions so this city might survive the winter. A million bushels of wheat. Half a million bushels each of barley, oats, and rye. Twenty thousand head of cattle. Fifty thousand sheep. You don't have to lecture me about wartime expenses. I'm quite familiar with them.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And we are so grateful for your contributions which are necessary for the preservation of the realm.

author: olenna tyrell
content: As is a royal wedding. The people are hungry for more than just food. They crave distractions. And if we don't provide them, they'll create their own. And their distractions are likely to end with us being torn to pieces. A royal wedding is much safer. Wouldn't you say?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I would.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And traditionally paid for by the royal family.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I was told you were drunk, impertinent, and thoroughly debauched. You can imagine my disappointment at finding nothing but a browbeaten bookkeeper. Where did you go for them, Volantis?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My lady-

author: olenna tyrell
content: Oh, very well. I won't have it said that House Tyrell refuses to play its part. We'll pay for half the expenses and the celebrations will go on as planned. Is that sufficient?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Quite sufficient. Thank you.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Very good, then. That's settled. Good day.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Give me that.

author: arya stark
content: What are you doing?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Just mending Lord Beric's armor.

author: arya stark
content: Why?

author: gendry baratheon
content: I'm going to stay on and smith for the Brotherhood.

author: arya stark
content: Have you lost your mind? When the Lannisters find this place, you think they'll spare the smiths? They'll cave your head in with your own helmet.

author: gendry baratheon
content: The Lannisters wanted to kill me long before I joined the Brotherhood.

author: arya stark
content: You don't have to do this.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I want to. They need good men.

author: arya stark
content: Robb needs good men, too. We're leaving tomorrow. And then you-

author: gendry baratheon
content: What? Serve him? I've served men my entire life. I served Master Mott at King's Landing and he sold me to the Watch. I served Lord Tywin at Harrenhal, wondering every day if I'd get tortured or killed. I'm done serving.

author: arya stark
content: You just said you were serving Lord Beric.

author: gendry baratheon
content: He may be their leader, but they chose him. These men are brothers. They're a family. I've never had a family.

author: arya stark
content: I can be your family.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You wouldn't be my family. You'd be 'my lady'.

author: martyn
content: Willem. Willem!

author: willem
content: Is this a rescue?

author: rickard karstark
content: Lannister filth! Take him!

author: martyn
content: Please, I didn't do anything. I'm just a squire. Please-

author: robb stark
content: Bring them in.

author: robb stark
content: Is that all of them? It took five of you to murder two unarmed squires?

author: rickard karstark
content: Not murder, Your Grace. Vengeance.

author: robb stark
content: Vengeance? Those boys didn't kill your sons. I saw Harrion die on the battlefield and Torrhen-

author: rickard karstark
content: Was strangled by the Kingslayer. They were his kin.

author: robb stark
content: They were boys! Look at them.

author: rickard karstark
content: Tell your mother to look at them. She killed them as much as I.

author: robb stark
content: My mother had nothing to do with this. This was your treason.

author: rickard karstark
content: It's treason to free your enemies. In war, you kill your enemies. Did your father not teach you that, boy?

author: robb stark
content: Leave him.

author: rickard karstark
content: Aye. Leave me to the king. He wants to give me a scolding before he sets me free. That's how he deals with treason. Our King in the North. Or should I call him the King Who Lost the North?

author: robb stark
content: Escort Lord Karstark to the dungeon. Hang the rest.

author: man
content: Mercy, sire! I didn't kill anyone. I only watched for the guards.

author: robb stark
content: This one was only the watcher. Hang him last so he can watch the others die.

author: man
content: Please! Please, no. They made me do it! They made me! They made me!

author: edmure
content: Word of this can't leave Riverrun. They were Tywin Lannister's nephews. The Lannisters pay their debts. They never stop talking about it.

author: robb stark
content: Would you make me a liar as well as a murderer?

author: edmure
content: It wouldn't be lying. We will bury them and remain silent until the war is done.

author: robb stark
content: I'm not fighting for justice if I don't serve justice to murderers in my ranks, no matter how highborn. He has to die.

author: catelyn stark
content: The Karstarks are Northmen. They won't forgive the killing of their lord.

author: talisa
content: Your mother's right. If you do this, the Karstarks will abandon you.

author: robb stark
content: You tended to their wounds. You brought them supper. Now they're dead.

author: talisa
content: And more boys will keep dying until this war is over. You need Karstark men to end it.

author: catelyn stark
content: Spare his life. Keep him as a hostage.

author: edmure
content: A hostage. Tell the Karstarks that as long as they remain loyal, he will not be harmed.

author: rickard karstark
content: The blood of the First Men flows through my veins as much as yours, boy. I fought the Mad King for your father. I fought Joffrey for you. We are kin- Stark and Karstark.

author: robb stark
content: That didn't stop you from betraying me. And it won't save you now.

author: rickard karstark
content: I don't want it to save me. I want it to haunt you to the end of your days.

author: robb stark
content: Kneel, my lord.

author: robb stark
content: Rickard Karstark, Lord of Karhold, here in sight of gods and men, I sentence you to die. Would you speak a final word?

author: rickard karstark
content: Kill me and be cursed. You are no king of mine.

author: arya stark
content: Joffrey. Cersei. Ilyn Payne. Ser Meryn. The Hound. What are you going to do with me?

author: thoros
content: At first light we'll ride for Riverrun. Your brother's there now. He'll make a contribution to our cause and you can go home.

author: arya stark
content: I'm a hostage and you're selling me.

author: thoros
content: Don't think of it that way.

author: arya stark
content: But it is that way.

author: thoros
content: It is. And it isn't.

author: arya stark
content: More is than isn't.

author: thoros
content: Beric admired your father a great deal, you know. He wanted to refuse your ransom altogether.

author: arya stark
content: So why don't you?

author: thoros
content: We need the gold.

author: beric
content: Do I frighten you, child?

author: arya stark
content: No.

author: beric
content: You're angry with me. And I don't blame you. But letting him go was the right thing. I have more reason than most to want him hanged.

author: arya stark
content: I thought he killed you.

author: beric
content: He did.

author: arya stark
content: But how?

author: beric
content: Thoros how many times have you brought me back?

author: thoros
content: It's the Lord of Light brings you back. I'm just the lucky drunk who says the words.

author: beric
content: How many times?

author: thoros
content: Five, I think. No, this makes six.

author: beric
content: Six.

author: thoros
content: There was the first time- the Mountain. Show her. Lance right through the chest.

author: beric
content: Then I was stabbed in the belly.

author: thoros
content: Then it was an arrow in the back. And that axe in the side.

author: beric
content: Then the Lannisters caught me and executed me for treason. Was it a hanging or a dagger in the eye?

author: thoros
content: Both. Fuckers couldn't decide.

author: thoros
content: And the Hound makes six.

author: beric
content: Second time I've been killed by a Clegane.

author: thoros
content: You'd think you'd learn. It's not getting any easier, you know.

author: beric
content: I know. Every time I come back, I'm a bit less. Pieces of you get chipped away.

author: arya stark
content: Could you bring back a man without a head? Not six times. Just once.

author: thoros
content: I don't think it works that way, child.

author: beric
content: He was a good man, Ned Stark. He's at rest now, somewhere. I would never wish my life upon him.

author: arya stark
content: I would. You're alive.

author: selyse
content: Lord, cast your light upon me. Protect me in the darkness. Burn away my sins. Help me serve you. Use me as you will. For the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: selyse
content: I have prayed day and night for you to come to me.

author: stannis baratheon
content: My lady.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I meant to come sooner. The battle-

author: selyse
content: I know of your troubles, My king. The Lady Melisandre has told me everything.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Yes, of course.

author: selyse
content: You mustn't despair. Your claim is true. You will be victorious.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I believed that once.

author: selyse
content: You are the one godo s champion and the finest man I've ever known.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Selyse. I've broken a sacred vow. I've sinned.

author: selyse
content: No.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I've wronged you. I have shamed you.

author: selyse
content: You're doing godo s work.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You don't understand. The Red Woman- the Lady Melisandre-

author: selyse
content: I know, Stannis. The Lady Melisandre has told me everything. No act done in service of the Lord of Light can ever be a sin. When she told me, I wept with joy.

author: selyse
content: Oh, my sweet boys. Petyr, Tommard, Edric. I thank god every day for bringing Melisandre to us. She gave you a son. I gave you - nothing.

author: stannis baratheon
content: That's not true.

author: selyse
content: So you've come to see her as well? There is no need. You must keep away from such distractions.

author: stannis baratheon
content: She's my daughter. I want to see her.

author: selyse
content: You are a king. You don't need my permission.

author: shireen
content: Under the sea I know, I know/ Oh, oh, oh

author: shireen
content: The birds have scales / And the fish take wing / I know, I know / Oh, oh, oh

author: stannis baratheon
content: Shireen.

author: shireen
content: Father!

author: stannis baratheon
content: You've grown since I last saw you.

author: shireen
content: Mother said you fought in a battle. Did you win?

author: stannis baratheon
content: No.

author: shireen
content: Did the Onion Knight come back with you?

author: stannis baratheon
content: He did. He fought bravely.

author: shireen
content: He hasn't come to visit me. He said he'd bring me back a present from the capital.

author: stannis baratheon
content: He won't be visiting, child.

author: shireen
content: Why not? He's my friend. Look.

author: shireen
content: He made this for me. But don't tell Mother I have it. It's a secret. Mother doesn't like the Onion Knight.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Ser Davos is a traitor. He's rotting in a dungeon cell for his crime. Best forget him.

author: jaime lannister
content: Not so hard. You'll scrub the skin off.

author: brienne
content: What are you doing here?

author: jaime lannister
content: I need a bath. Help me out of these rags.

author: jaime lannister
content: Now get out.

author: brienne
content: There's another tub.

author: jaime lannister
content: This one suits me fine. Don't worry. I'm not interested. If I faint, pull me out. I don't intend to be the first Lannister to die in a bathtub.

author: brienne
content: Why should I care how you die?

author: jaime lannister
content: You swore a solemn vow, remember? You're supposed to get me to King's Landing in one piece. Not going so well, is it? No wonder Renly died with you guarding him.

author: jaime lannister
content: That was unworthy. Forgive me. You protected me better than most-

author: brienne
content: Don't you mock me.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm apologizing. I'm sick of fighting. Let's call a truce.

author: brienne
content: You need trust to have a truce.

author: jaime lannister
content: I trust you.

author: jaime lannister
content: There it is. There's the look. I've seen it for seventeen years on face after face. You all despise me. Kingslayer. Oathbreaker. A man without honor. You've heard of wildfire?

author: brienne
content: Of course.

author: jaime lannister
content: The Mad King was obsessed with it. He loved to watch people burn, the way their skin blackened and blistered and melted off their bones. He burned lords he didn't like. He burned Hands who disobeyed him. He burned anyone who was against him. Before long, half the country was against him. Aerys saw traitors everywhere. So he had his pyromancer place caches of wildfire all over the city- beneath the Sept of Baelor and the slums of Flea Bottom. Under houses, stables, taverns. Even beneath the Red Keep itself. Finally, the day of reckoning came. Robert Baratheon marched on the capital after his victory at the Trident. But my father arrived first with the whole Lannister army at his back, promising to defend the city against the rebels. I knew my father better than that. He's never been one to pick the losing side. I told the Mad King as much. I urged him to surrender peacefully. But the king didn't listen to me. He didn't listen to Varys who tried to warn him. But he did listen to Grand Maester Pycelle, that grey, sunken cunt. 'You can trust the Lannisters,' he said. 'The Lannisters have always been true friends of the crown.' So we opened the gates and my father sacked the city. Once again, I came to the king, begging him to surrender. He told me to bring him my father's head. Then he turned to his pyromancer. 'Burn them all,' he said. 'Burn them in their homes. Burn them in their beds.' Tell me, if your precious Renly commanded you to kill your own father and stand by while thousands of men, women, and children burned alive, would you have done it? Would you have kept your oath then?

author: jaime lannister
content: First, I killed the pyromancer. And then when the king turned to flee, I drove my sword into his back. 'Burn them all,' he kept saying. 'Burn them all.' I don't think he expected to die. He- he meant to burn with the rest of us and rise again, reborn as a dragon to turn his enemies to ash. I slit his throat to make sure that didn't happen. That's where Ned Stark found me.

author: brienne
content: If this is true why didn't you tell anyone? Why didn't you tell Lord Stark?

author: jaime lannister
content: Stark? You think the honorable Ned Stark wanted to hear my side? He judged me guilty the moment he set eyes on me. By what right does the wolf judge the lion? By what right?

author: brienne
content: Help! Help! The Kingslayer!

author: jaime lannister
content: Jaime. My name is Jaime.

author: shireen
content: Onion Knight. Ser Onion Knight.

author: davos
content: Princess? Gods, what are you doing here?

author: shireen
content: Shh, you'll wake Bert.

author: davos
content: Bert?

author: shireen
content: He's the fat one. He's on guard duty tonight. He likes to drink wine and sleep a lot.

author: davos
content: Go back to your room. You're not supposed to be here. If your father knew-

author: shireen
content: he said you Were a traitor. Are you?

author: davos
content: I am, child. I disobeyed my king, your father, and now I'm paying the price.

author: shireen
content: I don't care. You're my friend. You must get bored down here. I brought you something to read. It's about Aegon and his dragons. Aegon used to live here. Did you know that? And the Targaryens built this castle.

author: davos
content: Aye. So they did.

author: shireen
content: You can hide the book under your cloak. It's a good one. I'll bring you more.

author: davos
content: Thank you, my lady. I'm sure it's a fine book, but it's wasted on me.

author: shireen
content: Take it. I have more.

author: davos
content: My lady, I can't read the words.

author: shireen
content: You can't?

author: shireen
content: I'll teach you. I'll come when Bert's on duty and teach you.

author: davos
content: No. No. No.

author: shireen
content: It's easy. It'll be fun.

author: davos
content: Go. We can't.

author: shireen
content: Why not? What will they do, lock us in cells?

author: davos
content: I wouldn't know where to start.

author: shireen
content: At the beginning. This word is Aegon. When you see A, E, and G together like that, it sounds like egg. And the title of the whole book is 'An History of Aegon the Conqueror and His Conquest of Westeros.'

author: jorah mormont
content: It was a bitch of a siege.

author: barristan
content: Mm, you were first through the breach at Pyke?

author: jorah mormont
content: The second. Thoros of Myr went in alone, waving that flaming sword of his.

author: barristan
content: Thoros of Myr. Bloody madman. Robert knighted you after the battle?

author: jorah mormont
content: Proudest moment of my life. One knee in the dust, the king's sword on my shoulder, listening to the words. 'In the name of the Warrior, I charge you to be brave.' All I could think of was how badly I had to piss.

author: jorah mormont
content: In full plate metal for sixteen hours. Never occurred to me till the fighting was over. I was very nearly the first man knighted to piss on the king's boots.

author: barristan
content: Robert would have laughed. He was a good man, a great warrior. And a terrible king. I burned away my years fighting for terrible kings.

author: jorah mormont
content: You swore an oath.

author: barristan
content: Yes. And a man of honor keeps his vows, even if he's serving a drunk or a lunatic. Just once in my life before it's over, I want to know what it's like to serve with pride, to fight for someone I believe in. Do you believe in her?

author: jorah mormont
content: With all my heart.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: These are the ones?

author: missandei
content: Yes, khaleesi. The officers.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You did not choose this life. But you are free men now. And free men make their own choices. Have you selected your own leader from amongst your ranks?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Remove your helmet

author: grey worm
content: This one has the honor.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What is your name?

author: grey worm
content: Grey Worm.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Grey Worm.

author: missandei
content: All Unsullied boys are given new names when they are cut- Grey Worm, Red Flea, Black Rat. Names that remind them what they are- vermin.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: From this day forward you will choose your own names. You will tell your fellow soldiers to do the same. Throw away your slave name. Choose the name your parents gave you, or any other. A name that gives you pride.

author: grey worm
content: Grey Worm" gives me pride. It is a very lucky name. The name this one was born with was cursed. That was the name he had when he was taken as a slave. But Grey Worm is the name this one had the day Daenerys Stormborn set him free.

author: jorah mormont
content: King Robert wanted her dead.

author: barristan
content: Of course he wanted her dead. She's a Targaryen. The last Targaryen.

author: jorah mormont
content: I suppose no one on the small council could speak sense to him.

author: barristan
content: I didn't sit on the small council.

author: jorah mormont
content: No? Doesn't the Lord of the Kingsguard traditionally-

author: barristan
content: Traditionally, yes, but I killed a dozen of Robert's friends during his rebellion.

author: barristan
content: He didn't want advice on how to govern from a man who had fought for the Mad King. Can't say I minded much. I always hated the politics.

author: jorah mormont
content: Yeah, I imagine I would, too. Hours spent jabbering about backstabbings - and betrayals the world over.

author: barristan
content: Mm-hmm.

author: jorah mormont
content: Still, she'll have to wade through that muck if she wants to rule the Seven Kingdoms.

author: barristan
content: She'll have good men around her to advise her, men with experience.

author: jorah mormont
content: Which men do you have in mind?

author: barristan
content: Forgive me, Ser Jorah, for what I'm about to say, but your reputation in Westeros has suffered over the years.

author: jorah mormont
content: It suffered for a reason. I sold men into slavery.

author: barristan
content: I don't know if your presence by her side will help our cause when we go home.

author: jorah mormont
content: Our cause? Forgive me, Ser Barristan, but I was busy defending the khaleesi against King Robert's assassins while you were still bowing to the man.

author: barristan
content: We both want her to rule. Am I wrong?

author: jorah mormont
content: You only joined us a few days ago. I can't speak to your intentions.

author: barristan
content: If we're truly her loyal servants, we will do whatever needs to be done, no matter the cost, no matter our pride.

author: jorah mormont
content: You're not Lord here. You're just another exile. And I take my orders from the queen.

author: talisa
content: Come to bed.

author: robb stark
content: You were right.

author: robb stark
content: The Karstarks are gone. Almost half our forces. Tywin Lannister knows what he needs to do to make us unravel. Nothing. Only wait.

author: talisa
content: Don't let him.

author: robb stark
content: What can I do? Attack King's Landing? There's nothing he'd like better. He'd crush us in a day.

author: talisa
content: We could ride north. Take your land back from the Greyjoys. Wait out the winter.

author: robb stark
content: Winter could last five years. Once my bannermen are home again, sitting by the fire, surrounded by their families, warm and safe, they'll never ride south again. When I gathered my lords together, we had a purpose, a mission. Now we're like a band of bickering children.

author: talisa
content: Give them a new purpose.

author: robb stark
content: What?

author: talisa
content: Oh, I don't know. I don't even know where Winterfell is.

author: robb stark
content: Here. And we're here. King's Landing-

author: talisa
content: What is it?

author: robb stark
content: I can't force them to meet us in the field and I can't attack them where they're strongest, but I can attack them where they're not.

author: robb stark
content: And Casterly Rock can't run away. I'm going to take their home away from them.

author: talisa
content: Can you do it?

author: robb stark
content: I need men to replace the Karstarks who marched home. There is only one person in this kingdom with that kind of army who hasn't already sided with the Lannisters. The man whose daughter I was supposed to marry- Walder Frey.

author: sansa stark
content: He's such a splendid fighter. Do you have any idea when we might

author: margaery tyrell
content: I'll plant the seed as soon as Joffrey and I are married. It should grow quickly.

author: sansa stark
content: Joffrey won't let me leave. He's got too many reasons to keep me here.

author: margaery tyrell
content: And only one to let you go. Because it will please me.

author: loras
content: Squire!

author: olyvar
content: Well fought, ser.

author: loras
content: That was no fight. I don't know you.

author: olyvar
content: Olyver, if it please you.

author: olyvar
content: I should like to see you spar with a proper partner, ser.

author: loras
content: How did you know?

author: olyvar
content: Know what?

author: loras
content: That I wanted to.

author: loras
content: My lord, I'll have you know I'm to be married soon and even my intended hasn't the slightest notion.

author: olyvar
content: They rarely do, in my experience.

author: loras
content: You have a good deal of experience, do you?

author: olyvar
content: With the husbands.

author: petyr baelish
content: That didn't take long.

author: olyvar
content: Well, it took long enough. It seems our Knight of Flowers is engaged to be wed.

author: petyr baelish
content: Is he? And who's the lucky girl?

author: petyr baelish
content: She may not be the grandest ship in the world or the fastest, but she's mine. I've always wanted a ship. Now I want a dozen. Strange, isn't it?

author: sansa stark
content: What is?

author: petyr baelish
content: It doesn't matter what we want, once we get it, then we want something else. Your hair is different.

author: sansa stark
content: Is it?

author: petyr baelish
content: Lady Margaery wears it that way.

author: sansa stark
content: Many ladies wear it this way.

author: petyr baelish
content: I have good news. I'll be leaving the city soon.

author: sansa stark
content: You still want me to come with you?

author: petyr baelish
content: It's not a question of what I want. It's what you want. You want to go home, don't you?

author: sansa stark
content: Of course. More than anything. But maybe it would be better to wait. I've been thinking how dangerous it would be. Not just for me, but for you. You've been so kind. I'd feel terrible if anything happened to you. I can't tell you how touched I am by your concern for my welfare.

author: petyr baelish
content: I hope you know that I'm your friend, Sansa. Your true friend.

author: sansa stark
content: I do, Lord Baelish.

author: petyr baelish
content: Petyr.

author: sansa stark
content: Petyr.

author: petyr baelish
content: If you wish to stay, then of course you will stay.

author: petyr baelish
content: We'll speak again when I return.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're late.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What's she doing here?

author: tywin lannister
content: Our business concerns her, too. Sit.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You'll be pleased to learn that after one conversation with Olenna Tyrell, I've saved the crown hundreds of thousands on this wedding.

author: tywin lannister
content: Never mind that now. We have something important to discuss.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm Master of Coin. Saving money is important.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stop that. You're making me uncomfortable.

author: tywin lannister
content: Your sister has learned that your new friends the Tyrells are plotting to marry Sansa Stark to Ser Loras.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Very well. She's a lovely girl. Missing some of Loras' favorite bits, but I'm sure they'll make do.

author: tywin lannister
content: Your jokes are not appreciated.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It wasn't my best, but-

author: tywin lannister
content: I bring them into the royal fold and this is how they repay me, by trying to steal the key to the North out from under me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sansa is the key to the North? I seem to remember she has an older brother.

author: tywin lannister
content: The Karstarks have marched home. The young wolf has lost half his army. His days are numbered. Theon Greyjoy murdered both his brothers. That makes Sansa Stark the heir to Winterfell. And I am not about to hand her over to the Tyrells.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Tyrell army is helping us to win this war. Do you really think it's wise to refuse them?

author: tywin lannister
content: There's nothing to refuse. This is a plot. Plots are not public knowledge. And the Tyrells won't carry this one out until after Joffrey's wedding. We need to act first and kill this union in its crib.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And how do we do that?

author: tywin lannister
content: We find Sansa Stark a different husband.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Wonderful.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes, it is.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You can't mean it.

author: tywin lannister
content: I can and I do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Joffrey has made this poor girl's life miserable since the day he took her father's head. Now she's finally free of him and you give her to me? That's cruel even for you.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you intend on mistreating her? The girl's happiness is not my concern, nor should it be yours.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She's a child!

author: cersei lannister
content: She's flowered, I assure you. She and I have discussed it at length.

author: tywin lannister
content: There, you see? You will wed her, bed her, and put a child in her. Surely you're capable of that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And if I refuse?

author: tywin lannister
content: You wanted to be rewarded for your valor in battle. Sansa Stark is a finer reward than you could ever dare hope for. And it is past time you were wed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I was wed. Or don't you remember?

author: tywin lannister
content: Only too well.

author: cersei lannister
content: You should be thanking the gods for this. This is more than you deserve.

author: tywin lannister
content: Tyrion will do as he's bid. As will you.

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you mean?

author: tywin lannister
content: You'll marry Ser Loras.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not.

author: tywin lannister
content: The boy is heir to Highgarden. Tyrion will secure the North, you will secure the Reach.

author: cersei lannister
content: No, I won't do it.

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes, you will. You're still fertile. You need to marry again and breed.

author: cersei lannister
content: I am Queen Regent, not some broodmare.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're my daughter! You will do as I command and you will marry Loras Tyrell and put an end to the disgusting rumors about you once and for all.

author: cersei lannister
content: Father, don't make me do it again, please.

author: tywin lannister
content: Not another word. My children. You've disgraced the Lannister name for far too long.

author: shireen
content: It's always summer / Under the sea / I know I know / Oh, oh, oh. / The birds have scales / And the fish take wing / I know I know / Oh, oh, oh. / The rain is dry / and snow falls up / I know, I know / Oh, oh, oh. / The stones crack open / The water burns / The shadows come to dance / My lord / The shadows come to play / The shadows come to dance / My lord / The shadows come to stay.

author: gilly
content: You've got too much wood in there.

author: sam
content: But the more wood, the bigger the fire.

author: gilly
content: It needs to breathe. Take off that big log.

author: sam
content: Huh. You know your fires.

author: gilly
content: Someone built your fires for you growing up?

author: sam
content: It doesn't get so cold down in the Reach. And there were servants, of course.

author: gilly
content: I knew you were highborn.

author: sam
content: Oh, I found something at the Fist of the First Men. Buried treasure. Thousands of years old. I think.

author: gilly
content: What does it do?

author: sam
content: I'm not sure that it does anything. It's beautiful, though, isn't it?

author: gilly
content: How much longer?

author: sam
content: Not so far. A few more days.

author: gilly
content: Is the Wall as big as they say?

author: sam
content: Bigger. So big you can't even see the top sometimes. It's hidden in clouds.

author: gilly
content: You're playing with me.

author: sam
content: I'm not. It's seven hundred feet high, all made of ice. On a warm day you can see it weeping. Castle Black is nice enough. They keep a fire burning in the long hall day and night. And Hobb makes venison stew with onions. Very tasty. Sometimes, one of the brothers will sing. Dareon sings best.

author: gilly
content: Do you sing?

author: sam
content: No. No, no, no. Not very well.

author: gilly
content: Sing me a song.

author: sam
content: Oh, all right. Let's see.

author: sam
content: Oh ahem. The father's face is stern and strong / He sits and judges right from wrong / He weighs our lives, the short and long / And loves the little children / The mother gives the gift of life / And watches over every wife / Her gentle smile ends all strife /And she loves her little children.

author: osha
content: That's not how you skin a rabbit.

author: meera
content: I know how to skin a rabbit.

author: osha
content: Not by the looks of it.

author: osha
content: You grow up north of the Wall, you learn the proper way to handle game.

author: meera
content: I didn't see any game before I got here.

author: osha
content: If I had a bow, I could have shot a dozen rabbits.

author: meera
content: Well, I made this bow myself. Guess you don't learn how to do that north of the Wall.

author: osha
content: You learn how to use your fists, though.

author: meera
content: Oh, you're gonna punch the rabbits to death?

author: osha
content: I had someone else in mind.

author: meera
content: Well, someone else is sitting right here.

author: bran stark
content: You're both very good at skinning rabbits.

author: osha
content: Some of us are just a little better.

author: meera
content: Well, some of us would say thank you when someone else hunts down their breakfast for them. Or don't they teach you to say thank you north of the Wall?

author: osha
content: You've got a big mouth, girl, and too many teeth.

author: bran stark
content: Stop it!

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: You've been fighting since you met. Just stop it.

author: osha
content: Lady Reed here's got a stick so far up her ass, it's a wonder her feet touch the ground.

author: bran stark
content: You've been nasty to her every day. Of course she's nasty back.

author: osha
content: Me? It's my fault? First time I met her, she put a knife to my throat.

author: bran stark
content: First time I met you, you held a knife at me. We can't fight each other. We'll never make it to the Wall. I want you both to make peace.

author: meera
content: Your way of skinning rabbits is quicker than mine.

author: osha
content: I said so, didn't I?

author: bran stark
content: Osha!

author: osha
content: You're a good little hunter.

author: meera
content: Thank you. See? Not so hard, is it? Thank you.

author: osha
content: Don't push me.

author: meera
content: Shh. I'm right here with you.

author: rickon
content: What's happening?

author: meera
content: I'm right here with you.

author: rickon
content: What's wrong with him?

author: meera
content: The visions take their toll.

author: bran stark
content: He's having one now?

author: jojen
content: I saw Jon Snow.

author: bran stark
content: You saw him? At Castle Black?

author: jojen
content: He was on the wrong side of the Wall surrounded by enemies.

author: tormund
content: Used to be you couldn't find a tree within a mile of the Wall. Crows would come out every morning with axes.

author: orell
content: Your flock gets smaller every year.

author: jon snow
content: You ever climbed it before?

author: ygritte
content: No. But Tormundo s done it half a hundred times. You're afraid.

author: jon snow
content: Aren't you?

author: ygritte
content: Aye. It's a long way up and a long way down. But I've waited my whole life to see the world from up there. Here, sit down.

author: ygritte
content: I brought a pair for you. They're too big for you, but they're good.

author: jon snow
content: You kill someone for them?

author: ygritte
content: Nah. I didn't kill him, but I bet his balls are still bruised.

author: ygritte
content: He wasn't good to me the way you're good to me. He didn't do that thing you do with your tongue.

author: jon snow
content: Can we not talk about that here?

author: ygritte
content: Can we not talk about that here? I'm Jon Snow. I've killed dead men and Qhorin Halfhand, but I'm scared of naked girls.

author: jon snow
content: Did I seem scared the other day?

author: ygritte
content: You were trembling like a leaf.

author: jon snow
content: Only in the beginning.

author: ygritte
content: Only in the beginning. You're a proper lover, Jon Snow. And don't worry. Your secret's safe with me.

author: jon snow
content: What secret?

author: ygritte
content: Do you think I'm as dumb as all those girls in silk dresses you knew growing up? You're loyal and you're brave. You didn't stop being a crow the day you walked into Mance Rayder's tent.

author: ygritte
content: But I'm your woman now, Jon Snow. You're going to be loyal to your woman. The Night's Watch don't care if you live or die. Mance Rayder don't care if I live or die. We're just soldiers in their armies and there's plenty more to carry on if we go down.

author: ygritte
content: It's you and me that matters to me and you. Don't ever betray me.

author: jon snow
content: I won't.

author: ygritte
content: Cause I'll cut your pretty cock right off and wear it 'round my neck.

author: tormund
content: Sink your metal deep and make sure it holds before taking your next step. And if you fall, don't scream. You don't want that to be the last thing she remembers.

author: arya stark
content: Joffrey. Cersei. Ilyn Payne.

author: anguy
content: You're good. You're not as good as you think you are.

author: arya stark
content: Face, tits, balls- I hit 'em right where I wanted to.

author: anguy
content: Aye, but you took your sweet time of it. You won't be fighting straw men, little lady. Show me your position.

author: anguy
content: Keep your elbow high. You want your back doing the hard labor. You're holding. Never hold.

author: arya stark
content: What?

author: anguy
content: Your muscles tense up when you hold. Pull the string back to the center of your chin and release. Never hold.

author: arya stark
content: But I have to aim.

author: anguy
content: Never aim.

author: arya stark
content: Never aim?

author: anguy
content: Your eye knows where it wants the arrow to go. Trust your eye.

author: arya stark
content: There's someone out there.

author: anguy
content: That's about far enough.

author: melisandre
content: We come as friends.

author: anguy
content: Begging your pardon, m'lady, but we'll be the judge of that.

author: melisandre
content: Valar morghulis.

author: thoros
content: Valar dohaeris. I don't see many priestesses of R'hollor in the Riverlands.

author: melisandre
content: You are Thoros of Myr.

author: melisandre
content: The High Priest gave you a mission. Turn King Robert away from his idols and towards the Lord of Light. What happened?

author: thoros
content: I failed.

author: melisandre
content: You quit, you mean. The heathen continue to slaughter each other and you continue to get drunk.

author: thoros
content: You worship Him in your way, and I'll worship Him in mine. Do you speak the common tongue?

author: thoros
content: My friends here don't speak High Valyrian. Why are you here, my lady?

author: beric
content: Forgive my manners. I don't see many ladies these days.

author: thoros
content: Lucky for the ladies.

author: melisandre
content: How many times has the Lord brought him back?

author: thoros
content: Six.

author: melisandre
content: That's not possible.

author: thoros
content: The Lord has smiled upon me.

author: melisandre
content: You should not have this power.

author: thoros
content: I have no power. I ask the Lord for His favor, and He responds as He will.

author: thoros
content: I've always been a terrible priest. Drank too much rum. Fucked all the whores in King's Landing. It's a terrible thing to say, but by the time I came to Westeros, I didn't believe in our Lord. I decided that He, that all the gods, were stories we told the children to make them behave. So I wore the robes and every now and then I'd recite the prayers, but it was just for show. A spectacle for the locals. Until the Mountain drove a lance through this one's heart. I knelt beside his cold body and said the old words. Not because I believed in them, but he was my friend and he was dead. And they were the only words I knew. And for the first time in my life, the Lord replied. Beric's eyes opened and I knew the truth. Our god is the one true god. And all men must serve Him.

author: melisandre
content: You've been to the other side.

author: beric
content: The other side? There is no other side. I have been to the darkness, my lady. He sent you to us for a reason.

author: melisandre
content: You have someone He needs.

author: anguy
content: Bodkin point. Penetrates plate at two hundred yards. Can you make 'em?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Yeah, nothing tricky about it. Just need decent steel.

author: anguy
content: I'll get you the steel.

author: man
content: Come on.

author: arya stark
content: I don't like that woman.

author: anguy
content: That's 'cause you're a girl.

author: arya stark
content: What does that have to do with anything?

author: beric
content: Forgive me, lad.

author: arya stark
content: What are you doing? Let go of him.

author: arya stark
content: Tell them to stop. Come on. He wants to be one of you. He wants to join the Brotherhood. Stop them!

author: beric
content: We serve the Lord of Light and the Lord of Light needs this boy.

author: arya stark
content: Did the Lord of Light tell you that or did she?

author: arya stark
content: You're not doing this for your god. You're doing it for gold.

author: thoros
content: We're doing it for both, girl. We can't defend the people without weapons and horses and food. And we can't get weapons and horses and food without gold.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You told me this was a Brotherhood. You told me I could be one of you.

author: melisandre
content: You are more than they can ever be. They're just foot soldiers in the great war. You will make kings rise and fall.

author: arya stark
content: You're a witch. You're going to hurt him.

author: melisandre
content: I see a darkness in you. And in that darkness, eyes staring back at me- brown eyes, blue eyes, green eyes. Eyes you'll shut forever. We will meet again.

author: ygritte
content: You staring at my ass, Jon Snow?

author: tormund
content: Look out!

author: ygritte
content: You all right?

author: tormund
content: Just seeing if you can take a hit, lad.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Sorry. Were you sleeping?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Wa-

author: ramsay bolton
content: Wa-? Wa-? Water? You want some water. I wish I had some for you.

author: ramsay bolton
content: So let's play a game. Which body part do you need the least?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Please.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Please is not a body part.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'll tell you everything, please.

author: ramsay bolton
content: But you've already told me everything. Remember? Your daddy was mean to you. The Starks didn't appreciate you. One good bit, though. The Stark boys, they're still alive. Wouldn't that be a hunt to remember? You failed, but I'm a better hunter than you.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Now how about your little finger? You don't use that for much, do you? No? Good. Let's start with that.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You've been wondering why you're here. Haven't you? Where you are. Who I am. Why I'm doing this to you. So guess. If you guess right, I'll tell you. By the old gods and the new, I swear it. You win the game if you can figure out who I am and why I'm torturing you and I win the game if you beg me to cut off your finger.

author: theon greyjoy
content: If I win, you'll let me go?

author: ramsay bolton
content: If you think this has a happy ending, you haven't been paying attention.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You say please again and you'll wish you hadn't. You first. Where are we?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The North.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Too vague.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Deepwood Motte.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Terrible guess.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Now, where?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Last Hearth.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Do I look like a fucking Umber to you?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Karhold!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Karhold? How did you know that? Did you see any banners flying when we came in?

author: theon greyjoy
content: No. It was just a guess.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Very good, Lord Theon. And who am I?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Torrhen Karstark.

author: ramsay bolton
content: He's dead. Strangled by the Kingslayer.

author: theon greyjoy
content: He was your brother. Your father is Lord Rickard Karstark.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You swore to tell me if I-

author: ramsay bolton
content: You're right.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Lord Rickard Karstark is Robb Stark's bannerman. I betrayed Robb. That's why you're torturing me.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Yes. You win.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Of course, you forgot to ask one question. You forgot to ask if I'm a liar.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I'm afraid I am.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Everything I told you is a lie.

author: ramsay bolton
content: This isn't happening to you for a reason. Well, one reason- I enjoy it.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Please, cut it off! Cut it off! Cut it off!

author: ramsay bolton
content: I win.

author: robb stark
content: Thank you for riding here so quickly. I know travel isn't easy in these times.

author: black walder
content: The roads are crawling with cutthroats and bandits. But when the King of the North summons us, we come.

author: lothar
content: Our father has instructed us to tell you that his alliance with the North can continue if his terms are met. Lord Frey requires a formal apology for your violation of your sacred oath to marry one of his daughters.

author: robb stark
content: Of course. He deserves as much. I was in the wrong.

author: black walder
content: As restitution for this betrayal, he demands Harrenhal and all its attendant lands.

author: edmure
content: I don't think that's-

author: robb stark
content: We are fighting for the North. Harrenhal is not in the North. It is his once the war is over and we have no further strategic need for it.

author: black walder
content: And there's something else.

author: robb stark
content: We will do whatever we can to give Lord Frey what he needs.

author: black walder
content: Not what, whom.

author: edmure
content: What?

author: edmure
content: No.

author: lothar
content: Our father requires Lord Edmure to wed one of his daughters- Roslin.

author: edmure
content: How old is she?

author: lothar
content: Nineteen.

author: edmure
content: Could I see her first?

author: black walder
content: You want to count her teeth? We depart for the Twins in the morning. We need an answer before we leave and a wedding not more than a fortnight thereafter or this alliance is at an end.

author: brynden
content: Your father does realize we're in the middle of a war?

author: lothar
content: Father is old. It will put his heart at peace if he could see her wed to a good husband.

author: black walder
content: And his recent experience has made him wary of long engagements.

author: robb stark
content: He has every right to be. Please excuse us while we discuss it.

author: edmure
content: Why should I let that old ferret choose my bride for me? At the very least, I should be offered the same choice you were. I'm his liege lord.

author: robb stark
content: He's a proud man and we've wounded him.

author: edmure
content: I didn't wound him. My answer is no.

author: brynden
content: Listen to me and listen very carefully. You-

author: edmure
content: The laws of gods and men are very clear. No man can compel another man to marry.

author: brynden
content: The laws of my fist are about to compel your teeth.

author: robb stark
content: It's all right. You heard him. If you refuse, our alliance with the Freys is dead.

author: edmure
content: He's wanted me for one of his daughters since I was 12. He's not gonna stop wanting it now. When I say no, he will come back and offer me a daughter of my choosing.

author: catelyn stark
content: You're willing to risk our freedom and our lives for a chance at a prettier wife?

author: robb stark
content: I have a war to fight. We can't win it without them. I have no time to haggle. You said you wanted to make amends for the Stone Mill.

author: brynden
content: You recall that heroic engagement?

author: edmure
content: I had something less permanent in mind.

author: robb stark
content: I've won every battle, but I'm losing this war. If we don't do this and do it now, we're lost.

author: edmure
content: I'll marry her.

author: robb stark
content: You're paying for my sins, Uncle. It's not fair or right. I'll remember it.

author: roose bolton
content: I see my men have finally found you something appropriate to wear.

author: brienne
content: Yes. Most kind of them. You're a Stark bannerman, Lord Bolton. I am acting on Lady Stark's orders to return Jaime Lannister to King's Landing.

author: roose bolton
content: When King Robb left Harrenhal, his mother was his prisoner. If she wasn't his mother, he'd have hanged her for treason.

author: roose bolton
content: I should send you back to Robb Stark.

author: jaime lannister
content: You should. But instead, you're sitting here watching me fail at dinner. Why might that be?

author: roose bolton
content: Wars cost money. Many people would pay a great deal for you.

author: jaime lannister
content: We both know who would pay the most. Or make you pay the most if he found out you had captured me and sent me back up north for a summary execution.

author: roose bolton
content: You're right. Perhaps the safest thing to do is to kill you both and burn your bodies.

author: jaime lannister
content: It would be, if you honestly believed my father would never find out about it.

author: roose bolton
content: King Robb is keeping your father quite busy. He doesn't have time for anything else.

author: jaime lannister
content: He'll make time for you.

author: roose bolton
content: As soon as you're well enough to travel, I will allow you to go to King's Landing as restitution for the mistakes my soldiers made. And you will swear to tell your father the truth, that I had nothing to do with your maiming.

author: jaime lannister
content: Shall we drink on it?

author: roose bolton
content: I don't partake.

author: jaime lannister
content: You do understand how suspicious that is to ordinary people?

author: jaime lannister
content: Very well. My lady, may our journey continue without further incident.

author: roose bolton
content: Oh, she won't be going with you.

author: brienne
content: I am charged with bringing Ser Jaime to-

author: roose bolton
content: You are charged with abetting treason.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm afraid I must insist.

author: roose bolton
content: You're in no place to insist on anything. I would have hoped you'd learned your lesson about overplaying your position.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Impossible.

author: tywin lannister
content: Why?

author: olenna tyrell
content: My grandson is the pride of Highgarden. The most desirable bachelor in all seven kingdoms. Your daughter-

author: tywin lannister
content: Is rich, the most beautiful woman in all seven kingdoms and the mother of the king.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Old.

author: tywin lannister
content: Old?

author: olenna tyrell
content: Old. I'm something of an expert on the subject. Her change will be upon her before long. I'll spare you the details of what will happen then. You men may have a stomach for bloodshed and slaughter, but this is another matter entirely.

author: tywin lannister
content: The years punish us as well, I promise you that. My stomach remains quite strong, however. The only thing that might turn it are details of your grandson's nocturnal activities. Do you deny them?

author: olenna tyrell
content: Oh, not at all. A sword swallower through and through.

author: tywin lannister
content: And a boy with his affliction should be grateful for the opportunity to marry the most beautiful woman in the kingdoms and remove the stain from his name.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Did you grow up with boy cousins, Lord Tywin? Sons of your father's bannermen, squires, stable boys?

author: tywin lannister
content: Of course.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And you never-

author: tywin lannister
content: No.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Not once? Not in any way?

author: tywin lannister
content: Never.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I congratulate you upon your restraint. But it's a natural thing, two boys having a go at each other beneath the sheets.

author: tywin lannister
content: Perhaps Highgarden has a high tolerance for unnatural behavior.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I wouldn't say that. True, we don't tie ourselves in knots over a discreet bit of buggery, but brothers and sisters- where I come from, that stain would be very difficult to wash out.

author: tywin lannister
content: I will not breathe further life into a malicious lie by discussing it.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Lie or not, you must admit many people find it quite convincing. Convincing enough to put swords in their hands and send them off to kill Lannisters and Tyrells thanks to our new affiliation.

author: tywin lannister
content: I don't care what people believe. And neither do you.

author: olenna tyrell
content: As an authority on myself, I must disagree.

author: tywin lannister
content: Now, if the rumors about my children were true, then Joffrey is no king at all and House Tyrell is throwing its prized flower into the dirt.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And if Cersei is too old to give Loras children, we're throwing another prized flower into the dirt. It is a chance we simply cannot take.

author: tywin lannister
content: The uncertainty makes you uncomfortable. All right. I'll remove it for you.

author: tywin lannister
content: If you refuse to marry Loras to Cersei, I will name him to the Kingsguard. I'm sure you're familiar with the Kingsguard vows. He will never marry. He will never have children.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Oh

author: tywin lannister
content: The Tyrell name will fade. And Highgarden will go to the children of Joffrey and Margaery.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You would have your grandson protected by someone who disgusts you?

author: tywin lannister
content: I would have my grandson protected by a skilled warrior who takes his vows seriously. So, shall I draw up the order? Or do you consent to this marriage?

author: olenna tyrell
content: It's a rare enough thing- a man who lives up to his reputation.

author: orell
content: No!

author: orell
content: We've gotta cut them loose!

author: tormund
content: No!

author: jon snow
content: Take my hand!

author: sansa stark
content: That's a wonderful pin.

author: loras
content: Oh, it's more of a brooch, really. Though I suppose a brooch is a sort of pin, so

author: sansa stark
content: I'm very happy about

author: loras
content: Uh, yes. I-I am as well.

author: sansa stark
content: I feel like I'm in a dream.

author: loras
content: Yes, me, too. Definitely. I've dreamed of a large wedding since I was quite young. The guests, the food, the tournaments. And the bride, of course. The most beautiful bride in the world in a beautiful gown of gold and green brocade with fringed sleeves. Have you ever been to Highgarden, my lady?

author: sansa stark
content: No. I had never left Winterfell before I came to King's Landing. But it sounds wonderful. I can't wait to see it. And to leave this place.

author: loras
content: It's terrible, isn't it? The most terrible place there is.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't suppose there's anything we can do about this.

author: cersei lannister
content: We can have them both killed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's hard to say which of the four of us is getting the worst of this arrangement. Probably Sansa. Though Loras will certainly come to know a deep and singular misery.

author: cersei lannister
content: Father doesn't discriminate. We're all being shipped off to hell together.

author: tyrion lannister
content: On a boat you built.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Tyrells were plotting to undermine our family. I did what I did to protect our family.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm your family. A member of your family who has actively contributed to that family's survival. Whether or not you or Father or anyone else wants to admit it.

author: cersei lannister
content: I do admit it. If it weren't for your trick with the wildfire, Stannis would have sacked the city before Father got here. Our heads would still be rotting on the city gate.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Trying to have me killed is an odd way of saying thank you. There are two people in King's Landing who can give an order to a Kingsguard. Did you or did you not order Ser Mandon to kill me during the Battle of the Blackwater?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The impulse I understand. He hates me because I'm the only one who tells him what he really is. So, fair enough. He wants me dead. But his stupidity? He could have had me poisoned and no one would have known. But the king orders a Kingsguard to murder the Hand of the King in full view of his own army. The boy's an idiot.

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you want me to say?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I want you to tell me if my life is still in danger.

author: cersei lannister
content: Probably. But not from Joffrey. He won't do anything now Father's here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Seven kingdoms united in fear of Tywin Lannister.

author: cersei lannister
content: Not the Tyrells. Soon they won't need to be afraid of him. Joffrey will belong to Margaery, the little doe-eyed whore. And so will his children and their children. History will be taken from our hands.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You may escape, at least. Once Jaime gets back, Ser Loras may come down with a terrible case of sword through bowels.

author: cersei lannister
content: When Jaime gets back, yes. But when do we think that's going to be? He's out there somewhere.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Jaime or not, I'm truly fucked.

author: cersei lannister
content: Who's going to tell her?

author: sansa stark
content: Do you think people will like it?

author: shae
content: I don't think they will even notice it.

author: sansa stark
content: You're right. It's not my wedding. Anyway, from what I can tell, the dressmakers in Highgarden will be far superior to the ones in King's Landing. They'd never make me anything as dull as this for my wedding. Loras likes green and gold brocade.

author: shae
content: I'm sure he does.

author: sansa stark
content: Will they let me invite my family?

author: shae
content: They haven't asked my opinion.

author: sansa stark
content: But do you think they will?

author: shae
content: No.

author: maid
content: Lady Sansa, Lord Tyrion to see you. Should I-

author: tyrion lannister
content: I beg your pardon, my lady.

author: sansa stark
content: Good afternoon, Lord Tyrion. I was just trying on a gown for King Joffrey's wedding.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, it should be quite a wedding. I need to speak with you, Lady Sansa.

author: sansa stark
content: Of course.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Alone, if I may.

author: shae
content: Why do you need to speak to her alone?

author: sansa stark
content: Shae. Please excuse her, Lord Tyrion. She's not from here. But I trust her, even though she tells me not to.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sometimes we think we want to hear something and it's only afterwards when it's too late that we realize we wished we'd heard it under entirely different circumstances.

author: sansa stark
content: It's all right, really.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How to begin? It's- this- this- this is awkward.

author: varys
content: A thousand blades taken from the hands of Aegon's fallen enemies, forged in the fiery breath of Balerion the Dread.

author: petyr baelish
content: There aren't. There aren't even two hundred. I've counted.

author: varys
content: Ha, I'm sure you have. Ugly old thing. Yet it has a certain appeal. The Lysa Arryn of chairs. Shame you had to settle for your second choice.

author: petyr baelish
content: Early days, my friend. It is flattering, really, you feeling such dread at the prospect of me getting what I want.

author: varys
content: Thwarting you has never been my primary ambition, I promise you. Although who doesn't like to see their friends fail now and then?

author: petyr baelish
content: You're so right. For instance, when I thwarted your plan to give Sansa Stark to the Tyrells. If I'm going to be honest, I did feel an unmistakable sense of enjoyment there. But your confidant, the one who fed you information about my plans, the one you swore to protect, you didn't bring her any enjoyment. And she didn't bring me any enjoyment. She was a bad investment on my part. Luckily, I have a friend who wanted to try something new. Something daring. And he was so grateful to me for providing this fresh experience.

author: varys
content: I did what I did for the good of the realm.

author: petyr baelish
content: The realm? Do you know what the realm is? It's the thousand blades of Aegon's enemies. A story we agree to tell each other over and over till we forget that it's a lie.

author: varys
content: But what do we have left once we abandon the lie? Chaos. A gaping pit waiting to swallow us all.

author: petyr baelish
content: Chaos isn't a pit. Chaos is a ladder.

author: petyr baelish
content: Many who try to climb it fail and never get to try again. The fall breaks them.

author: petyr baelish
content: And some are given a chance to climb, but they refuse. They cling to the realm or the gods or love. Illusions. Only the ladder is real. The climb is all there is.

author: ygritte
content: How far are we?

author: jon snow
content: About a week, I think.

author: ygritte
content: You think? You don't know?

author: jon snow
content: When we went to Castle Black, we took the Kingsroad.

author: ygritte
content: You and your roads. Is that how you lot do your fighting? You march down the road banging drums and waving banners?

author: jon snow
content: Most of the time, yes.

author: ygritte
content: How do the men holding the banners fight?

author: jon snow
content: They don't, really. It's a great honor to carry your house sigil.

author: ygritte
content: And the drummers- is that a great honor, too?

author: jon snow
content: Usually it's the young boys banging the drums.

author: ygritte
content: So what good are they?

author: jon snow
content: They help the men march.

author: ygritte
content: How?

author: jon snow
content: Well, it's- it's the rhythm.

author: ygritte
content: Oh, you mean right foot, left foot, right foot, left foot, right foot? You need help remembering that? When Mance gives the signal and we hit Castle Black, we won't be banging on drums to let them know we're coming.

author: jon snow
content: No. No, you're just gonna light the biggest fire the North has ever seen to let them know you're coming.

author: ygritte
content: You know nothing, Jon Snow.

author: orell
content: She's right, you don't.

author: jon snow
content: I know you cut me loose on the Wall.

author: orell
content: Cut her loose, too. Do you see her sulking about it? That's because she understands the way things are.

author: jon snow
content: And are you gonna share it with me? The deep wisdom you found inside the head of a bird?

author: orell
content: People work together when it suits them. They're loyal when it suits them. They love each other when it suits them. And they kill each other when it suits them. She knows that, you don't. Which is why you'll never hold onto her.

author: brynden
content: That rain will cost us another day.

author: robb stark
content: Frey will wait. He knows we're coming.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord Walder is prickly by nature.

author: brynden
content: Prickly? That what you call it? Might be the least pleasant man I've ever met.

author: catelyn stark
content: Yes, and that is why-

author: brynden
content: I've seen wet shits I liked better than Walder Frey. Apologies, Your Grace. Spent too many years around lancers and pikemen.

author: talisa
content: I've spent the last two years nursing wounded men, watching them bleed and die. I'm not afraid of wet shits.

author: catelyn stark
content: Lord Frey will take this delay as a slight.

author: edmure
content: He can take it as he likes. He's getting the wedding he wanted.

author: catelyn stark
content: He's getting a wedding. It was a king he wanted.

author: robb stark
content: Edmure is the best match a Frey has had in the history of their house. We should all get some sleep.

author: robb stark
content: If you don't put some clothes on, I can't promise I won't attack you again.

author: talisa
content: Attack. Attack.

author: robb stark
content: Who are you writing?

author: talisa
content: My mother.

author: robb stark
content: Is that Valyrian?

author: talisa
content: Gaaa.

author: robb stark
content: Gaaa? Say hello for me.

author: talisa
content: Rytsas.

author: robb stark
content: Ritsas.

author: talisa
content: That was close enough.

author: robb stark
content: Does she know her daughter's a queen?

author: talisa
content: Not yet.

author: robb stark
content: That will be a surprise, I expect.

author: talisa
content: Many surprises for her.

author: robb stark
content: How am I supposed to sit here planning a war when you're over there looking like that?

author: talisa
content: Will you come with me one day to Volantis? When all this is over?

author: robb stark
content: I will.

author: talisa
content: I promise. I know she'd love to meet you. And her grandchild.

author: robb stark
content: What, now? Are you certain?

author: talisa
content: Are you angry with me?

author: robb stark
content: Angry? You're my queen.

author: talisa
content: And I have your little prince or princess inside me.

author: robb stark
content: Maybe one of each.

author: talisa
content: Don't get greedy.

author: talisa
content: Can you leave the war for one night?

author: robb stark
content: I love you. Do you hear me? I love you.

author: tormund
content: Most men fuck like dogs.

author: tormund
content: No grace, no skill. A few dozen thrusts and done. You need to be patient. Give her time. Your cock shouldn't go near her till she's slick as a baby seal. And then you go inside, but slowly. Don't jam it in like you're spearing a pig. Come on! Hey, come on.

author: orell
content: You think he loves you, is that it? What did he tell you? He's gonna make you his lady and live with you in some castle?

author: ygritte
content: No, he didn't tell me anything. He barely talks.

author: orell
content: I've seen you two whispering in the night, giggling like a pair of girls.

author: ygritte
content: What, you're jealous?

author: orell
content: Of course I'm jealous. You should be with one of your own.

author: ygritte
content: And you're one of my own? I've never heard a kind word from your mouth.

author: orell
content: You would if you were mine. I'd tell you that you're beautiful and fierce and wild. I'd be good to you. You love him?

author: orell
content: Cause he's pretty? Is that it? You like his pretty hair and his pretty eyes? You think pretty is gonna make you happy?

author: ygritte
content: Don't touch me.

author: orell
content: You won't love him so much when you find out what he really is.

author: sansa stark
content: Growing up at Winterfell, all I ever wanted was to escape, to come here to the capital. See the southern knights and their painted armor and King's Landing after dark- all the candles burning in all those windows. I'm stupid. A stupid little girl with stupid dreams who never learns.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Come on. Come walk with me.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I remember the first time I saw you in the throne room. I'd never seen anyone who looked so unhappy. I want very much for you to be happy, Sansa, and so does my grandmother.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You would have been happy at Highgarden. But women in our position must make the best of our circumstances.

author: sansa stark
content: How do I make the best of my circumstances? I have to marry him.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Has Lord Tyrion mistreated you?

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Has he been kind to you?

author: sansa stark
content: He's tried.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You don't want him, though.

author: sansa stark
content: He's a Lannister.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Far from the worst Lannister, wouldn't you say?

author: sansa stark
content: I'm sorry. Here I am complaining to you.

author: margaery tyrell
content: My son will be king Sons learn from their mothers. I plan to teach mine a great deal. And your son, if I'm not mistaken, your son might be the Lord of Casterly Rock and the North someday. What?

author: sansa stark
content: My son with him. I'll have to- we'll have to-

author: margaery tyrell
content: If it's the pain you're worried about-

author: sansa stark
content: I'm not afraid of the pain. Not after what Joffrey's done to me.

author: margaery tyrell
content: What is it, then? He's rather good-looking even with the scar. Especially with the scar.

author: sansa stark
content: He's a dwarf. And Loras- Loras.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Some women like tall men. Some like short men. Some like hairy men. Some like bald men. Gentle men, rough men, ugly men, pretty men, pretty girls. Most women don't know what they like until they've tried it. And, sadly, so many of us get to try so little before we're old and gray. Tyrion may surprise you. From what I've heard, he's quite experienced.

author: sansa stark
content: And that's a good thing?

author: margaery tyrell
content: It can be. We're very complicated, you know. Pleasing us takes practice.

author: sansa stark
content: How do you know all this? Did your mother teach you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: Yes, sweet girl. My mother taught me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She's a child.

author: bronn
content: She's a foot taller than you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A tall child.

author: bronn
content: What's the youngest you've ever had?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not that young.

author: bronn
content: How much older?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Older.

author: bronn
content: You're a lord, she's a lady. And a beauty at that. I don't see the problem.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shae isn't going to like it.

author: bronn
content: Shae is a whore. Are you gonna marry her? Eh? How did marrying a whore work out for you the first time?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I should never have told you about that.

author: bronn
content: You want Shae, keep her. Wed one and bed the other. All you have to do is get a son in the Stark girl. He'll be Lord of Winterfell one day. You can rule the North in his name. You'll have two women and a whole kingdom of your own.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Two women to despise me and a whole kingdom to join them.

author: bronn
content: You waste time trying to get people to love you, you'll end up the most popular dead man in town. You want to fuck that Stark girl. You just don't want to admit it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't pay you to put evil notions in my head. The ones already there don't need company.

author: bronn
content: You pay me to kill people who bother you. Evil notions come free.

author: tywin lannister
content: Your Grace.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Grandfather.

author: tywin lannister
content: You wanted to speak to me?
