author: joffrey lannister
content: Yes. I'd like a report on the meetings of my small council.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're welcome to attend the meetings of your small council, Your Grace. Any or all of them.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I've been very busy. Many important matters require a king's attention.

author: tywin lannister
content: Of course.

author: joffrey lannister
content: You've been holding the council meetings in the Tower of the Hand instead of the small council chamber.

author: tywin lannister
content: I have, yes.

author: joffrey lannister
content: May I ask why?

author: tywin lannister
content: The Tower of the Hand is where I work. To walk from there to here would take time, time I could otherwise spend productively.

author: joffrey lannister
content: So if I wanted to attend a council meeting, I would now have to climb all the stairs in the Tower of the Hand?

author: tywin lannister
content: We could arrange to have you carried.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Tell me about the Targaryen girl in the east and her dragons.

author: tywin lannister
content: Where did you hear about this?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Is it true?

author: tywin lannister
content: Apparently so.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Don't you think we ought to do something about it?

author: tywin lannister
content: When I was Hand of the King under your father's predecessor, the skulls of all the Targaryen dragons were kept in this room. The skull of the last of them was right here. It was the size of an apple.

author: joffrey lannister
content: And the biggest was the size of a carriage.

author: tywin lannister
content: Yes, and the creature to whom it belonged died 300 years ago. Curiosities on the far side of the world are no threat to us.

author: joffrey lannister
content: But how do we know these dragons are just curiosities and not the beasts that brought the whole world to heel?

author: tywin lannister
content: Because we have been told as much by the many experts who serve the realm by counseling the king on matters about which he knows nothing.

author: joffrey lannister
content: But I haven't been counseled.

author: tywin lannister
content: You are being counseled at this very moment.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I should be consulted about such things.

author: tywin lannister
content: From now on, I will see to it that you are appropriately consulted on important matters whenever necessary. Your Grace.

author: jorah mormont
content: Yunkai. The Yellow City.

author: barristan
content: The Yunkish train bed slaves, not soldiers. We can defeat them.

author: jorah mormont
content: On the field, with ease. But they won't meet us on the field. They have provisions, patience, and strong walls. If they're wise, they'll hide behind those walls and chip away at us, man by man.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't want half my army killed before I've crossed the Narrow Sea.

author: jorah mormont
content: We don't need Yunkai, khaleesi. Taking this city will not bring you any closer to Westeros or the Iron Throne.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many slaves are there in Yunkai?

author: jorah mormont
content: Two hundred thousand if not more.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Then we have Two hundred thousand reasons to take the city.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Send a man to the city gates. Tell the slavers I will receive them here, and accept their surrender. Otherwise, Yunkai will suffer the same fate as Astapor.

author: missandei
content: Now comes the noble Razdal mo Eraz of that ancient and honorable house, master of men and speaker to savages, to offer terms of peace.

author: missandei
content: Noble lord, you are in the presence of Daenerys Stormborn of House Targaryen, Queen of the Andals and the First Men, Khaleesi of the Great Grass Sea, Breaker of Chains, and Mother of Dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You may approach. Sit.

author: missandei
content: Will the noble lord take refreshment?

author: radzal mo eraz
content: Ancient and glorious is Yunkai. Our empire was old before dragons stirred in old Valyria. Many an army has broken against our walls. You shall find no easy conquest here, khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Good. My Unsullied need practice. I was told to blood them early.

author: radzal mo eraz
content: If blood is your desire, blood shall flow. But why? 'Tis true you have committed savageries in Astapor. But the Yunkai are a forgiving and generous people.

author: radzal mo eraz
content: The wise masters of Yunkai have sent a gift for the silver queen.

author: radzal mo eraz
content: There is far more than this awaiting you on the deck of your ship.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My ship?

author: radzal mo eraz
content: Yes, khaleesi. As I said, we are a generous people. You shall have as many ships as you require.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what do you ask in return?

author: radzal mo eraz
content: All we ask is that you make use of these ships. Sail them back to Westeros where you belong and leave us to conduct our affairs in peace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I have a gift for you as well. Your life.

author: radzal mo eraz
content: My life?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And the lives of your wise masters. But I also want something in return. You will release every slave in Yunkai. Every man, woman, and child shall be given as much food, clothing, and property as they can carry as payment for their years of servitude. Reject this gift, and I shall show you no mercy.

author: radzal mo eraz

content: I'm not tired!

author: cersei lannister
content: Come.

author: tywin lannister
content: Not you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You just sent the most powerful man in Westeros to bed without his supper.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're a fool if you believe he's the most powerful man in Westeros.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A treasonous statement. Joffrey is king.

author: tywin lannister
content: You really think a crown gives you power?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No. I think armies give you power.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mm-hmm.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Robb Stark had one, never lost a battle, and you defeated him all the same.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, I know. Walder Frey gets all the credit. Or the blame, I suppose, depending on your allegiance. Walder Frey is many things, but a brave man? No. He never would have risked such an action if he didn't have certain assurances.

author: tywin lannister
content: Which he got from me. Do you disapprove?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm all for cheating. This is war.

author: tywin lannister
content: But to slaughter them at a wedding. Explain to me why it is more noble to kill ten thousand men in battle than a dozen at dinner.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So that's why you did it? To save lives?

author: tywin lannister
content: To end the war. To protect the family. Do you want to write a song for the dead Starks? Go ahead, write one. I'm in this world a little while longer to defend the Lannisters, to defend my blood.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Northerners will never forget.

author: tywin lannister
content: Good. Let them remember what happens when they march on the south. All the Stark men are dead. Winterfell is a ruin. Roose Bolton will be named Warden of the North until your son by Sansa comes of age.

author: tywin lannister
content: I believe you still have some work to do on that score.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you think she'll open her legs for me after I tell her how we murdered her mother and brother?

author: tywin lannister
content: One way or another, you will get that girl pregnant.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I will not rape her.

author: tywin lannister
content: Shall I explain to you in one easy lesson how the world works?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Use small words. I'm not as bright as you.

author: tywin lannister
content: The house that puts family first will always defeat the house that puts the whims and wishes of its sons and daughters first. A good man does everything in his power to better his family's position regardless of his own selfish desires.

author: tywin lannister
content: Does that amuse you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, it's a very good lesson. Only it's easy for you to preach utter devotion to family when you're making all the decisions.

author: tywin lannister
content: Easy for me, is it?

author: tyrion lannister
content: When have you ever done something that wasn't in your interest but solely for the benefit of the family?

author: tywin lannister
content: The day that you were born. I wanted to carry you into the sea and let the waves wash you away. Instead, I let you live. And I brought you as my son. Because you're a Lannister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sansa.

author: meera

author: bran stark
content: You ever heard about the Rat Cook?

content: No. Who's he?

author: bran stark
content: Just a cook in the Night's Watch. He was angry at the king for something, I don't remember. When the king was visiting the Nightfort, the cook killed the king's son, cooked him into a big pie with onions, carrots, mushrooms and bacon. That night he served the pie to the king. He liked the taste of his son so much, he asked for a second slice. The gods turned the cook into a giant white rat who could only eat his own young. He's been roaming the Nightfort ever since, devouring his own babies. But no matter what he does, he's always hungry.

author: meera
content: If the gods turned every killer into a giant white rat-

author: bran stark
content: It wasn't for murder the gods cursed the Rat Cook or for serving the king's son in a pie. He killed a guest beneath his roof. That's something the gods can't forgive.

author: walder frey
content: The late Walder Frey,' old Hoster called me because I didn't get my men to the Trident in time for battle. He thought he was witty. Look at us now, Tully. You're dead, your daughter Catelyn's dead, your grandson's dead, your son spent his wedding night in a dungeon, and I'm Lord of Riverrun.

content: You'll be needing a new young girl.

author: ramsay bolton

author: balon

author: balon
content: Theon disobeyed my orders.

author: balon

author: davos
content: I lived below the Street of Flour.

author: davos

author: gendry baratheon
content: Gin Alley.

author: davos
content: The Street of Steel, with your armor and your knights? Pfft. You lived in the fancy part of town. And here we are now. Two boys from Flea Bottom in the castle of a king.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Yeah, we've come a long way. We're all the same, really. She went to great pains to point that out to me.

author: davos

author: davos
content: Oh, that's a long story.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Better not, then. I'm a bit busy.

author: davos
content: Many years ago I helped King Stannis out of a difficult situation. He rewarded me with a lordship. And this.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You see? Highborns.

author: davos
content: I didn't want to be a lord. I nearly didn't accept.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Why did you?

author: davos

author: gendry baratheon
content: Does he?

author: davos
content: He's dead.

author: gendry baratheon
content: How'd he die?

author: davos

author: varys

author: shae
content: And now I'm his wife's servant. I brush her hair and clip her nails and empty her chamber pot.

author: varys
content: She is a sweet young thing. None of this is her fault.

author: shae
content: I love that girl. I would kill for her. Do you think that makes it easier for me?

author: varys
content: No, I expect not.

author: shae
content: She's young and she's beautiful and highborn.

author: varys
content: We break bread with them, but that doesn't make us family. We've learned their language, but we'll never be their countrymen. If you let yourself believe that a foreign girl with no name could spend her life with the son of Tywin Lannister-

author: shae
content: I have a name.

author: varys

author: varys
content: Diamonds. I'd tell you to beware carrying so much wealth, but you know how to protect yourself. Get on one of those ships. Sail to Pentos or Lys or Myr. You can buy a house with these diamonds, a very large house. Hire servants. Start a new life, a good life, far from here. The mysterious foreign beauty. You'll have suitors lining up.

author: varys

And you- you are a complication. I know you love him. And I know it's true love not bought by gold and silver. I'm not asking you to leave him for money. I'm asking you to leave because your presence in the capital endangers him. This will never be your home, my lady. Find a true home somewhere far from here while there's still time.

author: shae
content: Lord Varys.

content: There's nothing worse than a late-blooming philosopher.

content: Will you be facing your marriage to Ser Loras with the same philosophical spirit?

content: I seem to remember saying something similar about my own marriage.

content: You're not me. You want to make things better for Sansa? Give her a child.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So you can tell Father it was you who finally talked me into it?

author: tyrion lannister

content: Even Joffrey. He was all I had once. Before Myrcella was born. I used to spend hours looking at him. His wisps of hair. His tiny little hands and feet. He was such a jolly little fellow. You always hear the terrible ones were terrible babies. 'We should have known. Even then we should have known.' It's nonsense. Whenever he was with me, he was happy. And no one can take that away from me, not even Joffrey- how it feels to have someone. Someone of your own.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How long does it go on?

author: cersei lannister
content: Until we've dealt with all our enemies.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Every time we deal with an enemy, we create two more.

author: cersei lannister

author: frey soldier
content: Aye, not for long.

content: That's right. Black Walder shut her up right quick. None of the Starks had much to say about the end of that meal.

author: gendry baratheon
content: What are you doing?

author: davos
content: You're leaving.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Is this some kind of trick?

author: davos
content: Yes, but not on you.

author: davos
content: Aim for that star. Don't stop. There's bread and water. Go slow with it. If you finish it off, no matter how thirsty you get, don't drink seawater.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I know not to drink seawater.

author: davos
content: Row for a full day and night and you'll reach Rook's Rest. You'll want to stop there. Don't. She'll find you.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Where should I go?

author: davos
content: You must keep the coast on your left side until you reach King's Landing.

author: gendry baratheon
content: The gold cloaks are looking for me.

author: davos
content: They were looking for me for twenty years. Do they know your face?

author: gendry baratheon
content: No.

author: davos
content: I'd worry more about the Red Woman.

author: davos
content: The other way.

author: davos
content: You ever been in a boat before?

author: gendry baratheon
content: You know how to swim?

author: davos
content: Don't fall out. Go on.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Why are you doing this?

author: davos
content: Because it's right. And because I'm a slow learner.

author: davos
content: When you get to Flea Bottom, have a bowl of brown for me.

author: guard
content: Horse approaching! Halt! Halt!

author: sam
content: Jon! Jon! Jon, it's us.

author: pyp
content: I don't think he can see us.

author: jon snow
content: Pyp? Sam?

author: sam
content: Hush, now. You're home. Carry him inside. Gently.

author: man
content: Out of the way. Step aside, country boy. People working here.

author: jaime lannister
content: Cersei.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You don't deny it?

author: davos
content: No. I let him go.

author: melisandre
content: Your mercy saved the boy's life. You feel good about that?

author: davos
content: Aye, I do.

author: melisandre
content: You saved one innocent. How many tens of thousands have you doomed?

author: davos
content: There has got to be another way.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What other way?! Tell us about this other way.

author: davos
content: I don't know, Your Grace. I can't see the future in the fire.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Very well, Ser Davos Seaworth. I, Stannis of the House Baratheon, First of My Name, Rightful King of the Andals and the First Men, sentence you to die.

author: davos
content: I understand. But since you haven't yet unnamed me Hand of the King, it is my duty to advise you against it. You're gonna need me.

author: melisandre
content: Take him away.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Why am I gonna need you?

author: melisandre
content: My king.

author: davos
content: It's from Maester Aemon of the Night's Watch. Their Lord Commander is dead. Took a ranging party north and never made it back. One lad did, though. What he saw beyond the Wall- it's coming for all of us.

author: stannis baratheon
content: When did you learn to read?

author: davos
content: Matthos taught me before he died so I could be of better service to you.

author: melisandre
content: This War of Five Kings means nothing. The true war lies to the north, my king. Death marches on the Wall. Only you can stop him.

author: davos
content: You can't stop him alone. You need someone to rebuild your army for you, someone to convince this lord and that lord to fight for you, to bring sellswords and pirates to your side.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I've made my decision.

author: melisandre
content: He's right. You need him. He has a part to play in the war to come.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You see, Ser Davos? You've been saved by that fire god you like to mock. You're in his army now.

author: barristan
content: They will come, Your Grace. When they're ready.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Perhaps they didn't want to be conquered.

author: jorah mormont
content: You didn't conquer them. You liberated them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: People learn to love their chains.

author: missandei
content: This is Daenerys Targaryen, the Stormborn, the Unburnt, the Queen of the Seven Kingdoms of Westeros, Mother of Dragons. It is to her you owe your freedom

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You do not owe me your freedom. I cannot give it to you. Your freedom is not mine to give. It belongs to you and you alone. If you want it back, you must take it for yourselves. Each and every one of you.

author: man
content: Mhysa!

author: daughter
content: Mhysa!

content: What does it mean?

content: It is old Ghiscari, khaleesi. It means 'mother'.

author: crowd
content: Mhysa! Mhysa! Mhysa.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's all right. These people won't hurt me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Fly.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Let me pass

author: crowd
content: Mhysa! Mhysa! Mhysa. Mhysa!

author: jaime lannister
content: Magnificent.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mm-hmm.

author: jaime lannister
content: Looks fresh-forged.

author: tywin lannister
content: It is.

author: jaime lannister
content: No one's made a Valyrian steel sword since the Doom of Valyria.

author: tywin lannister
content: There are three living smiths who know how to rework Valyrian steel. The finest of them was in Volantis. Came here to King's Landing at my invitation.

author: jaime lannister
content: Where did you get this much Valyrian steel?

author: tywin lannister
content: From someone who no longer had need of it.

author: jaime lannister
content: You've wanted one of these in the family for a long time.

author: tywin lannister
content: And now we have two.

author: jaime lannister
content: Two?

author: tywin lannister
content: The original weapon was absurdly large. Plenty of steel for two swords.

author: jaime lannister
content: Well, thank you. It's glorious.

author: tywin lannister
content: You'll have to train your left hand.

author: jaime lannister
content: Any decent swordsman knows how to use both hands.

author: tywin lannister
content: You'll never be as good.

author: jaime lannister
content: No. But as long as I'm better than everyone else, I suppose it doesn't matter.

author: tywin lannister
content: You can't serve in the Kingsguard with one hand.

author: jaime lannister
content: Where's that written? I can and I will. The Kingsguard oath is for life.

author: tywin lannister
content: The war is over. The king is safe. The king is never safe.

author: jaime lannister
content: How many people in this city alone would love to see his head on a pike?

author: tywin lannister
content: Other knights protected the king while you were a prisoner. They will continue to do so when you go home.

author: jaime lannister
content: Home?

author: tywin lannister
content: You'll return to Casterly Rock and rule in my stead.

author: jaime lannister
content: You are the Lord of Casterly Rock.

author: tywin lannister
content: I am the King's Hand. My place is here. I don't expect to see the Rock again before I die.

author: jaime lannister
content: You know what they call me? Kingslayer. Oathbreaker. Man without honor. Now you want me to break another sacred vow.

author: tywin lannister
content: You won't be breaking anything. There is a precedent to relieve a Kingsguard of his duties. The king will exercise that prerogative.

author: jaime lannister
content: No.

author: tywin lannister
content: No?

author: tywin lannister
content: I don't believe I asked you a question.

author: jaime lannister
content: There's my answer.

author: tywin lannister
content: If you think your bloody honor comes before...

author: jaime lannister
content: My bloody honor is beyond repair, but my answer is still no. I don't want Casterly Rock. I don't want a wife. I don't want children.

author: tywin lannister
content: What do you want?

author: jaime lannister
content: Supper would be nice.

author: tywin lannister
content: For 40 years I've tried to teach you. If you haven't learned by now, you never will. Go. If serving as a glorified bodyguard is the sum of your ambition, go serve.

author: jaime lannister
content: I suppose you want the sword back.

author: tywin lannister
content: Keep it.

author: tywin lannister
content: A one-handed man with no family needs all the help he can get.

author: bronn
content: How many Dornishmen does it take to fuck a goat?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Please don't.

author: bronn
content: Seems to me the smart place to meet travelers is in a tavern. That way, one party is late, the other party can drink some ale inside.

author: tyrion lannister
content: This is the Prince of Dorne we're waiting for, not one of your sellsword friends.

author: bronn
content: If he's so damned important, how come they sent you to meet him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's bad blood between the Martells of Dorne and the Lannisters of Casterly Rock. Has been for years.

author: bronn
content: And just in case the Martells of Dorne are looking to spill some Lannister blood, it may as well be yours, eh?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No need for cynicism. I happen to be an accomplished diplomat.

author: bronn
content: Oh.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah, here we are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Can you read the sigils?

author: bronn
content: Yellow balls?

author: podrick
content: Wild lemons on a purple field, House Dalt of Lemonwood. A vulture grasping a baby in it's talons, House Blackmont. A crowned skull, the Manwoodys of Kingsgrave.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Boy knows his Dornish Houses.

author: bronn
content: I need a sigil.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And House Martell, a red sun pierced by a spear?

author: podrick
content: I don't see it, my lord.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well met, my lords. His Grace King Joffrey welcomes you in his name. My lord father, the King's Hand, sends his greetings as well. I am Tyrion Lannister of Casterly Rock, Master of Coin. Forgive me. I don't see Prince Doran in your company.

author: dornish lord
content: The prince's health forces him to remain at Sunspear. He sends his brother Prince Oberyn to attend the royal wedding in his stead.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, the king will be delighted to enjoy the company of a warrior as renowned as Prince Oberyn at his wedding feast.

author: dornish lord
content: Will he?

author: tyrion lannister
content: And where is Prince Oberyn?

author: dornish lord
content: Arrived before dawn. Not a man for welcome parties, our prince.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Very well. My lords, these fine men from the City Watch will escort you to your quarters in the Red Keep.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You must be weary after such a long journey.

author: bronn
content: Some accomplished diplomacy that was. Now where?

author: tyrion lannister
content: We must find Prince Oberyn before he kills somebody or several somebodies.

author: bronn
content: How do you plan on finding a single Dornishman in a city this big?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're famous for fucking half of Westeros. You just arrived at the capital after two weeks of bad roads, where would you go?

author: bronn
content: I'd probably go to sleep, but I'm getting old.

author: oberyn martell
content: Look at this one. How lovely is she?

author: ellaria
content: Beautiful. But pale.

author: oberyn martell
content: They like them pale in the capital. Shows they don't work the fields.

author: oberyn martell
content: You like?

author: ellaria
content: Timid. Timid bores me.

author: oberyn martell
content: You're a bit of mischief, aren't you?

author: oberyn martell
content: I think she likes you. ELLARIA" She has good taste.

author: oberyn martell
content: You're not timid, are you?

author: ellaria
content: Not timid.

author: oberyn martell
content: Do you like women?

author: whore
content: When they look like her, my lord.

author: ellaria
content: This one will do nicely.

author: olyvar
content: Very good, my lady.

author: ellaria
content: Oh, I'm not a lady.

author: olyvar
content: A term of courtesy in this establishment.

author: ellaria
content: A lie anywhere. Why not use the right words? I'm a bastard. She is a whore. And you're what? A procurer.

author: olyvar
content: Any of the others?

author: oberyn martell
content: The two girls can leave.

author: oberyn martell
content: You stay.

author: olyvar
content: I'm afraid I'm not an offer, my lord.

author: oberyn martell
content: Everyone who works for Littlefinger is an offer. Take off your clothes. We'll be here a while.

author: olyvar
content: My lord.

author: oberyn martell
content: I am a prince, boy. Have you ever been with a prince?

author: olyvar
content: Can't say I have. I'm wildly expensive.

author: oberyn martell
content: Take off your clothes.

author: olyvar
content: Which way do you like it?

author: oberyn martell
content: My way .

content: And so he spoke and so he spoke That Lord of Castamere. And now the rains

author: ellaria
content: Oberyn.

author: morgan
content: Weep o'er his hall...

content: Oberyn, don't.

author: morgan
content: With no one there to hear Yes, not the rains weep o'er his hall And not a soul to hear.

content: You lost, friend?

author: oberyn martell
content: Forgive me for staring. I don't see many Lannisters where I'm from.

author: morgans friend
content: I don't see many Dornishmen in the capital.

author: oberyn martell
content: We don't like the smell.

author: ellaria
content: Come with me, lover.

author: morgan
content: Gods, look at this one.

author: olyvar
content: Sirs, if you follow me, I'll arrange for a private room.

author: morgan
content: Why are you wasting a woman like this on a Dornishman? Bring him a shaved goat and a bottle of olive oil.

author: oberyn martell
content: Do you know why all the world hates a Lannister?

author: oberyn martell
content: You think your gold and your lions and your gold lions make you better than everyone. May I tell you a secret? You're not a golden lion. You're just a pink little man who is far too slow on the draw.

author: oberyn martell
content: Longsword is a bad option in close quarters. When I pull my blade, your friend starts bleeding. Quite a lot, I'm afraid. So many veins in the wrist.

author: oberyn martell
content: He'll live if you get him help straightaway. So, decisions.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Prince Oberyn, forgive the intrusion. We heard there might be...

author: tyrion lannister
content: trouble.

author: oberyn martell
content: Apologies, my love.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm here to welcome you to the capital.

author: oberyn martell
content: Ellaria Sand, my paramour. The king's own Uncle Imp. Tyrion, son of Tywin Lannister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If there's anything I can do to make your stay...

author: oberyn martell
content: What are you? His hired killer?

author: bronn
content: It started that way, aye. Now I'm a knight.

author: oberyn martell
content: How did that come to pass?

author: bronn
content: Killed the right people, I suppose.

author: oberyn martell
content: We'll need a few more girls. Girls, yes?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, I partook. Now I'm married.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Prince Oberyn, if I may, a word in private?

author: oberyn martell
content: Seems I visited the Lannister brothel by mistake.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, they take all kinds.

author: oberyn martell
content: Even Dornishmen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The king is very grateful that you traveled all this way for his wedding.

author: oberyn martell
content: Let us speak truth here. Joffrey is insulted. I am only the second son after all.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, speaking as a fellow second son, I have grown rather used to being the family insult.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why did you come to King's Landing, Prince Oberyn?

author: oberyn martell
content: I was invited to the royal wedding.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I thought we were speaking truth.

author: oberyn martell
content: The last time I was in the capital was many years ago. Another wedding. My sister Elia and Rhaegar Targaryen, the Last Dragon. My sister loved him. She bore his children. Swaddled them, rocked them, fed them at her own breast. Elia wouldn't let the wet nurse touch them. And beautiful, noble Rhaegar Targaryen left her for another woman. That started a war and the war ended right here when your father's army took the city...

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wasn't actually present.

author: oberyn martell
content: And butchered those children. My nephew and niece. Carved them up and wrapped them in Lannister cloaks. And my sister, you know what they did to her?

author: oberyn martell
content: I'm asking you a question.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I've heard rumors.

author: oberyn martell
content: So have I. The one I keep hearing is that Gregor Clegane the Mountain raped Elia and split her in half with his great sword.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wasn't there. I don't know what happened.

author: oberyn martell
content: If the Mountain killed my sister, your father gave the order. Tell your father I'm here. And tell him the Lannisters aren't the only ones who pay their debts.

author: jorah mormont
content: They're dragons, Khaleesi. They can never be tamed. Not even by their mother.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Ser Barristan.

author: barristan
content: Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Where's Daario Naharis? Where's Grey Worm?

author: barristan
content: Gambling, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Gambling?

author: crowd
content: Mhysa. Mhysa. Mhysa...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How long have they been at it?

author: missandei
content: Since midnight, Your Grace.

author: daario
content: Ser Worm is stronger than he looks. But I can see his arms beginning to shake.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What's the prize to winning this stupid contest?

author: daario
content: The honor of riding by your side on the road to Meereen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That honor goes to Ser Jorah and Ser Barristan as neither of them kept me waiting this morning. You two will ride in the rear guard and protect the livestock.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The last man holding his sword can find a new queen to fight for.

author: daario
content: You like this girl? Must be frustrating.

author: grey worm
content: You are not a smart man, Daario Naharis.

author: daario
content: I'd rather have no brains and two balls.

author: shae
content: You need to eat something.

author: shae
content: Pigeon pie.

author: sansa stark
content: No, thank you.

author: shae
content: Lemon cakes?

author: shae
content: You love lemon cakes.

author: shae
content: Tell her she needs to eat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My lady, you do need to eat.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't need to eat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If I could have a moment alone with my wife.

author: shae
content: She needs to eat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can't let you starve.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I swore to protect you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My lady, I am your husband. Let me help you.

author: sansa stark
content: How can you help me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't know, but I can try.

author: sansa stark
content: I lie awake all night staring at the canopy thinking about how they died.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I could get you essence of nightshade to help you sleep.

author: sansa stark
content: Do you know what they did to my brother? How they sewed his direwolf's head onto his body? And my mother. They say they cut her throat to the bone and threw her body in the river.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What happened to your family was a terrible crime. I didn't know your brother. He seemed like a good man, but I didn't know him. Your mother, on the other hand, I admired her. She wanted to have me executed, but I admired her. She was a strong woman. And she was fierce when it came to protecting her children. Sansa. Your mother would want you to carry on. You know it's true.

author: sansa stark
content: Will you pardon me, my lord? I'd like to visit the godswood.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course. Of course. Prayer can be helpful, I hear.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't pray anymore. It's the only place I can go where people don't talk to me.

author: shae
content: My lion.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What are you doing?

author: shae
content: What does it look like I'm doing? Come here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How many times have I told you? You can't visit me here.

author: shae
content: I know. I know. We have come to a dangerous place. Have you forgotten me? Do you know how long it's been?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course I haven't forgotten.

author: shae
content: I want you. Don't you want me?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Things are a bit tense right now.

author: shae
content: What things?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My nephew the king wants to murder me. My wife hates me because my father murdered her family. Oberyn Martell wants to murder everyone whose last name is Lannister.

author: shae
content: You need to relax.

author: shae
content: Don't you want to relax?

author: shae
content: What's wrong?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I told you. It's not a good time.

author: shae
content: It's never a good time. You have your child bride now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shae.

author: shae
content: Do you love her?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Love her? I barely know her. She's a child. She despises me.

author: shae
content: That's not an answer.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course I don't love her.

author: shae
content: You tried to ship me away.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ship you away?

author: shae
content: Give me diamonds and make me disappear.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What in the world are you talking about?

author: shae
content: If you want me to leave, just say it. Say it!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shh. I don't know what you're talking about.

author: shae
content: You want me to stay?

author: qyburn
content: A work of art, really. The craftsmanship is excellent.

author: jaime lannister
content: You like it so much, you're welcome to chop off your own hand and take it.

author: cersei lannister
content: Such an ingrate. I spent days with the goldsmith - getting the details just right.

author: jaime lannister
content: Days?

author: cersei lannister
content: Better part of an afternoon. There, how does that feel?

author: jaime lannister
content: Uh... a hook would be more practical.

author: cersei lannister
content: Elegant, I think.

author: cersei lannister
content: Thank you for your help with the other matter.

author: qyburn
content: The symptoms have abated?

author: cersei lannister
content: Gone completely. I am in your debt, Maester Qyburn.

author: qyburn
content: Not a maester, Your Grace, but happy to help whenever I can.

author: jaime lannister
content: Odd little man.

author: cersei lannister
content: I've grown rather fond of him. He's quite talented, you know?

author: jaime lannister
content: What symptoms?

author: cersei lannister
content: Symptoms that are not your concern.

author: jaime lannister
content: You let him touch you?

author: cersei lannister
content: You jealous?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm surprised. You never let Pycelle near you.

author: cersei lannister
content: You think I'd let that old lecher put his hands on me? He smells like a dead cat.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not sure I've ever smelled a dead cat.

author: cersei lannister
content: Well, they smell like Pycelle.

author: jaime lannister
content: You drink more than you used to.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes.

author: jaime lannister
content: Why?

author: cersei lannister
content: Let's see, you started a brawl in the streets with Ned Stark and disappeared from the capital. My husband died in a tragic hunting accident.

author: jaime lannister
content: It must have been traumatic for you.

author: cersei lannister
content: My only daughter was shipped off to Dorne. We suffered through a siege.

author: jaime lannister
content: A rather short siege.

author: cersei lannister
content: A rather short siege that I didn't expect to survive. And now I'm marrying my eldest son to a wicked little bitch from Highgarden while I'm supposed to marry her brother, a renowned pillow biter. So...

author: jaime lannister
content: Father disowned me today.

author: cersei lannister
content: He can't disown you. You're all he's got.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're forgetting Tyrion.

author: cersei lannister
content: You don't really plan on staying in the Kingsguard, do you?

author: jaime lannister
content: Staying in the Kingsguard means I live right here in the Red Keep with you.

author: cersei lannister
content: Not now.

author: jaime lannister
content: I want... Not now? When? I've been back for weeks.

author: jaime lannister
content: Something's changed.

author: cersei lannister
content: Everything's changed. You come back after all this time with no apologies and one hand and expect everything to be the same?

author: jaime lannister
content: What do you want me to apologize for?

author: cersei lannister
content: For leaving me.

author: jaime lannister
content: You think I wanted to be taken prisoner?

author: cersei lannister
content: Don't know what you wanted. You weren't here. You left me alone.

author: jaime lannister
content: Every day I was a prisoner, I plotted my escape. Every day. I murdered people so I could be here with you.

author: cersei lannister
content: You took too long.

author: jaime lannister
content: I... What are you saying?

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm saying you took too long.

author: cersei lannister
content: Come in.

author: jaime lannister
content: Go away.

author: marei
content: Forgive me, Your Grace. You told me to come at once if there was anything important.

author: tormund
content: You plan on killing all the crows yourself?

author: ygritte
content: Do you plan on sitting here scratching your balls till winter?

author: tormund
content: We wait for Mance's orders.

author: ygritte
content: You sent a man over the Wall at the full moon. If he's not back yet, he's not coming back.

author: tormund
content: And what is it you want? March on Castle Black with just this lot? Your pretty crow said 1,000 men are nesting there.

author: ygritte
content: Yeah, well, he's a liar.

author: tormund
content: He is? Shouldn't it be "he was"? You said you put three arrows in him.

author: ygritte
content: I did.

author: tormund
content: I've seen you slip a shaft through a rabbit's eye at 200 yards. If that boy's still walking, it's 'cause you let him go.

author: tormund
content: Thenns. I fucking hate Thenns.

author: tormund
content: Mance sent you?

author: tormund
content: How did you find us?

author: tormund
content: You came from the south, not the north.

author: warg
content: Took a detour. Got some supper from a village down that way.

author: styr
content: Why does the meat down here taste so much better than it does on our side of the Wall?

author: tormund
content: Help yourself.

author: styr
content: Maybe everything's just better fed down here.

author: styr
content: Fat and lazy. Easier for us, hmm?

author: styr
content: You didn't see us coming? Lost your warg? And that baby crow you had with you, lost him too?

author: tormund
content: I'll answer to Mance. I won't answer to you.

author: styr
content: She yours?

author: ygritte
content: I'm not anybody's.

author: styr
content: Too scrawny. Not like those crows at Castle Black.

author: styr
content: Think of them stuck in their larders stuffing their faces with ham and blood sausage and stew, getting nice and fat and marbled.

author: styr
content: I know we've had our differences, Tormund, but just one time before you die, you really ought to try crow.

author: officer
content: Draw. Loose.

author: jon snow
content: Last time I saw him, he was in the courtyard at Winterfell. "He said, " Next time I see you, you'll be all in black." I was jealous of Robb my whole life. The way my father looked at him, I wanted that. He was better than me at everything... fighting and hunting and riding and girls. Gods, the girls loved him. I wanted to hate him, but I never could.

author: sam
content: Sometimes I want to hate you.

author: sam
content: Well, you're better than me at everything. Except reading.

author: sam
content: They're... they're ready for you.

author: jon snow
content: He's wanted to hang me for a while. Now's his chance.

author: sam
content: No one's going to hang you. You've done nothing wrong.

author: jon snow
content: I've done plenty wrong.

author: alliser thorne
content: So you admit you murdered Qhorin Halfhand?

author: jon snow
content: I didn't murder him.

author: alliser thorne
content: No? You put your sword through a brother of the Night's Watch. What do you call that?

author: jon snow
content: He wanted me to kill him.

author: janos slynt
content: A bastard son of a traitor. What would you expect?

author: jon snow
content: The Halfhand believed our only chance to stop Mance was to get a man inside his army.

author: alliser thorne
content: Don't talk about the Halfhand as if you knew him. He was my brother.

author: jon snow
content: Then you'd know he'd do anything to defend the Wall. The free folk would have boiled him alive, but letting me kill him...

author: janos slynt
content: The free folk? Listen to him. He even talks like a wildling now.

author: jon snow
content: Aye, I talk like a wildling. I ate with the wildlings. I climbed the Wall with the wildlings. I... I laid with a wildling girl.

author: janos slynt
content: You admit to breaking your vows, then?

author: jon snow
content: I do.

author: janos slynt
content: The law is the law. The boy must die.

author: maester aemon
content: If we beheaded every ranger who lay with a girl, the Wall would be manned by headless men.

author: alliser thorne
content: There's a difference between sneaking off to the Mole's Town brothel and sleeping with the enemy.

author: jon snow
content: While we sit here debating which rules I broke, Mance Rayder marches on the Wall with an army of 100,000.

author: alliser thorne
content: Impossible. You can't get 50 wildlings together before they start killing each other.

author: jon snow
content: 100,000. He's united the Thenns, the Hornfoots, the ice-river clans. He has giants fighting for him.

author: janos slynt
content: Giants?

author: jon snow
content: Have you ever been beyond the Wall, ser?

author: janos slunt
content: I commanded the City Watch of King's Landing, boy.

author: jon snow
content: And now you're here. You must not have been very good at your job.

author: janos slynt
content: How dare you?!

author: jon snow
content: There's a band of wildlings south of the Wall already led by Tormund Giantsbane. I killed their warg and three others. They shot me full of arrows. Their orders are to attack Castle Black from the south when Mance hits it from the north. The signal for the attack will be a bonfire. Mance said it would be the greatest fire the North has ever seen. That's the truth. All the truth.

author: jon snow
content: Do you intend to execute me or am I free to go?

author: maester aemon
content: None of us are free. We are men of the Night's Watch. But we won't be taking your head today, Jon Snow. Go on.

author: alliser thorne
content: I am acting commander here, Maester Aemon.

author: maester aemon
content: Yes, you are.

author: alliser thorne
content: And I don't trust the bastard.

author: maester aemon
content: He told the truth.

author: alliser thorne
content: And you always know when a man's telling a lie? How did you acquire this magical power?

author: maester aemon
content: I grew up in King's Landing.

author: olenna tyrell
content: No. No. You're a queen, not an ox.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Your grandfather gave me a necklace just like this one for my 51st nameday.

author: margaery tyrell
content: The wedding is in a fortnight, Grandmother. You can't say no to everything.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Nonsense.

author: olenna tyrell
content: My little dears. Go and speak to the jewelers of King's Landing. Tell them who you are, tell them who sent you. The one who brings me the best necklace will get to keep the next best.

author: olenna tyrell
content: The Margaery Tyrell who walks into the sept a fortnight from now will inspire 1,000 songs. Now, how sad it will be if she's wearing rubbish like that.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Perhaps I should just let Joffrey choose it for me. End up with a string of dead sparrow heads around my neck.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You watch that. Even here, even with me.

author: olenna tyrell
content: My word.

author: brienne
content: My lady. My lady. Please pardon me for interrupting. My name is Brienne of Tarth.

author: olenna tyrell
content: We know who you are. We've heard all about you. But hearing is one thing. Aren't you just marvelous? Absolutely singular.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I hear you knocked my grandson into the dirt like the silly little boy he is.

author: brienne
content: My lady, I know this is a very busy time for you, but if I could just have a moment.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You dare not refuse.

author: margaery tyrell
content: A shadow?

author: brienne
content: A shadow with the face of Stannis Baratheon. I swear to you by all the gods it was Stannis. He plunged his sword through Renly's heart and disappeared. One day, my lady, I will avenge our king.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Joffrey is our king now.

author: brienne
content: I meant no offense.

author: margaery tyrell
content: And you've given none.

author: jaime lannister
content: All the Kingsguard will be on duty, of course. Ser Boros will be stationed here. Ser Preston will be stationed here beside the primary entertainment. Your Grace?

author: joffrey lannister
content: Yes, yes, one guard at the... the thing. Go on.

author: jaime lannister
content: Ser Meryn will guard Lady Margaery and Tommen.

author: meryn
content: I've always guarded the king himself, my lord. Ever since your absence.

author: jaime lannister
content: And I thank you for it, Ser Meryn. All very good. I don't expect any trouble.

author: meryn
content: The people love their king. They know who keeps them fed.

author: jaime lannister
content: Margaery Tyrell, I've heard.

author: joffrey lannister
content: By my leave. They know I saved the city. They know I won the war.

author: jaime lannister
content: The war's not won. Not while Stannis lives.

author: joffrey lannister
content: I broke Stannis on the Blackwater. Pity you weren't there to help, Uncle.

author: jaime lannister
content: My apologies, Your Grace. I was rather busy.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Busy getting captured.

author: jaime lannister
content: So this is the famous "Book of Brothers"? All the great deeds of all the great Kingsguard. Ser Arthur Dayne. The Sword of the Morning. Led the attack on the Kingswood Brotherhood. Defeated the Smiling Knight in single combat. Ser Duncan the Tall. Four pages for Ser Duncan. He must have been quite a man.

author: jaime lannister
content: So they say.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Ser Jaime Lannister.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Someone forgot to write down all your great deeds.

author: jaime lannister
content: There's still time.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Is there? For a 40-year-old knight with one hand? How can you protect me with that?

author: jaime lannister
content: I use my left hand now, Your Grace. Makes for more of a contest.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Have you ever been to Meereen?

author: missandei
content: Several times, Your Grace, with Master Kraznys.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And?

author: missandei
content: They say 1,000 slaves died building the Great Pyramid of Meereen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And now an army of former slaves is marching to her gates. You think the Great Masters are worried?

author: missandei
content: If they're smart, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You were told to ride at the back of the train.

author: daario
content: Yes, my queen. But I need to speak to you about something important. A matter of strategy.

author: missandei
content: Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: All right, what is this matter of strategy?

author: daario
content: A dusk rose.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Would you like to walk at the back of the train instead of riding?

author: daario
content: And this one's called lady's lace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Would you like to walk without shoes?

author: daario
content: You have to know a land to rule it. It's plants, it's rivers, it's roads, it's people. Dusk rose tea eases fever. Everyone in Meereen knows that. Especially the slaves who have to make the tea. If you want them to follow you, you have to become a part of their world. Strategy.

author: daario
content: Harpy's Gold. No tea from this one. Beautiful but poisonous.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You are a gambler, aren't you?

author: daario
content: Your Grace.

author: jorah mormont
content: There's one on every mile marker between here and Meereen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many miles are there between here and Meereen?

author: barristan
content: 163, Your Grace. I'll tell our men to ride ahead and bury them. You don't need to see this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will do no such thing. I will see each and every one of their faces. Remove her collar before you bury her.

author: brienne
content: There she is.

author: jaime lannister
content: Yes, there she is.

author: brienne
content: And? You made a promise.

author: jaime lannister
content: To return the Stark girls to their mother who is now dead.

author: brienne
content: To keep them safe.

author: jaime lannister
content: Well, Arya Stark hasn't been seen since her father was killed. Where do you think she is? My money's on dead. There's a certain safety in death, wouldn't you say? And Sansa Stark is now Sansa Lannister. Bit of a complication.

author: brienne
content: A complication does not release you from a vow.

author: jaime lannister
content: What do you want me to do? Kidnap my sister-in-law? And take her where? Where would she be safer than here?

author: brienne
content: Look me in the eye and tell me that you think she'll be safe in King's Landing.

author: jaime lannister
content: Are you sure we're not related? Ever since I've returned, every Lannister I've seen has been a miserable pain in my ass. Maybe you're a Lannister, too. You've got the hair for it if not the looks.

author: ser dontos
content: It's all right. It's all right. It's all right.

author: sansa stark
content: You're drunk.

author: ser dontos
content: Yes. I have good reason to be. Once I was a knight. Now I'm only a fool. Don't you know me?

author: sansa stark
content: Ser Dontos. The king's nameday celebration. I'm sorry. I should have remembered.

author: ser dontos
content: I can't accept your apology. I may be a fool, but I'm a living fool, thanks to you.

author: sansa stark
content: Anyone would have done the same.

author: ser dontos
content: But only you did. I can never repay you. You gave me my life. But this, this is worth more than my life.

author: ser dontos
content: It belonged to my mother and her mother before her. House Hollard was strong once. House on the rise. That's all that's left of those days, thanks to a few sad, fat drunks like me.

author: sansa stark
content: I can't take it. It's very, very kind of you, but I can't.

author: ser dontos
content: I don't have anything else left. That's all. Take it. Wear it. Let my name have one more moment in the sun before it disappears from the world.

author: sansa stark
content: I'll wear it with pride, Ser Dontos.

author: ser dontos
content: Yeah.

author: arya stark
content: When am I going to get a horse of my own?

author: sandor clegane
content: The little lady wants a pony.

author: arya stark
content: The little lady wants away from your stench.

author: sandor clegane
content: Horses aren't easy to come by. Even if they were, you think I'm gonna put you on your own horse? Watch the only thing of value I've got in the world ride away?

author: arya stark
content: Why don't you have any money? Didn't you steal anything from Joffrey before you left?

author: sandor clegane
content: No.

author: arya stark
content: You're not very smart, are you?

author: sandor clegane
content: I'm not a thief.

author: arya stark
content: You're fine with murdering little boys, but thieving is beneath you?

author: sandor clegane
content: A man's got to have a code.

author: arya stark
content: You think I'm gonna escape? Where would I go? I'd be dead by nightfall without you. My family's gone. I've got no one.

author: sandor clegane
content: You've got an aunt in the Vale. Your rich Aunt Lysa. After I sell you to her, maybe she'll have enough left over to buy you that pony you want so much.

author: arya stark
content: I'm hungry. You're hungry.

author: sandor clegane
content: Five horses, five men. More than I feel like killing on an empty stomach.

author: arya stark
content: I know him. The small one. His name is Polliver. He captured us and took us to Harrenhal.

author: arya stark
content: He killed Lommy.

author: sandor clegane
content: What the fuck's a Lommy?

author: arya stark
content: He was my friend. Polliver stole my sword and put it right through his neck. He's still got it.

author: sandor clegane
content: Got what?

author: arya stark
content: My sword Needle.

author: sandor clegane
content: Needle? Of course you named your sword.

author: arya stark
content: Lots of people name their swords.

author: sandor clegane
content: Lots of cunts.

author: sandor clegane
content: What are you... get back here.

author: arya stark
content: My brother gave me that sword.

author: sandor clegane
content: Get back here.

author: arya stark
content: He killed my friend.

author: sandor clegane
content: I don't care if he ate your friend. We're not going in there.

author: man
content: Come on, give it up.

author: man
content: Come here.

author: man
content: Let's have a feel there.

author: man
content: Leave it.

author: innkeeper
content: Please, she's a good girl.

author: polliver
content: Shut your mouth and pour us more ale and we may not take her with us when we're done with her.

author: polliver
content: I know you.

author: polliver
content: You're the Hound.

author: polliver
content: Pour our new friend some ale. What brings you so far north?

author: sandor clegane
content: I could ask the same of you. What are you doing up here?

author: polliver
content: Just keeping the king's peace.

author: sandor clegane
content: No need. The war's over.

author: polliver
content: So I've heard. Stannis defeated at the Blackwater. Robb Stark killed at the Twins. And where am I for all of it? Stuck with your brother. Meaning no offense.

author: sandor clegane
content: None taken.

author: polliver
content: He's good, the Mountain is. Best at what he does. But torture, torture, torture, torture. You spend enough time putting the hammer to people, you start to feel like a carpenter making chairs. Drains the fun right out of it. And what's life without a little fun?

author: polliver
content: But I don't need to tell you that, eh?

author: sandor clegane
content: She's all right. I've had better.

author: polliver
content: You know what? You should come with us. His kind, they've always got something hidden away somewhere. Gold, silver, more daughters. Always something if you know how to make them talk. And there's plenty of him between here and King's Landing. You could do well for yourself. We certainly have been.

author: sandor clegane
content: I'm not going to King's Landing.

author: polliver
content: Think about it. We could do whatever we like wherever we go. These are the king's colors. No one's standing in his way now. Which means no one's standing in ours.

author: sandor clegane
content: Fuck the king.

author: polliver
content: When I heard that Joffrey's dog had tucked tail and run from the Battle of the Blackwater, I didn't believe it. But here you are.

author: sandor clegane
content: Here I am. Bring me one of those chickens.

author: polliver
content: You got money to pay for it?

author: sandor clegane
content: You paid for it?

author: polliver
content: No. But we're the king's men. So, you got money?

author: sandor clegane
content: Not a penny.

author: sandor clegane
content: I'll still take that chicken.

author: polliver
content: Tell you what. We'll trade you. One of our little chickens for one of yours. Give us a go at your friend. Lowell there likes them a bit broken in.

author: sandor clegane
content: You're a talker. Listening to talkers makes me thirsty.

author: sandor clegane
content: Ah. And hungry. Think I'll take two chickens.

author: polliver
content: You don't seem to understand the situation.

author: sandor clegane
content: I understand that if any more words come pouring out of your cunt mouth, I'm gonna have to eat every fucking chicken in this room.

author: polliver
content: You lived your life for the king. You're gonna die for some chickens?

author: sandor clegane
content: Someone is.

author: arya stark
content: Something wrong with your leg, boy?

author: polliver
content: What? What do you mean?

author: arya stark
content: Can you walk? I've got to carry you?

author: polliver
content: Carry me?

author: arya stark
content: Fine little blade.

author: arya stark
content: Maybe I'll pick my teeth with it.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tansy! Tansy! Tansy!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tansy! Tansy!

author: ramsay bolton
content: There you are.

author: myranda
content: I can't see her, Ramsay.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tansy!

author: ramsay bolton
content: If you make it out of the woods, you win! Run, Tansy, run!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tansy.

author: myranda
content: Where is she?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tansy, Tansy, Tansy!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Good girls. Down, girls. Down. Well done. You, too.

author: myranda
content: I only wounded her.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You brought her down. That's what matters. A fine shot. Wasn't it, Reek?

author: theon greyjoy
content: A fine shot, master. My lady.

author: tansy
content: Please, my lord. It hurts.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Oh, sweet. Don't cry. It will be over soon.

author: myranda
content: She thinks she's pretty. Let me put one through her face.

author: ramsay bolton
content: We have to reward the hounds, love. They did all the hard work.

author: tansy
content: Why? I did whatever you asked.

author: ramsay bolton
content: But you made Myranda feel jealous.

author: myranda
content: Me jealous of her?

author: tansy
content: My lord, please.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You can see that your presence has become a bit of a problem.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Rip her! Rip her! Rip her!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Not so pretty now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your new hand, it's nicer than the old one. Wouldn't you agree, Pod?

author: podrick
content: Is it solid gold?

author: jaime lannister
content: Gilded steel.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're not eating. Why is no one eating? My wife wastes away and my brother starves himself.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not hungry.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You lost a hand, not a stomach. Try the boar. Cersei can't get enough of it since one killed Robert for her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A toast. To the proud Lannister children. The dwarf, the cripple, and the mother of madness.

author: jaime lannister
content: Oh!

author: podrick
content: I'll clean it up.

author: jaime lannister
content: No, I'll do it. Leave us.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's only wine.

author: jaime lannister
content: I can't fight anymore.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What about your left?

author: jaime lannister
content: I can hold a sword, but all my instincts are wrong. How can I protect the king when I can hardly wipe my own ass?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're the Lord Commander now. Command. Let others do the fighting. When was the last time Father used a sword?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not Father. I'm the Kingslayer. When people find out I can't slay a pigeon...

author: tyrion lannister
content: Train, then. Learn to fight with your other hand.

author: jaime lannister
content: With whom? You? Men talk. Soon as someone discovers I can't fight, he'll tell everyone.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You need a proper, discreet swordsman. As it happens, I have just the one.

author: jaime lannister
content: My brother tells me you can keep your mouth shut. Unusual talent for a sellsword.

author: bronn
content: He tells me you shit gold just like your father.

author: jaime lannister
content: Is this place safe?

author: bronn
content: There's this knight, Leygood, got thunderbolts on his shield.

author: jaime lannister
content: Uh-huh.

author: bronn
content: Right here is where I fuck his wife. She's a screamer, that one. If they don't hear her, they won't hear us.

author: bronn
content: I've never seen Valyrian steel before. She's a beauty. The problem is, if you fight with an edged blade, I'll have to.

author: bronn
content: And if I fight with an edged blade, I'll have no one left to pay me.

author: jaime lannister
content: I haven't used a sparring sword since I was nine.

author: jaime lannister
content: Ah! Bold warrior you are, attacking a man when his guardo s down.

author: bronn
content: Best time to attack a man.

author: bronn
content: Mind yourself. JAIME; If I still had my right hand...

author: bronn
content: Plan on growing it back?

author: jaime lannister
content: Come on, then.

author: man
content: Open the gates!

author: man
content: Riders coming in! Let's get these horses seen to!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Father. Welcome home.

author: roose
content: Walda, this is Ramsay Snow, my bastard.

author: ramsay bolton
content: A pleasure, Mother.

author: walda
content: Hello.

author: roose
content: See that the horses are fed, watered, and rubbed down. And take Lady Walda to her chambers.

author: woman
content: This way, my lady.

author: roose
content: Where is your prize?

author: ramsay bolton
content: With the hounds. I'll have a look at him.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I hear you took a hand from the Kingslayer.

author: locke
content: Word travels. How he screamed. You would have loved it.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Father.

author: roose
content: What did you do to him?

author: ramsay bolton
content: I trained him. He was a slow learner, but he learned.

author: roose
content: You flayed him.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Peeled a few bits. Removed a few others.

author: roose
content: This was Balon Greyjoy's son and heir.

author: ramsay bolton
content: We've been flaying our enemies for a thousand years. The flayed man is on our banners.

author: roose
content: My banners, not yours. You're not a Bolton. You're a Snow. Tywin Lannister has given me the North. But he won't lift a finger to help me take it. As long as the Ironborn hold Moat Cailin, our armies are trapped south of the Neck. Theon was a valuable hostage, not your plaything. I wanted to trade him for Moat Cailin.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I already asked. Lord Greyjoy refused. Savages have no-

author: roose
content: You sent terms to Balon Greyjoy without my consent?

author: ramsay bolton
content: You made me acting Lord of the Dreadfort. I acted.

author: roose
content: I had to smuggle myself into my own lands thanks to the Greyjoys. I needed Theon. I needed him whole.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Theon was our enemy. But Reek, Reek will never betray us.

author: roose
content: I placed far too much trust in you.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Reek, how could you let me stand before my father unshaven? It's disrespectful.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm sorry, my lord.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Give him the razor.

author: ramsay bolton
content: If I'm not a Bolton, Father, what does it matter?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Go on, Reek. A nice close shave.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Reek, tell Father where are Bran and Rickon Stark?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I don't know, my lord.

author: roose
content: You murdered them and displayed their corpses at Winterfell.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Reek, did you murder the Stark boys?

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, my lord. Just two farm boys.

author: ramsay bolton
content: And crisped them so no one would know.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes, my lord.

author: ramsay bolton
content: The Starks have always ruled the North. If Bran and Rickon are alive, the country will rally to their side now that Robb Stark is gone.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Oh, that's right, Reek. Robb Stark is dead. Sorry. I know he was like a brother to you. But my father put a knife through his heart. How do you feel about that?

author: roose
content: You ready for a hunt?

author: meryn trant
content: Always. Find those boys and I'll give you a thousand acres and a holdfast.

author: locke
content: Your pet rat have any thoughts on which way they went after Winterfell?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Jon Snow is at Castle Black.

author: locke
content: Who the fuck is Jon Snow?

author: roose
content: Their bastard brother. He could be sheltering them. He may know where they are.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Even if he doesn't, he's half Stark himself. Could be a threat.

author: roose
content: You want to prove yourself a Bolton? Gather whatever men you can and ride for Moat Cailin. Bring this creature of yours. Maybe he'll be of some use. Take the Moat for the family, for our family, and I'll reconsider your position.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Lord Varys. Breakfasting with the king?

author: varys
content: I'm afraid foreigners aren't welcome at such exclusive affairs.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, to be foreign.

author: varys
content: Ahem.

author: varys
content: Shae has been noticed. Sansa's maid saw you with her. She already told your sister. It's only a matter of time before your father hears.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So I'm guilty of being seen with my own wife's handmaiden. My father will ask you if there's anything more and you'll tell him some clever lie.

author: varys
content: No, I will not. How long do you imagine your father and sister would let me live if they suspected me of lying? I have no pet sellsword to protect me. No legendary brother to avenge me. Only little birds who whisper in my ear.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Forgive me if I don't weep for you.

author: varys
content: No one weeps for spiders or whores. I have friends across the sea who could help her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She won't leave. I've told her this is a dangerous place so many times, she no longer believes it.

author: varys
content: Your father has promised to hang the next whore he finds you with. Have you ever known your father to make an idle threat?

author: mace
content: From House Tyrell and the people of the Reach, Your Grace, it is my honor to present you with this wedding cup.

author: mace
content: May you and my daughter Margaery drink deep and live long.

author: joffrey lannister
content: A handsome goblet, my lord. Or shall I call you Father?

author: mace
content: I shall be honored, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: She's the whore I told you about. The dark-haired one.

author: tywin lannister
content: Have her brought to the Tower of the Hand before the wedding.

author: joffrey lannister
content: A book?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Lives of Four Kings." Grand Maester Kaeth's history of the reigns of Daeron the Young Dragon, Baelor the Blessed, Aegon the Unworthy, and Daeron the Good. A book every king should read.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Now that the war is won, we should all find time for wisdom. Thank you, Uncle.

author: tywin lannister
content: One of only two Valyrian steel swords in the capital, Your Grace, freshly forged in your honor.

author: pycelle
content: Careful, Your Grace. Nothing cuts like Valyrian steel.

author: joffrey lannister
content: So they say.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Such a great sword should have a name. What shall I call her?

author: man
content: Stormbringer.

author: man
content: Terminus.

author: man
content: Widow's Wail.

author: man
content: Wolfsbane.

author: joffrey lannister
content: Widow's Wail. I like that. Every time I use it, it'll be like cutting off Ned Stark's head all over again.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Don't.

author: shae
content: You want me on the desk? What's wrong, my lion?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Don't call me that.

author: shae
content: What should I call you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm afraid our friendship can't continue.

author: shae
content: Our friendship?

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's a ship waiting in the harbor bound for Pentos.

author: shae
content: What?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You'll have your own cabin, of course, and, across the Narrow Sea, a house, servants.

author: shae
content: What is this?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm a married man. My wife has suffered a great deal, as you well know. I don't want her to suffer anymore on my account. I need to uphold my vows.

author: shae
content: She doesn't want you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I need to do right by her.

author: shae
content: You don't want her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: By our children.

author: shae
content: What are you afraid of?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm not afraid.

author: shae
content: You are. You are afraid of your father and your sister. You're going to run from them all your life?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I need you to leave.

author: shae
content: I'm not afraid of them. I'm not going to run.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shae.

author: shae
content: We will fight them together. It's like you said, I am yours and you are mine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're a whore! Sansa is fit to bear my children and you are not. I can't be in love with a whore. I can't have children with a whore. How many men have you been with? Five hundred? Five thousand?

author: shae
content: How many whores have you been with?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I have enjoyed my time with all of them and I have enjoyed my time with you most of all. But now that time is over.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You'll have a comfortable life in Pentos. Bronn will escort you to your ship.

author: melisandre
content: Hear us now. Accept these tokens of our faith, my lord, and lead us from the darkness.

author: axell florent
content: Sire, I served you well.

author: melisandre
content: Lord of Light, show us the way...

author: axell florent
content: Selyse, you're my sister!

author: selyse
content: Yours are the stars that guide us.

author: axell florent
content: Tell him! Tell him!

author: melisandre
content: Lord of Light, protect us, for the night is dark and full of terrors.

author: selyse
content: Did you see? Their souls. It was their souls. Our lord took them. Did you see?

author: davos
content: Lord Florent was your brother by law.

author: stannis baratheon
content: He was an infidel.

author: davos
content: He worshipped the gods of his fathers and their fathers before him. They were the gods of your fathers, too.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I ordered him to tear down his idols. He disobeyed.

author: davos
content: How many ships did he bring to your 'cause? How many men?

author: stannis baratheon
content: A good deal more than you.

author: selyse
content: Did you see, Ser Davos? They're with our lord now. Their sins all burned away. Did you see?

author: davos
content: I'm sure they're more than grateful, my queen.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Meat's off.

author: selyse
content: Our larders are almost empty.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Serve fish, then. We're on an island.

author: selyse
content: You hate fish.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I hate a good many things, but I suffer them all the same.

author: selyse
content: When Storm's End was under siege and I was starving, Stannis boiled soup for me from books. The binding glue is made from horses. One morning, he shot two seagulls on the beach. I've never tasted anything as good as grilled seagull. Do you remember?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Of course I remember.

author: selyse
content: Have you ever known true hunger, my lady?

author: melisandre
content: It's all I knew when I was a child.

author: selyse
content: Until you found the Lord of Light?

author: melisandre
content: Until he found me.

author: selyse
content: I fear for our daughter's soul.

author: melisandre
content: Every mother should fear for her childo s soul.

author: selyse
content: She's a stubborn little beast.

author: stannis baratheon
content: She's a child.

author: selyse
content: You barely know her. You think she's sweet because she smiles when you visit. She's sullen and stubborn and sinful. Why else would the Lord of Light have seen fit to mark her face? She needs the rod.

author: stannis baratheon
content: She's my daughter. You will not strike her.

author: selyse
content: As you command. Perhaps the Lady Melisandre could speak with her.

author: shireen
content: Come in.

author: melisandre
content: Were you sleeping, Princess?

author: melisandre
content: Did you watch the ceremony on the beach?

author: shireen
content: I heard it.

author: melisandre
content: And it frightened you?

author: shireen
content: Ser Axell was my uncle. He was always kind to me.

author: melisandre
content: They're in a better place now, Princess. The fire cleansed them of the sins of the world.

author: shireen
content: But they screamed.

author: melisandre
content: Women scream when they give birth. Afterward they are filled with joy.

author: shireen
content: Afterward they aren't ash and bone.

author: melisandre
content: You have so many questions, don't you? So did I when I was a child. I was much like you. Only I wasn't a princess.

author: shireen
content: And you didn't have this.

author: melisandre
content: No. But I suffered in other ways, sweet girl, believe me. What do you know of the gods?

author: shireen
content: I read "The Seven-Pointed Star."

author: melisandre
content: Lies and fables. Septons speak of seven gods. There are but two... a god of light and love and joy and a god of darkness, evil, and fear. Eternally at war.

author: shireen
content: There are no seven heavens and no seven hells?

author: melisandre
content: There's only one hell, Princess. The one we live in now.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Why did you wake me?

author: meera
content: You've been gone for hours.

author: bran stark
content: I was hungry.

author: meera
content: We're all hungry.

author: bran stark
content: I was just eating.

author: jojen
content: Summer was eating. Your body can't live on the food your wolf consumes. Spending too much time in Summer's skin is dangerous. You're not a direwolf, Bran.

author: jojen
content: Must be glorious, though. To run, to leap, to hunt. To be whole. I know that's tempting, but if you're trapped in Summer for too long, you'll forget what it was to be human.

author: meera
content: You'd forget us, Bran. You'd forget your mother and father. You'd forget your brothers and sisters. You'd forget Winterfell. You'd forget you. And if we lose you, we lose everything.

author: bran stark
content: Hodor, take me to the tree.

author: threeeyed raven
content: Look for me... beneath the tree.

author: cersei lannister
content: He saw us.

author: threeeyed raven
content: North.

author: bran stark
content: I know where we have to go.

author: septon
content: Let it be known that Margaery of House Tyrell and Joffrey of the Houses Lannister and Baratheon are one heart, one flesh, one soul. Cursed be he who would seek to tear them asunder.

author: joffrey lannister
content: With this kiss, I pledge my love.

author: sansa stark
content: We have a new queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Better her than you.

author: tywin lannister
content: Bit much, wouldn't you say?

author: olenna tyrell
