author: lysa
content: Let's get married tonight.

author: petyr baelish
content: Ought we not... inform the Lords of the Vale about the ceremony?

author: lysa
content: There's only one Lord of the Vale. The others can all hang. Lurking and simpering on the stairs like buzzards the moment my husband died, trying to get their claws in me.

author: petyr baelish
content: I do think that we could wait until...

author: lysa
content: I'm done waiting, Petyr. We had our wedding night many years ago. Or don't you remember?

author: petyr baelish
content: Like it was yesterday.

author: lysa
content: What wife would do for you the things I've done for you? What wife would trust you the way I've trusted you? When you gave me those drops and told me to pour them into Jon's wine, my husbando s wine... when you told me to write a letter to Cat telling her it was the Lannisters...

author: petyr baelish
content: The deed is done. Faded into nothing. Only speaking of it can make it real.

author: petyr baelish
content: Tonight it is, then.

author: petyr baelish
content: Let me bathe and dress for the occasion. Once I'm presentable, I'll call on the septon immediately.

author: lysa
content: I'm warning you. I'm going to scream when my husband makes love to me. I'm going to scream so loud, they'll hear me clear across the Narrow Sea.

author: tywin lannister
content: When will the wedding take place in your mind?

author: cersei lannister
content: As soon as decency permits. After we've allowed Tommen the appropriate time to mourn his brother and Margaery to mourn her husband.

author: tywin lannister
content: A fortnight?

author: cersei lannister

author: tywin lannister
content: No jugglers, no jousting dwarves, no seventy-seven-course meals.

content: And your wedding to Loras?

author: cersei lannister
content: Shortly after Tommen's.

author: tywin lannister
content: Shortly?

author: cersei lannister
content: A fortnight.

author: tywin lannister
content: I know you don't like them. I didn't like your husband. Used to pat me on the back a lot. I didn't trust him.

author: cersei lannister
content: We had that in common.

author: tywin lannister
content: You don't need to make formal alliances with people you trust.

author: cersei lannister
content: Then whom can we trust?

author: tywin lannister
content: Ourselves alone.

author: tywin lannister
content: The Tyrells are our only true rivals in terms of resources and we need them on our side.

author: cersei lannister
content: Robert wasn't particularly rich.

author: tywin lannister
content: Robert had me funding him. Wars swallow gold like a pit in the earth.

author: cersei lannister
content: I suppose that explains why we did so well in the last one.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you know how much gold was mined in the Westerlands this past year?

author: cersei lannister
content: Haven't a clue.

author: tywin lannister
content: Go on, your best guess.

author: cersei lannister
content: Pounds, tons, ounces?

author: tywin lannister
content: Doesn't matter. The answer is the same.

author: cersei lannister
content: That can't be.

author: tywin lannister
content: Our last working mine ran dry three years ago.

author: cersei lannister
content: Then how do we pay for anything?

author: tywin lannister
content: The crown owes the Iron Bank of Braavos a tremendous amount of money.

author: cersei lannister
content: How much?

author: tywin lannister
content: A tremendous amount.

author: cersei lannister
content: There must be someone at the Iron Bank you can speak to, come to some arrangement.

author: tywin lannister
content: The Iron Bank is the Iron Bank. There is no someone.

author: cersei lannister
content: Someone does work there. It is comprised of people.

author: tywin lannister
content: And a temple is comprised of stones. One stone crumbles and another takes its place. And the temple holds its form for a thousand years or more. That's what the Iron Bank is... a temple. We all live in its shadow and almost none of us know it. You can't run from them. You can't cheat them. You can't sway them with excuses. If you owe them money and you don't want to crumble yourself, you pay it back. Vesting the Tyrells in the crown will help a great deal in this respect.

author: cersei lannister
content: It's for the good of the family, I understand that. I'm not sure my brothers do.

author: tywin lannister
content: I know you're building a strong case against Tyrion. And as a mother, that is your right. But as a judge, I cannot discuss the trial with you.

author: cersei lannister
content: I respect that. We don't need to discuss it.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Lannister legacy is the only thing that matters. You've started wars to protect this family. Turned your back on Jaime for refusing to contribute to its future. What does Tyrion deserve for lighting that future on fire?

author: arya stark
content: Joffrey. Cersei. Walder Frey. Meryn Trant. Tywin Lannister. The Red Woman. Beric Dondarrion. Thoros of Myr. Ilyn Payne. The Mountain.

author: sandor clegane
content: Would you shut up?

author: arya stark
content: I can't sleep until I say the names.

author: sandor clegane
content: The names of every fucking person in Westeros?

author: arya stark
content: Only the ones I'm going to kill.

author: sandor clegane
content: Hate's as good a thing as any to keep a person going. Better than most. We come across my brother, maybe we can both cross a name off our list.

author: arya stark
content: If he were here right now, what would you do?

author: sandor clegane
content: I'd tell him to shut the fuck up so I can get some sleep. Go on, get it over with, your list of doomed men.

author: arya stark
content: I'm almost done. Only one name left.

author: sandor clegane
content: Go on.

author: arya stark
content: The Hound.

author: sansa stark
content: Thank you.

author: lysa
content: Your mother always had a sweet tooth, you know?

author: sansa stark
content: Really?

author: lysa
content: Oh, yes. At suppertime, she would go straight for honey cakes, candied almonds, custard. Anything sweet. Eventually, your grandfather had to assign a septa to watch her at meals. Cat was the firstborn daughter after all. It was important that she remain desirable so Father could arrange a good match for her and she was starting to get fat.

author: sansa stark
content: My mother, fat? She never let me have my pudding until I'd finished all my proper food.

author: lysa
content: This is before she married your father and moved to the North. By the time you were born, your father's austerity had become hers. Marriage changes people. I didn't mean for you to stop. Go on, enjoy them. How do you like them?

author: sansa stark
content: They're delicious. Where did you get the lemons? You can't grow them up here.

author: lysa
content: Oh, gods, no. Petyr had three crates brought all the way from King's Landing. He knew you liked lemon cakes. He's so kind. He really cares for you. Think where you'd be without him. In their clutches and tried for murder.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes. I'm very lucky.

author: lysa
content: He feels responsible for you.

author: sansa stark
content: Oh, I know he does. I'm so grateful.

author: lysa
content: Why? Why does he feel responsible for you?

author: sansa stark
content: Well, I'm half Tully. He loved your family so much.

author: lysa
content: Loved your mother.

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: lysa
content: That's what you wanted to say.

author: sansa stark
content: He loves you, Aunt Lysa. He's married to you.

author: lysa
content: Your mother never loved him. Never. Cat always went straight for the sweetest thing. The most obvious thing. Your Uncle Brandon. Your handsome, arrogant, cruel Uncle Brandon. He almost killed Petyr in a duel. And your mother loved him anyway. And now Petyr is risking his life to save you, the daughter of a woman who didn't love him no more than those whores in his brothels. Has he told you about them?

author: lysa
content: He hasn't told you about the vile things they do with their bodies? The vile things they let him do with their bodies?

author: sansa stark
content: No, never.

author: lysa
content: Are you pregnant?

author: sansa stark
content: What? No, I told you. Lord Tyrion and I never-

author: lysa
content: I wasn't asking about Tyrion. What have you let Petyr do with your body?

author: sansa stark
content: Aunt Lysa, no, I-

author: lysa
content: Your young, pretty body.

author: sansa stark
content: Nothing. I'm a virgin.

author: lysa
content: Don't lie to me.

author: sansa stark
content: You're hurting me.

author: lysa
content: I'll know if you lie.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm a virgin, I swear it. He loves you, Aunt Lysa. All he says is that I'm stupid. I'm a stupid little girl with stupid dreams who never learns and I'm a terrible liar, so I should always tell the truth. And I swear to you that he has never touched me. Not once, not ever.

author: lysa
content: Shh. Shh. Shh. It's all right. It will all be all right. You'll be a widow soon. They'll execute that dwarf for murdering the king and you'll be free to marry Robin. You'll be the Lady of the Vale. Hmm.

author: brienne
content: Didn't they teach you how to ride a horse?

author: podrick
content: Yes, my lady, when I was young. There wasn't much call for it with Lord Tyrion, though. He preferred litters.

author: brienne
content: Perhaps you should have stayed with him. It's not going to be a pleasant journey for you. It could take weeks to get to the Wall, depending on the weather.

author: podrick
content: That's a long way off.

author: brienne
content: Well, Lady Sansa's brother's at Castle Black. If I were her, that's where I'd go. Feel free to stop at any point.

author: podrick
content: Never, my lady. I'm your squire.

author: brienne
content: I've made it this far in the world without a squire. I don't see why I need one now.

author: podrick
content: All knights have squires, my lady.

author: brienne
content: I'm not a knight. And I'm not a slaver, either. I don't own you.

author: podrick
content: I swore an oath, my lady.

author: brienne
content: I am releasing you from that oath. That means you could leave.

author: podrick
content: I know.

author: brienne
content: What do you think will happen if you leave?

author: podrick
content: They'll say I wasn't a very good squire.

author: sandor clegane
content: The hell you doing?

author: arya stark
content: Practicing.

author: sandor clegane
content: What, ways to die?

author: arya stark
content: No one's going to kill me.

author: sandor clegane
content: They will if you nance around like that. That's no way to fight.

author: arya stark
content: It's not fighting. It's water dancing.

author: sandor clegane
content: Dancing? Maybe you ought to put on a dress. Who taught you that shite?

author: arya stark
content: The greatest swordsman who ever lived. Syrio Forel, the First Sword to the Sealord of Braavos.

author: sandor clegane
content: Braavos. Greasy-haired little bastard, I bet. They all are.

author: arya stark
content: What do you know about anything?

author: sandor clegane
content: I bet his hair is greasier than Joffrey's cunt.

author: arya stark
content: It was not.

author: sandor clegane
content: Was? He dead?

author: arya stark
content: Yes.

author: sandor clegane
content: How?

author: arya stark
content: He was killed.

author: sandor clegane
content: Who by?

author: arya stark
content: Meryn Trant. That's why Ser Meryn-

author: sandor clegane
content: Meryn Trant? The greatest swordsman who ever lived killed by Meryn fucking Trant?

author: arya stark
content: He was outnumbered.

author: sandor clegane
content: Any boy whore with a sword could beat three Meryn Trants.

author: arya stark
content: Syrio didn't have a sword. Or armor. Just a stick.

author: sandor clegane
content: The greatest swordsman who ever lived didn't have a sword? All right. You have a sword. Let's see what he taught you. Go on, do it for your Braavosi friend. Dead like all the rest of your friends.

author: sandor clegane
content: Your friendo s dead and Meryn Trant's not 'cause Trant had armor and a big fucking sword.

author: oberyn martell
content: Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Prince Oberyn. Writing letters?

author: oberyn martell
content: A poem, actually.

author: cersei lannister
content: May I show you the gardens?

author: oberyn martell
content: I couldn't very well refuse a royal escort.

author: cersei lannister
content: No, you couldn't.

author: cersei lannister
content: I didn't realize you were a poet.

author: oberyn martell
content: Not a very good one.

author: cersei lannister
content: For your paramour?

author: oberyn martell
content: For one of my daughters.

author: cersei lannister
content: You have several, don't you?

author: oberyn martell
content: Eight.

author: cersei lannister
content: Eight? Eight daughters?

author: oberyn martell
content: The fifth is difficult. I named her after my sister Elia.

author: cersei lannister
content: Beautiful name.

author: oberyn martell
content: Yes. But I can't say it without turning sad. And after I turn sad, I grow angry.

author: cersei lannister
content: Perhaps that's why she's difficult. The gods love their stupid jokes, don't they?

author: oberyn martell
content: Which joke is that?

author: cersei lannister
content: You're a prince of Dorne. A legendary fighter. A brilliant man feared throughout Westeros. But you could not save your sister. I'm a Lannister. Queen for nineteen years. Daughter of the most powerful man alive. But I could not save my son. What good is power if you cannot protect the ones you love?

author: oberyn martell
content: We can avenge them.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes, we can avenge them.

author: oberyn martell
content: You really believe Tyrion murdered your son?

author: cersei lannister
content: I know he did.

author: oberyn martell
content: We will have a trial and we will learn the truth.

author: cersei lannister
content: We'll have a trial, anyway. I haven't seen my daughter in over a year.

author: oberyn martell
content: The last time I saw her, she was swimming with two of my girls in the Water Gardens. Laughing in the sun.

author: cersei lannister
content: I want to believe that. I want to believe she's happy.

author: oberyn martell
content: You have my word. We don't hurt little girls in Dorne.

author: cersei lannister
content: Everywhere in the world, they hurt little girls. Would you bring her a gift for me? I wasn't there for her name day. I don't know when I'll see her again.

author: oberyn martell
content: Anything at all.

author: cersei lannister
content: The best shipwrights in King's Landing have been working on it for months. Myrcella loves the open water.

author: oberyn martell
content: I will have it sailed down to Sunspear for her.

author: cersei lannister
content: Please tell her... her mother misses her very much.

author: podrick
content: Oh, no, no, no.

author: podrick
content: No, no, no, no.

author: podrick
content: Hells. Gods.

author: brienne
content: Did you remove the skin?

author: podrick
content: No, my lady.

author: brienne
content: Have you ever cooked a rabbit before?

author: brienne
content: Did you ever cook anything for Lord Tyrion?

author: podrick
content: No, my lady. That was the cooks.

author: brienne
content: What are you doing?

author: podrick
content: I'm helping you with your armor.

author: brienne
content: I've been removing my own armor for quite some time, thank you very much.

author: brienne
content: What exactly did you do for Lord Tyrion?

author: podrick
content: I brought him his meals and cleared his table when he was finished. I kept his clothing and linens clean. Carried his messages and returned the replies. Mostly I poured wine.

author: brienne
content: Oh. Whilst in Lord Tyrion's service, did you ever do anything remotely related to combat?

author: podrick
content: I killed a man.

author: brienne
content: Who?

author: podrick
content: A Kingsguard. He tried to kill Lord Tyrion at the Blackwater.

author: brienne
content: How did you kill a Kingsguard?

author: podrick
content: I pushed a spear through the back of his head.

author: brienne
content: Bloody ridiculous. Help me with these straps.

author: rast
content: Hey. Hey, get up. Get up.

author: man
content: That's it lad, put it inside. Get the fire going again. We're all freezing.

author: man
content: Aye. What we need is a girl there.

author: man
content: I've got to have a piss.

author: man
content: Now keep quiet.

author: meera
content: You need water.

author: jojen
content: It doesn't matter.

author: meera
content: Of course it matters.

author: jojen
content: You mustn't let anything stop you.

author: bran stark
content: They already have stopped me.

author: jojen
content: No. You're not here. You're far from here.

author: meera
content: What does that mean?

author: jojen
content: At the hill. A great weirwood tree.

author: bran stark
content: You've seen it, too.

author: jojen
content: Meera and I, even Hodor, we're only here to guide you. He's waiting for you. We have to find it. You have to make it.

author: bran stark
content: We will.

author: jojen
content: This... this isn't the end. Not for you. Not yet.

author: meera
content: How... will we know the end?

author: jojen
content: You'll know.

author: locke
content: Brothers.

author: dolorous edd
content: You do move quiet.

author: jon snow
content: How many?

author: locke
content: Eleven men. Most of them already drunk. No guards posted. They don't seem to have a care in the world. We'll carve them up like walnut pie.

author: grenn
content: Karl was a top paid cutthroat in Flea Bottom. I've seen what he can do with a knife.

author: locke
content: Have you seen what I can do with a knife?

author: grenn
content: Not yet.

author: locke
content: There's a hut on the west side of the keep. We should steer clear of it.

author: jon snow
content: Why?

author: locke
content: They've got some hounds chained up inside. Closer we can get without the dogs sniffing us, the better.

author: grenn
content: New moon tonight.

author: jon snow
content: Get some rest. We move at sundown.

author: karl tanner
content: I've always liked a girl with curls. A touch of class. You take whatever's left.

author: karl tanner
content: Get her up.

author: bran stark
content: Stop.

author: jojen
content: Stop. What are you doing?

author: hodor
content: Hodor. Hodor. Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Stop. Stop!

author: hodor
content: Hodor. Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Stop! Please.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Please, get off her!

author: bran stark
content: Please! Please, leave her alone!

author: bran stark
content: Please, stop. Stop.

author: bran stark
content: What are you doing? Leave her alone!

author: bran stark
content: No!

author: karl tanner
content: Shh. Shh, shh, shh.

author: karl
content: Shh.

author: karl tanner
content: You've got pretty hair, don't you? Now what is a pretty little highborn girl like you doing out here in the deep, dark woods, eh? You left your daddy's castle looking for trouble, didn't you? No dresses for you. You like it rough, don't you? You like it in the gutter, don't you?

author: jojen
content: If you let my sister go, I can help you.

author: karl tanner
content: You can help me?

author: jojen
content: I can.

author: karl tanner
content: And how you gonna do that?

author: jojen
content: I have the sight. I can see things.

author: karl tanner
content: That's very helpful.

author: jojen
content: Things that haven't happened yet.

author: karl tanner
content: What a fine thing. A fine thing.

author: karl tanner
content: Have you seen what I'm gonna do to your sister? Have you seen what they're going to do to your sister?

author: jojen
content: No.

author: karl tanner
content: Don't close your eyes.

author: jojen
content: I saw you die tonight. I saw your body burn. I saw the snow fall and bury your bones.

author: man
content: To arms!

author: rast
content: They're here, the Night's Watch.

author: locke
content: Rescue party is here, lads. Lady.

author: bran stark
content: Is Jon with you?

author: locke
content: Aye. I'll take you to him.

author: locke
content: You're Brandon Stark?

author: locke
content: The little crippled lord. We're going for a ride, boy.

author: bronn
content: Jon! Jon!

author: locke
content: Keep talking and I'll cut your friends' throats. Starting with the idiot. Do you hear? Do you hear?

author: hodor
content: Hodor! Hodor! Hodor. Hodor.

author: hodor
content: Hodor. Hodor. Hodor. Hodor. Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Hodor. Hodor, get his knife. Cut me loose.

author: bran stark
content: Hodor, get his knife. Hodor. Cut me loose, Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: Jojen and Meera, free them. Go!

author: bran stark
content: Jon.

author: bran stark
content: Jon!

author: jojen
content: If he sees you, he won't let you go north.

author: bran stark
content: He's my brother.

author: jojen
content: And wants to protect you. He'll take you back to Castle Black.

author: jojen
content: You have to decide. Do you want to find the three-eyed raven?

author: bran stark
content: Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: We need to free Summer. And we need to go.

author: karl tanner
content: Lord Snow. Are you bringing me back for trial?

author: karl tanner
content: We had a good thing here. We were free men. You'll never be free. You'll never know what that's like.

author: karl tanner
content: You learn how to fight in a castle?

author: karl tanner
content: Some old man teach you how to stand, how to parry?

author: karl tanner
content: How to fight with honor?

author: karl tanner
content: You know what's wrong with honor?

author: karl tanner
content: You.

author: jon snow
content: Are you all right? Come with me. Come on.

author: jon snow
content: We lost four brothers?

author: doloroud edd
content: Five.

author: grenn
content: What the seven hells could do that to a man?

author: jon snow
content: I count ten dead mutineers.

author: grenn
content: Locke said there were eleven of them.

author: dolrous edd
content: Where's Rast?

author: man
content: Here's another.

author: grenn
content: Jon.

author: jon snow
content: Where in seven hells? Come here.

author: jon snow
content: I missed you, boy.

author: dolorous edd
content: What should we do with this lot?

author: jon snow
content: It's not safe for you here on your own. Mance Rayder has an army heading this way and there's worse out there than Mance. Come with us to Castle Black. We can find you work. Keep you safe.

author: morag
content: Meaning all respect, Ser Crow, Craster beat us and worse. Your brother crows beat us and worse. We'll find our own way.

author: jon snow
content: You want to stay here in Craster's Keep?

author: morag
content: Burn it to the ground and all the dead with it.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, if you'd like to sit, I'm sure that--

author: stannis baratheon
content: We've been here since midday.

author: davos
content: Easterners have a difference sense of time, I've often found. Once I was waiting for Salladhor Saan here in Braavos. Together, we were going to run three shiploads of the finest--

author: tycho
content: Welcome to the Iron Bank. Please, sit.

author: tycho
content: What can we do for you, Lord Stannis?

author: davos
content: This is Stannis of the House Baratheon, King of the Andals and the First Men, Lord of the Seven Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm.

author: tycho
content: The Iron Throne is currently occupied by Tommen of the House Baratheon, King of the Andals and the First Men, Lord of the Seven Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm.

author: stannis baratheon
content: He shares no blood with me. He is a bastard born of incest. As was his brother before him.

author: tycho
content: Yes, we have heard this story.

author: stannis baratheon
content: It's not a story. It's the truth.

author: tycho
content: The king's grandfather tells a different story. A story about a jealous uncle whose attempts to usurp the throne from the rightful king cost the Seven Kingdoms dearly in blood and gold.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Gold you loaned him.

author: tycho
content: And you feel your blood gives you a claim on our gold?

author: stannis baratheon
content: More than any man living.

author: tycho
content: Across the Narrow Sea, your books are filled with words like "usurper" and "madman" and "blood right." Here, our books are filled with numbers. We prefer the stories they tell. More plain. Less open to interpretation. How many fighting men remain loyal to you?

author: tycho
content: And how many ships do you have? The ones still afloat, Ser Davos, not at the bottom of Blackwater Bay.

author: tycho
content: And how much wheat and barley and beef and pork do you produce on Dragonstone to feed your 4,000 men on your 32 ships?

author: stannis baratheon
content: None.

author: tycho
content: You can see why these numbers seem unlikely to add up to a happy ending from our perspective. I'm afraid we must respectfully decline your request. But we thank you for paying us the honor of your visit.

author: davos
content: My lord.

author: tycho
content: I'm not a lord, Ser Davos Seaworth. You would not be either here. In Braavos, thieves are not rewarded with titles.

author: davos
content: Well, strictly speaking, I didn't do the thieving. That would be the pirates. I just moved what they stole from one place to another. {DAVOS removes his right glove to show the stubs of his fingers.

author: davos
content: This is the payment that was demanded by King Stannis for my crimes. I consider it an honest accounting. He's an honest man and he's your best chance to get back the money you've sunk into Westeros. Which is a lot, I imagine. Wars are expensive.

author: tycho
content: The war is over.

author: davos
content: As long as Stannis lives, the war is not over. Who's the real power in King's Landing?

author: tycho
content: Ser Davos...

author: davos
content: Humor me.

author: tycho
content: Tywin Lannister.

author: davos
content: How old is Tywin Lannister?

author: stannis baratheon
content: 67. And when he dies, who's in command? A half-grown boy, the product of incest? Cersei Lannister, a queen whose people despise her? Jaime Lannister, a man best known for killing the king he was sworn to protect? When Tywin's gone, who do you back?

author: tycho
content: That is a problem for another time.

author: davos
content: Begging your pardon, I think it's a problem for now. There's only one reliable leader left in Westeros. Stannis. He's got the birthright. He's in his prime. He's a tried and tested battle commander. And he doesn't just talk about paying people back, he does it.

author: sallador
content: The lookout sees a pirate ship sailing their way. The captain shouts to his first mate, "Bring me my red shirt." The first mate brings the red shirt and the captain puts it on. And when the pirates try to board, the brave captain leads his men to victory. A few days later, the lookout screams, "Two pirate ships!" The crew is shivering like scared mice. But the courageous captain hollers, "Bring me my red shirt!"

author: sallador
content: After the battle, the first mate asks, "Captain, why do you call for your red shirt before battle?" The captain replies, "So that if I am stabbed, you will not see me bleed." The next morning the lookout screams, "10 pirate ships! We are surrounded!" The crew goes silent.

author: sallador
content: They all look to their brave captain, waiting for his usual command. Calm as ever, the captain bellows...

author: women
content: Bring me my brown pants!

author: davos
content: You think they ever met a pirate who didn't tell them that joke?

author: sallador
content: Davos. I heard you were rotting in a dungeon in Dragonstone.

author: davos
content: Only half rotted.

author: sallador
content: Join us, my friend. Join us. This is Lhara. And this is--

author: lhara
content: I am Lhara.

author: sallador
content: She's an artist, this one, truly.

author: davos
content: No time, I'm afraid. We sail at sunrise.

author: sallador
content: We?

author: davos
content: You, me-- we.

author: sallador
content: Once I thought this man loved me. Now I know he despises me. He wants to see me die poor and alone on some cold--

author: davos
content: You won't be alone. And you won't be poor.

author: davos
content: There's a chest of the good stuff left back at your house. I gave it to your wife.

author: sallador
content: You're not my friend, my friend.

author: davos
content: I'll see you at sunrise.

author: yara greyjoy
content: I give you until the full moon to order all ironborn scum out of the North and back to those shit-stained rocks you call home. On the first night of the full moon, I will hunt down every islander still on our lands and flay them living, the way I flayed the 20 ironborn scum I found at Winterfell. In the box you'll find a special gift-- Theon's favorite toy. He cried when I took it away from him. Leave the North now or more boxes will follow with more Theon. Signed Ramsay Snow, natural born son of Roose Bolton, Lord of the Dreadfort and Warden of the North.

author: myranda
content: Yes!

author: yara greyjoy
content: They skinned our countrymen and they mutilated my brother, your prince. Your prince. Everything they've done to him, they've also done to you.

author: myranda
content: Yes! Yes!

author: yara greyjoy
content: As long as they can hurt our prince with impunity, the word ironborn means nothing.

author: first mate
content: Go left.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Theon Greyjoy.

author: bolton guard
content: I don't know--

author: yara greyjoy
content: I'm here for Theon Greyjoy. Take me to the dungeons.

author: bolton guard
content: He's not in the dungeons.

author: bolton guard
content: Last cage on the right.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Thank you.

author: yara greyjoy
content: This way!

author: yara greyjoy
content: We're going home.

author: theon greyjoy
content: No!

author: yara greyjoy
content: It's all right. It's me, Yara.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You can't trick me. Tell him. Tell him you couldn't trick me.

author: yara greyjoy
content: I'm not tricking you, Theon. I'm saving you.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not Theon! Reek! Reek! My name is Reek!

author: first mate
content: They're here.

author: yara greyjoy
content: If they catch us in here, we're trapped. Help me with him.

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, you can't! You can't!

author: yara greyjoy
content: You're Theon Greyjoy.

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, I don't believe her! I know who I am! I'm Reek! Reek! Loyal Reek! Good Reek! I've always been Reek!

author: ramsay bolton
content: This is turning into a lovely evening.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm Reek! Loyal Reek!

author: yara greyjoy
content: Aah! Theon!

author: yara greyjoy
content: Give me my brother and no more of your men will die.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You've got bigger balls than he ever did. But with those big balls of yours...

author: ramsay bolton
content: how fast can you run?

author: yara greyjoy
content: Make for the ship, now.

author: ironborn
content: But your brother.

author: yara greyjoy
content: My brother is dead.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I have a treat for you. A reward.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Reward?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Yes, Reek. Those creatures who came in the night, they wanted to take you away. And you didn't let them. You remained loyal.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I-- I didn't want them to take me. I was so scared. I didn't want them--

author: ramsay bolton
content: Yes, yes, Reek. It's a bath. For you. Remove those rags. Now.

author: ramsay bolton
content: The britches, too, Reek. Take them off.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Do you love me, Reek?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes, of course, my lord.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Good. Because I need you to do something for me. Something very important. There's a castle, you see. Some bad men hold this castle. I need your help to take this castle back.

author: theon greyjoy
content: But how can--

author: ramsay bolton
content: I need you to play a role. To pretend to be someone you're not.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Pretend to be who?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Theon Greyjoy.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You stand before Daenerys Stormborn of the House Targaryen, the First of Her Name, Queen of Meereen, Queen of the Andals and the First Men, Khaleesi of the Great Sea, Breaker of Chains and Mother of Dragons. Don't be afraid, my friend.

author: missandei
content: The Queen says you may approach and speak.

author: missandei
content: He is a goatherd. He says he prayed for your victory against the slave masters.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I thank him for his prayers.

author: missandei
content: It was your dragons, he says. They came this morning for his flock.

author: missandei
content: He hopes he has not offended Your Grace, but now he has nothing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Tell this man I am sorry for his hardship. I cannot bring back his goats,

author: daenerys targaryen
content: but I will see he is paid their value three times over.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Send the next one in.

author: manservant
content: The noble Hizdahr zo Loraq begs an audience with the Queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The noble Hizdahr zo Loraq can speak to me himself.

author: hizdahr
content: Queen Daenerys. Tales of your beauty were not exaggerated.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I thank you.

author: hizdahr
content: Mine is one of the oldest and proudest families in Meereen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Then it is my honor to receive you.

author: hizdahr
content: My father, one of Meereen's most respected and beloved citizens, oversaw the restoration and maintenance of its greatest landmarks. This pyramid included.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: For that, he has my gratitude. I should be honored to meet him.

author: hizdahr
content: You have, Your Grace. You crucified him. I pray you'll never live to see a member of your family treated so cruelly.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your father crucified innocent children.

author: hizdahr
content: My father spoke out against crucifying those children. He decried it as a criminal act, but was overruled. Is it justice to answer one crime with another?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I am sorry you no longer have a father, but my treatment of the masters was no crime. You'd be wise to remember that.

author: hizdahr
content: What's done is done. You are the queen and I am a servant of Meereen. A servant who does not wish to see its traditions eradicated.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what traditions do you speak of?

author: hizdahr
content: The tradition of funeral rite. Proper burial in the Temple of the Graces. My father and 162 noble Meereenese are still nailed to those posts, carrion for vultures, rotting in the sun.

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace, I ask that you order these men taken down so that they might receive proper burials.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what of the slave children these noble Meereenese crucified? They were rotting in the sun as well. Would you have begged me for their right to a proper burial?

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace, I cannot defend the actions of the masters. I can only speak to you as a son who loved his father. Let me take his body down. Let me have him brought to the temple and buried with dignity so that he might find peace in the next world.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Bury your father, Hizdahr zo Loraq.

author: hizdahr
content: Thank you, my queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many more?

author: missandei
content: There are 212 supplicants waiting, Your Grace.

author: oberyn martell
content: These meetings aren't always going to be this early, are they? I was up late last night. So, does this mean I am a master of something now? Coins, ships?

author: mace
content: Lord Tywin and I already determined that I shall be the Master of Ships long before you--

author: mace
content: Lord Tywin, it's a great honor to have been granted a seat on this council. I--

author: tywin lannister
content: The trial begins this afternoon. We only have the morning for affairs of state. Shall we begin?

author: varys
content: Sandor Clegane has been spotted in the Riverlands, my lord.

author: cersei lannister
content: A coward and a traitor.

author: varys
content: My birds tell me the Hound slaughtered five of our soldiers. I believe the phrase "fuck the king" was uttered.

author: pycelle
content: Disgraceful.

author: tywin lannister
content: What would it take to make the common soldier stupid enough to try his luck with the Hound?

author: varys
content: 10 silver stags seems a generous bounty.

author: tywin lannister
content: Make it 100. What else?

author: varys
content: More whispers from the east, my lord.

author: tywin lannister
content: The Targaryen girl?

author: varys
content: Daenerys has taken up residence in Meereen. She has conquered the city and rules as its queen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Conquered with what?

author: varys
content: She commands an army of Unsullied, my queen. Some 8,000 strong. She has a company of sellswords-- the Second Sons. She has two knights advising her-- Jorah Mormont and Barristan Selmy. And she has three dragons.

author: cersei lannister
content: Baby dragons. Larger every year, Your Grace.

author: pycelle
content: Mormont is spying on her for us.

author: varys
content: No longer. He appears to be fully devoted to her. As for Ser Barristan, it would seem he took his dismissal from the Kingsguard a bit harder than anticipated.

author: cersei lannister
content: He's an old man. He wasn't fit to protect my son.

author: tywin lannister
content: Joffrey didn't die on his watch. Dismissing him was as insulting as it was stupid.

author: cersei lannister
content: Don't tell me you're worried about a child halfway across the world.

author: varys
content: A child with two seasoned warriors counseling her and a powerful army at her back, Your Grace.

author: oberyn martell
content: Lord Varys is right. I have been to Essos and seen the Unsullied firsthand. They are very impressive on the battlefield. Less so in the bedroom.

author: tywin lannister
content: Dragons haven't won a war in 300 years. Armies win them all the time. She must be dealt with.

author: pycelle
content: How, my lord? By force?

author: tywin lannister
content: Eventually, if it comes to that. Can your little birds find their way into Meereen?

author: varys
content: Most certainly, my Lord Hand.

author: tywin lannister
content: Mmm. Lord Tyrell, be a good man. Fetch my quill and paper.

author: varys
content: Prince Oberyn.

author: oberyn martell
content: Lord Varys...

author: varys
content: Only Varys. I'm not actually a nobleman. No one is under obligation to call me lord.

author: oberyn martell
content: And yet everyone does.

author: varys
content: You seem quite knowledgeable about the Unsullied. Did you spend much time in Essos?

author: oberyn martell
content: Five years.

author: varys
content: May I ask why?

author: oberyn martell
content: Tis a big and beautiful world. Most of us live and die in the same corner where we were born and never get to see any of it. I don't want to be most of us.

author: varys
content: Most of us aren't princes.

author: oberyn martell
content: You are from Essos. Where? Lys?

author: varys
content: I have an ear for accents. I've lost my accent entirely.

author: oberyn martell
content: I have an ear for that as well. How did you get here?

author: varys
content: It's a long story.

author: oberyn martell
content: One you don't like telling people.

author: varys
content: People I trust.

author: oberyn martell
content: My paramour Ellaria, she would find you very interesting. You should come to the brothel and meet her. We brought our own wine, not the swill they serve here. We have some lovely boys on retainer, but...

author: oberyn martell
content: You did like boys before?

author: oberyn martell
content: Really? Girls? Hmm. I hope you won't be offended when I say I never would have guessed.

author: varys
content: Not at all. But I was never interested in girls, either.

author: oberyn martell
content: What then?

author: varys
content: Nothing.

author: oberyn martell
content: Everybody is interested in something.

author: varys
content: Not me. When I see what desire does to people, what it's done to this country, I am very glad to have no part in it. Besides, the absence of desire leaves one free to pursue other things.

author: oberyn martell
content: Such as?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Let me guess, I've been pardoned.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Really?

author: jaime lannister
content: Father's orders.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, we mustn't disappoint Father.

author: man
content: Kingslayer!

author: tommen lannister
content: I, Tommen of the House Baratheon, First of my Name, King of the Andals and the First Men, and Lord of the Seven Kingdoms, do hereby recuse myself from this trial. Tywin of the House Lannister, Hand of the King, Protector of the Realm, will sit as judge in my stead. And with him Prince Oberyn of the House Martell and Lord Mace of the House Tyrell. And if found guilty... may the gods punish the accused.

author: tywin lannister
content: Tyrion of the House Lannister, you stand accused by the Queen Regent of regicide. Did you kill King Joffrey?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No.

author: tywin lannister
content: Did your wife, the Lady Sansa?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not that I know of.

author: tywin lannister
content: How would you say he died, then?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Choked on his pigeon pie.

author: tywin lannister
content: So you would blame the bakers?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Or the pigeons. Just leave me out of it.

author: tywin lannister
content: The crown may call its first witness.

author: meryn trant
content: Once we'd got King Joffrey safely away from the mob, the Imp rounded on him. He slapped the king across the face and called him a vicious idiot and a fool. It wasn't the first time the Imp threatened Joffrey. Right here in this throne room, he marched up those steps and called our king a halfwit. Compared His Grace to the Mad King and suggested he'd meet the same fate. And when I spoke in the king's defense, he threatened to have me killed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, why don't you tell them what Joffrey was doing?

author: tywin lannister
content: Silence.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Pointing a loaded crossbow at Sansa Stark while you tore at her clothes and beat her.

author: tywin lannister
content: Silence! You will not speak unless called upon. You're dismissed, Ser Meryn.

author: pycelle
content: Basilisk venom, widow's blood, wolfsbane, essence of nightshade, sweetsleep, tears of Lys, demon's dance... blind eye--

author: oberyn martell
content: I think you have made your point, Grand Maester. You have a lot of poison in your store.

author: pycelle
content: Had, Prince Oberyn. My stores were plundered.

author: tywin lannister
content: By whom?

author: pycelle
content: By the accused, Tyrion Lannister, after he had me wrongfully imprisoned.

author: tywin lannister
content: Grand Maester, you examined King Joffrey's corpse. Was it without question poison that killed him?

author: pycelle
content: Without question.

author: pycelle
content: This was found on the body of Dontos Hollard, the king's fool. He was last seen spiriting Sansa Stark, the wife of the accused, away from the feast. She wore this necklace the day of the wedding. Residue of a most rare and terrible poison was found inside.

author: tywin lannister
content: Was this one of the poisons stolen from your store?

author: pyelle
content: It was. The Strangler. A poison few in the Seven Kingdoms possess. And used to strike down the most noble child the gods ever put on this good earth.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will hurt you for this. A day will come when you think you are safe and happy and your joy will turn to ashes in your mouth and you will know the debt is paid.

author: mace
content: Your own brother said this to you?

author: cersei lannister
content: Shortly before the Battle of Blackwater Bay. I confronted him about his plans to put Joffrey on the front lines. As it turned out, when the attack came, Joff insisted on remaining at the battlements. He believed his presence would inspire the troops.

author: oberyn martell
content: Tyrion said, "And you will know the debt is paid." What debt?

author: cersei lannister
content: I discovered he'd been keeping whores in the Tower of the Hand. I asked him to confine his salacious acts to the brothel where such behavior belongs. He wasn't pleased.

author: tywin lannister
content: Thank you, Your Grace, for the courage of your testimony.

author: mace
content: Do you remember the precise nature of this threat?

author: varys
content: I'm afraid I do, my lord. He said, "Perhaps you should speak more softly to me, then. Monsters are dangerous and just now kings are dying like flies."

author: mace
content: And he said this to you at a meeting of the small council?

author: varys
content: Yes. After we received word of Robb Stark's death. He didn't seem gladdened by the news. Perhaps his marriage to Sansa Stark had made him more sympathetic to the northern cause.

author: tywin lannister
content: You're excused, Lord Varys.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Father, may I ask the witness one question?

author: tywin lannister
content: One.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You once said that without me, this city would have faced certain defeat. You said the histories would never mention me, but you would not forget. Have you forgotten, Lord Varys?

author: varys
content: Sadly, my lord, I never forget a thing.

author: tywin lannister
content: We will adjourn for now.

author: tywin lannister
content: Toll the bells in an hour's time.

author: guard
content: Clear the court!

author: jaime lannister
content: You'd condemn your own son to death?

author: tywin lannister
content: I've condemned no one. The trial is not over.

author: jaime lannister
content: This isn't a trial. It's a farce. Cersei has manipulated everything and you know it.

author: tywin lannister
content: I know nothing of the sort.

author: jaime lannister
content: You've always hated Tyrion.

author: tywin lannister
content: He killed his king.

author: jaime lannister
content: As did I. Do you know the last order the Mad King gave me? To bring him your head. I saved your life so you could murder my brother?

author: tywin lannister
content: It won't be murder. It'll be justice.

author: jaime lannister
content: Justice?

author: tywin lannister
content: I'm performing my sworn duty as Hand of the King. If Tyrion is found guilty, he will be punished accordingly.

author: jaime lannister
content: He'll be executed.

author: tywin lannister
content: No, he'll be punished accordingly.

author: jaime lannister
content: Once you said family is what lives on. All that lives on. You told me about a dynasty that would last 1,000 years. What happens to your dynasty when Tyrion dies? I'm a Kingsguard, forbidden by oath to carry on the family line.

author: tywin lannister
content: I'm well aware of your oath.

author: jaime lannister
content: What happens to your name? Who carries the lion banner into future battles? Your nephews? Lancel Lannister? Others whose names I don't even remember?

author: tywin lannister
content: What happens to my dynasty if I spare the life of my grandson's killer?

author: jaime lannister
content: It survives through me. I'll leave the Kingsguard. I'll take my place as your son and heir if you let Tyrion live.

author: tywin lannister
content: Done.

author: tywin lannister
content: When the testimony's concluded and a guilty verdict rendered, Tyrion will be given the chance to speak. He'll plead for mercy. I'll allow him to join the Night's Watch. In three days' time, he'll depart for Castle Black and live out his days at the Wall. You'll remove your white cloak immediately. You will leave King's Landing to assume your rightful place at Casterly Rock. You will marry a suitable woman and father children named Lannister. And you'll never turn your back on your family again.

author: jaime lannister
content: You have my word.

author: tywin lannister
content: And you have mine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not going well, is it?

author: jaime lannister
content: You're going to be found guilty.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, you think so?

author: jaime lannister
content: When you are, you need to enter a formal plea for mercy and ask to be sent to the Wall. Father's agreed to it. He'll spare your life and allow you to join the Night's Watch.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ned Stark was promised the same thing and we both know how that turned out.

author: jaime lannister
content: Father is not Joffrey. He'll keep his word.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How do you know?

author: jaime lannister
content: Do you trust me?

author: jaime lannister
content: Keep your mouth shut. No more outbursts. This will all be over soon.

author: tywin lannister
content: The crown may call its next witness.

author: tywin lannister
content: State your name.

author: shae
content: Shae.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you swear by all the gods that your testimony will be true and honest?

author: shae
content: I swear it.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you know this man?

author: shae
content: Yes. Tyrion Lannister.

author: tywin lannister
content: How do you know him?

author: shae
content: I was handmaiden to his wife Lady Sansa.

author: tywin lannister
content: This man stands accused of murdering King Joffrey. What do you know of this?

author: shae
content: I know that he's guilty.

author: shae
content: He and Sansa planned it together.

author: tywin lannister
content: Silence! Continue.

author: shae
content: She wanted revenge for her father, her mother, her brother. She blamed their deaths on the king. Tyrion was happy to help. He hated Joffrey. He hated the queen. He hated you, my lord.

author: shae
content: He stole poison from the Grand Maester's chamber to put in Joffrey's wine.

author: oberyn martell
content: How could you possibly know all this? Why would he reveal such plans to his wife's maid?

author: shae
content: I wasn't just her maid. I was his whore.

author: mace
content: I beg your pardon? You said you were his...

author: shae
content: His whore.

author: tywin lannister
content: How did you come to be in his service?

author: shae
content: He stole me. I was with another man, a knight in your lordship's army. But when Tyrion arrived at the camp, he sent one of his cutthroats into our tent. He broke the knight's arm and brought me to Lord Tyrion. "You belong to me now," he said. "I want you to fuck me like it's my last night in this world."

author: tywin lannister
content: Silence. Silence!

author: oberyn martell
content: And did you?

author: shae
content: Did I what?

author: oberyn martell
content: Fuck him like it was his last night in this world.

author: shae
content: I did everything he wanted. Whatever he told me to do to him. Whatever he felt like doing to me. I kissed him where he wanted. I licked him where he wanted. I let him put himself where he wanted. I was his property. I would wait in his chambers for hours so he could use me when he was bored. He ordered me to call him "my lion," so I did. I took his face in my hands and said, "I am yours and you are mine."

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shae. Please don't.

author: shae
content: I am a whore. Remember? That was before he married Sansa. After that, all he wanted was her. But she wouldn't let him into her bed. So he promised to kill King Joffrey for her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Father, I wish to confess. I wish... to confess.

author: tywin lannister
content: You wish to confess?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I saved you. I saved this city and all your worthless lives. I should have let Stannis kill you all.

author: tywin lannister
content: Tyrion. Do you wish to confess?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, Father. I'm guilty. Guilty. Is that what you want to hear?

author: tywin lannister
content: You admit you poisoned the king?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, of that I'm innocent. I'm guilty of a far more monstrous crime. I am guilty of being a dwarf.

author: tywin lannister
content: You are not on trial for being a dwarf.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, yes, I am. I've been on trial for that my entire life.

author: tywin lannister
content: Have you nothing to say in your defense?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Nothing but this-- I did not do it. I did not kill Joffrey, but I wish that I had.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Watching your vicious bastard die gave me more relief than 1,000 lying whores.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wish I was the monster you think I am. I wish I had enough poison for the whole pack of you. I would gladly give my life to watch you all swallow it.

author: tywin lannister
content: Ser Meryn. Ser Meryn. Escort the prisoner back to his cell.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I will not give my life for Joffrey's murder. And I know I'll get no justice here. So I will let the gods decide my fate. I demand a trial by combat.

author: jaime lannister
content: I made a deal for you to keep your ungrateful head on your ungrateful neck a little while longer.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm sorry, what am I grateful for? The opportunity to live and die at the Wall as punishment for a crime I did not commit?

author: jaime lannister
content: You threw your life away. You threw it away. It's not a joke. You understand that, don't you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course it's a joke, just not a very funny one. I couldn't- I couldn't listen to her standing there telling her lies. I couldn't do it.

author: jaime lannister
content: You fell in love with a whore.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, I fell in love with a whore. And I was stupid enough to think that she had fallen in love with me. That deal you made, it was everything Father wanted. You do see that? He gets you back as his heir. The future Lord of the Rock. And he ships me off to Castle Black, out of sight at last. All so perfect. It felt good to take that from him. He knows I'm innocent and he's willing to sacrifice me anyway. He's willing to sacrifice any of us. Not you. You're the golden son. You could kill a king, lose a hand, fuck your own sister, you'll always be the golden son.

author: jaime lannister
content: Careful. I'm the last friend you've got.

author: tyrion lannister
content: At least I got to tell them what they really are.

author: jaime lannister
content: Yes, brilliant speech. They'll be talking about it for days to come. I thought you were a realist. Didn't realize you'd die for pride.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Don't give up on me just yet. I survived one trial by combat, even though you weren't there to save me.

author: jaime lannister
content: I can't save you this time either. My training has proved that I can't beat a stable boy with my left hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where's your sense of adventure? Even if you lose, imagine the look on Father's face when you fall.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Our family name snuffed out with a single swing of the sword.

author: jaime lannister
content: It is tempting.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well... Bronn fought for me once, he'll do it again. If he wins, I expect I'll be in his debt for the rest of my life.

author: jaime lannister
content: If he wins.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Will you find him for me? Who does Cersei plan on naming as a champion? I hope it's Ser Meryn Trant. I'd enjoy watching Bronn disembowel that pompous child beater.

author: jaime lannister
content: No. Not Ser Meryn.

author: guard
content: Go on, move it.

author: guard
content: And you. Come on.

author: prisoner
content: Mercy. Please. Please, mercy.

author: cersei lannister
content: Ser Gregor. Welcome to the capital. Thank you for riding here so quickly.

author: cersei lannister
content: You seem to be in good form.

author: mountain
content: Who am I fighting?

author: cersei lannister
content: Does it matter?

author: sandor clegane
content: Could be food.

author: arya stark
content: Could be soldiers.

author: arya stark
content: You shouldn't be sitting out here like this.

author: dying man
content: Where else to sit? Tried to walk back to my hut, hurt too much. Then I remembered they burned my hut down.

author: sandor clegane
content: Who were "they"?

author: dying man
content: I stopped asking a while ago.

author: sandor clegane
content: That's not gonna get better.

author: dying man
content: Doesn't seem so.

author: sandor clegane
content: A bad way to go. Haven't you had enough?

author: dying man
content: Of what? I know. Time to go. Take matters into my own hands. The thought has occurred to me.

author: arya stark
content: So why go on?

author: dying man
content: Habit.

author: arya stark
content: Nothing could be worse than this.

author: dying man
content: Maybe nothing is worse than this.

author: arya stark
content: Nothing isn't better or worse than anything. Nothing is just nothing.

author: dying man
content: Who are you?

author: arya stark
content: My name is Arya. Arya Stark.

author: dying man
content: You her father?

author: sandor clegane
content: Her captor. Bringing her to her aunt for ransom.

author: dying man

Once they step into his light, they will see the lie for what it was-- a trick that lead them to the truth. A pinch of this powder in a bonfire will send a flaming column screaming towards the sky. And this one creates a black smoke that will make the bravest man piss himself with fear. And a drop of this in any man's wine will drive him wild with lust.
