author: petyr baelish
content: Let me worry about Aunt Lysa.

author: sansa stark
content: I was trying to remember what everything looked like. I'll never see it again.

author: petyr baelish
content: A lot can happen between now and never. If you want to build a better home, first you must demolish the old one.

author: sansa stark
content: Why did you really kill Joffrey? Tell me why.

author: petyr baelish
content: I loved your mother more than you could ever know. Given the opportunity, what do we do to those who've hurt the ones we love? In a better world, one where love could overcome strength and duty, you might have been my child. But we don't live in that world.

author: petyr baelish
content: You're more beautiful than she ever was.

author: sansa stark
content: Lord Baelish...

author: petyr baelish
content: Call me Petyr.

author: sansa stark
content: You wanted to see me, Aunt Lysa?

author: lysa
content: Come here, Sansa.

author: lysa
content: Do you know how far the fall is?

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: lysa
content: Neither do I, precisely. Hundreds of feet. It's fascinating what happens to bodies when they hit the rocks from such a height. The impact breaks them right apart. Like eggs dropped on the floor. Sometimes pieces remain intact. You'll find the head sitting on its own. Every hair in place. Blue eyes staring at nothing. I know what you did.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm so sorry, Aunt Lysa. I never should have hit Robin, I know it. I promise it won't happen-

author: lysa
content: Don't be coy with me, you little whore. You kissed him. You kissed Petyr.

author: sansa stark
content: I didn't. You don't understand.

author: lysa
content: I saw you! You can't lie to me because I saw it with my own eyes.

author: sansa stark
content: He kissed me. I pulled away.

author: lysa
content: Liar! Whore! He is mine!

author: sansa stark
content: Please!

author: lysa
content: My father, my husband, my sister, they all stood between us and now they're all dead. That's what happens to people who stand between Petyr and me. Look down! Look down! Look down! Look down!

author: petyr baelish
content: Lysa! Let her go.

author: lysa
content: You want her? This empty-headed child?

author: petyr baelish
content: Let her go.

author: lysa
content: She's just like her mother. She'll never love you. I lied for you. I killed for you. Why did you bring her here? Why?

author: petyr baelish
content: I'll send her away. I swear on my life. I swear to all the gods. Let her go, Lysa.

author: petyr baelish
content: Oh, my sweet wife. My sweet, silly wife.

author: petyr baelish
content: I have only loved one woman... only one, my entire life. Your sister.

author: man
content: Here we are.

author: man
content: The Rains of Castamere!

author: moles town whore
content: You fucking dick! Same wrong guess every fucking time. Listen, ya cunt.

author: man
content: Oh, The Bear and the Maiden Fair!

author: moles town whore
content: There's a man with an ear. Too bad you've got a hangnail for a cock. First time I saw you with your britches down, I thought you were a eunuch! You seen it girls. Like a baby snail peekin' out of his shell. *laughs and walks toward Gilly* *to Gilly* Your baby was crying this morning. It waked me up. You hear me?

author: gilly
content: Yes.

author: moles town whore
content: Well, what are you going to say?

author: gilly
content: I'm sorry it woke you up.

author: moles town whore
content: I don't care if you're sorry. Keep that baby quiet, or I will.

author: gilly
content: Don't you ever touch him.

author: moles town whore
content: Hehehe, little Wildling bitch. You shouldo ve stayed with your own kind. *an owl hoots in the distance* Are you listening to me?

author: gilly
content: Shut your mouth.

author: moles town whore
content: What? It's just an owl you dumb bitch.

author: gilly
content: No it's not.

author: sam
content: I should never have left her there.

author: jon snow
content: You couldn't have known.

author: sam
content: Of course I couldo ve known. They were raiding the villages close by.

author: grenn
content: And we just cower in here while they slaughter our brothers?

author: ed
content: Our brothers had orders to stay at Castle Black.

author: grenn
content: Oh, so it's alright then?! Black Jack and Kegs and Mully chopped to pieces 'cause they broke the rules?!

author: ed
content: I didn't say it was alright! I'm sayin' they shouldn't have been there.

author: grenn
content: We pledged to guard the realms of men.

author: sam
content: She's dead because of me.

author: grenn
content: We can't even guard Mole's Town.

author: jon snow
content: We can't go after them, you know that. That's what they want.

author: sam
content: Little Same. As if I'd cut their throats myself.

author: pyp
content: Maybe she managed to hide herself. I thought one of you was dead, you went North with Mormont and no one came back. Not for ages. But then you did.

author: ed
content: She survived Craster and he was the worst shit I've ever met. She survived the long march to the wall. She survived a white walker for fuck's sake. She might've got out.

author: sam
content: She might have.

author: jon snow
content: If they hit Mole's Town, then we're next. Mance's army must be close.

author: ed
content: A hundred thousand.

author: grenn
content: And there's what, 5 of us left.

author: ed
content: If you're counting Black Jack, Kegs, and Mully. A hundred and two.

author: pyp
content: How do a hundred and two men stop a thousand?

author: ed
content: Whoever dies last, be a good lad and burn the rest of us. Once I'm done with this world, I don't want to come back.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You think he was spying on you?

author: missandei
content: No, not spying.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Dothraki think outsiders are ridiculous taking shame in the naked body. They make love under the stars for the whole Khalasar to see.

author: missandei
content: Yes your grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But you are not Dothraki.

author: missandei
content: No.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, I don't see why it matters. Grey worm isn't interested, none of the unsullied care what's under our clothes.

author: missandei
content: He was interested.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What?

author: missandei
content: I believe he was interested.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: When the slavers castrate the boys, do they take all of it?

author: missandei
content: All of it?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The...the pillar an the stones.

author: missandei
content: I don't know, your grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Haven't you ever wondered?

author: missandei
content: Yes, your grace.

author: grey worm
content: Missandei. *in Valyrian* I have come to apologize.

author: missandei
content: in Valyrian* You don't need to apologize.

author: grey worm
content: in Valyrian* I hope I didn't frighten you.

author: missandei
content: in Valyrian* No.

author: grey worm
content: The lessons you give I in Common tongue, these are precious to I.

author: missandei
content: To me.

author: grey worm
content: To me.

author: missandei
content: I don't remember teaching you the word precious.

author: grey worm
content: Jorah the Andal, he teaches I...he teaches me this word.

author: missandei
content: Do you remember the name you were given at birth?

author: grey worm
content: I remember nothing. Only unsullied.

author: missandei
content: When they cut you, do you remember that?

author: missandei
content: I'm sorry. I'm sorry they did that to you.

author: grey worm
content: Why? Why sorry?

author: missandei
content: It's a terrible thing to do to a boy.

author: grey worm
content: approaches Missandei* If the masters never cut me, I am never unsullied. I never stand in the Plaza of Pride when Daenerys Stormborn orders us to kill the masters. I never am chosen to lead the unsullied. I never meet Missandei from the Island of Naath. I am sorry I...for today. I am sorry.

author: missandei
content: in Valyrian* Grey Worm.

author: missandei
content: in Valyrian* I'm glad you saw me.

author: grey worm
content: in Valyrian* So am I.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Bracken. Mmm, strong. As long as they're in the see. But when you take them out of the water, no bones. They collapse under their proud weight and slum into a heap of nothing. You'd think they'd know that. Unfortunately they're not very bright. What do you tell them?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm Theon Greyjoy, son of Balon, heir to the Iron Islands.

author: ramsay bolton
content: And what are you really?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm Reek.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Are you sure? You do look very much like a lord. Formidable, proud.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Until when?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Always. Forever.

author: ramsay bolton
content: That's right. Until you're rotting in the ground. Remember what you are and what you're not. Bring me Lord Kenning.

author: guard
content: to Theon* No closer. Who are you?

author: ralf
content: I'm Kenning, commander of this garrison. And you say you're Theon Greyjoy?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes.

author: ralf
content: And why should I believe that?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I was born on Pike to Balon Greyjoy. His third and last-living son. I am your prince. I swear it by the drowned god. What is dead may never die.

author: everyone
content: What is dead may never die.

author: ralf
content: And if you were my prince, why are you marching with a Bolton army?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Lord Bolton took me captive after Winterfell. He sent me to treat with you in good faith as your fellow Ironborn.

author: ralf
content: And what does Lord Bolton want?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You are fading from sickness. You are badly outnumbered and you're hundreds of miles from the sea. Lord Bolton implores you to protect your men and abandon this fortress you can no longer hold. Do this and he will be just and fair with you as he is being with me. The Boltons will give you safe passage to the stony shore.

author: ralf
content: He wants us to surrender?

author: theon greyjoy
content: My own father, your king, surrendered years ago to Robert Baratheon. I watched him bend the knee. There was no shame there. He fought with honor, as did you.

author: ralf
content: shame fought with honor.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm sorry, I didn't hear...

author: ralf
content: No shame fought with honor. Only a whipped dog would speak this way. Or a woman. Are you a woman boy?

author: theon greyjoy
content: scared* You don't know.

author: ralf
content: The Ironborn will not surrender.

author: theon greyjoy
content: whispering* Reek. Reek.

author: ralf
content: You go tell your master that, Theon Greyjoy. Or whoever the fuck you are. What in the hell are you muttering?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Reek.

author: man
content: If we yield, we live? Is that what it says on this paper here?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes. Have your men raise the white flag and open the gates. You're going home.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You didn't really think I'd let them go did you? It's falling out of fashion. Fileting. Sad, but true. Traditions are important. Where are we without our history, eh?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes m'lord. Will we go home now?

author: ramsay bolton
content: I believe we will. To our new home.

author: petyr
content: A great-grandfather from Braavos, yes. I suppose all of our ancestors came from somewhere else originally.

author: lord royce
content: Our forebearers settled the Vale thousands of years ago. We've fought off invaders ever since.

author: petyr
content: The beauty of the Vale is matched only by the nobility of its great families. Lady Arryn often told me that you were her rock, Lord Royce.

author: lord royce
content: She told me nothing about you, Baelish. But I didn't need to hear from her. Moneylender. Whoremonger. You've been licking Tywin Lannister's boots so long, it's a wonder your tongue's not black.

author: petyr
content: My lord...

author: lord royce
content: And when Jon Arryn named you Master of Coin, no one cared. Always been a grubby job. Why not let a grubby man do it? But when I heard you were lurking here, fawning over the Lady Arryn...

author: petyr
content: Lady Arryn invited me. She and I have been close since childhood.

author: lady anya
content: Yes, we all know how close you were. Lady Arryn's predilections were her own affair. Her death is our affair.

author: petyr
content: Of course. Her suicide shattered us all.

author: lady anya
content: She was an odd fish. Everyone knew that. But suicide? She adored that boy of hers. I don't see her abandoning him. Not by choice.

author: lord royce
content: Strange that within days of your arrival, you've married Lady Arryn and she's fallen through the Moon Door.

author: petyr
content: She was always prone to melancholy. My lady wasn't meant for a world as brutal as ours.

author: lord royce
content: We were told there was a witness. A girl.

author: lady anya
content: A niece of yours, I believe.

author: petyr
content: A girl with no learning and scattered wits. I assure you, she would be of no help.

author: lord royce
content: We'd like to speak with her.

author: petyr
content: Let me fetch her.

author: lady anya
content: No need. We prefer to hear her testimony unadulterated.

author: lady anya
content: Come closer, child. You have nothing to fear from us or him. Lord Baelish here is your uncle? Your name is Alayne? Perhaps you would feel more comfortable if Lord Baelish left the room.

author: petyr
content: My lady...

author: lady anya
content: I wasn't asking you.

author: sansa stark
content: He can stay.

author: lord royce
content: Speak up, girl, you're not a damn kitchen mouse. Tell us what you saw.

author: sansa stark
content: to Petyr* I'm sorry, Lord Baelish. I have to tell the truth. *to the council* I'll tell you everything.

author: lady anya
content: Please, Alayne, leave nothing out.

author: sansa stark
content: My name is not Alayne. It's Sansa Stark, eldest daughter of Lord Eddard Stark. Lord Royce, we met when you came to Winterfell. You were escorting your son Ser Waymar to the Wall.

author: lord royce
content: Sansa Stark? You tell lies right to my face, you little worm?

author: sansa stark
content: Lord Baelish has told many lies. All to protect me. Since my father was executed, I have been a hostage in King's Landing. A plaything for Joffrey to torture or Queen Cersei to torment. They beat me, they humiliated me, they married me to the Imp. I had no friends in King's Landing...except one. He saved me. Smuggled me away when he had the chance. He knew I'd be safe here in the Eyrie with my own blood, my Aunt Lysa. The Lannisters have friends everywhere. Even the Vale. He made me swear not to tell anyone my true name.

author: ser vance
content: Your secret is safe with us, my lady.

author: lord royce
content: Your father grew up right here in these halls. We hunted together many times. He was a fine man.

author: lady anya
content: Tell us what happened to your aunt, Sansa.

author: sansa stark
content: You knew her well, my lords, my lady. You knew she was a troubled woman. She always loved Lord Baelish. She told me herself. From the moment he arrived at the gates of Riverrun, a boy of eight carrying everything he owned in a little sack. She confessed to me she never loved Lord Arryn. She did as her father commanded, as so many of us have. When the gods finally allowed her to be with Lord Baelish, she was so happy. For a time. My aunt was a jealous lady. She was terrified that Lord Baelish didn't love her anymore. That he would abandon her for a younger woman. And then...one day she saw him kiss me.

author: lord royce
content: Lady Sansa.

author: sansa stark
content: It was a peck on the cheek, Lord Royce, nothing more. Lord Baelish is my uncle now, in truth, by marriage. He's always been so kind to me. I was so happy to be here, to be free. All because of him. But my aunt turned on me. She cursed me. Called me a whore. Promised to throw me through the Moon Door. When Lord Baelish tried to calm her, she struck him. She said she didn't want to live anymore. She stood on the edge of that Moon Door. He tried to reason with her. Promised her she was the only one he had ever loved, but she stepped through those doors and she was...*begins sobbing*

author: lady anya
content: Shh. Shh, it's not your fault, sweet girl. It's not your fault.

author: lord royce
content: You could see it in the way she raised that boy. Feeding him from her own teats when he was 10 years old.

author: lady anya
content: Lord Royce! This is hardly the time.

author: lord royce
content: Apologies, my lady. And to you as well, Baelish. We treated you a bit harshly.

author: petyr
content: You want justice, Lord Royce. I can hardly complain about that. I want the same.

author: lady anya
content: Not much justice to be meted out in suicide, is there?

author: petyr
content: For Lysa, no. But for her son? Only 20 years ago, the knights of the Vale rode behind Jon Arryn, Ned Stark, Robert Baratheon. They fought together to overcome the Mad King. And since then, Arryn and Royce, Corbray, Waynwood, all the great houses of the Vale watched from the corner. A timid boy at a tavern brawl.

author: lord royce
content: Are you questioning our courage?

author: petyr
content: I want to know which side you're on. Do you support the Lannisters, the house that executed your friend Ned Stark?

author: lord royce
content: Of course we don't support the damn Lannisters.

author: petyr
content: No? Catelyn Stark begged her sister for support and Lysa refused. By staying out of the fray, you've allowed Tywin Lannister to destroy his rivals on every compass point. Who stands against him now?

author: lady anya
content: Who would you have us back, Lord Baelish? Robb Stark is dead.

author: petyr
content: I'd have you back Robin Arryn, Lord of the Vale.

author: lady anya
content: Robin Arryn is a sickly little boy.

author: petyr
content: And sickly little boys sometimes become powerful men.

author: lady anya
content: More often they die young.

author: petyr
content: I adored Lysa with all my heart. But she loved her son so much, she became overprotective. He needs to learn how to swing a sword. How to ride a horse.

author: lord royce
content: Aye, it's time.

author: petyr
content: Yes, it's time. Time for him to tour the Vale, to visit all the castles in his domain. Time for Robin to leave the nest.

author: boy
content: Ser Barristan.

author: ser barristan
content: Yes? Who sent you?

author: ser jorah
content: Ser Barristan.

author: ser barristan
content: Ser Jorah.

author: ser jorah
content: Have I forgotten a council meeting?

author: ser barristan
content: No.

author: ser jorah
content: What's this?

author: ser barristan
content: A royal pardon signed by Robert Baratheon. You spied on her.

author: ser jorah
content: Who gave you this?

author: ser barristan
content: Does it matter?

author: ser jorah
content: Have you told her?

author: ser barristan
content: I wanted to tell you first, man-to-man rather than go behind your back.

author: ser jorah
content: Let me speak with her in private.

author: ser barristan
content: You'll never be alone with her again.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why did the usurper pardon you?

author: ser jorah
content: If we could speak alone.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No, speak to me here. Explain it to me.

author: ser jorah
content: Who do you think sent this to Meereen? Who profits? This is the work of Tywin Lannister. He wants to divide us. If we're fighting each other, we're not fighting him.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The pardon was signed the year we met. Why were you pardoned? Unless you're saying this document was forged.

author: ser jorah
content: It is not forged.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why, then?

author: ser jorah
content: I sent letters to Varys, the spymaster of King's Landing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What was the content of these letters?

author: ser jorah
content: Information.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What information?

author: ser jorah
content: When you and Viserys arrived in Pentos. His plan to marry you to Khal Drogo. When you were married. When your brother died.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You told him I was carrying Drogo's child?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Yes or no?

author: ser jorah
content: Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't call me that. Did you tell him I was carrying Drogo's child?

author: ser jorah
content: Yes.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That wine merchant tried to poison me because of your information.

author: ser jorah
content: I stopped you from drinking his wine.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Because you knew it was poisoned.

author: ser jorah
content: I suspected.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You betrayed me from the first.

author: ser jorah
content: Forgive me. I never meant...please, Khaleesi, forgive me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You sold my secrets to the man who killed my father and stole my brother's throne...

author: ser jorah
content: I have protected you. Fought for you. Killed for you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: and you want me to forgive you?

author: ser jorah
content: I have loved you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Love? Love? How can you say that to me? Any other man, and I would have you executed. But you, I do not want you in my city dead or alive. Go back to your masters in King's Landing. Collect your pardon if you can.

author: ser jorah
content: Daenerys, please.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't ever presume to touch me again or speak my name. You have until dusk to collect your things and leave this city. If you're found in Meereen past break of day, I'll have your head thrown into Slaver's Bay. Go. Now.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Moat Cailin is yours, Father.

author: lord bolton
content: Walk with me. Has there been any word from Locke?

author: ramsay bolton
content: No.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Unimportant. A cripple, a young boy. None of the northern lords have seen them. Dead most likely. Most of the Ironborn have fled the North. Now more will follow, thanks to you. Tell me what you see.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Moors, fields, hills.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tell me what you see.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Nothing.

author: roose
content: Not nothing. The North. Ride 700 miles that way, you're still in the North. 400 miles that way. 300 miles that way. The North is larger than the other six kingdoms combined. And I am the Warden of the North. The North is mine. Now tell me, what is your name?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Ramsay Snow.

author: roose
content: No, not Ramsay Snow. *hands Ramsay a scroll* Open it. From this day until your last day, you are Ramsay Bolton, son of Roose Bolton, Warden of the North.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You honor me. I swear I will uphold your name and your tradition. I will be worthy of you, Father, I promise.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Come, Reek, I'll be needing a bath.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes?

author: petyr
content: First time I saw you, you were just a child. A girl from the North come to the capital for the first time. Not a child any longer. Why did you help me?

author: sansa stark
content: They would have thrown you through the Moon Door if they found you guilty.

author: petyr
content: That's not an answer.

author: sansa stark
content: If they'd have executed you, what would they have done with me?

author: petyr
content: I don't know.

author: sansa stark
content: Neither do I.

author: petyr
content: Better to gamble on the man you know than the strangers you don't? And you think you know me?

author: sansa stark
content: I know what you want.

author: petyr
content: Do you?

author: sandor clegane
content: I thought it'd make me happy, but it doesn't. Not really. Nothing makes you happy.

author: arya stark
content: Lots of things make me happy.

author: sandor clegane
content: Like what?

author: arya stark
content: Killing Polliver, killing Rorge.

author: sandor clegane
content: So you're sad because you didn't get to kill Joffrey yourself. Is that it?

author: arya stark
content: At least I could have been there to watch. I wanted to see the look in his eyes when he knew it was over.

author: sandor clegane
content: Aye, nothing in the world beats that look.

author: arya stark
content: You protected him for most of his life. You think you could have saved him?

author: sandor clegane
content: I wasn't the damn wine taster. Little shit deserved to die, but poison...poison's a woman's weapon. Men kill with steel.

author: arya stark
content: That's your stupid pride talking. It's why you'll never be a great killer. I'd have killed Joffrey with a chicken bone if I had to.

author: sandor clegane
content: laughs* I'd pay good money to see that. *grunts and rubs his neck*

author: arya stark
content: You should have let me burn it.

author: sandor clegane
content: It's a fleabite.

author: arya stark
content: That fleabite's got you walking a lot slower than you used to.

author: sandor clegane
content: Well, we won't have to walk too much further.

author: arya stark
content: You really think my aunt will pay for me?

author: sandor clegane
content: Aye, she'll pay.

author: arya stark
content: I've never even met her.

author: sandor clegane
content: Doesn't matter. You're her blood. Family, honor, all that horseshit. It's all you lords and ladies ever talk about.

author: arya stark
content: I'm not a lady.

author: guard
content: Who would pass the Bloody Gate?

author: sandor clegane
content: The bloody Hound, Sandor Clegane. And his...traveling companion Arya Stark, niece of your lady Lysa Arryn.

author: guard
content: Then I offer my condolences. Lady Arryn died. Three days ago.

author: robin
content: I've never left home before, Uncle Petyr. I'm afraid to leave.

author: petyr
content: You shouldn't be.

author: robin
content: The Lord of the Vale belongs in the Eyrie, Mother said. She said it's not safe outside.

author: petyr
content: It wasn't safe for her inside. People die at their dinner tables. They die in their beds. They die squatting over their chamber pots. Everybody dies sooner or later. Don't worry about your death. Worry about your life. Take charge of your life for as long as it lasts. That is what it means to be Lord of the Vale.

author: sansa stark
content: Shall we go?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Wine always helps. I thank you for it. Trial by combat. Deciding a man's guilt or innocence in the eyes of the gods by having two other men hack each other to pieces. Tells you something about the gods. How much longer?

author: jaime lannister
content: Soon.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you think Oberyn has a chance? The Red Viper of Dorne. You don't get a name like that unless you're deadly, right?

author: jaime lannister
content: I've never seen him fight.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, he's going to die. I'm going to die.

author: jaime lannister
content: Oberyn believes in himself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's putting it mildly. What's the punishment for regicide? Drawing and quartering? Hanging? Breaking at the wheel?

author: jaime lannister
content: Beheading.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Seems rather ordinary. And he was my nephew as well, so what is that? Fratricide is brothers. Filicide is sons. Nepoticide. That's the one. Matricide, patricide, infanticide, suicide. There's no kind of killing that doesn't have its own word.

author: jaime lannister
content: Cousins.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cousins, you're right. There is no word for cousin killing. Well done. Do you remember cousin Orson? Orson Lannister?

author: jaime lannister
content: Of course. Wet-nurse dropped him on his head. Left him simple.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Simple? Used to sit all day in the garden. Crushing beetles with a rock.

author: together
content: Khuu! Khuu! Khuu!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Nothing made him happier.

author: jaime lannister
content: Nothing made you happier. You'd think being tormented from birth would have given you some affinity for the afflicted.

author: tyrion lannister
content: On the contrary. Laughing at another person's misery was the only thing that made me feel like everyone else.

author: jaime lannister
content: The joke wore thin, though.

author: tyrion lannister
content: For you. You drifted away.

author: jaime lannister
content: I had other interests.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, other interests. But I stayed with Orson.

author: jaime lannister
content: Why?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I was curious. Why was he smashing all those beetles? What did he get out of it? First thing I did was ask him. "Orson, why are you smashing all those beetles?" He gave me an answer. "Smash the beetles. Smash 'em. Khuu! Khuu! Khuu!" I wasn't deterred. I was the smartest person I knew. Certainly I had the wherewithal to unravel the mysteries that lay at the heart of a moron. So I went to Maester Volarik's library.

author: jaime lannister
content: Volarik. Tried to touch me once.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Turns out, far too much has been written about great men and not nearly enough about morons. Doesn't seem right. In any case, I found nothing that illuminated the nature of Orson's affliction or the reason behind his relentless beetle slaughter. So I went back to the source. I may not have been able to speak with Orson, but I could observe him, watch him the way men watch animals to come to a deeper understanding of their behavior. *picks up a beetle* And as I watched, I became more and more sure of it. There was something happening there. His face was like the page of a book written in a language I didn't understand. But he wasn't mindless. He had his reasons. And I became possessed with knowing what they were. I began to spend inordinate amounts of time watching him. I would eat my lunch in the garden, chewing my mutton to the music of "khuu, khuu, khuu". And when I wasn't watching him, I was thinking about him. Father droned on about the family legacy and I thought about Orson's beetles. I read the histories of Targaryen conquests. Did I hear dragon wings? No. I heard "khuu, khuu, khuu" and I still couldn't figure out why he was doing it. And I had to know, because it was horrible that all these beetles should be dying for no reason.

author: jaime lannister
content: Every day around the world, men, women, and children are murdered by the score. Who gives a dusty fuck about a bunch of beetles?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know, I know. But still, it filled me with dread. Piles and piles of them, years and years of them. How many countless living crawling things smashed and dried out and returned to the dirt? In my dreams I found myself standing on a beach made of beetle husks stretching as far as the eye could see. I woke up crying, weeping for their shattered little bodies. I tried to stop Orson once.

author: jaime lannister
content: He was twice your size.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He just pushed me aside with a "khuu" and kept on smashing. Every day until that mule kicked him in the chest and killed him. *puts the beetle back on the ground* So what do you think? Why did he do it? What was it all about?

author: jaime lannister
content: I don't know.

author: jaime lannister
content: Good luck today.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Looks like very light armor.

author: oberyn martell
content: I like to move around.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You could at least wear a helmet. You shouldn't drink before a fight.

author: oberyn martell
content: You learn this during your years in the fighting pits? I always drink before a fight.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It could get you killed. It could get me killed.

author: oberyn martell
content: Today is not the day I die.

author: ellaria
content: You're going to fight that?

author: oberyn martell
content: I'm going to kill that.

author: ellaria
content: He is the biggest man I've ever seen.

author: oberyn martell
content: Size does not matter when you are flat on your back.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank the gods.

author: pycell
content: In the sight of gods and men, we gather to ascertain the guilt or innocence of this...man Tyrion Lannister. May the Mother grant them mercy. May the Father give them such justice as they deserve. And may the Warrior guide the hand of our champion...

author: ellaria
content: Don't leave me alone in this world.

author: oberyn martell
content: Never.

author: oberyn martell
content: Have they told you who I am?

author: mountain
content: Some dead man.

author: oberyn martell
content: I am the brother of Elia Martell. Do you know why I have come all the way to this stinking shit-pile of a city? For you.

author: oberyn martell
content: I'm going to hear you confess before you die. You raped my sister. You murdered her. You killed her children. Say it now and we can make this quick.

author: oberyn martell
content: Say it. You raped her. You murdered her. You killed her children.

author: oberyn martell
content: You raped her! You murdered her! You killed her children!

author: oberyn martell
content: You raped her! You murdered her!

author: oberyn martell
content: You killed her children!

author: oberyn martell
content: Wait. Are you dying? No, no, no. You can't die yet. You haven't confessed. Say it. Say her name. Elia Martell. You raped her. You killed her children. Elia Martell. Who gave you the order? Who gave you the order?! Say her name! You raped her! You murdered her! You killed her children. Say it. Say her name. Say it!

author: mountain
content: Elia Martell. I killed her children. Then I raped her. Then I smashed her head in like this!

author: tywin lannister
content: standing up* The gods have made their will known. Tyrion Lannister, in the name of King Tommen of the House Baratheon, First of His Name, you are hereby sentenced to death.

author: sam
content: What was she like?

author: jon snow
content: She...she had red hair.

author: sam
content: Oh? How big were her feet?

author: jon snow
content: Well what do you want me to say?

author: sam
content: I want you to tell me what it was like to have someone. To be with someone. To love someone and have them love you back. We're all gonna die a lot sooner than I'd planned. You're the closest I'll ever get to know it.

author: jon snow
content: So you and Gilly never-

author: sam
content: No...she just had a baby! ...and she never offered.

author: jon snow
content: But if she had, you wouldo ve? You'd have broken your vows?

author: sam
content: The interesting thing is, our vows never specifically forbid intimate relations with women.

author: jon snow
content: What?

author: sam
content: I shall take no wife" yes, that's in there, there's no denying that. "I shall father no children" it's very specific. But what our vows have to say about other...activities...is open to interpretation.

author: jon snow
content: I don't think Ser Alliser cares much for interpretation.

author: sam
content: Anyway, there's nothing for him to interpret. We didn't. So what's it like?

author: jon snow
content: It's...there's this person, this whole other person. And you're wrapped up in them and they're wrapped up in you and...you...for a little...for a little while you're more than just you, you're...well I don't know, I'm not a bleedin' poet!

author: sam
content: No, you're really not.

author: jon snow
content: And what did I get for it? An arrow six inches from my heart.

author: sam
content: There'll be arrows for all of us soon I imagine.

author: jon snow
content: There will.

author: sam
content: They've already done the worst thing to me they could ever do.

author: jon snow
content: Go get some sleep, Sam. I'll take this watch.

author: tormund
content: Did I ever tell you about her? My Sheila?

author: ygritte
content: Yes.

author: tormund
content: Oh that was a night to remember. Of course, I'd had a good bit to drink *laughs* the fangs were sharp, but she knew how to use them. And she was nice and soft down below. No, she was no ordinary beast. Many's the man who--

author: ygritte
content: I know you never fucked a bear. You know you never fucked a bear. Right now I don't wanna think about the bear you never fucked. Right now all I want to think about is each one of these arrows finding its way into a Crow's heart.

author: tormund
content: We could be waiting here a while.

author: ygritte
content: Good. The longer we wait, the more arrows I'll have. When they came up here, to our land, and put up a big wall and said it was their's. Then they started hunting us down. But this time, we're the one's doing the hunting.

author: styr
content: You've got a lot to say about killing. Even more words than arrows.

author: ygritte
content: Back in those villages I killed just as many of them as you did. More, I reckon.

author: styr
content: Yes. But none of those were your Crow lover.

author: ygritte
content: I probably killed him already.

author: styr
content: So you've said.

author: ygritte
content: And if not. The only thing left of him is gonna be his fun-bits hanging around me neck.

author: styr
content: And more words. Know what I think you do when you see him? Serve him up a nice juicy slice of ginger minge.

author: ygritte
content: What, you been thinkin' about that ginger minge? Wondering what it tastes like?

author: styr
content: Maybe I have.

author: ygritte
content: Jon Snow is mine. *shouting* Anyone else tries to kill him, I'll have an arrow for them. *to Styr* And not one of your bald friends is fast enough to stop me.

author: aemon
content: And what is it that couldn't wait until morning, Tarly?

author: sam
content: Maester Aemon. How did you know-

author: aemon
content: That it was you? Who else but Samwell Tarly would be wasting candles to read in the middle of the night?

author: sam
content: Let me help you.

author: aemon
content: Oh, no need. I know my way around this library better than any other place in Castle Black. Thousands of books and no eyes to read them. Old age is a wonderful source of ironies if nothing else. But you didn't answer my question, what are you reading?

author: sam
content: Maester Faull

author: aemon
content: Ah, the Wildlings. I can assure you that the closest Maester Faull ever got to a Wildling was this very library.

author: sam
content: But what he says about what they do...it's all true. It's exactly what the survivors of their raids report.

author: aemon
content: Yes. Imagine the stories Wildlings tell about us! Love is the death of duty. I told that to your friend Jon Snow once. He didn't listen and neither did you. That's why you abandoned your watch atop the wall to come here and read about the things that may have happened to the girl you love.

author: sam
content: I don't love her.

author: aemon
content: Yes you do.

author: sam
content: No.

author: aemon
content: Yes you do! I heard it in your voice when you first brought her to me. I remember how it sounds! I was in love once.

author: sam
content: You were?

author: aemon
content: You can imagine all manner of horrors befalling that poor girl and her child, is it so difficult to imagine that an old person was once, more or less, like you?

author: sam
content: I'm sorry Maester, I didn't mean it like that.

author: aemon
content: You know who I was before I came here? What I couldo ve been if I'd only said the word? Of course you do. I met many girls when I was Aemon Targaryen. A future king always does. Some of them were quite forward in their attempts to win my affections. One of them succeeded. I was very young.

author: sam
content: Who was she?

author: aemon
content: Ah ha. I could tell you everything about her. Who she was. How we met. The color of her eyes and the shape of her nose. I can see her right in front of me. She's more real than you are. We could spend all night trading tales of lost love. Nothing makes the past a sweeter place to visit than the prospect of imminent death. Go to bed Tarly.

author: pyp
content: I'm sorry, I can't open the gate for nobody. It's orders!

author: gilly
content: They killed everyone! Everyone but me and my baby. And they're out there. I saw them on the way here, they may have seen me, they may have followed me please!

author: pyp
content: I'm sorry, I can't.

author: gilly
content: If they find the boy, you don't know what they'll do.

author: sam
content: Pyp! Open the gate.

author: pyp
content: I can't.

author: gilly
content: Sam, is that you?!

author: sam
content: Yes!

author: pyp
content: Thorne gave me strict orders to not open the gate.

author: sam
content: Oh, Pyp. Open the fucking gate!

author: pyp
content: I've never heard you curse before.

author: sam
content: Yes, well, best get used to it.

author: sam
content: Are you alright? Shh, you're alright. Yeah, of course you are my brave little fella.

author: gilly
content: It was horrible.

author: sam
content: I'm so so sorry. I didn't know until I got back.

author: gilly
content: Don't let them send me away, Sam.

author: sam
content: Never.

author: gilly
content: I know there's no women allowed.

author: sam
content: Anyone who tries to throw you out will be having words with me. From now on, wherever you go, I go too.

author: alliser
content: Get ready!

author: thenn warg
content: It's time.

author: janos
content: Pick up the pace!

author: jon snow
content: There we go, boys. That's one. There's two. Come on, let's get the next lot. That's the last of the oil, Ser Alliser.

author: alliser
content: A hundred thousand you say?

author: jon snow
content: Yes sir.

author: alliser
content: You can say it if you like. We shouldo ve sealed the tunnel while we had the chance like you suggested.

author: jon snow
content: It was a difficult decision either way, Ser.

author: alliser
content: Do you know what leadership means, Lord Snow? It means that the person in charge gets second-guessed by every clever little twat with a mouth. But if he starts second-guessing himself, that's the end. For him. For the clever little twats. For everyone. This is not the end. Not for us. Not if you lot do your duty for however long it takes to beat them back. And then you get to go on hating me and I get to go on wishing your Wildling whore had finished the job.

author: sam
content: You'll be safe down here. I'll check on you as soon as I can.

author: gilly
content: You're leaving me again?

author: sam
content: I'm not leaving you!

author: gilly
content: You're going up there and we're staying down here. That's leaving. You said from now on we'd stay together.

author: sam
content: I...I didn't mean in the same room.

author: gilly
content: What are you going to do out there?

author: sam
content: Help my brothers.

author: gilly
content: How?! You going to fight the Free Folk when they come? They'll kill you. In Molestown they killed everyone.

author: sam
content: I can't just hide here with you while they're fighting out there.

author: gilly
content: Why not? You won't matter up there, you will down here.

author: sam
content: Look. I am a man of the Night's Watch, Gilly. I made a promise to defend The Wall and I have to keep it, because that's what men do.

author: gilly
content: Promise me you won't die.

author: sam
content: I promise you I won't die.

author: sam
content: There's a lot more Wildlings on the other side of the wall than this side. We've got us some weapons and things. This is the perfect place for us to be.

author: pyp
content: I've never thrown a spear before. I've never held a sword with a proper edge. There's no place for me to be. You're not afraid?

author: sam
content: Of course I'm afraid, there's a band of Wildlings coming to kill us.

author: pyp
content: Well if you're afraid of a band of Wildlings, how in seven hells did you manage to kill a White Walker?

author: sam
content: I didn't know I was going to kill it, but I had to do something I didn't have any choice, he was going to kill Gilly and take the baby. If someone had asked me my name right then, I wouldn't have known. I wasn't Samwell Tarly anymore. I wasn't a Steward in the Night's Watch or son of Randyll Tarly or any of that. I was nothing at all. And when you're nothing at all, there's no more reason to be afraid.

author: pyp
content: But you're afraid now?

author: sam
content: Yes, well, I'm not nothing anymore.

author: ygritte
content: Most of their men are up top. Didn't count more than twenty down there. Leftovers. They've got a little fat one and a little bony one manning the front.

author: styr
content: How high are the walls?

author: ygritte
content: Well, we'll be up and over before they know what's happened.

author: tormund
content: Let's kill some Crows!

author: tormund
content: yells* Come on! *puts out the fire*

author: alliser
content: Archers knock, everyone else hold.

author: alliser
content: I said knock and hold you cunts! Does knock mean draw?!

author: nights watch
content: No Ser!

author: alliser
content: Does fucking hold mean fucking drop?!

author: alliser
content: You all plan to die here tonight?

author: alliser
content: That's very good to hear. Draw!

author: member
content: Help, down below.

author: janos
content: They're attacking the southern gates!

author: alliser
content: Now?

author: janos
content: Now!

author: alliser
content: I'm going down then. Brother Slynt, you have The Wall.

author: janos
content: What?!

author: alliser
content: What are you fucking waiting for, loose!

author: janos
content: You heard the man. Loose!

author: tormund
content: You, over there.

author: sam
content: Did you get one?

author: pyp
content: No. Ah shit, Pyp. Shit. Sam.

author: sam
content: Yeah?

author: pyp
content: I think we're gonna die.

author: sam
content: If you keep missing we will.

author: alliser
content: Brothers! A hundred generations have defended this castle. We've never fallen before. She will not fall tongiht. Those are Things at our walls. They eat the flesh of the men they kill. Do you want to fill the belly of a Thing tonight?

author: nights watch
content: No!

author: alliser
content: Tonight we fight. And when the sun rises I promise you, Castle Black will stand.

author: alliser
content: The Night's Watch will stand.

author: alliser
content: With me now! Now, with me!

author: janos
content: No discipline. No training. Gang of thieves, that's all this is. I commanded the city watch of King's Landing. Those men obeyed orders.

author: jon snow
content: We can't just let them attack the gate!

author: janos
content: The bars of those gates are four inches of cold, rolled steel.

author: jon snow
content: Those are giants riding mammoths down there. Do you think your cold, rolled steel's gonna stop them?

author: janos
content: No such thing as giants. They're stories for the children.

author: grenn
content: Brother Slynt! I've just got word that Ser Alliser needs you below. You're the most experienced man he's got, he said he needs ya.

author: janos
content: Needed below? Yes. Yes.

author: jon snow
content: Archers! Knock your arrows! Draw! Loose!

author: jon snow
content: They won't summit before dawn.

author: grenn
content: How do you know that?

author: jon snow
content: Because I've made that claim.

author: ed
content: I think they're in a bigger hurry than you were.

author: jon snow
content: Knock! Draw! Loose!

content: I got one. Right through the heart, he's dead.

author: sam
content: Oh, is it over?

author: pyp
content: Huh?

content: Well then. *hands Pyp a loaded crossbow*

author: sam
content: You're alright. You're alright. I'll get help. Shh, shh. Maester Aemon is coming, he's gonna make it alright.

author: jon snow
content: Now!

author: ed
content: Now!

author: jon snow
content: to Grenn* The outer gate won't hold. Take five men, hold the inner gate.

author: grenn
content: Alright.

author: jon snow
content: grabs Grenn's arm* Hold the gate. If they make it through...

author: grenn
content: They won't. Come on Hill! And you Cooper! You three, on me! Come on you lazy bastards!

author: jon snow
content: Oil!

author: ed
content: Oil on the ramp!

author: alliser
content: Protect the gate!

author: alliser
content: Hold the fucking gate! Hold it!

author: sam
content: to Grenn* We need more men down here.

author: grenn
content: We have to hold the gate.

author: sam
content: But we need men here.

author: grenn
content: Tell Jon! He's in command. *to the men behind him* Let's go!

author: sam
content: to Olly* Get me to the top! You hear me?!

author: sam
content: Your name's Olly, right? Listen to me Olly, get me to the top and when we give a signal, bring us back down. Do you hear me?

author: sam
content: And find a weapon, Olly. Fight them!

author: jon snow
content: What are you doing up here?

author: sam
content: The Wildlings are over the walls. Ser Alliser has fallen. The castle walls can't stand much longer.

author: jon snow
content: Ed. You have The Wall. If they try the mammoths again, drop fire on them. If the climbers get too high, drop the scythe on them.

author: jon snow
content: Two brothers now fight with me.

author: ed
content: Might as well enjoy our last night, right boys? Light the fuckers up. Knock! Draw! Loose!

author: donnel
content: How are we gonna stop that?

author: cooper
content: We shot twenty-eight arrows in him already.

author: grenn
content: You heard Jon, we hold the gate.

author: donnel
content: Jon Snow's not Lord Commander.

author: grenn
content: We hold the gate!

author: donnel
content: Mother save me. Father save me.

author: grenn
content: The gods aren't down here. It's the six of us, you hear me?

author: donnel
content: No, please.

author: grenn
content: Night gathers, and now my watch begins. It shall not end until my death. I shall take no wife, hold no lands, father no children. I shall wear no crowns

author: all together
content: And win no glory. I shall live and die at my post. I am the sword in the darkness. I am the watcher on the walls. I am the shield that guards the realms of men. I pledge my life and honor to the Night's Watch, for this night and all the nights to come!

author: jon snow
content: to Sam* I don't want you out there.

author: sam
content: You can't protect me forever. There won't be anywhere to hide if the castle falls.

author: jon snow
content: I need him more than I need you.

author: sam
content: We need you boy.

author: ygritte
content: Jon Snow.

author: jon snow
content: No, shh, don't talk.

author: ygritte
content: Do you remember that cave?

author: ygritte
content: We shouldo ve stayed in that cave.

author: jon snow
content: We'll go back there.

author: ygritte
content: You know nothing, Jon Snow.

author: ed
content: Drop the scythe, boys!

author: ed
content: Hoister up!

author: ed
content: They've had enough for one night.

author: ed
content: Don't cheer too loud. They still outnumber us a thousand to one.

author: jon snow
content: Tormund. It's over, let it end.

author: tormund
content: This is how a man ends.

author: jon snow
content: Put him in chains. We'll question him later.

author: tormund
content: I shouldo ve thrown you from the top of your wall boy!

author: jon snow
content: Aye, you shouldo ve.

author: sam
content: Woah! It's me. It's me. I promised you, didn't I?

author: sam
content: We held them off.

author: jon snow
content: For one night.

author: sam
content: This is a great victory.

author: jon snow
content: Great victory? Mance was testing our defenses. He almost made it through. And he has more giants, he has more mammoths. He has a thousand times as many men. They'll hit us again tonight. Maybe we can hold them off for a day or two, but we can never beat them.

author: sam
content: Where are you going?

author: jon snow
content: I'm going to find Mance.

author: sam
content: To...you can't do that. No one gave you any orders.

author: jon snow
content: Who's left to give orders? The Wildling army is only an army because of Mance. He united a hundred warring tribes. Without Mance they lose their leader. They lose their purpose, they go back to fighting each other, scatter back to their home.

author: sam
content: Without Mance? You're going to kill him?

author: jon snow
content: I'm going to try.

author: sam
content: They'll never let you within a hundred yards of him. And if you did, even if you managed to kill him.

author: jon snow
content: He'll kill me. If I don't go he'll kill me anyway. They'll kill the rest of us too.

author: sam
content: He won't just kill ya. They'll boil you. They'll filet you. They'll make it last days!

author: jon snow
content: You're right. It's a bad plan. What's your plan?

author: jon snow
content: They held the gate. Get some brothers down here to help you. You need to burn the bodies. Raise the outer gate, then lower it again as soon as I'm out.

author: sam
content: What are you doing?

author: jon snow
content: I promised Jeor I'd never lose it again. *he hands the sword to Sam* In case I don't come back.

author: sam
content: Jon. Come back.

author: mance
content: You're wearing a black cloak again.

author: jon snow
content: I've been sent to negotiate with you.

author: mance
content: It appears my trusting nature got the better of me. It's happened before. I was hoping your loyalty was real when you pledged yourself to us, Jon Snow, truly I was.

author: jon snow
content: The Halfhand ordered me to join your army and bring back whatever information I could to Castle Black. He made me kill him so you'd trust me. I was loyal, to him and to my Night's Watch vows.

author: mance
content: All of your vows? She wasn't enough to turn ya, eh? Were you enough to turn her?

author: jon snow
content: She put three arrows in me when I escaped.

author: mance
content: Did you see her again at Castle Black?

author: jon snow
content: Yes.

author: mance
content: And?

author: jon snow
content: She's dead.

author: mance
content: Your doing?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: mance
content: We'll drink to her.

author: mance
content: Of all the ways I'd kill you, poison would be the last.

author: mance
content: Ygritte.

author: jon snow
content: Ygritte.

author: jon snow
content: That's not wine.

author: mance
content: No, it's a proper Northern drink, Jon Snow. You did well. Fought hard. Killed some of our strongest men. One of our giants went into your tunnel and never came out again. Mag the Mighty.

author: jon snow
content: He's dead. He killed my friend Grenn.

author: mance
content: He was their king. Last of a bloodline that stretches back before the First Men.

author: jon snow
content: Grenn came from a farm.

author: mance
content: Mag and Grenn.

author: jon snow
content: Grenn and Mag.

author: mance
content: Kullback, could I trouble you for something to eat? I don't imagine our guest has eaten anything in quite some time. So. You're here to strike a bargain?

author: jon snow
content: Turn your army around and go home.

author: mance
content: You know I know you're low on arrows. You're low on oil. You're low on men. How many are left? 50?

author: jon snow
content: I told Tormund and Orell. We have more than a thousand men.

author: mance
content: I showed you everything I had. The whole army, a hundred thousand strong, and what did you do? You fired on us with everything you had. It wasn't much. Soon as I saw that I sent four hundred men to climb the wall. An unmanned stretch five miles west of here. A lot of them will die climbing, but most of them will be over by the end of the day. This is me being honest with you, Jon Snow, which is more than you've ever done for me. My people have bled enough. We're not here to conquer, we're here to hide behind your wall just like you. We need your tunnel. Now we both know that winter is coming and if my people aren't south of the wall when it comes in earnest, we'll all end up worse than dead. Wanna strike a bargain with me? Here's a bargain. You go back, you open the gates to us and I swear to you that no one else will die. Refuse and we'll kill every last man in Castle Black.

author: mance
content: Ah! Oh, that's why you're here. I reckon you could do it before any of them could stop ya. They'd kill you of course, they'd kill ya slow, but ya knew that when you came in here. Are you capable of that, Jon Snow? Killing a man in his own tent when he's just offered ya peace? Is that what the Night's Watch is? Is that what you are?

author: mance
content: You attacking us?

author: jon snow
content: No, it's like you said, we don't have the men.

author: mance
content: Hold! To me. To me.

author: mance
content: Stand down! I said my people have bled enough and I meant it.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You're the king beyond the wall?

author: stannis baratheon
content: You know who I am?

author: mance
content: Never had the pleasure.

author: davos
content: This is Stannis Baratheon, the one true king of the seven kingdoms.

author: mance
content: We're not in the seven kingdoms and you're not dressed for this weather.

author: stannis baratheon
content: It is customary to kneel when surrendering to a king.

author: mance
content: We do not kneel.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'll have thousands of your men in chains by nightfall, I'll have nowhere to put them and nothing to feed them. I'm not here to slaughter beat dogs. Their fate depends on their king.

author: mance
content: All the same, we do not kneel.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Take these men away.

author: davos
content: What are men of the Night's Watch doing in a Wildling camp?

author: jon snow
content: I was sent to discuss terms with the king beyond the wall.

author: davos
content: You're speaking to the one true king boy. You'll address him as your grace.

author: jon snow
content: I know he's the king. My father died for him. My name is Jon Snow, your grace. I'm Ned Stark's son.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Your father was an honorable man.

author: jon snow
content: He was, your grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What do you think he'd have done with him?

author: jon snow
content: I was this man's prisoner once. He couldo ve tortured me, he couldo ve killed me, but he spared my life. I think my father wouldo ve taken him prisoner, listened to what he had to say.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Very well. *to Davos* Take him.

author: jon snow
content: Your grace. If my father'd seen the things that I've seen, he'd also tell you to burn the dead before nightfall. All of them.

author: pycelle
content: I would suggest milk of the poppy to ease his pain but he is completely insensate.

author: cersei lannister
content: Bloody Martells.

author: pycelle
content: The cause appears to be manticore venom.

author: qyburn
content: It is, yes, manticore.

author: pycelle
content: I've read a good deal about it. It's a horrible poison, usually Mantari in origin. Oh! Yes, yes. There's nothing to be done.

author: qyburn
content: Yes there is.

author: pycelle
content: May I ask what you think you're doing?

author: qyburn
content: Saving him.

author: pycelle
content: Your grace. I wish it were otherwise, but Ser Gregor is beyond saving. Well, well beyond. This man is not even a Maester, let alone Grand Maester.

author: qyburn
content: That's for the best. No Maester knows how to save him.

author: pycelle
content: That is exactly the sort of arrogance that had him expelled from the citadel, your grace. His curiosity was deemed dangerous and unnatural. Rightly so in my opinion.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're dismissed, Grand Maester.

author: pycelle
content: Your grace. This is my laboratory!

author: cersei lannister
content: Not anymore.

author: cersei lannister
content: You can save him?

author: qyburn
content: Difficult to say, your grace, but if my past work is any guide. We stand a chance.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do everything you can. Come to me with anything you need.

author: qyburn
content: Thank you, your grace. You should know, the process may change him, somewhat.

author: cersei lannister
content: Will it weaken him?

author: qyburn
content: Oh no.

author: cersei lannister
content: Very well then.

author: tywin lannister
content: Not another word. We've been over this, the matter's closed.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm opening it again.

author: tywin lannister
content: You are betrothed to Loras Tyrell. Still betrothed to Loras Tyrell and you will marry Loras Tyrell as soon as Tommen marries Margaery.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not.

author: tywin lannister
content: Jaime cannot marry or inherit lands. Tyrion's sentence will be carried out tomorrow. You have, on several occasions, made great claims about your commitment to this family's future. Your role in that future is more vital now than it ever was.

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't care. I will stay in King's Landing where I belong with my son, the king.

author: tywin lannister
content: When you were nine years old, I was called to the capital. I decided to take your brother with me and not you. You insisted that you would not be left at Casterly Rock under any circumstances and if you recall-

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm not interested in hearing another one of your smug stories about the time you won. This isn't going to be one of those times.

author: tywin lannister
content: Do you think you'll be the first person dragged into a sept to be married against her will?

author: cersei lannister
content: When you marched into the throne room to tell me we'd won the Battle at Blackwater, do you remember?! I was sitting on the iron throne with Tommen. I was about to give him essence of nightshade, that's how far I was willing to go when I thought someone awful had come to take my son away. Someone awful is coming to take him away.

author: tywin lannister
content: No.

author: cersei lannister
content: Joffrey is dead. Myrcella's been sold like livestock. And now you want to ship me off to Highgarden and steal my boy, my last boy. Margaery will dig her claws in and you will dig your claws in and you will fight over him like beasts until you rip him apart. I will burn our house to the ground before I let that happen.

author: tywin lannister
content: And how will you do that?

author: cersei lannister
content: I'll tell everyone the truth.

author: tywin lannister
content: And what truth would that be?

author: cersei lannister
content: You don't know, do you? You never believed it. How is that possible? What am I saying, of course it's possible. How can someone so consumed by the idea of his family have any conception what his actual family was doing? We were right there in front of you and you didn't see us. One look in the past twenty years, one real look and you wouldo ve known.

author: tywin lannister
content: Known what?

author: cersei lannister
content: Everything they say is true. About Jaime and me.

author: tywin lannister
content: No, no, no, no, no.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your legacy is a lie.

author: tywin lannister
content: I don't believe you.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes you do.

author: cersei lannister
content: Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: You won. One fewer brother. Must be proud of yourself. There's really nothing you wouldn't do, is there?

author: cersei lannister
content: For my family, no. I would do things for my family you couldn't imagine.

author: jaime lannister
content: Tyrion is your family.

author: cersei lannister
content: He's not.

author: jaime lannister
content: You don't get to choose.

author: cersei lannister
content: I do, so do you. You can choose the creature that killed our mother to come into this world-

author: jaime lannister
content: Are you really mad enough to blame him for that? He didn't decide to kill her. He was an infant.

author: cersei lannister
content: A disease doesn't decide to kill you, all the same you cut it out before it does. What do you decide? What do you choose?

author: jaime lannister
content: The things I did to get back to you, to endure all that, only to find you-

author: cersei lannister
content: I choose you.

author: jaime lannister
content: Those are words.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes. Like the ones I just said to father. I told him.

author: jaime lannister
content: Told him what?

author: cersei lannister
content: I told him about us.

author: jaime lannister
content: You told him?

author: cersei lannister
content: I told him I wouldn't marry Loras Tyrell. I told him I'm staying right here with Tommen, with you.

author: jaime lannister
content: You think he'll just accept that?

author: cersei lannister
content: Go and ask him.

author: jaime lannister
content: What did you say?

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't want to talk about Tywin Lannister. I don't choose Tywin Lannister, I don't love Tywin Lannister. I love my brother. I love my lover. People will whisper, they'll make their jokes. Let them. They're all so small I can't even see them. I only see what matters.

author: jaime lannister
content: Someone will walk in.

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't care.

author: missandei
content: in Valyrian* You stand before Daenerys Stormborn, the Unburnt, Queen of Mereen, Queen of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the First Men. Khaleesi of the Great Grass Sea, Breaker of Chains and Mother of Dragons.

author: fennesz
content: in Valyrian* Thank you for seeing me, your grace. My name is Fennesz. I can speak the common tongue if you wish.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You speak it very well.

author: fennesz
content: Before you freed me, I belonged to Master Mighdal. I was tutor to his children. I taught them languages and history. They know a great deal about your family because of me. Little Calla is only seven, but she admires you very much.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I hope I can prove worthy of her admiration. What can I do for you?

author: fennesz
content: When you took the city, the children begged me not to leave the house. But Master Mighdal and I agreed that I must. So I lost my home. Now I live on the streets.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I have outfitted mess halls to feed all former slaves and barracks to shelter them.

author: fennesz
content: I do not mean to offend, your grace. I went to one of these places. The young prey on the old. Take what they want and beat us if we resist.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My Unsullied will make them safe again in short order my friend, this I promise you.

author: fennesz
content: Even if they are safe, who would I be there? What purpose would I serve? With my master, I was a teacher. I had the respect and love of these children.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What is it that you want from me?

author: fennesz
content: Your grace, I ask you to let me sell myself back to Master Mighdal.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You want to return to a man who owned you, like a goat or a chair?

author: fennesz
content: Please, your grace, the young may rejoice in the new world you've built for them. But for those of us too old to change there is only fear and squalor. I am not alone. There are many outside waiting to beg the same-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I did not take this city to preside over the injustice I fought to destroy. I took it to bring people freedom. But freedom means making your own choices. I will allow you to sign a contract with your former master. It may not cover a period lasting longer than a year.

author: fennesz
content: Thank you, your grace. Thank you.

author: barristan
content: The masters will take advantage of this situation. The men serving them will be slaves in all but name.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Approach my friend.

author: man
content: in Low Valyrian* I do not understand, my queen. I do not understand, my queen.

author: missandei
content: in Low Valyrian* The Queen says you may approach.

author: man
content: crying, speaking Low Valyrian*

author: missandei
content: translating* I have brought you. He came from the sky. The black one. The winged shadow. He came from the sky and...

author: missandei
content: translating* My girl. My little girl.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What was her name?

author: missandei
content: Zala, your grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How old was she?

author: missandei
content: Three.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Three. *in Valyrian* And still no word on Drogon?

author: grey worm
content: in Valyrian* Sailors saw him flying over the Black Cliffs three days ago, my queen. Nothing since then.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: in Valyrian* Meet me in the catacombs.

author: aemon
content: They came to us from White Harbor and Barrowton, from Fairmarket and King's Landing, from north and south, from east and west. They died protecting men, women, and children who will never know their names. It is for us to remember them. Our brothers, we shall never see their like again.

author: all together
content: And now their watch is ended.

author: aemon
content: And now their watch is ended.

author: tormund
content: Your old blind man patched me up. Why?

author: jon snow
content: He's sworn to treat all wounded men, friend or foe.

author: tormund
content: You want me alive so you can torture me?

author: jon snow
content: No one's going to torture you.

author: tormund
content: So how do we die? Hanging? Beheading? Drop us from the top of the wall?

author: jon snow
content: I don't know what happens to the prisoners.

author: tormund
content: Who decides?

author: jon snow
content: I suppose Stannis does.

author: tormund
content: He your king now?

author: jon snow
content: I don't have a king.

author: tormund
content: You spent too much time with us, Jon Snow. You can never be a kneeler again.

author: jon snow
content: We're gonna burn the bodies of your dead. Do you want to say any words over them?

author: tormund
content: Words? What kind of words?

author: jon snow
content: Funeral words. I don't know how the Free Folk do it.

author: tormund
content: Do what?

author: jon snow
content: Say farewell.

author: tormund
content: The dead can't hear us, boy.

author: tormund
content: Snow. Did you love her? She loved you.

author: jon snow
content: She told you?

author: tormund
content: No. All she ever talked about was killing you. That's how I know. She belongs in the North. The real North. You understand me?

author: meera
content: We can stop, we can rest.

author: jojen
content: We'll rest with the three-eyed raven.

author: meera
content: We're not going to make it.

author: jojen
content: We're already here.

author: bran stark
content: Jojen. Jojen! Look, Jojen, look.

author: meera
content: JOJEN! Hold on!

author: bran stark
content: Help them! Now!

author: meera
content: Hold on to me!

author: hodor
content: Hodor...

author: bran stark
content: Help them!

author: jojen
content: Bran! Save yourself, now!

author: girl
content: Come with me, Brandon Stark!

author: girl
content: He is lost. Come with me, or die with him.

author: jojen
content: Go with them.

author: girl
content: They cannot follow us. The power that moves them is powerless here.

author: bran stark
content: Who are you?

author: girl
content: The First Men called us The Children, but we were born long before them. Come, he waits for you.

author: bran stark
content: You're the three-eyed raven.

author: old man
content: I have been many things. Now, I am what you see.

author: meera
content: My brother, he led us to you, and now he…

author: old man
content: He knew what would happen. From the moment he left, he knew, and he went anyway.

author: meera
content: How do you know?

author: old man
content: I've been watching you. All of you, all of your lives, with a thousand eyes and one. Now you've come to me at last, Brandon Stark, though the hour is late.

author: bran stark
content: I didn't want anyone to die for me.

author: old man
content: He died so that you could find what you have lost.

author: bran stark
content: You're going to help me walk again?

author: old man
content: You'll never walk again. But you will fly.

author: brienne
content: Podrick. Podrick! Where are the horses?

author: podrick
content: I hobbled them last night.

author: brienne
content: What sort of hobble?

author: podrick
content: A figure-eight, like you taught me.

author: brienne
content: If you did it like I taught you then the horses would be here.

author: podrick
content: Thieves, maybe?

author: brienne
content: It's at least thirty miles to the Eyrie from here. You're carrying the saddle bags.

author: arya stark
content: People coming. You can shit later, there's people coming!

author: brienne
content: Morning!

author: arya stark
content: Morning.

author: brienne
content: I like your sword. Are we getting close to the bloody gate?

author: arya stark
content: About ten more miles.

author: brienne
content: Did you hear that Podrick? Only about ten more miles to the Bloody Gate.

author: arya stark
content: Are you a knight?

author: brienne
content: No.

author: arya stark
content: But you know how to use that sword.

author: brienne
content: I do.

author: arya stark
content: Does it have a name?

author: brienne
content: Oathkeeper.”

author: arya stark
content: Mine's “Needle.”

author: brienne
content: Good name.

author: arya stark
content: Who taught you how to fight?

author: brienne
content: My father.

author: arya stark
content: Mine never wanted to. Said fighting was for boys.

author: brienne
content: Mine said the same. But I kept fighting the boys anyway. Kept losing. Finally my father said, “If you're going to do it, you might as well do it right.”

author: brienne
content: Seven blessings. I'm Brienne of Tarth, this is Podrick Payne.

author: sandor clegane
content: You want something?

author: podrick
content: That's Sandor Clegane- the Hound.

author: brienne
content: You're Arya Stark.

author: sandor clegane
content: I asked if you wanted something.

author: brienne
content: I swore to your mother I would bring you home to her.

author: arya stark
content: My mother's dead.

author: brienne
content: I know. I wish I couldo ve been there to protect her.

author: arya stark
content: You're not a northerner.

author: brienne
content: I know, but I swore a sacred vow to protect her.

author: arya stark
content: Why didn't you?

author: brienne
content: She commanded me to bring Jaime Lannister back to King's Landing.

author: sandor clegane
content: You're paid by the Lannisters. You're here for the bounty on me.

author: brienne
content: I'm not paid by the Lannisters.

author: sandor clegane
content: No? Fancy sword you've got there. Where'd you get it? I've been looking at Lannister gold all my life. Go on, Brienne of fucking Tarth, tell me that's not Lannister gold.

author: brienne
content: Jaime Lannister gave me this sword.

author: arya stark
content: The Bloody Gate's ten miles.

author: brienne
content: I swore to your mother by the Old Gods and the New -

author: arya stark
content: I don't care what you swore!

author: brienne
content: Arya!

author: sandor clegane
content: You heard the girl! She's not coming with you.

author: brienne
content: She is.

author: sandor clegane
content: You're not a good listener. Valyrian steel-- I've always wanted some Valyrian steel.

author: brienne
content: Come with me Arya. I'll take you to safety.

author: sandor clegane
content: Safety?! Where the fuck's that? Her aunt in the Eyrie's dead. Her mother's dead, her father's dead, her brother's dead. Winterfell's a pile of rubble. There's no safety, you dumb bitch. If you don't know that by now, you're the wrong one to watch over her.

author: brienne
content: And that's what you're doing? Watching over her?

author: sandor clegane
content: Aye, that's what I'm doing.

author: brienne
content: I have no wish to kill you Ser.

author: sandor clegane
content: I'm not a knight.

author: brienne
content: Arya! Arya! ARYA! Where is she?

author: podrick
content: She was just here...

author: brienne
content: Why weren't you watching her?

author: podrick
content: I was watching you I thought you migth need some help…

author: brienne
content: Which way Pod? Which way did she go?

author: podrick
content: Ah, I think that way.

author: sandor clegane
content: You're still here? [Coughs] Big bitch saved you.

author: arya stark
content: I don't need saving.

author: sandor clegane
content: No, not you. You're a real killer. With your water dancing, and your needle.

author: arya stark
content: You're gonna die?

author: sandor clegane
content: Unless there's a Maester hiding behind that rock, aye, I'm done. I'd skin you alive for wine. [Arya offers water.] Fuck water! Killed by a woman. I bet you liked that. Go on, go after her. She'll help you. Going out alone, you won't last a day out there.

author: arya stark
content: I'll last longer than you.

author: sandor clegane
content: You remember where the heart is? Fuck it. I'm ready. Go on, girl. Another name off your list. You kept promising me. I cut down your butcher's boy, the ginger. He was begging for mercy. Please sir, please don't kill me, please, please. Bled all over my horse. Saddle stunk of butcher's boy for weeks. And your sister, your pretty sister. I shouldo ve taken her. That night the Blackwater burned, I shouldo ve fucked her bloody. At least I'd have one happy memory! Do I have to beg you? Do it. Do it.

author: sandor clegane
content: Kill me. Kill me! Kill me! Kill me!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, get on with it you son of a whore.

author: jaime lannister
content: Is that any way to speak about our mother?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What're you doing?

author: jaime lannister
content: What do you think I'm doing? The galley's waiting in the bay bound for the Free Cities.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who's helping you?

author: jaime lannister
content: Varys.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Varys?

author: jaime lannister
content: You have more friends than you thought.

author: jaime lannister
content: There's a locked door at the top of the stairs. Knock on it twice, and then twice again. Varys will open.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I suppose this is goodbye, then.

author: jaime lannister
content: Farewell, little brother.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Jaime, thank you. For my life.

author: jaime lannister
content: Quickly now.

author: woman
content: Tywin… my lion...

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

author: tywin lannister
content: Tyrion! Put down the crossbow. Who released you? Ah, your brother ,I expect. He always had a soft spot for you. Come, we'll go and talk in my chambers. Is this how you want to speak to me? Shaming your father has always given you pleasure…

author: tyrion lannister
content: All my life, you've wanted me dead.

author: tywin lannister
