content: Yes. But you refused to die. I respect that, even admire it. You fight for what's yours. I'd never let them execute you; is that what you fear? I'd never let Illyn Payne take your head. You're a Lannister. You're my son.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I loved her.

author: tywin lannister
content: Who?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Shae.

author: tywin lannister
content: Bah, Tyrion. Put down that crossbow.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I murdered her. With my own hands.

author: tywin lannister
content: It doesn't matter.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It doesn't matter?

author: tywin lannister
content: She was a whore!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Say that word again.

author: tywin lannister
content: And what? You'll kill your own father in the privy? No. You're my son. Enough of this nonsense…

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am your son, and you sentenced me to die. You knew I didn't poison Joffrey, but you sentenced me all the same. Why?

author: tywin lannister
content: Enough. We'll go back to my chambers and speak with some dignity.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can't go back there. She's in there.

author: tywin lannister
content: What, are you afraid of a dead whore?

author: tywin lannister
content: You shot me. You're no son of mine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am your son. I have always been your son.

author: varys
content: What have you done? Quickly. Trust me, my friend, I've brought you this far.

author: arya stark
content: I want to see the captain.

author: captain
content: You're seeing him.

author: arya stark
content: I want to go north, to the wall.

author: captain
content: No you don't.

author: arya stark
content: I can pay.

author: captain
content: There is nothing in the north but ice and war and pirates.

author: arya stark
content: I wouldn't need a cabin. Please, I could work, scrubbing the floors, or…

author: captain
content: I'm not going north, child, we're going home.

author: arya stark
content: Where's home?

author: captain
content: The Free City of Braavos.

author: arya stark
content: Wait, I have something else.

author: captain
content: More silver won't make a difference.

author: arya stark
content: It's not silver, it's iron.

author: arya stark
content: Valar morghulis.

author: captain
content: How did you… valar dohaeris. Of course, you shall have a cabin.

author: melara
content: We shouldn't be out here alone.

author: cersei lannister
content: Why not?

author: melara
content: If your father hears…

author: cersei lannister
content: He'll never know we've been gone.

author: melara
content: But if he finds out…

author: cersei lannister
content: You don't need to be afraid of my father.

author: melara
content: Are you sure?

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes.

author: melara
content: We shouldn't go in.

author: cersei lannister
content: Of course we should.

author: maggy
content: Get out. Get out!

author: melara
content: Let's go…

author: cersei lannister
content: No.

author: maggy
content: Listen to your friend.

author: cersei lannister
content: They said that you were terrifying. With cat's teeth and three eyes. You're not terrifying. You're boring.

author: maggy
content: You don't know what I am.

author: cersei lannister
content: I know you're a witch and you can see the future. Tell me mine.

author: maggy
content: Everybody wants to know their future. Until they know their future.

author: cersei lannister
content: This is my father's land. My land. Tell me my future or I'll have your two boring eyes gouged out of your head.

author: maggy
content: Your blood. Give me a taste.

author: maggy
content: Three questions you get. You won't like the answers.

author: cersei lannister
content: I've been promised to the prince. When will we marry?

author: maggy
content: You'll never wed the prince. You'll wed the king.

author: cersei lannister
content: But I will be queen?

author: maggy
content: Oh yes, you'll be queen. For a time. In comes another. Younger, more beautiful, to cast you down and take all you hold dear.

author: cersei lannister
content: Will the king and I have children?

author: maggy
content: No. The king will have 20 children, and you will have 3.

author: cersei lannister
content: That doesn't make sense.

author: maggy
content: Gold will be their crowns. Gold their shrouds.

author: melara
content: Come on, we have to go. We have to go! Cersei!

author: priest
content: Your grace, we are honored by your presence. The mourners are waiting.

author: cersei lannister
content: They will keep waiting. I want a moment alone with him.

author: priest
content: But your grace, many of these lords and ladies have travelled day and night to be here…

author: priest
content: From all seven kingdoms…

author: cersei lannister
content: They will wait.

author: cersei lannister
content: He never wanted you to be a King's Guard, but here you are, protecting his dead body.

author: jaime lannister
content: What he built. The towers. He built it for us. He meant it for us. They're going to try to take it away, all of it.

author: cersei lannister
content: They?

author: jaime lannister
content: All of them out there are enemies. They're waiting a night to make sure he's really dead and as soon as they see the stones on his eyes they'll set to work on tearing us apart.

author: cersei lannister
content: They had nothing to do with it. The man who murdered our father, he tore us apart, he's the enemy. I've been telling you for years, you've been defending him for years…

author: jaime lannister
content: This is exactly what they want.

author: cersei lannister
content: and now our father is dead. And that little monster is out there somewhere drawing breath. Did you set him free?

author: cersei lannister
content: Tyrion may be a monster but at least he killed our father on purpose. You killed him by mistake. With stupidity. You're a man of action, aren't you? When it occurs to you to do something you do it, nevermind the consequences. Take a look. Look at the consequences. Here they are. He loved you more than anyone in this world.

author: varys
content: Apologies.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I still don't see why I had to stay in this fucking crate once we set sail.

author: varys
content: I saved your life. If they catch you, they catch me. I cannot say I feel overly guilty about leaving you in that “fucking crate”.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you know what it's like to stuff your shit through one of those air holes?

author: varys
content: No. I only know what it's like to pick up your shit and throw it overboard.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Pentos?

author: varys
content: The home of my colleague. Ilyrio Mopatis. A merchant. He and I met many years ago, through mutual friends. A group of people who saw Robert Baratheon for the disaster he was. We tried to do what was best for the realm by supporting the Targaryen restoration. And thus began the chain of mistakes that has led us both here. Things have gotten worse, not better. Westeros needs to be saved from itself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Much better.

author: varys
content: My lord?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't think I am anymore. A lord. Are you a lord if you kill your father? I don't suppose they revoke your nobility for killing a whore. That has to be happen all the time.

author: varys
content: You already drank yourself across the Narrow Sea.

author: tyrion lannister
content: In a box. Why stop now?

author: varys
content: Because we are talking about the future of our country.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The future is shit. Just like the past.

author: prostitute
content: You want the same? Same as always?

author: white rat
content: You… you don't have to.

author: prostitute
content: Habit.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Sons of the Harpy?

author: barristan
content: Yes, your grace. They left it on the body.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They've never killed before.

author: barristan
content: It was only a matter of time, your grace. Conquerors are always met with resistance.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I didn't conquer them. Their own people did.

author: mossador
content: They do not see us as people, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Then they will have to learn to see things differently, Mossador. He did not risk his life fighting for freedom so cowards in masks could take it away. And I did not take up residence in this pyramid so I could watch the city below decline into chaos. What was the name of the man you lost?

author: grey worm
content: White Rat, your grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I want him buried with honor. Publicly. In the Temple of the Graces.

author: barristan
content: The Sons of the Harpy will hear that message.

author: mossador
content: Make them very angry.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Angry snakes lash out. Makes chopping off their heads that much easier. Find the men who did this and bring them to me.

author: missandei
content: Torgo Nudho.

author: grey worm
content: Missandei hin Naath.

author: missandei
content: I wanted to speak with you.

author: grey worm
content: Why do you come?

author: missandei
content: White Rat, the Unsullied who… I have heard they found his body in a brothel. I have heard that more than one Unsullied has been known to visit Meereen's brothels. May I ask you why? Why would an Unsullied go to a brothel?

author: grey worm
content: I do not know. I must go.

author: jon snow
content: Get your shield up.

author: olly
content: It's too heavy.

author: jon snow
content: If it wasn't heavy it wouldn't stop a sword, now get it up.

author: jon snow
content: Come. Try it again. Drive at me. Keep your shield up. Or I'll ring your head like a bell.

author: gilly
content: Shouldn't you be training, too?

author: sam
content: Well, I'm hardly a new recruit. How many brothers can say they've killed a white walker and a Thenn? I might be the first in history!

author: alliser
content: These men need a firm hand. Always have. They're poachers and thieves.

author: alliser
content: Not soldiers.

author: gilly
content: That one hates me.

author: sam
content: If Ser Alliser is chosen as the new Lord Commander… he hates the wildlings.

author: sam
content: All the wildlings.

author: gilly
content: Don't let them send us away.

author: sam
content: It's not a sure thing. Ser Denys Mallister has commanded the Shadow Tower for 20 years, and people say he's a good man. He's running against Ser Alliser--

author: gilly
content: Sam! Don't let them send us away.

author: sam
content: I told you. Wherever you go, I go, too.

author: gilly
content: You can't leave, they'll execute you.

author: jon snow
content: Good, good, pivot! Don't forget to pivot! Shield up!

author: melisandre
content: The king wants a word.

author: jon snow
content: You're not cold, my lady?

author: melisandre
content: Never. The Lordo s fire lives within me, Jon Snow.

author: melisandre
content: Feel.

author: melisandre
content: Are you a virgin?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: melisandre
content: Good.

author: melisandre
content: Your grace. The bastard of Winterfell.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You know who rules at Winterfell now?

author: jon snow
content: Roose Bolton.

author: stannis baratheon
content: The traitor who plunged a dagger into Robb Stark's heart. Don't you want to avenge him?

author: jon snow
content: I want a great many things, your grace. But I'm a sworn brother of the Night's Watch now.

author: davos
content: I've been talking to your sworn brothers. Many of them love you.

author: jon snow
content: They're good men.

author: davos
content: Many don't. You were seen taking the body of a wildling girl north of the Wall. Why?

author: jon snow
content: It's where she belonged.

author: davos
content: Some of the Night's Watch feel you have too much affection for the wildlings.

author: jon snow
content: They were born on the wrong side of the wall. That doesn't make them monsters.

author: stannis baratheon
content: No matter. I shall take back the North from the thieves who stole it. Tywin Lannister is dead. He can't protect them now. I shall mount Roose Bolton's head on a spike. But if I'm to take Winterfell I'll need more men.

author: jon snow
content: The men of the Night's Watch are sworn to play no part--

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'm not talking about the damn Night's Watch. I'm talking about the wildlings.

author: jon snow
content: Your grace, you want the wildlings to march in your army?

author: stannis baratheon
content: If they swear to follow me, I'll pardon them. We'll take Winterfell. Once the North is won, I'll declare them citizens of the realm. I'll give them land to live on.

author: davos
content: It's a fair offer. More than fair.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'll offer them their lives and their freedom if Mance kneels before me and swears his loyalty.

author: jon snow
content: I don't think that's likely.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You admire him, don't you?

author: jon snow
content: I respect him.

author: stannis baratheon
content: He likes you. Convince him to bend the knee...

author: jon snow
content: Your grace…

author: stannis baratheon
content: or he burns.

author: jon snow
content: How much time do I have?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Nightfall. The sun drops fast this time of year. Hurry, Jon Snow.

author: master of arms
content: Sword up! Attack, my lord! Attack! Don't cross your feet!

author: yohn royce
content: My sons have had swords in their hands from the time they could walk. This one…

author: petyr baelish
content: Lord Arryn will never be a great warrior.

author: royce
content: Great warrior? He sings a sword like a girl with palsy.

author: squire
content: My lord.

author: master of arms
content: Sword up, my lord!

author: petyr baelish
content: Some boys develop more slowly. He's still young.

author: royce
content: He's 13. Boys go to war at 13.

author: petyr baelish
content: He has other gifts.

author: royce
content: Does he?

author: petyr baelish
content: The gift of a great name. Sometimes that's all one needs.

author: sansa stark
content: Goodbye Lord Royce, and thank you for all you've done for me.

author: royce
content: I have done nothing more than my duty, my lady.

author: petyr baelish
content: I have no doubt that upon my return, Robin's skills will have improved immeasurably.

author: royce
content: He'll be safe here. As for his skills, I make no promises.

author: podrick
content: Will we head north at some point? He said Sansa had a brother at Castle Black. We're a few days ride from the Kingsroad, but that will take us--

author: brienne
content: Us? The only reason you're here is that Jaime Lannister told me you weren't safe in the capital. You're hundreds of miles from King's Landing. No one knows what you look like. No one cares. You're safe.

author: podrick
content: But I'm you're squire.

author: brienne
content: Do you even know what a squire is?

author: podrick
content: An attendant to a knight?

author: brienne
content: I'm not a knight. That means you're not a squire.

author: podrick
content: Well, where would I go?

author: brienne
content: I don't care, I'm not your mother.

author: podrick
content: You swore to find the Stark girls.

author: brienne
content: I found Arya. She didn't want my protection.

author: podrick
content: Sansa still might.

author: brienne
content: Will you shut your mouth? I didn't ask for advice. I don't want anyone following me. I'm not a leader. All I ever wanted is to fight for a Lord I believed in. The good lords are dead and the rest are monsters.

author: sansa stark
content: You told Lord Royce we were going to the Fingers.

author: petyr baelish
content: I did.

author: sansa stark
content: But we're heading west.

author: petyr baelish
content: We are.

author: sansa stark
content: If he wanted to betray us, he already would have.

author: petyr baelish
content: Lord Royce may be as honorable as he thinks he is, but he's not alone in that castle. Do you trust all those knights and ladies, stable boys and serving girls?

author: sansa stark
content: No. Do you trust the carriage driver or the knights escorting us?

author: petyr baelish
content: No. But I pay them well, and they've seen what happens to men who disappoint me.

author: sansa stark
content: So where are we going? To a land where you trust everyone?

author: petyr baelish
content: So a land so far from here, even Cersei Lannister can't get her hands on you.

author: loras
content: It was such a deep, deep shock to us all. Your father was a force to be reckoned with. He truly was. I wouldn't presume to claim to have known him as such…

author: loras
content: But just being in his presence was enough to make it so clear just how formidable a person you were dealing with. What a… what a force to be reckoned with.

author: cersei lannister
content: Thank you so much for your kind words.

author: grand maester pyrcelle
content: Deepest condolences, your grace. This tragedy… I never trusted Varys. I often warned…

author: lancel lannister
content: Your grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Cousin Lancel. I hardly recognized you.

author: lancel
content: My deepest sympathies.

author: kevan lannister
content: I apologize for my son's appearance.

author: cersei lannister
content: Uncle, it's quite alright.

author: kevan
content: They call themselves sparrows. Bloody fanatics. Religion has its place, of course, but at a certain point… They never would have come to the capital when Tywin was alive.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm sure he'll grow out of it. Whatever it is. Excuse me.

author: kevan
content: Of course.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your wounds from the Blackwater seem to have healed.

author: lancel
content: It wasn't my wounds that needed healing.

author: cersei lannister
content: What can I do for you?

author: lancel
content: You can forgive me.

author: cersei lannister
content: What could you possibly have done to warrant my forgiveness?

author: lancel
content: I led you into the darkness.

author: cersei lannister
content: I doubt you've ever led anyone anywhere.

author: lancel
content: I tempted you into our unnatural relations. And, of course, there was the king. His boar hunt. His wine.

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't know what you're talking about.

author: lancel
content: I'm a different person now. I found peace in the light of the Seven. You can too. They watch over all of us, ready to dole out mercy… or justice. Their world is at hand. I will pray for your father's soul.

author: cersei lannister
content: The day Tywin Lannister's soul needs your help…

author: olyvar
content: It looks like Dorne.

author: loras
content: No it doesn't.

author: olyvar
content: It does. That's the Sunspear bit right there. And that's where the mountains are. And over here is… Sunsnake? Stonespear?

author: loras
content: Sandstone.

author: olyvar
content: Yes. Yes, Sandstone. Just there.

author: loras
content: Fine.

author: loras
content: It's Dorne.

author: olyvar
content: We should go there. I think we would have a lovely time.

author: loras
content: Judging by my experience, that would be wonderful. Dorne, Highgarden. Anywhere but here.

author: margaery tyrell
content: We're late for dinner as it is.

author: loras
content: You're very respectful.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I'm very hungry.

author: margaery tyrell
content: What's your name?

author: olyvar
content: Olyvar, my lady.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I'm afraid my brother is keeping the king waiting, Olyvar.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Perhaps you might consider being a bit more discreet?

author: loras
content: Why? They all know about me anyway. Everybody knows everything about everyone. What's the point in trying to keep a secret in a place like this?

author: margaery tyrell
content: In any event… you shouldn't keep your intended waiting.

author: loras
content: My intended? Please. Tywin's dead. That means no one can force Cersei to marry me.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Lucky you.

author: loras
content: Unlucky you.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You think I want that woman married to my brother?

author: loras
content: If she doesn't marry me, she doesn't go to Highgarden. Which means she stays in King's Landing. Which means you're trapped here with Cersei Lannister as your mother-by-law.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Perhaps.

author: loras
content: Perhaps?

author: margaery tyrell
content: Perhaps?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Eunuch, the spider, the master of whisperers.

author: varys
content: Imp, half-man.

author: varys
content: There are faster ways to kill yourself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not for a coward.

author: varys
content: You are many things, my friend, but not a coward.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You never told me why you set me free.

author: varys
content: Your brother asked me to.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You could have said no.

author: varys
content: Refuse the Kingslayer? A dangerous proposition.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not as dangerous as releasing me. You risked your life, your position, everything. Why? You're not family, you owe me nothing.

author: varys
content: I didn't do it for you. I did it for the Seven Kingdoms.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A drunken dwarf will never be the savior of the Seven Kingdoms.

author: varys
content: I don't believe in saviors. I believe men of talent have a role to play in the war to come.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're going to have to find another soldier. I'm done with Westeros and Westeros is done with me.

author: varys
content: You have many admirable qualities, self-pity is not one of them. Any fool with a bit of luck can find himself born into power. But earning it for yourself, that takes work.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm not well-suited for work.

author: varys
content: I think you are. You have your father's instinct for politics, and you have compassion.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Compassion? Yes. I killed my lover with my bare hands. I shot my own father with a crossbow.

author: varys
content: I never said you were perfect.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What is it you want exactly?

author: varys
content: Peace. Prosperity. A land where the powerful do not prey on the powerless.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Where the castles are made of gingerbread and the moats are filled with blackberry wine. The powerful have always preyed on the powerless, that's how they became powerful in the first place.

author: varys
content: Perhaps. And perhaps we've grown so used to horror we assume there's no other way. If you sat on the Iron Throne, would you spread misery throughout the land?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I will never sit on the Iron Throne.

author: varys
content: No, you won't. But you could help another climb those steps and take that seat. The Seven Kingdoms need someone stronger than Tommen, but gentler than Stannis. A monarch who can intimidate the high lord and inspire the people. A ruler loved by millions with a powerful army and the right family name.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good luck finding him.

author: varys
content: Who said anything about him? You have a choice my friend. You can stay here at Ilyrio's palace and drink yourself to death, or you can ride with me to Mereen, meet Daenerys Targaryen, and decide if the world is worth fighting for.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Can I drink myself to death on the road to Meereen?

author: daario naharis
content: When did the Unsullied start patrolling the streets of Meereen? Looks like your friends haven't been behaving themselves.

author: hizdahr zo loraq
content: The mission to Yunkai was a resounding success. The Wise Masters of Yunkai have agreed to cede power to a council of elders, made up of both the freedmen and the former slaveholders. All matters of consequence will be brought to you for review.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Good.

author: hizdahr
content: They did ask for some concessions.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Concessions?

author: hizdahr
content: Politics is the art of compromise, your grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not a politician. I'm a queen.

author: hizdahr
content: Forgive me. You're right, of course. Still, it's easier to rule happy subjects than angry ones.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't expect the Wise Masters to be happy. Slavery made them rich, I ended slavery.

author: hizdahr
content: They do not ask for the return of slavery. They ask for the re-opening of the fighting pits.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The fighting pits? Where slaves fought slaves to the death?

author: hizdahr
content: In the new world that you've brought to us, free men would fight free men.

author: hizdahr
content: The pitfighters that you liberated plead for this opportunity. Bring some here and ask them yourself.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No fighting pits.

author: hizdahr
content: Opening them would show the people of Yunkai and Meereen that you respect their traditions.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I do not respect the tradition of human cockfighting.

author: hizdahr
content: If you--

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many times must I say no before you understand?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Whatever he wants from me he's not going to get it. If he really believes I'm going to reopen the fighting pits…

author: daario
content: You should reopen the fighting pits.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What?

author: daario
content: My mother was a whore, I told you that. She liked to drink pear brandy. The older she got, the less she made selling her body, the more she wanted to drink. So one day when I was 12, she sold me to a slaver she fucked the night before.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why?

author: daario
content: I was a bad child. I wasn't big, but I was quick. And I loved to fight. So they sold me to a man in Tolos who trained fighters for the pits. I had my first match when I was 16.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You were sold into slavery, forced to fight to the death for the amusement of the masters, and you're defending the fighting pits?

author: daario
content: I'm only here because of those pits. I learned to fight like a Dothraki screamer, a Norvoshi priest, a Westerosi knight. Soon I was famous. 10,000 men and women screamed my name when I stepped into the pit. I made so much money for my master he set me free when I died. I joined the Second Sons, and then I met you.

author: daario
content: You're the queen. Everyone's too afraid of you to speak truth. Everyone but me. You've made thousands of enemies all across the world. As soon as they see weakness, they'll attack. Show your strength here, now.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That's why I have the Unsullied patrolling the streets.

author: daario
content: Anyone with a chest full of gold can buy an army of Unsullied. You're not the Mother of Unsullied. You're the Mother of Dragons.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't want another childo s bones dropped at my feet. No one's seen Drogon in weeks. For all I know he's flown halfway across the world. I can't control them anymore.

author: daario
content: A dragon queen with no dragons is not a queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Viserion? Rhaegal?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Easy. Easy. Easy.

author: mance
content: So here we are.

author: jon snow
content: Here we are.

author: mance
content: When we first met you were my prisoner. And now, for our last meeting…

author: jon snow
content: This doesn't have to be our last meeting.

author: mance
content: No, but it will be.

author: jon snow
content: You know what Stannis wants?

author: mance
content: He wants me to bend the knee. And he wants the free folk to fight for him. I'll give him this much

author: jon snow
content: Shouldn't a king be bold?

author: mance
content: Oh, aye. I respect him. If he gets what he wants, I expect he'll be a better ruler than the fools sitting on the Iron Throne the last hundred years. But I'll never serve him.

author: jon snow
content: You told me you weren't here to conquer. You told me your people have bled enough.

author: mance
content: That's right. But I don't want them bleeding for Stannis Baratheon either.

author: jon snow
content: You spent your life convincing 90 clans to come together for the first time in history. Thenns and Hornfoots, the ice-river clans, even the giants. A life's work uniting them. You didn't do it for power. You didn't do it for glory. You brought them together to save them because none of them will survive the winter, not if they're north of the wall. Isn't their survival more important than your pride?

author: mance
content: Pride? Fuck my pride. This isn't about that.

author: jon snow
content: Then bend the knee and save your people.

author: mance
content: They followed me because they respected me. Because they believed in me. The moment I kneel for a Southern king that's all gone.

author: jon snow
content: And how many tens of thousands are out there right now? How many women? How many children? And you won't go out and rescue them because why? You're afraid of looking afraid.

author: mance
content: Oh, I am afraid. No shame in that. How will they do it? Beheading? Hanging?

author: jon snow
content: They'll burn you alive.

author: mance
content: Bad way to go. I'll be honest with you, I don't want to die. And burnt to death, I don't want people to remember me like that. Scorched and screaming. But it's better than betraying everything I believe.

author: jon snow
content: And what happens to your people? You preserve your dignity and die standing, and they'll sing songs about you. “You'd rather burn than kneel. The great hero.” Until winter comes, and the white walkers come for us all, and there's no one left to sing.

author: mance
content: You're a good lad. Truly, you are. But if you can't understand why I won't enlist my people in a foreigner's war, there's no point explaining.

author: jon snow
content: I think you're making a terrible mistake.

author: mance
content: The freedom to make my own mistakes was all I ever wanted.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Mance Rayder, you've been called the King Beyond the Wall. Westeros only has one king. Bend the knee, I promise you mercy.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Kneel and live.

author: mance
content: This was my home for many years. I wish you good fortune in the wars to come.

author: melisandre
content: Man or woman, young or old, lord or peasant, our choices are the same. We choose light, or we choose darkness. We choose good, or we choose evil. We choose the true god or the false.

author: melisandre
content: Free folk, there is only one true king, and his name is Stannis. Here stands the king of lies. Behold the fate of those who choose the darkness.

author: braavosi man
content: In the old times, whenever Braavos stood in danger, the titan would step with fire in his eyes. He'd wade into the sea and smash the enemies.

author: arya stark
content: He's just a statue.

author: man
content: Don't be afraid. He's announcing our arrival.

author: arya stark
content: I'm not afraid.

author: man
content: The House of Black and White

author: man
content: Here, I leave you.

author: arya stark
content: Thank you for bringing me.

author: man
content: Any man of Braavos would have done the same. Valar morghulis.

author: arya stark
content: Valar dohaeris.

author: arya stark
content: Hello. Valar Morghulis.

author: arya stark
content: Jaqen H'ghar gave me this.

author: old man
content: No one here by that name.

author: arya stark
content: Please. I crossed the Narrow Sea. I have nowhere else to go.

author: old man
content: You have everywhere else to go.

author: arya stark
content: But wait!

author: arya stark
content: Cersei, Walder Frey, The Mountain, Meryn Trant. Cersei, Walder Frey, The Mountain, Meryn Trant.

author: arya stark
content: The Mountain, Meryn Trant.

author: podrick
content: Must be good food if it's crowded.

author: waitress
content: Ale? Ale?

author: sansa stark
content: Before we left, a maester gave you a raven scroll.

author: petyr baelish
content: You are becoming an observant young lady.

author: sansa stark
content: My mother used to say, "dark wings, dark words".

author: petyr baelish
content: An old saying. Inaccurate in this case.

author: sansa stark
content: So it was good news.?

author: petyr baelish
content: My marriage proposal has been accepted.

author: sansa stark
content: I thought you still mourn the death of my beloved Aunt Lysa.

author: waitress
content: Ale?

author: sansa stark
content: I'll have some.

author: podrick
content: My lady!

author: brienne
content: What is it?

author: podrick
content: Sansa Stark. Don't look!

author: brienne
content: You sure?

author: podrick
content: She's dyed her hair, but it's her. She's sitting with Petyr Baelish.

author: brienne
content: Littlefinger?

author: podrick
content: A bunch of knights with him.

author: brienne
content: Bunch? What's a bunch? 100? 6? 20?

author: podrick
content: 10, I think. Too many. My lady, I don't think this is the right--

author: brienne
content: Ready the horses.

author: podrick
content: We only have one horse.

author: brienne
content: Find more.

author: petyr baelish
content: Do you like the taste?

author: sansa stark
content: I don't see what all the fuss is about. Why do men love it so much?

author: petyr baelish
content: It gives some men courage.

author: sansa stark
content: Does it give you courage?

author: guard
content: That's far enough.

author: brienne
content: Lord Baelish, Lady Sansa, my name is Brienne of Tarth.

author: petyr baelish
content: We've met. With Renly Baratheon. What did he say about you? He said, "You're a loyalty comes free of charge." Someone appears to have paid quite a bit for it since then.

author: brienne
content: Lady Sansa, before your mother's death, I was her sworn sword. I gave my word I would find you and protect you. I will shield your back and keep your council, and give my life for yours if need be. I swear it by the old gods and the new.

author: petyr baelish
content: Please, Lady Brienne. No need for such formality. You are Catelyn Stark's sworn sword?

author: brienne
content: I was.

author: petyr baelish
content: Strange. I knew Cat from the time we were children. She never mentioned you.

author: brienne
content: It was after Renly's murder.

author: petyr baelish
content: Ah, yes. You were accused of killing him.

author: brienne
content: I tried to save him.

author: petyr baelish
content: But you were accused.

author: brienne
content: By men who didn't see what happened.

author: petyr baelish
content: Then what did happen?

author: brienne
content: He was murdered by a shadow. A shadow with a face of Stannis Baratheon.

author: petyr baelish
content: A shadow? With a face? This woman swore to protect Renly; she failed. She swore to protect your mother; she failed. Why would I want somebody with your history of failure guiding Lady Sansa?

author: brienne
content: Why should you have any say in her affairs?

author: petyr baelish
content: Because I am her uncle. I married her Aunt Lysa shortly before my belovedo s untimely death. We're family now, and you're an outsider. Forgive me, Lady Brienne, but experiences made me wary of outsiders.

author: brienne
content: Lady Sansa, if we can have a word alone--

author: sansa stark
content: No.

author: brienne
content: Please, my lady. If I could explain--

author: sansa stark
content: I saw you at Joffrey's wedding bowing to the king.

author: brienne
content: Neither of us wanted to be there. Sometimes we don't have a choice.

author: sansa stark
content: And sometimes we do. You should leave.

author: petyr baelish
content: We don't want our new friend wandering the countryside alone. The roads of these parts aren't safe. Why don't you stay?

author: knight
content: He asked you to stay.

author: guard
content: After her!

author: brienne
content: Podrick!

author: podrick
content: Stop, stop, stop! That's a good boy.

author: knight
content: I guess that means you're unarmed.

author: brienne
content: Down, Podrick, down!

author: brienne
content: Podrick?

author: podrick
content: Yes, my lady?

author: brienne
content: You can stand now.

author: podrick
content: Yes, my lady. Sansa Stark?

author: brienne
content: Wary of strangers, as she should me. I saw her riding on the East Trail with Littlefinger. We'll follow them.

author: podrick
content: My lady, if those Stark girls refused your service, maybe you're released from your vow.

author: brienne
content: I swore to their mother I'd protect those girls.

author: podrick
content: If they don't want your protection--

author: brienne
content: Do you think she's safe from Littlefinger?

author: podrick
content: No, my lady.

author: brienne
content: Get your horse.

author: jaime lannister
content: A summons from the queen.

author: cersei lannister
content: There are only two like it in the world

author: jaime lannister
content: It's a threat.

author: cersei lannister
content: Of course it's a threat! Our daughter's in Dorne surrounded by people who hate our family. "It's a threat."

author: jaime lannister
content: No note.

author: cersei lannister
content: They blame us for the death of Oberyn and his sister, and every other tragedy that's befallen their cursed country. I will burn their cities to the ground if they touch her!

author: jaime lannister
content: Softer.

author: cersei lannister
content: What?

author: jaime lannister
content: Not so loud.

author: cersei lannister
content: Our daughter's in danger, and you're worried I'm speaking too loudly!

author: jaime lannister
content: The world can't know knows she's our daughter.

author: cersei lannister
content: Then don't call her your daughter. You've never been a father to her.

author: jaime lannister
content: If I was the father to any of my children, they'd be stoned in the streets.

author: cersei lannister
content: And what has your caution brought? Our eldest child murdered at his own wedding. Our only daughter shipped off to Dorne. Our baby boy sent to marry that smirking whore from Highgarden.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll make things better.

author: cersei lannister
content: You never made anything better.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm going to Dorne. I'll bring our daughter home.

author: cersei lannister
content: You can't just ask Prince Doran to give her back! She's promised his son.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not going to ask him anything.

author: cersei lannister
content: You go there with an army, it's an act of war.

author: jaime lannister
content: No army. Do you know where they're keeping her?

author: cersei lannister
content: Oberyn mentioned the Water Gardens.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll find her. Is there anything else, your grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: You're going to Dorne? A one-handed man? Alone?

author: jaime lannister
content: I never said I was going alone.

author: lollys stokeworth
content: No sunflowers. I don't like yellow. Roses are very nice, definitely roses. And music. I adore music. But no flutes, I hate flutes! We can have a harp if you like, but no flutes. Then there's the food. Food is the most important thing, don't you agree? We're going to need pigeon pies. That's what they eat in the capital, don't they?

author: lollys
content: Don't they?

author: bronn
content: Don't who?

author: lollys
content: People eat pigeon pie in the capital.

author: bronn
content: They certainly do, my dear. They certainly do.

author: bronn
content: It's a fine place, isn't it? A fine place. I never thought I'd end up settling down in a place like this.

author: lollys
content: You won't.

author: bronn
content: Pardon?

author: lollys
content: We won't get to live at Stokeworth. When Mother dies, my sister gets the castle because she's older.

author: bronn
content: Oh.

author: lollys
content: She hates me. She calls me mean names, and sometimes even still she pulls my hair when Mother isn't looking.

author: bronn
content: You know what I think? I think you're a good person. And your sister is a mean person.

author: lollys
content: She is.

author: bronn
content: I've been all over the world. And if there's one thing I've learned, it's that meanness comes around. People like your sister, they always get what's coming to them eventually. One way or another.

author: lollys
content: Who's that?

author: bronn
content: Jaime fucking Lannister.

author: bronn
content: Ser Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: Ser Bronn of the Blackwater.

author: bronn
content: I was very sorry to hear about your father.

author: jaime lannister
content: Thank you.

author: bronn
content: This is my betrothed, Lollys.

author: jaime lannister
content: A pleasure.

author: bronn
content: Run along, love.

author: jaime lannister
content: Beautiful bride you've chosen. When were you planning on getting married?

author: bronn
content: Just get on with it.

author: jaime lannister
content: On with what?

author: bronn
content: What you're here for. There's no way this little visit could possibly mean anything good for me.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's very good for you.

author: bronn
content: Lollys will be marrying Ser Wyllis Bracken.

author: jaime lannister
content: Mmm.

author: bronn
content: We made a deal, your sister and I.

author: jaime lannister
content: I would have advised against that.

author: bronn
content: How is this good for me?

author: jaime lannister
content: Cause you're going to come with me and help me with something important. And when we return, I'm going to give you a much better girl, and a much better castle.

author: bronn
content: Return from where?

author: jaime lannister
content: As far south as south goes.

author: trystane
content: My future queen.

author: areo
content: The prince does not wish to be disturbed.

author: ellaria
content: Remove myself from my path, or I'll take that long axe and shove it--

author: doran
content: Captain. Let her pass.

author: ellaria
content: Your brother was murdered, and you sit here at the Water Gardens, staring at the sky and doing nothing.

author: doran
content: Oberyn was slain during a trial by combat. By law, that is not murder.

author: ellaria
content: Your brother--

author: doran
content: You don't have to remind me. He was my brother long before he was anything to you.

author: ellaria
content: What will you do about his death.

author: doran
content: I will bury him. I will mourn for him.

author: ellaria
content: You would have me go to war?

author: doran
content: You would have me go to war?

author: ellaria
content: The whole country would have you go to war.

author: doran
content: Then we are lucky the whole country does not decide.

author: ellaria
content: The Sand Snakes are with me. They have the love of their people. They will avenge your father while you sit here in your chair doing nothing.

author: ellaria
content: Oberyn is dead. And this Lannister girl skips about the Water Gardens eating our food, breathing our air. How many of your brothers and sisters do they have to kill?

author: doran
content: I loved my brother. And you made him very happy. For that you will always have a place in my heart. But we do not mutilate little girls for vengeance. Not here. Not while I rule.

author: ellaria
content: And how long will that be?

author: daario
content: The Unsullied are too conspicuous.

author: daario
content: Anyone can see you coming from a mile off. Of course you haven't found any Sons of the Harpy. You haven't, have you?

author: daario
content: My Second Sons, on the other hand, they drink, they whore, fight in the streets--they blend in. They overhear things in taverns, follow people from the taverns to nice, quiet alleys, break a few fingers, overhear a few more things. Before you know it...

author: grey worm
content: No one here. We go.

author: daario
content: In a hurry? You're afraid?

author: grey worm
content: Unsullied fear nothing.

author: daario
content: Right. That's your problem. You understood fear once, long ago, but you've forgotten what it means. Someone who's forgotten fear has forgotten how to hide.

author: daario
content: Fear is useful that way.

author: mossador
content: Sons of the Harpy, they want to put a collar back on my neck. On all of our necks. Please, Your Grace, you must kill him.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It would send a message.

author: barristan
content: I think you should exercise restraint, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why?

author: barristan
content: For one thing, he may have valuable information.

author: daario
content: The Son of the Harpy has no more valuable information.

author: barristan
content: How do you know that?

author: daario
content: Because I questioned him.

author: hizdahr
content: And the information you did get, he is young and poor.

author: mossador
content: He is born free.

author: hizdahr
content: Why should he want to bring back slavery? What did it do for him?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Perhaps the only thing that gave him pride was knowing that there was someone lower than he was.

author: mossador
content: They pay him. Great families afraid to do a thing. They pay poor man to do it for them.

author: hizdahr
content: And how do you know this?

author: mossador
content: Everyone knows this.

author: hizdahr
content: I don't know it, and I'm the head of a great family.

author: barristan
content: We do not know what this man did or didn't do. Give him a trial, at least. A fair trial. Show all of the citizens of Meereen that you are better than those who would depose. Teach them a better way.

author: mossador
content: I do not know the place from where Old Ser comes. Things maybe are different there, I hope. But here, in Meereen, before Daenerys Stormborn, they own us. So we learn much about them or we do not live long. They teach me what they are. Mercy, fair trial

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you all for your counsel.

author: barristan
content: Your Grace, a word, please, I beg you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: About what?

author: barristan
content: About your father. About the Mad King.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Mad King? You're here to remind me of my enemies' lies? Consider me reminded.

author: barristan
content: Your Grace, I served in his Kingsguard. I was at his side from the first. Your enemies did not lie.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Go on.

author: barristan
content: When the people rose in revolt against him, your father set their towns and castles aflame. He murdered sons in front of their fathers. He burned men alive with Wildfire, and laughed as they screamed. And his efforts to stamp out dissent led to rebellion that killed every Targaryen except two.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not my father.

author: barristan
content: No, Your Grace. Thank the gods. But the Mad King gave his enemies the justice he thought they deserved. And each time it made him feel powerful and right. Until the very end.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will not have the Son of the Harpy executed without a fair trial.

author: barristan
content: Your Grace.

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's a bug.

author: varys
content: Yes, best be careful. You might accidentally consume some solid food.

author: tyrion lannister
content: When I agreed to come with you, did I misrepresent my intentions? Besides, what is there for me to do inside this fucking box?

author: varys
content: You don't like it?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I want to take a walk.

author: varys
content: You can't. Cersei has offered a lordship to the man who brings her your head.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She ought to offer her cunt. Best part of her for the best part of me. Well, I suppose a box is as good a place for me as anywhere.

author: varys
content: Are we really going to spend the entire road to Volantis talking about the futility of everything?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're right. No point. The road to Volantis? You said we were going to Meereen. What's in Volantis?

author: varys
content: The road to Meereen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And what do you hope to find at the end of the road to Meereen?

author: varys
content: I told you. A ruler.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We've already got a ruler. Everywhere has already got a ruler. Every pile of shit on the side of every road has someone's banner hanging from it.

author: varys
content: You were quite good, you know. At ruling. During your brief tenure as Hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I didn't rule. I was a servant.

author: varys
content: Still, a man of talent.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Managed to kill a lot of people.

author: varys
content: Yes, but showed great promise in other areas as well.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She wanted me to leave King's Landing. She begged me. I wouldn't go.

author: varys
content: Why?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cause I liked it. Power. Even as a servant.

author: varys
content: People follow leaders. And they will never follow us. They find us repulsive.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I find us repulsive.

author: varys
content: And we find them repulsive, which is why we surround ourselves with large, comfortable boxes to keep them away. And yet, no matter what we do, people like you and me are never really satisfied inside the box. Not for long.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're right. Let's go for a walk.

author: varys
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How many dwarves are there in the world? Is Cersei going to kill them all?

author: cersei lannister
content: Not him.

author: meryn
content: Are you trying to deceive your Queen? Shall I throw them in a cell, Your Grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: That won't be necessary, Ser Meryn. I don't want to dissuade the other hunters. Mistakes will be made.

author: hunters
content: Thank you, Your Grace. Thank you.

author: cersei lannister
content: Take the head.

author: qyburn
content: Pardon me, Your Grace. I would take it, if you don't mind. It could prove useful for my work.

author: cersei lannister
content: Very good.

author: qyburn
content: Over there will be fine.

author: meryn
content: You heard the man. Over there.

author: kevan
content: You're the Hand of the King?

author: cersei lannister
content: No, Uncle. Clearly it would not be appropriate for a woman to assume that role. I'm merely advising my son until he comes of age and chooses a Hand for himself.

author: mace tyrell
content: Your Grace, I would be willing to serve provisionally as the King's Hand until he becomes old enough--

author: cersei lannister
content: You're a good man, Lord Tyrell, but I don't imagine you'll have the time. In addition to being Master of Ships, the king has appointed you Master of Coin.

author: mace
content: Oh, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: He called your experience and wisdom in financial matters unparalleled. He said he would be honored to have you represent the crown's interests in the same.

author: mace
content: The honor is all mine, Your Grace.

author: pycelle
content: Your Grace, in the past on several occasions, a Grand Maester has served as the King's Hand.

author: cersei lannister
content: The King has named Qyburn the new Master of Whisperers.

author: pycelle
content: Your Grace, him? This man? This embarrassment to the Citadel? Your Grace, what qualifications can he possibly have for this post?

author: cersei lannister
content: The qualification of loyalty, Grand Maester. That's far more than the eunuch ever had. Far more than many ever have.

author: pycelle
content: I must say I cannot see--

author: cersei lannister
content: Uncle Kevan, in light of your position as commander of the Lannister armies, it would please the king if you would serve as his Master of War. No man living better deserves the title.

author: kevan
content: That is kind of you to say. I would like to hear it from the king himself.

author: cersei lannister
content: The king is very busy at this moment.

author: kevan
content: He should be here, learning what it means to rule.

author: cersei lannister
content: He is learning. On this occasion, in his capacity as ruler, he's asked me to speak on his behalf.

author: kevan
content: I returned to the capital to pay my respects to my brother. And to you. And to serve the king. I did not return to the capital to serve as your puppet. To watch you stack the small council with sycophants. Sending your own brother away so he wouldn't be--

author: cersei lannister
content: My brother has left the capital to lead a sensitive diplomatic mission.

author: kevan
content: What mission?

author: cersei lannister
content: That is not your concern as Master of War.

author: kevan
content: I do not recognize your authority to dictate what is and is not my concern. You are the Queen Mother. Nothing more.

author: cersei lannister
content: You would abandon your king in his time of need?

author: kevan
content: If he wants to send for me, I will be waiting for him. At Casterly Rock.

author: shireen
content: Come on. You know this one. It looks like an animal.

author: gilly
content: Snake. Snake... S! It's an S!

author: shireen
content: Right, very good!

author: sam
content: Hmm! Did you know that the youngest Lord Commander in history, Osric Stark, was elected at the age of 10?

author: gilly
content: I know "S".

author: shireen
content: You'll learn, I promise. I taught Ser Davos, and old people are terrible at learning new things.

author: gilly
content: Well, you're a wonderful teacher. Very patient!

author: sam
content: I only said that the more time you spend practicing, the faster you'll be able to read.

author: gilly
content: That's alright. We're doing just fine. I'm sure you and Ostrich Stark have a lot to talk about.

author: gilly
content: How old were you when you learned to read?

author: shireen
content: Three.

author: sam
content: Three?! Who taught you, your mother?

author: shireen
content: No. Old Maester Cressen did. I had a lot of time to practice. My mother kept me inside because...

author: gilly
content: What do you call it in the South, what happened to your face?

author: shireen
content: Greyscale. What do you call it north of the Wall?

author: gilly
content: I don't know. But two of my sisters had it. They both died. How did they cure you?

author: shireen
content: I don't remember. I was a baby. Lots of people came and tried, I think. Whatever they did, it went away. What happened to your sisters?

author: gilly
content: My father made them move out of the keep into the huts outside. None of us were allowed to go near them. But we heard them. Especially at night. They started to sound... not like themselves.

author: sam
content: Did you ever see them?

author: gilly
content: Only once at the end. They were covered with it. Their faces, their arms. They acted like animals. My father had to drag them out to the woods on a rope.

author: shireen
content: What did he do to them in the woods?

author: shireen
content: Mother.

author: selyse
content: Leave us.

author: sam
content: Your Grace.

author: selyse
content: You need to stay away from that girl.

author: shireen
content: Why?

author: selyse
content: She's a wildling.

author: shireen
content: Her name's Gilly. She's nice. I'm teaching her to read.

author: selyse
content: She's a wildling. Your father defeated their people. He executed her king for treason. They could strike at him by striking at you.

author: shireen
content: Gilly wouldn't do that.

author: selyse
content: You have no idea what people will do. All your books and you still don't know.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I ordered Mance Rayder burnt at the stake. You prevented that order from being carried out. You showed mercy to Mance Rayder. A king's word is law. Perhaps you should ask Ser Davos how much mercy I show to lawbreakers. Show too much kindness, people won't fear you. If people don't fear you, they don't follow you.

author: jon snow
content: With respect, Your Grace, the free folk will never follow you, no matter what you do. You're the man who burned their king alive.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Who then? You?

author: jon snow
content: No. Only one of their own.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Do you know this wretched girl Lyanna Mormont?

author: jon snow
content: The Lord Commander's niece.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Lady of Bear Island, and a child of 10. I asked her to commit her house to my cause, that's her response.

author: jon snow
content: Bear Island knows no king but the King in the North, whose name is Stark.

author: stannis baratheon
content: That amuses you?

author: jon snow
content: I apologize, Your Grace. Northerners can be a bit like the free folk. Loyal to their own.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I know. My brother Robert went on often and loudly about how difficult it was to control them - even with your father's help.

author: davos
content: Tonight, the Night's Watch elect a new Lord Commander. Ser Alliser Thorne is going to win.

author: jon snow
content: Most likely.

author: davos
content: Unpleasant man. He thinks you're a traitor. What's your life going to be like on the Wall with Thorne in command?

author: jon snow
content: Unpleasant, I expect.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Your bravery made him look weak. He'll punish you for it. I don't punish men for bravery. I reward them.

author: jon snow
content: I don't doubt it, Your Grace. But I'm a brother of the Night's Watch. I've pledged them my life, my honor, my sword. I don't know what I have left to give you.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You can give me the North.

author: jon snow
content: I can't. Even if I wanted to, I'm a bastard. A Snow.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Kneel before me. Lay your sword at my feet. Pledge me your service and you'll rise again as Jon Stark, Lord of Winterfell.

author: sam
content: He'll make you a Stark with the stroke of a pen?

author: jon snow
content: It's the first thing I ever remember wanting. I'd daydream that my father would ask the king, and just like that I would never be the bastard of Winterfell again.

author: sam
content: You deserve this. You do. I couldn't be happier for you.

author: jon snow
content: I'm going to refuse him.

author: sam
content: But you'd be Lord of Winterfell.

author: jon snow
content: I swore a vow to the Night's Watch. If I don't take my own word seriously, what sort of Lord of Winterfell would I be?

author: alliser
content: Crowded. You'd think we were serving venison stew.

author: aemon
content: Does anyone wish to speak for candidates before we cast our tokens for the 998th Lord Commander of the Night's Watch?

author: janos
content: Ser Alliser Thorne is not just a knight, he's a man of true nobility. He was acting commander when the Wall came under attack, and led us to victory against the wildlings.

author: men
content: Hear, hear.

author: janos
content: He's a veteran of 100 battles and has been a defender of the Watch and the Wall almost all of his life. He's the only true choice.

author: aemon
content: Is there anyone else?

author: shadow tower brother
content: Ser Denys Mallister joined the Watch as a boy and has served loyally longer than any other ranger. Through 10 winters he served. As commander of the Shadow Tower, he kept the wildlings away. We could do no better.

author: aemon
content: If there's no one else, we will begin the voting. The triangular tokens count for Ser Alliser Thorne. The square tokens for Ser Denys Mallister. Each brother will--

author: sam
content: Maester Aemon.

author: aemon
content: Samwell Tarly. Go on.

author: janos
content: Sam the Slayer.

author: janos
content: Another wildling lover just like his friend Jon Snow. How's your lady love Slayer?

author: sam
content: Her name is Gilly. Brother Slynt knows her quite well. They cowered together in the larder during the battle for the Wall.

author: janos
content: Lies!

author: sam
content: A wildling girl, a baby, and Lord Janos. I found him there when the battle was over in a puddle of his own making.

author: sam
content: Whilst Lord Janos was hiding with the women and children, Jon Snow was leading.

author: sam
content: Ser Alliser fought bravely, it is true. And when he was wounded, it is Jon who saved us. He took charge of the wall's defense. He killed the Magnar of the Thenns. He went North to deal with Mance Rayder, knowing it almost certainly meant his own death. Before that, he led the mission to avenge Lord Commander Mormont. Mormont himself chose Jon to be his steward. He saw something in Jon, and now we've all seen it, too. He may be young, but he's the commander we turned to when the night was darkest.

author: alliser
content: I can't argue with any of that. But who does Jon Snow want to command? Night's Watch or the wildlings? Everyone knows he loved a wildling girl and spoke with Mance Rayder many times. What would have happened in that tent between those two old friends if Stannis's army hadn't come along? We all saw him put the King-beyond-the-Wall out of his misery. Do you want to choose a man who has fought the wildlings all his life, or a man who makes love to them?

author: aemon
content: It is time.

author: brother
content: It appears to be a tie, Maester.

author: brothers
content: Jon Snow! Jon Snow! Jon Snow! Jon Snow!

author: man
content: You. You!

author: man
content: What have you got there?

author: man
content: I said--

author: arya stark
content: Turn around and go. Turn around and go.

author: man
content: That's a nice little sword. Worth 100 pieces, a sword like that.

author: arya stark
content: Nothing's worth anything to dead men.

author: men
content: Quickly, go, go!

author: arya stark
content: Who are you? Why were they scared of you?

author: old man
content: You lost this.

author: arya stark
content: You said there was no Jaqen H'ghar here.

author: jaqen hghar
content: There isn't. A man is not Jaqen H'ghar.

author: arya stark
content: Well who are you then?

author: jaqen hghar
content: No one. And that is who a girl must become.

author: harpy
content: She doesn't belong here. And no matter how many of your traitors call her "Mhysa", she will never be your mother.

author: mossador
content: For you, Mhysa. You wanted the Harpy dead, but your hands were tied. I set you free, as you did all of us.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He was our prisoner, awaiting trial. You had no right.

author: mossador
content: He would rather rip your city apart than see slaves lifted from the dirt.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: There are no more slaves. There are no more Masters.

author: mossador
content: Then who lives in the Pyramids? Who wears gold masks and murders your children? When Grey Worm came to us, I was the first to take up the knife for you. I remember the look on my father's face as I struck down his Master, who had traded his infant son for a dog. My father died in the fighting. If we allow the Sons of the Harpy to return us to chains, he never lived.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Harpy's life was not yours to take. Once, the Masters were the law--

author: mosador
content: and now you are the law!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The law is the law. Take him.

author: crowd
content: Mhysa! Myhsa!

author: hizdahr
content: She should have cut off the traitor's head in the Great Pyramid and been done with it.

author: daario
content: Which is what I keep telling her to do to you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You opened your gates to me because I promised you freedom and justice. One cannot exist without the other.

author: crowd
content: Brother! Brother!

author: mossador
content: Mhysa, please! Forgive me!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: A citizen of Meereen was awaiting trial and this man murdered him. The punishment is death.

author: crowd
content: Mercy! Mercy!

author: mossador
content: Mhysa...

author: crowd
content: Mhysa...

author: barristan
content: I'll stand guard outside your door tonight, Your Grace.

author: grey worm
content: We all guard tonight.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Leave me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Drogon...

author: end
content: EPISODE

author: man
content: Valar morghulis.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Valar dohaeris.

author: arya stark
content: I've been sweeping this floor for days.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Good.

author: arya stark
content: I didn't come here to sweep floors.

author: jaqen hghar
content: No? Why come, then?

author: arya stark
content: You said that I could be your apprentice. You said you'd teach me how to a Faceless Man.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A man teaches a girl. . Valar dohaeris. All men must serve. Faceless men, most of all. .

author: arya stark
content: I want to serve. .

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl wants to serve herself. Here we serve the Many-Faced God, to serve well. A girl must become no-one.

author: arya stark
content: Which one is the Many-Faced God? I see the Stranger. I see the Drowned God. I see the Weirwood Face.

author: jaqen hghar
content: There is only one god. A girl knows his name. And all men know his gift.

author: arya stark
content: Where are they taking him?

author: bystanders
content: Queen Margaery! Queen Margaery! Queen Margaery!

author: margaery tyrell
content: I am his/hers, and she/he is mine. From this day, until the end of my days.

author: tommen lannister
content: Did I hurt you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: No. You were lovely.

author: tommen lannister
content: It all happened so fast.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Yes. .

author: tommen lannister
content: I was scared maybe I hurt you, it sounded

author: margaery tyrell
content: No, no, no. You're very sweet. The sweetest king who ever lived.

author: tommen lannister
content: This is what I want to do all day, every day for the rest of my life.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Wouldn't that be glorious? . Shouldn't we rest a little while? Just to catch our breath, there's no rush, is there?

author: tommen lannister
content: Of course not. Are you hungry? Shall I have them bring you some cake or pomegranate juice?

author: margaery tyrell
content: No, I'm fine. I just want you all to myself. I want to know everything there is to know about King Tommen First of His Name.

author: tommen lannister
content: King Tommen. It still sounds strange to me. Does Queen Margaery sound strange to you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: So strange… Husband.

author: tommen lannister
content: Wife. . Sometimes it feels odd. I'm the king, I've married the most beautiful woman in the world, , and it's all because my brother died.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I understand. But it's not your fault, you know that, don't you? You mustn't feel guilty.

author: tommen lannister
content: I don't feel guilty. That's what's odd.

author: tommen lannister
content: Do you like to sail?

author: margaery tyrell
content: I love to sail.

author: tommen lannister
content: I do, too.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I think we're going to be very happy, you and I.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Living in a tower so high, it touches the clouds. Of course my grandmother couldn't wait to go home. The capital is not for everyone, I suppose. Does your mother like it here?

author: tommen lannister
content: I don't think so. She told me never to trust anyone in King's Landing.

author: margaery tyrell
content: It's so wonderful to have her watching over you. A lioness guiding her cub. .

author: tommen lannister
content: Well, but I'm a man now.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You are. And the king. . But you'll always be her baby-boy.

author: tommen lannister
content: I suppose.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I adore how she has always been so generous with me, so kind. And the horror she's had to injure. . Losing her husband, her eldest child and her father. It's no wonder she's so protective of you. She'll never let you out of her sight.

author: cersei lannister
content: You look very much in love. The first days of marriage are often so blissful. She's certainly very pretty, isn't she? Like a doll, she smiles quite a lot. Do you think she's intelligent? I can't quite tell. Not that it matters.

author: tommen lannister
content: Do you ever miss Casterly Rock?

author: cersei lannister
content: There's nothing for me in Casterly Rock.

author: tommen lannister
content: That's where you grew up. . You always told me that you liked the people there better. You said that King's Landing smelled of horse dung and sour milk.

author: cersei lannister
content: Why are we speaking of Casterly Rock?

author: tommen lannister
content: The way that you talked about it, I always thought that you missed it. That you... That it was your real home.

author: cersei lannister
content: This is my real home now. Where my family lives.

author: tommen lannister
content: I want you to be happy, mother.

author: cersei lannister
content: I know that. I know you do, my sweet boy.

author: tommen lannister
content: But wouldn't you be happier in Casterly Rock?

author: margaery tyrell
content: I said, "Darling, surely 4 times is enough, are you trying to set a new record?" . And he said, "Well, what is the record? I'm sure we can break it."

author: margaery tyrell
content: Mother! . Welcome.

author: cersei lannister
content: Don't you look lovely. Marriage agrees with you.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Can we bring you anything to eat or drink? I wish we had some wine for you. It's a bit early in the day for us.

author: cersei lannister
content: No, no. I, I can't stay. I just wanted to let you know if, there is ever anything I can do for you.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You are very sweet.

author: cersei lannister
content: Tommen seems quite taken with his new queen.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I absolutely adore him. You raised a gallant young man. I'm forever grateful.

author: cersei lannister
content: Good. Good. I'm glad to hear you're happy.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Ecstatic. I really am. Exhausted, to be honest, but what can I expect, he is half lion, half stag. .

author: cersei lannister
content: I'll leave you to it then. .

author: margaery tyrell
content: Oh, forgive me, I haven't been at Court for long, I get so confused. What's the proper way to address you now? Queen Mother or Dowager Queen?

author: cersei lannister
content: There's no need for such formalities.

author: margaery tyrell
content: In any event, judging from the King's enthusiasm, the Queen Mother will be a Queen Grandmother soon.

author: cersei lannister
content: Won't that be a lovely day.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Can you imagine the celebrations? They'll ring the bells all day and night.

author: cersei lannister
content: Remember. Anything you need.

author: roose
content: We can't hold the North with terror alone.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You can't hold the North if you let these lesser lords insult us.

author: roose
content: I sent you there to collect taxes, not bodies.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Lord Cerwyn refused to pay. Said the Warden of the North would always be a Stark, and he'd be damned if he kissed a traitor's boot.

author: roose
content: He left you no choice.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I flayed him living, along with his wife and brother. Made his son watch.

author: roose
content: And?

author: ramsay bolton
content: The new Lord Cerwyn paid his taxes.

author: roose
content: I have something important to tell you. Stop eating and listen.

author: roose
content: We don't have enough men to hold the North if the other Houses rise up against us. Do you understand that?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Our pact with the Lannisters protects -

author: roose
content: I had a pact with Tywin Lannister, and Tywin Lannister is dead. The remaining Lannisters are a thousand miles away dealing with that fact. They've never once in the history of the Seven Kingdoms sent their army this far north. If you think they will for us, you're a fool. We become a great house by entering in alliances with other houses, and parleying those alliances into greater power. The best way to forge a lasting alliance isn't by peeling a man's skin off. The best way is marriage. . Now that you're a Bolton by royal decree, it's time you married a suitable bride. And as it happens, I found the perfect girl to solidify our hold in the North.

author: sansa stark
content: That's Moat Cailin.

author: petyr baelish
content: Yes. A bit shabby, isn't it? You've been here before.

author: sansa stark
content: On our way down to King's Landing, with my father and Arya and… where are you taking me?

author: petyr baelish
content: Home.

author: sansa stark
content: The Boltons have Winterfell. . The marriage proposal, it wasn't for you?

author: petyr baelish
content: No.

author: sansa stark
content: Roose Bolton murdered my brother. He betrayed my family!

author: petyr baelish
content: He did.

author: sansa stark
content: He serves the Lannisters.

author: petyr baelish
content: For now.

author: sansa stark
content: I won't go.

author: petyr baelish
content: Winterfell is your home.

author: sansa stark
content: Not anymore.

author: petyr baelish
content: Always. You're a Stark. Dyeing your hair doesn't change that. You're Sansa Stark. The eldest surviving child of Ned and Catelyn Stark. Your place is in the North.

author: sansa stark
content: I can't marry him. You can't make me. He's a traitor. A murderer.

author: petyr baelish
content: You're not marrying Roose Bolton. No, you'll be marrying his son and heir, Ramsay. One day he'll be Warden of the North and you will -

author: sansa stark
content: No!

author: petyr baelish
content: Sansa -

author: sansa stark
content: No, you can't make me. I will starve myself. I will die before I have to go there.

author: petyr baelish
content: I won't force you to do anything. Don't you know by now how much I care for you? Say the word and we turn the horses round, but listen to me. Listen. . You've been running all your life. Terrible things happened to your family and you weep. You sit alone in a darkened room, mourning their fates. You've been a bystander to tragedy from the day they executed your father. Stop being a bystander, do you hear me? Stop running. There's no justice in the world. Not unless we make it. You loved your family. Avenge them.

author: podrick
content: How do we get through there?

author: brienne
content: We don't. We go around. .

author: podrick
content: It sets miles out of the way. We'll lose sight of them.

author: brienne
content: Doesn't matter. I know where they're going.

author: brienne
content: Aren't you getting a bit old to be a squire? How did you end up squiring for the Imp?

author: podrick
content: He hates that nickname.

author: brienne
content: Well, he's not here to complain about it, is he?

author: podrick
content: I squired for a knight name Ser Lorimer during the War of the Five Kings. One night, he had a bit too much to drink. And he was famished, so he borrowed a ham.

author: brienne
content: He borrowed it?

author: podrick
content: He wasn't a thief. He was drunk and hungry and he wasn't thinking. I was drunk too. He gave me half the ham. Next morning, one of the guards saw him passed out, under a wagon, with the ham bone still in his hand. They hanged the man afternoon. They tied the noose for me too, but, Lord Tywin heard my family name was Payne. So he pardoned me, and sent me to King's Landing to squire for his son.

author: brienne
content: As punishment. For both of you.

author: podrick
content: It didn't seem that way. Lord Tyrion was always very good to me.

author: brienne
content: Yes, all of your lords were very kind to you. All except me. Sorry you have to squire such a nasty person.

author: podrick
content: I'm not sorry. You're the best fighter I've ever seen. You beat The Hound. I'm proud to be your squire.

author: brienne
content: I'm sorry I'm always snapping at you.

author: podrick
content: If you wouldn't snap at me I wouldn't learn anything.

author: brienne
content: You want to be a knight, Pod?

author: podrick
content: Yes.

author: brienne
content: Starting tomorrow, we'll train with the sword twice a day, before we ride in the morning and after we camp for the evening. . And I'm going to show you how to ride properly.

author: podrick
content: Thank you.

author: brienne
content: I can't knight you, but I can teach you how to fight.

author: podrick
content: I suppose that's more important.

author: podrick
content: You weren't a knight, but you were a Kingsguard to Renly Baratheon, weren't you?

author: brienne
content: I was.

author: podrick
content: Lord Tyrion said he was a good man.

author: brienne
content: He was.

author: podrick
content: But how did you end up serving Renly?

author: brienne
content: When I was a girl, my father held a ball. I'm his only living child, so he wants to make a good match for me. He invited dozens of young lords to Tarth. I didn't want to go, but he dragged me to the ballroom. . And it was wonderful. None of the boys noticed how mulish and tall I was. The shoved each other, and threatened to duel if they thought it was their turn to dance. And whispered in my ear how they wanted to marry me and take me back to their castles. . My father smiled at me and I smiled at him. I'd never been so happy. . Till I saw a few of the boys sniggering. And then they all started to laugh, they couldn't keep the game going any longer. They were toying with me. ‘Brienne the Beauty', they called me. Great joke. And I realized I was the ugliest girl alive. A great lumbering beast. I tried to run away, but Renly Baratheon took me in his arms. “Don't let them see your tears,” he told me. “They're nasty little shits. The nasty little shits aren't worth crying over.” He danced with me and none of the other boys could say a word. And he was the king's brother after all.

author: podrick
content: But wasn't he... Lord Tyrion said he was...

author: brienne
content: Yes, Pod, he liked men, I'm not an idiot. He didn't love me, he didn't want me, he danced with me because he was kind and he wouldn't see me hurt. He saved me from being a joke. From that day until his last day. And I couldn't save him in return. Nothing's more hateful than failing to protect the one you love. One day, I will avenge King Renly.

author: podrick
content: But you said a shadow murdered him. How do you fight a shadow?

author: brienne
content: A shadow with the face of Stannis Baratheon. I know it was Stannis. I know it in my heart. Stannis is a man, not a shadow. And a man can be killed.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Lord Commander.

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace.
