author: stannis baratheon
content: I'd like to speak alone.

author: jon snow
content: Olly is my steward now, as I was Lord Commander Mormont's. I want him to attend my meetings, to learn from men with experience. One day, he might command.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Very well. . Have you considered my offer?

author: jon snow
content: I have. And I thank you for it. You do me great honor. All my life I wanted to be Jon Stark.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Say the word and you will be.

author: jon snow
content: But I have to refuse you. I'm Lord Commander of the Night's Watch. My place is here.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I'm giving you a chance to avenge your family. To take back the castle where you grew up. To rule the North.

author: jon snow
content: I wish I could fight beside you. Believe me, I do. But I swore a sacred vow at the Godswood. I pledged my life to the Night's Watch.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You're as stubborn as your father. And as honorable.

author: jon snow
content: I can imagine no higher praise.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I didn't mean it as praise. Honor got your father killed. . But if your mindo s made up, I won't try to persuade you.

author: jon snow
content: May I ask, Your Grace, how long you plan to stay at Castle Black?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Are you bored of us already?

author: jon snow
content: You saved us from Mance Rayder's army. We will never forget that. But it's a question of survival. The Night's Watch can't continue to feed your men and the wildling prisoners indefinitely. Winter is coming.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I know it. We march on Winterfell within the fortnight. Before the snows trap us here.

author: jon snow
content: And the wildlings?

author: stannis baratheon
content: They'd rather burn than fight for me, so be it. I leave their fate to you. You could execute them, that's the safest course. . Or you could see if this Tormund fellow is more willing to compromise than Mance ever was. I assume the brothers of the Night's Watch would rather see the wildlings dead.

author: jon snow
content: Most of the brothers, yes. There's little love for the free folk here. .

author: stannis baratheon
content: You're the Lord Commander. Your decision.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You have many enemies in Castle Black. Have you considered sending Alliser Thorne elsewhere? Give him command of Eastwatch-by-the-Sea.

author: jon snow
content: I heard it was best to keep your enemies close.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Whoever said that didn't have many enemies.

author: davos

author: tommen lannister
content: My Queen?

author: tommen lannister
content: There was no way to free Ser Loras without violence.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You're the King of the Andals, the Lord of the Seven Kingdoms, the Protector of the Realm. And you let a band of fanatics imprison your brother by law.

author: tommen lannister
content: I'm going to speak to the High Sparrow.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Are you? When?

author: tommen lannister
content: I--I don't know.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You don't know?

author: tommen lannister
content: He was praying just now.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I have to send word to Grandmother.

author: tommen lannister
content: Will you come back later? .

author: margaery tyrell
content: I need to be with my family, Your Grace. .

author: tommen lannister
content: Of course.

author: selyse
content: You think highly of this boy.

author: jon snow
content: Good.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Lord Commander of the Night's Watch.

author: selyse
content: A bastard by some tavern slut.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Perhaps, but that wasn't Ned Stark's way.

author: selyse
content: I should have given you a son.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Not your fault.

author: selyse
content: Whose then? . I gave you nothing but weakness. . And deformity. .

author: melisandre
content: Those scars mean nothing to the Lord of Light.

author: selyse
content: My Lady.

author: melisandre
content: Her father is the Lordo s chosen King. And her father's blood runs through her veins.

author: melisandre
content: You march on Winterfell soon?

author: stannis baratheon
content: We must. To beat the snows.

author: melisandre
content: Once before you put your faith in Ser Davos and left me behind. I hope you won't make that mistake again.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I won't. I need you.

author: melisandre
content: You only need faith, my King.

author: stannis baratheon
content: And you, my Lady, what do you need?

author: melisandre
content: To serve my Lord.

author: sam
content: Lord Ashford. . Lady Caulfield. . Lord Smallwood.

author: jon snow
content: Never even heard of these people.

author: sam
content: They haven't heard of you either. . But we need men and they have some.

author: jon snow
content: And how many men does this Lord Mazin have to send us?

author: sam
content: More than Lord Wibberley.

author: jon snow
content: Not him.

author: sam
content: I know, I'm sorry, but we need men and supplies. And Roose Bolton is the Warden of The North.

author: jon snow
content: He murdered my brother.

author: sam
content: We swore to be the Watchers on the Wall. We can't watch the Wall with 50 men. And we can't get more men without help from the Warden of the North.

author: sam
content: Apologies, my Lady.

author: melisandre
content: Lord Commander.

author: jon snow
content: How can I help you?

author: melisandre
content: Come with us when we ride south. . None of us know the castle as well as you do. Its hidden tunnels, its weaknesses, its people. Winterfell was your home once. Don't you want to chase the rats out of it? .

author: jon snow
content: Castle Black is my home now. Night's Watch takes no part in the wars of the Seven Kingdoms.

author: melisandre
content: There's only one war. Life against death. Come. Let me show what you're fighting for. .

author: jon snow
content: You're gonna show me some vision in the fire. Forgive me, my Lady. But I don't trust in visions.

author: melisandre
content: No visions. No magic. Just life.

author: melisandre
content: Do you feel my heart beating? This power in you, you resist it, and that's your mistake. Embrace it.

author: melisandre
content: The Lord of Light made us male and female. Two parts of a greater whole. We are joining this power. Power to make life, power to make light, and power to cast shadows.

author: jon snow
content: I don't think Stannis would like that very much.

author: melisandre
content: Then we shouldn't tell him. .

author: jon snow
content: I can't.

author: melisandre
content: Why?

author: jon snow
content: I swore a vow. . I loved another.

author: melisandre
content: The dead don't need lovers. Only the living.

author: jon snow
content: I know. But I still love her.

author: melisandre
content: You know nothing, Jon Snow.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Are you lonely?

author: shireen
content: Just bored.

author: stannis baratheon
content: My father used to tell me that boredom indicates a lack of inner resources.

author: shireen
content: Were you bored a lot, too?

author: stannis baratheon
content: I know Castle Black is no place for a child, but I -

author: shireen
content: I like it. . I thought I'd be left at home. I know mother didn't want to bring me. .

author: stannis baratheon
content: Why do you say that?

author: shireen
content: She told me, "I don't want to bring you."

author: stannis baratheon
content: She shouldn't have said that.

author: shireen
content: Are you ashamed of me, father?

author: stannis baratheon
content: When you were an infant, , the Dornish trailer landed on Dragonstone. His goods were junk except for one wooden doll. He'd even sewn a dress on it in the colors of our House. No doubt he'd heard of your birth, and assumed new fathers were easy targets. I still remember how you smiled when I put that doll in your cradle, , and you pressed it to your cheek. . By the time we burnt the doll, it was too late. . I was told you would die. Or worse, the grayscale would go slow. . Let you grow just enough to know the world before taking it away from you. Everyone advised me to send you to the ruins of Valyria to live out your short life with the Stone men, before the sickness spread to the castle. I told them all to go to hell. . I called in every maester on this side of the world. Every healer, every apothecary. They stopped the disease and saved your life. Because you did not belong across the world with the bloody Stone men. . You are the Princess Shireen of House Baratheon. And you are my daughter.

author: petyr baelish
content: I thought I might find you here. . Your Aunt Lyanna.

author: sansa stark
content: Father never talked about her. Sometimes I'd find him down here, lighting the candles. They say she was beautiful.

author: petyr baelish
content: I saw her once. I was a boy, living with your mother's family. Lord Whent had a great tourney at Harrenhal. Everyone was there. The Mad King, your father, Robert Baratheon. And Lyanna, she was already promised to Robert. You can imagine what it was like for me, a boy from nowhere, with nothing to his name, watching these legendary men, tilting at the lists. The last two riders were Barristan Selmy and Rhaegar Targaryen. When Rhaegar won, everyone cheered for the prince. I remember the girls laughing when he took off his helmet and they saw that silver hair. How handsome he was. Until he rode right past his wife, Elia Martell, and all the smiles died. I've never seen so many people so quiet. He rode past his wife, and he lay a crown of winter roses in Lyanna's lap. Blue as frost. How many tens of thousands had to die because Rhaegar chose your aunt?

author: sansa stark
content: Yes, he chose her… and then he kidnapped her and raped her.

author: petyr baelish
content: Come. . Let's speak somewhere the dead can't hear us. .

author: sansa stark
content: Dressed for riding?

author: petyr baelish
content: I am.

author: sansa stark
content: Where are you going?

author: petyr baelish
content: King's Landing.

author: sansa stark
content: King's Landing?

author: petyr baelish
content: Cersei sent for me. . We must not let her sniff out any trouble.

author: sansa stark
content: You can't leave me here!

author: petyr baelish
content: I know how hard it is to live with people you despise, believe me. But it won't be for long.

author: sansa stark
content: How do you know?

author: petyr baelish
content: Stannis Baratheon garrisons at Castle Black. He'll march south to King's Landing before the winter snows block his way. But first, he has to take Winterfell.

author: sansa stark
content: You don't know that.

author: petyr baelish
content: I do. Once he liberates these lands from the Boltons he'll rally your father's bannermen to his cause. With the North behind him, Stannis can finally take the Iron Throne.

author: sansa stark
content: You think he'll defeat the Boltons?

author: petyr baelish
content: He has a larger army. He's the finest military commander in Westeros. A betting man would put his money on Stannis. . As it happens, I am a betting man.

author: sansa stark
content: And if you're right?

author: petyr baelish
content: Stannis takes Winterfell, he rescues you from the most despised family in the North. Grateful for your late father's courageous support for his claim, he names you Wardeness of the North.

author: sansa stark
content: But I, I wouldn't… Wardeness of the North

author: petyr baelish
content: You are the last surviving Stark. He needs you.

author: sansa stark
content: What if you're wrong? What if Stannis never attacks Winterfell, or he does and the Boltons defeat him?

author: petyr baelish
content: Then you will take this Bolton boy, Ramsay, and make him yours.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't know how to do that.

author: petyr baelish
content: Of course you do. He's already fallen for you.

author: sansa stark
content: His father frightens me.

author: petyr baelish
content: He should, he's a dangerous man. But even the most dangerous men can be outmaneuvered. And you've learnt to maneuver from the very best. . I return before too long. . You'll be strong without me. . The North will be yours. Do you believe me?

author: sansa stark
content: I expect I'll be a married woman by the time you return.

author: bronn
content: Breakfast.

author: bronn
content: That would have been a shit way to die.

author: jaime lannister
content: As far as I've seen, they're all shit ways to die.

author: bronn
content: Aye. But your lot like to give the singers a good ending.

author: jaime lannister
content: I don't care what's sung about me when I'm dead.

author: bronn
content: No? Two knights, off to rescue a princess. Sounds like a good song to me.

author: jaime lannister
content: Sounds like all the rest.

author: jaime lannister
content: What about you? What shit way would you choose?

author: bronn
content: In my own keep, drinking my own wine, watching my sons grovel for my fortune.

author: jaime lannister
content: How disappointing. I thought you'd have something more exciting planned.

author: bronn
content: I've had an exciting life. I want my death to be boring. How do you want to go?

author: jaime lannister
content: In the arms of the woman I love.

author: bronn
content: She want the same thing?

author: jaime lannister
content: Let's go.

author: bronn
content: The captain to that ship… What was he, Braavosi?

author: jaime lannister
content: Pentoshi.

author: bronn
content: And he's headed to Oldtown?

author: jaime lannister
content: As I said. Why?

author: bronn
content: What's to stop him from docking down the coast and telling the locals that Jaime Lannister's in Dorne?

author: jaime lannister
content: A bag of gold.

author: bronn
content: I'm not sure you understand how much people hate your family in this part of the world.

author: jaime lannister
content: It was a heavy bag.

author: bronn
content: And I bet he swore all kinds of oaths to get it. But you won't be around if he breaks them.

author: bronn
content: How many you count?

author: jaime lannister
content: Four.

author: bronn
content: How many you think you can take?

author: jaime lannister
content: One, if he's slow.

author: rider
content: Halt!

author: bronn
content: Fucked in the arse. . Hiya! . Morning, lads. Glad we found you.

author: rider
content: Who are you?

author: bronn
content: Cooper. . This is Darnell.

author: rider
content: You're from King's Landing.

author: bronn
content: Accent gave me away? Flea Bottom. Whelped and whipped.

author: rider
content: Why are you here?

author: bronn
content: Our ship capsized in the night. We managed to swim ashore. It was a near thing, really.

author: jaime lannister
content: I thought the sharks would get us. .

author: rider
content: There are no sharks in Dorne.

author: jaime lannister
content: I could have sworn those were shark fins.

author: bronn
content: Dolphins maybe.

author: rider
content: Throw your swords in the sand.

author: bronn
content: Boys, there's no need for this. Just, point us in the right direction. We'll find our way home.

author: rider
content: Swords in the sand! Now!

author: bronn
content: That one should be slow enough.

author: bronn
content: Nice move! .

author: jaime lannister
content: Luck.

author: bronn
content: You had a wonderful teacher.

author: bronn
content: Always wanted a Dornish stallion. Beasts can run a day and night without tiring. We'll ride to the Water Gardens with a nice breeze in our face.

author: jaime lannister
content: First we need to bury these bodies.

author: bronn
content: Birds have to eat too.

author: jaime lannister
content: Corpses raise questions, questions raise armies. We're not here to start a war.

author: bronn
content: Do you know how long it will take us to dig all those holes?

author: jaime lannister
content: I can't dig very well with one hand. Not at all, really.

author: tyene
content: Nama!

author: elaria
content: Nym, Obara.

author: obara
content: Will it be war?

author: elaria
content: Prince Doran will weep for your father, but nothing else. We must avenge Oberyn ourselves.

author: obara
content: Without Doran we have no army to march against the Lannisters.

author: elaria
content: We don't need an army to start a war. . Queen Cersei loves her children, and we have one of them.

author: nymeria
content: We may have a problem.

author: obara
content: A ship's captain, who found me in Planky Town, claiming he had information to sell. He told me he smuggled Jaime Lannister into Dorne.

author: elaria
content: He's come for Myrcella. If he gets to her before we do, we lose our only chance for revenge. You must choose. Doran's way and peace, or my way and war.

author: tyene
content: I'm with you. Always. .

author: elaria
content: Nym? . Obara?

author: obara
content: When I was a child, , Oberyn came to take me to court. I'd never seen this man, and yet he called himself my father. My mother wept, said I was too young, and a girl.

author: obara
content: I made my choice long ago.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank you. . Who are you?

author: jorah mormont
content: Your captor.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you have wine?

author: jorah mormont
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can't sleep without wine.

author: jorah mormont
content: Then stay awake.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're going the wrong way. My sister's in Westeros. Westeros is west! We're heading east.

author: jorah mormont
content: I'm not taking you to your sister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You said you were taking me to the Queen.

author: jorah mormont
content: I am. Queen Daenerys Targaryen. She's the Queen I serve.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What a waste of a good kidnapping. So happens I was heading there myself!

author: jorah mormont
content: What business would you have with the Queen?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Gold and glory. Oh, and hate. If you've ever met my sister, you'd understand. So now that it's clear we're on the same side? . A high born knight from the North of Westeros, down on his luck in Essos. Dragon epaulettes? Bear sigil breast plate. You're Jorah Mormont. I have to ask how, exactly, were you serving your Queen in a whore house, half a world away? Is it possible, that you were running? Why would you be running? And why would she have sent you away? Oh, wait! You were spying on her, weren't you? It's all coming back to me! I was drunk through most of the Small Council meetings, but it's all coming back. You passed notes to Varys's little birds. She found out, didn't she? Found out, and exiled you. . And now you hope to win back her favor with a gift. A risky scheme. One might even say, desperate. Do you think Daenerys would execute me, and pardon you? I'd say the reverse is just as likely.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Everyone looks happy enough from up here. . What?

author: barristan
content: I was thinking of all the times your brother made me go with him down from the Red Keep, into the streets of King's Landing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why?

author: barristan
content: He liked to walk among the people, he liked to sing to them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He sang to them?

author: barristan
content: Yes. Rhaegar would take a spot on the Hook or the Street of Seeds and then he'd sing. Just like all the other minstrels.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what did you do?

author: barristan
content: I made sure no one killed him. And I collected the money. . Well he liked to see how much he could make.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He was good?

author: barristan
content: He was very good. Viserys never told you?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He told me Rhaegar was good at killing people. .

author: barristan
content: Rhaegar never liked killing. He loved singing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what did you do with the money?

author: barristan
content: Well, one time, he gave it to the next minstrel down the street. One time, he gave it to an orphanage in Flea Bottom. One time... we got horribly drunk. .

author: daario
content: Your Grace. Hizdahr is here, waiting in your audience chamber.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many others are there?

author: daario
content: Fifty a hundred.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will you be joining us, Ser Barristan?

author: daario
content: I think I can protect you from Hizdahr Zo Loraq.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I think I can protect me from Hizdahr Zo Loraq. Go, Ser Barristan. Sing a song for me.

author: barristan
content: Your Grace. .

author: hizdahr
content: All men must die. But not all can die in glory.

author: missandei
content: Glory?

author: hizdahr
content: Why else do men fight? Why did your ancestors cross the Narrow Sea and conquer the Seven Kingdoms? So their names would live on. Those who find victory in the fighting pits, will never become kings, but their names will live on. It's the best chance they'll ever have.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Is that what you used to tell men before you set them to butchering each other for sport?

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace, today is the traditional start of the fighting season.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I do not recognize this tradition.

author: hizdahr
content: Traditions are the only thing that will hold this city, your city, together. . Without them, former slaves and former masters have nothing in common. Nothing but centuries of mistrust and resentment. I can't promise this is the answer to all our problems, but it's a start.

author: woman
content: Sons of the Harpy.

author: end
content: EPISODE

author: hizdahr
content: I am so sorry, my queen. He was a good man.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Barristan the Bold" they called him. He crossed a continent to serve me. He was a loyal friend. And he died in an alley, butchered by cowards who hide behind masks.

author: daario
content: We could pull back to the pyramid district, secure it, and use it as a base from which to operate. Then we clean the city out, neighborhood by neighborhood, street by street, until the rats have nowhere left to hide.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I prefer your earlier suggestion. Round up the leaders of each of Meereen's great families and bring them to me.

author: hizdahr
content: But... I'm the leader of my family.

author: hizdahr
content: No, Your Grace! I had nothing to do with this. Your Grace!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Walk forward.

author: man
content: You cannot do this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Another step.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They will eat you, if I tell them to. They may eat you even if I don't. Children. Some say I should give up on them. . But a good mother never gives up on her children. She disciplines them if she must.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But she does not give up on them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who is innocent? Maybe all of you are, , maybe none of you are. Maybe, , I should let the dragons decide.

author: hizdahr
content: All men must die.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't want to overfeed them. Tomorrow perhaps.

author: sam
content: And though Daenerys maintains her grip on Slaver's Bay, forces rise against her from within and without. She refuses to leave until the freedom of the former slaves is secure." She sounds like quite a woman.

author: aemon
content: And she's alone, under siege, no family to guide her or protect her. Her last relation thousands of miles away, useless, dying.

author: sam
content: Don't say that, Maester Aemon.

author: aemon
content: A Targaryen, alone in the world, is a terrible thing.

author: jon snow
content: Maester Aemon.

author: aemon
content: Lord Commander.

author: jon snow
content: Sam, I'd like to speak to the maester alone.

author: jon snow
content: How are you feeling?

author: aemon
content: Oh, like a hundred-year-old man slowly freezing to death.

author: jon snow
content: I need your advice. There's something I want to do, something I have to do. But it'll divide the Night's Watch. Bitterly. Half the men will hate me the moment I give the order.

author: aemon
content: Half the men hate you already, Lord Commander. Do it.

author: jon snow
content: But you don't know what it is.

author: aemon
content: That doesn't matter. You do. You will find little joy in your command. But with luck, you will find the strength to do what needs to be done. Kill the boy, Jon Snow. Winter is almost upon us. Kill the boy, and let the man be born.

author: jon snow
content: Where are the rest of the free folk now? . Where have they gone? . Who leads them?

author: tormund
content: They followed Mance. They won't follow anyone else.

author: jon snow
content: What about you?

author: tormund
content: Hard to lead when you're in chains.

author: jon snow
content: What if I unchained you?

author: tormund
content: Why would you do that?

author: jon snow
content: Because you are not my enemy. And I'm not yours.

author: tormund
content: You sure seemed like my enemy when you were killing my friends.

author: jon snow
content: For 8,000 years the Night's Watch have sworn an oath to be the shield that guards the realms of men. And for 8,000 years we've fallen short of that oath. You belong to the realms of men. All of you.

author: tormund
content: And now everything is going to change?

author: jon snow
content: It is.

author: tormund
content: Why now?

author: jon snow
content: Because now, , I am Lord Commander of the Night's Watch.

author: tormund
content: What would you have me do, , Lord Commander?

author: jon snow
content: I'd have you go north of the Wall. Gather the remaining free folk wherever they are and bring them back here. I'll open the gates for them and let them through. I'll find them lands to settle south of the Wall.

author: tormund
content: They won't kneel for you and neither will I.

author: jon snow
content: I don't want them to kneel for me. I want them to fight with me when the time comes.

author: tormund
content: The day I ask my people to fight with the crows is the day my people cut my guts from my belly and make me eat them.

author: jon snow
content: And how many of your people can't fight? The women, the children, the old, the sick, what happens to them? You're condemning them to death. Worse than death because you're too proud to make peace. Or maybe you're not proud. Maybe you're just a coward.

author: tormund
content: Easy thing to say to a man in chains.

author: jon snow
content: Your people need a leader. And they need to get south of the Wall before it's too late. We don't have much time and they have less. The walkers are coming and they'll hit your people first. I'm not asking you to make peace to save your skin. Make peace to save your people.

author: tormund
content: Most of them are at Hardhome. You know where that is?

author: jon snow
content: Up on Storroldo s Point. I can give you 10 horses and nine other men. You can get there in a week.

author: tormund
content: We'll need ships.

author: jon snow
content: I'll talk to King Stannis about lending you his fleet.

author: tormund
content: All right, then. You're coming with me. You're the Lord Commander of the Night's Watch. They need to hear it from you. They need to know the ships they are boarding won't be torched in the middle of the sea. You come with me, or I don't go.

author: man
content: You'd bring wildlings here, through our gates?

author: jon snow
content: Men, women, and children will die by the thousands if we do nothing.

author: man
content: Let them die. We got our own to worry about. Less enemies for us.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Fewer.

author: davos
content: What?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Nothing.

author: sam
content: There is good farmland in the Gift. . Land that no one uses now. A dozen abandoned villages.

author: man
content: And why do you think the farmers abandoned those villages? Because the wildlings raided them for years. Cut them down! Just like they did this boy's people.

author: allister
content: We've been fighting them all for thousands of years. They've slaughtered villages. They've slaughtered our brothers.

author: jon snow
content: And we've slaughtered theirs.

author: edd
content: I will follow you anywhere, you know that. But they killed Grenn. And they killed Pyp. . They killed 50 of our brothers. I can't forget that. I can't forgive it.

author: jon snow
content: You were at the Fist of the First Men. If we abandon them, you know what they become. We can learn to live with the wildlings or we can add them to the army of the dead. Whatever they are now, they're better than that.

author: jon snow
content: Thank you. . Olly. . If you have something you want to say to me, say it. It's all right.

author: olly
content: You don't mean it, do you? Telling the wildlings you want to make peace. You're just doing it to trick them.

author: jon snow
content: It's not a trick.

author: olly
content: They burned my village. They put an arrow through my father's head right in front of me. They butchered my mother, everyone I ever knew.

author: jon snow
content: I know what it's like to lose the people you love. I know this is hard for you. But winter is coming. We know what's coming with it. We can't face it alone.

author: olly
content: Will there be anything else you need, Lord Commander?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: podrick
content: She's far away from the Lannisters. This is her home. Maybe Lady Sansa is better off here.

author: brienne
content: Better off with the Boltons who murdered her mother and brother? Sansa's in danger even if she doesn't realize it.

author: brienne
content: Thank you. You've lived here a long time?

author: man
content: Aye.

author: brienne
content: Did you know Lord Eddard?

author: man
content: I knew him and his father before him. The Starks are gone now.

author: brienne
content: Not all of them. I know who's inside that castle.

author: man
content: Everyone knows. The Boltons.

author: brienne
content: I'm not talking about the Boltons. I need to get a message to her. To Sansa Stark.

author: man
content: Who are you?

author: brienne
content: Someone who swore to keep her safe.

author: man
content: Swore to who?

author: brienne
content: Her mother.

author: man
content: Her mother's dead.

author: brienne
content: That doesn't release me from an oath. I served Lady Catelyn. I serve her still. Who do you serve?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Come back here. Myranda.

author: myranda
content: I saw you staring at her.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I'm going to marry her. That will involve looking at her from time to time.

author: myranda
content: You said you'd marry me.

author: ramsay bolton
content: And I meant it. When I was a bastard named Snow. But I'm a Bolton now. What I want is no longer the primary consideration. I'm furthering a dynasty.

author: myranda
content: Do you think she's pretty?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Of course I do. I'm not blind.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You think she's pretty, too. I'm looking forward to our wedding night. But don't worry, I'll have plenty of time for you.

author: myranda
content: Perhaps I'll marry, too.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You're the kennel master's daughter. Who are you going to marry, the stable keeper's son? . You're mine. You're not going anywhere. Unless I have to listen to more of your jealousy. Jealousy bores me. You remember what happens to people who bore me. You're not going to bore me, are you, Myranda?

author: myranda
content: Never.

author: woman
content: Beg pardon, my lady. I've come to refill the wash basin.

author: sansa stark
content: Oh, I don't need-

author: woman
content: You still have friends in the North. If you're ever in trouble, light a candle in the highest window of the broken tower.

author: sansa stark
content: But who -

author: woman
content: You're not alone.

author: myranda
content: I like your dress. Who made it for you?

author: sansa stark
content: I made it myself.

author: myranda
content: Really?

author: sansa stark
content: Who, who are you?

author: myranda
content: I'm Myranda, the kennel master's daughter. May I? . Oh, wonderful. The stitching. Who taught you?

author: sansa stark
content: My mother. .

author: myranda
content: I'm sorry for what happened to her.

author: sansa stark
content: Thank you.

author: myranda
content: It's good that she taught you. It was a gift. Now every time you wear something you made, you can remember her.

author: sansa stark
content: I'd rather have a mother.

author: myranda
content: I know. It's not the same. Still, it's good to remember. Remember the way things were. I almost forgot. There's something else to help you remember.

author: myranda
content: Down there at the end.

author: sansa stark
content: What is it?

author: myranda
content: That would spoil the surprise. Go ahead, it's perfectly safe. You won't believe it when you see it.

author: sansa stark
content: Theon?

author: theon greyjoy
content: You shouldn't be here.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You smell particularly ripe this evening. Pour me some wine.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Do you have something to tell me?

author: theon greyjoy
content: No, my lord.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Reek.

author: theon greyjoy
content: She saw me.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Who?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Sansa. Lady Sansa. She came to the kennels.

author: ramsay bolton
content: She saw you?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes. I'm sorry, master. Forgive me. I didn't think -

author: ramsay bolton
content: Come here.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You mustn't keep secrets from me, Reek. Get on your knees.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Give me your hand.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I forgive you.

author: roose
content: I trust you find your chamber suitable, my lady.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes, thank you, my lord.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Allow me.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Mother.

author: walda
content: Thank you, Ramsay.

author: ramsay bolton
content: My lady, we are all a family, we northerners. Our blood ties go back thousands of years. So I'd like to drink to our wedding. May our happiness spread from Moat Cailin to the Last Hearth.

author: roose
content: To your wedding.

author: walda
content: To your wedding.

author: walda
content: It must be difficult for you being in a strange place.

author: sansa stark
content: This isn't a strange place. This is my home. It's the people who are strange.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You're right. Very strange. More wine, please.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I heard you two had reunited. A fitting place for it. . I like to imagine that the last time you spoke was in this very room. Are you still angry with him after he - what he did? Don't worry. The North remembers. I punished him for it. He's not ironborn anymore. Not Theon Greyjoy anymore. He's a new man. A new person, anyway. Aren't you, Reek?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yes, master.

author: ramsay bolton
content: That's his new name, Reek.

author: sansa stark
content: Why are you doing this?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Because Reek has something to say to you. Don't you, Reek? . An apology. Apologize to Lady Sansa for what you did. Apologize for murdering her two brothers.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm sorry.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Look at her, Reek. An apology doesn't mean anything if you're not looking the person in the eye.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Sorry about what?

author: theon greyjoy
content: For killing your brothers.

author: ramsay bolton
content: There, over and done with. Doesn't everyone feel better? I do. That was getting very tense. Whew. . You know what, my lady? What with him having murdered your brothers and the rest of your family gone Reek here is the nearest thing to living kin that you have left. Reek. You will give away the bride. Someone has to. What better person? Good? Good?

author: roose
content: Yes, yes, very good.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Wonderful. .

author: roose
content: Walda and I have some good news as well, since we're all together.

author: walda
content: We're going to have a baby.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm very happy for you.

author: roose
content: From the way she's carrying, Maester Wolkan says it looks like a boy.

author: ramsay bolton
content: How can you be sure?

author: roose
content: Sure of what?

author: ramsay bolton
content: That she's pregnant. I mean how can you tell?

author: roose
content: Maester Wolkan has assured us beyond all doubt.

author: ramsay bolton
content: So how did you manage it?

author: roose
content: Manage what?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Getting her pregnant.

author: roose
content: I imagine you're familiar with the procedure.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Of course, but how did you find it?

author: roose
content: You disgraced yourself at dinner, parading that creature before the Stark girl.

author: ramsay bolton
content: And if it's a boy?

author: roose
content: You're worried about your position.

author: ramsay bolton
content: My position is quite clear. I'm your son until a better alternative comes along.

author: roose
content: You've never asked me about your mother.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Why would I? She had me, she died. And here we are.

author: roose
content: She was a peasant girl. Pretty in a common sort of way. She was the miller's wife. Apparently they had married without my knowledge or consent. So I had him hanged and I took her beneath the tree where he was swaying. She fought me the whole time. She was lucky I didn't hang her, too. A year later she came to my gates with a squalling baby in her arms. A baby she claimed was mine. I nearly had her whipped and the child thrown in the river. . But then I looked at you and I saw then what I see now. You are my son. . Stannis Baratheon has an army at Castle Black. But he won't stay for long. He wants the Iron Throne, and the road to King's Landing comes right through Winterfell. He means to take the North. But the North is ours. It's yours and mine. Will you help me defeat him?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Yes.

author: gilly
content: Is this every book there is?

author: sam
content: Every book there is?

author: gilly
content: In the world.

author: sam
content: Well, no. There are thousands and thousands of books out there. This library is rather small, actually.

author: gilly
content: Where you grew up, were there more books?

author: sam
content: My father's not the most literate man. They say the Citadel has the largest library in the world.

author: gilly
content: Where's that?

author: sam
content: The Citadel? In Oldtown.

author: gilly
content: I'm sorry I don't know things.

author: sam
content: Gilly, look at me. You know how to do a hundred things I can never do. You can build a fire with wet wood. You can cook. You can stitch a wound.

author: gilly
content: I can wash the linens. I can sweep the floor.

author: sam
content: Well -

author: gilly
content: Why does the Citadel have the biggest library?

author: sam
content: It's where they train the maesters.

author: gilly
content: Like Maester Aemon?

author: sam
content: I wanted to be one when I was young. Instead, I became a man of the Night's Watch. Far more adventure up here anyway. I wouldn't have met you.

author: sam
content: Ah, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You're Samwell Tarly?

author: sam
content: I am, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Your father is Randyll Tarly. He defeated my brother at the Battle of Ashford. Only battle Robert ever lost. I told him he shouldn't go so far west so soon, but he never listened. Fine soldier, your father. You don't look like a soldier. But I'm told you killed a white walker.

author: sam
content: I did, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: How?

author: sam
content: With a dagger made of dragonglass.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Dragonglass?

author: sam
content: What the maesters call obsidian -

author: stannis baratheon
content: I know what it is. We have it in Dragonstone. Why would obsidian kill a walker?

author: sam
content: I don't know. I've been going through all the old manuscripts hoping to find something, and all I've learned is that the children of the forest used to hunt with dragonglass.

author: stannis baratheon
content: The Lady Melisandre told me that death marches on the Wall.

author: sam
content: I've seen it, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Seen what?

author: sam
content: The army of the dead. And when they come -

author: stannis baratheon
content: We have to know how to fight them. . Keep reading, Samwell Tarly.

author: stannis baratheon
content: It's time.

author: davos
content: Uh, Your Grace. Wouldn't it be better to wait? When Jon Snow returns with the wildlings, we could have thousands more men.

author: stannis baratheon
content: If Jon Snow returns with the wildlings. We can't wait that long. We have the advantage, more men, more horses, all fed and rested. But every day we wait, the odds shift in Bolton's favor. This could turn to winter at any moment. We have to act now. Give the order. We march at sunrise.

author: davos
content: I'll choose a dozen men to stay and guard the queen and the princess.

author: stannis baratheon
content: No need, they're coming with us.

author: davos
content: It's a tough road ahead, Your Grace. Won't they be safer -

author: stannis baratheon
content: Here? Half these watchmen are killers and rapists. No, they march with us.

author: davos
content: As you wish, Your Grace.

author: shireen
content: Do you think Father will let me go down into the crypt?

author: davos
content: Beg your pardon?

author: shireen
content: At Winterfell. All the Kings in the North are buried there. Bran the Builder and King Dorren and-

author: davos
content: First things first. It's a long march ahead. And then we have to take the castle.

author: shireen
content: Is there going to be a battle?

author: davos
content: Aye, princess, but you won't be anywhere near -

author: selyse
content: That's enough talk of battle, Ser Davos. You'll scare the child.

author: davos
content: Yes, my queen.

author: shireen
content: I'm not scared.

author: davos
content: Well, I am. When the battle comes, promise you'll protect me.

author: shireen
content: I promise.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I hope you know what you're doing with these wildlings. I need those ships.

author: jon snow
content: You'll get them back, I swear it. Have a safe journey, Your Grace. And thank you.

author: missandei
content: You're still too weak. .

author: grey worm
content: How long have I been here?

author: missandei
content: Three days.

author: grey worm
content: Ser Barristan?

author: grey worm
content: I failed him. I failed my men, I failed my queen.

author: missandei
content: You failed no one. You fought bravely. You'll fight again. Are you ashamed? You were ambushed, outnumbered. There was no way you could have known.

author: grey worm
content: This is not why. Wounded in war, there is no shame for this. I am ashamed because when the knife go in and I fall to the ground, I am afraid.

author: missandei
content: All men fear death.

author: grey worm
content: No, not death. I fear I never again see Missandei from the Island of Naath.

author: missandei
content: Now you have given the Masters what they deserve.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If I give everyone what they deserve, I'll have no one left to rule. Ser Barristan counseled mercy when I took this city right up to the morning he died. Daario Naharis thinks I should kill the former Masters and let the rest of the city fend for itself. What do you think?

author: missandei
content: Your Grace, I think that I am not fit to have an opinion on these matters.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You are as fit as anyone I know. You know why I'm here. And you know who will suffer the most if this all falls apart. So what do you think?

author: missandei
content: I can only tell you what I have seen, Your Grace. . I have seen you listen to your counselors. I have seen you lean on their experience when your own was lacking and weigh the choices they put before you. And I have seen you ignore your counselors, because there was a better choice. One that only you could see.

author: hizdahr
content: My, my queen, please do not do this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What about "Valar Morghulis"?

author: hizdahr
content: I did not want to die a coward. Apparently I do not want to die at all. .

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It takes courage to admit fear. And to admit a mistake. I came here to tell you that I was wrong. I was wrong and you were right. About tradition. About bringing the people of this city together. I will reopen the fighting pits. To free men only. Slavery will never return to Meereen, not while I live.

author: hizdahr
content: Yes, my queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And in order to forge a lasting bond with the Meereenese people, I will marry the leader of an ancient family. . Thankfully a suitor is already on his knees.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Don't worry. I'll be fine. Nothing broken, I don't think. Where are we now? Not the Rhoyne. . Long, sullen silences and an occasional punch in the face. The Mormont way. Let's start over. I apologize for before. My mouth sometimes runs away from me. This doesn't have to be an unpleasant trip. We're going to be spending a lot of time together on the way to Meereen.

author: jorah mormont
content: We are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What would make our time together truly enjoyable would be some wine.

author: jorah mormont
content: No wine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am a person who drinks. People who drink need to keep drinking. Otherwise, they're not…

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know where we are. You're taking us through Valyria.

author: jorah mormont
content: I am.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Have you sailed this route before?

author: jorah mormont
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're going to bring Daenerys a souvenir from her ancestral homeland in case I'm not enough?

author: jorah mormont
content: I think you'll be plenty.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You know what they say. The Doom still rules Valyria. What about the demons and the flames? Aren't you afraid of the Doom?

author: jorah mormont
content: No. But the pirates are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Smoking Sea. How many centuries before we learn how to build cities like this again? Thousands of years the Valyrians were the best in the world at almost everything. And then -

author: jorah mormont
content: And then they weren't.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And then they weren't. "They held each other close and turned their backs upon the end. The hills that split asunder and the black that ate the skies; The flames that shot so high and hot that even dragons burned; Would never be the final sights that fell upon their eyes. A fly upon a wall, the waves the sea wind whipped and churned -"

author: jorah mormont
content: The city of a thousand years, and all that men had learned; The Doom consumed it all alike, and neither of them turned.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I would clap.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I suppose this is it, then. This is what remains.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What was that?

author: jorah mormont
content: Stone Men! Don't let them touch you!

author: jorah mormont
content: Get behind!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mormont, cut me free! . Mormont!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mormont! Mormont!

author: jorah mormont
content: Tyrion? Tyrion. Tyrion. Tyrion. You're all right.

author: jorah mormont
content: You're heavier than you look. Did any of them touch you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You? . I've seen greyscale before, but nothing like that.

author: jorah mormont
content: I suppose that's why they send them there.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It'd be kinder to put daggers in their hearts and be done with it. . Thank you for saving me. Of course, I wouldn't have needed saving if you hadn't kidnapped me in the first place. . So what now?

author: jorah mormont
content: We walk, up the coast. With luck, we'll find a fishing village. Maybe another boat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Without luck?

author: jorah mormont
content: We've got a long walk ahead of us. I'll get some wood for a fire. Try to get some rest, huh?

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's the best idea you've had all day.

author: arya stark
content: What are they doing with the bodies?

author: waif
content: Get back to work.

author: arya stark
content: No! I've been here for weeks. I'm not scrubbing one more corpse until you tell me why I'm doing it.

author: waif
content: You will know why.

author: arya stark
content: When?

author: waif
content: When it's time. Not before. Get back to work.

author: arya stark
content: When do I get to play the game?

author: waif
content: Game?

author: arya stark
content: The game. The game of faces.

author: waif
content: You tried already. You failed.

author: arya stark
content: I didn't even know I was playing.

author: waif
content: Who are you?

author: arya stark
content: No one.

author: arya stark
content: Well who are you? What are you doing here? How'd you get here?

author: waif
content: I'm from Westeros. Just like you. Daughter of a Lord. Just like you. Except I was an only child. Heir to his fortune. My mother died. My father remarried and his new wife gave birth to a girl. My stepmother didn't want any rivals for her precious daughter so she tried to kill me with poison. I found out, sought help from the Faceless Men and my father was widowed again. I've been serving them ever since.

author: waif
content: Was that true or a lie?

author: arya stark
content: What?

author: waif
content: Did you believe every word I said?

author: jaqen hghar
content: Who are you?

author: arya stark
content: Arya.

author: jaqen hghar
content: And where did you come from?

author: arya stark
content: Westeros. My family home is Winterfell. I'm the youngest daughter of a great lord. Eddard Stark. He died in battle.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A lie.

author: arya stark
content: After he was executed I fled the capital. Had to kill a stable boy. Drove my sword through his back.

author: arya stark
content: I stabbed him in the gut. I tried to find my mother and brother. I never did. They were murdered by Walder Frey. An outlaw kidnapped me. A man called Polliver.

author: arya stark
content: A man called the Hound. Sandor Clegane. He tried to sell me but was wounded in a fight. He begged me to kill him but I wouldn't. I left him in the mountains to die. I wanted him to suffer, I hated him.

author: arya stark
content: I hated him.

author: arya stark
content: I hated him!

author: arya stark
content: That's not a lie!

author: jaqen hghar
content: The girl lies. To me. To the Many Faced God. To herself. Does she truly want to be no one?

author: arya stark
content: Yes.

author: arya stark
content: I'm not playing this stupid game anymore!

author: jaqen hghar
content: We never stop playing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So, those villages we were supposed to find. We can't live on berries and roots.

author: jorah mormont
content: I can.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're not hungry?

author: jorah mormont
content: Of course I'm hungry.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're an awful travelling companion, do you know that? Possibly the least charming man I have ever met.

author: jorah mormont
content: I am not your travelling companion.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We are travelling together. In each other's company. Therefore…

author: jorah mormont
content: Do you ever shut up?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I sailed from King's Landing to Pentos in a crate. Without ever saying a word.

author: jorah mormont
content: Why?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Never occurred to you to ask why until now? You never wondered why Tyrion Lannister decided to visit a brothel in Volantis.

author: jorah mormont
content: I'm sure you've visited many brothels in many cities.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I killed my father. He wanted to execute me for a crime I didn't commit. And he was fucking the woman I loved.

author: tyrion lannister
content: As miserable as you are, Mormont, at least your father was a good man.

author: jorah mormont
content: What do you know about my father?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I met him. I visited the Wall. When I asked him about his men he knew all the stories, every one of them. He actually cared about the people in his command. How did they put it in the Watch? “We shall never see his like again.”

author: tyrion lannister
content: You didn't know. I'm sorry. I am.

author: jorah mormont
content: How?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I only know what I heard

author: tyrion lannister
content: He was leading an expedition beyond the wall. There was a mutiny. He was murdered by his own men.

author: jorah mormont
content: We better keep moving.

author: man
content: Valar morghulis.

author: arya stark
content: Valar dohaeris.

author: man
content: I have nowhere else to go. I've taken her to every healer in Braavos. I've spent every penny I had. She suffers every day of her life. I just want it to end.

author: girl
content: It hurts.

author: arya stark
content: I know. Don't be afraid. I used to be like you. I was sick. I was dying. But my father never gave up on me. He loved me. More than anything in the world, just like your father loves you. So he brought me here. My father prayed to the many faced god. And I drank the water from this fountain. It healed me.

author: arya stark
content: I've devoted my life to him now. You don't want to hurt anymore. Drink.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Is the girl ready to give up her ears, her nose, her tongue, her hopes and dreams, her loves and hates, all that makes a girl who she is, forever?

author: jaqen hghar
content: No. The girl is not ready to become no one. But she is ready to become someone else.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why Daenerys? Why is she worth all this? As I recall, the Mormonts fought against the Targaryens during Robert's Rebellion.

author: jorah mormont
content: Do you believe in anything?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I believe in many things.

author: jorah mormont
content: In something greater than ourselves, I mean. The Gods. Destiny. Do you believe there's a plan for this world?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No.

author: jorah mormont
content: Neither did I. I was a cynic, just like you. Then I saw a girl step into a great fire with three stone eggs. When the fire burned out I thought I'd find her blackened bones. Instead I found her. Daenerys. Alive and unhurt. Holding her baby dragons. Have you ever heard baby dragons singing?

author: jorah mormont
content: It's hard to be a cynic after that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Doesn't mean she's going to be a great queen.

author: jorah mormont
content: No it doesn't.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Targaryens are famously insane. What if she conquers the world? Then what? 1,000 years of peace and prosperity?

author: jorah mormont
content: First we have to conquer the world.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We? Alright, let's assume your dreams come true. She's ecstatic when you bring her this enemy dwarf. She hacks off my head and restores your position. You command her army, sail to Westeros, defeat all your enemies, then watch as she climbs those steps and sits on the Iron Throne. Hurrah, long live the Queen. Then what?

author: jorah mormont
content: Then she rules.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So a woman who has not spent a single day of her adult life in Westeros becomes the ruler of Westeros? That's justice?

author: jorah mormont
content: She is the rightful heir.

author: petyr baelish

author: cersei lannister

content: House Tyrell won't tolerate these insults.

author: cersei lannister
content: House Tyrell won't tolerate it? I'm the insulted party, Lord Baelish. Ser Loras was promised to me, instead he chose the company of boys.

content: One's choice of companion is a curious thing.

author: cersei lannister
content: Most curious. Lysa Arryn for instance. A sorrily repellent woman. Forgive me. I know you're still in mourning.

content: Lysa was a good woman. A kind woman.

content: She was neither of those things, we both know it. Still, I pity her son. How fortunate that the young Lord of the Vale has a new father to counsel him.

author: petyr baelish

author: petyr baelish

author: cersei lannister
content: Good. If there's nothing else.

author: petyr baelish
content: There is another matter, your Grace. Something so urgent I couldn't trust the words to a raven. You once charged me with finding Arya Stark. To my shame I failed you. But I have found Sansa Stark. Alive, and well, and home again. In Winterfell.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's not possible.

author: petyr baelish
content: My sources are well placed. They tell me Roose Bolton plans to marry her to his son, Ramsay, a bastard recently legitimized by King Tommen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Roose Bolton is Warden of the North by the grace of my father.

author: petyr baelish

author: cersei lannister
content: We were fools to trust a turncloak.

author: petyr baelish
content: Marrying his son to the last of the Starks gives him more legitimacy in the North than an alliance with a hated southern house.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will skin him and his bastard like that wretch on that bloody sigil.

author: petyr baelish
content: I would counsel patience, your grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: Patience? Sansa helped murder my son, Roose Bolton is a traitor.

author: petyr baelish
content: Stannis Baratheon is also a traitor, marching with his army on Winterfell. Let Stannis and Roose battle, let the enemies of the throne slaughter each other and when they're done seize Winterfell from whichever thief survives.

author: cersei lannister
content: Winterfell is 1,000 miles away from here. The weather has already begun to turn.

author: petyr baelish
content: That is why it is critical to strike soon, while the victor still licks his wounds. Surely your Uncle Kevan could muster a force.

author: cersei lannister
content: My Uncle Kevan has all the courage of a kitchen mouse.

author: petyr baelish

author: petyr baelish

author: petyr baelish

author: cersei lannister

author: petyr baelish
content: Name me Warden of the North.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'll speak to the king this evening. Have him issue a royal decree.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'll not rest until the lion flies over Winterfell.

author: cersei lannister
content: And I'll l know you're a man of your word when I see Sansa Stark's head on a spike.

author: petyr baelish
content: As I said. I live to serve.

Just a small hearing to determine whether the charges against Loras have merit, which I'm sure they don't. Loras will be freed, our happy alliance will continue, and we'll forget this unfortunate conversation ever happened. Good day, Lady Olenna.

She had gorgeous blond hair. But she got pregnant and, well, that was boring. Then Tamsay. Such a sweet girl. Of course sweet girls get a bit dull after a while, don't they? Ramsay let me come with him on that hunt.

author: sam
content: His name was Aemon Targaryen. He came to us from King's Landing, a Maester of the Citadel, chained and sworn. And a sworn brother of the Night's Watch, ever faithful. No man was wiser or gentler or kinder. At the Wall a dozen Lord Commanders came and went during his years of service, but he was always there to counsel them. He was the blood of the dragon, but now his fire has gone out. And now his watch has ended.

author: brothers

author: alliser
content: You're losing all your friends, Tarly.

author: ramsay bolton
content: My beautiful wife.

author: ramsay bolton
content: When my father told me we were marrying I half expected a fat, bearded beast. Do you know how pleased I was when I saw you? You've made me very happy.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Our scouts report that Stannis Baratheon rides for Winterfell. He's a respected commander. His troops are loyal and battle tested. He's hired thousands of foreign sell swords to bolster his army. But this storm was a stroke of luck for us northerners. Our people are used to fighting in frost. His army's out there now, suffering in the snow. One day I'll be Lord of Winterfell, and Warden of the North. You'll be my Lady and Wardeness.
