content: Why? Winterfell is your home and I am your husband.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Tough old bird. Everyone talks when I start beating them. But this one. Her heart gave out before I got to her face. We do breed them tough in the North. Bring my wife back to her chamber. It's far too cold out here for a lady. You should hold on to your candles. The nights are so long now.

author: davos
content: 40 horses died in the night. We'll lose more come sunset. We're running out of food. We can't open the supply line until the snow clears.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What else?

author: davos
content: The Stormcrows rode off last night.

author: stannis baratheon
content: 500 men.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Sell swords, loyal to nothing but gold.

author: davos
content: We still have a hard march to Wintefell and we won't be marching anywhere in this weather.

author: stannis baratheon
content: And?

author: davos
content: This isn't our time, we should head back to Castle Black when the snow clears.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I retreated from King's Landing, Ser Davos. If I retreat again, I become “The King Who Ran.”

author: davos
content: Your Grace..

author: stannis baratheon
content: Winter is coming. Those arent just the Stark words, it's a fact. If we march back to Castle Black, we winter at Castle Black. And who can say how many years this winter will last.

author: davos
content: It's better to wait for the right time than to risk everything.

author: stannis baratheon
content: This is the right time, and I will risk everything. Because if I don't, we've lost. We march to victory or we march to defeat, but we go forward only forward,

author: davos
content: Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I've trusted in your visions, in your prophecies for years.

author: melisandre
content: You saw it yourself, my king, when you stared into the flames. A great battle in the snow.

author: stannis baratheon
content: I don't know what I saw.

author: melisandre
content: You do know. Trust yourself.

author: stannis baratheon
content: And you, do you trust yourself?

author: melisandre
content: I trust in the Lord.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Are you sure?

author: melisandre
content: I have seen myself walk along the battlements of Wintefell. I have seen the flayed men banners lowered to the ground.

author: melisandre
content: But sometimes sacrifices must be made to ensure victory. I have shown you the power of king's blood. The Usurper Robb Stark. The Usurper Joffrey Baratheon.

author: stannis baratheon
content: We don't have Robert's bastard here.

author: melisandre
content: No, we have someone better, and your blood runs through her veins.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Have you lost your mind?

author: melisandre
content: Do you doubt me still? After all that you've seen?

author: stannis baratheon
content: There must be another way. Leeches or something.

author: melisandre
content: There is only one way. You must become king before the Long Night begins. Only you can lead the living against the dead. All your life has led us to this moment. To this decision.

author: stannis baratheon
content: She's my daughter.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Get out.

author: derryk
content: The beauty from beyond The Wall.

author: bran stark
content: Where are you going, huh? Aren't we better looking than the fat man?

author: derryk
content: The question is, is she pretty down south in the real world, or is she pretty because she's the only girl here?

author: bran stark
content: Even in White Harbor, I'd want a kiss.

author: derryk
content: Come on love, give us a kiss.

author: gilly
content: Leave me alone.

author: derryk
content: If you were my girl I wouldn't leave you alone.

author: bran stark
content: One little kiss.

author: derryk
content: Come on, give him a kiss.

author: bran stark
content: A man gets lonely guarding the Wall.

author: bran stark
content: There's no need to be rude.

author: derryk
content: We just want a little affection.

author: sam
content: Get your hands off her. Brother Derryk. Brother Brand. I believe you both have guard duty tonight.

author: bran stark
content: Sam the Slayer. Are you gonna slay me with that sword?

author: derryk
content: Look at his hands shaking.

author: sam
content: Gilly go on, Get back to your room and lock the door.

author: sam
content: I'm warning you.

author: derryk
content: Come on! Come on!

author: derryk
content: You lying sack of shit! Killed a White Walker, eh? You fatass fuck. Come on, get up. He's your hero. He's a hog!

author: gilly
content: Leave him alone!

author: derryk
content: Stubborn little wilding bitch aren't ya?

author: gilly
content: Sam! Sam! Sam!

author: bran stark
content: Alright. Hold still.

author: sam
content: I said get your hands off her.

author: bran stark
content: You're gonna get yourself killed.

author: derryk
content: Roll over. Jon Snow's not here to save you.

author: sam
content: I killed a White Walker. I killed a Thenn. I'll take my chances with you.

author: gilly
content: Sam!

author: sam
content: I'm alright.

author: gilly
content: You're not.

author: sammy
content: Just a bit woozy.

author: gilly
content: The next time you see something like that you leave it alone.

author: sam
content: I will not. They wouldo ve… I don't know what they would have done

author: gilly
content: I know they would have killed you if Ghost hadn't come.

author: sam
content: No. They were tiring out. I had them in the palm of my hand.

author: gilly
content: Don't be stupid Sam, you're not a fighter.

author: sam
content: What kind of man would I be if I ran away when I saw someone hurting you?

author: gilly
content: Just promise me that whatever happens you'll take care of little Sam.

author: sam
content: Of course I will. And I'll take care of you, too.

author: gilly
content: I need more water.

author: sam
content: Stay. Please.

author: gilly
content: Am I hurting you?

author: gilly
content: Are you sure?

author: sam
content: Oh. Oh my.

author: malko
content: A rare find for the fighting pits, my friends. Not your usual street tough old drunken pirate. This one's a Westerosi knight from an ancient house, trained in sword and lance. he fought beside the Stag King Robert on the far side of the Narrow Sea. He was first from the breach during the siege of Pyke, slaughtering 50 men with his flaming sword. He killed the great Khal Drogo in single combat. Betrayed by his woman, he sold himself into slavery to repay his debts. Bidding begins at 12 gold honors.

author: malko
content: 13. Do I have 14?

author: malko
content: 15? 15 golds honors. Do I have 16?

author: malko
content: Sold!

author: tyrion lannister
content: Wait! You have to buy me as well.

author: buyer
content: Why?

author: tyrion lannister
content: We're a team. I'm a great fighter, too.

author: malko
content: He's funny. You have to give him that.

author: buyer
content: Alright. He's funny.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank you my Lord. Thank you.

author: buyer
content: Yes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My Lord, if I may. I've heard Mereen's become a free city. You might run into trouble if you try to fight slaves in the fighting pits. Now if you were to fight free men who were paid a wage…

author: buer
content: Here's your wages, funny man. It'll last the rest of your life.

author: daario
content: How long before the king of Mereen comes to claim my pillow?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't be ridiculous. My marriage to Hizdahr is political. I think he's smart enough to understand that.

author: daario
content: I think the Sons of the Harpy have stopped killing because their leader was made king.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Are you jealous?

author: daario
content: Do you think I'm petty enough to speak ill of a man just because he represents competition?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I do.

author: daario
content: You're right. My motivations are entirely impure.

author: daario
content: Doesn't make me wrong.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You told me yourself, I can't fight enemies within and without. So when enemies from without come knocking, I need the city of Mereen behind me. I have no choice.

author: daario
content: Everyone has a choice. Even slaves have a choice. Death or slavery.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So what else can I do?

author: daario
content: Marry me instead.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Even if I wanted to do such an inadviseable thing, I couldn't.

author: daario
content: Why not? You're our queen, you can do as you like.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No. I can't

author: daario
content: Then you are the only person in Mereen who's not free.

author: daario
content: I know I'm here to serve my queen and not to give advice, but can I make one more suggestion?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Of course

author: daario
content: On the day of the Great Games, gather all the great masters, and wise masters, and worthy masters you can find, and slaughter them all.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I am a queen. Not a butcher.

author: daario
content: All rulers are either butchers or meat.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You there! Where would I find the High Septon, or High Sparrow, or whatever bloody fool name he's got.

author: sparrow
content: It's not as good a name as Queen of Thorns, I'll admit.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You should have the decency to stand when you talk to a lady.

author: sparrow
content: You should have the decency to kneel before the gods

author: olenna tyrell
content: Don't spar with me little fellow.

author: sparrow
content: For me, it's the knees. You?

author: olenna tyrell
content: Hips.

author: sparrow
content: Huh.

author: olenna tyrell
content: A man of the people, is that your game? It's an old game. dull and unconvincing. A man of the people who does Cersei's dirty work for her.

author: sparrow
content: The people always do the dirty work.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Spare me the homilies, I can smell a fraud from a mile away.

author: sparrow
content: A useful talent.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I'm here for my grandson and granddaughter.

author: sparrow
content: Your grandson and granddaughter swore sacred vows and lied. The Father judges us all. Sons of high lords, sons of fishermen. If you break his laws you will be punished.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Don't you walk away from me.

author: sparrow
content: You don't give commands here, Lady Olenna.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What is it you want? Gold? I'll make you the richest septon who ever lived.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What then?

author: sparrow
content: I imagine this is strange for you. Everyone you meet has a hidden motive, and you pride yourself on slitting in and out. But I'm telling you a simple truth

author: olenna tyrell
content: How do they communicate their demands? By raven or horse?

author: sparrow
content: By the holy text. The seven pointed star. If you don't have one in your library I'll give you my own.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I've read the seven pointed star.

author: sparrow
content: Then you'll remember the passages concerning buggery and perjury. Your grandchildren will be punished in the same manner as anyone who breaks the sacred laws.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Half the men, women, and children in this foul city break the sacred laws. You live among murderers, thieves, and rapists. And yet you punish Loras for shagging and Margaery for defending her brother?

author: sparrow
content: Yes. The Gods' laws must be applied to all equally.

author: olenna tyrell
content: If it's equality you want then so be it. When House Tyrell stops sending our crops to the capital, everyone here will starve. And I'll make sure the hungry know who to blame,

author: sparrow
content: Have you ever served the field, Lady Olenna? Have you ever reaped the grain? Has anyone in House Tyrell? A lifetime of wealth and power has left you blind in one eye. You are the few. We are the many. And when the many stop fearing the few…

author: squire
content: Lady Olenna.

author: cersei lannister
content: Starving yourself won't make things any better for her, my love.

author: tommen lannister
content: She's in a prison cell and there's nothing I can do. I am the king! The queen is in prison and there's nothing I can do!

author: cersei lannister
content: No matter who you are, no matter how strong you are, sooner or later, you'll face circumstances beyond your control.

author: tommen lannister
content: I'll call in the army. I'll take back the sept and kill every last one of them. I'll start a war if I have to.

author: cersei lannister
content: You know as well as I do who the first casualty in that war would be.

author: tommen lannister
content: I love her. I love her. I can't help her.

author: cersei lannister
content: We must be strong for those we love. We cannot give in to despair.

author: tommen lannister
content: I will speak to the high sparrow. There must be something--

author: cersei lannister
content: Let me speak to him on your behalf. The king cannot dirty sully himself negotiating with an unwashed fanatic.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your happiness is all I want in this world

author: tommen lannister
content: I know.

author: cersei lannister
content: No you don't. You can't possibly. Not until you have children of your own. I would do anything for you. Anything to keep you from harm. I would burn cities to the ground. That is all that matters. You and your sister. From the moment you came into this world, my boy. My only boy.

author: areo
content: Prince Doran hopes this satisfies your concerns about the princess's wellbeing.

author: myrcella
content: You looked different when I left. You had more hair.

author: jaime lannister
content: And more hands. How's Trystane?

author: myrcella
content: He'll be alright.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm sorry for that. It wasn't supposed to happen that way.

author: myrcella
content: Why is it happening at all?

author: jaime lannister
content: Your mother's worried about you. Threats have been made. Dorne is too dangerous for you. I've come to take you home.

author: myrcella
content: This is my home, this has been my home for years. I didn't want to come here but she told me to. I did what she said, I did my duty and now she's forcing me to go back?

author: jaime lannister
content: It's for your own good. These are complicated matters.

author: myrcella
content: It's not complicated at all, it's simple. I love Trystane, I'm going to marry him, and we're staying right here.

author: jaime lannister
content: I don't understand.

author: myrcella
content: Of course you don't! You don't know me!

author: bronn
content: Brothers oh brothers, my days here are done, the Dornishman's taken my life. Bur what does it matter, for all men must die, and I've tasted the Dornishman's wife! Yes I've tasted the Dornishman's wife!

author: tyene
content: He's got a good voice.

author: obara
content: We're lucky he's a singer. If he were a fighter we might have been in trouble.

author: bronn
content: It's against my code to hurt a woman.

author: obara
content: It's amazing how many men we beat seem to have this code.

author: bronn
content: I wouldn't say you beat me.

author: tyene
content: How's your arm?

author: bronn
content: Wonderful. Wouldn't feel right to leave Dorne without a new scar.

author: tyene
content: You think you're leaving Dorne?

author: bronn
content: No great hurry. Dornish women are the most beautiful women in the world.

author: tyene
content: Thank you.

author: bronn
content: I said Dornish women. I didn't say you.

author: tyene
content: I'm not the most beautiful woman you've ever seen?

author: bronn
content: I've seen quite a few women in all the Seven Kingdoms.

author: tyene
content: Name one more beautiful than I am.

author: bronn
content: Well now, in King's Landing there was an absolutely gorgeous...

author: tyene
content: There was a what? In King's Landing you were saying.

author: bronn
content: Was I?

author: tyene
content: There was a woman more beautiful than I am.

author: bronn
content: Was there? My memory's not what it was earlier.

author: tyene
content: How's your arm now?

author: bronn
content: You seem concerned with it. You must really like me.

author: tyene
content: And how about your head?

author: bronn
content: My head… You don't even wanna know what's going on in…

author: tyene
content: Your nose is bleeding.

author: bronn
content: It's nothing. It's the dry air.

author: tyene
content: My dagger was coated with a special ointment from Asshei. They call it the Long Farewell. It takes time to work, but if a single drop makes contact with the skin, death.

author: tyene
content: The only antidote. Who's the most beautiful woman in the world?

author: tyene
content: Sorry? Who?

author: bronn
content: You.

author: tyene
content: Don't drop it.

author: tyene
content: I think you're very handsome as well.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm sorry about the locale.

author: olenna tyrell
content: No you're not.

author: petyr baelish
content: It felt like the safest place.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Not for your clientele, clearly.

author: petyr baelish
content: It was an establishment like no other. The sheer range of appetites catered to, desires that didn't exist until we invented them.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You've always been rather impressed with yourself, haven't you?

author: petyr baelish
content: The past is the past. The future is all that's worth discussing. The future of House Tyrell.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Don't pretend to have any concern for my house, my grandchildren, or me. I should have known you'd return to the capital once things started going wrong.

author: petyr baelish
content: I promise you..

author: olenna tyrell
content: I promise you, Lord Baelish, that our fates are joined. Together we murdered a king. And if my house should fall, I would have nothing to hide. And if i should meet with some accident here at this broken little flesh market, they'll never even find what's left of you. So do you deny a part in all of this?

author: petyr baelish
content: Cersei summoned me to King's Landing. I dared not refuse her.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And what did she want?

author: petyr baelish
content: A piece of info that she know that I had. Neither silence nor lies were an option. But I have other information of which she is unaware. And as you say, our interests are aligned. I have a gift for you.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What kind of gift?

author: petyr baelish
content: The same kind I gave Cersei. A handsome young man.

author: slave owner
content: Many worthy fighters have died trying to make it to the Great Games. When most of you worthless scum join them in death this afternoon it will represent a significant rise in your station. But if you happen to triumph here you will fight at the great pit of Daznak itself in front of the queen. So whatever happens, the gods have smiled upon you today. Today is the day your lives actually start to mean something.

author: owner
content: You and you, you, you two, you, you, and you.

author: owner
content: Valar morghulis.

author: men
content: Valar dohaeris.

author: owner
content: Prepare yourselves.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Sitting through the great games will be bad enough.

author: hizdahr
content: For generations, in the days leading up to the great games, it has been customary for our ruler to make the rounds to the lower pits to pay the fighters there the honor of her presence.

author: owner
content: Move yourselves!

author: owner
content: Your Grace. Your Future Grace. You honor us all.

author: owner
content: We fight and die for your glory, O glorious queen.”

author: men
content: We fight and die for your glory, O glorious queen.”

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I think I've seen enough.

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace, it's a tradition for the queen to stay until the victor has emerged.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I've sacrificed more than enough for your traditions.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What are you doing?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Get him out of my sight.

author: jorah mormont
content: Khaleesi, please, I just need a moment of your time. I brought you a gift.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's true. He has.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who are you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am the gift. It's a pleasure to meet you, Your Grace. My name is Tyrion Lannister.

author: cersei lannister
content: This is horrible. Unacceptable. Are they feeding you enough at least? I brought you this. Venison. It's quite good. I had it myself for supper only last night. We did everything we could from the moment they took your brother. Tommen even went to the sept himself to confront the high sparrow, but I fear The Faith has left reason behind.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I know you did this.

author: cersei lannister
content: We are making every effort on your behalf. I swear to you by all the seven gods.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Lies come easily to you. Everyone knows that. But innocence, decency, concern? You're not very good at those, I'm afraid. Perhaps that's why your son was so eager to cast you aside for me.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're upset. You're not thinking clearly. I'll visit again when you've had a chance to calm down.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I don't want to see you again.

author: cersei lannister
content: I do hope you change your mind about that. I've been told men often go mad in the Black Cells below the Red Keep, but I suppose your isolation will end once your trial begins.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Leave.

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes, I'm afraid I must. My son needs me now more than ever.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Get out you hateful bitch!

author: cersei lannister
content: Sleep well, sister.

author: sparrow
content: Thank you. You saw her?

author: cersei lannister
content: Yes.

author: sparrow
content: And?

author: cersei lannister
content: Her accommodations seem sufficient. What happens to her now?

author: sparrow
content: Well she and her brother are both being held under fair suspicion. A trial will be held for each of them to determine if they are guilty of any acts that might constitute a violation of the tenants of the faith.

author: cersei lannister
content: Who will stand judge?

author: sparrow
content: Seven septons. As it was in all trials before the Targaryens.

author: cersei lannister
content: Will you be one of them?

author: sparrow
content: I will.

author: cersei lannister
content: If one or both of them were to confess before the trial…

author: sparrow
content: Then they will be at The Mother's mercy.

author: cersei lannister
content: What does The Mother's mercy entail?

author: sparrow
content: It depends on the situation. The acts themselves, the degree of contrition.

author: cersei lannister
content: Thank you High Septon for bringing them whatever justice they deserve in the eyes of the Seven.

author: sparrow
content: Did you know this chapel is one of the oldest structures in King's Landing?

author: cersei lannister
content: I think I may have heard at one point.

author: sparrow
content: Baelor built his sept around it. But men worshipped here long before him.

author: sparrow
content: Who carved this altar do you know?

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm afraid i don't.

author: sparrow
content: No one does. There's no name on it. Or anywhere else in the chapel. The people who built this place didn't inflict their vanity on the people who came after them. The way Baelor did with that great gilded monstrosity out there. Their faith was clean.

author: sparrow
content: A young man came to us not long ago, broken in body and spirit. He had so much to strip away, so much weighing him down. But piece by piece he unburdened himself. Let go of vanity, pride, sin, now his soul is so light he will float through the Seven Heaves like a bird.

author: sparrow
content: And he has much to say about you.

author: cersei lannister
content: Move. Let me go immediately.

author: cersei lannister
content: You will order her to let me go! I am the queen! I am the queen! Have you lost your mind? Let me go! You filthy… I am the queen! Let me go!

author: cersei lannister
content: Look at me. Look at my face. It's the last thing you'll see before you die.

author: end
content: EPISODE

author: jorah mormont
content: Your Grace, I want to say--

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will not speak. How do I know you are who you say you are?

author: tyrion lannister
content: If only I were otherwise.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If you are Tyrion Lannister why shouldn't I kill you? To pay your family back for what it did to mine

author: tyrion lannister
content: You want revenge against the Lannisters? I killed my mother Joanna Lannister the day I was born. I killed my father Tywin Lannister with a bow to the heart. I am the greatest Lannister killer of our time.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So I should welcome you into my service because you murdered members of your own family?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Into your service? Your Grace we have only just met. It's too soon to know if you deserve my service.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If you'd rather return to the fighting pits just say the word.

author: tyrion lannister
content: When I was a young man I heard a story about a baby born during the worst storm in living memory. She had no wealth, no lands, no army, only a name and a handful of supporters, most of whom probably thought they could use that name to benefit themselves. They kept her alive, moving her from place to place, often hours ahead of the men who had been sent to kill her. She was eventually sold off to some warlord on the edge of the world and that appeared to be that. And then a few years later the most well informed person I knew told me that this girl without wealth, lands, or armies had somehow acquired all 3 in a very short span of time, along with three dragons. He thought she was our best, last chance to build a better world. I thought you were worth meeting at the very least.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And why are you worth meeting? Why should I spend my time listening to you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Because you can not build a better world on your own. You have no one at your side who understands that land you want to rule. The strengths and the weaknesses of the houses that will either support or oppose you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I have a very large army and very large dragons.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Killing and politics aren't always the same thing. When I served as Hand of the King I did quite well with the latter considering the king in question preferred torturing animals to leading his people. I could do an even better job advising a ruler worth the name.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So you want to advise me. Very well. What would you have me do with him? I swore I would kill him if he ever returned.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why should the people trust a queen who can't keep her promises?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Whomever Ser Jorah was when he started informing on you, he is no longer that man. I can't remember seeing the same man as devoted to anything as he is to serving you. He claims he would kill for you and die for you, and nothing I have witnessed gives me reason to doubt him. And yet he did betray you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did he have an opportunity to confess his betrayals?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Yes, many opportunities.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And did he?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No. Not until forced to do so.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He worships you. He is in love with you, I think. But he did not trust you with the truth - an unpleasant truth, to be sure - but one of great significance to you. He did not trust that you would be wise enough to forgive him.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So I should kill him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: A ruler who kills those that are devoted to her is not a ruler that inspires devotion. And you're going to need to inspire devotion, and lots of it, if you're ever going to rule across the Narrow Sea. But you cannot have him by your side when you do.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Remove Ser Jorah from the city.

author: septa
content: Confess.

author: cersei lannister
content: My son. Let me speak to--

author: septa
content: Confess. I meant it.

author: cersei lannister
content: My face will be the last thing you see before--

author: arya stark
content: My name is Lana. I'm an orphan. When I was 8 I begged enough money to buy my first bucket of oysters, and I sold that bucket and made enough money to buy 2 more.

author: arya stark
content: Iit took a while but I finally saved enough to buy myself an oyster cart. Now every morning I make my way down to the canals. I pass the fish mongers and the bakers. I usually see Lhara, my first customer of the day on my way home. Then I turn left onto Moonsinger Lane--

author: arya stark
content: Left onto Ragman Lane, where I do most of my trade.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Lana is very impressive. Very industrious. She will make a fine servant for the Many Faced God.

author: arya stark
content: How will she serve him?

author: jaqen hghar
content: She will no longer turn left onto Ragman Lane. She will turn right and go to Ragman Harbor.

author: arya stark
content: What will she do there?

author: jaqen hghar
content: She will see.

author: arya stark
content: See what?

author: jaqen hghar
content: How can a man tell a girl this. If he knew what she would see, there would be no reason to send her.

author: arya stark
content: Oysters, clams and cockles!

author: arya stark
content: Oysters clams and cockles! Oysters clams and cockles!

author: thin man
content: Your oysters fresh?

author: arya stark
content: Best in the city.

author: thin man
content: You wouldn't lie to an old man would you?

author: thin man
content: Very nice. Give me 4. With vinegar.

author: man
content: It's my 18th voyage. I've returned from all of them without a scratch on me.

author: thin man
content: Can't do it.

author: man
content: Please I have 3 children. Without me-- here take it you have to, I have 3 children, what will they do? Please you have to! Please! You don't understand?

author: jaqen hghar
content: The man is a gambler. He wages that his sailor's ship will make it to its destination. It is a strange wager for the captain. He only wins if he loses his life.

author: arya stark
content: So why would a captain make the wager in the first place?

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl tells a man that she has seen.

author: arya stark
content: If the captain dies, the thin man pays his family a lot of money.

author: jaqen hghar
content: But perhaps the gambler loses his bet and decides that he doesn't have to pay after all. A destitute woman and her small child, what can they do to such a man if he keeps their money for himself? To whom can they turn for recourse?

author: arya stark
content: The Many Faced God. You said you didn't know what I would see at the docks.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A man had no idea what she would see and what she would not. A girl named Lana will return to the docks. She will watch the gambler. She will come to know as much about him as she knows about herself.

author: arya stark
content: And then what?

author: jaqen hghar
content: A gift for the Thin Man.

author: waif
content: She is not ready.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Perhaps she is, perhaps she's not.

author: waif
content: And if she's not?

author: jaqen hghar
content: It is all the same to the Many Faced God.

author: qyburn
content: The trial will take place. The High Sparrow will be presenting a substantial case against you.

author: cersei lannister
content: The charges?

author: qyburn
content: Fornication, treason, incest, the murder of King Robert.

author: cersei lannister
content: All lies.

author: qyburn
content: Of course, Your Grace. My concern is that The Faith does not adhere to the same standards of proof as the crown. And I hope you'll excuse me for saying it, but belief is so often the death of reason.

author: cersei lannister
content: I wish you'd said it sooner. Any word from Jaime?

author: qyburn
content: I'm afraid not. Your Grace, Grand Maester Pycelle has summoned your Uncle Kevan back from Casterly Rock to serve as Hand of the King. He now presides over the small council.

author: cersei lannister
content: Tell him I need to speak to him.

author: qyburn
content: I implored him to visit you but he would not.

author: cersei lannister
content: What about my son, the king? If you can visit me then surely the king--

author: qyburn
content: Your arrest, and Queen Margaery's arrest, the king has not taken well. He remains in his chambers, his servants often find his food in the hall. Left untouched.

author: cersei lannister
content: You need to talk to him, you need to talk to my son to come and see me, come and see his mother.

author: qyburn
content: I tried my grace, he wouldn't see me. He wouldn't see anyone.

author: cersei lannister
content: I can't stay here.

author: qyburn
content: There is a way, Your Grace. A way out.

author: cersei lannister
content: Confess? To the High Sparrow? I won't. I made him. I rose him up from nothing, I will not kneel before some barefooted commoner and beg his forgiveness.

author: qyburn
content: Goodbye my queen. The work continues.

author: sansa stark
content: Why. Why Theon.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not Theon. There is no Theon. Reek.

author: sansa stark
content: Reek. Why did you tell him, Reek?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I was helping you. You were trying to escape, there is no escape. Not ever. Theon Greyjoy tried to escape. The master knew. He knows everything. He hunted him, he caught him, he strapped him to a cross, and cut away piece after piece until there was no Theon left.

author: sansa stark
content: Good. If it weren't for you I'd still have a family. If I could do to you what Ramsay did to you right here, right now, I would.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I deserved everything. I deserve to be Reek. I did terrible things. Turned on Robb. Captured Winterfell. Killed those boys.

author: theon greyjoy
content: They weren't “those boys”, they were Bran and Rickon. They were your brothers, you'd know them since they were born.

author: theon greyjoy
content: They weren't. They were only--

author: sansa stark
content: Only what?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I can't..

author: sansa stark
content: Tell me!

author: theon greyjoy
content: I can't, not unless the master says...

author: sansa stark
content: Tell me, they weren't what?!

author: theon greyjoy
content: They weren't...

author: sansa stark
content: Tell me why Bran and Rickon should be dead while you still breathe the air. Tell me to my face Theon, tell me that they weren't your brothers!

author: theon greyjoy
content: They weren't Bran and Rickon! I couldn't find them. It was two farm boys. I killed them and burned them so no one would know.

author: sansa stark
content: You didn't…?

author: sansa stark
content: Do you know where they went, Bran and Rickon?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I can't talk to you anymore.

author: sansa stark
content: Theon, you have to tell me, do you have any idea where Bran and Rickon--

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not Theon, Reek!

author: bolton bannerman
content: Our scouts tells us he's got no more than 6000 men. More than half of them are mounted, however.

author: roose
content: And how high can Stannis' horses jump? Our walls have been full repaired our walls have been reinforced. We have enough food for six months. We are more prepared for a siege than they could have ever been. All we have to do is wait for them to freeze, starve, and mutiny.

author: roose
content: You disagree?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Stannis isn't from the North. You are, father. I think you're missing an opportunity to show the people of the North how House Bolton treats southern invaders.

author: roose
content: And what do you recommend?

author: ramsay bolton
content: That we not sit and wait to let Stannis to decide what type of fight this is going to be. That we hit first, and hit hard, and leave a feast for the crows.

author: roose
content: A smart commander does not surrender a defensive advantage. As long as we stay behind these walls they can't touch us. Not to mention that the snow is so deep that we couldn't get an army through if we wanted to.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I don't need an army. I need 20 good men.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So have you decided yet? Whether I'm worthy of your service?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Have you decided yet whether you're going to have me killed?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's probably my safest option.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can see why you would think so. It's what your father would have done.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what would your father do?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My father? Who publicly sentenced me to death? I'd say his thoughts on having me killed were abundantly clear.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Is that why you killed him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Some day if you decide not to execute me, I'll tell you all about why I killed my father. And on that day, should it ever come, we'll need more wine than this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I know what my father was. What he did. I know the Mad King earned his name.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So here we sit, two terrible children of two terrible fathers.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm terrible?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I've heard stories.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why did you travel to the other side of the world to meet someone terrible?

author: tyrion lannister
content: To see if you were the right kind of terrible.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Which kind is that?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The kind that prevents your people from being even more so.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I did reopen the fighting pits. Under my rule murder will once again become entertainment.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, that was wise. And you agreed to marry someone you loathed for the greater good. Very impressive. My own sister married someone she loathed as well, though not by choice and certainly not for the greater good, Gods forbid. She ended up having him killed.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Perhaps it won't come to that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not impossible that Varys was right about you after all.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Varys? King Robert's spy master?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes. He was the one who convinced me to come find you. He was my travelling companion before Ser Jorah seized that role for himself.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Jorah sent my secrets to Varys. For 20 years the spider oversaw the campaign to find and kill me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He did what he had to do to survive. He did a lot of other things that he didn't have to do. I suspect he's the main reason you weren't slaughtered in your crib.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But you trust him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, oddly. He might be the only person in the world that I trust. Besides my brother.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The brother who killed my father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's the one.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Perhaps I will have you killed after all.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your queenly prerogative. I had given up on life until Varys convinced me you might be worth living for. You chop off my head? Well, my final days were interesting.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not going to kill you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No? Banish me?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So if I'm not going to be murdered, and I'm not going to be banished...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You're going to advise me. While you can still speak in complete sentences.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Advise you on what?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How to get what I want.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Iron Throne. Perhaps you should try wanting something else.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If I want jokes I'll get myself a proper fool.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm not entirely joking. There's more to the world than Westeros after all. How many hundreds of thousands of lives have you changed for the better here? Perhaps this is where you belong. Where you can do the most good.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I fought so that no child born into Slaver's Bay would ever know what it was like to be bought or sold. I will continue that fight here and beyond. But this is not my home.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And when you get back to your home, who supports you?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The common people.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Let's be generous and assume that's going to happen. Here in Slaver's Bay you had the support of the common people and only the common people. What was that like, ruling without the rich? House Targaryen is gone, not a single person who shares your blood is alive to support you. The Starks are gone as well, our two terrible fathers saw to that. The remaining Lannisters won't back you, not ever. Stannis Baratheon won't back you either, his entire claim to the Throne depends on the illegitimacy of yours. That leaves the Tyrells. Not impossible, but not enough.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Lannister, Targaryen, Baratheon, Stark, Tyrell. They're all just spokes on a wheel. This one's on top, then that ones on top and on and on it spins, crushing the people on the ground.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's a beautiful dream. Stopping the wheel. You're not the first person to have dreamt it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not going to stop the wheel. I'm going to break the wheel.

author: jorah mormont
content: You said whoever wins would fight at the Great Pit in front of the queen. I won.

author: master
content: You struck me.

author: jorah mormont
content: I've been flogged if it makes you happy. I'm the best you've got. If I win at the Great Pit how much can you sell me for?

author: master
content: You're a free man, you could have gone anywhere, why did you come back?

author: jorah mormont
content: Let me fight for her and I belong to you.

author: septa
content: Thirsty? Confess.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'll get out of here, you realize. Before long.

author: cersei lannister
content: I can make you a wealthy woman. A lady of the court.

author: cersei lannister
content: I can make sure you die in the most hideous way imaginable, and all I do is sit here imagining ways for you to die.

author: gilly
content: Does it hurt?

author: sam
content: No.

author: gilly
content: Good.

author: sam
content: How are you?

author: gilly
content: I'm not the one who got punched and kicked in the face.

author: sam
content: You know what I mean.

author: gilly
content: I'm good.

author: sam
content: Are you scared?

author: gilly
content: A little.

author: sam
content: Me too.

author: sam
content: Who's there?

author: olly
content: Olly.

author: sam
content: Come in.

author: olly
content: I heard what happened.

author: sam
content: Not to worry. Men brawl from time to time. It's only natural.

author: olly
content: Figured you were hungry.

author: sam
content: You're a good lad.

author: olly
content: Wanted to ask you something. If you've got the time.

author: gilly
content: I need to check on baby Sam.

author: sam
content: Now then. How can I help?

author: olly
content: It's about the Lord Commander.

author: sam
content: Yes?

author: olly
content: He's going up to Hardhome to save all them wildlings. Wildlings killed my mom and dad. They killed everyone in my village.

author: sam
content: We've been fighting them for years.

author: olly
content: This wasn't a fight. We were farmers and they slaughtered us. So why's he saving them?

author: sam
content: Wildlings are people, just like us. There are good ones and bad ones.

author: olly
content: The one he's travelling with, the one with the red beard, he led the raid on my village.

author: sam
content: Olly...

author: olly
content: How can he trust him?

author: sam
content: I've seen the army of the dead. I've seen the white walkers, and they're coming for us, for all the living. And when it's time we'll need every last man we can find.

author: olly
content: But what if we let the wildings through the gates and they cut our throats while we sleep?

author: sam
content: Jon's taking a risk, but he has to. We don't stand a chance otherwise. Sometimes a man has to make hard choices, choices that might look wrong to others but you know are right in the long run.

author: olly
content: You believe that?

author: sam
content: With all my heart.

author: sam
content: Try not to worry Olly. I've been worrying about Jon for years. He always comes back.

author: tormund
content: You trust me Jon Snow?

author: jon snow
content: Does that make me a fool?

author: tormund
content: We are fools together now.

author: tormund
content: Lord of Bones. Been a long time.

author: lord of bones
content: Last time I saw you the little crow was your prisoner. The other way around now. What happened?

author: tormund
content: War.

author: lord of bones
content: You call that a war? The greatest army the North has ever seen cut to pieces by a southern king.

author: tormund
content: We should gather the elders find somewhere quiet to talk.

author: lord of bones
content: You don't give the orders here.

author: tormund
content: I'm not giving an order.

author: lord of bones
content: Why aren't you in chains?

author: jon snow
content: He's not my prisoner.

author: lord of bones
content: What is he?

author: jon snow
content: We're allies.

author: lord of bones
content: You fucking traitor! You fight for the crows now.

author: tormund
content: I don't fight for the crows.

author: jon snow
content: We're not here to fight. We're here to talk.

author: lord of bones
content: Is that right? You and the pretty crow do a lot of talking, Tormund. And when you're done talking, do you get down on your knees and suck his cock--

author: tormund
content: Gather the elders and let's talk.

author: jon snow
content: My name's Jon Snow. I'm Lord Commander of the Night's Watch. We're not friends. We've never been friends. We won't become friends today. This isn't about friendship. This is about survival. This is about putting a 700 foot wall between you and what's out there.

author: karsi
content: You built that wall to keep us out.

author: loboda
content: Since when do the crows give 2 shits if we live?

author: jon snow
content: In normal times we wouldn't. But these aren't normal times. The white walkers don't care if a man's Free Folk or Crow. We're all the same to them. Meat to their army. But together we can beat them.

author: karsi
content: Beat the white walkers? Good luck with that. Run from them, maybe.

author: jon snow
content: It's not a trick. It's a gift for those who join us.

author: jon snow
content: Dragonglass. A man of the Night's Watch used one of these daggers to kill a walker.

author: loboda
content: You saw this?

author: jon snow
content: No. But I trust the man.

author: karsi
content: There are old stories about Dragonglass.

author: loboda
content: There are old stories about ice spiders big as hounds.

author: karsi
content: And with the things we've seen you don't believe them?

author: jon snow
content: Come with me and I'll share these weapons.

author: karsi
content: Come with you where?

author: jon snow
content: There are good lands south of the wall. The Night's Watch will allow you through the tunnel and allow your people to farm those lands.

author: jon snow
content: I knew Mance Rayder. He never wanted a war with the Night's Watch, he wanted a new life for his people. For you. We're prepared to give you that new life.

author: karsi
content: If…?

author: jon snow
content: If you swear you join us when the real war begins.

author: loboda
content: Where is Mance?

author: jon snow
content: He died.

author: loboda
content: How?

author: jon snow
content: I put an arrow through his heart.

author: loboda
content: I say we send the Lord Commander back to Castle Black with no eyes.

author: tormund
content: None of you saw Mance die! I did. The Southern King who broke our army, Stannis, wanted to burn him alive to send him a message. Jon Snow defied that cunt's orders. His arrow was mercy. What it did took courage, and that's what we need today

author: karsi
content: I lost my father, my uncle, and 2 brothers fighting the damn crows.

author: jon snow
content: I'm not asking you to forget your dead. I'll never forget mine. I lost 50 brothers the night that Mance attacked the wall. But I'm asking you to think about your children now. They'll never have children of their own if we don't band together. The Long Night is coming and the dead come with it. No clan can stop them. The free folk can't stop them. The Night's Watch can't stop them. And all the southern kings can't stop them. Only together, all of us, and even then it might not be enough, but at least then we'll give the fuckers a fight.

author: karsi
content: You vouch for this man, Tormund?

author: tormund
content: He's prettier than both my daughters, but he knows how to fight. He's young, but he knows how to lead. He didn't have to come to Hardhome. He came because he needs us. And we need him.

author: loboda
content: My ancestors would spit on me if I broke bread with a crow.

author: karsi
content: So would mine, but fuck 'em, they're dead.

author: tormund
content: This is the way.

author: wildling elder
content: I'm with Tormund. We stay here we're dead men. At least with King Crow there's a chance.

author: giant
content: Tormund.

author: loboda
content: Keep that new life you want to give us. Keep your glass, King Crow. Soon as you get on his ships they're gonna slit your throats and dump your bodies to the bottom of the Shivering Sea. That's our enemy. That has always been our enemy.

author: karsi
content: I fucking hate Thenns.

author: jon snow
content: How many are with us? 5000?

author: tormund
content: I'm not good at counting.

author: jon snow
content: We're leaving too many behind.

author: tormund
content: The free folk are stubborn. You know how long it took Mance to band them together. 20 fucking years.

author: jon snow
content: And he knew them better than I ever will.

author: tormund
content: They're running out of food and there's nothing to hunt. They'll come around.

author: karsi
content: Johnna is gonna look after you. She's in charge, you listen to her.

author: daughter
content: I wanna go with you.

author: karsi
content: I need to get the old folks on the boats. I'm right behind you, I promise. Go on.

author: wun wun
content: Lokh kif rukh?

author: loboda
content: Shut the gate.

author: loboda
content: Shut the gate!!

author: shouting
content: Wait! Open the gate! Let us in! Help us! Please open it!

author: loboda
content: Ready your arrows!

author: jon snow
content: Get in line! Get in line!

author: jon snow
content: Hold the line! Hold the line!

author: nights watch brother
content: Lord Commander!

author: jon snow
content: Get them to the ship and come back for me!

author: brother
content: But you'll never make it--

author: jon snow
content: Now!

author: jon snow
content: You should be on one of those boats.

author: karsi
content: So should you ! My little girl has gone on. They're gonna let them pass the wall even if you're not there ?

author: jon snow
content: You have my word. I've given orders.

author: karsi
content: Don't think you're gonna be there to enforce those orders !

author: tormund
content: If they get through, everyone dies !

author: jon snow
content: Night's Watch with me! Move! Move! Move!

author: jon snow
content: The Dragonglass!

author: loboda
content: You're with me, lad! Now!

author: loboda
content: Get the glass.

author: edd
content: Fuck the glass! We're gonna die here.

author: jon snow
content: Go! Go! Go!

author: tormund
content: Wun Wun, to the sea.

author: jon snow
content: Let's go now! Now!

author: end
content: EPISODE

author: davos
content: A band of 20 men, maybe less. They were in and out before anyone spotted them, burnt our food stores to the ground, all our siege weapons were destroyed, dozens of tents were--

author: stannis baratheon
content: Horses?

author: davos
content: We're still getting a count, but hundreds are dead.

author: stannis baratheon
content: 20 men rode into our camp without a single guard sounding the alarm?

author: davos
content: The northerners know more about their land than we ever will.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Put last night's guards in chains, either they fell asleep or they were conspiring with the enemy. Find out the truth and then hang them.

author: davos
content: Unless there's a thaw, we can't press forward to Winterfell, and we don't have enough food to get us back to Castle Black.

author: stannis baratheon
content: We're not returning to Castle Black.

author: davos
content: Forgive me, Your Grace, I never claimed to be an expert in military matters. But if we can't march forward, and we won't march back…

author: stannis baratheon
content: Have the dead horses butchered for meat.

author: alliser
content: Open the gates.

author: jon snow
content: It was a failure.

author: sam
content: It wasn't.

author: jon snow
content: I went to save them, I failed.

author: sam
content: You didn't fail him, or him, or her. Every one of them is alive because of you, and no one else.

author: jon snow
content: I don't think that fact's lost on them.

author: alliser
content: You have a good heart, Jon Snow. It will get us all killed.

author: davos
content: You sent for me, Your Grace.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Find you some healthy horses and a few good men to guard you, I'm sending you back to Castle Black. Tell the Lord Commander to send food, supplies, fresh horses, in return when I take the throne I'll make sure the Night's Watch has all the men it requires. He can guard all 19 castles if he so wishes.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, you've named me your Hand.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Yes.

author: davos
content: The King's Hand should never abandon the King, especially in a time of war.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You're not abandoning me, you're obeying a command.

author: davos
content: A boy with a scroll could deliver this message.

author: stannis baratheon
content: And if Jon Snow refuses a boy with a scroll, what does the boy say? I didn't name you hand for your expertise in military matters, ride for Castle Black, don't come back empty handed.

author: davos
content: Your Grace, perhaps Queen and Princess Shireen could accompany me.

author: stannis baratheon
content: My family stays with me.

author: davos
content: At least let me take Shireen. A siege is no place for a little girl.

author: davos
content: What's this one now?

author: shireen
content: The Dance of Dragons

author: davos
content: Well that sounds like a proper story.

author: shireen
content: Ser Byron Swann wanted to kill the dragon Vhagar. He polished his shield for a week, til the steel was like a mirror. Then he crouched behind it, and crept forward, hoping the dragon would only see his own reflection.

author: davos
content: But the dragon only saw a dumb man, holding a mirrored shield.

author: shireen
content: And burnt him to a crisp.

author: davos
content: Thus ending the dragonslaying career of Ser Byron Swann. I made you something, Princess.

author: davos
content: Do you like it?

author: shireen
content: He's beautiful.

author: shireen
content: Thank you.

author: davos
content: You're very welcome.

author: shireen
content: Will you make me a doe, too, so that he can have company?

author: davos
content: Of course I will.

author: shireen
content: But why am I getting a present?

author: davos
content: Because you deserve it. My son was always on me trying to teach me to read. Gods, I was stubborn about it. Made it this far without reading, seemed to me I could make it to the grave. I wish I had listened to them. This is my own poor way of saying thank you for teaching me to be a grown up. I'll be gone for a few days, Princess. I'll want to hear all about the dance of dragons when I'm back.

author: shireen
content: You'll just have to read it yourself.

author: jaime lannister
content: Prince Doran.

author: doran
content: Forgive us, we started without you. Please, sit.

author: jaime lannister
content: Princess Myrcella.

author: myrcella
content: Uncle.

author: jaime lannister
content: What a lovely dress.

author: myrcella
content: You don't like it?

author: jaime lannister
content: You must be cold.

author: myrcella
content: Not at all. The Dornish climate agrees with me.

author: jaime lannister
content: Prince Trystane. How's your jaw?

author: trystane
content: A fleabite.

author: ellaria
content: What are you doing in Dorne?

author: jaime lannister
content: Looking out for the safety of my niece, the princess Myrcella.

author: doran
content: And rather than send a raven or speak to me directly you decided to enter my country in secret and abduct our guest by force.

author: jaime lannister
content: We received a threatening message. The princess's necklace in the jaws of a viper.

author: myrcella
content: That necklace was stolen from my room.

author: jaime lannister
content: Ah. Excellent. The last meal before the beheading.

author: doran
content: We can't behead you. Many in Dorne want war. But I've seen war. I've seen the bodies piled on the battlefields. I've seen the orphans starving in the cities. I don't want to lead my people into that hell.

author: ellaria
content: No, you want to break bread with the Lannisters.

author: doran
content: And that is precisely what we are doing. Let us drink to Tommen, the first of his name, the King of the Andals and the First Men, Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

author: doran
content: King Tommen insists on his sister's return to the capital?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm afraid he does.

author: doran
content: I cannot disobey my King's command. She will return with you to King's Landing. And my son, Prince Trystane, will accompany you both. If the alliance between Dorne and the Iron Throne is to continue, their engagement must stand.

author: jaime lannister
content: I accept.

author: doran
content: One more thing. My brother was named to the small council before his death. Your father understood the importance of keeping Dorne in the loop. With Oberyn gone, Trystane will take his place on the small council.

author: jaime lannister
content: You have my word.

author: ellaria
content: The word of a Kingslayer.

author: ellaria
content: No wonder you can't stand. You have no spine.

author: doran
content: You are mother to four of my nieces, girls I love very much. For their sake, I hope you live a long life. Talk to me that way again and you won't.

author: jaime lannister
content: May I inquire into the fate of my man?

author: doran
content: Tell me, Ser Jaime, in King's Landing, how do they punish a commoner who strikes a prince?

author: jaime lannister
content: He said it was just a fleabite. The fault is mine. Bronn is merely a soldier following my orders. If anyone should be punished it's me.

author: doran
content: Prince Trystane must learn judgement if he's to rule one day. I'll let him decide.

author: trystane
content: I have learned the value of mercy from my father. I will set your man free.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're a good man.

author: trystane
content: On one condition.

author: nymeria
content: Why do we play? I'm better than you, I'll always be better than you. Have I ever missed once? I don't think, I can't recall. You must love humiliation or pain. Which do you love most? Humiliation or-- -- pain? That one hurt didn't it? You going to cry? Give up, little sister.

author: tyene
content: You're going to miss.

author: nymeria
content: I never miss.

author: tyene
content: You will. You're thinking too much. Now you're nervous. “What if she's right?”

author: nymeria
content: Luck.

author: tyene
content: Now it's my turn.

author: nymeria
content: You're too slow. You've always been too slow.

author: bronn
content: Am I going to be happy at the end of this walk?

author: areo
content: You'll find out very soon.

author: tyene
content: Say it one more time, handsome. Who am I?

author: bronn
content: The most beautiful woman in the world.

author: tyene
content: And that's the truth!

author: nymeria
content: Slut.

author: bronn
content: Only the one.

content: I believe you've already met Prince Trystane.

author: bronn
content: Prince. Sorry about the other day.

author: jaime lannister
content: Prince Trystane here is a man of mercy. He's agreed to grant you your freedom.

author: bronn
content: I'm glad to hear it. The pie looks good.

author: jaime lannister
content: There was one condition.

author: doran
content: Perhaps some soup instead?

author: arya stark
content: Oysters, clams, and cockels! Oysters, clams, and cockels! Oysters, clams, and cockels! Oysters, clams, and cock--

content: How much for your little clam?

content: Oysters, clams, and cockels! Oysters, clams, and cockels!

author: thin man
content: Come on.

content: Some oysters, girl! I'm talking to you! Girl?! Are you deaf? Girl?!

author: banker
content: Lord Tyrell! On behalf of the Iron Bank, may I be the first to welcome you to the free city of Braavos. I hope your journey was trouble free.

author: mace
content: Bit of chop the last few days but nothing too awful. Good to see the old chap is still guarding the Harbor.

author: banker
content: And how goes the harvest in the Reach?

author: mace
content: Vintnors say this might be the best year for red grapes in half a century. If we come to a satisfactory arrangement, I'll be sure to send the Arbor's finest your way.

author: banker
content: I'm afraid I don't partake.

author: mace
content: Some consider usury distasteful, dishonorable. Pure nonsense, of course.

author: banker
content: I'm glad we see eye-to-eye on this matter.

author: mace
content: Did you know that at one point Maegor the third tried to outlaw it in the Seven Kingdoms? Wanted to arrest anyone caught charging interest and cut off both their hands.

author: banker
content: Most unfortunate for the glovers.

author: mace
content: If a man charges low interest on a loan then he has nothing to gain and everything to lose, so why charge him? Whereas a reward makes a man willing to gamble.

author: banker
content: We are not gamblers here at the Iron Bank, Lord Tyrell.

author: mace
content: You are the worldo s best gamblers. And all those bets you won built this.

author: banker
content: I'm afraid I still have a good deal of work to do.

author: mace
content: Oh, nonsense. Work's over. Do you sing?

author: banker
content: I don't have that gift.

author: mace
content: It's not a gift, it's a skill, anyone can learn it. “So give me a kiss by the Long Canall and give me two kisses in Salty Town, for we are going to die, tomorrow. The bareheaded beggar, the king with his crown…”

author: meryn
content: I thought that old shit would never stop singing.

author: man
content: It wasn't bad, though.

author: meryn
content: The Tyrells can all rot in hell, treasonous cunts. They were going to make that boy-fucker Renly king.

author: meryn
content: This is the place, lads. The sleekest little minks in Braavos.

author: man
content: You're buying?

author: meryn
content: Oh, I'm buying. But I never was good at sharing.

author: brothel keeper
content: Sell your fish somewhere else.

author: prostitute
content: Oh let her in, Brusco, I'm hungry. Come here, sweetness.

author: prostitute
content: They say oyster's get the juices flowing. We'll take half a dozen.

author: arya stark
content: Three coppers.

author: jon snow
content: Here's a silver because the lady likes you.

author: meryn
content: Too old.

author: head prostitute
content: Brea.

author: head
content: I have just the one. Anara our most expensive girl, but well worth it, I assure you.

author: meryn
content: Do you have what I want or not?

author: head
content: Of course. Of course.

author: man
content: Fresh? Come on, the lads are hungry.

author: man
content: Nothing better for you cock stand than fresh oysters.

author: man
content: I'll have one.

author: head
content: Who let this girl in? Shoo shoo!

author: meryn
content: Good.

author: meryn
content: I'll tell you when we're done.

author: meryn
content: You'll have a fresh one for me tomorrow.

author: head
content: Of course.

author: head
content: I'll have you whipped, girl! Go on!

author: man
content: Valaar morghulis.

author: jaqen hghar
content: And?

author: arya stark
content: The Thin Man wasn't hungry today.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Perhaps that's why the man is thin.

author: arya stark
content: Tomorrow.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Tomorrow.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A girl has work to do.

author: doran
content: Your rebellion is over. You can swear your allegiance to me now, or you can die.

author: doran
content: I believe in second chances. I don't believe in third chances.

author: ellaria
content: You write like a 7 year old.

author: jaime lannister
content: Your maester kindly agreed to copy it over for me.

author: ellaria
content: He didn't try to make you pay?

author: ellaria
content: Then maybe he's changed. The Queen will be thrilled to know you'll be bringing her daughter home

author: jaime lannister
content: She will.

author: ellaria
content: You love her very much, don't you?

author: jaime lannister
content: Of course, she's my niece.

author: ellaria
content: I wasn't talking about her.

author: ellaria
content: You think I disapprove. Why? Because people disapprove of that sort of thing where you are from? They disapproved of Oberyn and me where you are from. Here, no one blinked an eye. 100 years ago, no one would have blinked an eye at you if you had been named Targaryen. It's always changing, who we're supposed to love and who we're not.The only thing that stays the same is that we want who we want.

author: ellaria
content: I know your daughter had no part in the terrible thing that happened to the man I loved. Perhaps even you were innocent of that.

author: shireen
content: Father. Aren't you cold?

author: stannis baratheon
content: No. What are you reading?

author: shireen
content: The Dance of Dragons.

author: stannis baratheon
content: What's it about?

author: shireen
content: It's the story of the fight between Rhaenyra Targaryen and her half-brother Aegon for control of the Seven Kingdoms. Both of them thought they belonged on the Iron Throne. When people started for declaring for one of them or the other, their fight divided the kingdom in two. Brothers fought brothers. Dragons fought dragons. By the time it was over, thousands were dead. And it was a disaster for the Targaryens as well. They never truly recovered.

author: stannis baratheon
content: The dance of dragons”? Why is that a dance?

author: shireen
content: That's just what they call it.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Doesn't make much sense.

author: shireen
content: I think it's poetic.

author: stannis baratheon
content: If you had to choose between Rhaenyra and Aegon, who would you have chosen?

author: shireen
content: I wouldn't have chosen either. It's all the choosing sides that made things so horrible.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Sometimes a person has to choose. Sometimes the world forces his hand. If a man knows what he is and remains true to himself, the choice is not choice at all. He must fulfill his destiny and become who he is meant to be. However much he may hate it.

author: shireen
content: It's alright, father.

author: stannis baratheon
content: You don't even know what I'm talking about.

author: shireen
content: It doesn't matter. I want to help you. Is there any way I can help?

author: stannis baratheon
content: Yes there is.

author: shireen
content: Good, I want to. I'm the Princess Shireen of House Baratheon and I'm your daughter.

author: stannis baratheon
content: Forgive me.

author: shireen
content: Where's my father? I want to see my father.

author: melisandre
content: It will all be over soon, Princess.

author: shireen
content: Where's my father? No you can't do this, father where are you?!

author: shireen
content: Let me see my father! Where are you, please?!

author: selyse
content: It's what the Lord wants. It's a good thing. A great thing.

author: melisandre
content: The year is now, my Lord. For you we offer up this girl, that you may cleanse her with your fire and that its light may lead our way.

author: selyse
content: If we don't act then we'll all starve here all of us, but if we make this sacrifice…

author: melisandre
content: Accept this token of our faith, my lord and lead us from the darkness. Lord of Light show us the way!

author: shireen
content: Mother, please mother! Mother, please mother!

author: selyse
content: I can't.

author: stannis baratheon
content: There's no other way. She has King's blood.

author: melisandre
content: Lord of Light protect us, for the night is dark and full of terrors!

author: shireen
content: Mother, don't do this please! Please help! Don't do this! Please, father! Mother, help!

author: selyse
content: No...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Where have you been?

author: hizdahr
content: Just making sure everything's in order.

author: announcer
content: Free citizens of Meereen! By the blessings of the Graces and her majesty the Queen, welcome to the Great Games!

author: announcer
content: My queen, our first contest. Who will triumph

author: quick
content: I fight and die for your glory, oh glorious queen.

author: strong
content: I fight and die for your glory, oh glorious queen.

author: hizdahr
content: They're waiting for you. Clap your hands.

author: daario
content: That one, the smaller man, no question, that's where you should put your money.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The smaller man it is.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not putting my money anywhere.

author: hizdahr
content: Kings and queens never bet on the games. Perhaps you should go find someone who does.

author: daario
content: People used to bet against me when I fought in the pits. He would have bet against me. Common novice mistake.

author: hizdahr
content: I have spent much of my life in Meereen, and in my experience, larger men do triumph over smaller man, far more often than not.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Has your experience ever involved any actual fighting? You, yourself, have you ever tried to kill a man that was trying to kill you?

author: daario
content: Whenever I got into the pit against a beast like that one, the crowd saw me, all skin and bone back then, then they saw a pile of angry muscles ready to murder me. They couldn't get their money out fast enough. But the pile of angry muscles never had any muscles here or here . And the big men were always too slow to stop my dagger from going where their muscles weren't. Yes, whenever I saw a beast like that one, standing across from me making his beast faces, I knew I could rest easy.

author: hizdahr
content: You don't approve?

author: tyrion lannister
content: There's always been more than enough death in the world for my taste. I can do without it in my leisure time.

author: hizdahr
content: Fair enough, yet -- it's an unpleasant question -- but what great thing has ever been accomplished without killing or cruelty?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's easy to confuse what is with what ought to be. Especially when what is has worked in your favor.

author: hizdahr
content: I'm not talking about myself. I'm talking about the necessary conditions of greatness.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That is greatness?

author: hizdahr
content: That is a vital part of the great city of Meereen. Which has existed long before you arrived and will remain standing long after we have returned to the dirt.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My father would have liked you.

author: announcer
content: We ask again

author: daenerys targaryen
content: One day your great city will return to the dirt as well.

author: hizdahr
content: At your command?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If need be.

author: announcer
content: A Meereenese champion?

author: hizdahr
content: How many people will die to make this happen?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If it comes to that they would have died for a good reason.

author: hizdahr
content: Those men think they're dying for a good reason.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Someone else's reason.

author: hizdahr
content: So your reasons are true, and theirs are false. They don't know their own minds, but you do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well said, you're an eloquent man. Doesn't mean you're wrong. In my experience, eloquent men are right every bit as often as imbeciles.

author: announcer
content: or a Westerosi Knight?!

author: jorah mormont
content: I fight and die for your glory, oh glorious Queen.

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace--

author: daario
content: Shut your mouth.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You can end this.

author: hizdahr
content: She cannot.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You can!

author: daario
content: Protect your queen!

author: hizdahr
content: Your Grace, Your Grace, come with me! I know a way out! I know a way--

author: tyrion lannister
content: Stay close!

author: jorah mormont
content: This way!

author: daario
content: The other side, follow me!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Drogon!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Valahd..

author: jon snow
content: He raised his hands. And they all stood up at once. Tens of thousands of them, the biggest army in the world.

author: sam
content: So what are you gonna do?

content: I'm gonna hope they don't learn how to climb the wall.

author: sam

content: With Longclaw. I saw them shatter steel axes like they were glass. But Longclaw…

content: He's made of Valyrian steel. How many Valyrian steel swords are left in the Seven Kingdoms?

content: Not enough. The first Lord Commander in history to sacrifice the lives of sworn Brothers to save the lives of Wildlings. How's it feel to be friends with the most hated man in Castle Black?

content: You were friends with me when I first got here. And I wasn't winning any elections back then.

author: jon snow
content: Here's to us then. Long may they sneer.

author: jon snow
content: What?

author: sam
content: I wanted to ask you something. To ask something of you. Send me, Gilly, and the baby to Oldtown so I can become a Maester. That's what I'm meant to be, not this.

author: jon snow
content: I need you here, Sam. If you leave, who's left to give me advice I trust?

author: sam
content: Well, there's Edd.

author: sam
content: I'll be more use to you as a Maester. More use to everyone now that Maester Aemon's gone. The Citadel has the worldo s greatest library. I'll learn about history, strategy, healing. And other things. Things that will help when they come.

author: sam
content: If Gilly stays here then she'll die. And the baby that she named after me will die. And I'll end up dying, too, trying to protect them. Which means that the last thing that I'll see in this world will be the look in her eyes when I fail them. I'd rather see a thousand White Walkers than see that.

author: sam
content: Thank you.

content: You know that The Citadel will make you swear off women, too.

content: They'll bloody try.

author: jon snow
content: Sam?

author: sam

author: jon snow
content: Sam…

content: You've just been beaten half to death. How did you--

author: sam

content: I'm glad the end of the worldo s working out for someone.

author: sam

Just the parts he'll use to make his heir. Until you've given him a boy or two and he's finished using them. He's got incredible plans for those parts. So. Shall we wait for him to come back, or shall we begin now?

content: You're leaving it to me? Good. Let's begin.

content: Stop! Stop!

content: Open the gates!

content: I can't hear you.

author: arya stark
content: You know who I am. I'm Arya Stark.

author: arya stark
content: Do you know who you are?
