author: sparrow
content: If I were to let you leave right now, where would you go? What would you seek out?

author: margaery tyrell
content: I'd go to my brother, my husband, my family

author: sparrow
content: Of course, but for you, that means seeking out money, finery, power Seeking out your family means seeking out sin I'm not maligning you I sought those things out, too. To the exclusion of all else My father was a cobbler He died with I was young and I took over his shop He was a simple man and he made simple shoes But I found that the more work I put into my shoes, the more people wanted them Fine leather, ornamentation, detailing, and time Time most of all Dozens of hours spent on a single pair

author: margaery tyrell
content: Quality takes time

author: sparrow
content: Yes I imagine you've worn a year of someone's life on your back The highborn liked to cover their feet with my time and they paid well for the privilege I used their money to buy a taste of their lives for myself Each time I indulged, I felt myself ascending to something better

author: margaery tyrell
content: And one day you walked through a graveyard and realized it was all for nothing and set out on the path to righteousness Book of the Stranger, verse 25

author: sparrow
content: You know

author: margaery tyrell
content: Septa Unella reads it to me At me

author: sparrow
content: Yes, yes, she does enjoy reading at people You're close But it wasn't a graveyard It was a feast I bought old fine wine and young pretty girls and invited my friends to come share it all We passed around the wine, passed around the women, and soon we fell into a stupor I woke before dawn I could barely stand Everyone else was asleep on the couches or on the floor, lying in heaps next to their fine clothes The truth of their bodies laid bare I could smell them beneath the incense and the perfume and the fine food that had already started to turn And I saw it with perfect clarity I saw what my sins were The gold I had, the wine I drank, the women I used, my ceaseless struggle to maintain my position It was all part of a story A story I was telling myself about who I was A collection of lies that would disappear in the light The people I was trying to climb away from, the beggars in the street, the poor, they were closer to the truth than I ever was

author: margaery tyrell
content: So what did you do?

author: sparrow
content: I left to go and find them I didn't even put on my shoes I walked out the door and never went back

author: sparrow
content: Come, let's go and see him

author: margaery tyrell
content: Who?

author: sparrow
content: Your brother

author: margaery tyrell
content: enters her brother's cell. The door closes and locks behind her. Loras is lying on the floor.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Loras. Loras.

author: margaery tyrell
content: helps LORAS to his knees. He cries.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Listen to me. You need to stay strong.

author: loras
content: I can't stay strong. I never was strong.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You are strong. You are the future of our house, the future of our family.

author: loras
content: I don't care about that.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Shh. Have you -- have you told them that? That you don't care?

author: loras
content: I just want it to stop. Help me.

author: margaery tyrell
content: They want me to help you. They want me told help tear you down. That's why he's letting me see you, I know it is. And if either of us give in to what they want, then they win.

author: loras
content: Let them win. Just make it stop. Please.

author: loras
content: begins sobbing. MARGAERY embraces him.

author: margaery tyrell
content: All right.

author: cersei lannister
content: is walking down the hall to TOMMEN's chamber. She hears MAESTER PYCELLE talking.

author: maester pycelle
content: And now, how to avert disaster with our current predicament. This High Sparrow. I have dealt with fanatics of every description, Your Grace. Not setting them off, that's the most important thing. You are beset with enemies both within and without.

author: cersei lannister
content: enters the room

author: cersei lannister
content: What are you doing here?

author: maester pycelle
content: I am advising the king on our current predicament.

author: cersei lannister
content: Leave.

author: maester pycell
content: I am a member of the Small Council. The king's small --

author: cersei lannister
content: Is this a Small Council meeting?

author: maester pycell
content: Obviously not. I'm here to lend my wisdom and my support.

author: tommen lannister
content: Thank you for your counsel, Grand Maester. That will be all for now.

author: maester pycell
content: Your Grace.

author: maester
content: PYCELLE hobbles towards the door. As he leaves, he flashes CERSEI a smile. CERSEI closes the door.

author: cersei lannister
content: Since I've missed the past several Small Coucil meetings, I wanted to speak to you about a few things.

author: tommen lannister
content: I've been thinking about the High Sparrow.

author: cersei lannister
content: As have we all, unfortunately.

author: tommen lannister
content: We need to be careful in dealing with such a man. To prevent things from escalating any further. We have to be careful not to antagonize him. He has Margaery. We can't put her at risk. He's dangerous.

author: cersei lannister
content: Look at me. What did they do to me? To the king's own mother?

author: cersei lannister
content: It's all right. It's done. It's in the past. And of course Margaery's safety is paramount.

author: tommen lannister
content: You don't like Margaery, do you?

author: cersei lannister
content: Whether I like her or not is completely unimportant. Margaery is the queen. Queens must command respect. Kings even more so. Not just for their own sake, but for everyone's. The High Sparrow has no respect for kings or queens. No respect for anything in this world. He has no use for the things of this world. He want to knock them down and replace them with what? With fantasies. With beggars in the street. With nothing.

author: tommen lannister
content: Mother...there's something I want to tell you. Something the High Sparrow told me.

author: cersei lannister
content: You've spoken with him?

author: tommen lannister
content: I promised him I wouldn't tell anyone. If he found out I told --

author: cersei lannister
content: It would be a breach of confidence which he would not take lightly, given his constant prattling about the truth. I am your mother. You can always trust me.

author: kevan
content: and LADY OLENNA are waiting in the Small Council chamber for the meeting to start. CERSEI and JAIME enter.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Small Council meeting has been postponed on the king's orders.

author: kevin
content: and LADY OLENNA stand up.

author: lady olenna
content: I would have thought we were perfectly clear the first time. You're not welcome.

author: cersei lannister
content: You once spoke of your respect for our father because he understood the necessity of working with one's rivals.

author: lady olenna
content: My dear, you have been stripped of your dignity and authority, publicly shamed, and confined to the Red Keep. What's left to work with?

author: jaime lannister
content: Cersei is the mother of the king. She has the king's ear and his trust. And the king has been speaking regularly with the High Sparrow about Queen Margaery and Ser Loras.

author: cersei lannister
content: The High Sparrow seized power knowing full well we'd bicker amongst ourselves instead of seizing it back. Here we are. Well done to us. Now the future of the Seven Kingdoms rest in his dirty, peasant hands. In a few days, he'll have a trial for me. But before that, Queen Margaery will make her walk of atonement. Yes, Margaery will repent her sins before the good people of the city.

author: lady olenna
content: Oh, no. That cannot happen. That will not happen.

author: cersei lannister
content: I agree.

author: jaime lannister
content: You've got the second largest army in Westeros. You'll bring them into the city, stop queen Margaery's humiliation before it starts, and take her back into Crown custody.

author: kevan
content: The king has ordered me to take no action against the High Sparrow or the Faith Militant out of fear for the queen's safety.

author: jaime lannister

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How long does it take?

author: jorah mormont
content: I don't know that either. But I've seen what happens when it goes far enough. I'll end things before that.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

author: jorah mormont
content: Don't be. All I've ever wanted was to serve you. Tyrion Lannister was right. I love you. I'll always love you. Goodbye, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do not walk away from your queen, Jorah the Andal.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You have not been dismissed. You pledged yourself to me. You swore to obey my commands for the rest of your life.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, I command you to find the cure wherever it is in this world. I command you to heal yourself and then return to me. When I take the Seven Kingdoms, I need you by my side.

author: varys
content: In the last fortnight since our pact with the Masters, how many killings have been carried out by the Sons of the Harpy?

author: grey worm
content: None.

author: varys
content: And how many Masters have been butchered by the free men.

author: grey worm
content: Two, but that was the day of the pact. Since then, nothing.

author: varys
content: So it's safe to say that a fragile peace has taken hold.

author: grey worm
content: For now.

author: varys
content: For now is the best we get in our profession.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not enough.

author: varys
content: Considering the city was on the brink of civil war, I'd say it's a good start.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not enough for Meereen to have peace. They need to know Daenerys is responsible for it. The Sons of the Harpy have a good story. Resist the foreign invaders. Our queen has an even better story. Mother of Dragons, Breaker of Chains and...all that.

author: missandei
content: The people know who brought them freedom.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, but do they know who brought them security? Who brought about an end to the violence? We need someone the people trust, someone they know who cannot be bought or influenced.

author: varys
content: Sounds like quite the hero. Where would we find him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who said anything about “him”?

author: man
content: You stand in the presence of Kinvara, High Priestess of the Red Temple of Volantis, the Flame of Truth, the Light of Wisdom, the First Servant of the Lord of Light.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Welcome to Meereen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's about the extent of my Valyrian.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank you for travelling all this way. I know from personal experience how uncomfortable the journey can be.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The truth is we need your help. We had hoped that we could somehow persuade you to --

author: kinvara
content: You don't need to persuade me. I came to help.

author: kinvara
content: Daenerys Stormborn is the one who was promised. From the fire she was reborn to remake the world.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes.

author: kinvara
content: She has freed the slaves from their chains and crucified the Masters for their sins.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She did indeed.

author: kinvara
content: Her dragons are fire made flesh, a gift from the Lord of Light. But you heard all this before, haven't you? On the Long Bridge of Volantis. The dragons will purify nonbelievers by the thousands, burning their sins and flesh away.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ideally we'd avoid purifying too many nonbelievers. The Mother of Dragons has followers of many different faiths.

author: kinvara
content: You want your queen to be worshipped and obeyed. And while she's gone, you want her advisors to be worshipped and obeyed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'd settle for obeyed.

author: kinvara
content: I will summon my most eloquent priests. They will spread the word. Daenerys has been sent to lead the people against the darkness in this war and in the great war still to come.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That sounds most excellent --

author: varys
content: A man named Stannis Baratheon was anointed as the chosen one by one of your priestesses. He, too, had a glorious destiny. He attacked King's Landing and was soundly defeated by the man standing beside me. Last I had heard, he'd been defeated again, this time at Winterfell and this time for good.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We'd be most grateful for any support you could provide the queen.

author: varys
content: I suppose it's hard for a fanatic to admit a mistake. Isn't that the whole point of being a fanatic? You're always right. Everything is the Lordo s will.

author: kinvara
content: Everything is the Lordo s will. But men and women make mistakes. Even honest servants of the Lord.

author: varys
content: And you, an honest servant of the lord, why should I trust you to know any more than the priestess who counseled Stannis?

author: tyrion lannister
content: My friend has a healthy skepticism of religion, but we are all loyal supporters of the queen.

author: kinvara
content: Everyone is what they are and where they are for a reason. Terrible things happen for a reason. Take what happened to you, Lord Varys, when you were a child. If not for your mutilation at the hand of a second-rate sorcerer, you wouldn't be here helping the Lordo s Chosen bring his light into the world. Knowledge has made you powerful. But there's still so much you don't know. Do you remember what you heard that night when the sorcerer tossed your parts in the fire? You heard a voice call out from the flames. Do you remember? Should I tell you what the voice said?

author: kinvara
content: Should I tell you the name of the one who spoke?

author: kinvara
content: We serve the same queen. If you are her true friend, you have nothing to fear from me.

author: bran stark
content: What?

author: bran stark
content: He saw me, the Night King! He saw me!

author: threeeyed raven
content: He touched you.

author: bran stark
content: I don't know. He was close, but --

author: threeeyed raven
content: He knows you are here. He'll come for you.

author: bran stark
content: But he can't get in.

author: threeeyed raven
content: He can now. His mark is on you. You must leave, all of you.

author: meera
content: Come on, Hodor. Help me with the sledge.

author: hodor
content: Hodor.

author: bran stark
content: I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

author: threeeyed raven
content: The time has come.

author: bran stark
content: The time for what?

author: threeeyed raven
content: For you to become me.

author: bran stark
content: But am I ready?

author: threeeyed raven
content: No.

author: jon snow
content: We can't defend the north from the Walkers and the south from the Boltons. If we want to survive, we need Winterfell, and to take Winterfell, we need more men.

author: davos
content: Aside from the Starks and the Boltons, the most powerful houses in the North are the Umbers, the Karstarks, and the Manderlys.

author: davos
content: The Umbers and the Karstarks have already declared for the Boltons, so we're not doing so well there.

author: sansa stark
content: The Umbers gave Rickon to our enemies. They can hang. But the Karstarks declared for Ramsay without knowing they had another choice.

author: davos
content: I beg your pardon, my lady, but they know that a Stark beheaded their father. I don't think we can count on them either.

author: sansa stark
content: How well do you know the North, Ser Davos?

author: davos
content: Precious little, my lady.

author: sansa stark
content: My father always said Northerners are different. More loyal, more suspicious of outsiders.

author: davos
content: They may well be loyal, but how many rose up against the Boltons when they betrayed your family? I may not know the North, but I know men. They're more or less the same in any corner of the world and even the bravest of them don't want to see their wives and children skinned for a lost cause. If Jon's going to convince them to fight alongside him, they need to believe it's a fight they can win.

author: jon snow
content: There are more than three other houses in the North -- Glover, Mormont, Cerwyn, Mazin, Hornwood. Two dozen more. Together they equal all the others. We can start small and build.

author: sansa stark
content: The North remembers. They remember the Stark name. People will still risk everything for it, from White Harbor to Ramsay's own door.

author: davos
content: I don't doubt it. But Jon doesn't have the Stark name.

author: sansa stark
content: No, but I do.

author: sansa stark
content: Jon is every bit as much Ned Stark's son as Ramsay is Roose Bolton's. Ant there are also the Tullys. They're not Northern, but they will back us against the Boltons without question.

author: davos
content: I didn't know the Tullys still had an army.

author: sansa stark
content: My uncle the Blackfish has reformed it and retaken Riverrun.

author: jon snow
content: How do you know that?

author: sansa stark
content: Ramsay received a raven before I escaped Winterfell.

author: davos
content: That's good. The Blackfish is a legend. His support would mean a great deal. Stark, Tully, a few more houses, almost starts to look like a winning side.

author: brienne
content: I've sworn to protect you, my lady.

author: sansa stark
content: You heard them. We need more men and my uncle has an army.

author: brienne
content: We can send the Blackfish a raven.

author: sansa stark
content: Can't risk Ramsay intercepting it. It has to be you.

author: sansa stark
content: Ride for Riverrun. My uncle will talk to you and you'll know how to talk to him.

author: sansa stark
content: What is it?

author: brienne
content: I don't like leaving you here alone.

author: sansa stark
content: With Jon?

author: brienne
content: Not him. He seems trustworthy. A bit brooding, perhaps. I suppose that's understandable, considering. The others, though. Davos and the Red Woman helped a man murder his own brother with blood magic. And when Stannis paid for his crime, where were they? Already out looking for a leader with better prospects. And that wildling fellow with the beard --

author: sansa stark
content: Jon isn't Tormund. Jon isn't Davos, the Red Woman, or Stannis for that matter. Jon is Jon. He's my brother. He'll keep me safe. I trust him.

author: brienne
content: Then why did you lie to him when he asked you how you learned about Riverrun?

author: jon snow
content: New dress?

author: sansa stark
content: I made it myself. Do you like it?

author: jon snow
content: Year, it's -- I like the wolf bit.

author: sansa stark
content: Good, because I made this for you.

author: sansa stark
content: I made it like the one Father used to wear. As near as I can remember.

author: jon snow
content: Thank you, Sansa.

author: sansa stark
content: You're welcome.

author: jon snow
content: Don't knock it down while I'm gone.

author: dolorous edd
content: I'll do my best.

author: dolorous edd
content: Good luck.

author: man
content: Should we close the gate, Lord Commander?

author: dolorous edd
content: I'm not the Lord Comman --

author: dolorous edd
content: Yeah, ahem, close the bloody gate.

author: meera
content: We can go home now, Hodor. Well, maybe not home home, but somewhere that isn't a cave.

author: meera
content: Eat something that isn't moss. I want an egg. How do you like ‘em? Boiled? Fried up with some butter?

author: meera
content: With a rasher of bacon and some blood sausage.

author: leaf
content: Get Bran and run!

author: meera
content: Bran. Bran, wake up. Bran.

author: hodor
content: Hodor. Hodor.

author: meera
content: Bran, wake up.

author: meera
content: Hodor.

author: meera
content: Help me!

author: rickard
content: Remember that you are a Stark. Comport yourself with dignity at the Vale and try to stay out of fights.

author: young ned
content: Yes, Father.

author: rickard
content: But if you have to fight, win.

author: meera
content: Bran! Bran, wake up!

author: meera
content: Bran! Bran! Bran, wake up.

author: meera
content: You have to wake up. We need Hodor.

author: meera
content: Bran, we're all going to die!

author: meera
content: Bran, wake up! We're all going to die! Bran! Bran!

author: meera
content: Bran, you have to wake up! We need Hodor!

author: meera
content: Warg into Hodor now!

author: meera
content: Bran, wake up. We need Hodor. We need Hodor. Warg into Hodor now! Now!

author: threeeyed raven
content: Listen to your friend, Brandon.

author: hodor
content: Hodor. Hodor. Hodor. Hodor.

author: meera
content: Summer!

author: leaf
content: Go. Go!

author: threeeyed raven
content: The time has come. Leave me.

author: meera
content: What are you doing?

author: leaf
content: Go!

author: meera
content: Hodor, hurry!

author: meera
content: Hold the door!

author: meera
content: Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door!
Wylis! What's the matter?

author: young hodor
content: Hold the door!

author: young hodor
content: Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door!

author: young hodor
content: Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold the door! Hold door! Hold door! Hold door! Hold door! Hodor! Hodor! Hodor! Hodor! Hodor! Hodor! Hodor!

author: bran stark
content: Meera. They found us.

author: meera
content: I'm so sorry.

author: rider
content: Come with me, now.

author: rider
content: The dead don't rest.

author: gilly
content: It's so green.

author: sam
content: Oh, yes. Once you get south of the Riverlands, very different sorts of trees start to take over. Maple, elm, beech, poplar. The odd willow. And of course now that summer's over, you'll start seeing the autumn colors coming in. Still, you'll find more green here than anywhere else.

author: gilly
content: You're nervous. You're a nervous talker.

author: gilly
content: That's not any better being a nervous mute.

author: sam
content: I didn't think I'd ever come back here after my father made me renounce my title and inheritance and, well, threaten to kill me if I didn't. A person just doesn't feel welcome at that point.

author: sam
content: And I certainly didn't expect to be introducing him to my family. So you know what to tell them.

author: gilly
content: That Little Sam is your baby.

author: sam
content: Yes, now that's very important. If he thinks that Little Sam is his grandchild, he'll take you in. He'll get an education. He'll learn to read. And you can help teach him. Huh?

author: gilly
content: What did you tell your family about me?

author: sam
content: I told them I met you in the North.

author: gilly
content: Did you tell them how far north?

author: sam
content: Well, it wasn't a very large piece of parchment.

author: gilly
content: You didn't tell them where I'm really from? You didn't tell them I'm a wildling?

author: sam
content: The thing is...my father doesn't like wildlings. He hoped I'd make a man of myself by “killing some bloody wildlings,” so it's probably a good subject to avoid if at all possible.

author: gilly
content: I think we're here.

author: melessa
content: Sam. Oh, Sam.

author: sam
content: Oh, hello, Mother.

author: melessa
content: I never thought I'd see you again. You look wonderful.

author: sam
content: Oh.

author: sam
content: Talla? Gods, you're a woman now.

author: talla
content: Father says I have to marry Symun Fossoway. He has yellow teeth- -

author: melessa
content: That's enough, Talla.

author: sam
content: Oh, um, Mother, this is Gilly.

author: melessa
content: Oh, my. You are lovely.

author: gilly
content: I am happy to know you, Lady Tarly.

author: sam
content: Oh, and this, this is our son Samwell.

author: melessa
content: Hello, little one. It's me, your grandmother.

author: melessa
content: May I hold him?

author: gilly
content: Yes, of course.

author: melessa
content: You have a curious mind, I can tell. You'll be a scholar like your father.

author: sam
content: Where is Father? And Dickon?

author: melessa
content: They're on a hunt. They'll join us for dinner. Come inside. Such a journey. You must be exhausted.

author: talla
content: Come, you'll be wanting a bath after all that travel. Oh, and a dress for dinner. You can wear one of mine. What's your color? Midnight blue or silver? Silver, maybe. Come. You can choose one of my bedrooms if you want.

author: tommen lannister
content: Is there no other way?

author: sparrow
content: You're afraid for her?

author: tommen lannister
content: Of course I'm afraid for her! It just seems very dangerous.

author: sparrow
content: She'll be protected the entire way. The Faith Militant are very stern with those who overstep their bounds. And Queen Margaery isn't your mother. I suspect the gods will predispose the common people to gentleness on her behalf. She's truly opened her heart to them.

author: tommen lannister
content: She's always been very devoted to the poor and the unfortunate.

author: sparrow
content: And now she's devoted to the gods as well. Would you like to see her?

author: tommen lannister
content: Have they hurt you? Have they mistreated you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: No, Your Grace.

author: tommen lannister
content: I've missed you. More than you could know.

author: margaery tyrell
content: We'll be together again soon and everything will be better than it was before.

author: tommen lannister
content: Better how? Soon the- - walk of atonement. He says there's no other way.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Have you spoken to him at all, the High Sparrow?

author: tommen lannister
content: Yes, a few times. Have you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: Yes, I have. He's not quite what we thought he was, is he?

author: margaery tyrell
content: You think I'm mad. I sound mad.

author: tommen lannister
content: No. No, you don't. You- - you could never. You're right, he's not. He's a lot more- -

author: margaery tyrell
content: He is. There's something about him. His way of looking at the world. It's not an easy thing admitting to yourself what you really are. It's taken me a while. He's helped me.

author: tommen lannister
content: What are you talking about? You're a good person. You've always been a good person. You're the best person I know.

author: tommen lannister
content: I was just telling him about your devotion to the poor.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Ah, yes, I visited their hovels and I fed them soup and I made sure I was seen doing it. I never gave them what they really needed, though. I've had lots of time to think about how good I was at seeming good. All those stories I told myself about who I was and why I did the things I did. There were so many lies in those stories.

author: tommen lannister
content: I don't understand.

author: margaery tyrell
content: It's all right. It really is. It's such a relief to let go of those lies.

author: tommen lannister
content: What about Loras?

author: margaery tyrell
content: I love my brother. I will always love my brother. His soul is pure and perfect. His sins don't erase that purity, they only obscure it. He just needs to atone for them. We all do. Sooner or later, one way or another. The gods have a plan for us all.

author: gilly
content: It's hard to walk in this.

author: sam
content: It's beautiful. You're beautiful.

author: sam
content: This venison, it's very tasty. Is it from today's hunt?

author: dickon
content: Well, no. We haven't been able to cure that one yet. This is last week's.

author: sam
content: Oh, of course. Sorry. Long journey.

author: dickon
content: Brought it down from 70 yards. One shot.

author: sam
content: Oh, that's a fair distance.

author: dickon
content: So do you do much hunting up at the wall?

author: sam
content: Oh, yes. Yes. A good amount. North of the Wall, you don't hunt, you don't eat.

author: dickon
content: Mm-hmmm. Mostly deer or is it elk as well?

author: sam
content: Rabbits. Sometimes squirrels. I say “we,” it's my friend Jon mostly. Sometimes Edd. Oh, and Gilly. She's- - she's quite a good hunter as well. Um, huntress.

author: melessa
content: I imagine it's common where you're from. We once met a man, Lord Umber from Last Hearth, wasn't it, Randyll, who said he taught all his daughters how to hunt.

author: talla
content: Your father taught you to hunt? Our father would never teach us. I think our father could learn a thing or two from your father.

author: randyll
content: That's enough of that.

author: melessa
content: Samwell, would you care for more bread?

author: sam
content: Oh, yes. Yes, please. Thank you, Mother.

author: randyll
content: Not fat enough already?

author: sam
content: I travelled south under orders from the Lord Commander. He wants me to- -

author: randyll
content: I read your letter. You're to be a maester.

author: sam
content: Yes. And once I have my chain, I'll return to Castle Black.

author: randyll
content: I thought the Night's Watch might make a man of you. Something resembling a man at least. You managed to stay soft and fat.

author: randyll
content: Your nose buried in books. Spending your life reading about the achievements of better men. I'll wager you still can't sit a horse or wield a sword.

author: melessa
content: Randyll, to be maester of the Night's Watch is a great honor.

author: gilly
content: He can wield a sword. He killed a Thenn. He killed a White Walker.

author: dickon
content: There's no such thing.

author: gilly
content: I saw it with my own eyes on our way down to Castle Black. He drove a dagger into the walker's heart. He risked his own life to save mine more than once. He's a greater warrior than either of you will ever be.

author: randyll
content: Your way down to Castle Black? Where did he kill a white walker? Where are you from? How'd you come to meet my son?

author: gilly
content: The Night's Watch came to our keep.

author: randyll
content: Where?

author: sam
content: Gilly.

author: gilly
content: North of the Wall.

author: randyll
content: North of the Wall? You're a Wildling. The Seven Kingdoms have waged war against these savages for centuries and here I sit hosting one in my hall thanks to my son. See that sword?

author: randyll
content: It's called Heartsbane. It's been in our family for 500 years. It's Valyrian steel. Only a handful of them left in the world. It's supposed to go to my firstborn son after I die. To him. He will never wield that sword. If he were to become Lord Tarly of Horn Hill, it would be the end of this house. I took you for a Mole's Town whore when I saw you and I made my peace with that. Who else would have him? But I overestimated him. No. It was a wildling whore that seduced my son. This you getting back at me, boy? Hmm? Bring that to my table and making me dine with it. And you got what you were after, didn't you? A bastard. A half-breed bastard. Your invitation into our home.

author: melessa
content: Come, my dear. Talla.

author: melessa
content: I've lost my appetite.

author: randyll
content: He dishonors us.

author: melessa
content: You dishonor yourself.

author: randyll
content: Your mother's a fine woman. You're not worthy of her. To please her, I'll take the wildling in. She can work in the kitchens. The bastard will be raised here. But this will be the last night you ever spend at Horn Hill.

author: sam
content: I'm sorry I let him treat you that way. I was afraid he'd turn you and Little Sam away.

author: gilly
content: I'm not angry at you. I'm angry that horrible people can treat good people that way and get away with it. When do you have to go?

author: sam
content: First light.

author: sam
content: Say good-bye to him for me.

author: gilly
content: You're not what he thinks you are, Sam. He doesn't know what you are.

author: sam
content: Good-bye, Gilly.

author: gilly
content: Sam?

author: sam
content: We're leaving.

author: gilly
content: What?

author: sam
content: Get your things.

author: gilly
content: I don't have any things.

author: gilly
content: What are you doing?

author: sam
content: We belong together. All of us.

author: gilly
content: What about your mother and sister?

author: sam
content: Oh, they'll understand.

author: gilly
content: Your sister's dress.

author: sam
content: She won't mind. Looks better on you anyway.

author: gilly
content: Sam. That's your father's sword.

author: sam
content: It's my family's sword.

author: gilly
content: Sam. Won't he come for it?

author: sam
content: He can bloody well try.

author: clarenzo
content: The lion and the rose are one. I thank the gods above.

author: clarenzo
content: And to you, my beauteous bridge, I pledge undying love.

author: all
content: Hail King Joffrey. Hail Queen Margaery.

author: clarenzo
content: I'll drink a toast to my new queen, for there is no one fairer. Dear Uncle, will you share my joy and be my royal cupbearer?

author: bobono
content: Drink long and deep, my noble king, from this cup of sweet wine.

author: bobono
content: The last drink he shall ever take. And vengeance shall be mine.

author: clarenzo
content: Poison! Murder! I gasp. I- - I die.

author: clarenzo
content: I limp. And it was he…

author: clarenzo
content: that poisoned me. My evil Uncle Imp.

author: lady crane
content: My firstborn son. My golden lion foully, falsely slain. I pray you found a lasting peace free from strife and pain.

author: lady crane
content: Hear my prayer, O cruel gods. Take my life instead. For I cannot face another day when my sweet boy is dead. Oh, woe. Oh grief.

author: lady crane
content: Oh, darkest day, my heart is full of sorrow. All hope is lost. All joy is gone. And there is no tomorrow.

author: bobono
content: What is that I hear and smell? Someone I'll soon send to hell.

author: bobono
content: It's time to see if truth they told who said Tywin Lannister shits gold.

author: izembaro
content: You beast. You beast. You killed my wife and now you've taken your father's life.

author: izembaro
content: No worse child ever stained this land.

author: izembaro
content: Curse the day I named you.

author: bobono
content: My greatest crime. Now I must flee.

author: bobono
content: Then sail across the Narrow Sea to do unto you more treachery.

author: bobono
content: Don't fear the winter.

author: bobono
content: Fear me!

author: izembaro
content: Thank you. Ladies and gentlemen, I give you Bianca, Clarenzo.

author: izembaro
content: I give you Bobono.

author: izembaro
content: I give you Camello.

author: izembaro
content: And last but not least, sweet Lady Crane.

author: camello
content: Give this a good beating. Shake those fleas out. That's a dear.

author: izembaro
content: That crowd was shit.

author: lady crane
content: Girl.

author: lady crane
content: What are you doing back here?

author: arya stark
content: Nothing.

author: lady crane
content: I saw you the other day in the audience. How many times have you seen this stupid play?

author: arya stark
content: Three times.

author: lady crane
content: Did you pay?

author: arya stark
content: No.

author: lady crane
content: I remember when the players came to my village. I didn't have any money, so I snuck in. Just like you. Saw the painted faces, the costumes, listened to the songs, cried when the young lovers died in each other's arms. I ran off and joined them the next day, never looked back.

author: arya stark
content: You're very good.

author: lady crane
content: My final speech is shit.

author: lady crane
content: But to be fair to myself, which I always like to be, the writing's no good.

author: arya stark
content: So change it. It would all just be farting, belching, and slapping without you.

author: lady crane
content: How would you change it?

author: arya stark
content: The queen loves her son more than anything. And he was taken from her before she could say good-bye. She wouldn't just cry. She would be angry. She would want to kill the person who did this to her.

author: lady crane
content: What's your name?

author: arya stark
content: Mercy.

author: lady crane
content: You have very expressive eyes, Mercy.

author: lady crane
content: Wonderful eyebrows. Do you like pretending to be other people?

author: arya stark
content: I have to go. My father's waiting for me.

author: bianca
content: Lady Crane, they loved you.

author: lady crane
content: They were sweet. Or drunk. Drunkenly sweet.

author: izembaro
content: No laugh for Nedo s death. These people are worse than animals.

author: izembaro
content: But they loved her. They all love her.

author: camello
content: Yes, you are adored by people and animals alike.

author: lady crane
content: I do what I can with what I'm given.

author: izembaro
content: With what you're given?

author: lady crane
content: Well, I was thinking- -

author: izembaro
content: Oh, we're all thinkers now, are we?

author: izembaro
content: Full to the tits with ideas.

author: lady crane
content: I didn't mean- -

author: izembaro
content: You have ideas, I have ideas, he has ideas. Why should my ideas have any more value than yours simply because I've been doing this my whole life? Who is anyone to judge my work? This is my profession. I know what I'm doing.

author: izembaro
content: You have no right to an opinion.

author: arya stark
content: Careful of that one. She wants you dead.

author: jaqen hghar
content: And?

author: waif
content: As I expected.

author: jaqen hghar
content: A shame. A girl had many gifts.

author: waif
content: You promised me.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Don't let her suffer.

author: mace
content: My lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: My lord.

author: mace
content: My friends, the hour has come. Madness has overtaken this city and grasped in its claws my children. But now we must drive it back under the rocks whence it came. Madness has had its day!

author: captain
content: Forward, march!

author: sparrow
content: Rich or poor, noble or common, if we win, we must atone. Margaery of House Tyrell came to us a sinner. She stood before the gods in the holy sept and lied. She turned a blind eye to her brother's sins. She disgraces her house, the king, and herself.

author: captain
content: Company, halt! Face front! Turn!

author: sparrow
content: Lord Tyrell.

author: sparrow
content: Ser Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: Sorry to interrupt. We're here for Queen Margaery and Ser Loras Tyrell. Give them to us and we'll be on our way.

author: sparrow
content: I don't have the authority to give them to you. And you don't have the authority to take them.

author: captain
content: Lock spears!

author: jaime lannister
content: I speak for King Tommen of House Baratheon, First of His Name.

author: sparrow
content: The gods don't recognize his authority in this matter.

author: jaime lannister
content: You already insulted one great house. It won't happen twice. Every last sparrow will die before Margaery walks down that street.

author: sparrow
content: To die in the service of the gods would please each and every one of us. We yearn for it. But there is no call for it today. There will be no walk of atonement.

author: captain
content: Order up!

author: sparrow
content: Queen Margaery has already atoned for her sins by bringing another into the true light of the Seven.

author: sparrow
content: Together we announce a new age of harmony. A holy alliance between the Crown and the Faith.

author: woman
content: Long live King Tommen and bless you, Queen Margaery!

author: tommen lannister
content: The crown and the faith are the twin pillars upon which the world rests. Together we will restore the Seven Kingdoms to glory.

author: mace
content: What's happening?

author: olenna tyrell
content: He's beaten us. That's what's happening.

author: tommen lannister
content: When you attack the Faith, you attack the Crown. Anyone who attacks the Crown is unfit to serve as Lord Commander of the Kingsguard.

author: jaime lannister
content: I've been a member of the Kingsguard since before you were born. You don't have to do this. You don't have to do anything.

author: tommen lannister
content: I have to answer to the gods.

author: jaime lannister
content: Not when you're sitting in that chair.

author: tommen lannister
content: The Crown's decision on this matter is final.

author: jaime lannister
content: Will I be walking naked in the streets? Or will I spend a few months in the sept dungeons first to teach me about the gods' mercy?

author: tommen lannister
content: You have served your house and your king faithfully for many years. And you will continue to do so. But not in this city.

author: walder
content: You've lost it?

author: black walder
content: Yes, father.

author: walder
content: It's a castle, not a bloody sheep. Presumably you still know where it is. You didn't lose Riverrun. You let the Blackfish take it from you.

author: lothar
content: He surprised us. He knows the castle better than anyone.

author: walder
content: You did lose the Blackfish after the Red Wedding. You had him right here in this hall and you let him leave. Then when I told you to hunt him down and kill him, you couldn't find him. That's what it means to lose something. Now he's come back and taken Riverrun.

author: black walder
content: I don't think it's fair to blame us- -

author: walder
content: For 300 years we kissed Tully boots, swore oaths to them and their stinking fish banners. Not again. Riverrun is ours. Take it back.

author: black walder
content: We don't have the men.

author: walder
content: We've got 10 times as many men as the damn Blackfish.

author: black walder
content: The Mallisters have risen against us. And the Blackwoods.

author: lothar
content: The Brotherhood Without Banners is rallying the commoners against us, raiding our supply trains and camps.

author: black walder
content: Riverrun can withstand a siege for a year.

author: walder
content: If I want excuses, I'll put her in charge. They're laughing at us. All across the Riverlands right down to King's Landing, they're laughing at us.

author: walder
content: I hear it in my sleep! I'm not dead yet, unfortunately for you. And I'll not leave this world until they all choke on that laughter. Take that castle back.

author: lothar
content: He'll never yield, Father.

author: walder
content: Oh, he'll yield.

author: walder
content: You'll show him the knife you used to kill Robb Stark's child in his whore mother's belly, and you'll show him the knife you used to open his niece's throat. And you'll remind him who it was that got married at the Red Wedding in the first place. His nephew.

author: walder
content: Cheer up, Lord Edmure. You're going home.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm being sent to deal with the Blackfish. Apparently Walder Frey can't manage it on his own because he's 400 years old. Sent me with an army to the Riverlands and a siege that could last months.

author: cersei lannister
content: BEtter you're elsewhere at the head of an army than in the sept dungeons.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not going to the Riverlands.

author: cersei lannister
content: What, then?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm going to give Bronn the largest bag of gold anyone's ever seen and have him gather the best killers he knows. I'll take them to the sept and I'll remove the High Sparrow's head and every other sparrow head I can find.

author: cersei lannister
content: You can't.

author: jaime lannister
content: He has our son! He stole our son! He's torn our family apart. How should we treat people who tear us apart?

author: cersei lannister
content: We should treat them without mercy and we will. But if you kill the High Sparrow, you won't leave the sept alive. And without you, this is all for nothing. Stand at the head of our army where you belong, where Father wanted you. Show our men where their loyalties belong. Show them what lannisters are, what we do to our enemies. And take that stupid little castle back because it's ours and because you can.

author: jaime lannister
content: You'll stand trial soon. I need to he here for you.

author: cersei lannister
content: It will be a trial by combat. I have the Mountain. They've made us both stronger, all of them.

author: cersei lannister
content: They have no idea how strong we are. No idea what we're going to do to them.

author: cersei lannister
content: We've always been together. We'll always be together. We're the only two people in the world.

author: meera
content: Why did you help us?

author: rider
content: The Three-Eyed Raven sent for me.

author: meera
content: The Three-Eyed Raven's dead.

author: rider
content: Now he lives again.

author: rider
content: When I last saw you, you were a boy. A fearless boy. Loved to climb the castle walls, frighten his mother.

author: bran stark
content: Who are you?

author: bran stark
content: Uncle Benjen. The last letter Jon wrote me said you had been lost beyond the Wall.

author: benjen
content: I led a ranging party deep into the North to find White Walkers. They found us. A white walker stabbed me in the gut with a sword of ice. Left me there to die. To turn. The Children found me. Stopped the walker's magic from taking hold.

author: bran stark
content: How?

author: benjen
content: The same way they made the Walkers in the first place. You saw it yourself.

author: bran stark
content: Dragonglass. A shard of dragonglass plunged into your heart.

author: benjen
content: You are the Three-Eyed Raven now.

author: bran stark
content: I didn't have time to learn. I can't control anything.

author: benjen
content: You must learn to control it before the Night King comes.

author: benjen
content: Drink.

author: benjen
content: One way or another, he will find his way to the world of men. When he does, you will be there waiting for him. And you will be ready.

author: daario
content: Everything all right?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many days' ride to Meereen?

author: daario
content: A week at best.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many ships will I need to bring my khalasar to Westeros?

author: daario
content: Dothraki and all their horses, the Unsullied, the Second Sons- - 1,000 ships easily. Probably more.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And who has that many?

author: daario
content: Nobody.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Nobody yet.

author: daario
content: So we ride for Meereen and after that we sail for Westeros. What then?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I take what is mine.

author: daario
content: You weren't made to sit on a chair in a palance.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What was I made for?

author: daario
content: You're a conqueror, Daenerys Stormborn.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Wait here.

author: daario
content: I'm going after her. Wait for me here.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Every khal who ever lived chose three blood riders to fight beside him and guard his way. But I am not a khal. I will not choose three blood riders. I choose you all.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will ask more of you than any khal has ever asked of his khalassar! Will you ride the wooden horses across the black salt sea?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will you kill my enemies in their iron suits and tear down their stone houses?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will you give me the Seven Kingdoms, the gift Khal Drogo promised me before the Mother of Mountains?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Are you with me?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Now and always?

author: man
content: That's it. Get it to the top.

author: man
content: Steady. Steady.

author: ray
content: Up she goes.

author: ray
content: Hey, come on. Put your back into it, huh?

author: ray
content: Here you are, son.

author: ray
content: Oh, gentlemen, please.

author: ray
content: And you lot, come on. Come on, get it moving. Come on, come on.

author: ray
content: In all my days I've never seen a man swing an ax like that. How many men did it take to cut you down?

author: sandor
content: Just one.

author: ray
content: Ooh. he must have been some kind of monster.

author: sandor
content: He was a woman.

author: ray
content: I think some of the men are a bit afraid of you.

author: sandor
content: I'm used to it.

author: ray
content: When I found you, I thought you'd been dead for days. The way you were stinking already and you had bugs all over you and bone was coming through right there.

author: ray
content: I was gonna give you a proper burial and then you coughed. Oh, nearly shit myself. I reckoned you were gonna die by the time I loaded you on the wagon, but you didn't. Now, I reckoned you'd die a dozen more times over the next few days, but you didn't. What kept you going?

author: sandor
content: Hate.

author: ray
content: No, there's a reason you're still here.

author: sandor
content: Aye, there's a reason. I'm a big fucker and I'm tough to kill.

author: ray
content: No, a reason. Gods aren't done with you yet.

author: sandor
content: I've heard that before. Man was talking about a different god, though.

author: ray
content: Well, maybe he was right. I don't know much about the gods.

author: sandor
content: You're in the wrong line of work.

author: ray
content: Oh, there's plenty of pious sons of bitches who think they know the word of god or gods. I don't. I don't even know their real names. Maybe it is the Seven. Or maybe it's the old gods. Or maybe it's the Lord of Light. Or maybe they're all the same fucking thing. I don't know. What matters, I believe, is that there's something greater than us. And whatever it is, it's got plans for Sandor Clegane.

author: sandor
content: You didn't know me back in my time. You don't know the things I've done.

author: ray
content: I've heard stories.

author: sandor
content: If the gods are real...why haven't they punished me?

author: ray
content: They have.

author: sparrow
content: Your Grace. What are we reading today?

author: margaery tyrell
content: The Book of the Mother, Your Holiness. Chapter three, verse 12.

author: sparrow
content: Ah, “As water rounds the stones, smoothing- -”

author: margaery tyrell
content: Smoothing what was jagged, so does a woman's love calm a man's brute nature. A wife salves her husbando s wounds, a mother sings her son to sleep.”

author: sparrow
content: You learn quickly. There are some who know every verse of the sacred text, but don't have a drop of the Mother's mercy in their blood and savages who can't read at all who understand the Father's wisdom.

author: margaery tyrell
content: For year I pretended to love the poor, the afflicted. I had pity for them, but I never loved them. They disgusted me.

author: sparrow
content: They are hard to love.

author: sparrow
content: The poor disgust us because they are us, shorn of our illusions. They show us what we'd look like without our fine clothes. How'd we smell without perfume.

author: sparrow
content: Can I ask you about a personal matter?

author: margaery tyrell
content: Of course.

author: sparrow
content: The king mentioned that since your reunion, you haven't joined him in the marriage bed.

author: margaery tyrell
content: No.

author: sparrow
content: You have a duty, Your Grace. To your husband, your king, your country, to the gods themselves.

author: margaery tyrell
content: It's just...the desires that once drove me no longer do.

author: sparrow
content: Congress does not require desire on the woman's part, only patience. The king must have an heir if we are to continue our good work.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Forgive me. Sometimes the truth path is hard to find.

author: sparrow
content: Hard to find and harder still to walk upon. But you've made great progress. I only pray your grandmother follows your lead.

author: margaery tyrell
content: My grandmother?

author: sparrow
content: Yes. The Queen of Thorns is a remarkable woman, a strong woman, and an unrepentant sinner. You must teach her the new way as she taught you the old. Or I fear for her safety, body and soul.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Does it move or talk? I want to speak with you alone.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Septa Unella has been my true friend and counselor.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Oh, this is madness!

author: olenna tyrell
content: You're not in your sanctuary now, my dear. All I have to do is whistle and my men will stroll in here and bash you about...

author: margaery tyrell
content: Grandmother.

author: olenna tyrell
content: until I tell them to stop. If I tell them to stop. You could use a good bashing.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Grandmother, please.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What have they done to you?

author: margaery tyrell
content: You marched against the High Sparrow, against the Faith.

author: olenna tyrell
content: We marched for you.

author: margaery tyrell
content: The gods could have punished you and Father, but they didn't. They showed mercy.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And what about your brother? What mercy did they show him?

author: margaery tyrell
content: Loras's only hope is to confess his crimes and repent. If he does, the Faith will allow him to return to Highgarden. He'll have to renounce his name and title...

author: olenna tyrell
content: Have you lost your mind?

author: margaery tyrell
content: and live his life as a penitent.

author: olenna tyrell
content: He is the heir to Highgarden, the future of House Tyrell.

author: margaery tyrell
content: He can begin again.

author: olenna tyrell
content: As a mindless fanatic.

author: margaery tyrell
content: As a free man.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You will leave for Highgarden today. There is no law that says you must stay here.

author: margaery tyrell
content: I am the queen. It is my duty to serve my husband the king.

author: margaery tyrell
content: But you should leave, Grandmother. Your place is at home.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I will never leave you. Never.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You must.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Go home. Find comfort in prayer and good works.

author: margaery tyrell
content: The Mother watches over us all.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I'll see you soon, my dear.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Seven blessings to you, Grandmother.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Shall we pray?

author: dim dalba
content: We said we'd fight with you, King Crow, when the time comes and we meant it, but this isn't what we agreed to. These aren't White Walkers. This isn't an army of the dead. This isn't our find.

author: tormund
content: If it weren't for him, none of us would be here. All of you would be meat in the Night King's army. And I'd be a pile of charred bones just like Mance.

author: dim dalba
content: Remember Mance's camp? It stretched all the way to the horizon. And look at us now. Look what's left of us. And if we lose this, we're gone. Dozens of tribes, hundreds of generations. Be like we were never there at all. We'll be the last of the free folk.

author: jon snow
content: That's what'll happen to you if we lose. The Boltons, the Karstarks, the Umbers, they know you're here. They know that more than half of you are women and children. After they finish with me, they'll come for you. You're right. This isn't your fight. You shouldn't have to come to Winterfell with me. I shouldn't be asking you. It's not the deal we made. I need you with me if we're gonna beat them, and we need to beat them if you're going to survive.

author: tormund
content: The crows killed him because he spoke for the free folk when no other southerners would. He died for us. If we are not willing to do the same for him, we're cowards. And if that's what we are, we deserve to be the last of the free folk.

author: wun wun
content: Snow.

author: jon snow
content: Are you sure they'll come?

author: tormund
content: We're not clever like you southerners. When we say we'll do something, we do it.

author: cersei lannister
content: I heard you were leaving King's Landing.

author: olenna tyrell
content: That is hardly your concern.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your grandson is still a prisoner. You'll leave him rotting in a cell?

author: olenna tyrell
content: Loras rots in a cell because of you. THe High Sparrow rules this city because of you. Our two ancient houses face collapse because of you and your stupidity.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're right. I made a terrible mistake. I carry it with me every single day.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Good.

author: cersei lannister
content: I delivered an army of fanatics onto our doorstep. And now we must fight them together. We need each other.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I wonder if you're the worst person I've ever met. At a certain age, it's hard to recall. But the truly vile do stand out through the years. Do you remember the way you smirked at me when my grandson and granddaughter were dragged off to their cells? I do. I'll never forget it.

author: cersei lannister
content: You love your granddaughter. I love my son. It's the only truth I know. We must defend them.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I'm leaving this wretched city as fast as I can before that shoeless zealot throws me into one of his cells. If you're half as bright as you think you are, you'll find your way out of here, too.

author: cersei lannister
content: Never. I'll never leave my son.

author: olenna tyrell
content: What'll you do, then? You have no support. Not anymore. Your brother's gone. The High Sparrow saw to that. The rest of your family have abandoned you. The people despise you. You're surrounded by enemies, thousands of them. You're going to kill them all by yourself? You've lost, Cersei. It's the only joy I can find in all this misery.

author: man
content: Pick the pace up. Keep going.

author: man
content: Keep it moving!

author: bronn
content: Now, that is a sorry attempt at a siege. Someone needs to teach those sad twats how to dig trenches.

author: jaime lannister
content: Someone certainly does.

author: bronn
content: Oh, no. Not me. I'm just an upjumped sellsword.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're an anointed knight. There's quite a difference.

author: bronn
content: Aye, knights don't get paid.

author: jaime lannister
content: You have better instincts than any officer in the Lannister army.

author: bronn
content: That's like saying I have a bigger cock than anyone in the Unsullied army.

author: jaime lannister
content: I expect to command all the Lannister forces before long. You can be the right hand I lost.

author: bronn
content: You promised me a lordship and a castle and a highborn beauty for a wife.

author: jaime lannister
content: And you'll get all three. A Lannister always- -

author: bronn
content: Don't say it. Don't fucking say it.

author: lothar
content: Come out and fight us, Blackfish. Yield the castle or we'll hang him.

author: lothar
content: This is your last warning. Yield the castle.

author: black walder
content: You think I won't do it, old man?

author: black walder
content: I sliced your niece's throat from ear to ear. And where were you? Running and hiding like a fucking coward. Yield the castle or I cut his throat.

author: brynden
content: Go on, then. Cut his throat.

author: jaime lannister
content: Lothar, is it?

author: lothar
content: Ser Jaime. We didn't know you were coming.

author: jaime lannister
content: Cause you didn't set up a proper perimeter. You just allowed 8,000 men to approach unchallenged.

author: bronn
content: Good thing we're friends or we'd be fucking you in the ass right now.

author: jaime lannister
content: Have Lord Edmure bathed and fed.

author: black walder
content: Whoa, whoa.

author: lothar
content: Walder.

author: black walder
content: Edmure is a prisoner of House Frey.

author: jaime lannister
content: Only a fool makes threats he's not prepared to carry out. Now let's say I threatened to hit you unless you shut your mouth, but you kept talking. What do you think I'd do?

author: black walder
content: I don't give a rat's- -

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm here by the king's command to take back this castle. Have him bathed and fed. Unless you'd like to take his place.

author: lothar
content: Apologies, Ser Jaime.

author: lothar
content: Do as he says.

author: jaime lannister
content: The siege is now under my command. The next time the Blackfish looks out from those ramparts, he'll see an army at his gates, not whatever this is.

author: bronn
content: Have your lads start digging perimeter trenches. Set pickets every hundred yards. And work double-time on those siege towers and trebuchets.

author: black walder
content: Those are our siege towers- -

author: jaime lannister
content: As I said, the siege is under my command. If that's not to your liking, go home.

author: jaime lannister
content: Get word to the Blackfish. I want a parley.

author: bronn
content: A parley or a fight?

author: jaime lannister
content: He's an old man.

author: bronn
content: You've got one hand. My money's on the old boy.

author: jon snow
content: Lady Mormont.

author: lyanna
content: Welcome to Bear Island.

author: sansa stark
content: I remember when you were born, my lady. You were named for my Aunt Lyanna. It was said she was a great beauty. I'm sure you will be, too.

author: lyanna
content: I doubt it. My mother wasn't a great beauty or any other kind of beauty. She was a great warrior, though. She died fighting for your brother, Robb.

author: jon snow
content: I served under your uncle at Castle Black, Lady Lyanna. He was also a great warrior and an honorable man. I was his steward. In fact- -

author: lyanna
content: I think we've had enough small talk. What are you here?

author: jon snow
content: Stannis Baratheon garrisoned at Castle Black before he marched on Winterfell and was killed. He showed me the letter you wrote to him when he petitioned for men. It said- -

author: lyanna
content: I remember what it said. “Bear Island knows no king but the King in the North whose name is Stark.”

author: jon snow
content: Robb is gone, but House Stark is not. And it needs your support now more than ever. I've come with my sister to ask for House Mormont's allegiance.

author: lyanna
content: As far as I understand, you're a Snow and Lady Sansa is a Bolton. Or is she a Lannister? I've heard conflicting reports.

author: sansa stark
content: I did what I had to do to survive, my lady. But I am a Stark. I will always be a Stark.

author: lyanna
content: If you say so. In any case, you don't just want my allegiance. You want my fighting men.

author: lyanna
content: All right, Ser Davos of House Seaworth. How is it you understand how I feel?

author: davos
content: You never thought you'd find yourself in your position. Being responsible for so many lives at such a young age. I never thought I'd be in my position. I was a crabber's son, then I was a smuggler. And now I found myself addressing the lady of a great house in time of war. But I'm here because this isn't someone else's war. It's our war.

author: lyanna
content: Go on, Ser Davos.

author: davos
content: Your uncle, Lord Commander Mormont, made that man his steward. He chose Jon to be his successor because he knew had the courage to do what was right, even if it meant giving his life. Because Jeor Mormont and Jon Snow both understood that the real war isn't between a few squabbling houses. It's between the living and the dead. And make no mistake, my lady, the dead are coming.

author: lyanna
content: Is this true?

author: jon snow
content: Your uncle fought them at the Fist of the First Men. I fought them at Hardhome. We both lost.

author: lyanna
content: House Mormont has kept faith with House Stark for 1,000 years. We will not break faith today.

author: jon snow
content: Thank you, my lady. How many fighting men can we expect?

author: lyanna

author: jaime lannister

author: jaime lannister

author: brynden

author: ray
content: I was a soldier once. All my superiors thought I was brave. I wasn't. I mean, I never ran from a fight. Only because I was afraid my friends would see I was afraid. That's all I was, a coward. We followed orders no matter the orders. Burn that village. Fine, I'm your arsonist. Steal that farmer's crops. Good, I'm your thief. Kill those young lads so they won't take up arms against us. I'm your murderer. I remember once a woman screaming at us, calling us animals as we dragged her son from their hut. But we weren't animals. Animals are true to their nature and we had betrayed ours. I cut that young boy's throat myself as his mother screamed and my friends held her back.

author: ray
content: That night...I felt such shame. Shame was so heavy on me, I couldn't eat, I couldn't sleep.

author: ray
content: All I could do was stare into that dark sky and listen to that mother screaming her son's name. I'll hear her screaming the rest of my life.

author: ray
content: Now, I know I can never bring that lad back. All I can do with time I've got left is bring a little goodness into the world. That's all any of us can do, isn't it? Never too late to stop robbing people, to stop killing people. Start helping people.

author: ray
content: It's never too late to come back.

author: ray
content: And it's not about waiting for the gods to answer your prayers. It's not even about the gods. It's about you. Learning you have to answer your prayers yourself.

author: ray
content: Seven save you, friends. How can we help you?

author: lem
content: What are you doing here?

author: ray
content: Well, we're talking about life. You?

author: lem

author: ray

author: lem

author: ray

author: lem

author: ray

author: lem

author: sandor

author: ray

author: sandor

author: ray

author: sandor

author: ray

Shut your blue eyes, my love. Let the crown fall. The Father above beckons you into his hall. In Seventh Heaven I'll see you once more. But now I seek vengeance on Sansa the whore and my brother the Imp who killed his own king. Born amongst lions, our curse from within. I will slay him, I swear. With noose or with knife, though it take me a fortnight, a moon, or my life.

content: If you think I'm abandoning my family's seat on the Kingslayer's word of honor, you're a bloody fool.

author: brienne
content: Riverrun cannot stand against the Lannisters and the Freys.

author: brynden
content: We can stand longer than your one-handed friend thinks we can.

author: brienne
content: He's not my friend.

author: brynden
content: No?

author: brynden
content: Who gave you permission to cross the siege line and enter the castle? Who gave you that sword with the gold lion on the pommel?

author: brienne
content: Ser Jaime kept his word to your niece Catelyn Stark. He sent me to find Sansa, to help her as Catelyn wanted. He gave me this sword to protect her. That is what I have done and I will continue to do until the day I die.

author: brynden
content: She's exactly like her mother.

author: brynden
content: I don't have enough men to help her take Winterfell.

author: brienne
content: You have more than she does.

author: brynden
content: She wants her home back. I understand that. But this is my home. And if Jaime Lannister wants it, he can bloody well take it the way everyone else does.

author: brienne
content: Find the maester. We need to get a raven north to Sansa.

author: podrick
content: What should I write?

author: brienne
content: Tell her I failed.

author: cersei lannister
content: There's to be a royal announcement?

author: kevan
content: There is.

author: cersei lannister
content: Why wasn't I informed?

author: kevan
content: There is to be a royal announcement in the throne room at this very moment.

author: kevan
content: Where are you going?

author: cersei lannister
content: To stand by my son.

author: kevan
content: Your place is in the gallery with the other ladies of the court.

author: tommen lannister
content: Lords and ladies, the Faith and the Crown are the two pillars that hold up this world. One collapses, so does the other. The Father judges us all. If you break his laws...you will be punished. After conferring with His Holiness the High Septon, we have determined that Loras Tyrell and Cersei lannister's trial will be held in the Great Sept of Baelor on the first day of the Festival of the Mother.

author: tommen lannister
content: Furthermore, after much prayer and reflection, the Crown has decided that from this day forward, trial by combat will be forbidden throughout the Seven Kingdoms. The tradition is a brutish one, a scheme devised by corrupt rulers in order to avoid true judgment from the gods. Cersei Lannister and Loras Tyrell will stand trial before seven septons as it was in the earliest days of the Faith. Seven blessings to all.

author: crowd
content: Seven blessings.

author: qyburn
content: Your Grace...that old rumor you told me about. My little birds investigated.

author: cersei lannister
content: And? Was it just a rumor or something more?

author: qyburn
content: More. Much more.

author: missandei
content: You seem happy.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am happy. You should both be as well. Not so long ago, this city was ready to devour itself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Now it's like a man reborn.

author: missandei
content: I will be happy when our queen returns.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why don't you drink? Why don't either of you ever drink?

author: grey worm
content: Unsullied never drink.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why not?

author: grey worm
content: Rules.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And who made these rules? Your former masters?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Those miserable old shits didn't want you to be human. Have a drink with me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And you? What's your excuse?

author: missandei
content: I have tried wine before. It made me feel funny.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's how you know it's working.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Here's to our queen. Anyone not drinking is disrespecting our queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: To Daenerys Stormborn, Mother of Dragons, Breaker of Chains, long may she reign.

author: grey worm
content: Long may she reign.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do you like it?

author: grey worm
content: Tastes like it has turned.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, yes. Fermentation. One day, after our queen has taken the Seven Kingdoms...I'd like to have my own vineyard. Make my own wine. The Imp's Delight. Only my close friends could drink it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Tell me a joke, Missandei of Naath.

author: missandei
content: I do not know any jokes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Grey worm?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Right. Three lords walk into a tavern- - a Stark, a Martell, and a Lannister. They order ale...

author: tyrion lannister
content: but when the barkeep brings them over, each of them finds a fly in his cup. The Lannister, outraged, shoves the cup aside and demands another. The Martell plucks the fly out and swallows it whole. The Stark reaches into his cup, pulls out the fly and shouts, “Spit it out, you see shit. Spit it out.”

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's funnier in Westeros.

author: grey worm
content: The Starks and the lannisters, i thought these were enemies.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes.

author: missandei
content: A joke is like a story, Torgo Nudho. Not a true story, necessarily.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A story that's supposed to make you laugh, ideally. Not at the moment, perhaps.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Missandei, do you like the wine?

author: missandei
content: I do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Tell a joke.

author: missandei
content: Two translators are on a sinking ship.

author: missandei
content: The first says, “Do you know how to swim?” The second says, “No, but I can shout for help in 19 languages.”

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah!

author: grey worm
content: That is the worst joke I ever heard.

author: missandei
content: You don't even know what a joke is.

author: grey worm
content: I am soldier all my life. You think I never hear joke?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You lied to us.

author: grey worm
content: I make joke.

author: missandei
content: More jokes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I once walked into a brothel with a honeycomb and a jackass. The madam says- -

author: missandei
content: The Masters have come for their property.

author: jaime lannister
content: Lord Edmure.

author: jaime lannister
content: I apologize for the way the Freys treated you. A man of your birth deserved better. You have my word you'll be properly fed and clothes from now on.

author: edmure
content: I have your word?

author: edmure
content: Oh, good. Good, that's- - that's a fine thing. My uncle will never surrender the castle, ser. Whatever game you're playing.

author: jaime lannister
content: The Blackfish is an old man. A good death is all he can hope for. But you, you have a child now, I've heard. A son you sired on your wedding night. You're a potent man.

author: edmure
content: A son I've never met born of a wife that I haven't seen since our first night together.

author: jaime lannister
content: You should be with them both. I can arrange that, you realize? Comfortable rooms for you at Casterly Rock. A tutor for your boy, knights to train him to fight and to ride. And when he comes of age, he'll have a keep of his own.

author: edmure
content: Do you imagine yourself a decent person? Is that it? After you've massacred my family. Kept me in a cell for years. Stolen our lands.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll remind you that our houses are at war. I'm sorry if this conflict has inconvenienced you, but rebelling against the Crown does have consequences.

author: edmure
content: Says the man who shoved his sword through his king's back.

author: jaime lannister
content: Did I give you the impression that this was a negotiation? It's not.

author: edmure
content: You understand. On some level you understand that you're an evil man.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll leave the judgments to the gods.

author: edmure
content: Well, that is convenient for you. You're a fine-looking fellow, aren't you?

author: edmure
content: Your square jaw, your golden armor. Tell me, I want to know. I truly do. How do you live with yourself? All of us have to believe that we're decent, don't we? You have to sleep at night. How do you tell yourself that you're decent after everything that you've done?

author: jaime lannister
content: I was your sister's prisoner once. She hit me on the head with a rock if I remember correctly.

author: edmure
content: Yeah. She should have killed you.

author: jaime lannister
content: Perhaps, but she didn't. Catelyn Stark hated me just like you hate me. But I didn't hate her. I admired her. Far more than her husband or her son.

author: edmure
content: Do you think I care whom you admire and whom you don't?

author: jaime lannister
content: No, I don't, but I'm telling you anyway because you're my prisoner. You don't have a choice. The love she had for her children, I was a little awed by it. Reminded me of my sister.

author: edmure
content: Oh. Oh, I see. You're a madman.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not here to trade insults. Your sister was a strong- -

author: edmure
content: Don't talk about Cat!

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll talk about whomever I want.

author: jaime lannister
content: She loved her children. I suppose all mothers do, but Catelyn and Cersei, there's a fierceness you don't often see.

author: jaime lannister
content: They'd do anything to protect their babies.

author: jaime lannister
content: Start a war. Burn cities to ash. Free their worst enemies. The things we do for love.

author: edmure
content: You didn't come here to talk about our sisters.

author: jaime lannister
content: That's exactly why I came here. I love Cersei. You can laugh at that if you want. You can sneer. It doesn't matter. She needs me. And to get back to her, I have to take Riverrun. I'll send for your baby boy.

author: jaime lannister
content: And I'll launch him into Riverrun with a catapult. Because you don't matter to me, Lord Edmure. Your son doesn't matter to me. The people in the castle don't matter to me. Only Cersei. And if I have to slaughter every Tully who ever lived to get back to her, that's what I'll do.

author: guard captain
content: Who goes there?

author: edmure
content: Edmure Tully, son of Hoster Tully, and the rightful Lord of Riverrun. I demand entry.

author: brynden
content: Don't let him in.

author: guard captain
content: He's the Lord of Riverrun. I have to obey his commands.

author: brynden
content: He's been their captive ever since they murdered his king at the Red Wedding. Why do you think the people who murdered his king at the Red Wedding would decide to let him come home? Because it's a trap, you idiot. Don't let him in.

author: guard captain
content: He's my lord, my lord. I've sworn to serve the Lord of Riverrun and obey his commands.

author: brynden
content: You're not obeying Edmure's commands. You're obeying the fucking Kinglsayer's commands.

author: edmure
content: I demand entry.

author: guard captain
content: My lord has given an order.

author: brynden
content: WIth a knife to his throat. That is not a valid order.

author: guard captain
content: Lower the drawbridge and open the gate for Lord Ed- -

author: brynden
content: I'll have your head before I surrender Riverrun.

author: guard captain
content: You are not lord of this castle, my lord.

author: guard captain
content: Lower the drawbridge!

author: guard
content: Aye, ser!

author: black walder
content: If you're wrong, we're just surrendered our most valuable prisoner.

author: guard captain
content: Welcome home, my lord.

author: edmure
content: Command all the forces within the castle to lay down their arms. Open the gates.

author: guard captain
content: My lord- -

author: edmure
content: Your lord has given a command.

author: edmure
content: Find the Blackfish. Put him in irons and hand him over to the Freys.

author: guard captain
content: Find him.

author: brynden
content: Go on.

author: brienne
content: Come with us.

author: brynden
content: I've run before from the Red Wedding. I'm not running again. This is my family home.

author: brienne
content: Your family is in the North. Come with us. Don't die for pride when you can fight for your blood.

author: brynden
content: You'll serve Sansa far better than I ever could.

author: brynden
content: Go on, now.

author: brynden
content: I haven't had a proper sword fight in years. I expect I'll make a damn fool of myself.

author: guard
content: We found the Blackfish, my lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: Good. Bring him to me.

author: guard
content: He died fighting, my lord.
