author: tyrion lannister
content: I was wrong. I admit it.

author: missandei
content: That changes nothing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Unsullied could mount a defense off the beachhead. If the slavers' forces- -

author: grey worm
content: No more talking from you. Your talking gave us this.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And I have acknowledged that. I'm trying- -

author: grey worm
content: You're trying to tell me what the army should do. You do not know what the army should do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: All right, what should the army do?

author: grey worm
content: We'll not go to the beach. If we go to the beach, the Masters will take the pyramid. The pyramid is the only place in the city we can defend. We stay here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And then?

author: grey worm
content: We wait for them to come to us. Then we fight them.

author: beric
content: Clegane.

author: thoros
content: What the fuck you doing here?

author: sandor
content: Chasing them. You?

author: thoros
content: Hanging them.

author: sandor
content: Any particular reason?

author: beric
content: They're our men. Or they were. They attacked a nearby sept and murdered the villagers. Why do you want them?

author: sandor
content: Same reason. I was helping build it. They killed a friend of mine.

author: thoros
content: You've got friends?

author: sandor
content: Not anymore. They're mine.

author: beric
content: It's the Brotherhoodo s good name they've dragged through the dirt.

author: sandor
content: Fuck your name. They're mine. I killed you once before, Dondarrion. Happy to do it again.

author: sandor
content: Drop that arrow, you bloody girl.

author: sandor
content: Tougher girls than you have tried to kill me.

author: beric
content: You can have one of them.

author: sandor
content: Two.

author: thoros
content: No, no, no.

author: thoros
content: We're not butchers. We hang them.

author: sandor
content: hanging? All over in an instant. Where's the punishment in that?

author: thoros
content: They die.

author: sandor
content: We all bloody die.

author: sandor
content: Except this one here. I'll only gut one of them.

author: beric
content: No.

author: sandor
content: I'll chop off one hand.

author: beric
content: We gave you two of the three out of respect for your loss. That's generous.

author: sandor
content: Bunch of nancies.

author: sandor
content: There was a time I would have killed all seven of you just to gut these three.

author: thoros
content: You're getting old, Clegane.

author: sandor
content: He's not.

author: lem
content: Please don't. I'll give you anything.

author: sandor
content: Got anything to eat?

author: thoros
content: Enjoying yourself?

author: sandor
content: I prefer chicken.

author: beric
content: You ought to join us. We could use you.

author: sandor
content: I tried joining. Didn't work out for me.

author: thoros
content: Clegane, we're here for a reason. The Lord of Light is keeping Beric alive for a reason. He gave a failed, drunk priest the power to bring him back for a reason. We are part of something larger than ourselves.

author: sandor
content: Lots of horrible shit in this world gets done for something larger than ourselves.

author: beric
content: Cold winds are rising in the North.

author: sandor
content: And you're going to go stop them?

author: beric
content: We need good men to help us.

author: sandor
content: Last time you saw me, you wanted to execute me.

author: beric
content: True enough. But the Lord of Light gave you the power to defeat me. Why?

author: sandor
content: I beat you because I'm better than you, Beric. I was better than you before you started yammering on about the Lord and I'm better than you now.

author: beric
content: Aye, you're probably right. You're a fighter. You were born a fighter. You walked away from the fight. How did that go? Good and bad, young and old, the things we're fighting will destroy them all alike. You can still help a lot more than you've harmed Clegane, it's not too late for you.

author: arya stark
content: Lady Crane?

author: waif
content: If you'd have done your job, she would have died painlessly.

author: waif
content: Instead…

author: waif
content: The Many-Faced God was promised a name. He must always receive what is his. You can't change that. I can't change that. No one can. And now he's been promised another name.

author: waif
content: It will all be over soon. On your knees or on your feet?

author: waif
content: Haven't we been through this already? That won't help you.

author: arya stark
content: You told her to kill me.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Yes. But here you are. And there she is.

author: jaqen hghar
content: Finally a girl is no one.

author: arya stark
content: A girl is Arya Stark of Winterfell and I'm going home.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Despite appearances, I think you'll find the city's on the rise.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Perhaps we should take shelter.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The city is on the rise?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Meereen is strong. Commerce has returned to the markets. The people are behind you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, not all the people, of course. No ruler that ever lived had the support of all the people. But the rebirth of Meereen is the cause of this violence. The Masters cannot let Meereen succeed. Because if Meereen succeeds, a city without slavery, a city without Masters…

author: tyrion lannister
content: it proves that no one needs a Master.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Good. Shall we begin?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Do we have a plan?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will crucify the Masters. I will set their fleets afire, kill every last one of their soldiers, and return their cities to the dirt. That is my plan.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You don't approve?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You once told me you knew what your father was. Did you know his plans for King's Landing when the Lannister armies were at his gates?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Probably not. Well, he told my brother and Jaime told me. He had caches of wildfire hidden under the Red Keep, the Guildhalls, the Sept of Baelor, all the major thoroughfares. He would have burned every one of his citizens. The loyal ones and the trators. Every man, woman, and child. That's why Jaime killed him.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This is entirely different.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're talking about destroying cities. It's not entirely different. I'd like to suggest an alternate approach.

author: razdal
content: Once before, I offered you peace. If you had not been so arrogant, you could have returned to your homeland with a fleet of ships. Instead, you will flee Slaver's Bay on foot like the beggar queen you are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We are here to discuss terms of surrender, not to trade insults.

author: yezzan
content: The terms are simple. You and your foreign friends will abandon the Great Pyramid and the city of Meereen. The Unsullied you stole from Kraznys mo Nakloz will remain to be sold again to the highest bidder. The translator you stole from Kraznys mo Nakloz will remain to be sold again to the highest bidder. The dragons beneath the Great Pyramid will be slaughtered.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We obviously didn't communicate clearly. We're here to discuss your surrender, not mine.

author: razdal
content: I imagine it's difficult adjust to the new reality. Your reign is over.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My reign has just begun.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dracarys.

author: grey worm
content: You men have a choice

author: grey worm
content: fight and die for the masters who would never fight and die for you, or go home to your families.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Thank you for the armada. Our queen does love ships. Now, last time we spoke, we made a pact. You violated that pact. You declared war upon us. Though our queen does have a forgiving nature, this cannot be forgiven.

author: missandei
content: Our queen insists that one of you must die as punishment for your crimes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It always seems a bit abstract, doesn't it, other people dying?

author: razdal
content: Him. He should die.

author: belicho
content: Yes, him.

author: razdal
content: He's not one of us. He's an outsider, a lowborn. He does not speak for us.

author: yezzan
content: Please.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Tell your people what happened here. Tell them you live by the grace of Her Majesty. When they come forward with notions of retribution or ideas about returning the slave cities to their former glory, remind the what happened when Daenerys Stormborn and her dragons came to Meereen.

author: jon snow
content: You don't have to be here.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes, I do.

author: ramsay bolton
content: My beloved wife. I've missed you terribly.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Thank you for returning Lady Bolton safely. Now, dismount and kneel before me, surrender your army and proclaim me the true Lord of Winterfell and Warden of the North. I will pardon you for deserting the Night's Watch. I will pardon these treasonous lords for betraying my house. Come, bastard, you don't have the men, you don't have the horses, and you don't have Winterfell. Why lead those pour souls into slaughter? There's no need for a battle. Get off your hose and kneel. I'm a man of mercy.

author: jon snow
content: You're right. There's no need for a battle. Thousands of men don't need to die. Only one of us. Let's end this the old way. You against me.

author: ramsay bolton
content: I keep hearing stories about you, bastard. The way people in the North talk about you, you're the greatest swordsman who ever walked. Maybe you are that good. Maybe not. I don't know if I'd beat you. But I know that my army will beat yours. I have 6,000 men. You have, what, half that? Not even?

author: jon snow
content: Aye, you have the numbers. Will your men want to fight for you when they hear you wouldn't fight for them?

author: ramsay bolton
content: He's good. Very good. Tell me, will you let your little brother die because you're too proud to surrender?

author: sansa stark
content: How do we know you have him?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Now, if you want to save —

author: sansa stark
content: You're going to die tomorrow, Lord Bolton. Sleep well.

author: ramsay bolton
content: She's a fine woman, your sister. I look forward to having her back in my bed. And you're all fine-looking men. My dogs are desperate to meet you. I haven't fed them for seven days. They're ravenous. I wonder which parts they'll try first. Your eyes? Your balls? We'll find out soon enough. In the morning, then, bastard.

author: jon snow
content: If he was smart, he'd stay inside the walls of Winterfell and wait us out.

author: davos
content: That's not his way. He knows the North is watching. If the other houses sense weakness on his part, they'll stop fearing him. He can't have that. Fear is his power.

author: jon snow
content: It's his weakness, too. His mean don't want to fight for him. They're forced to fight for him. If they feel the tide turning...

author: tormund
content: It's not his men that worry me. It's his horses. I know what mounted knights can do to us.

author: tormund
content: You and Stannis cut through us like piss through snow.

author: jon snow
content: We're digging trenches all along our flanks. They won't be able to hit us the way that Stannis hit you, in a double envelopment.

author: tormund
content: stares blankly at JON SNOW.

author: jon snow
content: A pincer move.

author: jon snow
content: They won't be able to hit us from the sides.

author: tormund
content: Good.

author: davos
content: It's crucial that we let them charge at us. They've got the numbers, we need the patience. If we let him buckle our center, he'll pursue. Then we'll have him surrounded on three sides.

author: tormund
content: Did you really think that cunt would fight you man to man?

author: jon snow
content: No. But I wanted to make him angry. I want him coming at us full tilt.

author: davos
content: We should all get some sleep.

author: tormund
content: Rest, Jon Snow. We need you sharp tomorrow.

author: sansa stark
content: So you've met the enemy, drawn up your battle plans.

author: jon snow
content: Aye, for what they're worth.

author: sansa stark
content: You've known him for the space of a single conversation, you and your trusted advisors, and you sit around and make your plans on how to defeat a man you don't know. I lived with him. I know the way his mind works. I know how he likes to hurt people. Did it ever once occur to you that I might have some insight?

author: jon snow
content: You're right.

author: sansa stark
content: You think he's going to fall into your trap. He won't He's the one who lays traps.

author: jon snow
content: He's overconfident.

author: sansa stark
content: He plays with people. He's far better at it than you. He's been doing it all his life.

author: jon snow
content: Aye, and what have I been doing all my life? Playing with broomsticks? I fought beyond the Wall against worse than Ramsay Bolton. I've defended the Wall from worse than Ramsay Bolton.

author: sansa stark
content: You don't know him.

author: jon snow
content: All right, tell me. What should we do? How do we get Rickon back?

author: sansa stark
content: We'll never get him back. Rickon is Ned Starks trueborn son, which makes him a greater threat to Ramsay than you, a bastard, or me, a girl. As long as he lives, Ramsay's claim to Winterfell will be contested, which means he won't live long.

author: jon snow
content: We can't give up on our brother.

author: sansa stark
content: Listen to me, please. He wants you to make a mistake.

author: jon snow
content: Of course he does. What should I do differently?

author: sansa stark
content: I don't know! I don't know anything about battles! Just don't do what he wants you to do.

author: jon snow
content: Aye, that's good advice.

author: sansa stark
content: You think that's obvious?

author: jon snow
content: Well, it is a bit obvious.

author: sansa stark
content: If you had asked for my advice earlier, I would have told you not to attack Winterfell until we have a larger force, or is that obvious, too?

author: jon snow
content: When will we have a larger force?! We've pleaded with every house that'll have us! The Blackfish can't help us! We're lucky to have this many men!

author: sansa stark
content: It's not enough!

author: jon snow
content: Now, it's not enough! It's what we have! Battles have been won against greater odds.

author: sansa stark
content: If Ramsay wins, I'm not going back there alive. Do you understand me?

author: jon snow
content: SNOW I won't ever let him touch you again. I'll protect you, I promise.

author: sansa stark
content: No one can protect me. No one can protect anyone.

author: davos
content: You think there's hope?

author: tormund
content: I've never seen these Bolton fuckers fight. And they've never seen the free folk fight, so, yes, there's hope. You want to avenge your king, don't you?

author: davos
content: It wasn't the Boltons defeated Stannis. It was Stannis himself. I loved the man. He lifted me up and made me something. But he had demons in his skull whispering foul things.

author: tormund
content: You saw these demons?

author: davos
content: What?

author: davos
content: No, it's a manner of speaking. Not actual demons.

author: tormund
content: Oh. Well, you loved that cunt Stannis and I loved the man he burned. Mance didn't have demons in his skull. He didn't torch people or listen to some red witch. I believed in him. I thought he was the man to lead us through the Long Night. But I was wrong just like you.

author: davos
content: Maybe that was our mistake, believing in kings.

author: tormund
content: Jon Snow's not a king.

author: davos
content: No, he's not.

author: tormund
content: I need a good drink to help me sleep the night before a fight. You want some? I have a jug of sour goat's milk stronger than any of that grape water you southern twats like sucking on.

author: davos
content: No, thanks. It does sound delicious, but I better keep a clear head. I can never sleep the night before a battle.

author: tormund
content: So what do you do all night?

author: davos
content: I walk. Think and walk. Think and walk until I'm far enough away from camp that no one can hear me shitting my guts out.

author: tormund
content: Happy shitting.

author: jon snow
content: My lady. You weren't at the war council.

author: melisandre
content: I'm not a soldier.

author: jon snow
content: Any advice?

author: melisandre
content: Don't lose.

author: jon snow
content: If I do, if I fall, don't bring me back.

author: melisandre
content: I'll have to try.

author: jon snow
content: I'm ordering you not to bring me back.

author: melisandre
content: I am not your servant, Jon Snow.

author: jon snow
content: You're in my camp. I'm the commander.

author: melisandre
content: I serve the Lord of Light. I do what he commands.

author: jon snow
content: How do you know what he commands?

author: melisandre
content: I interpret his signs as well as I can. If the Lord didn't want me to bring you back, how did I bring you back? I have no power. Only what he gives me and he gave me you.

author: jon snow
content: Why?

author: melisandre
content: I don't know. Maybe you're only needed for this small part of his plan and nothing else. Maybe he brought you here to die again.

author: jon snow
content: What kind of god would do something like that?

author: melisandre
content: The one we've got.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Last time we saw each other was at Winterfell, yes? You were making jokes about my height, I seem to recall. Everyone who makes a joke about a dwarf's height thinks he's the only person ever to make a joke about a dwarf's height. “The height of nobility,” “a man of your stature,” “someone to look up to.” You're all making the same five or six jokes.

author: theon greyjoy
content: It was a long time ago.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It was. And how have things been going for you since then? Not so well, I gather. Can't imagine you would have murdered the Stark boys if things had been going well.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I didn't murder the Stark boys. But I did things that were just as bad or worse.

author: yara greyjoy
content: And he paid for them.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Doesn't seem like it. He's still alive. It was complicated for you, I'm sure, growing up at Winterfell. Never quite knowing who you were. But then, we all live complicated lives, don't we?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You've brought us 100 ships from the Iron Fleet with men to sail them. In return, I expect you want me to support your claim to the throne of the Iron Islands?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not my claim. Hers.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what's wrong with you?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I'm not fit to rule.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We can agree upon that at least.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Has the Iron Islands ever had a queen before?

author: yara greyjoy
content: No more than Westeros.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Our Uncle Euron returned home after a long absence. He murdered our father and took the Salt Throne from yara. He would have murdered us if we had stayed.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Lord Tyrion tells me your father was a terrible king.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You and I have that in common.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We do. And both murdered by a usurper as well.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will their ships be enough?

author: tyrion lannister
content: With the former Masters' fleet, possibly. Barely. There are more than 100 ships in the Iron Fleet.

author: theon greyjoy
content: There are and Euron is building more. He's going to offer them to you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So why shouldn't I wait for him?

author: theon greyjoy
content: The Iron Fleet isn't all he's bringing. He also wants to give you --

author: yara greyjoy
content: His big cock, I think he said. Euron's offer is also an offer of marriage, you see. You won't get one without the other.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And I imagine your offer is free of any marriage demands?

author: yara greyjoy
content: I never demand, but I'm up for anything, really.

author: theon greyjoy
content: He murdered our father and would have murdered us. He'll murder you as soon as you have what he wants.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Seven Kingdoms.

author: theon greyjoy
content: All of them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you don't want the Seven Kingdoms?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Your ancestors defeated ours and took the Iron Islands. We ask you to give them back.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And that's all?

author: yara greyjoy
content: We'd like you to help us murder an uncle or two who don't think a woman's fit to rule.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Reasonable.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What if everyone starts demanding their independence?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: She's not demanding, she's asking. The others are free to ask as well. Our father were evil men, all of us here. They left the world worse than they found it. We're not going to do that. We're going to leave the world better than we found it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will support my claim as queen of the Seven Kingdoms and respect the integrity of the Seven Kingdoms. No more reaving, roving, raiding, or raping.

author: yara greyjoy
content: That's our way of life.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No more.

author: yara greyjoy
content: No more.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Do you like games, little man? Let's play a game. Run to your brother. The sooner you make it to him, the sooner you get to see him. That's it. That's the game. Easy. Ready? Go.

author: ramsay bolton
content: No, you have to run, remember? Those are the rules.

author: tormund
content: Don't.

author: davos
content: Prepare to charge! Prepare to charge!

author: davos
content: Go! Go! Follow your commander!

author: tormund
content: Run and fight!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Now.

author: karstark
content: Cavalry, charge!

author: davos
content: We'll just kill our own men. Stand down.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Loose!

author: jon snow
content: Get word --

author: davos
content: We may as well be taking shits back here.

author: davos
content: Follow!

author: ramsay bolton
content: It's time, go.

author: smalljon
content: Who owns the North?

author: all
content: We do!

author: smalljon
content: Show me!

author: tormund
content: Hey!

author: man
content: Infantry, advance!

author: davos
content: With me, lads! Break their line!

author: man
content: Tormund!

author: man
content: Get him back!

author: tormund
content: Fuck this, come on!

author: ramsay bolton
content: Their army's gone.

author: man
content: Our army's gone.

author: ramsay bolton
content: We have Winterfell. They don't have the men for a siege. All we have to do is wait.

author: ramsay bolton
content: You suggested one on one combat, didn't you?

author: ramsay bolton
content: I've reconsidered. I think that sounds like a wonderful idea.

author: jon snow
content: We're going to bury my brother in the crypt next to my father.

author: sansa stark
content: Jon.

author: sansa stark
content: Where is he?

author: ramsay bolton
content: Ah. Sansa. Hello, Sansa. Is this where I'll be staying now? No. Our time together is about to come to an end. That's all right. You can't kill me. I'm part of you now.

author: sansa stark
content: Your words will disappear. Your house will disappear. Your name will disappear. All memory of you will disappear.

author: ramsay bolton
content: My hounds will never harm me.

author: sansa stark
content: You haven't fed them in seven days. You said it yourself.

author: ramsay bolton
content: They're loyal beasts.

author: sansa stark
content: They were. Now they're starving.

author: ramsay bolton
content: Sit. Down! Down! Down! Down! Down!

author: attendant
content: Your Grace. The trial will be getting underway soon.

author: mistress
content: You got my money?

author: pycelle
content: Later. Go away.

author: girl
content: Grand Maester.

author: sparrow
content: Ser Loras Tyrell. Are you prepared to stand trial and profess your guilt or innocence before the Seven?

author: loras
content: There'll be no need for a trial. I confess before the Seven and freely admit to my crimes.

author: sparrow
content: To which crimes will you be confessing?

author: loras
content: All of them. I lay with other men including the traitor Renly Baratheon.

author: loras
content: I perjured myself before the gods. I am guilty of depravity… dishonesty, profligacy, and arrogance. I see that now. I humble myself before the Seven and accept whatever punishment the gods deem just.

author: sparrow
content: The gods' judgment is fierce, but also fair. The Warrior punishes those who believe themselves beyond the reach of justice. But the Mother shows her mercy to those who kneel before her.

author: loras
content: I take full responsibility for my many sins and unburden myself of my desires. My only remaining wish is to devote my life to the Seven. May I be a living example of their grace for others to witness.

author: sparrow
content: You understand fully what this means?

author: loras
content: I do. I will abandon the Tyrell name and all that goes with it. I will renounce my lordship and my claims on Highgarden. I will never marry and I will never father children.

author: sparrow
content: Brother Loras…

author: sparrow
content: I ask you to dedicate your life to the seven gods.

author: sparrow
content: Will you fight to defend your faith against heretics and apostates?

author: loras
content: I will.

author: mace
content: No, I can't let them…

author: margaery tyrell
content: Faith is the way, Father.

author: tommen lannister
content: All right. I'm ready.

author: tommen lannister
content: I have to go, I'm-- I'm late for the trial.

author: margaery tyrell
content: You mutilated him. You gave me your word.

author: sparrow
content: I've kept my word. Once the queen mother's trial is concluded, Brother Loras is free to leave.

author: margaery tyrell
content: And where is the queen mother?

author: lancel
content: Her litter never left the Red Keep.

author: sparrow
content: It appears the queen mother doesn't wish to attend her own trial.

author: sparrow
content: Go to the Red Keep and show her the way.

author: lancel
content: Get the others.

author: pycelle
content: Where's the king?

author: qyburn
content: Elsewhere, I'm afraid.

author: pycelle
content: What's the meaning of this? I was told that-- I have more important things to do with my time than waste them in the presence--

author: qyburn
content: Please, Grand Maester. I bear you no ill will. Please forgive me if you can.

author: qyburn
content: This pains me, my lord. Whatever your faults, you do not deserve to die alone in such a cold, dark place. But sometimes before we can usher in the new, the old must be put to rest.

author: lancel
content: The longer you wait, the worse it'll be for you.

author: lancel
content: What are you doing?

author: margaery tyrell
content: There's something wrong.

author: sparrow
content: You have nothing to fear, Your Grace. The trial will begin shortly.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Cersei is not here. Tommen is not here. Why do you think they are not here?

author: sparrow
content: If the accused is not here, she will be tried regardless. We cannot escape the justice of the gods--

author: margaery tyrell
content: Forget about the bloody gods and listen to what I'm telling you. Cersei understands the consequences of her absence and she is absent anyway, which means she does not intend to suffer those consequences. The trial can wait. We all need to leave.

author: margaery tyrell
content: We all need to leave now!

author: margaery tyrell
content: Loras. Stay with me.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Let me through. Let me through. Get out of my way.

author: margaery tyrell
content: Let us through!

author: cersei lannister
content: Confess. Confess.

author: septa unella
content: No.

author: cersei lannister
content: Confess.

author: cersei lannister
content: Confess. It felt good. Beating me, starving me, frightening me, humiliating me. You didn't do it because you cared about my atonement. You did it because it felt good. I understand. I do things because they feel good. I drink because it feels good. I killed my husband because it felt good to be rid of him. I fuck my brother because it feels good to feel him inside me. I lie about fucking my brother… because it feels good to keep our son safe from hateful hypocrites. I killed your High Sparrow… and all his little sparrows… all his septons, all his septas, all his filthy soldiers, because it felt good to watch them burn. It felt good to imagine their shock and their pain. No thought has ever given me greater joy. Even confessing feels good under the right circumstances.

author: cersei lannister
content: You've always been quiet.

author: cersei lannister
content: I said my face would be the last thing you saw before you died. Do you remember?

author: septa unella
content: Good. I'm glad to see your face. I'm ready to meet the gods.

author: cersei lannister
content: What? Now? Today? You're not going to die today. You're not going to die for quite a while. Ser Gregor.

author: cersei lannister
content: This is Ser Gregor Clegane. He's quiet, too.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your gods have forsaken you. This is your god now.

author: cersei lannister
content: Shame.

author: attendant
content: I'm very sorry, Your Grace. Very sorry.

author: walder
content: For House Lannister!

author: men
content: Hear me roar!

author: walder
content: For House Frey!

author: men
content: We stand together!

author: walder
content: May we stand together through the centuries, good friends to the last.

author: walder
content: And when we drive our swords through our enemies' hearts, may we speak the words of our alliance, “The Freys and the Lannisters send their regards.”

author: bronn
content: You don't even have to do anything, do you?

author: bronn
content: You just sit there, a rich slab of beef, and all the birds come pecking.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're welcome to her.

author: bronn
content: She doesn't want me. She wants your golden fingers up her twat.

author: jaime lannister
content: Those two have their eyes on you.

author: bronn
content: They have their eyes on you, cunt.

author: jaime lannister
content: Not my type.

author: bronn
content: Not blonde enough?

author: jaime lannister
content: Ladies, have you met Ser Bronn of the Blackwater, hero of the Battle of Blackwater Bay.

author: jaime lannister
content: There you go.

author: bronn
content: Maybe I'm not in the mood.

author: bronn
content: Fuck it.

author: bronn
content: No need to call me ser just because I'm an anointed knight.

author: walder
content: This came together rather well. Your father would be pleased.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm sure he would be.

author: walder
content: Edmure is back in a cell. Can't go killing my son by law. It wouldn't be right. Give the family a bad name.

author: walder
content: So the famous Blackfish killed by footsoldiers, eh? Legendary warrior, everyone said.

author: jaime lannister
content: Have you done much fighting yourself, Lord Frey?

author: walder
content: I'm a bit old for all that.

author: jaime lannister
content: No, but back in your day.

author: walder
content: The purpose of fighting is defeating your enemies, isn't it?

author: walder
content: I've defeated mine. Riverrun belonged to House Tully for a thousand years. Now it's mine. What do you call that? Victory.

author: jaime lannister
content: Yes, you're a great conqueror.

author: walder
content: Go on, mock me, boy. You think I mind? The Tullys mocked me for years. The Starks mocked me. Where are they now? You talk about war as if you're an expert but the one battle I remember you fighting, you were captured by Robb Stark, the Young Wolf. But it doesn't matter. Here we are now, two kingslayers. We know what it's like to have them grovel to our faces and snigger behind our backs. We don't mind, do we? Fear is a marvelous thing.

author: jaime lannister
content: They don't fear the Freys, though. They fear the Lannisters. We gave you the Riverlands to hold the Riverlands. If we have to ride north and take them back for you every time you lose them, why do we need you?

author: cersei lannister
content: Show me.

author: qyburn
content: Your Grace, there's no need--

author: qyburn
content: What are your thoughts concerning the king's funeral? As the Sept of Baelor is no longer an option, perhaps a ceremony in the throne room?

author: cersei lannister
content: He should be with his grandfather, his brother, his sister. Burn him and bury his ashes where the sept once stood.

author: sam
content: Hello.

author: sam
content: From Lord Commander Snow at Castle Black.

author: sam
content: I'm-- I'm to be the new maester.

author: maester
content: Oh.

author: maester
content: According to our records, Jeor Mormont is Lord Commander.

author: sam
content: He died.

author: maester
content: We received no report from the maester at Castle Black.

author: sam
content: Maester Aemon became quite ill shortly after the election. He's since passed away. Which is why I'm here.

author: maester
content: This is irregular.

author: sam
content: Yes, well, I suppose that life is irregular.

author: maester
content: The archmaester will discuss these irregularities with you. In the meantime, you are permitted to use the library. Follow me.

author: maester
content: No women or children!

author: jon snow
content: When we had feasts, our family would sit up here… and I'd sit down there.

author: melisandre
content: Could have been worse, Jon Snow. You had a family. You had feasts.

author: jon snow
content: Aye, you're right. I was luckier than most.

author: jon snow
content: What is that?

author: davos
content: Tell him. Tell him who it belonged to.

author: melisandre
content: The Princess Shireen.

author: davos
content: Tell him what you did to her. Tell him!

author: melisandre
content: We burned her at the stake.

author: davos
content: Why?

author: melisandre
content: The army was trapped. The horses were dying. It was the only way.

author: davos
content: You burned a little girl alive!

author: melisandre
content: I only do what my Lord commands!

author: davos
content: If he commands you to burn children, your Lord is evil!

author: melisandre
content: We are standing here because of him. Jon Snow is alive because the Lord willed it.

author: davos
content: I loved that girl like she was my own. She was good. She was kind. And you killed her!

author: melisandre
content: So did her father. So did her mother. Her own blood knew it was the only way.

author: davos
content: The only way for what? They all died anyway! You told everyone Stannis was the one. You had him believing it, all of them fooled. And you lied.

author: melisandre
content: I didn't lie. I was wrong.

author: davos
content: Aye, you were wrong. How many died because you were wrong?

author: davos
content: I ask your leave to execute this woman for murder. She admits to the crime.

author: jon snow
content: Do you have anything to say for yourself?

author: melisandre
content: I've been ready to die for many years. If the Lord was done with me, so be it, but he's not. You've seen the Night King, Jon Snow. You know the great war is still to come. You know the army of the dead will be upon us soon. And you know I can help you win that war.

author: jon snow
content: Ride south today. If you return to the North, I'll have you hanged as a murderer.

author: davos
content: If you ever come back this way, I will execute you myself.

author: jon snow
content: I'm having the lordo s chamber prepared for you.

author: sansa stark
content: Mother and Father's room? You should take it.

author: jon snow
content: I'm not a Stark.

author: sansa stark
content: You are to me.

author: jon snow
content: You're the Lady of Winterfell. You deserve it. We're standing here because of you. The battle was lost until the Knights of the Vale rode in. They came because of you. You told me Lord Baelish sold you to the Boltons.

author: sansa stark
content: He did.

author: jon snow
content: And you trust him?

author: sansa stark
content: Only a fool would trust Littlefinger. I should have told you about him, about the Knights of the Vale. I'm sorry.

author: jon snow
content: We need to trust each other. We can't fight a war amongst ourselves. We have so many enemies now.

author: sansa stark
content: Jon.

author: sansa stark
content: A raven came from the Citadel. A white raven. Winter is here.

author: jon snow
content: Well, Father always promised, didn't he?

author: olenna tyrell
content: The last time a Tyrell came to Dorne, he was assassinated. 100 red scorpions, was it?

author: ellaria
content: You have nothing to fear from us, Lady Olenna.

author: olenna tyrell
content: You murder your own prince, but you expect me to trust you?

author: obara
content: We invited you to Dorne because we needed your help. You came to Dorne because you needed our help?

author: olenna tyrell
content: What is your name again? Barbaro?

author: obara
content: Obara.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Obara. You look like an angry little boy. Don't presume to tell me what I need.

author: nymeria
content: Forgive my sister. What she lacks in diplomacy, she makes--

author: olenna tyrell
content: Do shut up, dear.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Anything from you?

author: olenna tyrell
content: No? Good. Let the grown women speak.

author: ellaria
content: The Lannisters have declared war on House Tyrell. They have declared war on Dorne. We must be allies now if we wish to survive.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Cersei stole the future from me. She killed my son. She killed my grandson. She killed my granddaughter. Survival is not what I'm after now.

author: ellaria
content: You're absolutely right. I chose the wrong words. It is not survival I offer. It is your heart's desire.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And what is my heart's desire?

author: ellaria
content: Vengeance. Justice.

author: varys
content: Fire and blood.

author: daario
content: Your ships are nearly ready. I saw them painting the sails.

author: daario
content: I'm curious to see how the Dothraki do on the poison water.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You're not coming with us.

author: daario
content: New strategy? You want the Second Sons to attack from the west coast? If we take Casterly Rock, the Lannisters will have nowhere to run when you hit King's Landing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You're not going to Westeros. You're staying here with the Second Sons. There's finally peace in Meereen. You will keep the peace while the people choose their own leaders.

author: daario
content: Fuck Meereen. Fuck the people. I'm here for you, not them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You promised me. “My sword is yours. My life is yours.” This is what I command. If I'm going to rule in Westeros, I'll need to make alliances. The best way to make alliances is with marriage.

author: daario
content: Who are you marrying this time?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't know. Maybe no one.

author: daario
content: But you need to lure all the noble houses to the table? Are you a queen or fish bait?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I can't bring a lover to Westeros.

author: daario
content: A king wouldn't think twice about it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So that's what you want? To be my mistress?

author: daario
content: I'm not proud. I don't care what perfumed aristocrat sits beside you in the throne room. I don't want a crown. I want you.

author: daario
content: I love you. And I make you happy. You know I do. Bring me with you. Let me fight for you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I can't.

author: daario
content: The dwarf told you to do this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No one tells me to do anything.

author: daario
content: Clever fellow. Can't argue with his logic. I'm no use to you over there.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't get angry.

author: daario
content: I'm not angry. I'm full of self-pity. Who comes after you? Who can ever follow Daenerys Stormborn, the Mother of Dragons?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: A great number of women, I imagine. Specific orders will be left for you regarding the welfare of Meereen and the Bay of Dragons.

author: daario
content: Bay of Dragons?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We can't call it Slaver's Bay anymore, can we?

author: daario
content: You'll get that throne you want so badly, I'm sure of it. I hope it brings you happiness.

author: daario
content: I pity the lord of Westeros. They have no idea what's coming for them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Farewell, Daario Naharis.

author: tyrion lannister
content: How did he take it?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No tears.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know it was hard for you. You turned away a man who truly loves you because he would have been a liability in the Seven Kingdoms. That's the kind of self-sacrifice that makes for a good ruler, if it's any consolation.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's not.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, I suppose not. I'm terrible at consoling.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Yes, you really are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: All right, how about the fact that this is actually happening? You have your armies, you have your ships, you have your dragons. Everything you've ever wanted since you were old enough to want anything. It's all yours for the taking. Are you afraid?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. You're in the great game now. And the great game's terrifying. The only people who aren't afraid of failure are madmen like your father.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do you know what frightens me? I said farewell to a man who loves me. A man I thought I cared for. And I felt nothing. Just impatient to get on with it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He wasn't the first to love you and he won't be the last.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, you have completely failed to console me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: For what it's worth, I've been a cynic for as long as I can remember. Everyone's always asking me to believe in things-- family, gods, kings, myself. It was often tempting until I saw where belief got people. So I said no, thank you to belief. And yet here I am.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I believe in you. It's embarrassing, really. I'd swear you my sword, but I don't actually own a sword.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's your counsel I need.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's yours. Now and always.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Good. I, um… I had something made for you. I'm not sure if it's right.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Tyrion Lannister, I name you Hand of the Queen.

author: walder
content: You're not one of mine, are you?

author: handmaiden
content: No, my lord.

author: walder
content: Didn't think so. Too pretty.

author: walder
content: Where are my damn moron sons? Black Walder and Lothar promised to be here by midday.

author: handmaiden
content: They're here, my lord.

author: walder
content: Well, what are they doing, trimming their cunt hairs? Tell them to come here now.

author: handmaiden
content: But they're already here, my lord.

author: handmaiden
content: Here, my lord.

author: handmaiden
content: They weren't easy to carve. Especially Black Walder.

author: walder
content: What…

author: arya stark
content: My name is Arya Stark. I want you to know that. The last thing you're ever going to see is a Stark smiling down at you as you die.

author: petyr
content: Forgive me, my lady… if you're at prayer.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm done with all that. I came here every day when I was a girl. I prayed to be somewhere else. Back then I only ever thought about what I wanted, never about what I had.

author: sansa stark
content: I was a stupid girl.

author: petyr
content: You were a child.

author: sansa stark
content: What do you want?

author: petyr
content: I thought you knew what I wanted.

author: sansa stark
content: I was wrong.

author: petyr
content: No, you weren't. Every time I'm faced with a decision, I close my eyes and see the same picture. Whenever I consider an action, I ask myself will this action help to make this picture a reality? Pull it out of my mind and into the world? And I only act if the answer is yes. A picture of me on the Iron Throne… and you by my side.

author: sansa stark
content: It's a pretty picture.

author: petyr
content: News of this battle will spread quickly through the Seven Kingdoms. I've declared for House Stark for all to hear.

author: sansa stark
content: You've declared for other houses before, Lord Baelish. It's never stopped you from serving yourself.

author: petyr
content: The past is gone for good. You can sit here mourning its departure or you can prepare for the future. You, my love, are the future of House Stark. Who should the North rally behind? A trueborn daughter of Ned and Catelyn Stark born here at Winterfell or a motherless bastard born in the south?

author: benjen
content: This is where I leave you.

author: meera
content: You're not coming with us?

author: benjen
content: The Wall is not just ice and stone. Ancient spells were carved into its foundations. Strong magic to protect men from what lies beyond. And while it stands, the dead cannot pass. I cannot pass.

author: meera
content: Where will you go?

author: benjen
content: The great war is coming and I still fight for the living. I'll do what I can… as long as I can.

author: bran stark
content: Thank you, Uncle Benjen.

author: benjen
content: I wish you both good fortune.

author: meera
content: Are you sure you're ready for this?

author: bran stark
content: I'm the Three-Eyed Raven now. I have to be ready for this.

author: lyanna
content: Ned?

author: eddard stark
content: Lyanna.

author: lyanna
content: Is that you? Is that really you?

author: lyanna
content: You're not a dream.

author: eddard stark
content: No, I'm not a dream. I'm here. Right here.

author: lyanna
content: I've missed you, big brother.

author: eddard stark
content: I've missed you, too.

author: lyanna
content: I want to be brave.

author: eddard stark
content: Shh. You are.

author: lyanna
content: I'm not.

author: lyanna
content: I don't want to die.

author: eddard stark
content: You're not going to die.

author: eddard stark
content: Get her some water!

author: lyanna
content: No, no water.

author: eddard stark
content: Is there a maester?

author: lyanna
content: Please. Listen to me, Ned.

author: lyanna
content: If Robert finds out, he'll kill him, you know he will. You have to protect him. Promise me, Ned. Promise me.

author: lyanna
content: Promise me, Ned. Promise me.

author: vale knight
content: You can't expect Knights of the Vale to side with wildling invaders.

author: tormund
content: We didn't invade. We were invited.

author: vale knight
content: Not by me.

author: jon snow
content: The free folk, the northerners, and the Knights of the Vale fought bravely, fought together, and we won. My father uses to say we find our true friends on the battlefield.

author: man
content: The Boltons are defeated. The war is over. Winter has come. If the maesters are right, it'll be the coldest one in a thousand years. We should ride home and wait out the coming storms.

author: jon snow
content: The war is not over. And I promise you, friend, the true enemy won't wait out the storm. He brings the storm.

author: lyanna
content: Your son was butchered at the Red Wedding, Lord Manderly. But you refused the call. You swore allegiance to House Stark, Lord Glover, but in their hour of greatest need, you refused the call. And you, Lord Cerwyn, your father was skinned alive by Ramsay Bolton. Still you refuse the call. But House Mormont remembers. The North remembers. We know no king but the King in the North whose name is Stark. I don't care if he's a bastard. Ned Stark's blood runs through his veins. He's my king from this day until his last day.

author: manderly
content: Lady Mormont speaks harshly and truly. My son died for Robb Stark, the Young Wolf. I didn't think we'd find another king in my lifetime. I didn't commit my men to your cause ‘cause I didn't want more Manderlys dying for nothing. But I was wrong. Jon Snow avenged the Red Wedding. He is the White Wolf. The King in the North.

author: glover
content: I did not fight beside you on the field and I will regret that until my dying day. A man can only admit when he was wrong and ask forgiveness.

author: jon snow
content: There's nothing to forgive, my lord.

author: glover
content: There will be more fights to come. House Glover will stand behind House Stark as we have for a thousands years. And I will stand behind Jon Snow… the King in the North!

author: glover
content: The King in the North!

author: all
content: The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North! The King in the North!

author: jaime lannister
content: Come on.

author: qyburn
content: I now proclaim Cersei of the House Lannister First of Her Name, Queen of the Andals and the First Men, Protector of the Seven Kingdoms.

author: qyburn
content: Long may she reign.

author: all
content: Long may she reign.

author: walder frey
content: You're wonder why I brought you all here. After all, we just had a feast. Since when does old Walder give us two feasts in a single fortnight?

author: walder frey
content: Well, it's no good being lord of the Riverlands if you can't celebrate with your family. That's what I say!

author: walder frey
content: I've gathered every Frey who means a damn thing so I can tell you my plans for this great house now that winter has come. But first, a toast! No more of that Dornish horse piss! This is the finest Arbor gold! Proper wine for proper heroes!

author: waldery frey
content: Stand together!

author: all
content: Stand together!

author: walder
content: Not you. I'm not wasting good wine on a damn woman.

author: walder
content: Maybe I'm not the most pleasant man. I'll admit it. But I'm proud of you lot. You're my family, the men who helped me slaughter the Starks at the Red Wedding.

author: walder
content: Yes, yes. Cheer. Brave men, all of you. Butchered a woman pregnant with her babe. Cut the throat of a mother of five. Slaughtered your guests after inviting them into your home. But you didn't slaughter every one of the Starks.

author: walder
content: No, no, that was your mistake. You should have ripped them all out, root and stem.

author: walder
content: Leave one wolf alive and the sheep are never safe.

author: arya stark
content: When people ask you what happened here, tell them the North remembers. Tell them winter came for House Frey.

author: edd
content: You wildlings?

author: meera
content: I'm Meera Reed, daughter of Howland Reed. This is Brandon Stark, son of Ned Stark.

author: edd
content: How do I know that's true?

author: bran stark
content: You were at the Fist of the First Men. You were at Hardhome. You've seen the Army of the Dead. You've seen the Night King. He's coming for us. For all of us.

author: edd
content: Okay, come on. Let's get them inside.

author: jon snow
content: I want every northern maester to scour their records for any mention of dragonglass. Dragonglass kills white walkers. It's more valuable to us now than gold. We need to find it, we need to mine it, we need to make weapons from it. Everyone aged 10 to 60 will drill daily with spears, pikes, bow and arrow.

author: robett
content: It's about time we taught these boys of summer how to fight.

author: jon snow
content: Not just the boys.

author: jon snow
content: We can't defend the North if only half the population is fighting.

author: robett
content: You expect me to put a spear in my granddaughter's hand?

author: lyanna
content: I don't plan on knitting by the fire while men fight for me. I might be small, Lord Glover, and I might be a girl, but I am every bit as much a Northerner as you.

author: robett
content: Indeed you are, my lady. No one has questioned--

author: lyanna
content: And I don't need your permission to defend the North.

author: lyanna
content: We'll begin training every man, woman, boy, and girl on Bear Island.

author: jon snow
content: While we're preparing for attack, we need to shore up our defenses. The only thing standing between us and the Army of the Dead is the Wall and the Wall hasn't been properly manned in centuries. I'm not the king of the Free Folk.

author: jon snow
content: But if we're going to survive this winter together...

author: tormund
content: You want us to man the castles for you?

author: jon snow
content: Last time we saw the Night King was at Hardhome. The closest castle to Hardhome is Eastwatch-by-the-Sea.

author: tormund
content: Then that's where I'll go. Looks like we're the Night's Watch now.

author: jon snow
content: If they breach the wall, the first two castles in their path are Last Hearth and Karhold.

author: yohn
content: The Umbers and the Karstarks betrayed the North. Their castles should be torn down with not a stone left standing.

author: sansa stark
content: The castles committed no crimes. And we need every fortress we have for the war to come. We should give the Last Hearth and Karhold to new families, loyal families who supported us against Ramsay.

author: all
content: Aye!

author: jon snow
content: The Umbers and the Karstarks have fought beside the Starks for centuries. They've kept faith for generation after generation.

author: sansa stark
content: And then they broke faith.

author: jon snow
content: I'm not going to strip these families of their ancestral homes because of the crimes of a few reckless sons.

author: sansa stark
content: So there's no punishment for treason and no reward for loyalty?

author: jon snow
content: The punishment for treason is death. Smalljon Umber died on the field of battle. Harald Karstark died on the field of battle.

author: sansa stark
content: They died fighting for Ramsay. Give the castles to the families of the men who died fighting for you.

author: jon snow
content: When I was Lord Commander of the Night's Watch I executed men who betrayed me. I executed men who refused to follow orders. My father always said, "The man who passes the sentence should swing the sword," and I have tried to live by those words. But I will not punish a son for his father's sins, and I will not take a family home away from a family it has belonged to for centuries. That is my decision, and my decision is final.

author: jon snow
content: Ned Umber.

author: jon snow
content: Alys Karstark.

author: jon snow
content: For centuries, our families fought side by side on the battlefield. I ask you to pledge your loyalty once again to House Stark, to serve as our bannermen and come to our aid whenever called upon.

author: jon snow
content: Stand.

author: jon snow
content: Yesterday's wars don't matter anymore. The North needs to band together, all the living north. Will you stand beside me, Ned and Alys, now and always?

author: ned alys
content: Now and always!

author: jon snow
content: You are my sister, but I am king now.

author: sansa stark
content: Will you start wearing a crown?

author: jon snow
content: When you question my decisions in front of the other lords and ladies, you undermine me.

author: sansa stark
content: So I can't question your decisions anymore?

author: jon snow
content: Of course you can, but--

author: sansa stark
content: Joffrey never let anyone question his authority. You think he was a good king?

author: jon snow
content: Do you think I'm Joffrey?

author: sansa stark
content: You're as far from Joffrey as anyone I've ever met.

author: jon snow
content: Thank you.

author: sansa stark
content: You're good at this, you know.

author: jon snow
content: At what?

author: sansa stark
content: At ruling.

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: sansa stark
content: You are. You are. They respect you, they really do, but you have to--

author: sansa stark
content: Why are you laughing?

author: jon snow
content: What did father used to say? Everything before the word "but" is horse shit.

author: sansa stark
content: He never said that to me.

author: jon snow
content: No. No, he never cursed in front of his girls.

author: sansa stark
content: Because he was trying to protect us. He never wanted us to see how dirty the world really is, but Father couldn't protect me and neither can you. Stop trying.

author: jon snow
content: All right, I'll stop trying to protect you and you stop trying to undermine me.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm not trying to undermine you.

author: sansa stark
content: You have to be smarter than Father. You need to be smarter than Robb. I loved them, I miss them, but they made stupid mistakes, and they both lost their heads for it.

author: jon snow
content: And how should I be smarter? By listening to you?

author: sansa stark
content: Would that be so terrible?

author: wolkan
content: A raven from King's Landing, Your Grace.

author: jon snow
content: Cersei of House Lannister, First of Her Name, Queen of the Andals and the First Men, Protector of the Seven Kingdoms--

author: sansa stark
content: What does she want?

author: jon snow
content: Come to King's Landing. Bend the knee or suffer the fate of all traitors.

author: sansa stark
content: You've been so consumed with the enemy to the north, you've forgotten about the one to the south.

author: jon snow
content: I'm consumed with the Night King because I've seen him. And believe me, you'd think of little else if you had, too.

author: sansa stark
content: We still have a wall between us and the Night King. Theres nothing between us and Cersei.

author: jon snow
content: There's a thousand miles between us and Cersei. Winter is here. The Lannisters are a southern army. They've never ranged this far north.

author: sansa stark
content: You're the military man, but I know her. If you're her enemy, she'll never stop until she's destroyed you. Everyone who's ever crossed her, she's found a way to murder.

author: jon snow
content: You almost sound as if you admire her.

author: sansa stark
content: I learned a great deal from her.

author: jaime lannister
content: What is this?

author: cersei lannister
content: Its what we've been waiting for our whole lives. It's what Father trained us for, whether he knew it or not.

author: jaime lannister
content: He knew it. Made me memorize every damn city, town, lake, forest, and mountain.

author: cersei lannister
content: It's ours now, we just have to take it.

author: cersei lannister
content: You've been quiet since you came home. Are you angry with me?

author: jaime lannister
content: No, not angry.

author: cersei lannister
content: Are you afraid of me?

author: jaime lannister
content: Should I be?

author: cersei lannister
content: Daenerys Targaryen has chosen Tyrion to be her Hand. Right now, they're sailing across the Narrow Sea, hoping to take back her father's throne. Our little brother, the one you love so much, the one you set free, the one who murdered our father and our first-born son, now he stands beside our enemies and gives them counsel. He's out there somewhere at the head of an armada. Where will they land?

author: jaime lannister
content: Dragonstone.

author: jaime lannister
content: They have deep-water ports for the ships. Stannis left the castle unoccupied, and that's where she was born.

author: cersei lannister
content: Enemies to the east.

author: cersei lannister
content: Enemies to the south--Ellaria Sand and her brood of bitches.

author: cersei lannister
content: Enemies to the west--Olenna, the old cunt. Another traitor.

author: cersei lannister
content: Enemies to the north. Ned Stark's bastard has been named King in the North and that murdering whore Sansa stands beside him. Enemies everywhere. We're surrounded by traitors. You're in command of the Lannister army now. How do we proceed?

author: jaime lannister
content: Winter is here. We can't win a war if we can't feed our men and our horses. The Tyrells have the grain, the Tyrells have the livestock.

author: cersei lannister
content: Will the Tyrell bannermen stand alongside a Dothraki horde and Unsullied slave soldiers?

author: jaime lannister
content: If they think Daenerys will win. No one wants to fight on the losing side. Right now, we look like the losing side.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm the Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

author: jaime lannister
content: Three kingdoms, at best. I'm not sure you understand how much danger we're in.

author: cersei lannister
content: I understand we're in a war for survival. I understand whoever loses dies. I understand whoever wins could launch a dynasty that lasts a thousand years.

author: jaime lannister
content: A dynasty for whom? Our children are dead. We're the last of us.

author: cersei lannister
content: A dynasty for us, then.

author: jaime lannister
content: We never talked about Tommen.

author: cersei lannister
content: There's nothing to say.

author: jaime lannister
content: Our baby boy killed himself.

author: cersei lannister
content: He betrayed me. He betrayed us both. Should we spend our days mourning the dead--mother, father, and all our children?

author: jaime lannister
content: Cersei--

author: cersei lannister
content: I loved them. I did. But they're ashes now and we're still flesh and blood. We're the last Lannisters, the last ones who count.

author: jaime lannister
content: Even Lannisters can't survive without allies. Where are our allies now? You saw what happened to Walder Frey and his family.

author: cersei lannister
content: I heard. How could we ever trust a man like that?

author: jaime lannister
content: We couldn't. He was a useless, old coward, but the Freys supported us. Now they're all dead. Whoever killed them is no friend of ours. We need allies. Stronger, better allies. We can't win this war alone.

author: cersei lannister
content: You think I listened to Father for 40 years and learned nothing?

author: jaime lannister
content: The Greyjoys? You invited the Greyjoys to King's Landing?

author: cersei lannister
content: Not all of them.

author: jaime lannister
content: Well, it looks like all of them.

author: cersei lannister
content: I invited Euron Greyjoy, the new King of the Iron Islands. You said yourself we needed stronger, better allies. There you are.

author: jaime lannister
content: How are they better allies? How are they different from the Freys? They both broke their promises and murdered their former friends as soon as it suited them.

author: cersei lannister
content: So does everyone when it suits them. Unlike the Freys, they have ships. And they're good at killing.

author: jaime lannister
content: They're not good at anything. I know the Ironborn. They're bitter, angry little people. All they know how to do is steal things they can't build or grow themselves.

author: cersei lannister
content: Euron Greyjoy didn't come here for that.

author: jaime lannister
content: Oh, what did he come here for, then?

author: cersei lannister
content: A queen.

author: euron greyjoy
content: The moment I was chosen Lord of the Iron Islands, they turned on me. Their own uncle. They stole my best ships and ran. Sailed the right across the world and gave them to the Dragon Queen so she could bring her armies here to attack you.

author: euron greyjoy
content: It's nothing compares to the treason you suffered at the hands of a family members, from what I hear. But still, it bothers me. Murdering them would make me feel a lot better. And since it appears that all our treasonous family members are fighting for the same side, I thought we rightful monarchs could murder them together.

author: jaime lannister
content: You're not a rightful monarch, though, are you?

author: jaime lannister
content: The Greyjoys rebelled agains the throne for the right to be monarchs, but as I recall, you were soundly defeated. Come to mention it, weren't you the one who started that rebellion by sailing to Casterly Rock and burning the Lannister fleet? You certainly caught us there. Very smart move on your part. Of course, we all made it to the Iron Islands anyway. I was there.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I remember very well. I saw you. I heard so much talk. The best in the world. No one can stop him. I didn't believe it, to be honesty. But I must say, when you rushed through the breach and started cutting people down...it was glorious. Like a dance.

author: jaime lannister
content: The people I was cutting down were your own kin.

author: euron greyjoy
content: The place was getting crowded. I enjoyed watching it. I truly did.

author: jaime lannister
content: And I enjoyed killing Greyjoys.

author: euron greyjoy
content: A good thing for me. If you hadn't crushed us, I wouldn't have gone into exile. If I hadn't done that, I wouldn't be the greatest captain on the 14 seas.

author: cersei lannister
content: If not the most humble.

author: euron greyjoy
content: You're not humble. You're the queen of a great nation. You don't care about the Iron Islands. They're nothing but rocks and bird shit and--and a lot of very unattractive people. The Iron Fleet, on the other hand, that's something else entirely. It's the greatest armada Westeros has ever seen. With the Iron Fleet, you own the seas. You can defeat the invaders of the east and the pretenders of the north and south.

author: cersei lannister
content: What do you want in return?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Ever since I was a little boy, I wanted to grow up and mary the most beautiful woman in the world. So here I am, with a thousand ships and two good hands.

author: cersei lannister
content: I decline your proposal.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Why?

author: cersei lannister
content: You're not trustworthy. You've broken promises to allies before and murdered them at the nearest opportunity. You murdered your own brother.

author: euron greyjoy
content: You should try it. Feels wonderful.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I don't expect you to trust me outright. You need proof of my honest intentions. In my experience, the surest way to a woman's heart is with a gift. A priceless gift. I won't return to King's Landing until I have that for you.

author: marwyn
content: Ah, Maester Weyland. A drinker's liver if ever I saw one.

author: marwyn
content: Weigh that.

author: marwyn
content: The triumph of transitory pleasures. Mankindo s curse.

author: sam
content: Archmaester, I was wondering...

author: marwyn
content: What's the weight?

author: sam
content: I was wondering if you had considered my proposition.

author: marwyn
content: I don't remember your proposition.

author: sam
content: I asked you if, in light of what I've seen in the North, if I could have access to the restricted area of the library.

author: marwyn
content: That area is reserved for maesters. Are you a maester?

author: sam
content: No.

author: marwyn
content: Not a very strong proposition, is it?

author: sam
content: Archmaester, with respect, I've seen them--the Army of the Dead. The white walkers. W was sent here to learn how to defeat them, but everyone in the Citadel, those who will even talk to me, they all doubt the walkers ever existed in the first place.

author: marwyn
content: Everyone in the Citadel doubts everything. It's their job. But the tales of the Long Night can't be pure fabrication. Too many similarities from unconnected sources.

author: sam
content: Sources in the restricted area?

author: marwyn
content: The very same. And the simplest explanation for your grating obsession with the white walkers is that you're telling the truth and that you saw what you say you saw.

author: sam
content: So, you believe me.

author: marwyn
content: I do. You'll finish weighing that heart?

author: sam
content: That makes you the only person south of the Twins who does.

author: marwyn
content: We're not lie the people south of the Twins. And we're not like the people north of the Twins. In the Citadel, we lead different lives for different reasons. We are this worldo s memory, Samwell Tarly. Without us, men would be little better than dogs. Don't remember any meal but the last, can't see forward to any but the next. And every time you leave the house and shut the door, they howl like you're gone forever. When Robert's Rebellion was raging, people that the end was near. The end of the Targaryen dynasty. "How will we survive?" When Aegon Targaryen turned his eye westward and flew his dragons to Blackwater Rush--"The end is near! How will we survive?" And thousands of year before that, during the Long Night, we can forgive them for thinking it truly was the end. But it wasn't. None of it was. The Wall has stood through it all. And every winter that ever came has ended.

author: marwyn
content: Be a good lad. Clean this up.

author: brienne
content: Nope.

author: tormund
content: You're a lucky man.

author: petyr
content: I've heard she beat the Hound in single combat. She's a very impressive woman.

author: sansa stark
content: What do you want, Lord Baelish?

author: petyr
content: I want you to be happy. I want you to be safe.

author: sansa stark
content: I am safe. I'm at home, surrounded by friends. I have Brienne to protect me from anyone who would harm me.

author: petyr
content: What about happy? Why aren't you happy? What do you want that you do not have?

author: sansa stark
content: At the moment, peace and quiet.

author: sansa stark
content: No need to seize the last word, Lord Baelish. I'll assume it was something clever.

author: petyr
content: My lady.

author: brienne
content: Why is he still here?

author: sansa stark
content: We need his men. Without the Vale, Ramsay Bolton would still hold this castle. Littlefinger saved us.

author: brienne
content: He wants something.

author: sansa stark
content: I know exactly what he wants.

author: man
content: He rode through the streets of the city / Down from his hill on high / O'er the winds and the steps and the cobble / He rode to a woman's sigh / For she was his secret treasure / She was his shame and his bliss / And a chain and a keep are nothing / Compared to a woman's kiss / For hands of gold are always cold / But a woman's hands are warm / For hands of gold are always cold / But a woman's hands are--

author: arya stark
content: That's a pretty song. I've never heard it before.

author: man
content: It's a new one.

author: man
content: Are you hungry? We've got some rabbit.

author: arya stark
content: I don't want to steal your food.

author: man
content: You're not stealing, we're offering. Come on, it's gonna be a cold night.

author: man
content: You heading south?

author: arya stark
content: King's Landing.

author: man
content: Poor girl.

author: arya stark
content: Not so bad, is it?

author: man
content: Depends on your taste, I guess. If you like your streets covered in shit and pig's blood, it's the town for you.

author: man
content: All my life, I wanted to see the Red Keep, the Sept of Baelor, the Dragonpit. Then when I finally make it, they wouldn't let me within a mile of the Red Keep, the Sept of Baelor's blown to hell, and the Dragonpit is a damn ruin.

author: man
content: The people who live there, they'd skin you alive if they could make two coppers off your hide.

author: man
content: Worst place in the world.

author: arya stark
content: What are you doing in the Riverlands?

author: man
content: There's been some trouble with the Freys up at The Twins, so we're part of the army that's been sent to keep the peace.

author: man
content: Here you go. Guests first.

author: arya stark
content: Oh, no, I couldn't. You don't have enough.

author: man
content: My mother always told me to be kind to strangers. Strangers will be kind to you.

author: arya stark
content: You're a long way from home. I'm sure you've had some adventures, though.

author: man
content: Yeah, endless adventures. They'll be singing about us for a thousand years.

author: man
content: 3; The truth is when we left home, we couldn't wait to get away. But now we've been gone a while, we can't wait to get home.

author: man
content: I just think about my dad out there on his boat all alone. I ought o be out there with him.

author: man
content: My wife's just had our first baby.

author: arya stark
content: Boy or girl?

author: man
content: Oh, who knows? You think soldiers get ravens with news from home?

author: man
content: I hope it's a girl.

author: arya stark
content: Why?

author: man
content: Girls take care of their papas when their papas grow old. Boys just go off to fight in someone else's wars.

author: man
content: Are you old enough to drink?

author: man
content: It's blackberry wine. I made it myself.

author: arya stark
content: It's really good.

author: man
content: So, why is a nice girl on her own heading to King's Landing?

author: arya stark
content: I'm going to kill the queen.

author: thoros
content: Bad night to be outdoors.

author: sandor
content: You've got real powerful magic to figure that out. Did the Lord of Light whisper that in your ear? "It's snowing, Thoros. It's windy. It's gonna be a cold night."

author: thoros
content: You're a grouchy old bear, aren't you, Clegane? You want some rum?

author: sandor
content: Don't like that shit. It's too sweet.

author: thoros
content: Why are you always in such a foul mood?

author: sandor
content: Experience.

author: beric
content: This seems like a good place to spend the night.

author: sandor
content: These people don't want us here.

author: beric
content: Seems deserted to me. No livestock. No smoke coming from the chimney.

author: sandor
content: I don't like the look of it.

author: thoros
content: For a big, hard man, you scare easy.

author: sandor
content: I'll tell you what doesn't scare me

author: thoros
content: Come on. Maybe they've got some ale hidden away.

author: sandor
content: They don't.

author: thoros
content: See if there's a larder. They always leave something behind.

author: beric
content: How do you think it ended for them?

author: sandor
content: With death.

author: beric
content: Girl died in her father's arms. Both of them covered in blood and a knife at their feet. I'd say they were starving. And rather than letting his little girl suffer, he ended it for both of them.

author: sandor
content: Doesn't matter now.

author: beric
content: No, doesn't matter now.

author: sandor
content: I've known you a long time, Dondarrion.

author: beric
content: Aye. I think the first time we met was at that tournament--

author: sandor
content: And I always thought you were dull as dirt.

author: sandor
content: You're not bad. I don't hate you. Don't like, but you're not bad.

author: beric
content: Thank you, Clegane. That warms the heart.

author: sandor
content: But there's nothing special about you.

author: beric
content: You're right about that.

author: sandor
content: So why does the Lord of Light keep bringing you back? I've met better men than you, and they've been hanged from crossbeams, or beheaded, or just shat themselves to death in a field somewhere. None of them came back. So, why you?

author: beric
content: You think I don't ask myself that? Every hour of every day? Why am I here? What am I supposed to do? What does the Lord see in me?

author: sandor
content: And?

author: beric
content: I don't know. I don't understand our Lord.

author: sandor
content: Your Lord.

author: beric
content: I don't know what He wants from me. I only know that He wants me alive.

author: sandor
content: If he's so all-powerful, why doesn't he just tell you what the fuck he wants?

author: thoros
content: Clegane.

author: thoros
content: Come over here. Don't worry. The fire won't bite. I want to show you something.

author: sandor
content: It's my fucking luck I end up with a band of fire worshippers.

author: beric
content: Aye. Almost seems like divine justice.

author: sandor
content: There's no divine justice, you dumb cunt. If there was, you'd be dead...and that girl would be alive.

author: sandor
content: What do you want?

author: thoros
content: Look into the flames.

author: sandor
content: I don't want to look in the damn flames.

author: thoros
content: You saw me bring him back from the dead after you cut him down. Don't you want to know what gave me the power?

author: sandor
content: I keep asking and no one wants to tell me.

author: thoros
content: We can't tell you. Only the fire can tell you.

author: thoros
content: What do you see?

author: sandor
content: Logs burning.

author: thoros
content: Keep looking. What do you see?

author: sandor
content: Ice. A wall of ice. The Wall.

author: thoros
content: What else?

author: sandor
content: It's where the Wall meets the sea. There's a castle there.

author: sandor
content: There's a mountain. Looks like an arrowhead. The dead are marching past.

author: sandor
content: Thousands of them.

author: beric
content: Do you believe me now, Clegane? Do you believe we're here for a reason?

author: thoros
content: What the hell are you doing, Clegane?

author: sandor
content: Burying the dead.

author: thoros
content: You knew these people.

author: sandor
content: Not really.

author: sandor
content: We ask the Father to judge us with mercy. We ask the Mother to... Fuck it, I don't remember the rest. I'm sorry you're dead. You deserved better. Both of you.

author: little sam
content: Mom.

author: gilly
content: You should really sleep, Sam.

author: sam
content: The dead don't.

author: gilly
content: Legends of the Long Night.

author: sam
content: The Targaryens used dragonglass to decorate their weapons without even knowing what the First Men used it for.

author: gilly
content: What is it?

author: sam
content: It's a map of Dragonstone. The Targaryens built their first stronghold there when they invaded Westeros.

author: gilly
content: That's dragonglass?

author: sam
content: A mountain of it. Beneath the ground. Stannis told me, but I didn't think... This is important. Jon needs to know.

author: jorah mormont
content: Has she come yet?

author: sam
content: Who?

author: jorah mormont
content: The Dragon Queen. Daenerys Stormborn.

author: sam
content: Haven't heard anything.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Shall we begin?

author: tyrion lannister
content: On a night like this, you came into the world.

author: varys
