content: I remember that storm. All the dogs in King's Landing howled through the night.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I wish I could remember it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I always thought this would be a homecoming. It doesn't feel like home.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We won't stay on Dragonstone for long.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Good.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Not so many lions.

author: varys
content: Cersei controls fewer than half the Seven Kingdoms. The lord of Westeros despise her. Even before your arrival, they plotted against her. Now...

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They cry out for their true queen? They drink secret toasts to my health?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: People used to tell my brother that sort of thing, and he was stupid enough to believe them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: If Viserys had three dragons and an army at his back, he'd have invaded King's Landing already.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Conquering Westeros would be easy for you. But you're not here to be queen of the ashes.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We can take the Seven Kingdoms without turning it into a slaughterhouse. If the great houses support your claim against Cersei, the game is won. With the Tyrell army and the Dornish on our side, we have powerful allies in the south.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I never properly thanked you for that.

author: varys
content: They joined our side, my queen, because they believe in you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You served my father, didn't you, Lord Varys?

author: varys
content: I did.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And then you served the man who overthrew him?

author: varys
content: I had a choice, Your Grace--serve Robert Baratheon or face the headman's axe.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But you didn't serve him long. You turned against him.

author: varys
content: Robert was an improvement on your father, to be sure. There have been few rulers in history as cruel as the Mad King. Robert was neither mad nor cruel. He simply had no interest in being king.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So you took it upon yourself to find a better one.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace, when I was ready to drink myself into a small coffin, Lord Varys told me about a queen in the east who--

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Before I came to power, you favored my brother. All your spies, your little birds, did they tell you Viserys was cruel, stupid, and weak? Would those qualities have made for a good king in your learned opinion?

author: varys
content: Until your marriage to Khal Drogo, Your Grace, I knew nothing about you, save your existence and that you were said to be beautiful.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So you and your friends traded me like a prized horse to the Dothraki.

author: varys
content: Which you turned to your advantage.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who gave the order to kill me?

author: varys
content: King Robert.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who hired the assassins?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who sent word to Essos to murder Daenerys Targaryen?

author: varys
content: Your Grace, I did what had to be done to--

author: daenerys targaryen
content: To keep yourself alive.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Lord Varys has proven himself a loyal servant.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Proven himself loyal? Quite the opposite. If he dislikes one monarch, he conspires to crown the next one. What king of a servant is that?

author: varys
content: The kind the realm needs. Incompetence should not be rewarded with blind loyalty. As long as I have my eyes, I'll use them. I wasn't born into a great house. I came from nothing. I was sold as a slave and carved up as an offering. When I was a child, I lived in alleys, gutters, abandoned houses. You wish to know where my true loyalties lie? Not with any king or queen, but with the people. The people who suffer under despots and prosper under just rule. The people whose hearts you aim to win. If you demand blind allegiance, I respect your wishes. Grey Worm can behead me or your dragons can devour me. But if you let me live, I will serve you well. I will dedicate myself to seeing you on the Iron Throne because I choose you. Because I know the people have no better chance than you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Swear this to me, Varys. If you ever think I'm failing the people, you won't conspire behind my back. You'll look me in the eye as you have done today, and you'll tell me how I'm failing them.

author: varys
content: I swear it, my queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And I swear this--if you ever betray me, I'll burn you alive.

author: varys
content: I would expect nothing less from the Mother of Dragons.

author: grey worm
content: Forgive me, my queen. A red priestess from As'shai has come to see you.

author: melisandre
content: Queen Daeneys, I was a slave once, bought and sold, scourged and branded. It is an honor to meet the Breaker of Chains.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Red Priests helped bring peace to Meereen. You are very welcome here. What is your name?

author: melisandre
content: I am called Melisandre.

author: varys
content: She once served another who wanted the Iron Throne. It didn't end well for Stannis Baratheon, did it?

author: melisandre
content: No, it didn't.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You chose an auspicious day to arrive at Dragonstone.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We've just decided to pardon those who served the wrong king.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The Lord of Light doesn't have many followers in Westeros, does he?

author: melisandre
content: Not yet. But even those who don't worship the Lord can serve his cause.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What does your Lord expect from me?

author: melisandre
content: The Long Night is coming. Only the prince who was promised can bring the dawn.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The prince who was promised will bring the dawn. I'm afraid I'm not a prince.

author: missandei
content: Your Grace, forgive me, but your translation is not quite accurate. That noun has no gender in High Valyrian, so the proper translation for that prophecy would be the prince or princess who was promised will bring the dawn.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Doesn't really roll off the tongue, does it?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No, but I like it better.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you believe this prophecy refers to me?

author: melisandre
content: Prophecies are dangerous things. I believe you have a role to play, as does another. The King in the North, Jon Snow.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Jon Snow? Ned Stark's bastard?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You know him?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I traveled with him to the Wall when he joined the Night's Watch.

author: varys
content: And why do you think the Lord of Light singled out this Jon Snow aside from the visions you've seen in the flames, that is?

author: melisandre
content: As Lord Commander of the Night's Watch he allowed the Wildlings south of the Wall to protect them from great danger. As King in the North he has united those Wildlings with the northern houses so together they may face their common enemy.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He sounds like quite a man.

author: melisandre
content: Summon Jon Snow. Let him stand before you and tell you things that have happened to him, the things that he has seen with his own eyes.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I can't speak to prophecies or visions in the flames, but I like Jon Snow and I trusted him, and I am an excellent judge of character.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If he does rule the north, he would make a valuable ally. The Lannisters executed his father and conspired to murder his brother. Jon Snow has even more reason to hate Cersei than you do.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Very well. Send a raven north. Tell Jon Snow that his Queen invites him to come to Drangonstone...and bend the knee.

author: sansa stark
content: Do you think it's really Tyrion? It could be someone trying to lure you into a trap.

author: jon snow
content: Read the last bit.

author: sansa stark
content: All dwarfs are bastards in their father's eyes." What does that mean?

author: jon snow
content: It's something he said to me the first night we met. You know him better than any of us. What do you think?

author: sansa stark
content: Tyrion is not like the other Lannisters. He was always kind to me, but it's too great a risk. "The Seven Kingdoms will bleed as long as Cersei sits on the Iron Throne. Join us. Together we can end her tyranny."

author: davos
content: Sounds like a charmer. Of course, the casual mention of a Dothraki horde, a legion of Unsullied and three dragons, a bit less charming.

author: jon snow
content: What?

author: davos
content: Fire kills Whites, you told me. What breathes fire?

author: sansa stark
content: You're not suggesting Jon meet with her?

author: davos
content: No, too dangerous.

author: jon snow
content: But?

author: davos
content: But if the Army of the Dead makes it passed the Wall, do we have enough men to fight them?

author: cersei lannister
content: If the Mad King's daughter takes the Iron Throne, she will destroy the Realm as we know it. Some of you are bannermen of House Tyrell. But House Tyrell is in open rebellion against the Crown. With their help the Mad King's daughter has ferried an army of savages to our shores. Mindless Unsullied soldiers who will destroy your castles and your holdfasts. Dothraki heathens who will burn your villages to the ground, rape and enslave your women, and butcher your children without a second thought. This is how Olenna Tyrell rewards centuries of service and loyalty.

author: cersei lannister
content: You all remember the Mad King. You remember the horrors he inflicted upon his people. His daughter is no different. In Essos her brutality is already legendary. She crucified hundreds of noblemen in Slaver's Bay. And when she grew bored of that, she fed them to her dragons.

author: cersei lannister
content: It is my solemn duty to protect the people, and I will but I need your help, My Lords. We must stand together, all of us, if we hope to stop her.

author: randyll
content: She has three full-grown dragons, Your Grace. The same as Aegon when he conquered the Seven Kingdoms. How do you propose to stop them?

author: qyburn
content: We are currently at work on a solution, My Lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: Lord Tarley.

author: randyll
content: Ser, Jaime. I believe you know my son.

author: dickon
content: Ser, Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: Rickon, isn't it?

author: dickon
content: Dickon.

author: jaime lannister
content: That's it.

author: jaime lannister
content: Thank you for coming. The other lords of the Reach look to you for guidance now more than ever. They might not have come if you hadn't.

author: randyll
content: If my queen summons me, I answer the call. And I've heard what she does to those that defy her.

author: jaime lannister
content: Do you ride for Hornhill today?

author: randyll
content: I have an army to mobilize. It won't be long until the fighting starts.

author: jaime lannister
content: And what side will you be fighting for? You were the only man to defeat Robert Baratheon in battle. Not even Rhaegar Targaryen could --

author: randyll
content: It's a long ride back to the reach, Ser Jaime. How may I serve?

author: jaime lannister
content: I want you to be my ranking general in the wars to come. I want you to swear allegiance to Cersei and I want you to help her destroy her enemies. All of her enemies.

author: randyll
content: Including Olenna Tyrell? I'm a Tarley. That name means something. We're not oath breakers. We're not schemers. We don't stab our rivals in the back or cut their throats at weddings. I swore an oath to House Tyrell.

author: jaime lannister
content: You swore an oath to the Crown as well, Lord Tarley.

author: randyll
content: I've known Olenna since I was a child.

author: jaime lannister
content: She was a great woman, once. Now she's broken. She wants revenge so badly she brought the Dothraki to our shores. The Dothraki in Westeros for the first time in history. I know you don't like my sister, but you have to make a choice. Do you fight with us or with the foreign savages and eunuchs?

author: jaime lannister
content: When the war is won the queen will need a new warden of the south. I can think of no better man than Randyll Tarley.

author: marwyn
content: The infection has spread too far. You should have cut off your arm the moment you were touched.

author: jorah mormont
content: How long?

author: marwyn
content: It will be years before it kills you. It could be 10, could be 20.

author: jorah mormont
content: But how long 'till...

author: marwyn
content: Your mind? Six months, maybe fewer.

author: sam tarly
content: Pardon, Archmaester. I met Stannis Baratheon's daughter at Castle Black. She had Greyscale as a baby and was cured. Isn't there some way --

author: marwyn
content: Does this look like a baby to you?

author: sam tarly
content: No.

author: marwyn
content: Have you studied the varying rates of Greyscale progression in infants and fully grown men?

author: marwyn
content: Maester Chrissen discovered Shireen Baratheon's affliction immediately.

author: marwyn
content: This is quite advanced and beyond our skills, Ser. Were you a commoner I'd have you shipped to Valyria at once to live out your life with the Stone Men. As an anointed Knight I'll allow you one more day. How you choose to spend that time is up to you.

author: marwyn
content: Come, Samwell.

author: sam tarly
content: Should we send word to your family, Ser...

author: jorah mormont
content: Jorah. Jorah Mormont.

author: sam tarly
content: Mormont?

author: jorah mormont
content: There's no need. I've been dead to them for years.

author: qyburn
content: Have you ever been down here, Your Grace?

author: cersei lannister
content: No, I can't say I have. I haven't seen these since Robert had them removed from the Throne Room.

author: qyburn
content: Curious that King Robert did not have them destroyed.

author: cersei lannister
content: They were his trophies. He couldn't keep them around. They would have made him look small. Sometimes he would come down here and look at them. I believe he brought his whores on occasion.

author: qyburn
content: Balerion the Dread. The beast that Aegon rode across the sea. Its flames forged the Iron Throne and brought the Seven Kingdoms to heel. Powerful, but not invincible.

author: qyburn
content: Apparently one of Daenarys' dragons was wounded by spears in the fighting pits of Meereen. If they can be wounded, they can be killed.

author: qyburn
content: The finest artilleters and blacksmiths in King's Landing have been laboring day and night, Your Grace. If you'd kindly pull that lever.

author: yara greyjoy
content: If you want the Iron Throne, take it. We have an army, a fleet, and three dragons. We should hit King's Landing now. Hard. With everything we have. The city will fall within a day.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If we turn the dragons loose, tens of thousands will die in the firestorms.

author: ellaria
content: It's called war. You don't have the stomach for it, scurry back into hiding.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know how you wage war. We don't poison little girls here. Myrcella was innocent.

author: ellaria
content: She was a Lannister. There are no innocent Lannisters. My greatest regret is that Oberyn died fighting for you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That's enough. Tyrion is the Hand of the Queen. You will treat him with respect.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I am not here to be queen of the ashes.

author: olenna tyrell
content: That's very nice to hear. Of course, I can't remember a queen who was better loved than my grand daughter. The common people loved her, the nobles loved her. And what is left of her now? Ashes. Commoners, nobles, they're all just children really. They won't obey you unless they fear you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm grateful to you, Lady Olenna, for your council. I'm grateful to all of you. But you have chosen to follow me. I will not attack King's Landing. We will not attack King's Landing.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Then how do you mean to take the Iron Throne? By asking nicely?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We will lay siege to the capital surrounding the city on all sides. Cersei will have the Iron Throne but no food for her army or the people.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But we won't use Dothraki and Unsullied.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cersei will try to rally the lords of Westeros by appealing to their loyalty, their love for their country. If we besiege the city with foreigners, we prove her point. Our army should be Westerosi.

author: ellia
content: And I suppose we're providing the Westerosi?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You are.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Lady Greyjoy will escort you home to Sunspear and her Iron Fleet will ferry the Dornish army back up to King's Landing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Dornish will lay siege to the capital alongside the Tyrell army. Two great kingdoms united against Cersei.

author: olenna tyrell
content: So, your master plan is to use our armies? Forgive me for asking, but why did you bother to bring your own?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The unsullied will have another objective. For decades House Lannister has been the true power in Westeros. And the seat of that power is Casterly Rock. Grey Worm and the Unsullied will sail for the Rock and take it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Do I have your support?

author: yara greyjoy
content: You have mine.

author: ellia
content: Dorne is with you, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you all. Lady Olenna, may I speak with you alone?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I realize you're here out of hatred for Cersei and not love for me. But I swear to you she will pay for what she's done and we will bring peace back to Westeros.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Peace. Do you think that's what we had under your father or his father or his? Peace never lasts, my dear. Would you take a bit of advice from an old woman?

author: olenna tyrell
content: He's a clever man, your Hand. I've known a great many clever men. I've outlived them all. Do you know why? I ignored them. The lords of Westeros are sheep. Are you a sheep? No. You're a dragon. Be a dragon.

author: grey worm
content: Enter.

author: missandei
content: You leave tomorrow. Were you going to say goodbye?

author: grey worm
content: I will see you when I return.

author: missandei
content: But you don't know when that will be.

author: grey worm
content: No one knows.

author: missandei
content: I wish you good fortune.

author: grey worm
content: Missandei --

author: grey worm
content: It is hard for me to say goodbye to you.

author: missandei
content: Why?

author: grey worm
content: You know why.

author: missandei
content: I don't.

author: grey worm
content: You are my weakness.

author: missandei
content: That's what I am? Your weakness?

author: grey worm
content: When Unsullied are young their masters learn their fears. One boy is scared of dogs. One boy hates high places. One is frightened of the ocean. They make the boy sleep with dogs or climb a cliff. They throw him in the water. If he learns to swim, good. If he drowns, good. Either way, strong Unsullied. But I had no fears. I was never the biggest, never the strongest, but I was bravest always.

author: missandei
content: I believe it.

author: grey worm
content: Until I meet Missandei from the Isle of Naarth. Now I have fear.

author: missandei
content: I do too.

author: grey worm
content: No.

author: missandei
content: I want to see you. Please.

author: marwyn
content: It might be useful. Fouthen was a dreadful writer but an excellent researcher.

author: sam tarly
content: Archmaester, I wanted to --

author: marwyn
content: And this one.

author: marwyn
content: Maester Faol was quite the opposite. A brilliant stylist who invented half the stories he tells.

author: sam tarly
content: I wanted to ask you --

author: marwyn
content: If you need to write histories, Tarley, you have to do the research. If you want people to read your histories, you need a bit of style. I'm not writing the Chronicle of the Wars Following the Death of King Robert the First so it can sit on a shelf unread.

author: marwyn
content: What? You don't like the title? What would you call it then?

author: sam tarly
content: Possibly something a bit more poetic?

author: marwyn
content: We're not poets, Tarley.

author: sam tarly
content: Archmaester, if I could just have a moment.

author: marwyn
content: This is your moment. Use it wisely.

author: sam tarly
content: I may have found a way to treat Ser Jorah. There are two recorded cases of advanced Greyscale being cured. I found the procedure in the Study of Rare Diseases by Archmaester Pilos.

author: marwyn
content: I'm familiar with Archmaester Pylos and the Study of Rare Diseases.

author: sam tarly
content: Oh, you are?

author: marwyn
content: Yes. Should I tell you how he died? From Greyscale.

author: sam tarly
content: Oh.

author: marwyn
content: The procedure is far too dangerous which is why it's now forbidden.

author: sam tarly
content: Hello.

author: jorah mormont
content: What are you doing?

author: sam tarly
content: You're Jorah Mormont. You're the only son of Jeor Mormont.

author: sam tarly
content: My name is Samwell Tarley. I'm a sworn brother of the Night's Watch training to serve as maester of Castle Black. I knew your father. I was with him when he died. You're not dying today, Ser Jorah.

author: sam tarly
content: Drink this.

author: jorah mormont
content: What is it?

author: sam tarly
content: Rum. Drink it all, please. I'm afraid this is going to hurt.

author: sam tarly
content: If you could take off your shirt.

author: sam tarly
content: If you wouldn't mind, bite down hard. I'm sorry but no one knows I'm here. If they hear you screaming then we're both finished.

author: jorah mormont
content: Have you ever done this before?

author: sam tarly
content: No. No one else will try, so I'm the best you've got. Have a seat. I'm going to remove the entire layer of infected tissue, then apply a medicinal ointment to the --

author: sam tarly
content: Shh, shhh. Again, I'm sorry. Please try not to scream.

author: man
content: They say her dragons are bigger than Aegons.

author: man
content: Horse shit. Cersei is just trying to frighten us.

author: man
content: If it's true, if she lays siege to King's Landing prices will triple.

author: man
content: As long as we get back there before they start.

author: man
content: One more round. It's a long ride.

author: hot pie
content: Ary!

author: arya stark
content: Hello, Hot Pie. Sit down. Who's that for?

author: arya stark
content: Mmm. This is good.

author: hot pie
content: You think so? The secret is browning the butter before making the dough. Most people don't don't do that because it takes up too much time.

author: arya stark
content: I didn't do that.

author: hot pie
content: You've been making pies?

author: arya stark
content: One or two.

author: hot pie
content: I can't believe you're here. Did you meet the big lady?

author: arya stark
content: Big lady?

author: hot pie
content: The lady knight. I figured she was a knight because she had armor on. She was looking for your sister but I told her about you. Did she ever find you?

author: arya stark
content: She found me.

author: hot pie
content: What happened to you Ary?

author: arya stark
content: You got any ale?

author: hot pie
content: Where are you heading?

author: arya stark
content: King's Landing.

author: hot pie
content: Why?

author: arya stark
content: I heard Cersei's queen now.

author: hot pie
content: I heard she blew up the Great Sept. That must have been something to see. Boom.

author: arya stark
content: Hmm.

author: hot pie
content: I can't believe someone could do that.

author: arya stark
content: Cersei would do that.

author: hot pie
content: I thought you'd be heading for Winterfell.

author: arya stark
content: Why would I go there? The Boltons have it.

author: hot pie
content: No. The Boltons are dead.

author: arya stark
content: What?

author: hot pie
content: Jon Snow came down from Castle Black with a Wildling army and won the Battle of the Bastards. He's King in the North now.

author: arya stark
content: You're lying.

author: hot pie
content: Why would I lie about that? He's your brother right?

author: arya stark
content: Thanks for the pie.

author: hot pie
content: Friends don't pay. I can't believe I thought you were a boy. You're pretty.

author: arya stark
content: Thanks.

author: arya stark
content: Take care of yourself, Hot Pie. Try not to get killed.

author: hot pie
content: No, I won't. I'm like you, Ary. I'm a survivor.

author: jon snow
content: Come in.

author: wolkan
content: A raven, My King, from the Citadel.

author: jon snow
content: This message was sent to me by Samwell Tarley. He was my brother at the Night's Watch. A man I trust as much as anyone in this world. He's discovered proof that Dragonstone sits on a mountain of Dragonglass.

author: jon snow
content: I received this a few days ago from Dragonstone. It was sent to me by Tyrion Lannister.

author: jon snow
content: He's now Hand of the Queen to Daenerys Targaryen. She intends to take the Iron Throne from Cersei Lannister. She has a powerful army at her back and if this message is to be believed, three dragons.

author: jon snow
content: Lord Tyrion has invited me to Dragonstone to meet with Daenerys and I'm going to accept.

author: jon snow
content: We need this Dragonglass, My Lords. We know that Dragonglass can destroy both White Walkers and their army. We need to mine it and turn it into weapons.

author: jon snow
content: But more importantly, we need allies. The Night King's army grows larger by the day. We can't defeat them on our own. We don't have the numbers. Daenerys has her own army and she has dragon fire. I need to try and persuade her to fight with us. Ser Davos and I will ride for White Harbor tomorrow, then sail for Dragonstone.

author: sansa stark
content: Have you forgotten what happened to our grandfather? The Mad King invited him to King's Landing and roasted him alive.

author: jon snow
content: I know that.

author: sansa stark
content: She is here to reclaim the Iron Throne and the Seven Kingdoms. The north is one of those seven kingdoms. This isn't an invitation, it's a trap.

author: jon snow
content: It could be, but I don't believe Tyrion would do that. You know him. He's a good man.

author: yohn royce
content: Your Grace, with respect I must agree with Lady Sansa. I remember the Mad King all too well. A Targaryen cannot be trusted, nor can a Lannister.

author: robett glover
content: We called your brother king, and then he rode south and lost his kingdom.

author: lyanna mormont
content: Winter is here, Your Grace. We need the King in the North in the north.

author: jon snow
content: You all crowned me your king. I never wanted it, I never asked for it, but I accepted it because the north is my home. It's part of me and I will never stop fighting for it, no matter the odds. But the odds are against us. None of you have seen the Army of the Dead. None of you. We can never hope to defeat them alone. We need allies, powerful allies. I know it's a risk. But I have to take it.

author: sansa stark
content: Then send an emissary. Don't go yourself.

author: jon snow
content: Daenerys is a queen. Only a king can convince her to help us. It has to be me.

author: sansa stark
content: You're abandoning your people. Your abandoning your home.

author: jon snow
content: I'm leaving both in good hands.

author: sansa stark
content: Whose?

author: jon snow
content: Yours. You are my sister. You are the only Stark in Winterfell. Until I return, the north is yours.

author: petyr baelish
content: I delivered his bones myself. I presented them to Lady Catlyn as a gesture of goodwill from Tyrion Lannister. It seems like a lifetime ago. Do give Lord Tyrion my best when you see him.

author: petyr baelish
content: I was sorry when he died. Your father and I had our differences but he loved Cat very much. So did I. She wasn't fond of you, was she? Well, it appears she vastly underestimated you. Your father and brothers are gone, yet here you stand King in the North. Last best hope against the coming storm.

author: jon snow
content: You don't belong down here.

author: petyr baelish
content: Forgive me. We have never talked properly. I wanted to remedy that.

author: jon snow
content: I have nothing to say to you.

author: petyr baelish
content: Not even thank you? If it weren't for me you'd have been slaughtered at that battlefield. You have many enemies, My King, but I swear to you I'm not one of them. I love Sansa as I loved her mother.

author: jon snow
content: Touch my sister and I'll kill you myself.

author: arya stark
content: Nymeria?

author: arya stark
content: Nymeria, it's me, Arya. I'm heading north, girl, back to Winterfell. I'm finally going home. Come with me.

author: arya stark
content: Come with me.

author: arya stark
content: That's not you.

author: nymeria
content: You can't have them all. It's not fair.

author: obara
content: I'm oldest.

author: tyene
content: Momma will want Cersei for herself.

author: obara
content: She's not my momma. You can have Cersei. I want The Mountain.

author: nymeria
content: The Mountain killed father. He'll crush you with one hand.

author: tyene
content: Father got careless. That's what Momma says.

author: obara
content: Will you shut up about Momma? Momma, momma.

author: tyene
content: Maybe I'll kill you both before we take King's Landing and then I won't have to share.

author: ellaria
content: How can you drink this piss? When we reach Sunspear I'll treat you to a Dornish red, the best in the world. Have you ever been to Dorne?

author: yara greyjoy
content: A few times. Never stayed long.

author: ellaria
content: A boy in every port?

author: yara greyjoy
content: A boy, a girl. Depends on the port.

author: ellaria
content: Could we get some more?

author: yara greyjoy
content: I thought it wasn't for you.

author: ellaria
content: I'm developing a taste for it.

author: yara greyjoy
content: He's not your servant.

author: theon greyjoy
content: It's fine.

author: ellaria
content: So, you're going to be Queen of the Iron Islands.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Once I kill my uncle.

author: ellaria
content: And what will you be, handsome?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Whatever my queen demands.

author: yara greyjoy
content: He'll be my advisor, my protector.

author: ellaria
content: Oh, I see. Your protector.

author: ellaria
content: So if someone gets too close to you --

author: yara greyjoy
content: He might have to intervene.

author: ellaria
content: hold that person back.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Until they've made their intentions known.

author: ellaria
content: Why are you standing all the way over there then? A foreign invasion is under way. It seems like you don't need a protector.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Stay here.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Euron.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Your mother is below deck. Keep her safe.

author: ellaria
content: Kill us! Get it over with!

author: euron greyjoy
content: Give your uncle a kiss.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Theon!

author: euron greyjoy
content: Ah, come on your cockless hound. I have her. Come and get her.

author: end
content: CREDITS

author: tyrion lannister
content: The bastard of Winterfell.

author: jon snow
content: The dwarf of Casterly Rock.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I believe we last saw each other on top of the wall.

author: jon snow
content: You were pissing off the edge, if I remember right. You picked up some scars along the road.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's been a long road. But we're both still here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm Tyrion Lannister.

author: davos
content: Davos Seaworth.

author: tyrion lannister
content: and DAVOS shake hands.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah, the Onion Knight. We fought on opposite sides at the Battle of Blackwater Bay.

author: davos
content: Unluckily for me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Missandei is the queen's most trusted advisor.

author: missandei
content: Welcome to Dragonstone. Our queen knows this is a long journey. She appreciates the effort you have made on her behalf. If you wouldn't mind handing over your weapons.

author: jon snow
content: Of course.

author: missandei
content: Please, this way.

author: davos
content: Where are you from? I can't place the accent.

author: missandei
content: I was born on the Island of Naarth.

author: davos
content: Ah. I hear it's beautiful down there. Palm trees and butterflies. I haven't been myself.

author: davos
content: This place has changed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And Sansa, I hear she's alive and well.

author: jon snow
content: She is.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Does she miss me terribly?

author: tyrion lannister
content: A sham marriage and unconsummated.

author: jon snow
content: I didn't ask --

author: tyrion lannister
content: Well, it was. It wasn't. Anyway, she's much smarter than she lets on.

author: jon snow
content: She's starting to let on.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. At some point I want to hear how a Knight's Watch recruit became King in the North.

author: jon snow
content: As long as you tell me how a Lannister became Hand to Daenerys Targaryen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A long and bloody tale. To be honest, I was drunk for most of it.

author: jon snow
content: My bannermen think I'm a fool for coming here.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Of course they do. If I was your hand I would have advised against it. General rule of thumb, Stark men don't fare well when they travel south.

author: jon snow
content: True. But I'm not a Stark.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'd say you get used to them, but you never really do.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Come. Their mother is waiting for you.

author: varys
content: I wondered why you weren't there to meet our guests. You begged us to summon the King in the North. Don't you want to see him again?

author: melisandre
content: I've done my part. I've brought ice and fire together.

author: varys
content: Strange. You spoke so highly of Jon Snow but when he arrives you hide on a cliff. I didn't take you for a bashful girl.

author: melisandre
content: My time whispering in the ears of kings has come to an end.

author: varys
content: Oh, I doubt that. Give us common folk one taste of power we're like the lion who tasted man. Nothing is ever so sweet again.

author: melisandre
content: Neither of us is common folk anymore. I did not part on good terms with the King in the North, or his advisor.

author: varys
content: Why?

author: melisandre
content: Because of mistakes I made. Terrible mistakes. I would only be a distraction if I stayed.

author: varys
content: So where will you go?

author: melisandre
content: Volantis.

author: varys
content: Good. If you don't mind my saying, I don't think you should return to Westeros. I'm not sure you'd be safe here.

author: melisandre
content: I will return, dear spider. One last time.

author: varys
content: My Lady --

author: melisandre
content: I have to die in this strange country, just like you.

author: missandei
content: You stand in the presence of Daenerys Stormborn of House Targaryen, rightful heir to the Iron Throne, rightful Queen of the Andals and the First Men, Protector of the Seven Kingdoms, the Mother of Dragons, the Khaleesi of the Great Grass Sea, The Unburnt, The Breaker of Chains.

author: davos
content: This is Jon Snow.

author: davos
content: He's King in the North.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you for traveling so far, My Lords. I hope the seas weren't too rough.

author: jon snow
content: The winds were kind, Your Grace.

author: davos
content: Apologies. I have a Flea Bottom accent, I know. But Jon Snow is King in the North, Your Grace. He's not a lord.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Forgive me --

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace, this is Ser Davos Seaworth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Forgive me, Ser Davos. I never did receive a formal education, but I could have sworn the last King in the North was Torren Stark who bent the knee to my ancestor Aegon Targaryen in exchange for his life and the lives of the northmen. Torren Stark swore fealty to House Targaryen in perpetuity. But do I have my facts wrong?

author: davos
content: I wasn't there, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No. Of course not. But still, an oath is an oath. In perpetuity means -- what does perpetuity mean, Lord Tyrion?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Forever.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Forever. So I assume, My Lord, that you're here to bend the knee.

author: jon snow
content: I am not.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Oh. Well, that is unfortunate. You've travelled all this way to break faith with House Targaryen?

author: jon snow
content: Break faith? Your father burned my grandfather alive. He burned my uncle alive. He would have burned the Seven Kingdoms.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My father was an evil man. On behalf of House Targaryen I ask your forgiveness for the crimes he committed against your family. And I ask you not to judge a daughter by the sins of her father. Our two houses were allies for centuries. Those were the best centuries the kingdom's ever known. Centuries of peace and prosperity with the Targaryens sitting on the Iron Throne and a Stark serving as Warden of the North. I am the last Targaryen, Jon Snow. Honor the pledge your ancestor made to mine. Bend the knee and I will name you Warden of the North. Together we will save this country from those who would destroy it.

author: jon snow
content: You're right. You're not guilty of your father's crime. And I'm not beholden to my ancestor's vows.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Then why are you here?

author: jon snow
content: Because I need your help and you need mine.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Did you see three dragons flying overhead when you arrived?

author: jon snow
content: I did.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And did you see the Dothraki, all of whom have sworn to kill for me?

author: jon snow
content: They're hard to miss.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But still, I need your help?

author: davos
content: Not to defeat Cersei. You could storm King's Landing tomorrow and the city would fall. Hell, we almost took it and we didn't even have dragons.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Almost.

author: jon snow
content: But you haven't stormed King's Landing. Why not? The only reason I can see is you don't want to kill thousands of innocent people. It's the fastest way to win the war but you won't do it. Which means at the very least you're better than Cersei.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Still, that doesn't explain why I need your help.

author: jon snow
content: Because right now you and I and Cersei and everyone else, we're children playing at a game screaming that the rules aren't fair.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You told me you liked this man.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I do.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: In the time since he's met me he's refused to call me queen, he's refused to bow and now he's calling me a child.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I believe he's calling all of us children. Figure of speech.

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace, everone you know will die before winter is over if we don't defeat the enemy to the north.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: As far as I can see, you are the enemy to the north.

author: jon snow
content: I am not your enemy. The dead are the enemy.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The dead?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Is that another figure of speech?

author: jon snow
content: The Army of the Dead is on the march.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Army of the Dead?

author: jon snow
content: You don't know me well, My Lord, but do you think I am a liar or a madman?

author: tyrion lannister
content: No, I don't think you're either of those things.

author: jon snow
content: The Army of the Dead is real. The White Walkers are real. The Knight King is real. I've seen them. If they get past the wall and we're squabbling amongst ourselves --

author: jon snow
content: we're finished.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I was born at Dragonstone. Not that I can remember it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We fled before Robert's assassins could find us. Robert was your father's best friend, no? I wonder if your father knew his best friend sent assassins to murder a baby girl in her crib. Not that it matters now of course. I spent my life in foreign lands. So many men have tried to kill me. I don't remember all of their names. I have been sold like a brood mare. I have been chained and betrayed, raped and defiled. Do you know what kept me standing through all those years in exile? Faith. Not in any gods. Not in myths and legends. In myself. In Daenerys Targaryen. The world hadn't seen a dragon in centuries until my children were born. The Dothraki hadn't crossed the sea. Any sea.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They did for me. I was born to rule the Seven Kingdoms. And I will.

author: jon snow
content: You'll be ruling over a graveyard if we don't defeat the Night King.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The war against my sister has already begun. You can't expect us to halt hostilities and join you in fighting --

author: tyrion lannister
content: whatever you saw beyond the wall.

author: davos
content: You don't believe him. I understand that. It sounds like nonsense.

author: davos
content: But if destiny has brough Daenerys Targaryen back to our shores, it has also made Jon Snow King in the North. You were the first to bring Dothraki to Westeros. He was the first to make allies with Wildlings and northmen. He was named Lord Commander of the Night's Watch. He was named King in the North. Not because of his birthright. He has no birthright. He's a damn bastard. All those hard son's of bitches chose him as their leader because they believe in him.

author: davos
content: All those things you don't believe in, he faced those things. He fought those things for the good of his people. He risked his life for his people. He took a knife in the heart for his people. He gave his own --

author: davos
content: If we don't put asside our enmities and band together we will die. And then it doesn't matter whose skeleton sits on the Iron Throne.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If it doesn't matter you might as well kneel.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Swear your allegiance to Queen Daenerys. Help her to defeat my sister and together our armies will protect the north.

author: jon snow
content: There's no time for that. There's no time for any of this. While we stand here debating --

author: tyrion lannister
content: It takes no time to bend the knee. Pledge your sword to her cause.

author: jon snow
content: And why would I do that?

author: jon snow
content: I mean no offense, Your Grace, but I don't know you. As far as I can tell your claim to the throne rests entirely on your father's name. And my own father fought to overthrow the Mad King. The lords of the north placed their trust in me to lead them. And I will continue to do so as well as I can.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That's fair. It's also fair to point out that I'm the rightful queen of the Seven Kingdoms. By declaring yourself king of the northern most kingdom, you are in open rebellion.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You must forgive my manners. You will both be tired after your long journey. We'll have baths drawn for you and supper sent to your rooms.

author: jon snow
content: Am I your prisoner?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Not yet.

author: varys
content: Our Iron Born and Dornish allies were attacked on route to Dorne.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And?

author: varys
content: Two or three ships escaped. The rest sunk our captured. Ellaria and the sand snakes dead or captured. The Greyjoys are dead or captured.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: All of them?

author: captain
content: Your sister's dead?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Euron has her.

author: captain
content: You saw him take her? And you got away?

author: theon greyjoy
content: I couldn't save her. I tried.

author: captain
content: You wouldn't be here if you tried.

author: euron greyjoy
content: This is the life. Look at them. Cheering for a Greyjoy.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I have to be honest, it's making me hard. Did you see little Theon's face right before he jumped overboard?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Oh no!

author: euron greyjoy
content: What a twat.

author: euron greyjoy
content: My queen. Please accept this gift on behalf of all of your loyal subjects in the Iron Islands.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I give you --

author: euron greyjoy
content: what no other man could give. Justice. Justice for your murdered daughter.

author: cersei lannister
content: You've proven yourself the greatest captain on the 14 seas and a true friend to the crown.

author: euron greyjoy
content: A bit more than a true friend.

author: cersei lannister
content: And you deserve a proper reward for your heroism.

author: euron greyjoy
content: There's only one reward I want.

author: cersei lannister
content: You shall have what your heart desires --

author: cersei lannister
content: when the war is won.

author: cersei lannister
content: With Euron Greyjoy commanding our naval forces and Jaime Lannister leading our armies, the sons and daugters of Westeros shall defend our country.

author: euron greyjoy
content: There's nothing quite like it, is there? The love of the people. I suppose you wouldn't know.

author: jaime lannister
content: This same mob spat at my sister not long ago, and if you turn on us, they'll cheer to see your head mounted on a spike.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Or yours. They just like severed heads really. Listen, if you have any advice at all I'd love to hear it when we have an hour or two to speak as brothers.

author: jaime lannister
content: Advice?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Does she like it gentle or rough? A finger in the bum?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Shhh, shhh, shhh, not now. We'll talk later.

author: cersei lannister
content: I want you to know I understand. Even though we're enemies, you and I, I understand the fear that drives you. I was there that day when Ser Gregor crushed your lover's head. I close my eyes I can hear the sound of Oberyn's skull breaking.

author: cersei lannister
content: The sound of your scream. I never heard a sound like that. I thought, that's true love. Oberyn looked beautiful that day. He really did. No one moved like him. No one had such skill with a spear. Even Ser Gregor couldn't stop him. If only he hadn't taunted him. He could have walked away and left poor Ser Gregor to die. But that wasn't your lover's way, was it? Now he's burried somewhere. And here Ser Gregor is stronger than ever. That must be difficult for you. When my daughter was taken from me, my only daughter, well, you can't imagine how that feels unless you've lost a child. I fed her at my own breast even though they told me to give her to the wet nurse. I couldn't bear to see her in another woman's arms. I never got to have a mother. But Myrcella did. She was mine and you took her from me. Why did you do that?

author: cersei lannister
content: It doesn't matter now.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your daughter is a beauty too. Brown eyes, those lips. A perfect Dornish beauty.

author: cersei lannister
content: I imagine she is your favorite.

author: cersei lannister
content: I know, I know, we're not supposed to have favorites. But still, we're only human. We love who we love.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'm sorry. I can't understand you. The gag makes it difficult to understand what you're saying. It must be frustrating.

author: cersei lannister
content: We all make our choices. You chose to murder my daughter. You must have felt powerful after you made that choice.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you feel powerful now? I don't sleep very well, not at all really. I lie in bed and I stare at the canopy and imagine ways of killing my enemies. How to destroy Ellaria Sand, the woman who murdered my only daughter. I thought about having Ser Gregor crush your skull the way he did Oberyn's. It would be poetic I suppose but fast. Too fast.

author: cersei lannister
content: I thought about having him crush your daughter's skull.

author: cersei lannister
content: She's so beautiful. The thought of this lovely face cracking open like a duck egg, no, it's just not right.

author: tyene
content: Momma!

author: cersei lannister
content: Qyburn, he's the cleverest man I know. Clever enough to learn what poison you used to murder Myrcella. The long goodbye, was that it?

author: qyburn
content: The Long Farewell.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's the one.

author: cersei lannister
content: How long does the poison take?

author: qyburn
content: Difficult to say. Hours, days, it depends on the subject's constitution.

author: cersei lannister
content: But death is certain?

author: qyburn
content: Oh yes, Your Grace, quite certain.

author: cersei lannister
content: Your daughter will die here in this cell. You will be here watching when she does. You will be here the rest of your days. If you refuse to eat we will force food down your throat. You will live to watch your daughter rot, to watch that beautiful face collapse to bone and dust all the while contemplating the choices you've made.

author: cersei lannister
content: Make sure the guards change the torches every few hours. I don't want her to miss a thing.

author: jaime lannister
content: No.

author: jaime lannister
content: Don't.

author: jaime lannister
content: What are you doing? No one can see us like this ?

author: cersei lannister
content: I am queen of the Seven Kingdoms. I'll do as I please.

author: messenger
content: Forgive me, Your Grace. The visitor from Braavos has arrived.

author: cersei lannister
content: Good. And we'll need fresh sheets for the bed.

author: messenger
content: At once, Your Grace.

author: tycho
content: No, thank you.

author: tycho
content: My condolences, Your Grace, on the death of your son. From all reports he was a fine young man.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Iron Bank didn't send you hear to offer condolences.

author: tycho
content: Condolences and congratulations. You've become the first ruling queen in the Seven Kingdoms. That's quite an accomplishment. The Iron Bank appreciates how you cast off the yoke of superstition freeing the crown from elements that sought to subvert the rule of law.

author: cersei lannister
content: The destruction of the Sept of Baelor was a tragic accident.

author: tycho
content: Indeed. But sometimes tragedies are necessary to restore order and rational leadership.

author: cersei lannister
content: The Iron Bank wants its gold back.

author: tycho
content: Your father never minced words either. But, yes, your debts are considerable. And you are now engaged in a conflict on several fronts. We both know how expensive war can be.

author: cersei lannister
content: And we both know gold wins wars. Your vaults are empty. Your late husbando s profligacy saw to that.

author: tycho
content: Your wealthiest ally is the Tyrells who are now your enemies. You're surrounded on all sides by rivals for the throne.

author: cersei lannister
content: And the Iron Bank wants to bet on a winner.

author: tycho
content: We don't make bets. We invest in endeavors we deem likely to be successful.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's a fancy way of saying bet. The war has already begun. I've drawn first blood. I decapitated the Dornish snake. My armada owns the Narrow Sea.

author: tycho
content: Euron Greyjoy's armada owns the Narrow Sea.

author: cersei lannister
content: Euron Greyjoy is loyal to me.

author: tycho
content: For now. Daenerys Targaryen has three full grown dragons. How well do wooden ships fare against fire breathing dragons?

author: cersei lannister
content: Her dragons might not be as invulnerable as some think. Now, let's talk about the Targaryen girl. You want to invest in her? I'm guessing the Iron Bank invested considerable gold in the slave trade. How are you profits now that Daenerys has freed all the slaves?

author: tycho
content: The slave trade has entered a down turn, it's true.

author: cersei lannister
content: From what I gather she considers herself more of a revolutionary that a monarch. In your experience how do bankers usually fare with revoltionaries?

author: cersei lannister
content: The Lannisters owe the Iron Bank quite a lot of money but Lannisters always pay their debts. Do former slaves or Dothraki or dragons?

author: tycho
content: Your father's daughter indeed.

author: cersei lannister
content: Give me a fortnight. Stay in King's Landing as my honored guest and when you return to Braavos I swear to you my debt will be paid in full.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I came out here to brood over my failure to predict the Greyjoy attack. You're making it difficult. You look a lot better brooding than I do. You make me feel like I'm failing at brooding over failing.

author: jon snow
content: I'm a prisoner on this island.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wouldn't say you're a prisoner on this island. You're free to walk the castle, the beaches, to go wherever you want.

author: jon snow
content: Except to my ship. They took my ship.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wouldn't say we took your ship.

author: jon snow
content: I'm not playing word games with you. The dead are coming for us all.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why don't you figure out what to do about my missing fleet and murdered allies, and I'll figure out what to do about your walking dead men.

author: jon snow
content: It's hard for me to fathom. It really is. If someone told me about the White Walkers and the Night King --

author: jon snow
content: You probably don't believe me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I do actually.

author: jon snow
content: You didn't before. Grumpkins and snarks you called them. Do you remember? You said it was all nonsense.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It was all nonsense. Everybody knew it. But then Mormont saw them and you saw them, and I trust the eyes of an honest man more than I trust what everybody knows.

author: jon snow
content: How do I convince people who don't know me that an enemey they don't believe in is coming to kill them all?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good question.

author: jon snow
content: I know it's a good question. I'm looking for an answer.

author: tyrion lannister
content: People's minds aren't made for problems that large. White Walkers, the Night King, Army of the Dead, it's almost a relief to confront a familiar monster like my sister.

author: jon snow
content: I need to help prepare my people for what's coming. I can't help them from here. I'd like to leave.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It seems unlikely that you became King in the North by giving up that easily.

author: jon snow
content: Everyone told me to learn from my father's mistakes. Don't go south. Don't answer a summons from the Mad King's daughter, a foreign invader. And here I am. A northern fool.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Children are not their fathers, luckily for all of us. And sometimes there's more to foreign invaders than northern fools that meets the eye. Daenerys could have sailed for Westeros long ago but she didn't. Instead she stayed where she was and saved many people from horrible fates some of whom are on this island with us right now. While you're our guest here you might consider asking them what they think of the Mad King's daughter. She protects people from monsters, just as you do. That's why she came here. And she's not about to head north to fight an enemy she's never seen on a word of a man she doesn't know after a single meeting. That's not a reasonable thing to ask.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So do you have anything reasonable to ask?

author: jon snow
content: What do you mean?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Maybe you are a northern fool. I'm asking if there's something I can do to help you.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dragonglass?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes. Volcanic glass, obsidian. He says you have a tremendous amount of it here.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Why are we talking about glass? We just lost two of our allies.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Which is why I was speaking to Jon Snow, a potential ally.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what does the King in the North want with Dragonglass?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Apparently it can be turned into weapons that kill White Walkers and their foot soldiers, or stop them, destroy them. I'm unsure of the nomenclature.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And what do you think of this Army of the Dead and White Walkers and Night Kings?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'd very much like to believe that Jon Snow is wrong, but a wise man once said that you should never believe a thing simply because you want to believe it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Which wise man said this?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't remember.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Are you trying to present your own statements as ancient wisdom?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I would never do that...to you. The reason I believe Jon Snow is because he's here. All of his advisors would have told him not to come. I would have told him not to come, yet he's here anyway. You don't have to believe him. Let him mine the Dragonglass. If he's wrong it's worthless. You didn't even know it was here. It's nothing to you. Give him something by giving him nothing. Take a step toward a more productive relationship with a possible ally. Keep him occupied while we focus on the task at hand. Casterly Rock.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What was that Ser Davos said about taking a knife in the heart for his people? Did you notice that?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You must allow them their flights of fancy. It's dreary in the north.

author: jon snow
content: Amazing thing to see.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I named them for my brothers Vicerys and Rhaegon. They're both gone now.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You lost two brothers as well?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: People thought dragons were gone forever but here they are. Perhaps we should all be examining what we think we know.

author: jon snow
content: You've been talking to Tyrion?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He is my Hand.

author: jon snow
content: He enjoys talking.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We all enjoy what we're good at.

author: jon snow
content: I don't.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You know I'm not going to let Cersei stay on the Iron Throne.

author: jon snow
content: I never expected that you would.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And I haven't changed my mind about which kingdoms belong to the throne.

author: jon snow
content: I haven't either.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will allow you to mine the Dragonglass and forge weapons from it. Any resources or men you need I will provide for you.

author: jon snow
content: Thank you.

author: jon snow
content: So you believe me then about the Night King and the Army of the Dead?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You better get to work, Jon Snow.

author: sansa stark
content: How much do we have?

author: wolkan
content: 4,000 bushels, My Lady.

author: sansa stark
content: What does that mean?

author: yohn
content: For the current occupants of the castle it's enough food for a year, perhaps more.

author: sansa stark
content: What's the longest winter in the past 100 years?

author: wolkan
content: I'm not entirely certain. I'll check Maester Llewyn's records. He kept a copy of every raven scroll.

author: sansa stark
content: You're telling me we don't have enough food, especially not if the armies of the north come back to defend Winterfell.

author: wolkan
content: No, My Lady, most likely not.

author: sansa stark
content: We must prepare for that eventuality. Every direction the threat comes from, this is the best place to be. We need to start building up our grain stores with regular shipments from every keep in the north. If we don't use it by winter's end we'll give it back to them, but if the entire north has to flee to Winterfell there won't be enough time to bring wagonloads of grain with them.

author: yohn
content: Very wise, My Lady.

author: sansa stark
content: Maester Wolkan, you'll see to it?

author: sansa stark
content: Are they covering those breastplates in leather?

author: yohn
content: No, My Lady.

author: sansa stark
content: Well, shouldn't they be once the real cold comes?

author: yohn
content: They should indeed. Pardon me, My Lady.

author: yohn
content: You there, why isn't there leather on these?

author: petyr baelish
content: Command suits you. The northerns are all facing north worried about the threat beyond the wall.

author: sansa stark
content: So they should be.

author: petyr baelish
content: I know Cersei better than anyone here. If you turn your back on her --

author: sansa stark
content: You don't know Cersei better than anyone here.

author: petyr baelish
content: I only meant to say --

author: sansa stark
content: That the woman who murdered my mother, father and brother is dangerous? Thank you for your wise council.

author: petyr baelish
content: One of two things will happen. Either the dead will defeat the living, in which case all our troubles come to an end. Or life will win out. And what then?

author: petyr baelish
content: Don't fight in the north or the south. Fight every battle everywhere always in your mind. Everyone is your enemy, everyone is your friend, every possible series of events is happening all at once. Live that way and nothing will surprise you. Everything that happens will be something that you've seen before.

author: guard
content: Lady Sansa, at the gate.

author: bran stark
content: Hello, Sansa.

author: sansa stark
content: I wish Jon was here.

author: bran stark
content: Yes. I need to speak to him.

author: sansa stark
content: Your father's last living true born son. You're Lord of Winterfell.

author: bran stark
content: I can never be the Lord of Winterfell. I can never be lord of anything. I'm the three-eyed raven.

author: sansa stark
content: I don't know what that means.

author: bran stark
content: It's difficult to explain.

author: sansa stark
content: Try, please, for me.

author: bran stark
content: It means I can see everything. Everything that's ever happened to everyone. Everything that's happening right now. It's all pieces, fragments. I need to learn to see better. When the long night comes again I need to be ready.

author: sansa stark
content: How do you know all of this?

author: bran stark
content: The three-eyed raven taught me.

author: sansa stark
content: I thought you were the three-eyed raven.

author: bran stark
content: I told you it's difficult to explain.

author: sansa stark
content: Bran --

author: bran stark
content: I'm sorry for all that's happened to you. I'm sorry it had to happen here at our home. It was so beautiful that night. Snow falling just like now. And you were so beautiful in your white wedding dress.

author: sansa stark
content: I have to go back inside, Bran.

author: bran stark
content: I'll stay a bit longer.

author: marwyn
content: Hmm.

author: marwyn
content: Hmm. Does it hurt?

author: jorah mormont
content: A bit. Less than before.

author: marwyn
content: The infection no longer appears to be active.

author: marwyn
content: Unusual. Unlikely. One could almost be forgiven for thinking the entire upper layer of diseased skin was debrided and the underlying region treated with some sort of ointment.

author: jorah mormont
content: I don't know anything about that. I just started feeling better. I assumed it was the rest that did it.

author: jorah mormont
content: And the climate.

author: marwyn
content: The climate? You're free to go, Ser. This chamber is needed for the infectious, which you are no longer.

author: marwyn
content: Tarley, I'd like to speak with you in my study this evening.

author: jorah mormont
content: How bad is it?

author: sam tarly
content: I suppose I'll find out this evening.

author: sam tarly
content: Where will you go?

author: jorah mormont
content: I surrendered to this sickness the moment I first saw it. I knew it would kill me or I'd kill myself before it could. Daenerys Stormborn convinced me otherwise. The only place for me is with her.

author: jorah mormont
content: I owe my life to her and you.

author: sam tarly
content: Your father saved me more than once. It's the least I could do.

author: jorah mormont
content: Perhaps our paths will cross again?

author: sam tarly
content: I hope they do.

author: marwyn
content: You treated him?

author: sam tarly
content: Yes.

author: marwyn
content: Who told you to treat him?

author: sam tarly
content: No one.

author: marwyn
content: Who forbade you or anyone to attempt to treat him?

author: sam tarly
content: I seem to remember you.

author: marwyn
content: But you treated him anyway?

author: sam tarly
content: I did.

author: marwyn
content: I forbade it because it's dangerous and rarely successful. Especially on someone of that age. You could have infected yourself and others. You could have devastated the entire Citadel. But you didn't. It's a meticulous, difficult procedure. Many maesters whose chains are heavy with healing links have attempted it and failed. But you succeeded. How?

author: sam tarly
content: I read the books and followed the instructions.

author: marwyn
content: That man is alive because of you. You should be proud.

author: sam tarly
content: Thank you, Archmaester.

author: marwyn
content: Come here.

author: marwyn
content: All these manuscripts and scrolls and rotting away. I need you to make copies of them.

author: marwyn
content: You were expecting a reward? Your reward is not being immediately expelled from the Citadel. You'd better get started. Be mindful of the paper mites. They like flesh as well.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We need to find Euron Greyjoy's fleet and sink it.

author: varys
content: Your Grace, he's already destroyed a good portion of our fleet. To send our remaining ships after him --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not talking about sending our ships after him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But you'll have to go yourself. Euron's ships could be anywhere or in more than one place. You'd be flying around the open seas alone for who knows how long.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I wouldn't be alone. I'd have Drogon, Vicerion and Rhaegal. What can anyone do to them?

author: missandei
content: They can still do something to you. It only takes one arrow.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's too great a risk. You're too important.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What about Casterly Rock?

author: varys
content: The Unsullied will be there soon.

author: missandei
content: And what will they face?

author: varys
content: A difficult situation. They know we're coming.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes. Cersei believes my sole purpose in life is to destroy House Lannister. She will be ready.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No one has ever taken the rock.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Lannister army is still the army my father built. Well trained and well provisioned. 10,000 men at least. They will see us coming.

author: tyrion lannister
content: They will be ready.

author: man
content: Draw! Loose!

author: tyrion lannister
content: The gates of Casterly Rock are impregnable.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The fight up the walls will be hard. We'll be at a disadvantage. Many men will die.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Interesting thing about my father. He built our house up from near ruin. He built our army. He built Casterly Rock as we know it, but he didn't build the sewers. That was beneath him. So he gave the job to the lowest person he could find. Me. He was right. I was low. The company I kept low, women mostly. They weren't welcome at the Rock. Father disapproved of that sort of behavior. I couldn't walk them through the front gates. I couldn't have them in my chambers. So in the process of building the sewers I threw in something for myself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It was a passage that began by the sea and ended beneath one of the main guard towers.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No better place for low pursuits. Casterly Rock, the impregnable fortress.

author: tyrion lannister
content: As a good friend of mine once said, "give me 10 good men and I'll impregnate the bitch."

author: tyrion lannister
content: And so it begins. They will face the bulk of the Lannister forces. They will be outnumbered. They will have less armor and fewer weapons.

author: tyrion lannister
content: But as my sister's armies fights for her, the Unsullied will be fighting for something greater. They will be fighting for freedom and the person who gave it to them. They will be fighting for you. And that is why they will triump.

author: unsullied
content: There are none left.

author: grey worm
content: There are supposed to be more than this. Many more.

author: grey worm
content: Where are they? Where are the rest of the Lannisters?

author: olenna tyrell
content: It's done?

author: jaime lannister
content: It is.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And now the rains weep for our whores. Did we fight well?

author: jaime lannister
content: I suppose as well as can be expected.

author: olenna tyrell
content: It was never our forte. Golden roses indeed. Your brother and his new queen thought you would be defending Casterly Rock.

author: jaime lannister
content: The truth is Casterly Rock isn't worth much anymore. Well, it is to me. My fond childhood memories won't keep Cersei on the throne.

author: olenna tyrell
content: So you'll just let them take it?

author: jaime lannister
content: For now. They won't be able to hold it. Euron Greyjoy's navy burned their ships, we emptied the larders before we left. Eventually they'll be forced to abandon their position and march all the way across Westeros.

author: olenna tyrell
content: And you took your army, your real army, and went where they weren't?

author: jaime lannister
content: As Robb Stark did to me at Whispering Wood. There are always lessons in failures.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Yes. You must be very wise by now.

author: jaime lannister
content: My father always said I was a slow learner.

author: olenna tyrell
content: If he was so clever why didn't he take Highgarden the moment your gold mines ran dry? I suppose I'll be able to ask him myself soon enough. No more learning from my mistakes, eh? How will you do it? With that sword?

author: olenna tyrell
content: That was Joffrey's sword, wasn't it? Not that he ever used it. What did he call it?

author: jaime lannister
content: Widow's Wail.

author: olenna tyrell
content: He really was a cunt, wasn't he? I did unspeakable things to protect my family, or watched them being done on my orders. I never lost a night's sleep over them. They were necessary. And whatever I imagined necessary for the safety of House Tyrell I did. But your sister has done things I wasn't capable of imagining. That was my prize mistake, a failure of imagination. She's a monster, you do know that?

author: jaime lannister
content: To you, sure. To others as well. But after we've won and there's no one left to oppose us, the people living peaceful in the world she built, do you really think they'll wring their hands over the way she built it?

author: olenna tyrell
content: You love her. You really do love her. You poor fool. She'll be the end of you.

author: jaime lannister
content: Possibly. Not much to be gained from discussing it with you though, is there?

author: olenna tyrell
content: What better person to discuss it with? What better guarantee could you have that the things you say will never leave this room? But perhaps you're right. If she's driven you this far it's gone beyond your control.

author: jaime lannister
content: Yes, it has.

author: olenna tyrell
content: She's a disease. I regret my role in spreading it. You will too.

author: jaime lannister
content: I think we're done here.

author: olenna tyrell
content: How will it happen?

author: jaime lannister
content: Cersei had several ideas. Whipping you through the streets and beheading you in front of the Red Keep. Flaying you alive and hanging you from the walls of King's Landing. I talked her out of those.

author: olenna tyrell
content: Will there be pain?

author: jaime lannister
content: No. I made sure of that.

author: olenna tyrell
content: That's good.

author: olenna tyrell
content: I'd hate to die like your son clawing at my neck, foam and bile spilling from my mouth, eyes blood red, skin purple. It must have been horrible for you as a Kingsguard, as a father. It was horrible enough for me. A shocking scene. Not at all what I intended. You see, I'd never seen the posion work before. Tell Cersei. I want her to know it was me.

author: end
content: CREDITS

author: jaime lannister
content: Halt that wagon!

author: jaime lannister
content: opens the carriage. It is filled with gold bars and coins. He picks up a large sack and hands it to BRONN.

author: bronn
content: You just won the biggest prize in the world. What could you possibly have to be upset about? Come on. You can tell me. Queen of Thorns give you one last prick in the balls before saying goodbye?

author: jaime lannister
content: I'll save my confessions for the High Septon.

author: bronn
content: There is no more High Septon.

author: jaime lannister
content: No, there isn't, is there?

author: bronn
content: There is still the question of my prize.

author: jaime lannister
content: is putting a padlock on the wagon bearing the gold. He stops and turns to BRONN.

author: jaime lannister
content: That's a lot of money I just gave you.

author: bronn
content: It's not a castle.

author: bronn
content: turns and points to Highgarden.

author: bronn
content: How about that one? It's available.

author: jaime lannister
content: You don't want Highgarden.

author: bronn
content: I beg to differ.

author: jaime lannister
content: We're at war. Daenerys Targaryen could come take it back the day after you move in. Besides, think of the upkeep. The more you own, the more it weighs you down.

author: bronn
content: Oh, is that why you're so fucking glum, eh? All your new riches weighing you down?

author: jaime lannister
content: pounds on the back of the carriage and the horses start trotting.

author: jaime lannister
content: They're not mine. The gold belongs to the Iron Bank. We pay our debts.

author: bronn
content: Right. Just not to me.

author: jaime lannister
content: Bronn of the Blackwater, formerly of whatever nameless shit heap you're from with a saddlebag full of gold complaining about not getting paid. When we win this war all the castles in the Seven Kingdoms will be yours to choose from with no one left to take them away from you.

author: bronn
content: Yes, I'm sure Queen Cersei's reign will be quiet and peaceful.

author: jaime lannister
content: Stranger things have happened.

author: bronn
content: Like what?

author: randyll
content: TARLEY and his son DICKON come riding up on horseback. RANDYLL addresses JAIME.

author: randyll
content: The granaries are being emptied and loaded into wagons, My Lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: The current harvest?

author: dickon
content: We have teams of men collecting it and more farmers in the Reach.

author: jaime lannister
content: looks over to BRONN.

author: jaime lannister
content: Ser Bronn, will you accompany the Tarleys and help them accelerate this process?

author: bronn
content: I'm not much for shoveling weight.

author: jaime lannister
content: No, but motivating reluctant farmers to hand over their harvest, I've heard you guys have a real talent for that.

author: randyll
content: My Lord.

author: dickon
content: My Lord.

author: randyll
content: DICKON and BRONN break away from the Lannister army and ride into the distance. Horse drawn carts are carrying spoils from Highgarden and Lannister men are marching down the road.

author: cersei lannister
content: and TYCHO NESTORIS from the Iron Bank of Braavos are sitting having a discussion.

author: tycho
content: I must say, I don't think the Iron Bank has ever had a debt of this magnitude repaid in a single installment. I always considered your father a very effective and efficient man, but you appear to be redefining those terms entirely.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're too kind, My Lord.

author: tycho
content: I am neither kind, nor a lord, Your Grace. I am merely an instrument of the institution I represent, its wellbeing is a matter of arithmetic, not sentiment. And the current arithmetic is outstanding. The gold --

author: cersei lannister
content: Is on its way. My brother is supervising its transportation himself.

author: tycho
content: Some at the Iron Bank will be disappointed. They've grown rather fond of your interest payments.

author: cersei lannister
content: We must devise a way to raise their spirits.

author: tycho
content: Yes. Perhaps we could be of assistance in some current venture.

author: cersei lannister
content: My only venture at the moment is reestablishing control over this continent and every person on it.

author: tycho
content: I see a great deal of potential in that venture. I imagine that it would require outside investment?

author: cersei lannister
content: It will indeed. I need to expand my armies, my navies. My hand, Qyburn, had made overtures to the Golden Company in Essos.

author: tycho
content: I know them well. They've helped us recover significant sums from parties who had fallen into deep arrears.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's good to hear. I too would like them to recover some things that belong to me.

author: tycho
content: Rest assured, Your Grace, you can count on the Iron Bank's support, as soon as the gold arrives.

author: bran stark
