content: is sitting in a wheelchair. PETER BAELISH is sitting next to him. BAELISH unsheathes a Valyrian steel dagger and shows it to BRAN. It's the same dagger used in the attempt to assassinate BRAN years ago.

author: petyr baelish
content: This is for you.

author: petyr baelish
content: flips the knife in his hand and extends it towards BRAN.

author: petyr baelish
content: The last man who wielded it meant to cut your throat, but your mother fought him off.

author: bran stark
content: reaches out and takes the knife, turning it and looking it over carefully.

author: petyr baelish
content: The other dagger, the one that took her life, I would have stopped that dagger with my own heart if I could have. I wasn't there for her when she needed me most. But I am here for her now. To do what she would have done, to protect her children. Anything I can do for you, Brandon, you need only ask.

author: bran stark
content: Do you know who this belonged to?

author: petyr baelish
content: No. That very question was what started the War of the Five Kings. In a way, that dagger made you what you are today. Forced from your home, driven out to the wilds beyond the Wall. I imagine you've seen things most men wouldn't believe.

author: petyr baelish
content: hands the sheath of the knife to BRAN. BRAN slides the knife into the sheath.

author: petyr baelish
content: To go through all of that and make your way home again only to find such chaos in the world, I can only imagine --

author: bran stark
content: Chaos is a ladder.

author: bran stark
content: is staring at BAELISH. BAELISH stops speaking. The door opens and Meera appears.

author: petyr baelish
content: I'm sorry to have disturbed you, Lord Stark.

author: petyr baelish
content: stands up to leave.

author: bran stark
content: I'm not Lord Stark.

author: petyr baelish
content: bows and walks past Meera and closes the door.

author: meera
content: notices BRAN sitting in a wheelchair.

author: meera
content: What's that?

author: bran stark
content: Maester Wolkan built it for me so I can move around more easily.

author: meera
content: It's a very good idea.

author: bran stark
content: You're leaving?

author: meera
content: I don't want to leave you, but when they come I need to be with my family. And you're safe, safe as anyone can be now. You don't need me anymore.

author: bran stark
content: No, I don't.

author: meera
content: That's all you've got to say?

author: bran stark
content: Thank you.

author: meera
content: Thank you?

author: bran stark
content: For helping me.

author: meera
content: My brother died for you. Hodor and Summer died for you. I almost died for you. Bran!

author: bran stark
content: I'm not really, not anymore. I remember what it felt like to be Brandon Stark, but I remember so much else now.

author: meera
content: begins to cry.

author: meera
content: You died in that cave.

author: meera
content: turns to walk out the door. She hesitates looking at BRAN, then walks out.

author: arya stark
content: approaches the main gate on foot. Two guards are huddled by a brazier getting warm. There's indistinct chatter. One of the men notice ARYA walking to the gate and approach her.

author: man
content: Hey, oh. Where are you going?

author: arya stark
content: In there. I live here.

author: man
content: Fuck off.

author: arya stark
content: I'm Arya Stark. This is my home.

author: man
content: Arya Stark is dead.

author: arya stark
content: Send for Maester Llewyn or Ser Rodrick. They'll tell you who I am.

author: man
content: There's no Rodrick here.

author: man
content: Maester's name is Wolkan.

author: arya stark
content: Go ask Jon Snow then, the King in the North. He's my brother

author: man
content: He's a thousand miles away.

author: man
content: It's cold. We're busy. So, you know, best fuck off.

author: man
content: Mm-hmm.

author: arya stark
content: If Jon Snow is gone who is in charge of Winterfell?

author: man
content: The Lady of Winterfell, Lady Stark.

author: arya stark
content: Which Lady Stark?

author: man
content: You tell us. You're the one impersonating her sister.

author: arya stark
content: Tell Sansa her sister is home.

author: man
content: Lady Sansa is too busy to waster her breath on you, just like us. So for the last time, fuck off.

author: man
content: 1 goes to grab Arya but she easily dodges out of his grasp.

author: arya stark
content: I'm getting into this castle one way or another. If I'm not who I say I am, I won't last long. But if I am, and Sansa finds out that you turned me away...

author: arya stark
content: keeps glancing at the men. They look uneasy. They bring her inside of the gate. They indicate towards a cart near the entrance.

author: man
content: You sit there. Right there. Don't move.

author: man
content: Go tell Lady Stark. I'll watch her.

author: arya stark
content: is glancing around Winterfell. Men are working building tools and cutting wood. ARYA looks over and sees a Winterfell flag sigil hanging from the wall. The two guards are still arguing.

author: man
content: You tell her.

author: man
content: I'm not.

author: man
content: Because if you don't I'll hit you right in the fucking face as hard as I can.

author: man
content: We told her to wait. We were standing right next to her.

author: sansa stark
content: sighs.

author: man
content: When we turned around she had gone, My Lady. She was nothing. Some winter town girl.

author: man
content: She comes in asking for Ser Rodrick and Maester Llewyn.

author: man
content: Don't trouble yourself over it, My Lady. We'll find her.

author: sansa stark
content: You don't have to. I know where she is.

author: arya stark
content: is standing look at a statue of Ned Stark holding his sword. ARYA hears a sound and turns to see SANSA approaching. SANSA stops when she sees ARYA.

author: arya stark
content: Do I have to call you Lady Stark now?

author: sansa stark
content: hesitates for a moment.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes.

author: sansa stark
content: begins smiling then walking towards ARYA. SANSA reaches out and hugs ARYA.

author: sansa stark
content: You shouldn't have run from the guards.

author: arya stark
content: I didn't run. You need better guards.

author: sansa stark
content: smirks at ARYA.

author: arya stark
content: It suits you, Lady Stark. Jon left you in charge?

author: sansa stark
content: He did. I hope he comes back soon. I remember how happy he was to see me. When he sees you, his heart will probably stop.

author: arya stark
content: That doesn't look like him. It should have been carved by someone who knew his face.

author: sansa stark
content: Everyone who knew his face is dead.

author: arya stark
content: We're not.

author: arya stark
content: turns to face SANSA.

author: arya stark
content: They say you killed Joffrey. Did you?

author: sansa stark
content: I wish I had.

author: arya stark
content: Me too. I was angry when I heard someone else had done it. However long my list got he was always first.

author: sansa stark
content: Your list?

author: arya stark
content: Of people I'm going to kill.

author: sansa stark
content: begins to laugh. ARYA joins her.

author: sansa stark
content: How did you get back to Winterfell?

author: arya stark
content: It's a long story. I imagine yours is too.

author: sansa stark
content: Yes. It's not a very pleasant one.

author: arya stark
content: Mine neither, but our stories aren't over yet.

author: sansa stark
content: No, they're not.

author: sansa stark
content: Arya, Bran's home too.

author: arya stark
content: smiles and looks at SANSA. SANSA doesn't smile back. The smile fades from ARYA's face.

author: bran stark
content: is sitting next to the Weirwood tree. SANSA and ARYA approach. BRAN turns to look at them. BRAN begins speaking to ARYA.

author: bran stark
content: You came home.

author: arya stark
content: steps forward and throws her arms around BRAN. SANSA smiles in the background. ARYA lets go and steps back.

author: bran stark
content: I saw you at the crossroads.

author: arya stark
content: You saw me?

author: bran stark
content: I see quite a lot now.

author: sansa stark
content: Bran has visions.

author: bran stark
content: I thought you might go to King's Landing.

author: arya stark
content: So did I.

author: sansa stark
content: Why would you go back there?

author: bran stark
content: Cersei is on her list of names.

author: arya stark
content: stares at BRAN. ARYA turns to look at SANSA.

author: sansa stark
content: Who else is on your list?

author: arya stark
content: Most of them are dead already.

author: bran stark
content: produces the Valyrian dagger that BAELISH gave him and unsheathes it.

author: arya stark
content: Where did you get this?

author: bran stark
content: Littlefinger gave it to me.

author: arya stark
content: Littlefinger, he's here?

author: arya stark
content: turns to look at SANSA.

author: sansa stark
content: He's declared for House Stark.

author: sansa stark
content: steps up closer to BRAN and speaks to him.

author: sansa stark
content: Why would he give you a dagger?

author: bran stark
content: He thought I'd want it.

author: sansa stark
content: Why?

author: bran stark
content: Because it was meant to kill me.

author: sansa stark
content: The cutthroat after your fall?

author: arya stark
content: Why would a cutthroat have a Valyrian steel dagger?

author: bran stark
content: Someone very wealthy wanted me dead.

author: sansa stark
content: He's not a generous man. He wouldn't give you anything unless he thought he was getting something back.

author: bran stark
content: It doesn't matter.

author: sansa stark
content: What do you mean it doesn't matter?

author: bran stark
content: I don't want it.

author: bran stark
content: holds the knife out to ARYA. ARYA looks at BRAN.

author: arya stark
content: Are you sure? It's Valyrian steel.

author: bran stark
content: It's wasted on a cripple.

author: arya stark
content: looks down at the dagger. She steps forward and takes it from BRAN.

author: arya stark
content: is pushing BRAN in his wheelchair and SANSA is next to them. The Stark children are walking back through the gate of Winterfell. Men are milling around doing various jobs. BRIENNE and PODRICK see the Stark children all back at Winterfell together.

author: podrick
content: Catelyn Stark would be proud. You kept your vow.

author: brienne
content: I did next to nothing.

author: podrick
content: You're too hard on yourself, My Lady.

author: brienne
content: I'm not a --

author: brienne
content: pauses for a moment.

author: brienne
content: Thank you, Podrick.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: and MISSANDEI are walking along a path outside of Dragonstone followed by members of the Queensguard.

author: missandei
content: Your Grace, there's still no word from the Unsullied.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Soon. They will come back to me.

author: missandei
content: He better.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: stops and turns to look at MISSANDEI. She then continues walking.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What happened?

author: missandei
content: begins smirking.

author: missandei
content: Many things.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Many things?

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: looks at MISSANDEI then her Queensguard. She speaks in Valyrian and motions to her guard to stand down.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It's all right.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: descends the stairs with MISSANDEI and they begin walking with JON. They walk along the beach until they reach a cave. DAVOS is waiting for them with a lit torch.

author: jon snow
content: I wanted you to see it before we start hacking it to bits.

author: jon snow
content: leads DAENERYS and MISSANDEI into the cave. He lights a brazier and illuminates the Dragonglass along the walls. He continues walking deeper into the cave.

author: jon snow
content: So this is it, all we'll ever need.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: is looking up at the walls of Dragonglass.

author: jon snow
content: There is something else I want to show your, Your Grace.

author: jon snow
content: and DAENERYS go to a further chamber in the cave. There are murals painted on the walls of Dragonglass.

author: jon snow
content: The Children of the Forest made these.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: When?

author: jon snow
content: A very long time ago.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They were right here standing where we're standing before there were Targaryens or Starks or Lannisters. Maybe even before there were men.

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: stops looking at the walls and turns to look at JON. JON walks to another wall and begins to examine the murals. The murals depict Children of the Forest and the First Men standing together.

author: jon snow
content: They were here together the Children and the First Men.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Doing what? Fighting each other?

author: jon snow
content: takes DAENERYS by the arm and swings her torch to another part of the wall. There is a mural of the Night King and White Walkers.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They fought together against their common enemy. Despite their differences, despite their suspicions, together. We need to do the same if we're going to survive.

author: jon snow
content: and DAENERYS look back at the wall with the Night King.

author: jon snow
content: Because the enemy is real. It's always been real.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns to look at JON.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And you say you can't defeat them without my armies and my dragons?

author: jon snow
content: No, I don't think I can.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: steps forward closer to JON.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I will fight for you. I will fight for the north...when you bend the knee.

author: jon snow
content: My people won't accept a southern ruler, not after everything they've suffered.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: steps even closer to JON until they're face to face.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They will if their king does. They chose you to lead them. They chose you to protect them. Isn't their survival more important than your pride?

author: jon snow
content: and DAENERYS, DAVOS and MISSANDEI are walking out of the cave. As they exit TYRION and VARYS are standing on the beach awaiting them. DAENERYS begins addressing Tyrion.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What is it?

author: tyrion lannister
content: We took Casterly Rock.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: That's very good to hear.

author: tyrion lannister
content: and VARYS look at each other. They aren't eager to deliver the bad news.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Isn't it?

author: davos
content: You'll want to discuss this amongst yourselves. Perhaps --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will stay. All my allies are gone. They've been taken from me while I've been sitting here on this island.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We still have the largest army.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who won't be able to eat because Cersei has taken all the food from the Reach.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Call Grey Worm and the Unsullied back. We still have enough ships to carry the Dothraki to the mainland. Commit to the blockade of King's Landing. We have a plan. It's still the right plan.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: stops walking, turns and speaks harshly to Tyrion.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The right plan? Your strategy has lost us Dorne, the Iron Islands and the Reach.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If I've underestimated our enemies --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Our enemies? Your family, you mean. Perhaps you don't want to hurt them after all.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: begins looking out to the ocean. Three dragons are flying in the sky over the water.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Enough with the clever plans.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns back and looks at TYRION.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I have three large dragons. I'm going to fly them to the Red Keep.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We've discussed this.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: My enemies are in the Red Keep. What kind of a queen am I if I'm not willing to risk my life to fight them?

author: tyrion lannister
content: A smart one.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: looks over to JON SNOW.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: What do you think I should do?

author: jon snow
content: I would never presume to --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm at war. I'm losing.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: begins walking close to JON.

author: jon snow
content: looks over the ocean at the dragons flying.

author: jon snow
content: I never thought that dragons would exist again. No one did. The people who follow you know that you made something impossible happen. Maybe that helps them believe that you can make other impossible things happen. Build a world that's different from the shit one they've always known.

author: jon snow
content: glances back towards the dragons.

author: jon snow
content: But if you use them to melt castles and burn cities, you're not different. You're just more of the same.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: looks back out to her dragons flying along the water.

author: brienne
content: and PODRICK are sparring. BRIENNE kicks PODS foot out from under him and he lands face first in the dirt.

author: brienne
content: Don't lunge.

author: podrick
content: pushes himself back up and picks up his sword. PODRICK attacks again. Brienne blocks his blows and kicks his foot out again.

author: brienne
content: Don't go where your enemy leads you.

author: arya stark
content: is watching the sparring session from across the courtyard. She begins to approach Brienne.

author: brienne
content: Up.

author: brienne
content: begins striking at PODRICK while he blocks her blows. BRIENNE hits PODRICK in the stomach with the hilt of her sword and PODRICK lands on the ground.

author: brienne
content: And don't --

author: arya stark
content: Don't fight someone like her in the first place.

author: podrick
content: stands up and retrieves his sword. ARYA walks closer to speak to BRIENNE.

author: brienne
content: Nice sword. Very nice dagger.

author: arya stark
content: looks down at the Valyrian dagger and unsheathes it. She approaches BRIENNE flipping the knife several times in her fingers. BRIENNE takes the dagger and examines it.

author: sansa stark
content: and BAELISH are walking along the upper section of the courtyard having a conversation.

author: sansa stark
content: If they haven't contributed the right amount of grain to the stores then I'm afraid they'll have to make due with --

author: sansa stark
content: sees ARYA in the courtyard speaking with BRIENNE and stops to watch her.

author: arya stark
content: It's been awhile since I've trained.

author: brienne
content: I can go and find the Master of Arms for you, My Lady.

author: arya stark
content: He didn't beat the hound. You did. I want to train with you.

author: brienne
content: chuckles.

author: arya stark
content: You swore to serve both of my mother's daughters, didn't you?

author: brienne
content: nods her head in agreement.

author: brienne
content: Move aside, Podrick.

author: podrick
content: backs away. ARYA draws her sword, Needle.

author: brienne
content: You can't use that, My Lady. It's too small.

author: arya stark
content: I won't cut you. Don't worry.

author: brienne
content: smirks and raises her sword to a fighting posture.

author: brienne
content: I'll try not to.

author: brienne
content: strikes at ARYA who quickly sidesteps and parries the attack. BRIENNE attacks again and ARYA sidesteps, dodges multiple strikes and parries BRIENNE while smiling. ARYA strikes at BRIENNE and hits her hand causing BRIENNE to flinch and lose her two-handed grip on her sword. BRIENNE regains composure and starts to circle ARYA. BAELISH and SANSA are still watching from the upper balcony. ARYA is waiting for an attack with her sword behind her back. BRIENNE strikes and ARYA blocks her attacks, spins and stabs behind her back and hits BRIENNE in the knee causing BRIENNE's sword to strike the dirt. BRIENNE kicks ARYA in the stomach and sends ARYA to the ground. ARYA quickly gets back to her feet. BRIENNE overpowers ARYA and ARYA drops her sword on the ground. BRIENNE strikes again but ARYA dodges, draws her Valyrian dagger and puts it near BRIENNE's neck. BRIENNE and ARYA both stop fighting and sheathe their weapons smiling.

author: brienne
content: Who taught you to do that?

author: arya stark
content: No one.

author: arya stark
content: collects her sword. SANSA walks away. BAELISH remains on the balcony staring at ARYA who looks up at him. BAELISH bows to ARYA and walks away.

author: jon snow
content: and DAVOS are walking along the paths outside of Dragonstone having a discussion.

author: davos
content: What do you think of her?

author: jon snow
content: Who?

author: davos
content: sighs

author: davos
content: I believe you know of whom I speak.

author: jon snow
content: I think she has a good heart.

author: davos
content: A good heart? I've noticed you starring at that good heart.

author: jon snow
content: There's no time for that. I saw the Night King, Davos. I looked into his eyes. How many men do we have in the north to fight him? 10,000? Less?

author: davos
content: Fewer.

author: jon snow
content: What?

author: davos
content: and JON near the end of the path. MISSANDEI is standing along the path looking at the ocean.

author: davos
content: Speaking of good hearts, Missandei of Naarth.

author: missandei
content: turns to looks at DAVOS and JON.

author: missandei
content: Ser Davos, Lord Snow.

author: davos
content: King Snow, isn't it? No? That doesn't sound right. King Jon?

author: jon snow
content: It doesn't matter.

author: missandei
content: Forgive me, but may I ask a question?

author: jon snow
content: Of course.

author: missandei
content: Your name is Jon Snow, but your father's name was Ned Stark?

author: jon snow
content: I'm a bastard. My mother and father weren't married.

author: davos
content: Is the custom different in Naarth?

author: missandei
content: We don't have marriage in Naarth so the concept of a bastard doesn't exist.

author: davos
content: The sounds liberating.

author: jon snow
content: Why did you leave your homeland?

author: missandei
content: I was stolen away by slavers.

author: jon snow
content: I'm sorry.

author: davos
content: If I may, how did a slave girl come to advise Daenerys Targaryen?

author: missandei
content: She bought me from my master and set me free.

author: davos
content: That was good of her. Of course you're serving her now, aren't you?

author: missandei
content: I serve my queen because I want to serve my queen. Because I believe in her.

author: jon snow
content: And if you wanted to sail home to Naarth tomorrow --

author: missandei
content: Then she would give me a ship and wish me good fortune.

author: jon snow
content: You believe that?

author: missandei
content: I know it. All of us who came with her from Essos, we believe in her. She's not our queen because she's the daughter of some king we never knew. She's the queen we chose.

author: davos
content: You'll forgive me if I switch sides.

author: jon snow
content: notices a single ship sailing into the bay. It has a kraken sigil. MISSANDEI turns to look.

author: jon snow
content: Is that a Greyjoy ship?

author: theon greyjoy
content: GREYJOY and other Iron Born are pulling their landing boat onto the beach wading through the surf. They pull the boat onto the sand. JON SNOW, MISSANDEI, DAVOS and Dothraki guards are waiting to meet them. JON sees THEON and both men freeze and stare at each other. JON steps forward towards THEON.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Jon. I didn't know you were here.

author: theon greyjoy
content: steps closer to JON.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Sansa, is she all right?

author: jon snow
content: grabs THEON by his shirt and pulls him face to face.

author: jon snow
content: What you did for her is the only reason I'm not killing you.

author: jon snow
content: releases THEON.

author: davos
content: We heard your uncle attacked your fleet. We thought you were dead.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I should be.

author: davos
content: Your sister?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Euron has her. I came to ask the queen to help get her back.

author: jon snow
content: The queen is gone.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Where did she go?

author: randyll
content: All of the gold is safely through the gates of King's Landing.

author: jaime lannister
content: Good.

author: randyll
content: We need to get the last of these wagons over the Blackwater Rush before nightfall. If the head of the line is ambushed, the tail will never be able to reinforce in time.

author: jaime lannister
content: We are stretched a bit thin.

author: randyll
content: With your permission, flogging stragglers has a marked effect on mobility.

author: jaime lannister
content: Let's give them fair warning first. These men fought well at Highgarden.

author: randyll
content: is clearly disappointed. He turns and rides off back to the line of soldiers. JAIME and BRONN exchange glances, then follow RANDYLL. BRONN and JAIME are riding through the ranks. DICKON TARLEY sees JAIME and starts a conversation.

author: dickon
content: Ser Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: Rickon.

author: dickon
content: Dickon.

author: bronn
content: openly laughs in DICKON's face and looks at JAIME.

author: jaime lannister
content: I hear you fought bravely at Highgarden. Your first battle?

author: dickon
content: nods his head in agreement.

author: jaime lannister
content: And?

author: dickon
content: It was glorious.

author: bronn
content: Come on. Your father's not here.

author: dickon
content: All my life we've been pledged to House Tyrell. I knew some of those men. I hunted with them.

author: jaime lannister
content: They didn't deserve to die. But Lady Olenna chose to betray the queen and support the Targaryen girl. So here we are.

author: dickon
content: I didn't expect it to smell like that.

author: bronn
content: Men shit themselves when they die. Didn't they teach you that at fancy lad school?

author: jaime lannister
content: looks over at BRONN

author: bronn
content: Well, I learned it when I was 5.

author: bronn
content: pauses and strains to hear a noise far in the distance.

author: jaime lannister
content: What?

author: bronn
content: Listen.

author: jaime lannister
content: Spears and shields! Spears and shields!

author: jaime lannister
content: Spears and shields!

author: bronn
content: In line now!

author: randyll
content: is riding across the battlefield yelling orders to men.

author: randyll
content: Come on, lads. Not those wagons. Fall in line. Fall in line.

author: dickon
content: draws his sword. RANDYLL is yelling orders to the men.

author: randyll
content: Spears armed!

author: bronn
content: Get back to King's Landing.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not abandoning my army.

author: bronn
content: You're a commander, not a damned infantryman. These fuckers are about to swamp us.

author: jaime lannister
content: We can hold them off.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dracarys!

author: drogon
content: breathes fire into the first line of Lannister soldiers. The men burst into flames and start screaming. DICKON looks on in shock. A flanking group of Dothraki Screamers ride over the flames through the hole created by Drogon and start cutting men down. JAIME attempts to issue orders to the men.

author: jaime lannister
content: Hold the line!

author: jaime lannister
content: Archers! Archers with me!

author: jaime lannister
content: Knock!

author: archers
content: Knock! Draw!

author: drogon
content: loops around and is making a pass on JAIME and the archers. DAENERYS and DROGON are diving at the group of men.

author: jaime lannister
content: Loose!

author: jaime lannister
content: Qyburn's scorpion is over there.

author: bronn
content: Go get it then.

author: jaime lannister
content: I can't shoot with one hand.

author: jaime lannister
content: holds up his gold hand to illustrate his point.

author: bronn
content: hesitates for a moment. He turns his horse and rides to man the artillery crossbow. JAIME draws his sword and rides into battle.

author: jaime lannister
content: Come on!

author: bronn
content: Where are you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: walks to the edge of the battlefield accompanied by Dothraki guards. He can see Lannisters being slaughtered. One of the Dothraki guards begin to speak.

author: guard
content: Your people can't fight.

author: tyrion lannister
content: is watching the mayhem. Men are screaming and engulfed in flames. Horses and carriages run wild with no driver. JAIME is still on the battlefield struggling against the horde. Burning Lannister men are taking off their helmets revealing melted faces. Men crawl to the river in search of relief from the dragonfire. DROGON and DAENERYS are flying over the river creating wake in the water. JAIME sees her approaching his position.

author: jaime lannister
content: Take cover!

author: drogon
content: spits flames into the Lannister position. The men standing there are reduced to standing ash. The wind blows them away. BRONN is lining up DROGON in the sights of the crossbow. He reaches down and pulls the lever to fire. A bolt sails past DROGON and misses. BRONN reloads the machine. DROGON and DAENERYS circle around and dive on the crossbow. BRONN takes his time aiming his shot.

author: bronn
content: Come on you fucker.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: commands DROGON to fire at the crossbow.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Flee, you idiot!

author: jaime lannister
content: looks at DAENERYS and readies himself. He spurs his horse onward.

author: jaime lannister
content: Come on, boy. Come on!

author: jaime lannister
content: grabs the spear as he rides by and brings it up to position. JAIME's horse is galloping full speed on the edge of the river kicking up water. TYRION is watching JAIME's attempt to kill DAENERYS.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You fucking idiot.

author: jaime lannister
content: is getting close. DAENERYS turns at the last moment to see JAIME bearing down on her spear in hand. DROGON notices JAIME, turns his head and spews flames. BRONN appears from nowhere and manages to dive off of his horse and knock JAIME and himself in the water before they're both consumed by fire. Their horses are instantly burned to death. JAIME is being dragged down by a full set of armor into the dark water. JAIME sinks into blackness and out of sight.

author: end
content: CREDITS

author: jaime lannister
content: You could have killed me.

author: bronn
content: What the fuck were you doing back there?

author: jaime lannister
content: Ending the war by killing her.

author: bronn
content: You saw the dragon between you and her?

author: bronn
content: looks incredulously at JAIME.

author: bronn
content: And?

author: jaime lannister
content: sits up and says nothing to BRONN. BRONN sits up and faces JAIME.

author: bronn
content: Listen to me, cunt. Till I get what I'm owed, a dragon doesn't get to kill you. You don't get to kill you. Only I get to kill you.

author: jaime lannister
content: That was only one of them. She has two more. If she decides to use them, to really use them --

author: bronn
content: You're fucked.

author: jaime lannister
content: Don't you mean we're fucked?

author: bronn
content: No, I do not. Dragons are where our partnership ends. I'm not going to be around when those things start spitting fire on King's Landing.

author: jaime lannister
content: I have to tell Cersei.

author: bronn
content: pauses and looks at JAIME.

author: bronn
content: Best well jump back in that river.

author: bronn
content: stands up and walks away. JAIME continues sitting on the shore looking at the smoke and fire from the distant battle.

author: tyrion lannister
content: is walking over an ash covered ground. There are burned bodies and cargo strewn about. Dothraki are looting dead Lannister soldies. A group of mounted Dothraki are escorting captured Lannister soldiers to where DAENERYS and DROGON are awaiting the prisoners. DAENERYS addresses the captured soldiers.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I know what Cersei has told you, that I've come to destroy your cities --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: burn down your homes, murder you and orphan your children. That's Cersei Lannister, not me. I'm not here to murder. And all I want to destroy is the wheel that is rolled over rich and poor to the benefit of no one but the Cersei Lannisters of the world. I offer you a choice. Bend the knee and join me. Together we will leave the world a better place than we found it, or refuse and die.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Step forward, My Lord.

author: randyll
content: takes several steps towards DAENERYS and stands in front of the kneeling Lannister men.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will not kneel?

author: randyll
content: I already have a queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My sister, she wasn't your queen until recently though, was she, until she murdered your rightful queen and destroyed House Tyrell for all time. So it appears your allegiances are somewhat flexible.

author: randyll
content: There are no easy choices in war. Say what you will about your sister, she was born in Westeros, has lived here all her life. You on the other hand, you murdered your own father and chose to support a foreign invader. One with no ties to this land, an army of savages at her back.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You will not trade your honor for your life. I respect that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: turns to speak to DAENERYS.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Perhaps he could take the black, Your Grace. Whatever else he is, he is a true soldier. He would be invaluable at the Wall.

author: randyll
content: You cannot send me to the Wall. You are not my queen.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns to look at her Dothraki escort. The Dothraki walk forward to collect RANDYLL. As the men are pulling RANDYLL away DICKON steps forward.

author: dickon
content: You will have to kill me too.

author: randyll
content: pulls away from the Dothraki and turns to face his son.

author: randyll
content: Step back and shut your mouth.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who are you?

author: randyll
content: A stupid boy.

author: dickon
content: I'm Dickon Tarley, son of Randyll Tarley.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You are the future of your house. This war has already wiped one great house from the world. Don't let it happen again. Bend the knee.

author: dickon
content: looks to RANDYLL. RANDYLL nods to his son.

author: dickon
content: I will not.

author: tyrion lannister
content: turns to speak to DAENERYS. He speaks softly so no one but the queen can hear.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace, nothing strips bold notions from a man's head like a few weeks in a dark cell.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I meant what I said. I'm not here to put men in chains. If that becomes an option many will take it. I gave them a choice. They made it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace, if you begin beheading entire families --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm not beheading anyone.

author: tyrion lannister
content: pauses and looks over the DROGON. DRGON roars and shakes his head and flexes his wings.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: looks to her Dothraki escort and gives a signal. The men grab RANDYLL and DICKON and walk them over to DROGON. RANDYLL takes DICKON by the arm.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Lord Randyll Tarley, Dickon Tarley, I, Daenerys of House Targaryen, First of my name, Breaker of Chains and Mother of Dragons, sentence you to die.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: pauses a moment and looks at RANDYLL and DICKON.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Dracarys.

author: drogon
content: draws a deep breath and begins spewing dragonfire at the two men. They are instantly engulfed in flames. They both collapse into ash after a few seconds. There are two craters left where RANDYLL and DICKON stood. The Lannister men recoil in horror. Any Lannister soldier that was still standing kneels to the ground. DAENERYS silently turns and begins to walk off the battlefield.

author: jaime lannister
content: is quickly walking down the hall leading to CERSEI's room. As he approaches, QYBURN exits the queen's chambers.

author: qyburn
content: My Lord.

author: jaime lannister
content: passes by QYBURN without saying a word and barges into CERSEI's quarters. CERSEI stand and walks over to JAIME.

author: cersei lannister
content: How many men did we lose?

author: jaime lannister
content: We haven't done a full counting.

author: cersei lannister
content: It's armies that win wars. We have the Tyrell gold, we have the Iron Bank behind us. We can buy mercenaries.

author: jaime lannister
content: shakes his head.

author: cersei lannister
content: They're not the same as our men but they'll fight if they're well paid, which they will be.

author: jaime lannister
content: I just saw the Dothraki fight. They'll beat any mercenary army. They'll beat any army I've ever seen. Killing our men wasn't war for them, it was sport. Her dragon burned a thousand wagons. Qyburn's scorpion fired bolts bigger than you. They couldn't stop it. And she has three of them. This isn't a war we can win.

author: cersei lannister
content: So what do we do? Sue for peace? I sit on her father's throne, the father you betrayed and murdered. And in her mind she's winning. What sort of offer do you think she'd make?

author: cersei lannister
content: turns and walks away from JAIME.

author: cersei lannister
content: Maybe we can count on Tyrion to intercede on our behalf by way of apology for murdering our father and our son.

author: jaime lannister
content: He didn't.

author: cersei lannister
content: You saw the crossbow, you saw his body.

author: jaime lannister
content: walks across the room to where CERSEI is standing.

author: jaime lannister
content: I'm not talking about father. Tyrion didn't kill Joffrey. He had nothing to do with it.

author: cersei lannister
content: After all this time it still amazes me --

author: jaime lannister
content: It was Olenna. She confessed before she died.

author: cersei lannister
content: And this was before or after she drank the poison you so kindly provided her?

author: jaime lannister
content: After.

author: cersei lannister
content: And you believed her?

author: jaime lannister
content: If you were Olenna would you rather have seen your granddaughter married to Joffrey or Tommen? Which one would Margerey been better able to control? Which one would have made Olenna the true ruler of the Seven Kingdoms? She was telling the truth.

author: cersei lannister
content: looks away, then sits down.

author: cersei lannister
content: I shouldn't have listened to you. She should have died screaming.

author: jaime lannister
content: She's dead like her son, her grandchildren, her whole house. And if we don't find a way out of this war we'll follow them.

author: cersei lannister
content: So we fight and die or we submit and die. I know my choice. A soldier should know his.

author: jon snow
content: SNOW is standing on the edge of a cliff looking towards the ocean. DROGON roars and flies over him with DAENERYS on his back. DROGON lands next to JON and charges towards him. DROGON opens his jaws and roars in JON's face. DROGON creeps closer until he is inches from JON. JON removes his glove and slowly extends his hand toward DROGON. DROGON lowers his head and allows JON to touch him. DAENERYS looks surprised and steps down from her mount. DROGON turns and flies away.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They're beautiful, aren't they?

author: jon snow
content: That wasn't the word I was thinking of, but, yes, they are. Gorgeous beasts.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They're not beasts to me. No matter how big they get, how terrifying to everyone else, they're my children.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns to look at her three dragons as they fly over Dragonstone in the distance.

author: jon snow
content: You weren't gone long.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns back to JON.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No.

author: jon snow
content: And?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And I have fewer enemies today than I did yesterday.

author: jon snow
content: pauses and doesn't say anything.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You're not sure how you feel about that?

author: jon snow
content: No, I'm not.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns and starts walking towards the castle, JON follows.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many men did your army kill taking Winterfell back from the Boltons?

author: jon snow
content: Thousands.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We both want to help people. We can only help them from a position of strength. Sometimes strength is terrible. When you first came here Ser Davos said you took a knife in the heart for your people.

author: jon snow
content: Ser Davos gets carried away.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So it was a figure of speech?

author: jon snow
content: doesn't say anything. A group of Dothraki guards approach DAENERYS and speak in their native tongue.

author: guard
content: This man says he is your friend, Khaleesi.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He is my friend.

author: jorah mormont
content: kneels before DAENERYS.

author: jorah mormont
content: Your Grace.

author: jorah mormont
content: stands.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Jon Snow, this is Ser Jorah Mormont, an old friend.

author: jon snow
content: I served with your father. He was a great man.

author: jorah mormont
content: nods to JON.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You look strong. You found a cure?

author: jorah mormont
content: I wouldn't be here if I hadn't. I return to your service, my queen, if you'll have me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It would be my honor.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: steps forward and hugs JORAH.

author: bran stark
content: s eyes are pure white. They wash back to their normal color. He is sitting in front of the Weirwood. Maester Wolkan stands next to him.

author: bran stark
content: Ravens. We need to send ravens.

author: wolkan
content: nods his head to BRAN.

author: archmaester
content: MARWYN and other citadel maesters are seated at a council table. MARWYN has a raven scroll in his hand and the maesters are discussing the contents. SAMWELL enters the room carrying a large stock of books and scrolls. MARWYN points SAM to a nearby table to offload the books.

author: maester
content: I put very little stock in it myself. Prophecies of doom are never in short supply, especially when winter comes.

author: marwyn
content: I remember Wolkan. A bit timid but a sharp mind.

author: maester
content: The north has dulled many good maester's wits. I'm not sure if it's the cold, the drink, or the company.

author: maester
content: A crippled boy claims to have seen dead men on the march beyond the wall thanks to the magical help of a raven with three eyes.

author: sam
content: stops working and turns around.

author: marwyn
content: It is a bit much. Still we ought to --

author: sam tarly
content: Brandon Stark --

author: sam tarly
content: the crippled boy.

author: marwyn
content: Do you know him?

author: sam tarly
content: I let him through the Wall years ago. I saw him go beyond the wall.

author: marwyn
content: And?

author: sam tarly
content: Somehow a crippled boy survived for years beyond the wall when no one else could. Not the Night's Watch, not the Wildlings, no one. Perhaps we ought to listen to what he has to say.

author: maester
content: Perhaps you need more scribing work to discipline your mind.

author: marwyn
content: I sense a more detailed proposal is forthcoming.

author: sam tarly
content: steps forward and clears his throat.

author: sam tarly
content: Everyone in Westeros trusts and respects you. If you tell people the threat is real they'll believe it. If you advise all the lords to send their men north to hold the wall they'll do it. And if you tell every maester in the Citadel to search every word of every faded scroll about the long night, they may find something that lets us defeat the Army of the Dead for good.

author: marwyn
content: It could be done. And this news could be authentic. It's possible. It's also possible this message is part of a ploy by the dragon queen to lure southern armies away from the lands they are currently defending to open those lands to easy conquest.

author: maester
content: That does seem far more likely than magic birds talking to cripples.

author: sam tarly
content: Archmaester, please. It's real. I've seen it.

author: marwyn
content: We will write to Maester Wolkan at Winterfell for clarification. I promise you we will get to the truth of it one way or another.

author: sam tarly
content: Archmaester --

author: marwyn
content: That will be all, Tarley.

author: sam
content: turns to collect his work and leave. The maesters begin talking to one another.

author: maester
content: It brings to mind the work of Davy Moonstone, the charlatan who claimed to see the children of the forest.

author: maester
content: Don't forget the Prophet Lodock that promised the Drowned God would rise up and destroy Aegon the Conquerer.

author: maester
content: Is he the one whose father and brother were just burned alive?

author: marwyn
content: I'm afraid so.

author: maester
content: Horrible business.

author: marwyn
content: I don't have the heart to tell him yet. He's a good lad.

author: marwyn
content: crumples the raven scroll and throws it dismissevely on the table.

author: marwyn
content: Right. The ravenry was falling apart last time I checked...

author: varys
content: and TYRION are sitting on the stairs of the Throne Room alone. VARYS has a sealed raven scroll in his hand tapping it on the stone. TYRION is drinking a glass of wine having a discussion with VARYS.

author: tyrion lannister
content: All rulers demand that people bend the knee. It's why they're rulers. She gave Tarley a choice. A man who had taken up arms against her. What else could she do?

author: varys
content: Not burn him alive alongside his son.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am her hand, not her head. I can't make her decisions for her.

author: varys
content: That's what I used to tell myself about her father. I found the traitors but I wasn't the one burning them alive. I was only a purveyor of information.

author: varys
content: reaches over to TYRION's cup of wine, picks it up and begins to drink from it. He grimaces as he drinks.

author: varys
content: It's what I told myself when I watched them beg for mercy, "I'm not the one doing it." As the pitch of their screams rose higher, "I'm not the one doing it." When their hair caught fire and the smell of the burning flesh filled the Thone Room, "I'm not the one doing it."

author: varys
content: drinks again and sets the cup down next to TYRION. TYRION picks it up.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Daenerys is not her father.

author: varys
content: And she never will be... with the right counsel. You need to find a way to make her listen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: looks down at the note in VARYS's hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Who is that for?

author: varys
content: Jon Snow.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did you read it?

author: varys
content: It's a sealed scroll for the King in the North.

author: tyrion lannister
content: pauses and drinks from his cup of wine.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What's it say?

author: varys
content: Nothing good.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: and VARYS are seated at the painted table. TYRION and JORAH stand near the queen. DAVOS and JON SNOW are standing on the other end of the table. JON is holding a raven scroll and reading it.

author: jon snow
content: I thought Arya was dead. I thought Bran was dead.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm happy for you. You don't look happy.

author: jon snow
content: Bran saw the Night King and his army marching towards Eastwatch. If they make it past the wall --

author: varys
content: The Wall has kept them out for thousands of years. Presumably --

author: jon snow
content: interrupts VARYS.

author: jon snow
content: I need to go home.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You said you don't have enough men.

author: jon snow
content: We'll fight with the men we have. Unless you'll join us.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And give the country to Cersei? As soon as I march away she marches in.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Perhaps not. Cersei thinks the Army of the Dead is nothing but a story made up by wet nurses to frighten children. What if we prove her wrong?

author: jon snow
content: I don't think she'll come see the dead at my invitation.

author: tyrion lannister
content: begins walking around the table closer to JON.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So bring the dead to her.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I thought that was what we are trying to avoid.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We don't have to bring the whole army. Only one soldier.

author: davos
content: Is that possible?

author: jon snow
content: The first White I ever saw was brought into Castle Black from beyond the Wall.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Bring one of these things down to King's Landing and show her the truth.

author: varys
content: Anything you bring back will be useless unless Cersei grants us an audience and is somehow convinced not to murder us the moment we set foot in the capital.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The only person she listens to is Jaime. He may listen to me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And how would you get into King's Landing.

author: davos
content: I can smuggle you in, but if the Goldcloaks were to recognize you, I'm warning you, I'm not a fighter.

author: tyrion lannister
content: nods his head.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, it will all be for nothing if we don't have one of these dead men.

author: varys
content: Fair point. How do you propose to find one?

author: jon snow
content: pauses and stares at the ground. JORAH breaks the silence.

author: jorah mormont
content: With the queen's permission I'll go north and take one.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: turns to look at JORAH.

author: jorah mormont
content: You asked me to find a cure so I could serve you. Allow me to serve you.

author: jon snow
content: The free folk will help us. They know the real north better than anyone.

author: davos
content: They won't follow Ser Jorah.

author: jon snow
content: They won't have to.

author: davos
content: You can't lead a raid beyond the wall. You're not in the Night's Watch anymore. You're King in the North.

author: jon snow
content: I'm the only one here whose fought them. I'm the only one here who knows them.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I haven't given you permission to leave.

author: jon snow
content: With respect, Your Grace, I don't need your permission. I am a king. And I came here knowing that you could have your men behead me or your dragons burn me alive. I put my trust in you, a stranger, because I knew it was the best chance for my people, for all our people. Now I'm asking you to trust in a stranger because it's our best chance.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: pauses for a moment then nods her head in agreement.

author: robett
content: The King in the North should stay in the north. We did not choose you to rule us, My Lady, but perhaps we should have.

author: yohn
content: The Knights of the Vale came here for you, Lady Stark.

author: sansa stark
content: You're very kind, my lords, but Jon is our king. He is doing what he thinks is best.

author: sansa stark
content: and ARYA are walking through the hall to SANSA's quarters having a discussion.

author: sansa stark
content: I warned Jon this would happen. He can't leave the north and expect it to just sit and wait for him like Ghost.

author: arya stark
content: He didn't. He trusted you to hold it for him.

author: sansa stark
content: Well, he's not making it easy. The northern lords are proud.

author: arya stark
content: These are mother and father's chambers.

author: sansa stark
content: And?

author: arya stark
content: Nothing.

author: sansa stark
content: Don't do that.

author: sansa stark
content: turns around to face ARYA.

author: arya stark
content: What?

author: sansa stark
content: Say what you mean.

author: arya stark
content: You always liked nice things. It made you feel better than everyone.

author: sansa stark
content: drops the papers in her hand on a table and looks at ARYA.

author: sansa stark
content: Are you angry with me?

author: arya stark
content: They were insulting Jon and you sat there and listened.

author: sansa stark
content: I listened to their complaints, which is my responsibility as Lady of Winterfell.

author: arya stark
content: Their opinions are important to you?

author: sansa stark
content: Glover has 500 men. Royce has 2,000. Offend them and Jon loses his army.

author: arya stark
content: Not if they lose their heads first.

author: sansa stark
content: Winterfell didn't just fall into our hands. We took it back, and the Mormonts and the Hornwoods and the Wildlings and the Vale, all of us working together. Now, I'm sure cutting off heads is very satisfying, but that's not the way you get people to work together.

author: arya stark
content: And if Jon doesn't come back, you'll need their support, so you can work together to give you what you really want.

author: sansa stark
content: How can you even think such a horrible thing?

author: arya stark
content: You're thinking it right now. You don't want to be, but the thought just won't go away.

author: sansa stark
content: and ARYA stare at each in silence for a moment.

author: sansa stark
content: I have work to do.

author: sansa stark
content: turns and walks away from ARYA.

author: arya stark
content: My lady.

author: arya stark
content: exits the room.

author: davos
content: and TYRION are standing on the beach of King's Landing. DAVOS is securing a small row boat. TYRION is looking up towards the city walls.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Last time I was here I killed my father with a crossbow.

author: davos
content: Last time I was here you killed my son with wildfire.

author: tyrion lannister
content: turns to look at DAVOS. DAVOS walks next to TYRION and stakes the boat anchor into the sand.

author: davos
content: There's a path to the left that hugs the cliff. The guards hardly ever patrol it. Too many steps.

author: tyrion lannister
content: begins walking towards the path. DAVOS follows him and quickly takes the lead. TYRION stops and looks back towards the unattended boat.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're not staying here?

author: davos
content: I've got my own business in Flea Bottom.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What if someone takes the boat?

author: davos
content: Then we're fucked. Best hurry.

author: bronn
content: and JAIME are walking by the dragon skulls. Both men have sparring swords in their hand.

author: jaime lannister
content: We don't have time for this. We should be preparing the city for a siege. The Dothraki are coming.

author: bronn
content: All the more reason for you to train. Unless you plan on fighting Dothraki 12 year olds.

author: jaime lannister
content: I seem to recall them giving you a bit of trouble as well.

author: bronn
content: And here I am ready to train.

author: jaime lannister
content: Why down here?

author: bronn
content: I don't think you want people to see how you look swinging that thing yet.

author: jaime lannister
content: Today might be the day I kill you by accident.

author: bronn
content: Oh, you won't be swinging it at me.

author: bronn
content: stops walking and holds his torch out. TYRION steps from around a pillar and looks at JAIME. JAIME looks angrily at BRONN.

author: bronn
content: I'll leave you to it.

author: bronn
content: turns and walks away leaving JAIME and TYRION alone.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I needed to see you and I knew you'd never agree to meet.

author: jaime lannister
content: remains silent and stares at TYRION.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You made me look like a complete fool. I thought I'd surprise you by hitting Casterly Rock, but you were three steps ahead of me. You abandoned the family home. Completely unsentimental. Father would have been proud.

author: jaime lannister
content: Don't talk about our father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Listen to me --

author: jaime lannister
content: I once told Bronn that if I ever saw you again I'd cut you in half.

author: tyrion lannister
content: glances down at the sword in JAIME's hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It would take you awhile with a sparring sword.

author: jaime lannister
content: shakes his head and says nothing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He was going to execute me. He knew I was innocent. He didn't hate me because of anything I did, he hated me because of what I am. The little monster sent to punish him. Do you think I wanted to be born this way? Did he think I chose --

author: jaime lannister
content: What do you want?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Daenerys will win this war. You're a military man. You must know there is no way around it. Daenerys is not her father. She's even willing to suspend hostilities if Cersei agrees to certain terms.

author: jaime lannister
content: You want Cersei to bend the knee you can ask her yourself.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I -- I don't. Daenerys doesn't. Not right now anyway. She has a more important request.

author: davos
content: I wasn't sure I'd find you.

author: davos
content: I thought you might still be rowing.

author: gendry baratheon
content: chuckles and DAVOS smiles.

author: davos
content: I looked in shops, taverns, brothels. I should have known to come straight to the Street of Steel.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Weren't you worried about the Goldcloaks?

author: davos
content: I haven't been here in years. Why should they recognize me? Sometimes I hardly do. Nothing fucks you harder than time.

author: davos
content: walks to the side of the shop and inspects a rack of swords. He pulls one, nods in approval and puts it back in its place. He turns back to GENDRY.

author: davos
content: Anybody give you any trouble?

author: gendry baratheon
content: Here I am arming Lannisters. I never get a second look. You were right. Safest place for me was right under the queen's nose.

author: davos
content: Don't be so sure. Safety is never a permanent state of affairs. Bad things are coming.

author: gendry baratheon
content: nods.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You came to get me. You want me to come with you.

author: davos
content: I think you need to understand --

author: gendry baratheon
content: I'm ready. Let's go.

author: davos
content: You should know what you're heading into.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Don't you think I've been thinking about it every swing of the hammer... how happy I am making weapons for the family that killed my father? They tried to kill me.

author: gendry baratheon
content: is tossing his tools and apron to the side. He picks up a satchel and swings it over his head.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I've been getting ready. I never knew what for, but I've always known I'd know it when it comes.

author: davos
content: You might want to bring one of those swords.

author: gendry baratheon
content: smiles at DAVOS and begins walking towards the weapons.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I don't know much about swinging swords, but this --

author: gendry baratheon
content: removes a giant war hammer from the wall.

author: gendry baratheon
content: this I know.

author: gendry baratheon
content: and DAVOS turn and walk out of the shop.

author: davos
content: and GENDRY are walking towards the boat DAVOS left on the beach.

author: davos
content: Keep your father's name to yourself. The situation is complicated enough already.

author: gendry baratheon
content: and DAVOS arrive at the boat. GENDRY lays his hammer on top of the boat cargo. DAVOS is gathering the anchor and rope. Two Goldcloaks begin walking down the beach towards the boat unnoticed by DAVOS and GENDRY.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Who should I say I am?

author: davos
content: turns and notices the two guards approaching the boat. He turns and loudly addresses GENDRY.

author: davos
content: I told you, Clovis, if we don't get out of here soon someone is going to --

author: guard
content: You there.

author: davos
content: No weapons, friends. I promise. What can I do for you?

author: guard
content: Is that your boat?

author: davos
content: It is.

author: gendry baratheon
content: looks down into the boat and sees his weapon in plain view.

author: guard
content: The docks are that way.

author: gendry baratheon
content: That they are. I try to stay away from them to avoid good men such as yourselves.

author: davos
content: Still five gold dragons?

author: guard
content: Are you joking?

author: guard
content: You must be even older than you look. 15.

author: guard
content: Apiece.

author: davos
content: angrily reaches into his pouch and pays the men.

author: davos
content: I can't say it was a pleasure doing business with you.

author: davos
content: turns and begins walking back to his boat.

author: guard
content: What's in the boat?

author: davos
content: pauses and turns back to the guards.

author: davos
content: Not more gold.

author: guard
content: Wine?

author: guard
content: Mmm.

author: guard
content: I like wine.

author: guard
content: Or hams.

author: davos
content: Come and have a look.

author: davos
content: Fermented crab.

author: guard
content: What?

author: davos
content: Fermented crab. One bucket of this triples the brothel's earnings for the week. A man thinks he's done, he's ready to go back to his loving family, but before he gets his britches up his lady of the hour pops a tiny spoon of that into his mouth. Five minutes later, he's back in the race. Here, have a taste.

author: davos
content: scoops up a bit of fermented crab and offers it to the guards. Both men reach out and take a pinch. The guards sniff the crab and put it in their mouth. They both recoil from the taste and look at each other.

author: davos
content: I'd hurry to your favorite establishment or you'll put a whole in that chainmail.

author: guard
content: Oi, Dwarf!

author: davos
content: quickly walks to cut the guards off.

author: davos
content: I really wouldn't try anymore until you see how the first bite hits you.

author: guard
content: That dwarf --

author: guard
content: Where did you get that scar?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Fish hook. Some men you just can't teach.

author: guard
content: We was looking for a dwarf with a scar like that awhile back.

author: davos
content: is still standing behind the guards. He retrieves his gold pouch again and holds it up shaking it.

author: davos
content: Perhaps there's some arrangement?

author: guard
content: Arrangement? You gonna arrange to pay us more than Queen Cersei?

author: gendry baratheon
content: can be seen behind the backs of the guards. He slowly retrieves his hammer and creeps up behind GUARD 2. He swings his hammer and connects with the side of the guardo s head. The man drops. As GENDRY transitions onto the second guard and swings his hammer, GUARD 1 turns to look and catches a hammer blow to the face.

author: davos
content: is looking at TYRION and motions towards GENDRY.

author: davos
content: This is Gendry.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He'll do.

author: jaime lannister
content: opens the door and step into the queen's room. CERSEI is seated near a window speaking to QYBURN.

author: cersei lannister
content: That won't be necessary.

author: qyburn
content: bows his head and walks to leave the room. As he passes by JAIME he addresses him.

author: qyburn
content: Ser Jaime.

author: qyburn
content: closes the door as he leaves. JAIME and CERSEI are alone. CERSEI begins walking over to a chair in front of JAIME and sits.

author: jaime lannister
content: Why was QYBURN here?

author: cersei lannister
content: He's Hand of the Queen. Why are you here?

author: jaime lannister
content: I met with Tyrion.

author: cersei lannister
content: pauses for a moment making JAIME uncomfortable.

author: cersei lannister
content: What did our brother have to say?

author: jaime lannister
content: Daenerys wants to meet.

author: cersei lannister
content: To discuss a surrender?

author: jaime lannister
content: To discuss an armistice.

author: cersei lannister
content: She just won a great victory. Why would she want a truce now?

author: jaime lannister
content: Because an army of dead men is marching on the Seven Kingdoms. Tyrion claims he'll have proof.

author: cersei lannister
content: smirks and looks away from JAIME.

author: cersei lannister
content: Are you going to punish him?

author: jaime lannister
content: Tyrion?

author: cersei lannister
content: Bronn.

author: jaime lannister
content: looks confused.

author: cersei lannister
content: He betrayed you. He set up a meeting without your knowledge or consent. Do you think anything of importance happens in this city without me knowing?

author: jaime lannister
content: You let it happen. Why?

author: cersei lannister
content: I've come to believe that accomodation with the Dragon Queen could be in our immediate interest. She has the numbers. If we want to beat her we have to be clever. We have to fight her like father would have. Dead men, dragons and Dragon Queens, whatever stands in our way we will defeat it ourselves for our house. For this.

author: cersei lannister
content: lifts her hands from the chair and places them both on her stomach indicating she's pregnant. JAIME looks shocked.

author: jaime lannister
content: Who will you say is the father?

author: cersei lannister
content: You.

author: jaime lannister
content: People won't like that.

author: cersei lannister
content: stands from her chair and walks in front of JAIME.

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you remember what father used to say about people?

author: jaime lannister
content: The lion doesn't concern himself with the opinions of the sheep.

author: jaime lannister
content: reaches forward and takes CERSEI and kisses her. While they embrace CERSEI speaks to JAIME.

author: cersei lannister
content: Never betray me again.

author: gendry baratheon
content: and DAVOS are walking down the beach near the Dragonglass cave. Groups of men are carrying boxes filled with Dragonglass out of the cave. DAVOS and GENDRY are having a discussion.

author: davos
content: We're leaving today. The king's got a lot on his mind.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I understand.

author: davos
content: He doesn't need to be thinking about harboring the bastard of a dead king.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You don't have to worry.

author: davos
content: You're just Clovis, a smith who's come to pay his respects before he heads off to work at the Winterfell forges.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Understood.

author: davos
content: and GENDRY enter the mouth of the cave. JON is walking along the corridor.

author: davos
content: Begging your pardon, Your Grace.

author: jon snow
content: stops and turns around to face DAVOS.

author: jon snow
content: You survived King's Landing.

author: davos
content: Yet again.

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace, this is --

author: gendry baratheon
content: steps forward in front of DAVOS.

author: gendry baratheon
content: It's Gendry, Your Grace. I'm Robert Baratheon's son. Bastard son.

author: jon snow
content: looks to DAVOS.

author: davos
content: He was meant to keep that to himself.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Our fathers trusted each other. Why shouldn't we?

author: jon snow
content: I saw your father once at Winterfell.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I met yours in my shop.

author: jon snow
content: You're a lot leaner.

author: gendry baratheon
content: You're a lot shorter.

author: jon snow
content: stops smiling and pauses a moment. Then he chuckles.

author: jon snow
content: I grew up on stories about them.

author: gendry baratheon
content: All I ever knew was they fought together and won. Ser Davos told me where you're going, Your Grace, and why. Let me come with you.

author: davos
content: Don't be a fool. You're not a soldier.

author: gendry baratheon
content: No, but I'm a fighter. And he won't be needing a smith with a sword like that.

author: jon snow
content: Do you know how to use one?

author: gendry baratheon
content: shakes his head.

author: jon snow
content: Well, that's a problem.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I prefer a hammer.

author: gendry baratheon
content: looks to DAVOS.

author: davos
content: He can handle himself.

author: jon snow
content: nods.

author: jon snow
content: We could use the help.

author: davos
content: As my father used to say, it's better to be a coward for a minute than dead for the rest of your life.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I owe you my life. Twice over. But if what you said is true about what's out there, I can't wait out this war.

author: davos
content: Yeah. Nobody mind me. All I've ever done is live to a ripe old age.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You may not believe it, but I've missed you Mormont. Nobody glowers quite like you. Not even Grey Worm.

author: tyrion lannister
content: retrieves a gold coin from his pocket and turns it in his hands.

author: tyrion lannister
content: This is the coin the slaver gave me when I suggested he free us and pay us. Remember?

author: jorah mormont
content: It was supposed to last us the rest of our lives.

author: tyrion lannister
content: smiles and hands the coin to JORAH.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Take it with you. You'll bring it back. Our queen needs you.

author: jorah mormont
content: nods to TYRION. DAENERYS appears and walks up to JORAH.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We should be better at saying farewell by now.

author: jorah mormont
content: Your Grace, I --

author: daenerys targaryen
content: reaches forward and takes JORAH by his hands. JON SNOW, DAVOS and GENDRY exit the cave and walk towards the boats. JORAH bends and kisses DAENERY's hand. He turns and continues readying the boat. JON stands in front of DAENERYS.

author: jon snow
content: If I don't return at least you won't have to deal with the King in the North anymore.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: smiles.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But I've grown used to him.

author: jon snow
content: I wish you good fortune in the wars to come, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: nods to JON. JON turns and walks to the head of the boat. The men take hold of it.

author: jon snow
content: Heave!

author: sam
content: is seated at a table surround by papers and candles. He is writing notes into a book. Gilly is seated across from him reading aloud from a tome. SAM JR. is playing on the bed.

author: gilly
content: Do you know how many steps there are in the Citadel?

author: sam
content: No.

author: sam
content: looks up from his work annoyed. He remains silent and continues working.

author: gilly
content: Guess how many windows are in the Great Sept of Baelor.

author: sam tarly
content: looks away and pauses.

author: sam tarly
content: None anymore.

author: gilly
content: That's true. This High Septon Meynard, he recorded everything. He even recorded his own bowel movements. What does "annulment" mean?

author: sam tarly
content: It's when a man sets asside his lawful wife.

author: gilly
content: Meynard says here that he issued an anullment for Prince Rhaegar and remarried him to someone else at the same time in a secret ceremony in Dorne. Is that a common thing --

author: sam tarly
content: isn't paying much attention to GILLY. He loudly interrupts her.

author: sam tarly
content: These maesters, they set me to the task of preserving that man's window counting and anullments and bowel movements for all eternity while the secret to defeating the Night King's probably sitting on some dusty shelf somewhere completely ignored. But that's all right, isn't it. We could all become slavering, murderous imbecils enthralled to evil incarnate as long as we can have access to the full records of High Septon Meynardo s 15,782 shits.

author: gilly
content: Steps. That number was steps.

author: sam tarly
content: is dismayed. He sets his quill down and grabs the book he was writing in and hands it to SAM Jr. He retrieves his cloak and walks out the door.

author: sam
content: is walking through a dark library. He heads to the restricted section and unlocks the barred gate. He begins removing books and scrolls from shelfs and stuff them in his satchel. After retrieving what he needs, SAM quickly walks to the exit of the library. He pauses before he leaves and turns around. He glances back at the library. It is many stories tall lined with countless shelves of books. SAMWELL looks at the library one last time, turns and walks out of the door.

author: sam tarly
content: is loading a wagon with his things. He walks around to the driver seat. GILLY and SAM JR. are already in the wagon dressed for the road. SAM climbs aboard and takes the reins in his hand.

author: gilly
content: Are you sure you want to do this? You always wanted to be a maester.

author: sam tarly
content: I'm tired of reading about the achievements of better men.

author: arya stark
content: is in the kennels observing PETER BAELISH and a Winterfell servant having a conversation. The servent is whispering in BAELISH's ear. ARYA can't hear the conversation. ARYA sees BAELISH hand the servant a raven scroll. The servant turns to leave. BAELISH senses someone is watching him and he looks to where ARYA stood but she has already vanished. BAELISH turns and leaves the kennels.

author: arya stark
content: is on the upper level looking down at BAELISH. He is having a conversation with ROBETT GLOVER and YOHN ROYCE. She can't hear what's being said. BAELISH finishes his conversation and walks away from the men. ARYA disappears behind the corner and continues following BAELISH.

author: arya stark
content: is walking down the hallway. She pauses, peers around a corner and looks towards the door of BAELISH's quarters. BAELISH appears and unlocks his door. Before he walks in MAESTER WOLKAN approaches him. She continues watching the men.

author: wolkan
content: I found it, my Lord.

author: wolkan
content: hands BAELISH a raven scroll.

author: wolkan
content: It took some searching. Maester Llewyn's archives are thorough.

author: petyr baelish
content: reads the note then looks at WOLKAN.

author: petyr baelish
content: Are you sure this is the only copy at Winterfell?

author: wolkan
content: Yes, my Lord.

author: petyr baelish
content: Lady Stark thanks you for your service.

author: wolkan
content: turns and walks away. BAELISH enters his room and shuts the door. ARYA continues watching. A moment later BAELISH opens the door and exits the room, locking the door as he leaves. After he is gone ARYA walks to the door and produces a lockpick from her sleeve. She enters the room and begins searching for the raven scroll. She opens a cabinet but finds nothing of value. She checks another cabinet, then looks in the fireplace and above the mantle finding nothing. She lifts up the mattress and finds a small hole cut into the bedding. She reaches in and retrives the raven scroll. She unrolls it and reads the contents.

author: jon snow
content: and the raiding party land on the Beach of Eastwatch. JON looks up at the castle. The men collect their equipment and make for the castle.

author: tormund
content: JON, DAVOS, GENDRY, and JORAH sit at a table having a conversation.

author: tormund
content: Isn't it your job to talk him out of stupid fucking ideas like this?

author: davos
content: I've been failing at that job of late.

author: tormund
content: How many queens are there now?

author: jon snow
content: Two.

author: tormund
content: And you need to convince the one with the dragons or the one who fucks her brother?

author: jon snow
content: Both.

author: tormund
content: How many men did you bring?

author: jon snow
content: looks around the table.

author: jon snow
content: Not enough.

author: tormund
content: The big woman?

author: jon snow
content: smiles and shakes his head. TORMUND is disappointed.
