content: I imagine for most of them it would be an improvement.

author: jon snow
content: This is serious. I wouldn't be here if it weren't.

author: cersei lannister
content: I don't think it's serious at all. I think it's another bad joke. If my brother Jaime has informed me correctly, you're asking me for a truce.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Yes. That's all.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's all? Pull back my armies and stand down while you go on your monster hunt. Or while you solidify and expand your position. Hard for me to know which it is with my armies pulled back until you return and march on my capital with four times the men.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your capital will be safe until the northern threat is dealt with. You have my word.

author: cersei lannister
content: The word of a would-be usurper.

author: tyrion lannister
content: There is no conversation that will erase the last 50 years. We have something to show you.

author: jon snow
content: We can destroy them by burning them.

author: jon snow
content: And we can destroy them with dragonglass. If we don't win this fight, then that is the fate of every person in the world.

author: jon snow
content: There is only one war that matters the Great War. And it is here.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I didn't believe it until I saw them. I saw them all.

author: jaime lannister
content: How many?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: A hundred thousand, at least.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Can they swim?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Good. I'm taking the Iron Fleet back to the Iron Islands.

author: cersei lannister
content: What are you talking about?

author: euron greyjoy
content: I've been around the world. I've seen everything, things you couldn't imagine, and this this is the only thing I've ever seen that terrifies me.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I'm going back to my island. You should go back to yours. When winter's over, we'll be the only ones left alive.

author: cersei lannister
content: He's right to be afraid. And a coward to run. If those things come for us, there will be no kingdoms to rule. Everything we suffered will have been for nothing. Everything we lost will have been for nothing. The crown accepts your truce. Until the dead are defeated, they are the true enemy.

author: cersei lannister
content: In return, the King

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Just the King

author: cersei lannister
content: I would never ask it of you. You would never agree to it. And if you did, I would trust you even less than I do now. I ask it only of Ned Stark's son. I know Ned Stark's son.

author: jon snow
content: I am true to my word. Or I try to be. That is why I cannot give you what you ask. I cannot serve two queens. And I have already pledged myself to Queen Daenerys of House Targaryen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Then there is nothing left to discuss. The dead will come north first. Enjoy dealing with them. We will deal with whatever is left of you.

author: brienne
content: Ser Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: It's been good to see you. I imagine the next time will be across a battlefield.

author: brienne
content: We both saw what just happened. We both saw that thing.

author: jaime lannister
content: Yes, and I'm not looking forward to seeing more of them. But I'm loyal to the queen and you're loyal to Sansa and her dolt brother.

author: brienne
content: Oh, fuck loyalty!

author: jaime lannister
content: Fuck loyalty?

author: brienne
content: This goes beyond houses and honor and oaths. Talk to the queen.

author: jaime lannister
content: And tell her what?

author: davos
content: I wish you hadn't done that.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'm grateful for your loyalty, but my dragon died so that we could be here. If it's all for nothing, then he died for nothing.

author: jon snow
content: I know!

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm pleased you bent the knee to our queen

author: jon snow
content: I'm not going to swear an oath I can't uphold. Talk about my father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That is indeed a problem. The more immediate problem is that we're fucked.

author: davos
content: Any ideas as to how we might change that state of affairs?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Only one. Everyone stays here, and I go and talk to my sister.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I didn't come all this way to have my Hand

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't want Cersei to murder me either. I could have stayed in my cell and saved a great deal of trouble.

author: jon snow
content: I did this. I should go.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She'll definitely murder you. I go see my sister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You spoke with her?

author: jaime lannister
content: At her until she kicked me out. She thinks I was an idiot to trust you. A lot of people seem to think that, actually.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm about to step into a room with the most murderous woman in the world who's already tried to kill me twice, that I know of. Who's an idiot?

author: jaime lannister
content: I suppose we should say goodbye, one idiot to another.

author: cersei lannister
content: I shouldn't be surprised, I suppose. She's your kind of woman a foreign whore who doesn't know her place.

author: tyrion lannister
content: A foreign whore you can't abduct, beat, or intimidate. That must be difficult for you.

author: cersei lannister
content: So you bring her here with her pet Northerner, whom you've convinced to bow down before her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I didn't know about that.

author: cersei lannister
content: And now you've got them both working towards the same goal, the goal you've worked towards your entire life.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Cersei, I didn't know.

author: cersei lannister
content: the destruction of this family.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am the one preventing that from happening. Daenerys didn't want to debate and negotiate. She didn't want to bring you words. She wanted to bring you fire and blood until I advised her otherwise. I don't want to destroy our family. I never have.

author: cersei lannister
content: You killed our father

author: tyrion lannister
content: After he sentenced me to death for a crime I didn't commit, yes, I killed him. Hate me for it if you want. I hate myself for it in spite of what he was, in spite of what he did to me.

author: cersei lannister
content: Oh, poor little man. Your papa was mean to you. Do you have any idea what you did when you fired that crossbow? You left us open. You laid us bare for the vultures, and the vultures came and tore us apart. You may not have killed Joffrey, but you killed Myrcella, you killed Tommen. No one wouldo ve touched them if Father--

author: tyrion lannister
content: I have never been more sorry about anything.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not hear it, not from you.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not hear it!

author: tyrion lannister
content: All right. You love your family, and I have destroyed it. I will always be a threat. So put an end to me.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If it weren't for me, you'd have a motherIf it weren't for me, you'd have a father.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I am more sorry about the children than you could ever know.

author: cersei lannister
content: I will not

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't care. I loved them. You know I did. You know it in your heart if there's anything left of it.

author: cersei lannister
content: It doesn't matter. Your love doesn't matter. Your feelings don't matter. I don't care why you did what you did. I only care what it cost us. It cost us our future.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If there's no future, then why are we here? Why did you allow me to come?

author: cersei lannister
content: Not to help my enemies collaborate in my destruction.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, no, not what you hoped for, but you must have hoped for something.

author: cersei lannister
content: What did you hope for? To make Jon Snow submit to your queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Mm, not like this.

author: cersei lannister
content: But eventually, you want everyone to bend the knee to her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes.

author: cersei lannister
content: Why?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Because I think she will make the world a better place.

author: cersei lannister
content: You said she'd destroy King's Landing.

author: tyrion lannister
content: She knows herself. She chose an advisor who would check her worst impulses instead of feeding them.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's the difference between you. I don't care about checking my worst impulses. I don't care about making the world a better place. Hang the world.

author: cersei lannister
content: That thing you dragged here, I know what it is, I know what it means. And when it came at me, I didn't think about the world. Not at all. As soon as it opened its mouth, the world disappeared for me, right down its black throat. All I could think about was keeping those gnashing teeth away from the ones who matter most, away from my family. Maybe Euron Greyjoy had the right idea. Get on a boat, take those who matter.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're pregnant.

author: jon snow
content: No one is less happy about this than I am.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I know. I respect what you did. Wish you hadn't done it, but I respect it.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: This place was the beginning of the end for my family. A dragon is not a slave. They were terrifying. Extraordinary. They filled people with wonder and awe, and we locked them in here. They wasted away. They grew small. And we grew small as well. We weren't extraordinary without them. We were just like everyone else.

author: jon snow
content: You're not like everyone else. And your family hasn't seen its end. You're still here.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I can't have children.

author: jon snow
content: Who told you that?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The witch who murdered my husband.

author: jon snow
content: Has it occurred to you she might not have been a reliable source of information?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You were right from the beginning. If I had trusted you, everything would be different.

author: jon snow
content: So, what now?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I can't forget what I saw north of the Wall. And I can't pretend that Cersei won't take back half the country the moment I march north.

author: jon snow
content: It appears Tyrion's assessment was correct. We're fucked.

author: cersei lannister
content: My armies will not stand down. I will not pull them back to the capital. I will march them north to fight alongside you in the Great War. The darkness is coming for us all. We'll face it together. And when the Great War is over, perhaps you'll remember I chose to help with no promises or assurances from any of you. I expect not. Call our banners. All of them.

author: petyr baelish
content: It's not easy for ravens to fly in these storms. Perhaps Jon tried to send word earlier.

author: sansa stark
content: No, this is the way he is, the way he's always been. He never asked for my opinion. Why would he start now?

author: petyr baelish
content: I can't believe he'd surrender the Northern crown without consulting you.

author: sansa stark
content: This is his writing, his signature. He pledged to fight for Daenerys Targaryen. He's bent the knee.

author: petyr baelish
content: I've heard gossip that the Dragon Queen is quite beautiful.

author: sansa stark
content: What does that have to do with anything?

author: petyr baelish
content: Jon is young and unmarried. Daenerys is young and unmarried.

author: sansa stark
content: You think he wants to marry her?

author: petyr baelish
content: An alliance makes sense. Together, they'd be difficult to defeat. He was named King.

author: sansa stark
content: Even if I wanted to, Arya would never go along. She always loved Jon far more than she ever loved me, and she'd kill anyone who betrayed her family.

author: petyr baelish
content: You are family, too. Would Arya really murder her own sister?

author: sansa stark
content: Do you know what she is now? Do you know what the Faceless Men are?

author: petyr baelish
content: Only by reputation. They worship the God of Death, I believe. I never trust godly men.

author: sansa stark
content: They're killers. And Arya was one of them. What do you think she's after?

author: petyr baelish
content: She's your sister

author: sansa stark
content: She could want me dead because she thinks I wronged my family.

author: petyr baelish
content: Why did she come to Winterfell?

author: sansa stark
content: To kill me for marrying our enemies and betraying my family.

author: petyr baelish
content: Why did she unearth the letter Cersei made you write?

author: sansa stark
content: To provide proof of my betrayals. To provide justification after she murders me.

author: petyr baelish
content: And after she murders you, what does she become?

author: sansa stark
content: Lady

author: jon snow
content: If we have the Dothraki ride hard on the kingsroad, they'll arrive at Winterfell within the fortnight.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And the Unsullied? We can sail with them to White Harbor, meet the Dothraki here on the kingsroad, then ride together to Winterfell.

author: jorah mormont
content: Perhaps you should fly to Winterfell, Your Grace. You have many enemies in the North. Thousands fell fighting your fatherAll it takes is one angry man with a crossbow. He'll see your silver hair on the kingsroad and know that one well-placed bolt will make him a hero. The man who killed the conqueror.

author: jon snow
content: It's your decision, Your Grace. But if we're going to be allies in this war, it's important for the Northerners to see us as allies. If we sail to White Harbor together, I think it sends a better message.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I've not come to conquer the North. I'm coming to save the North. We sail together.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Jon.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Can I speak with you?

author: jon snow
content: All right.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What you did in King's Landing, what you said... You couldo ve lied to Cersei about bending the knee to Daenerys. You risked everything to tell an enemy the truth.

author: jon snow
content: We went down there to make peace. And it seems to me we need to be honest with each other if we're going to fight together.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You've always known what was right. Even when we were all young and stupid, you always knew. Every step you take it's always the right step.

author: jon snow
content: It's not. It may seem that way from the outside, but I promise you, it's not true. I've done plenty of things that I regret.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not compared to me, you haven't.

author: jon snow
content: No. Not compared to you.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I always wanted to do the right thing. Be the right kind of person. But I never knew what that meant. It always seemed like there's like there was an impossible choice I had to make. Stark or Greyjoy.

author: jon snow
content: Our father was more of a father.

author: theon greyjoy
content: He was.

author: jon snow
content: And you betrayed him. Betrayed his memory.

author: theon greyjoy
content: I did.

author: jon snow
content: But you never lost him. He's a part of you. Just like he's a part of me.

author: theon greyjoy
content: But the things I've done.

author: jon snow
content: It's not my place to forgive you for all of it. But what I can forgive, I do. You don't need to choose. You're a Greyjoy and you're a Stark.

author: theon greyjoy
content: When I was Ramsay's prisoner, Yara tried to save me. She's the only one who tried to save me. She needs me now.

author: jon snow
content: So, why are you still talking to me?

author: harrag
content: Load up. Load up, lads. Go on. Tide's coming in.

author: theon greyjoy
content: All of us chose to follow Yara. We left the Iron Islands for Yara. She would never leave one of us behind. We're not leaving her behind.

author: harrag
content: Your sister--

author: theon greyjoy
content: She's not dead.

author: harrag
content: She's dead. Even if Euron hasn't cut her throat yet, she's dead.

author: theon greyjoy
content: She's our queen

author: harrag
content: She's your sister

author: theon greyjoy
content: I did. I ran from my uncle.

author: harrag
content: So, why in fuck's name should we listen to you? They say the dead can't swim. We're going to sail east, find a nice, quiet island, kill all the men, and take their wives for ourselves.

author: theon greyjoy
content: We're done with all that.

author: harrag
content: Who says we are?

author: theon greyjoy
content: Yara did. She made a pledge. We're going to find her, and we're going to set her free.

author: harrag
content: Run away, little Theon. It's what you do best.

author: man
content: He needs to shut his mouth.

author: man
content: Hey!

author: man
content: Oh, yes!

author: man
content: That's more like it.

author: harrag
content: Stay down or I'll kill you!

author: harrag
content: I said stay down or I'll kill you!

author: theon greyjoy
content: Not for me. For Yara!

author: men
content: Yara!

author: sansa stark
content: Have my sister

author: arya stark
content: Are you sure you want to do this?

author: sansa stark
content: It's not what I want. It's what honor demands.

author: arya stark
content: And what does honor demand?

author: sansa stark
content: That I defend my family from those who would harm us. That I defend the North from those who would betray us.

author: arya stark
content: All right, then. Get on with it.

author: sansa stark
content: You stand accused of murder. You stand accused of treason. How do you answer these charges Lord Baelish?

author: arya stark
content: My sister asked you a question.

author: petyr baelish
content: Lady Sansa, forgive me I'm a bit confused.

author: sansa stark
content: Which charges confuse you? Let's start with the simplest one you murdered our aunt, Lysa Arryn. You pushed her through the Moon Door and watched her fall. Do you deny it?

author: petyr baelish
content: I did it to protect you.

author: sansa stark
content: You did it to take power in the Vale. Earlier, you conspired to murder Jon.

author: petyr baelish
content: Whatever your aunt

author: sansa stark
content: You had Aunt Lysa send a letter to our parents telling them it was the Lannisters who murdered Jon.

author: petyr baelish
content: I know of no such letter.

author: sansa stark
content: You conspired with Cersei Lannister and Joffrey Baratheon to betray our father.

author: petyr baelish
content: I deny it! None of you were there to see what happened. None of you knows the truth.

author: bran stark
content: You held a knife to his throat.

author: bran stark
content: You said, "I did warn you not the trust me."

author: arya stark
content: You told our mother

author: petyr baelish
content: Lady Sansa, I have known you since you were a girl. I've protected you.

author: sansa stark
content: Protected me? By selling me to the Boltons?

author: petyr baelish
content: If we could speak alone, I can explain everything.

author: sansa stark
content: Sometimes when I'm trying to understand a person's motives, I play a little game. I assume the worst. What's the worst reason you have for turning me against my sisterThat's what you do, isn't it? That's what you've always done turn family against family, turn sister against sister. That's what you did to our mother.

author: petyr baelish
content: Sansa, please.

author: sansa stark
content: I'm a slow learner, it's true. But I learn.

author: petyr baelish
content: Give me a chance to defend myself. I deserve that.

author: petyr baelish
content: I am Lord Protector of the Vale and I command you to escort me safely back to the Eyrie.

author: john royce
content: I think not.

author: petyr baelish
content: Sansa, I beg you! I loved your mother since the time I was a boy.

author: sansa stark
content: And yet, you betrayed her.

author: petyr baelish
content: I loved you. More than anyone.

author: sansa stark
content: And yet, you betrayed me.

author: sansa stark
content: When you brought me back to Winterfell, you told me there's no justice in the world, not unless we make it. Thank you for all your many lessons, Lord Baelish. I will never forget them.

author: petyr baelish
content: Sansa! I--

author: jaime lannister
content: Our men in King's Landing will march north in three days' time.

author: man
content: It'll take us a fortnight just to gather supplies for the train.

author: jaime lannister
content: We don't have a fortnight. If the North falls, we fall. Three days. The remaining forces in the Westerlands will take the river road east. We'll meet at Lord Harroway's Town and march together to Winterfell.

author: cersei lannister
content: Ser Jaime.

author: jaime lannister
content: Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: My lords, I need a moment with my brother.

author: men
content: Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: What are you doing?

author: jaime lannister
content: Preparing the expedition north.

author: cersei lannister
content: Expedition north? I always knew you were the stupidest Lannister. The Starks and Targaryens have united against us, and you want to fight alongside them? Are you a traitor or an idiot?

author: jaime lannister
content: You pledged our forces to fight our common enemy.

author: cersei lannister
content: I'll say whatever I need to say to ensure the survival of our house. You expect me to trust the man who murdered our father.

author: jaime lannister
content: You saw it with your own eyes. You saw a dead man trying to kill us.

author: cersei lannister
content: I saw it burn. If dragons can't stop them, if Dothraki and Unsullied and Northmen can't stop them, how will our armies make a difference?

author: jaime lannister
content: This isn't about noble houses, this is about the living and the dead!

author: cersei lannister
content: And I intend to stay amongst the living. Let the Stark boy and his new queen--

author: jaime lannister
content: I made a promise.

author: cersei lannister
content: Our child will rule Westeros.

author: jaime lannister
content: Our child will never be born if the dead come south.

author: cersei lannister
content: The monsters are real. The white walkers, the dragons, the Dothraki screamers all the frightening stories we heard when we were young, they're all real. So be it. Let the monsters kill each other. And while they battle in the North, we take back the lands that belong to us.

author: jaime lannister
content: And then what?

author: cersei lannister
content: And then we rule.

author: jaime lannister
content: When the fighting in the North is over, someone wins. You understand that, don't you? If the dead win, they march south and kill us all. If the living win, and we've betrayed them, they march south and kill us all!

author: cersei lannister
content: The Targaryens and the Starks already want to kill us all. Most of them will die in the North.

author: jaime lannister
content: I faced them in the field. We can't beat them. We can't beat their dragons.

author: cersei lannister
content: How many dragons did you see at the pit?

author: jaime lannister
content: Two.

author: cersei lannister
content: What happened to the third?

author: jaime lannister
content: For all we know, it's guarding her fleet!

author: cersei lannister
content: She came here with her dragons and her Dothraki and her Unsullied. She came here to show us all her power. No, something happened.The dragons are vulnerable.

author: jaime lannister
content: We can't beat the Dothraki. We don't have the numbers. We don't have the support of the other houses!

author: cersei lannister
content: No, we have something better. We have the Iron Bank. You shouldo ve listened more when Father--

author: jaime lannister
content: The Golden Company is not here. They're in Essos. How is a mercenary company in Essos going to help us?

author: cersei lannister
content: Do you really think Euron Greyjoy turned tail and sailed back to the Iron Islands? Do you think he abandoned the chance to marry the queen?

author: jaime lannister
content: You plotted with Euron Greyjoy without telling me, the commander.

author: cersei lannister
content: And you conspired with Tyrion, the man who murdered our father without telling me, your queen.

author: jaime lannister
content: I didn't conspire with him.

author: cersei lannister
content: You met with him in secret without my consent. You planned to promote my enemies' interests. That is the definition of conspiracy.

author: jaime lannister
content: I pledged to ride north. I intend to honor that pledge.

author: cersei lannister
content: And that will be treason.

author: jaime lannister
content: Treason?

author: cersei lannister
content: Disobeying your queen

author: jaime lannister
content: Doesn't matter what I'd call it.

author: cersei lannister
content: I told you no one walks away from me.

author: jaime lannister
content: Are you going to order him to kill me? I'm the only one you have left. Our children are gone, our father

author: cersei lannister
content: There's one more yet to come.

author: jaime lannister
content: Give the order, then.

author: jaime lannister
content: I don't believe you.

author: bran stark
content: Come in.

author: bran stark
content: Samwell Tarly.

author: sam
content: I wasn't sure if you'd remember me.

author: bran stark
content: I remember everything.

author: bran stark
content: You helped us get beyond the Wall. You're a good man.

author: sam
content: Oh, well, thank you, but, um, I'm not sure that I am. What happened to you beyond the Wall?

author: bran stark
content: I became the Three-Eyed Raven.

author: sam
content: Oh! I don't know what that means.

author: bran stark
content: I can see things that happened in the past. I can see things happening now all over the world. Why did you come to Winterfell?

author: sam
content: Um, Jon's the one to lead the fight against the dead. I know he is. But he can't do it alone, so I've come here to help him.

author: bran stark
content: He's on his way back to Winterfell with Daenerys Targaryen. You you saw this in a vision?

author: sam
content: Oh.

author: bran stark
content: He needs to know the truth.

author: sam
content: The truth about what?

author: bran stark
content: About himself. No one knows. No one but me. Jon isn't really my father's son He's the son of Rhaegar Targaryen and my aunt.

author: sam
content: It's not.

author: bran stark
content: Dornish bastards are named Sand.

author: sam
content: At the Citadel, I transcribed a High Septon's diary. He annulled Rhaegar's marriage to Elia. He wed Rhaegar and Lyanna in a secret ceremony.

author: bran stark
content: Are you certain?

author: sam
content: It's what the High Septon wrote in his private diary. I don't know why he'd lie. Is this something you can see?

author: rhaegar
content: Father, Smith, Warrior, Mother, Maiden, Crone, Stranger. I am hers and she is mine from this day until the end of my days.

author: lyanna
content: Father, Smith, Warrior, Mother, Maiden, Crone, Stranger. I am his and he is mine from this day until the end of my days.

author: bran stark
content: Robert's Rebellion was built on a lie. Rhaegar didn't kidnap my aunt.

author: bran stark
content: He loved her. And she loved him.

author: bran stark
content: And Jon - Jon's real name.

author: lyanna
content: His name is Aegon.

author: bran stark
content: He's never been a bastard.

author: brans voice
content: He needs to know. We need to tell him.

author: arya stark
content: Are you all right?

author: sansa stark
content: It's just strange. In his own horrible way, I believe he loved me.

author: arya stark
content: You did the right thing.

author: sansa stark
content: You did it.

author: arya stark
content: I'm just the executioner. You passed the sentence. You're the Lady.

author: sansa stark
content: Does that bother you?

author: arya stark
content: I was never going to be as good a lady as you. So I had to be something else. I never could have survived what you survived.

author: sansa stark
content: You would have. You're the strongest person I know.

author: arya stark
content: I believe that's the nicest thing you've ever said to me.

author: sansa stark
content: Well, don't get used to it. You're still very strange and annoying.

author: arya stark
content: In winter, we must protect ourselves. Look after one another.

author: sansa stark
content: Father

author: arya stark
content: I miss him.

author: sansa stark
content: Me, too.

author: beric
content: It's a long way down.

author: tormund
content: Yeah. The crows keep telling me I'll get used to it.

author: man
content: I can see movement. Watch, on the tree line!

author: man
content: What is it?

author: tormund
content: Come on! Run! Run!

author: tyrion lannister
content: You should consider yourself lucky. At least your balls won't freeze off.

author: varys
content: You take great offense at dwarf jokes, but love telling eunuch jokes. Why is that?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Because I have balls, and you don't.

author: jon snow
content: I warned you. Northerners don't much trust outsiders.

author: jon snow
content: Look at you.

author: jon snow
content: You're a man.

author: bran stark
content: Almost.

author: jon snow
content: Where's Arya?

author: sansa stark
content: Lurking somewhere.

author: jon snow
content: Queen Daenerys of House Targaryen. My sister, Sansa Stark, the Lady of Winterfell.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Thank you for inviting us into your home, Lady Stark. The North is as beautiful as your brother claimed, as are you.

author: sansa stark
content: Winterfell is yours, Your Grace.

author: bran stark
content: We don't have time for all this. The Night King has your dragon.

author: bran stark
content: He's one of them now. The Wall has fallen, the dead march south.

author: sansa stark
content: As soon as we heard about the Wall, I called all our banners to retreat to Winterfell. Lord Umber when can we expect your people to arrive?

author: umber
content: We need more horses and wagons, if it please my lady.

author: umber
content: And my lord.

author: umber
content: And my queen. Sorry.

author: sansa stark
content: You'll have as many as we can spare. Hurry back to Last Hearth and bring your people here.

author: jon snow
content: We need to send ravens to the Night's Watch as well. There's no sense in manning the castles anymore. We make our stand here.

author: maester wolkan
content: At once, Your Grace.

author: lyanna mormont
content: Your Grace.

author: lyanna
content: But you're not. Are you? You left Winterfell a king and came back a- I'm not sure what you are now.

author: lyanna
content: A lord? Nothing at all?

author: jon snow
content: It's not important.

author: lyanna
content: Not important? We named you King in the North.

author: man
content: King of the North!

author: jon snow
content: You did, my lady. It was the honor of my life. I'll always be grateful for your faith. But when I left Winterfell, I told you we need allies or we will die. I have brought those allies home to fight alongside us. I had a choice, keep my crown or protect the North. I chose the North.

author: tyrion lannister
content: If anyone survives the war to come, we'll have Jon Snow to thank. He risked his life to show us the threat is real. Thanks to his courage, we have brought with us the greatest army the world has ever seen. We have brought two full-grown dragons. And soon, the Lannister army will ride north to join our cause.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know, I know, our people haven't been friends in the past. But we must fight together now or die.

author: sansa stark
content: May I ask, how are we meant to feed the greatest army the world has ever seen? While I ensured our stores would last through winter, I didn't account for Dothraki, Unsullied and two full-grown dragons. What do dragons eat, anyway?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Whatever they want.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Hey, careful, lads. We need every last bit of it.

author: man
content: Sorry 'bout that.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Are these the last of the wagons?

author: man
content: Aye.

author: gendry baratheon
content: All right, let's get it all to the forges.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My lord. My lady.

author: royce
content: My lady.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The Lady of Winterfell. Has a nice ring to it.

author: sansa stark
content: So does Hand of the Queen. Depending on the queen, I suppose.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Last time we spoke was at Joffrey's wedding. Miserable affair.

author: sansa stark
content: It had its moments.

author: sansa stark
content: Apologies for leaving like that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, it was a bit hard to explain why my wife fled moments after the king's murder.

author: sansa stark
content: We both survived.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Many underestimated you. Most of them are dead now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm sure you weren't thrilled to hear the Lannister army's marching north. You have every right to be fearful of my sister. No one fears her more than I do. But I promise, you'll be safe-

author: sansa stark
content: Cersei told you her army was coming north to fight for you?

author: tyrion lannister
content: She did.

author: sansa stark
content: And you believed her?

author: tyrion lannister
content: She has something to live for now. I believe she wants to survive.

author: sansa stark
content: I used to think you were the cleverest man alive.

author: arya stark
content: You used to be taller.

author: jon snow
content: How did you sneak up on me?

author: arya stark
content: How did you survive a knife through the heart?

author: jon snow
content: I didn't.

author: jon snow
content: You still have it.

author: arya stark
content: Needle.

author: jon snow
content: Have you ever used it?

author: arya stark
content: Once or twice.

author: arya stark
content: Valyrian steel.

author: jon snow
content: Jealous?

author: arya stark
content: Too heavy for me.

author: jon snow
content: Where were you before? I couldo ve used your help with Sansa.

author: arya stark
content: She doesn't like your queen, does she?

author: jon snow
content: Sansa thinks she's smarter than everyone.

author: arya stark
content: She's the smartest person I've ever met.

author: jon snow
content: Now you're defending her?

author: jon snow
content: You?

author: arya stark
content: I'm defending our family. So is she.

author: jon snow
content: Yeah. I'm her family too.

author: arya stark
content: Don't forget that.

author: qyburn
content: Your Grace, I'm afraid I bring terrible news. The dead have broken through the Wall.

author: cersei lannister
content: Good.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Why don't you just get it over with and kill me?

author: euron greyjoy
content: But we're family. The last Greyjoys left in the world. The last ones with balls anyway.

author: euron greyjoy
content: If I kill you who can I talk to? Hmm?

author: euron greyjoy
content: I've got a crew full of mutes. It gets lonely at sea.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Are we in King's Landing?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Mm.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You picked the losing side.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Then I'll sail the Iron Fleet somewhere else.

author: euron greyjoy
content: But first I'm gonna fuck the queen.

author: cersei lannister
content: Twenty-thousand men, is it?

author: harry
content: Yes, Your Grace. A few died in transit.

author: euron greyjoy
content: They cheated at dice. Or maybe I cheated. Someone cheated. They weren't good fighters. You won't miss them.

author: cersei lannister
content: Horses?

author: harry
content: Two thousand.

author: cersei lannister
content: And elephants?

author: harry
content: Uh, no elephants, Your Grace.

author: cersei lannister
content: That's disappointing. I was told the Golden Company had elephants.

author: harry
content: They are excellent beasts, Your Grace, but not well-suited to long sea voyages.

author: cersei lannister
content: In any event, you are most welcome here in King's Landing, Captain Strickland.

author: harry
content: We look forward to fighting on your behalf, Your Grace.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Am I most welcome here?

author: cersei lannister
content: You are a true friend of the crown and an honored guest.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Good. As a true friend and an honored guest

author: euron greyjoy
content: I was hoping we could talk in private.

author: cersei lannister
content: After the war. That was our agreement.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Wars sometimes last years.

author: cersei lannister
content: You want a whore, buy one. You want a queen, earn her.

author: euron greyjoy
content: How?

author: euron greyjoy
content: I've given her justice, an army, and the Iron Fleet, yet she gives me no sign of affection. My heart is nearly broken.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're insolent. I've executed men for less.

author: euron greyjoy
content: They were lesser men.

author: dirah
content: I hear the dragon burnt up a thousand Lannister men.

author: crayah
content: Burnt up some of my favorite boys.

author: dirah
content: Archie, was it?

author: crayah
content: And William.

author: dirah
content: Tall handsome William?

author: crayah
content: Yeah, tall handsome William.

author: dirah
content: They said what's left of him could fit in a wine glass.

author: bronn
content: I am the only man you ever met who shot a dragon.

author: crayah
content: Did you?

author: bronn
content: Nearly killed it.

author: marei
content: That's brave.

author: crayah
content: That boy Eddie.

author: dirah
content: The ginger?

author: crayah
content: That's him. Came back with his face burnt right off. He's got no eyelids now.

author: dirah
content: How does he sleep with no eyelids?

author: bronn
content: All right, can we stop talking about the fucking dragons now?

author: qyburn
content: Ser Bronn of the Blackwater.

author: bronn
content: You're kidding me.

author: qyburn
content: Apologies for the interruption, but the queen did urge me to hurry.

author: bronn
content: Sorry, ladies. Another time perhaps.

author: crayah
content: You ever get lonely; I am partial to older gentlemen.

author: qyburn
content: Poor girl. The pox will take her within the year.

author: bronn
content: Which girl?

author: qyburn
content: The queen's brothers made promises to you and broke them. Her Grace wants to rectify their mistake.

author: bronn
content: She once gave me a castle and a wife, then rectified me right out of them.

author: qyburn
content: That was Ser Jaime's doing, not hers. When Queen Cersei wants something, she pays in advance and in gold. Several chests of it, in fact. Waiting for you in a wagon just outside.

author: bronn
content: So, she wants to murder someone, but she can't send her soldiers. If it's the Dragon Queen she's after-

author: qyburn
content: She has other plans for the Targaryen girl.

author: bronn
content: Yeah, well, good luck with that.

author: qyburn
content: Our queen's brothers are unlikely to survive their Northern adventures. But in the event that they do-

author: qyburn
content: She has a keen sense of poetic justice.

author: bronn
content: That fucking family.

author: qyburn
content: When the Citadel expelled me, I thought I would die poor and alone, but in exchange for my service, Queen Cersei made me her Hand. What would she do for the man who rids her of her treasonous brothers?

author: cersei lannister
content: I wanted those elephants.

author: euron greyjoy
content: So, how do I compare to the fat king?

author: cersei lannister
content: You're insulting my late husband?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Are you offended?

author: cersei lannister
content: Robert had a different whore every night, but he still didn't know his way around a woman's body.

author: euron greyjoy
content: And the Kingslayer?

author: cersei lannister
content: You enjoy risking your neck, don't you?

author: euron greyjoy
content: Life is boring.

author: cersei lannister
content: You're not boring, I'll give you that.

author: euron greyjoy
content: Do I please the queen?

author: cersei lannister
content: You might be the most arrogant man I've ever met. I like that.

author: cersei lannister
content: But now I want to be alone.

author: euron greyjoy
content: I'm going to put a prince in your belly.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Euron can't defend the Iron Islands, not if he's in King's Landing with all his men and his ships.

author: yara greyjoy
content: We can take our home back.

author: theon greyjoy
content: Daenerys went north.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Daenerys will need somewhere to retreat if they can't hold the North. Somewhere the dead can't go.

author: theon greyjoy
content: You're my queen. I go where you command.

author: yara greyjoy
content: You want to go to Winterfell. To fight for the Starks. Go. What is dead may never die.

author: theon greyjoy
content: What is dead may never die.

author: yara greyjoy
content: But kill the bastards anyway.

author: wolkan
content: Welcome back, my lady. If you'd follow me

author: varys
content: The Karstarks.

author: tyrion lannister
content: One of the better sigils. Beats an onion, anyway.

author: davos
content: Can't argue with that.

author: davos
content: Not so long ago, the Starks and the Karstarks were slaughtering each other on the battlefield. Jon Snow brought peace to the houses.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And our queen is grateful.

author: davos
content: Her gratitude is lovely, but that's not my point. The Northmen are loyal to Jon Snow, not to her. They don't know her. The Free Folk don't know her. I've been up here a while, and I'm telling you, they're stubborn as goats. You want their loyalty, you have to earn it.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I sense that you're leading to a proposal.

author: davos
content: A proposal is what I'm proposing. On the off chance that we survive the Night King, what if the Seven Kingdoms, for once in their whole shit history, were ruled by a just woman and an honorable man?

author: tyrion lannister
content: They do make a handsome couple.

author: varys
content: You overestimate our influence. Jon and Daenerys don't want to listen to lonely old men.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I'm not that old.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Not as old as him.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Our queen respects the wisdom of age.

author: varys
content: Of course she does. Respect is how the young keep us at a distance, so we don't remind them of an unpleasant truth.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What is that?

author: varys
content: Nothing lasts.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your sister doesn't like me.

author: jon snow
content: She doesn't know you. If it makes you feel any better, she didn't like me either when we were growing up.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: She doesn't need to be my friend but I am her queen. If she can't respect me-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: How many today?

author: dothraki man
content: Only eighteen goats and eleven sheep.

author: jon snow
content: What's the matter?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The dragons are barely eating.

author: jon snow
content: What's wrong with them?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They don't like the North.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Go on.

author: jon snow
content: I don't know how to ride a dragon.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Nobody does. Until they ride a dragon.

author: jon snow
content: What if he doesn't want me to?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Then I've enjoyed your company, Jon Snow.

author: jon snow
content: What do I hold onto?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Whatever you can.

author: jon snow
content: You've completely ruined horses for me.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We could stay a thousand years-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: No one would find us.

author: jon snow
content: We'd be pretty old.

author: jon snow
content: It's cold up here for a southern girl.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So keep your queen warm.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Don't be afraid.

author: man
content: Gendry?

author: man
content: He's here.

author: gendry baratheon
content: It isn't easy making a blade that big with dragonglass.

author: sandor
content: You're saying you're good, is that it?

author: gendry baratheon
content: I'm just saying it's a tricky material to-

author: sandor
content: You know who makes weapons for the wildlings? Cripples and cocksuckers. Which one are you?

author: arya stark
content: Leave him be.

author: sandor
content: I heard you were here. You left me to die.

author: arya stark
content: First I robbed you.

author: sandor
content: You're a cold little bitch, aren't you? Guess that's why you're still alive.

author: arya stark
content: That was a nice ax you made for him. You've gotten better.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Yeah, thanks. So have you.

author: gendry baratheon
content: I mean, you look good.

author: arya stark
content: Thanks. So do you.

author: gendry baratheon
content: It's not a bad place to grow up, if it wasn't so cold.

author: arya stark
content: Stay close to that forge, then.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Is that a command, Lady Stark?

author: arya stark
content: Don't call me that.

author: gendry baratheon
content: As you wish, milady.

author: arya stark
content: Here's my wish.

author: arya stark
content: Can you make it?

author: gendry baratheon
content: What do you need something like this for?

author: arya stark
content: Can you make it or not?

author: gendry baratheon
content: You already have a sword. What's that?

author: gendry baratheon
content: It's Valyrian steel. I always knew you were just another rich girl.

author: arya stark
content: You don't know any other rich girls.

author: sansa stark
content: Come in.

author: sansa stark
content: Lord Glover wishes us good fortune, but he's staying in Deepwood Motte with his men.

author: jon snow
content: House Glover will stand behind House Stark as we have for a thousand years." Isn't that what he said?

author: sansa stark
content: I will stand behind Jon Snow," he said.

author: sansa stark
content: The King in the North.

author: jon snow
content: I told you we needed allies.

author: sansa stark
content: You didn't tell me you were going to abandon your crown.

author: jon snow
content: I never wanted a crown. All I wanted was to protect the North. I brought two armies home with me, two dragons.

author: sansa stark
content: And a Targaryen queen.

author: jon snow
content: Do you think we can beat the Army of the Dead without her? I fought them, Sansa. Twice. You want to worry about who holds what title, I'm telling you it doesn't matter. Without her, we don't stand a chance.

author: jon snow
content: Do you have any faith in me at all?

author: sansa stark
content: You know I do.

author: jon snow
content: She'll be a good queen. For all of us. She's not her father.

author: sansa stark
content: No, she's much prettier.

author: sansa stark
content: Did you bend the knee to save the North or because you love her?

author: sam tarly
content: Oh!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: So you're the man?

author: sam tarly
content: Um. Which man am I, Your Grace?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: The one who saved Ser Jorah when no one else could.

author: jorah mormont
content: They could, they just wouldn't.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I'll have to make some changes in the Citadel when I take my throne. A great service merits a great reward.

author: sam tarly
content: Oh, it's my honor to serve you, Your Grace.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Well, there must be something I could give you.

author: sam tarly
content: If it's not too much trouble, I could use a pardon.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: For what crime?

author: sam tarly
content: Um, I borrowed a few books from the Citadel.

author: sam tarly
content: And also a sword.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: From the Citadel?

author: sam tarly
content: From my family. It's been in House Tarly for generations.

author: sam tarly
content: It wouldo ve been mine anyway, eventually, but my father had other ideas.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Not Randyll Tarly?

author: sam tarly
content: You know him?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I offered to let him retain his lands and titles if he bent the knee. He refused.

author: sam tarly
content: Well At least I'll be allowed home again, now that my brother's the lord.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your brother stood with your father.

author: sam tarly
content: Hm. Thank you, Your Grace. For telling me. And m- may I?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Of course.

author: sam tarly
content: What are you doing out here?

author: bran stark
content: Waiting, for an old friend. It's time to tell Jon the truth.

author: sam tarly
content: No, no. You're his brother. Shouldn't you tell him?

author: bran stark
content: I'm not his brother. He trusts you more than anyone. Now's the time.

author: jon snow
content: Sam?

author: sam tarly
content: I'm sorry, I know I'm not supposed to be down here.

author: jon snow
content: Were you hiding from me?

author: sam tarly
content: Of course not.

author: jon snow
content: What are you doing in Winterfell? Or did you read every book in the Citadel already?

author: jon snow
content: What's wrong? Gilly? Is she all right?

author: sam tarly
content: She's good.

author: jon snow
content: Little Sam?

author: sam tarly
content: Don't you know?

author: jon snow
content: Know what?

author: sam tarly
content: Daenerys. She executed my father and brother. They were her prisoners.

author: sam tarly
content: She didn't tell you.

author: jon snow
content: I'm so sorry. We need to end this war.

author: sam tarly
content: Would you have done it?

author: jon snow
content: Well, I've executed men who disobeyed me.

author: sam tarly
content: You've also spared men. Thousands of wildlings when they refused to kneel.

author: jon snow
content: I wasn't a king.

author: sam tarly
content: But you were. You've always been.

author: jon snow
content: I gave up my crown, Sam.

author: jon snow
content: I bent the knee. I'm not King in the North anymore.

author: sam tarly
content: I'm not talking about the King in the North. I'm talking about the King of the bloody Seven Kingdoms.

author: sam tarly
content: Bran and I worked it out. I had a High Septon's diary. Bran had whatever Bran has.

author: jon snow
content: What are you talking about?

author: sam tarly
content: Your mother was Lyanna Stark.

author: sam tarly
content: And your father- your real father was Rhaegar Targaryen. You've never been a bastard. You're Aegon Targaryen, true heir to the Iron Throne. I'm sorry, I know it's a lot to take in.

author: jon snow
content: My father was the most honorable man I ever met. You're saying he lied to me all my life.

author: sam tarly
content: No. Your father- Well, Ned Stark. He promised your mother he'd always protect you. And he did. Robert would have murdered you if he knew. You're the true king. Aegon Targaryen, Sixth of His Name, Protector of the Realm, all of it.

author: jon snow
content: Daenerys is our queen.

author: sam tarly
content: She shouldn't be.

author: jon snow
content: That's treason.

author: sam tarly
content: It's the truth. You gave up your crown to save your people. Would she do the same?

author: edd
content: Stay back, he's got blue eyes!

author: tormund
content: I've always had blue eyes!

author: beric
content: Did you find anyone?

author: edd
content: The Umber boy.

author: beric
content: It's a message. From the Night King.

author: tormund
content: His army's between us and Winterfell. We're on foot.

author: edd
content: We rode down from Castle Black. We can double up on the horses.

author: tormund
content: If the horses last, we'll get there before the dead.

author: tormund
content: We just have to hope the Night King doesn't come first-

author: daenerys targaryen
content: When I was a child, my brother would tell me a bedtime story about the man who murdered our father.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Who stabbed him in the back and cut his throat. Who sat down on the Iron Throne and watched as his blood poured onto the floor.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He told me other stories as well. About all the things we would do to that man once we took back the Seven Kingdoms and had him in our grasp.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Your sister pledged to send her army north.

author: jaime lannister
content: She did.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I don't see an army. I see one man, with one hand. It appears your sister lied to me.

author: jaime lannister
content: She lied to me as well. She never had any intention of sending her army north.

author: jaime lannister
content: She has Euron Greyjoy's fleet and 20,000 fresh troops. The Golden Company from Essos, bought and paid for. Even if we defeat the dead, she'll have more than enough to destroy the survivors.

It is our duty and our honor to keep them alive in memory for those who come after us and those who come after them for as long as men draw breath. Keep following the stairways down, down as far as they'll go. You'll come out onto a beach at the foot of the keep. A dinghy will be waiting for you. Sail out of the bay. If the winds are kind, you'll make it to Pentos. Start a new life.

content: Torgo Nudho.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You have walked beside me since the Plaza of Pride. You are the bravest of men, the most loyal of soldiers. I name you commander of all my forces, the Queen's Master of War.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Unsullied. All of you were torn from your mother's arms and raised as slaves. Now you are liberators. You have freed the people of King's Landing from the grip of a tyrant!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: But the war is not over. We will not lay down our spears until we have liberated all the people of the world!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: From Winterfell to Dorne, from Lannisport to Qarth, from the Summer Isles to the Jade Sea! Women, men and children have suffered too long beneath the wheel.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Will you break the wheel with me?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You freed your brother. You committed treason.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Take him.

author: jon snow
content: What are you doing here?

content: Hey, what happened?

author: arya stark
content: I came to kill Cersei. Your queen got there first.

author: jon snow
content: She's everyone's queen now.

author: arya stark
content: Try telling Sansa.

author: jon snow
content: Wait for me outside the city gates. I'll come find you.

content: Jon. She knows who you are. Who you really are. You'll always be a threat to her. And I know a killer when I see one.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Did you bring any wine?

author: jon snow
content: No.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ah... Well... thank you for coming to see me. Our queen doesn't keep prisoners for long. I suppose there's a crude kind of justice. I betrayed my closest friend and watched him burn. Now Varys's ashes can tell my ashes, "See, I told you." It just occurred to me. I'm talking to the only man alive who knows where I'm going.

author: tyrion lannister
content: So is there life after death?

author: jon snow
content: Not that I've seen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I should be thankful. Oblivion is the best I could hope for. I strangled my lover. I shot my own father with a crossbow. I betrayed my queen.

author: jon snow
content: You didn't.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I did. And I'd do it again, now that I've seen what I've seen. I chose my fate. The people of King's Landing did not.

author: jon snow
content: I can't justify what happened. I won't try. But the war is over now.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Is it? When you heard her talking to her soldiers, did she sound like someone who's done fighting?

author: tyrion lannister
content: She liberated the people of Slaver's Bay. She liberated the people of King's Landing. And she'll go on liberating until the people of the world are free and she rules them all.

author: jon snow
content: And you've been by her side, counseling her. Until today.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Until today. Varys was right. I was wrong. It was vanity to think I could guide her. Our queen's nature is fire and blood.

author: jon snow
content: You think our house words are stamped on our bodies when we're born and that's who we are? Then I'd be fire and blood too. She's not her father, no more than you're Tywin Lannister.

author: tyrion lannister
content: My father was an evil man. My sister was an evil woman. Pile up all the bodies of all the people they ever killed, there still won't be half as many as our beautiful queen slaughtered in a single day.

author: jon snow
content: Cersei left her no choice.

author: tyrion lannister
content: The moment the gates fell, the battle was over.

author: jon snow
content: She saw her friend beheaded. She saw her dragon shot out of the sky.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And she burned down a city for it.

author: jon snow
content: Ah, it's easy to judge when you're standing far from the battlefield.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Would you have done it?

author: jon snow
content: What?

author: tyrion lannister
content: You've been up there, on a dragon's back. You've had that power. Would you have burned the city down?

author: jon snow
content: I don't know.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, you do. You won't say because you don't want to betray her but you know.

author: jon snow
content: What's it matter what I'd do?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It matters more than anything. When she murdered the slavers of Astapor, I'm sure no one but the slavers complained. After all, they were evil men.

author: tyrion lannister
content: When she crucified hundreds of Meereenese nobles, who could argue? They were evil men. The Dothraki khals she burned alive? They would have done worse to her. Everywhere she goes, evil men die and we cheer her for it. And she grows more powerful and more sure that she is good and right. She believes her destiny is to build a better world for everyone. If you believed that if you truly believed it, wouldn't you kill whoever stood between you and paradise?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know you love her. I love her too. Not as successfully as you. But I believed in her with all my heart. Love is more powerful than reason. We all know that. Look at my brother.

author: jon snow
content: Love is the death of duty.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You just came up with that?

author: jon snow
content: Maester Aemon said it a long time ago.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Sometimes duty is the death of love. You are the shield that guards the realms of men. And you've always tried to do the right thing. No matter the cost, you've tried to protect people. Who is the greatest threat to the people now?

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's a terrible thing I'm asking. It's also the right thing. Do you think I'm the last man she'll execute? Who is more dangerous than the rightful heir to the Iron Throne?

author: jon snow
content: That's her decision. She is the queen.

author: jon snow
content: I'm sorry it came to this.

author: tyrion lannister
content: And your sisters? Do you see them bending the knee?

author: jon snow
content: My sisters will be loyal to the throne.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Why do you think Sansa told me the truth about you? Because she doesn't want Dany to be queen.

author: jon snow
content: She doesn't get to choose.

author: tyrion lannister
content: No. But you do. And you have to choose now.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: When I was a girl, my brother told me it was made with a thousand swords from Aegon's fallen enemies. What do a thousand swords look like in the mind of a little girl who can't count to twenty? I imagined a mountain of swords too high to climb. So many fallen enemies, you could only see the soles of Aegon's feet.

author: jon snow
content: I saw them executing Lannister prisoners in the street. They said they were acting on your orders.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: It was necessary.

author: jon snow
content: Necessary? Have you been down there? Have you seen? Children, little children, burned!

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I tried to make peace with Cersei. She used their innocence as a weapon against me. She thought it would cripple me.

author: jon snow
content: And Tyrion?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: He conspired behind my back with my enemies. How have you treated people who've done the same to you, even when it broke your heart?

author: jon snow
content: Forgive him.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: I can't.

author: jon snow
content: You can. You can forgive all of them, make them see they made a mistake. Make them understand.

author: jon snow
content: Please, Dany.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: We can't hide behind small mercies. The world we need won't be built by men loyal to the world we have.

author: jon snow
content: The world we need is a world of mercy. It has to be.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: And it will be. It's not easy to see something that's never been before. A good world.

author: jon snow
content: How do you know? How do you know it'll be good?

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Because I know what is good. And so do you.

author: jon snow
content: I don't.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: You do. You do. You've always known.

author: jon snow
content: What about everyone else? All the other people who think they know what's good.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: They don't get to choose.

author: daenerys targaryen
content: Be with me. Build the new world with me. This is our reason. It has been from the beginning, since you were a little boy with a bastardo s name and I was a little girl who couldn't count to twenty. We do it together. We break the wheel together.

author: jon snow
content: You are my queen. Now, and always.

author: sansa stark
content: Where's Jon?

author: grey worm
content: He is our prisoner.

author: sansa stark
content: So is Lord Tyrion. They were both to be brought to this gathering.

author: grey worm
content: We will decide what we do with our prisoners. This is our city now.

author: sansa stark
content: If you look outside the walls of your city, you'll find thousands of Northmen who will explain to you why harming Jon Snow is not in your interest.

author: grey worm
content: And you will find thousands of Unsullied who believe that it is.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Some of you may be quick to forgive. The Ironborn are not. I swore to follow Daenerys Targaryen.

author: sansa stark
content: You swore to follow a tyrant.

author: yara greyjoy
content: She freed us from a tyrant. Cersei is gone because of her, and Jon Snow put a knife in her heart. Let the Unsullied give him what he deserves.

author: arya stark
content: Say another word about killing my brother and I'll cut your throat.

author: davos
content: Friends, please. We've been cutting each other's throats long enough. Torgo Nudho. Am I saying that properly?

author: davos
content: If it weren't for you and your men, we wouldo ve lost the war with the dead. This country owes you a debt it can never repay, but let us try. There is land in the Reach. Good land. The people that used to live there are gone. Make it your own. Start your own house with the Unsullied as your bannermen. We've had enough war. Thousands of you, thousands of them. You know how it ends. We need to find a better way.

author: grey worm
content: We do not need payment. We need justice. Jon Snow cannot go free.

author: tyrion lannister
content: It's not for you to decide.

author: grey worm
content: You are not here to speak! Everyone has heard enough words from you.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're right. And no one's any better for it. But it's not for you to decide. Jon committed his crime here. His fate is for our king to decide. Or our queen.

author: maester wolkan
content: We don't have a king or queen.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You're the most powerful people in Westeros. Choose one.

author: grey worm
content: Make your choice, then.

author: edmure
content: My lords and ladies. I suppose this is the most important moment of our lives. What we decide today will reverberate through the annals of history. I stand before you as one of the senior lords in the country. A veteran of two wars. And I like to think my experience has led to some small skill in statecraft - and underst-

author: sansa stark
content: Uncle? Please sit.

author: maester wolkan
content: Well, we have to choose someone.

author: sam
content: Why just us?

author: sam
content: Um- We represent all the great houses, but whomever we choose, they won't just rule over lords and ladies. Maybe the decision about what's best for everyone should be left to well, everyone.

author: edmure
content: Maybe we should give the dogs a vote as well.

author: yohn royce
content: I'll ask my horse.

author: edmure
content: I suppose you want the crown.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Me? The Imp?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Half the people hate me for serving Daenerys, the other half hate me for betraying her.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Can't think of a worse choice.

author: davos
content: Who, then?

author: tyrion lannister
content: I've had nothing to do but think these past few weeks. About our bloody history. About the mistakes we've made.

author: tyrion lannister
content: What unites people? Armies? Gold? Flags? Stories. There's nothing in the world more powerful than a good story. Nothing can stop it. No enemy can defeat it. And who has a better story than Bran the Broken? The boy who fell from a high tower and lived. He knew he'd never walk again, so he learned to fly. He crossed beyond the Wall, a crippled boy, and became the Three-Eyed Raven. He is our memory, the keeper of all our stories. The wars, weddings, births, massacres, famines. Our triumphs... mm, our defeats, our past. Who better to lead us into the future?

author: sansa stark
content: Bran has no interest in ruling and he can't father children.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. Sons of kings can be cruel and stupid, as you well know. His will never torment us. That is the wheel our queen wanted to break.

author: tyrion lannister
content: From now on, rulers will not be born. They will be chosen on this spot by the lords and ladies of Westeros to serve the realm.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I know you don't want it. I know you don't care about power. But I ask you now, if we choose you will you wear the crown? Will you lead the Seven Kingdoms to the best of your abilities from this day until your last day?

author: bran stark
content: Why do you think I came all this way?

author: tyrion lannister
content: To Brandon of House Stark... I say aye.

author: sam
content: Aye.

author: edmure
content: Aye.

author: riverlands lord
content: Aye.

author: yohn royce
content: Aye.

author: maester wolkan
content: Aye.

author: robin
content: Aye.

author: dornish prince
content: Aye.

author: yara greyjoy
content: Aye.

author: ironborn lord
content: Aye.

author: vale lord
content: Aye.

author: gendry baratheon
content: Aye.

author: davos
content: I'm not sure I get a vote, but aye.

author: brienne
content: Aye.

author: sansa stark
content: I love you, little brother. I always will. You'll be a good king. But tens of thousands of Northmen fell in the Great War defending all of Westeros. And those who survived have seen too much and fought too hard ever to kneel again. The North will remain an independent kingdom, as it was for thousands of years.

author: tyrion lannister
content: All hail Bran the Broken, First of His Name, King of the Andals and the First Men, Lord of the Six Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm.

author: all
content: All hail Bran the Broken!

author: bran stark
content: Lord Tyrion, you will be my Hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: N- No, Your Grace, I don't want it.

author: bran stark
content: And I don't want to be king.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I don't deserve it. I thought I was wise, but I wasn't. I thought I knew what was right, but I didn't. Choose Ser Davos. Choose anyone else.

author: bran stark
content: I choose you.

author: grey worm
content: You cannot.

author: bran stark
content: Yes, I can. I'm king.

author: grey worm
content: This man is a criminal. He deserves justice.

author: bran stark
content: He just got it. He's made many terrible mistakes. He's going to spend the rest of his life fixing them.

author: grey worm
content: It is not enough.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Giving you to the Unsullied would start a war. Letting you walk free would start a war. So our new king has chosen to send you to the Night's Watch.

author: jon snow
content: There's still a Night's Watch?

author: tyrion lannister
content: The world will always need a home for bastards and broken men.

author: tyrion lannister
content: You shall take no wife, hold no lands, father no children. The Unsullied wanted your head of course, but Grey Worm has accepted the justice of a life sentence. Sansa and Arya wanted you freed, but they understand our new king needs to make peace. No one is very happy. Which means it's a good compromise, I suppose.

author: jon snow
content: Was it right? What I did?

author: tyrion lannister
content: What we did.

author: jon snow
content: It doesn't feel right.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ask me again in ten years.

author: jon snow
content: I don't expect we'll ever see each other again.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I wouldn't be so sure. A few years as Hand of the King would make anyone want to piss off the edge of the world.

author: unsullied captain
content: All the men have boarded.

author: grey worm
content: Good. We sail for the isle of Naath.

author: sansa stark
content: I wish there had been another way. Can you forgive me?

author: jon snow
content: The North is free, thanks to you.

author: sansa stark
content: But they lost their king.

author: jon snow
content: Ned Stark's daughter will speak for them. She's the best they could ask for.

author: jon snow
content: You can come see me, you know, at Castle Black.

author: arya stark
content: I can't.

author: jon snow
content: You think anyone will dare tell you women aren't allowed?

author: arya stark
content: I'm not going back north.

author: sansa stark
content: Where are you going?

author: arya stark
content: What's west of Westeros?

author: arya stark
content: No one knows. It's where all the maps stop. That's where I'm going.

author: jon snow
content: You have your Needle?

author: arya stark
content: Right here.

author: jon snow
content: Your Grace.

author: jon snow
content: I'm sorry I wasn't there when you needed me.

author: bran stark
content: You were exactly where you were supposed to be.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That's not- Uh-

author: tyrion lannister
content: What's this?

author: sam
content: A Song of Ice and Fire. Archmaester Ebrose's history of the wars following the death of King Robert. I helped him with the title.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I suppose I come in for some heavy criticism.

author: sam
content: Oh, I wouldn't say that.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Oh, he's kind to me. Never wouldo ve guessed.

author: tyrion lannister
content: He's not kind?

author: sam
content: He-

author: tyrion lannister
content: He what? What does he say about me?

author: sam
content: I don't believe you're mentioned, ahem.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Your Grace.

author: davos
content: Your Grace.

author: bronn
content: Your Grace.

author: sam
content: Your Grace.

author: bran stark
content: We appear to be missing a Master of Whisperers. And a Master of Laws. And a Master of War.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Yes, Your Grace. Suitable prospects will be brought to you for an audience in the coming weeks.

author: bran stark
content: And Drogon? Any word?

author: sam
content: He was last spotted flying east, toward-

author: bronn
content: The farther away, the better.

author: bran stark
content: Perhaps I can find him. Do carry on with the rest.

author: tyrion lannister
content: As you wish, Your Grace.

author: brienne
content: Ser Podrick.

author: tyrion lannister
content: We serve at your pleasure, King Bran the Broken, ruler of the Six Kingdoms and Protector of the Realm. Long may he reign.

author: sam
content: Long may he reign.

author: davos
content: Long may he reign.

author: brienne
content: Long may he reign.

author: bronn
content: Long may he reign.

author: tyrion lannister
content: That will improve.

author: bran stark
content: I'm sure it will.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Ser Bronn of the Blackwater, Lord of Highgarden, Lord Paramount of the Reach and Master of Coin, would you say the crown's debt to you has been paid?

author: bronn
content: In full, my lord Hand.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Good. Time to start incurring a new one. We have hungry people to feed. Can we expect some assistance in this regard?

author: bronn
content: Indeed we can.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Lord Davos, we have an armada to rebuild and ports to repair.

author: davos
content: We have. These projects will begin as soon as the Master of Coin and Lord of Lofty Titles provides funding.

author: bronn
content: The Master of Coin looks forward to helping the Master of Ships, but first he has to ensure we're not wasting coin, or soon there won't be no more coin.

author: davos
content: Any more.

author: bronn
content: You Master of Grammar now too?

author: tyrion lannister
content: Grandmaester, ahem, it is my theory, based on my years of work on the Casterly Rock sewers, that clean water leads to a healthier population.

author: sam
content: The Archmaester has done some research on this subject and it turns out-

author: bronn
content: The strong live and the weak don't.

author: tyrion lannister
content: Find the best builders and set them to the task.

author: bronn
content: Oh, speaking of builders, all the best brothels burned down. The Master of Coin is willing to fund reconstruction.

author: sam
content: Uh... the Archmaester is less than enthusiastic about the salutary effects of brothels.

author: bronn
content: Well, I imagine he isn't using them properly.

author: brienne
content: I think we can all agree that ships take precedence over brothels.

author: bronn
content: I think that's a very presumptuous statement.

author: tyrion lannister
content: I once brought a jackass and a honeycomb into a brothel.

author: man
content: The Queen in the North!

author: all
content: The Queen in the North! The Queen in the North! The Queen in the North! The Queen in the North! The Queen in the North!
